p-smacking sound; the somatic gesture is a shaking motion.","link":""},"freshen":{"name":"Freshen","level":"0","school":"Enchantment","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster brings new life or freshness to the object desired. The magic applies to food and drink items such as milk, beer, meat, and raw vegetables. It also works with cut vegetables, flowers, herbs, etc. Although it will remove a slight taint of spoilage, restore drooping flowers, and so on, it is not as effective as a purify food & drink spell, and it lasts for but an hour. The subject must be of relatively small size, i.e. a small cask of liquid, a sheep, a bushel of vegetables, etc. If used on a creature that is harmed by magics such as purify food & drink, the cantrip inflicts 1-4 points of damage. The verbal component is an mmmmmm sound, while the hand makes a mystic symbol with thumb and forefinger forming a circle and the other fingers upright and apart.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster brings new life or freshness to the object desired. The magic applies to food and drink items such as milk, beer, meat, and raw vegetables. It also works with cut vegetables, flowers, herbs, etc. Although it will remove a slight taint of spoilage, restore drooping flowers, and so on, it is not as effective as a purify food & drink spell, and it lasts for but an hour. The subject must be of relatively small size, i.e. a small cask of liquid, a sheep, a bushel of vegetables, etc. If used on a creature that is harmed by magics such as purify food & drink, the cantrip inflicts 1-4 points of damage. The verbal component is an mmmmmm sound, while the hand makes a mystic symbol with thumb and forefinger forming a circle and the other fingers upright and apart.","link":""},"gather":{"name":"Gather","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1 sq. yd.","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip enables the caster to neatly gather numerous small objects into a stack or pile. For instance, if nails, nuts, coins, papers, or like objects were spilled, the magic would bring them together. It can be used selectively, for instance to separate one type of material from another, but only the selected type would be gathered neatly. The caster verbalizes the type of material to be gathered while making a gathering motion.","notes":"This cantrip enables the caster to neatly gather numerous small objects into a stack or pile. For instance, if nails, nuts, coins, papers, or like objects were spilled, the magic would bring them together. It can be used selectively, for instance to separate one type of material from another, but only the selected type would be gathered neatly. The caster verbalizes the type of material to be gathered while making a gathering motion.","link":""},"polish":{"name":"Polish","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"When this cantrip is used, the caster magically smooths and brings a luster to materials such as wood, metal, stone, leather, or ceramic. Naturally, the desired object must be relatively clean in order for the cantrip to be effective. The object affected must be of reasonable size — a floor of up to 1,000 square feet, an armoire, etc. It works better on smaller objects, of course, such as boots, mirrors, crystal containers, etc. The caster hums a ditty while making a buffing motion.","notes":"When this cantrip is used, the caster magically smooths and brings a luster to materials such as wood, metal, stone, leather, or ceramic. Naturally, the desired object must be relatively clean in order for the cantrip to be effective. The object affected must be of reasonable size — a floor of up to 1,000 square feet, an armoire, etc. It works better on smaller objects, of course, such as boots, mirrors, crystal containers, etc. The caster hums a ditty while making a buffing motion.","link":""},"salt":{"name":"Salt","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip causes a sprinkling of fine salt to magically appear and descend upon the desired object — a stew, some troublesome weed patch, or a barrel full of stock fish to be preserved. The object must be of a reasonable size — up to perhaps 4 square yards in area or about 30 gallons liquid volume. Care must be taken to avoid over-salting if the object involved is smaller, and if the object is larger, it will not receive much salt. Creatures adversely affected by salt (such as a giant slug) take 1-4 points of damage from this cantrip. The verbal component is a labial smacking, performed while the hand makes a sprinkling motion.","notes":"This cantrip causes a sprinkling of fine salt to magically appear and descend upon the desired object — a stew, some troublesome weed patch, or a barrel full of stock fish to be preserved. The object must be of a reasonable size — up to perhaps 4 square yards in area or about 30 gallons liquid volume. Care must be taken to avoid over-salting if the object involved is smaller, and if the object is larger, it will not receive much salt. Creatures adversely affected by salt (such as a giant slug) take 1-4 points of damage from this cantrip. The verbal component is a labial smacking, performed while the hand makes a sprinkling motion.","link":""},"shine":{"name":"Shine","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Similar to the polish cantrip, this magic allows the caster to remove tarnish, rust, corrosion, and similar substances from the desired object. This cantrip brings about a mirror-bright shine to objects capable of such, causing their surfaces to be smooth and unmarred. A piece of jewelry, for instance, would be made more attractive, and the gems (only) of such a piece might be actually made more valuable: If base value of the gem(s) in a piece of jewelry was originally decreased, and a shine cantrip is used upon the object, then the owner may (if desired) find out whether the value of the gem(s) has been changed. (The DM should roll again on the “Increase or Decrease of Worth Beyond Base Value” table on page 26 of the DMG, with a -1 modifier to the die roll.) No gem can be “re-valued” in this manner more than once. A single object up to about 1 cubic yard in volume can be treated by this cantrip. Its components are similar to those of polish.","notes":"Similar to the polish cantrip, this magic allows the caster to remove tarnish, rust, corrosion, and similar substances from the desired object. This cantrip brings about a mirror-bright shine to objects capable of such, causing their surfaces to be smooth and unmarred. A piece of jewelry, for instance, would be made more attractive, and the gems (only) of such a piece might be actually made more valuable: If base value of the gem(s) in a piece of jewelry was originally decreased, and a shine cantrip is used upon the object, then the owner may (if desired) find out whether the value of the gem(s) has been changed. (The DM should roll again on the “Increase or Decrease of Worth Beyond Base Value” table on page 26 of the DMG, with a -1 modifier to the die roll.) No gem can be “re-valued” in this manner more than once. A single object up to about 1 cubic yard in volume can be treated by this cantrip. Its components are similar to those of polish.","link":""},"spice":{"name":"Spice","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Unlike the flavor cantrip, this magic actually brings a particular spice to the object of food or drink. Thus, ginger, pepper, and like spices can be brought to add zest (or disguise). Herbs such as bay leaf, garlic, parsley, and so forth can likewise be evoked by this cantrip. The quantity is sufficient to spice food or drink for about a dozen people. The spice (or herb) appears over the object vessel as a fine powder or flake, falls upon it, and adds its substance to the dish or drink. A ditty is hummed for the verbal component, while the hand makes a crumbling and sprinkling motion.","notes":"Unlike the flavor cantrip, this magic actually brings a particular spice to the object of food or drink. Thus, ginger, pepper, and like spices can be brought to add zest (or disguise). Herbs such as bay leaf, garlic, parsley, and so forth can likewise be evoked by this cantrip. The quantity is sufficient to spice food or drink for about a dozen people. The spice (or herb) appears over the object vessel as a fine powder or flake, falls upon it, and adds its substance to the dish or drink. A ditty is hummed for the verbal component, while the hand makes a crumbling and sprinkling motion.","link":""},"sprout":{"name":"Sprout","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1 cubic yd.","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes acceleration in the growth of plants, particularly with respect to the germination of plant seeds. Upon its casting, the cantrip will cause seeds to shoot forth tiny sprouts, newly sprouted plants to grow an inch or so, buds to flower, etc. Fruits and vegetables can be caused to ripen (or actually go past ripening to spoilage) by this cantrip. A susurrant sound is verbalized while the caster’s hand makes hoeing motions.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes acceleration in the growth of plants, particularly with respect to the germination of plant seeds. Upon its casting, the cantrip will cause seeds to shoot forth tiny sprouts, newly sprouted plants to grow an inch or so, buds to flower, etc. Fruits and vegetables can be caused to ripen (or actually go past ripening to spoilage) by this cantrip. A susurrant sound is verbalized while the caster’s hand makes hoeing motions.","link":""},"stitch":{"name":"Stitch","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip magically sews seams in cloth or leather. It will make new ones, or repair old work. About 20 yards of cloth can be thus stitched, but only about 2 yards of leather. The seam thus created is neither stronger nor weaker than a seam done without magic. Usually a brief rhyme is recited as the hand makes a sewing motion.","notes":"This cantrip magically sews seams in cloth or leather. It will make new ones, or repair old work. About 20 yards of cloth can be thus stitched, but only about 2 yards of leather. The seam thus created is neither stronger nor weaker than a seam done without magic. Usually a brief rhyme is recited as the hand makes a sewing motion.","link":""},"sweeten":{"name":"Sweeten","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip is the same as a spice cantrip, except that the result is the evocation of a sweetener — sugar, honey, or even a syrup. Components are a buzzing sound and a stirring motion.","notes":"This cantrip is the same as a spice cantrip, except that the result is the evocation of a sweetener — sugar, honey, or even a syrup. Components are a buzzing sound and a stirring motion.","link":""},"tie":{"name":"Tie","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster can magically cause the object of the magic — thread, string, cord, rope, or even cable — to tightly knot itself to either its other end or an end of a similar object within 1' of it. The resulting knot will be a normal one such as a square knot, half-hitch, running bowline, or whatever other sort is desired. The caster verbalizes the name of the knot while holding up three fingers.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster can magically cause the object of the magic — thread, string, cord, rope, or even cable — to tightly knot itself to either its other end or an end of a similar object within 1' of it. The resulting knot will be a normal one such as a square knot, half-hitch, running bowline, or whatever other sort is desired. The caster verbalizes the name of the knot while holding up three fingers.","link":""},"warm":{"name":"Warm","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1 cu. yd. cube","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip is the same as chill, except that the magic brings a warming of the liquid or solid. The temperature will rise at most about 40° F. The cantrip will never cause living creatures to become warmer than their normal body temperature. Components are an aah sound vocalized while the hands are rubbed briskly together.","notes":"This cantrip is the same as chill, except that the magic brings a warming of the liquid or solid. The temperature will rise at most about 40° F. The cantrip will never cause living creatures to become warmer than their normal body temperature. Components are an aah sound vocalized while the hands are rubbed briskly together.","link":""},"wrap":{"name":"Wrap","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"When a wrap cantrip is employed, the caster creates a strong and sturdy wrapping around the subject desired — a bit of herbs, a heap of flour, a bundle of cloth, etc. The material of the cantrip is of a suitable type and thickness for the item(s) to be wrapped. Thus, a few ounces of fine powder will be contained in a waxy tissue, gemstones in a felt-like envelope, meal in cloth, and so forth. The wrapping can be undone normally, but the caster can just as easily order it to open, so the cantrip is often used to enfold the material components of a spell. The caster verbalizes a general class of wrapping desired while making folding motions with his hands.\nReversed Cantrips: Curdle (Enchantment)\nThis cantrip is broader than its name, for it affects many food and drink items. The magic curdles milk and hastens spoilage or wilting, but does not putrefy food & drink as per that spell. It has a permanent effect on the object. It is otherwise similar to freshen. The caster verbalizes a retching sound while pointing the thumb downward.","notes":"When a wrap cantrip is employed, the caster creates a strong and sturdy wrapping around the subject desired — a bit of herbs, a heap of flour, a bundle of cloth, etc. The material of the cantrip is of a suitable type and thickness for the item(s) to be wrapped. Thus, a few ounces of fine powder will be contained in a waxy tissue, gemstones in a felt-like envelope, meal in cloth, and so forth. The wrapping can be undone normally, but the caster can just as easily order it to open, so the cantrip is often used to enfold the material components of a spell. The caster verbalizes a general class of wrapping desired while making folding motions with his hands.\nReversed Cantrips: Curdle (Enchantment)\nThis cantrip is broader than its name, for it affects many food and drink items. The magic curdles milk and hastens spoilage or wilting, but does not putrefy food & drink as per that spell. It has a permanent effect on the object. It is otherwise similar to freshen. The caster verbalizes a retching sound while pointing the thumb downward.","link":""},"dirty":{"name":"Dirty","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"4 sq. yds.","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"The opposite of a clean cantrip, this enables the caster to soil, spot, and sully walls, floors, dishes, garments, etc. Verbal component is a spitting sound, made while the feet are shuffled and stamped.","notes":"The opposite of a clean cantrip, this enables the caster to soil, spot, and sully walls, floors, dishes, garments, etc. Verbal component is a spitting sound, made while the feet are shuffled and stamped.","link":""},"dusty":{"name":"Dusty","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"10' radius","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes a film of dust and grime to settle upon all exposed surfaces within the cantrip area of effect. The verbal component is a low humming sound, made while the hands move in shaking motions.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes a film of dust and grime to settle upon all exposed surfaces within the cantrip area of effect. The verbal component is a low humming sound, made while the hands move in shaking motions.","link":""},"hairy":{"name":"Hairy","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"While this cantrip is not actually one of the standard useful ones which apprentices reverse for mischievousness, it is one which is generally used for no good purpose. It causes hair, fur, or hairlike growth to thicken and lengthen. Thus, a head of hair, a peach, a beard, a cat, or whatever could be affected. The growth will cause the subject material to increase from 2-12 inches in length. The subject material must be trimmed or cut to remove the cantrip’s effect. This cantrip can be reversed to shorten growth or effectively shave, but since the effect on short material (growth under 1 inch in length) is complete absence of growth for 2-12 days, it is not often used. The caster verbalizes snicking sounds while making massaging motions for growth, or scissoring motions for removal.","notes":"While this cantrip is not actually one of the standard useful ones which apprentices reverse for mischievousness, it is one which is generally used for no good purpose. It causes hair, fur, or hairlike growth to thicken and lengthen. Thus, a head of hair, a peach, a beard, a cat, or whatever could be affected. The growth will cause the subject material to increase from 2-12 inches in length. The subject material must be trimmed or cut to remove the cantrip’s effect. This cantrip can be reversed to shorten growth or effectively shave, but since the effect on short material (growth under 1 inch in length) is complete absence of growth for 2-12 days, it is not often used. The caster verbalizes snicking sounds while making massaging motions for growth, or scissoring motions for removal.","link":""},"knot":{"name":"Knot","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip is a permutation of the tie cantrip. It causes the thread, string, cord, or rope to knot itself in such a manner as to be very difficult to untie, and from 2-8 rounds, minus dexterity bonus for reaction of the individual untying the knot, to undo. It works even on material already affected by a tie cantrip, but not on magical ropes, ropes being held onto by a character or creature, or taut lines such as a bowstring. The caster verbalizes a low zzzz sound while moving the arm forward with a strong wrist motion.","notes":"This cantrip is a permutation of the tie cantrip. It causes the thread, string, cord, or rope to knot itself in such a manner as to be very difficult to untie, and from 2-8 rounds, minus dexterity bonus for reaction of the individual untying the knot, to undo. It works even on material already affected by a tie cantrip, but not on magical ropes, ropes being held onto by a character or creature, or taut lines such as a bowstring. The caster verbalizes a low zzzz sound while moving the arm forward with a strong wrist motion.","link":""},"ravel":{"name":"Ravel","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip is the reverse of a stitch. It will work only if there is a loose or broken thread in the seam or fabric to be affected, except for material magically stitched by the appropriate cantrip. When the latter sort of seam or material is involved, the ravel cantrip will always work except in a case where the subject is otherwise magical, i.e. a bag of holding, a cloak of protection, boots of elvenkind, etc. The name of the cantrip is verbalized while the fingers make a plucking motion.","notes":"This cantrip is the reverse of a stitch. It will work only if there is a loose or broken thread in the seam or fabric to be affected, except for material magically stitched by the appropriate cantrip. When the latter sort of seam or material is involved, the ravel cantrip will always work except in a case where the subject is otherwise magical, i.e. a bag of holding, a cloak of protection, boots of elvenkind, etc. The name of the cantrip is verbalized while the fingers make a plucking motion.","link":""},"sour":{"name":"Sour","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"When this cantrip is used, the caster causes the subject food or drink to take on a sour taste, not unlike vinegar of the appropriate sort. While it is typically used to spoil wine, beer, or some pastry, the sour cantrip can be used to useful purpose. The magic actually causes about a pint (maximum) of vinegar to appear over the subject. This can be an empty container in which such liquid is desired. The caster purses the lips and makes a whoosh sound while clenching the hand.","notes":"When this cantrip is used, the caster causes the subject food or drink to take on a sour taste, not unlike vinegar of the appropriate sort. While it is typically used to spoil wine, beer, or some pastry, the sour cantrip can be used to useful purpose. The magic actually causes about a pint (maximum) of vinegar to appear over the subject. This can be an empty container in which such liquid is desired. The caster purses the lips and makes a whoosh sound while clenching the hand.","link":""},"spill":{"name":"Spill","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One container","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"The opposite of a gather cantrip, this enables the caster to cause the contents of a container to spill out. The object container is actually tipped by the cantrip, and since the magic is not powerful, containers of more than about a gallon size, or magical ones, will not be affected by the cantrip. Solids and/or liquids within the object container will spill out, if the container is not securely closed or capped. To bring about the magic, the caster verbalizes an uh-oh sound while making an abrupt hand motion.","notes":"The opposite of a gather cantrip, this enables the caster to cause the contents of a container to spill out. The object container is actually tipped by the cantrip, and since the magic is not powerful, containers of more than about a gallon size, or magical ones, will not be affected by the cantrip. Solids and/or liquids within the object container will spill out, if the container is not securely closed or capped. To bring about the magic, the caster verbalizes an uh-oh sound while making an abrupt hand motion.","link":""},"tangle":{"name":"Tangle","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A permutation of the tie cantrip, this magic allows the caster to cause fine material such as thread, hair, small grass, and the like to become twisted and entwined in a tangle. It will not work on heavy material such as rope. Untangling subject material will take 3-12 rounds, unless it is roughly done — and the material is broken and snapped in the process, torn loose, etc. The cantrip will tangle mixed materials such as grass and string, hair and threads, and so forth. A buzzing is verbalized while the finger makes a stirring motion.","notes":"A permutation of the tie cantrip, this magic allows the caster to cause fine material such as thread, hair, small grass, and the like to become twisted and entwined in a tangle. It will not work on heavy material such as rope. Untangling subject material will take 3-12 rounds, unless it is roughly done — and the material is broken and snapped in the process, torn loose, etc. The cantrip will tangle mixed materials such as grass and string, hair and threads, and so forth. A buzzing is verbalized while the finger makes a stirring motion.","link":""},"tarnish":{"name":"Tarnish","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"The reverse of a shine cantrip, this causes a covering of rust, corrosion, verdigris, or the like to cover an object normally subject to such tarnishing. The object must be of about 1 cubic yard or less in volume. Verbal component is a spitting sound, while the hand makes a sprinkling motion.","notes":"The reverse of a shine cantrip, this causes a covering of rust, corrosion, verdigris, or the like to cover an object normally subject to such tarnishing. The object must be of about 1 cubic yard or less in volume. Verbal component is a spitting sound, while the hand makes a sprinkling motion.","link":""},"untie":{"name":"Untie","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This permutation of a tie cantrip is simply the reverse of the magic. The caster selects an object — thread, string, cord, etc. — which is knotted or tied. The cantrip removes the knot or tying. Note that the untie cantrip will cause a tangle to be nullified. The cantrip will not remove both a knot and a normal tying (normal knot or one caused by a tie cantrip), but it will cause the former to disappear so that only a normal tying remains. This cantrip has no effect on magical objects. Somatic and verbal components vary according to the desired result. In general, a popping sound is made while the hands are moved apart — either as if a knot were being untied or a cord snapped.","notes":"This permutation of a tie cantrip is simply the reverse of the magic. The caster selects an object — thread, string, cord, etc. — which is knotted or tied. The cantrip removes the knot or tying. Note that the untie cantrip will cause a tangle to be nullified. The cantrip will not remove both a knot and a normal tying (normal knot or one caused by a tie cantrip), but it will cause the former to disappear so that only a normal tying remains. This cantrip has no effect on magical objects. Somatic and verbal components vary according to the desired result. In general, a popping sound is made while the hands are moved apart — either as if a knot were being untied or a cord snapped.","link":""},"wilt":{"name":"Wilt","level":"0","school":"Enchantment","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A reverse of the freshen cantrip which affects only vegetable material — whether growing or picked. Thus, a plant can be made to wilt (or possibly wither if it is not very healthy), or a bunch of cut flowers sag or droop. Verbal component is a descending hum, while the forefinger is slowly curled from an upright position.\nLegerdemain Cantrips: Change (Alteration)\nBy means of a change cantrip, the caster alters one small object to another, although the change must be within the same kingdom, and only animal and vegetable objects are affected. Thus, a piece of parchment can be changed to a brightly colored cloth square, then the cloth can be changed to a rose by another use of the cantrip. Likewise, a bird can be changed into a bat, the bat to a flying squirrel by another use of the same type of cantrip, and so forth. Each change requires a change cantrip. The cantrip will not cause more than a 50% increase or decrease in size/volume, and the effect will last for a base time of 1 turn. If the change is radical, then the time will be reduced accordingly; i.e., changing a dead object to a live one is a radical change and will last only 1 round. On the other hand, a very slight alteration such as color change or the like will last for 1 or more days. A saving throw against this magic does not apply as long as small, animal-intelligence, non-magical creatures of normal sort are concerned. Typically, a magic word is verbalized while the hand makes a pass over the object to be affected.","notes":"A reverse of the freshen cantrip which affects only vegetable material — whether growing or picked. Thus, a plant can be made to wilt (or possibly wither if it is not very healthy), or a bunch of cut flowers sag or droop. Verbal component is a descending hum, while the forefinger is slowly curled from an upright position.\nLegerdemain Cantrips: Change (Alteration)\nBy means of a change cantrip, the caster alters one small object to another, although the change must be within the same kingdom, and only animal and vegetable objects are affected. Thus, a piece of parchment can be changed to a brightly colored cloth square, then the cloth can be changed to a rose by another use of the cantrip. Likewise, a bird can be changed into a bat, the bat to a flying squirrel by another use of the same type of cantrip, and so forth. Each change requires a change cantrip. The cantrip will not cause more than a 50% increase or decrease in size/volume, and the effect will last for a base time of 1 turn. If the change is radical, then the time will be reduced accordingly; i.e., changing a dead object to a live one is a radical change and will last only 1 round. On the other hand, a very slight alteration such as color change or the like will last for 1 or more days. A saving throw against this magic does not apply as long as small, animal-intelligence, non-magical creatures of normal sort are concerned. Typically, a magic word is verbalized while the hand makes a pass over the object to be affected.","link":""},"distract":{"name":"Distract","level":"0","school":"Enchantment","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes all who are watching to look at an area of the caster’s choice. The area must be to the right or left of the caster, and the distraction must be within 10 feet of the caster. Thus, the caster can cause viewers to watch his or her right hand and a location a few feet distant where the caster’s finger is pointing, while the caster’s left hand does something unnoticed. Saving throws apply only to individuals above 0 level, or with at least 1 + 1 hit dice and an intelligence rating of greater than low. The distract cantrip has a duration of only 1 segment. The caster speaks an attention-getting word or phrase and gestures to the left or right to effectuate the cantrip.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes all who are watching to look at an area of the caster’s choice. The area must be to the right or left of the caster, and the distraction must be within 10 feet of the caster. Thus, the caster can cause viewers to watch his or her right hand and a location a few feet distant where the caster’s finger is pointing, while the caster’s left hand does something unnoticed. Saving throws apply only to individuals above 0 level, or with at least 1 + 1 hit dice and an intelligence rating of greater than low. The distract cantrip has a duration of only 1 segment. The caster speaks an attention-getting word or phrase and gestures to the left or right to effectuate the cantrip.","link":""},"hide":{"name":"Hide","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip allows the caster to magically hide an object of virtually any size for a short period of time. The cantrip casts a dweomer over the desired object so that it becomes invisible to all who are in front of the caster. Note that the magic does not affect sound, so that if a crowing rooster were made to seemingly disappear, the noise of its cry would still be heard. Likewise, if an elephant were hidden by the cantrip, the sound of its tread, trumpeting, or even breathing might be heard. The dweomer will not work if viewers are beside or behind the caster. The cantrip lasts for 1 turn on an object of 2 cubic yards or less in volume. The duration is reduced by 1 round for every additional 2 cubic yards of volume made to seemingly disappear, until at 20 cubic yards of volume, the duration is 1 round. At over 20 cubic yards of volume, duration is reduced by 1 segment per 2 additional cubic yards; i.e., the hide cantrip will have a duration of 9 segments if cast on an object of 22 cubic yards volume; 8 segments for 24 cubic yards, 7 segments for 26, 6 for 28, 5 for 30, 4 for 32, 3 for 34, 2 for 36, and 1 segment for 38 cubic yards. Anything over 38 cubic yards in volume will at best momentarily disappear and then reappear again. Verbal component is an activating word such as abracadabra while the hand makes a pass across the forepart of the object. The caster can dispel the cantrip simply by speaking the activating word.","notes":"This cantrip allows the caster to magically hide an object of virtually any size for a short period of time. The cantrip casts a dweomer over the desired object so that it becomes invisible to all who are in front of the caster. Note that the magic does not affect sound, so that if a crowing rooster were made to seemingly disappear, the noise of its cry would still be heard. Likewise, if an elephant were hidden by the cantrip, the sound of its tread, trumpeting, or even breathing might be heard. The dweomer will not work if viewers are beside or behind the caster. The cantrip lasts for 1 turn on an object of 2 cubic yards or less in volume. The duration is reduced by 1 round for every additional 2 cubic yards of volume made to seemingly disappear, until at 20 cubic yards of volume, the duration is 1 round. At over 20 cubic yards of volume, duration is reduced by 1 segment per 2 additional cubic yards; i.e., the hide cantrip will have a duration of 9 segments if cast on an object of 22 cubic yards volume; 8 segments for 24 cubic yards, 7 segments for 26, 6 for 28, 5 for 30, 4 for 32, 3 for 34, 2 for 36, and 1 segment for 38 cubic yards. Anything over 38 cubic yards in volume will at best momentarily disappear and then reappear again. Verbal component is an activating word such as abracadabra while the hand makes a pass across the forepart of the object. The caster can dispel the cantrip simply by speaking the activating word.","link":""},"mute":{"name":"MUte","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"The mute cantrip allows the caster to alter the shape of small objects of a mineral nature. The magic is effective against glass, metal, stone, etc. A plane can be altered to a rod, a torus to a sphere, etc. Thus, a coin could be changed to be a ring. Similarly, glass could be changed to crystal, lead to silver, copper to gold, etc. However, the dweomers of magical items are too strong for this cantrip to affect them. The duration of the mute is but 1 round. If another individual actually touches the object affected, the dweomer of the cantrip might be affected: The individual touching it makes a saving throw versus spell, and if it succeeds the cantrip is dispelled. The components for the mute cantrip are similar to those of a change cantrip.","notes":"The mute cantrip allows the caster to alter the shape of small objects of a mineral nature. The magic is effective against glass, metal, stone, etc. A plane can be altered to a rod, a torus to a sphere, etc. Thus, a coin could be changed to be a ring. Similarly, glass could be changed to crystal, lead to silver, copper to gold, etc. However, the dweomers of magical items are too strong for this cantrip to affect them. The duration of the mute is but 1 round. If another individual actually touches the object affected, the dweomer of the cantrip might be affected: The individual touching it makes a saving throw versus spell, and if it succeeds the cantrip is dispelled. The components for the mute cantrip are similar to those of a change cantrip.","link":""},"palm":{"name":"Palm","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One small item","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip enables the caster to secret a small object in his hand without seeming to do so. The dweomer creates an illusory duplicate of the object to be palmed, so that the other can be taken while under a form of hide cantrip (which actually works regardless of viewer position). The illusory duplicate of the palmed object lasts but 1 segment, so it must be covered or screened from view, or else any onlookers will see it wink out of existence. A special word is spoken while a digit points at the object to be palmed. The caster may then pick up the now-invisible actual object while seemingly only touching or handling the illusory duplicate.","notes":"This cantrip enables the caster to secret a small object in his hand without seeming to do so. The dweomer creates an illusory duplicate of the object to be palmed, so that the other can be taken while under a form of hide cantrip (which actually works regardless of viewer position). The illusory duplicate of the palmed object lasts but 1 segment, so it must be covered or screened from view, or else any onlookers will see it wink out of existence. A special word is spoken while a digit points at the object to be palmed. The caster may then pick up the now-invisible actual object while seemingly only touching or handling the illusory duplicate.","link":""},"present":{"name":"Present","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One person","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A present cantrip enables the caster to bring any small object or series of objects from within a 2-foot radius of his or her person to his or her hand. The object or objects will appear magically in the caster’s hand as he or she puts the hand upward or outward with a flourish and speaks the key word to begin the dweomer. If an object as large as a tankard is thus presented, the cantrip will be exhausted, but as many as a dozen coins could be brought to the hand before the dweomer failed. The caster must know the exact nature and location of the object or objects to be presented. If they are on the person of another individual, a saving throw versus spell applies to the individual, unless the object or objects are in plain sight.\nPerson-Affecting Cantrips: Belch (Evocation)\nWhen this cantrip is cast, the subject will involuntarily belch. A saving throw is applicable only to see how loud or muffled the burping is, failure indicating a very loud belch, success meaning that the sound is relatively low and muffled. The verbal component is an almost inaudible belch, done at the same time that the caster’s hand presses his or her diaphragm.","notes":"A present cantrip enables the caster to bring any small object or series of objects from within a 2-foot radius of his or her person to his or her hand. The object or objects will appear magically in the caster’s hand as he or she puts the hand upward or outward with a flourish and speaks the key word to begin the dweomer. If an object as large as a tankard is thus presented, the cantrip will be exhausted, but as many as a dozen coins could be brought to the hand before the dweomer failed. The caster must know the exact nature and location of the object or objects to be presented. If they are on the person of another individual, a saving throw versus spell applies to the individual, unless the object or objects are in plain sight.\nPerson-Affecting Cantrips: Belch (Evocation)\nWhen this cantrip is cast, the subject will involuntarily belch. A saving throw is applicable only to see how loud or muffled the burping is, failure indicating a very loud belch, success meaning that the sound is relatively low and muffled. The verbal component is an almost inaudible belch, done at the same time that the caster’s hand presses his or her diaphragm.","link":""},"blink":{"name":"Blink","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Personal","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Blink\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Personal\nThis spell causes the magic-user’s material form to blink out and back into the current plane at random times and directions each round. The segment in which the caster blinks is determined by 2d4. The caster reappears 2 feet from the previous position in a random direction: 1 = right ahead, 2 = right, 3 = right behind, 4 = behind, 5 = left behind, 6 = left, 7 = left ahead, 8 = ahead. If the destination is occupied, the caster is displaced away from the starting position by the shortest distance needed to appear in empty space, up to 10 additional feet. If no empty space is available, the caster is trapped on the Ethereal Plane. During and after the blink segment, the caster can only be attacked by effects that strike both locations at once, such as breath weapons or fireball. Other attacks can hit only if made before the blink segment. The caster is only 75% likely to perform actions other than physical attacks with hand-held weapons correctly while the spell lasts; spell, device, or item use may fail or be misdirected at the referee’s discretion.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"cough":{"name":"Cough","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One person","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip enables the caster to make the subject individual cough spasmodically. If a saving throw is made, the cough is only a brief hacking which will not usually disturb other activities. Failing the saving throw indicates the victim is affected by a loud and active series of coughs lasting from 1 to 3 seconds. The somatic component is a gagging gesture while a gasp is verbalized.","notes":"This cantrip enables the caster to make the subject individual cough spasmodically. If a saving throw is made, the cough is only a brief hacking which will not usually disturb other activities. Failing the saving throw indicates the victim is affected by a loud and active series of coughs lasting from 1 to 3 seconds. The somatic component is a gagging gesture while a gasp is verbalized.","link":""},"giggle":{"name":"Giggle","level":"0","school":"Charm","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One person","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes the subject individual to involuntarily giggle. The loudness and length of this reaction depend on the saving throw. If the subject fails to save, the result will be a chuckle or giggle lasting about 2 or 3 seconds. If the save succeeds, only a brief chuckle will be caused. The verbal component is a single word or phrase (known in magical circles as a “punch line”) to be spoken while one finger is moved back and forth rapidly.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes the subject individual to involuntarily giggle. The loudness and length of this reaction depend on the saving throw. If the subject fails to save, the result will be a chuckle or giggle lasting about 2 or 3 seconds. If the save succeeds, only a brief chuckle will be caused. The verbal component is a single word or phrase (known in magical circles as a “punch line”) to be spoken while one finger is moved back and forth rapidly.","link":""},"nod":{"name":"Nod","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One person","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip causes the subject to give an involuntary nod of the head due to muscle contraction. The effect is as if the subject were nodding in agreement or as a greeting. A successful saving throw negates the effect. The caster gives a slight nod of the head while pointing his or her small finger at the subject.","notes":"This cantrip causes the subject to give an involuntary nod of the head due to muscle contraction. The effect is as if the subject were nodding in agreement or as a greeting. A successful saving throw negates the effect. The caster gives a slight nod of the head while pointing his or her small finger at the subject.","link":""},"scratch":{"name":"Scratch","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One creature","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A scratch cantrip causes the subject creature to experience an annoying itch on some portion of the body. Unless a saving throw is successful, the subject will involuntarily scratch at this itch. This scratching will take but a second, and will immediately cause the itch to cease. Verbal component is the name of some body pest (flea, louse, etc.), uttered while the area of the itch is pointed to.","notes":"A scratch cantrip causes the subject creature to experience an annoying itch on some portion of the body. Unless a saving throw is successful, the subject will involuntarily scratch at this itch. This scratching will take but a second, and will immediately cause the itch to cease. Verbal component is the name of some body pest (flea, louse, etc.), uttered while the area of the itch is pointed to.","link":""},"sneeze":{"name":"Sneeze","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One creature","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A cantrip of this nature causes an irritation in the nasal passages of the subject. Unless the subject makes a successful saving throw versus spell, a sneeze will occur. This single sneeze will relieve the irritation. The caster verbalizes the name of an irritant substance while touching his or her nose.","notes":"A cantrip of this nature causes an irritation in the nasal passages of the subject. Unless the subject makes a successful saving throw versus spell, a sneeze will occur. This single sneeze will relieve the irritation. The caster verbalizes the name of an irritant substance while touching his or her nose.","link":""},"twitch":{"name":"Twitch","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One creature","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes a muscle contraction in some portion of the subject creature’s appendages — head, neck, hand, arm, foot, leg, etc. The twitch will be noticeable, but will not cause the subject great discomfort or loss of control or concentration. The cantrip is negated by a successful saving throw. Verbal component is the name of the area to be affected while the caster gazes at the area and makes a twitching motion with the hand.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes a muscle contraction in some portion of the subject creature’s appendages — head, neck, hand, arm, foot, leg, etc. The twitch will be noticeable, but will not cause the subject great discomfort or loss of control or concentration. The cantrip is negated by a successful saving throw. Verbal component is the name of the area to be affected while the caster gazes at the area and makes a twitching motion with the hand.","link":""},"wink":{"name":"Wink","level":"0","school":"Enchantment","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One person","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip enables the caster to cause the subject individual to wink one eye. A saving throw indicates that the winking is rapid and not greatly noticeable, while failure to save indicates a greatly exaggerated, prolonged winking. The caster speaks a magical phrase (such as twenty-three skidoo) while making an imperceptible winking of his or her eye.","notes":"This cantrip enables the caster to cause the subject individual to wink one eye. A saving throw indicates that the winking is rapid and not greatly noticeable, while failure to save indicates a greatly exaggerated, prolonged winking. The caster speaks a magical phrase (such as twenty-three skidoo) while making an imperceptible winking of his or her eye.","link":""},"yawn":{"name":"Yawn","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One bee","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A yawn cantrip makes the subject creature feel a brief wave of drowsiness which in turn evokes a yawn reaction. If a saving throw versus spell succeeds, the subject creature is totally unaffected by the dweomer of the cantrip. Failure, however, not only forces a yawn to immediately occur, but the subject is then more susceptible to a sleep spell. During the balance of the round in which the yawn cantrip was cast, and during the whole of the following round, the subject will automatically fall into comatose slumber from a sleep spell cast upon it, so 1 additional creature will be vulnerable to the spell if more than 1 creature of 4 or fewer hit dice are subjected to the spell. Further, if creatures of 4 + 1 to 4 + 4 hit dice are involved, there is then a chance that two such creatures will actually be affected by sleep. Even a creature of up to 5 + 2 hit dice can be affected by sleep if previously victimized by a yawn cantrip, but the effect of the sleep spell is rolled for as if the creature had 4 + 1 to 4 + 4 hit dice; i.e., there is a 50% chance that it will not be affected. The caster hums a lullaby for the verbal component while making a rocking motion with cupped hands.\nPersonal Cantrips: Bee (Summoning)\nWhen this cantrip is used, the caster summons a honey bee from someplace — where is of no importance, for the creature appears in seconds. The bee will appear in whatever spot the caster is gazing at, up to 1' distance from him or her. The bee is, of course, annoyed, and it is 90% likely to sting any living creature it finds itself upon. (This will certainly cause the subject to react violently if it would otherwise be so affected by a bee sting.) The verbal component is a low buzzing sound, made while the caster moves a forefinger through flight-like passes.","notes":"A yawn cantrip makes the subject creature feel a brief wave of drowsiness which in turn evokes a yawn reaction. If a saving throw versus spell succeeds, the subject creature is totally unaffected by the dweomer of the cantrip. Failure, however, not only forces a yawn to immediately occur, but the subject is then more susceptible to a sleep spell. During the balance of the round in which the yawn cantrip was cast, and during the whole of the following round, the subject will automatically fall into comatose slumber from a sleep spell cast upon it, so 1 additional creature will be vulnerable to the spell if more than 1 creature of 4 or fewer hit dice are subjected to the spell. Further, if creatures of 4 + 1 to 4 + 4 hit dice are involved, there is then a chance that two such creatures will actually be affected by sleep. Even a creature of up to 5 + 2 hit dice can be affected by sleep if previously victimized by a yawn cantrip, but the effect of the sleep spell is rolled for as if the creature had 4 + 1 to 4 + 4 hit dice; i.e., there is a 50% chance that it will not be affected. The caster hums a lullaby for the verbal component while making a rocking motion with cupped hands.\nPersonal Cantrips: Bee (Summoning)\nWhen this cantrip is used, the caster summons a honey bee from someplace — where is of no importance, for the creature appears in seconds. The bee will appear in whatever spot the caster is gazing at, up to 1' distance from him or her. The bee is, of course, annoyed, and it is 90% likely to sting any living creature it finds itself upon. (This will certainly cause the subject to react violently if it would otherwise be so affected by a bee sting.) The verbal component is a low buzzing sound, made while the caster moves a forefinger through flight-like passes.","link":""},"bluelight":{"name":"Bluelight","level":"0","school":"Conjuration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"¼' diam. sphere","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip enables the caster to conjure a small sphere of glowing blue radiance. The light has an eerie effect when seen from a distance, but the 3-inch sphere only illuminates an area of 5' around itself. Furthermore, the bluelight does not cast reflections beyond this radius. The light does not affect either infravision or ultravision. When the caster says a rhyme using the words blue and light in any combination, the bluelight appears in his or her open palm and remains aglow until the caster ceases to concentrate on it.","notes":"This cantrip enables the caster to conjure a small sphere of glowing blue radiance. The light has an eerie effect when seen from a distance, but the 3-inch sphere only illuminates an area of 5' around itself. Furthermore, the bluelight does not cast reflections beyond this radius. The light does not affect either infravision or ultravision. When the caster says a rhyme using the words blue and light in any combination, the bluelight appears in his or her open palm and remains aglow until the caster ceases to concentrate on it.","link":""},"bug":{"name":"Bug","level":"0","school":"Summoning","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One bug","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A variation of the bee cantrip, the bug cantrip enables the caster to summon some form of crawling insect. The beetle or bug appears in the same manner as the bee summoned by the cantrip of that name. It will likewise be irritated and will pinch, bite, or otherwise attack the creature it might find itself upon, with appropriate results. Verbal component is the name of the insect desired while the caster’s forefinger makes a sliding and pointing motion at the desired area of the bug’s appearance (up to 1' distant).","notes":"A variation of the bee cantrip, the bug cantrip enables the caster to summon some form of crawling insect. The beetle or bug appears in the same manner as the bee summoned by the cantrip of that name. It will likewise be irritated and will pinch, bite, or otherwise attack the creature it might find itself upon, with appropriate results. Verbal component is the name of the insect desired while the caster’s forefinger makes a sliding and pointing motion at the desired area of the bug’s appearance (up to 1' distant).","link":""},"firefinger":{"name":"Firefinger","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"½v line","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"The firefinger cantrip enables the caster to cause a jet of flame up to one-half foot in length to shoot forth from his or her finger. The flame is very hot and will ignite combustible materials such as parchment, twigs, kindling, and the like without difficulty, providing the materials are relatively dry. The flame persists for up to 1 segment. To bring about the magic of this cantrip, the caster speaks a word of power over elemental fire (such as ron-son, zip-po, or the much revered word, dun-hill), extends the forefinger, and makes a sideways motion with the thumb.","notes":"The firefinger cantrip enables the caster to cause a jet of flame up to one-half foot in length to shoot forth from his or her finger. The flame is very hot and will ignite combustible materials such as parchment, twigs, kindling, and the like without difficulty, providing the materials are relatively dry. The flame persists for up to 1 segment. To bring about the magic of this cantrip, the caster speaks a word of power over elemental fire (such as ron-son, zip-po, or the much revered word, dun-hill), extends the forefinger, and makes a sideways motion with the thumb.","link":""},"gnats":{"name":"Gnats","level":"0","school":"Summoning","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1 cubic foot","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A cantrip of this nature is similar to the bee and bug cantrips described above, except that when it is used a cloud of gnats is summoned. The swarm will immediately proceed to fly around the head of the nearest living creature (which must be no more than 1' from the caster), and unless this creature makes a successful saving throw versus poison, the cloud of gnats will distract the creature for from 1-4 segments before the gnats fly elsewhere. The verbal component is a high-pitched buzzing sound made with the tongue and upper palate while the caster points a digit at the area in which the gnat cloud is to appear.","notes":"A cantrip of this nature is similar to the bee and bug cantrips described above, except that when it is used a cloud of gnats is summoned. The swarm will immediately proceed to fly around the head of the nearest living creature (which must be no more than 1' from the caster), and unless this creature makes a successful saving throw versus poison, the cloud of gnats will distract the creature for from 1-4 segments before the gnats fly elsewhere. The verbal component is a high-pitched buzzing sound made with the tongue and upper palate while the caster points a digit at the area in which the gnat cloud is to appear.","link":""},"mouse":{"name":"Mouse","level":"0","school":"Summoning","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One mouse","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Similar to the cantrip which summons a bee or a bug, the mouse cantrip enables the caster to bring forth a mouse up to 1' from his or her position. The animal will be a typical field mouse or as similar a species as possible. When it arrives, the caster will have no control over the mouse, and the animal will behave as would any mouse in the given situation. The caster speaks a summoning word (typically the name of a food desirable by mice) while holding his or her hands in such a way as to resemble mouse ears.","notes":"Similar to the cantrip which summons a bee or a bug, the mouse cantrip enables the caster to bring forth a mouse up to 1' from his or her position. The animal will be a typical field mouse or as similar a species as possible. When it arrives, the caster will have no control over the mouse, and the animal will behave as would any mouse in the given situation. The caster speaks a summoning word (typically the name of a food desirable by mice) while holding his or her hands in such a way as to resemble mouse ears.","link":""},"smokepuff":{"name":"Smokepuff","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1' diam. cloud","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"When this cantrip is employed, a puff of actual smoke appears in the desired location, up to 1' distant from the caster, and will ascend as would a normal cloud of smoke, or be dissipated, depending on the prevailing conditions. The caster can cause the smoke to be either white, gray, black, brown, yellow, or green. The caster names the color of smoke desired while moving a hand from an extended horizontal position to a vertical one, meanwhile breathing forth a puff of air.","notes":"When this cantrip is employed, a puff of actual smoke appears in the desired location, up to 1' distant from the caster, and will ascend as would a normal cloud of smoke, or be dissipated, depending on the prevailing conditions. The caster can cause the smoke to be either white, gray, black, brown, yellow, or green. The caster names the color of smoke desired while moving a hand from an extended horizontal position to a vertical one, meanwhile breathing forth a puff of air.","link":""},"spider":{"name":"Spider","level":"0","school":"Summoning","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One spider","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip, much as does a bee or bug or mouse or gnats cantrip, summons a small, ordinary spider from elsewhere to the location desired by the caster, up to 1' distant from his or her person. The arachnid so summoned will usually be a common garden spider or the like, no larger than an inch or two in diameter, and basically harmless. There is a 5% chance that the creature will turn out to be one with powerful poison (black widow, brown recluse, etc.). Since the spider summoned will be annoyed, the creature upon which it finds itself, if such is the case, will be subject to an immediate bite attack. This will have only a momentary effect, distracting the victim for 1 segment, for a normal spider. If the spider is of the very poisonous sort, the victim must also make a saving throw versus poison at +4. Success indicates 1 point of damage is inflicted. Failure indicates 2 points of damage are inflicted, and the victim will feel sick and be unable to act normally for 1-4 days unless a neutralize poison spell is cast to remove the toxin. (A slow poison will defer the sickness for 1 day.) To cast the cantrip, the caster speaks the word arachnid while spreading his or her fingers and wiggling them.","notes":"This cantrip, much as does a bee or bug or mouse or gnats cantrip, summons a small, ordinary spider from elsewhere to the location desired by the caster, up to 1' distant from his or her person. The arachnid so summoned will usually be a common garden spider or the like, no larger than an inch or two in diameter, and basically harmless. There is a 5% chance that the creature will turn out to be one with powerful poison (black widow, brown recluse, etc.). Since the spider summoned will be annoyed, the creature upon which it finds itself, if such is the case, will be subject to an immediate bite attack. This will have only a momentary effect, distracting the victim for 1 segment, for a normal spider. If the spider is of the very poisonous sort, the victim must also make a saving throw versus poison at +4. Success indicates 1 point of damage is inflicted. Failure indicates 2 points of damage are inflicted, and the victim will feel sick and be unable to act normally for 1-4 days unless a neutralize poison spell is cast to remove the toxin. (A slow poison will defer the sickness for 1 day.) To cast the cantrip, the caster speaks the word arachnid while spreading his or her fingers and wiggling them.","link":""},"tweak":{"name":"Tweak","level":"0","school":"Conjuration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One creature","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes an unseen thumb and forefinger to harmlessly, but annoyingly, tweak some portion of a chosen subject within a 1' radius of the caster. Portions subject to the tweak cantrip are: cheek, nose, ear, beard, moustache, whiskers, or tail. The cantrip’s effects do not disturb spell casting, although the tweaking might distract any creature by causing it to turn to discover the source of the annoyance. A failure to save versus spell (with respect to creatures with an intelligence under 7), or failure to roll a score greater than intelligence on 3d6 (with respect to creatures with intelligence of 7 or greater), indicates a 1-segment distraction. The caster speaks a magic phrase (such as kitchy-kitchy-coo) while making a pinching and pulling motion with thumb and forefinger.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes an unseen thumb and forefinger to harmlessly, but annoyingly, tweak some portion of a chosen subject within a 1' radius of the caster. Portions subject to the tweak cantrip are: cheek, nose, ear, beard, moustache, whiskers, or tail. The cantrip’s effects do not disturb spell casting, although the tweaking might distract any creature by causing it to turn to discover the source of the annoyance. A failure to save versus spell (with respect to creatures with an intelligence under 7), or failure to roll a score greater than intelligence on 3d6 (with respect to creatures with intelligence of 7 or greater), indicates a 1-segment distraction. The caster speaks a magic phrase (such as kitchy-kitchy-coo) while making a pinching and pulling motion with thumb and forefinger.","link":""},"unlock":{"name":"Unlock","level":"0","school":"Conjuration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip enables the caster to conjure an invisible, key-like force appropriate to the locking mechanism to be opened (or closed). The unlock cantrip will affect only simple locks of the most basic sort — typically those which have closing pressure prongs or bolt and pins, or bolt and spring closures. Locks with tumblers or levers, as well as secret-combination locks, are not subject to this cantrip. Note that simple locks with complex wards to prevent skeleton-key triggering will be subject to an unlock cantrip. While the caster speaks a word or phrase associated with locks (tick-tock-doublelock or yah-el, etc.) he or she makes a twisting motion with fingers held as if to grasp a key.\nHaunting-Sound Cantrips: Creak (Evocation)\nBy means of this cantrip, the caster evokes a noise similar to that of a door with corroded hinges slowly opening, or else a sound as if someone or something were walking across squeaking floorboards. The former sound lasts for 1 /3 segment; the latter noise will last half a segment and seem to traverse up to 10 feet distance. The caster makes a low creaking sound in his or her throat while using a hand to make an opening motion or fingers to make a walking motion.","notes":"This cantrip enables the caster to conjure an invisible, key-like force appropriate to the locking mechanism to be opened (or closed). The unlock cantrip will affect only simple locks of the most basic sort — typically those which have closing pressure prongs or bolt and pins, or bolt and spring closures. Locks with tumblers or levers, as well as secret-combination locks, are not subject to this cantrip. Note that simple locks with complex wards to prevent skeleton-key triggering will be subject to an unlock cantrip. While the caster speaks a word or phrase associated with locks (tick-tock-doublelock or yah-el, etc.) he or she makes a twisting motion with fingers held as if to grasp a key.\nHaunting-Sound Cantrips: Creak (Evocation)\nBy means of this cantrip, the caster evokes a noise similar to that of a door with corroded hinges slowly opening, or else a sound as if someone or something were walking across squeaking floorboards. The former sound lasts for 1 /3 segment; the latter noise will last half a segment and seem to traverse up to 10 feet distance. The caster makes a low creaking sound in his or her throat while using a hand to make an opening motion or fingers to make a walking motion.","link":""},"footfall":{"name":"Footfall","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"When this cantrip is used, the caster creates the aural illusion of footsteps. The sound is as if a human or humanoid was walking. The footfalls can be soft or fairly noisy. They can approach, move away from, follow, or otherwise seem to parallel a person or party. They must begin within 1' of the caster, but they may thereafter move away from him or her up to a 2' distance, or may approach closer than 1'. The caster must softly vocalize sounds similar to footsteps while pointing in the area they are to occur initially and subsequently.","notes":"When this cantrip is used, the caster creates the aural illusion of footsteps. The sound is as if a human or humanoid was walking. The footfalls can be soft or fairly noisy. They can approach, move away from, follow, or otherwise seem to parallel a person or party. They must begin within 1' of the caster, but they may thereafter move away from him or her up to a 2' distance, or may approach closer than 1'. The caster must softly vocalize sounds similar to footsteps while pointing in the area they are to occur initially and subsequently.","link":""},"groan":{"name":"Groan","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A groan cantrip creates the audible illusion of a wracking cry coming from some location no more than 1' from the caster. Naturally, those creatures within hearing distance are allowed a saving throw versus spell, and if it succeeds, the individual will hear no such noise. The caster makes a soft groaning sound in his or her throat while pointing to the area from which the sound is to appear to come. A container or door will not hamper the range, so that a groaning sound can be made to seem to come from behind a door, in a chest, etc.","notes":"A groan cantrip creates the audible illusion of a wracking cry coming from some location no more than 1' from the caster. Naturally, those creatures within hearing distance are allowed a saving throw versus spell, and if it succeeds, the individual will hear no such noise. The caster makes a soft groaning sound in his or her throat while pointing to the area from which the sound is to appear to come. A container or door will not hamper the range, so that a groaning sound can be made to seem to come from behind a door, in a chest, etc.","link":""},"moan":{"name":"Moan","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip is the same as a groan cantrip, except that the sound involved is either a pitiful moaning or else an eerie one. The desired sound is either a low-pitched one for the haunting effect or a high-pitched one for the pitiful effect.","notes":"This cantrip is the same as a groan cantrip, except that the sound involved is either a pitiful moaning or else an eerie one. The desired sound is either a low-pitched one for the haunting effect or a high-pitched one for the pitiful effect.","link":""},"rattle":{"name":"Rattle","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes the audible illusion of a rattling sound associated with chains. Its direction and distance is the same as for a groan cantrip. The sound will last for up to 2 seconds. All creatures within 1' of the sound are entitled to a saving throw versus spell to determine whether they hear the illusory sound. The spell caster names the rattling device which he or she desires to create the illusion of while shaking one hand vigorously.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes the audible illusion of a rattling sound associated with chains. Its direction and distance is the same as for a groan cantrip. The sound will last for up to 2 seconds. All creatures within 1' of the sound are entitled to a saving throw versus spell to determine whether they hear the illusory sound. The spell caster names the rattling device which he or she desires to create the illusion of while shaking one hand vigorously.","link":""},"tap":{"name":"Tap","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1 sq. ft.","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster is able to evoke an invisible force which will tap or rap against some solid object — a door, lid, floor, table, wall, pane, or whatever. The sound will occur once, twice, or thrice, according to the number of fingers extended by the caster. It is an actual sound; creatures within 1' of the noise will certainly hear it if they are able. Verbal component is a hollow sound created by the tongue against the palate, or a key phrase spoken softly, while the finger makes a tapping motion.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster is able to evoke an invisible force which will tap or rap against some solid object — a door, lid, floor, table, wall, pane, or whatever. The sound will occur once, twice, or thrice, according to the number of fingers extended by the caster. It is an actual sound; creatures within 1' of the noise will certainly hear it if they are able. Verbal component is a hollow sound created by the tongue against the palate, or a key phrase spoken softly, while the finger makes a tapping motion.","link":""},"thump":{"name":"Thump","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"An audible illusion, the thump cantrip causes all creatures within a 1' radius of the area of effect to hear a loud but muffled thumping sound, as if something large just fell from a height of a foot or so. A successful saving throw versus spell nullifies the cantrip’s effect. The caster can cause the sound to seemingly come from any location within a 1' radius of his or her person. The caster swallows loudly while pointing toward the area where the cantrip is to come from, while thinking of the thumping sound.","notes":"An audible illusion, the thump cantrip causes all creatures within a 1' radius of the area of effect to hear a loud but muffled thumping sound, as if something large just fell from a height of a foot or so. A successful saving throw versus spell nullifies the cantrip’s effect. The caster can cause the sound to seemingly come from any location within a 1' radius of his or her person. The caster swallows loudly while pointing toward the area where the cantrip is to come from, while thinking of the thumping sound.","link":""},"whistle":{"name":"Whistle","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"When this cantrip is cast, the dweomer causes a faint or loud whistling sound. A faint whistling can be heard within 10', a loud one within 30'. The sound can be sharp and normal-seeming or echoing, hollow, and eerie. The caster must whistle softly in a manner similar to the desired sound while he or she looks at the area from which the sound is to come and holds two fingers near his or her mouth.","notes":"When this cantrip is cast, the dweomer causes a faint or loud whistling sound. A faint whistling can be heard within 10', a loud one within 30'. The sound can be sharp and normal-seeming or echoing, hollow, and eerie. The caster must whistle softly in a manner similar to the desired sound while he or she looks at the area from which the sound is to come and holds two fingers near his or her mouth.","link":""},"affect normal fires":{"name":"Affect Normal Fires","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"3-foot diameter fire","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Affect Normal Fires\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3-foot diameter fire\nThis spell allows the magic-user to affect small fires, from a torch or lantern up to a normal bonfire no more than 3 feet in diameter. The caster may reduce the fire’s size and light until it becomes match-like, or increase its light until it is as bright as a light spell. Reducing the fire halves fuel consumption, while increasing the fire doubles fuel consumption. Heat output is not changed.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"burning hands":{"name":"Burning Hands","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 round","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Burning Hands\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nWhen this spell is cast, jets of searing flame shoot from the magic-user’s fingertips. The hands must be held with thumbs touching and fingers spread, producing a fan-like sheet of flame. The flame extends 3 feet in a horizontal arc of about 120 degrees in front of the caster. Any creature in the area takes 1 point of damage per caster level, with no saving throw. Flammable materials touched by the fire, such as cloth, paper, parchment, and thin wood, ignite.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"charm person":{"name":"Charm Person","level":"1","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"12”","duration":"Special","aoe":"One person","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Charm Person\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One person\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 2nd-level druid spell charm person or mammal, but the magic-user can charm only persons. This includes brownies, dwarves, elves, gnolls, gnomes, goblins, half-elves, halflings, half-orcs, hobgoblins, humans, kobolds, lizard men, nixies, orcs, pixies, sprites, and troglodytes. All other comments regarding the spell’s effects apply to persons.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"comprehend languages":{"name":"Comprehend Languages","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"One written object or speaking creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Comprehend Languages\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Confuse Languages\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One written object or speaking creature\nThis spell allows the magic-user to read an otherwise incomprehensible written message, such as a treasure map, or understand the language of a speaking creature. It does not allow magical writing to be read, except to recognize it as magical. The caster must touch the writing or creature. The spell does not enable the caster to write or speak the language. The reverse, confuse languages, prevents comprehension or cancels comprehend languages. Material Components: A pinch of soot and a few grains of salt.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"dancing lights":{"name":"Dancing Lights","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"4” + 1” per level","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Dancing Lights\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 4” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates, at the caster’s option, 1 to 4 lights resembling torches or lanterns, glowing spheres like will-o-wisps, or one faintly glowing, vaguely man-like shape similar to a creature from the Elemental Plane of Fire. The lights move as the caster desires: forward, backward, straight, or around corners, without concentration. The spell ends if range or duration is exceeded. Material Component: A bit of phosphorus, wytchwood, or a glowworm.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"detect magic":{"name":"Detect Magic","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"1” path, 6” long","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Magic\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” path, 6” long\nThis spell is the same as the 1st-level cleric spell detect magic, except as noted above: it has a different duration and area of effect, and it requires no material component.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"enlarge":{"name":"Enlarge","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Enlarge\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Reduce\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes instant growth of one creature or object, increasing both size and weight. The target must be visible. Living creatures increase by 20% per caster level, to a maximum additional growth of 200%. Objects increase by 10% per caster level, to a maximum additional growth of 100%. The maximum initial volume affected is 10 cubic feet of living material per caster level, or 5 cubic feet of nonliving matter per caster level. Magical properties are not increased, but weight, mass, and strength are. For example, a table blocking a door becomes heavier and more effective; a hurled stone becomes more massive if enlarged just before impact; chains become more massive; doors become thicker; a thin line becomes a sizable rope; a 12-foot person is comparable to an ogre; and an 18-foot person is effectively a giant for the spell’s duration. The reverse, reduce, negates enlarge or makes creatures and objects smaller by the same ratios. Unwilling targets receive a saving throw; success means the spell has no effect and is wasted. Material Component: A pinch of powdered iron.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"erase":{"name":"Erase","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"3”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One scroll or two facing pages","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Erase\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One scroll or two facing pages\nThis spell removes magical or mundane writing from a scroll, or from one or two pages or sheets of paper, parchment, or similar surfaces. It does not remove explosive runes or a symbol. The base chance of success is 50%, plus 2% per caster level for magical writing, or plus 4% per caster level for mundane writing. This chance represents the saving throw; a percentile roll above the adjusted chance means the spell fails.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"feather fall":{"name":"Feather Fall","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 segment per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, M","ct":"1/10 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Feather Fall\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1/10 segment\nDuration: 1 segment per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes affected falling creatures or objects to assume the mass of a feathery piece of down. Their falling rate immediately changes to 2 feet per second, or 12 feet per segment, and they take no damage on landing while the spell is active. When the spell ends, normal falling resumes. The spell may affect the caster, another creature, or an object within range. It affects an area of 1 cubic inch, and the total maximum weight is 2,000 gold pieces plus 2,000 gold pieces per caster level. For example, a 2nd-level magic-user has a 2” range, 2-segment duration, and 6,000 gold piece, or 600-pound, weight maximum. The spell works only on free-falling or propelled objects. It does not affect a sword blow or charging creature, but it can affect a missile. Material Component: A small feather or piece of down somewhere on the caster’s person.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"find familiar":{"name":"Find Familiar","level":"1","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1 mile per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"As spell range","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1–24 hours","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Find Familiar\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1 mile per level\nCasting Time: 1–24 hours\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: As spell range\nThis spell summons a familiar, which benefits a magic-user by adding to the caster’s hit points, conveying sensory powers, conversing with the caster, and serving as guard, scout, or spy. The magic-user has no control over what type of creature answers, or whether any creature comes. The spell may be attempted only once per year. To cast it, the magic-user must burn charcoal in a brass brazier, then add 100 gp worth of incense, herbs, and fat. The herbs must include basil, savory, and catnip. The incantation continues until the familiar arrives or the casting time ends. The referee secretly determines all results.\n\nFamiliar Table\nd20 Roll\tFamiliar\tSensory Powers\n1–4\tBlack cat\tExcellent night vision and superior hearing\n5–6\tCrow\tExcellent vision\n7–8\tHawk\tVery superior distance vision\n9–10\tScreech owl\tNight vision equal to human daylight vision and superior hearing\n11–12\tToad\tWide-angle vision\n13–14\tWeasel\tSuperior hearing and very superior smell\n15\tSpecial\tSee special familiar table\n16–20\tNo familiar available\tNone\n\nSubtract 1 from the die roll for each 3 caster levels. If the modified score is 15 or less, roll again using d16; if a 16 is rolled, that result is final.\n\nSpecial Familiar Table\nMagic-User Alignment\tSpecial Familiar\nChaotic evil or chaotic neutral\tQuasit\nChaotic good, neutral, or neutral good\tPseudo-dragon\nLawful neutral or lawful good\tBrownie\nLawful evil or neutral evil\tImp\n\nNormal familiars have 2–4 hit points and Armor Class 7 due to size and speed. Each is unusually intelligent and totally faithful to the magic-user. The familiar’s hit points are added to the caster’s hit point total while it is within 12” of its master. If the familiar is killed, the magic-user permanently loses double that number of hit points. Special familiars have powers described in the Monster Manual, except for the brownie. A brownie familiar becomes a friend and companion; the magic-user gains Dexterity 18, cannot be surprised, and gains +2 on all saving throws. Special familiars receive a saving throw versus magic when summoned. If successful, they ignore the spell, and no familiar is available that year. A familiar fights for the magic-user’s life only in a life-or-death situation, and imps and quasits are 90% likely not to do so if risking their own lives.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"friends":{"name":"Friends","level":"1","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"1” + 1” per level radius sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Friends\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 1” + 1” per level radius sphere\nThis spell temporarily increases the magic-user’s Charisma by 2d4 points or lowers it by 1d4 points, depending on whether creatures in the area fail or make their saving throws versus magic. Creatures that fail are impressed by the caster and strongly desire to be friendly and helpful. Creatures that save are uneasy around the caster and tend to find them irritating. This spell has no effect on creatures of animal intelligence or lower. Material Components: Chalk or white flour, lampblack or soot, and vermillion applied to the face before casting.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"hold portal":{"name":"Hold Portal","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"2” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"80 square feet per level","components":"V","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Hold Portal\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V\nRange: 2” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 80 square feet per level\nThis spell magically bars a door, gate, or valve of wood, metal, or stone. The closure holds fast as if securely stopped and locked. Any extra-dimensional creature, such as a demon, devil, or elemental, shatters such a held portal. A magic-user at least 4 experience levels higher than the caster can open the portal at will. Knock or dispel magic negates the spell. Held portals can also be broken or battered down.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"identify":{"name":"Identify","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"1 segment per level","aoe":"One item","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Identify\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 segment per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One item\nThis spell allows the magic-user to touch and handle one item to possibly determine its magical properties. The item must be held or worn in the normal manner, such as a bracelet on the wrist, helm on the head, boots on the feet, cloak worn, dagger held, and so on. Any consequences of using the item fall fully on the magic-user, though any normal saving throw still applies. For each segment the spell remains in force, there is a 15% chance plus 5% per caster level that one property becomes known, including the possibility that the item has no true properties and is a ruse, such as Nystul’s magic aura or magic mouth. Each time a property might be learned, the referee secretly checks the caster’s saving throw versus magic. If successful, the property is known. If the save is missed by 1 point, a false power is revealed. If missed by more than 1, no information is gained. Exact bonuses to hit or damage are never revealed, though the caster may learn whether the item has few or many such bonuses. If the item has charges, the exact number is never revealed, but the caster senses a number within 25% of the actual total. The item must be examined within 1 hour per caster level after discovery, or impressions become blended with those of later possessors. After casting and learning what can be learned, the magic-user loses 8 Constitution points and must rest 6 turns per point to regain them. If this loss drops Constitution below 3, the caster falls unconscious and does not awaken until full Constitution is restored 24 hours later. Material Components: A pearl worth at least 100 gp and an owl feather steeped in wine, with the infusion drunk and a live miniature carp swallowed whole before casting. If a luckstone is powdered and added to the infusion, the probability increases by 25%, and all saving throws are made at +4.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"jump":{"name":"Jump","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Jump\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell allows the recipient to leap up to 30 feet forward, 10 feet backward, or 10 feet straight upward. Horizontal leaps have only a slight arc, about 2 feet per 10 feet traveled. The spell does not ensure safe landing or grasping at the end of the leap. For every 3 caster levels beyond 1st, the caster grants one additional leap: 2 leaps at 4th level, 3 leaps at 7th level, and so on. All leaps must be completed within 1 turn after casting. Material Component: One grasshopper hind leg for each leap, broken when the leap is made.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"light":{"name":"Light","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"6”","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"2” radius globe","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Light\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2” radius globe\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 1st-level cleric spell light.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic missile":{"name":"Magic Missile","level":"1","school":"Evocation","range":"6” + 1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"One or more creatures in a 10-square-foot area","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Magic Missile\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One or more creatures in a 10-square-foot area\nThis spell creates one or more magical missiles that dart from the magic-user’s fingertip and unerringly strike their target. Each missile deals 1d4 + 1 damage. If the caster has multiple missiles, they may strike one creature or several creatures as desired. Range is 6” plus 1” per caster level. The caster gains one additional missile for every 2 levels of experience: 2 missiles at 3rd level, 3 at 5th level, 4 at 7th level, and so on.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"mending":{"name":"Mending","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"3”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mending\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One object\nThis spell repairs small breaks in objects. It can weld a broken ring, chain link, medallion, or slender dagger, provided there is only one break. Ceramic or wooden objects with multiple breaks can be invisibly rejoined and made as strong as new. A hole in a leather sack or wineskin is completely sealed. The spell does not repair magic items. Material Components: Two small magnets, likely lodestones, or two burrs.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"message":{"name":"Message","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"6” + 1” per level","duration":"5 segments + 1 segment per level","aoe":"¼” path","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Message\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 5 segments + 1 segment per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: ¼” path\nWhen this spell is cast, the magic-user whispers a message and secretly or openly points at the intended recipient. The whispered message travels in a straight line and is audible to the creature pointed at. The message must fit within the spell’s duration. If time remains, the recipient may whisper a reply that the caster hears. There must be an open, unobstructed path between caster and recipient. Material Component: A short piece of finely drawn copper.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"niam s magic aura":{"name":"Niam’S Magic Aura","level":"1","school":"School: Illusion","range":"Touch","duration":"1 day/level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Creates a false magical aura around one object (maximum weight 5 lbs. per level). Detect magic perceives the object as magical.\nNotes:\nIf the item is handled by someone who has cast detect magic, that caster may save to realize the aura is false.","notes":"Creates a false magical aura around one object (maximum weight 5 lbs. per level). Detect magic perceives the object as magical.\nNotes:\nIf the item is handled by someone who has cast detect magic, that caster may save to realize the aura is false.","link":""},"protection from evil":{"name":"Protection From Evil","level":"1","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Protection From Evil\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Protection From Good\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 1st-level cleric spell protection from evil. The magic-user version requires powdered iron and silver as material components for tracing the protective circle.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"push":{"name":"Push","level":"1","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1” + ¼” per level","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Push\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” + ¼” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates an invisible force that strikes the object or creature the magic-user points at. The force is slight, equal to 1 foot-pound per caster level. It can move small objects up to 1 foot directly away from the caster, topple an object under proper conditions, or cause a creature to lose balance. For example, a creature attacking may lose balance and be unable to attack that round if it fails its saving throw. The creature’s mass cannot exceed the force of the push by more than a factor of 50; a 1st-level magic-user cannot effectively push a creature weighing more than 50 pounds. Used against an object held by a creature, the spell subtracts its force in foot-pounds from the creature’s chance to hit, or adds to opponent saving throws as applicable, if the holder fails its saving throw versus magic. Material Component: A small pinch of powdered brass blown from the palm before pointing.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"read magic":{"name":"Read Magic","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Read Magic\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Unreadable Magic\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the magic-user to read magical inscriptions on objects such as books, scrolls, and weapons that would otherwise be unintelligible. The caster’s own spellbooks and works already read by magic are already intelligible. Deciphering does not normally invoke the magic in the writing, though it may do so with a cursed scroll. Once the spell has been used to read a particular inscription, the magic-user can read that writing thereafter without using read magic. The reverse, unreadable magic, makes magical writing unreadable to any creature, even with read magic, until the spell ends or is dispelled. Material Component: For read magic, a clear crystal or mineral prism, not consumed by casting. For unreadable magic, a pinch of dirt and a drop of water.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"shield":{"name":"Shield","level":"1","school":"Evocation","range":"0","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Shield\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates an invisible barrier in front of the magic-user. It completely negates magic missile attacks. It provides Armor Class 2 against hand-hurled missiles such as axes, darts, javelins, and spears; Armor Class 3 against small device-propelled missiles such as arrows, bolts, bullets, manticore spikes, and sling stones; and Armor Class 4 against all other attacks. The shield also grants +1 on saving throws against attacks that are basically frontal. These benefits apply only to attacks from the caster’s front, where the shield can interpose itself.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"shocking grasp":{"name":"Shocking Grasp","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"One touch","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Shocking Grasp\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: One touch\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell gives the magic-user a powerful electrical charge. The touched creature takes 1d8 damage plus 1 point per caster level. For example, a 2nd-level magic-user deals 1d8 + 2 damage. The caster need only touch the opponent’s body or an electrical conductor touching the opponent. A touch from the opponent does not discharge the spell.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"sleep":{"name":"Sleep","level":"1","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"3” + 1” per level","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Sleep\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell usually causes one or more creatures to fall into comatose slumber, excluding undead and certain other creatures specifically immune to the spell. All affected creatures must be within a 3” diameter circle. The number affected depends on Hit Dice or life energy levels.\n\nCreature Hit Dice\tNumber Affected\nUp to 1\t4d4\n1+1 to 2\t2d4\n2+1 to 3\t1d4\n3+1 to 4\t1d2\n4+1 to 4+4\t0–1, affected on d4 roll of 3 or 4\n\nThe caster determines the center of the area within range. Slapping or wounding awakens affected creatures, but noise does not. Awakening requires 1 complete melee round. Sleeping creatures can be slain automatically at a rate of 1 per slayer per melee round. Material Component: A pinch of fine sand, rose petals, or a live cricket.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"spider climb":{"name":"Spider Climb","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round + 1 round per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Spider Climb\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell allows the recipient to climb and travel on vertical surfaces like a giant spider, at 3” movement rate, and even hang upside down from ceilings. The creature must have bare hands and feet to climb this way. During the spell, the recipient cannot handle objects weighing less than 50 gold pieces, since such objects stick to their hands and feet. A magic-user under spider climb will find spellcasting virtually impossible. Material Components: A drop of bitumen and a live spider, both eaten by the recipient.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"tanzur s floating disk":{"name":"Tanzur’S Floating Disk","level":"1","school":"School: Evocation","range":"20 ft.","duration":"3 turns + 1 turn/level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Fast","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Conjures an invisible disk about 3 feet across, shaped like a shallow bowl. It floats and moves by the caster’s command, but disappears if more than 20 feet from the caster.\nNotes:\n    Maximum speed: 60 ft. per round.\n    Capacity: 100 lbs. per caster level.","notes":"Conjures an invisible disk about 3 feet across, shaped like a shallow bowl. It floats and moves by the caster’s command, but disappears if more than 20 feet from the caster.\nNotes:\n    Maximum speed: 60 ft. per round.\n    Capacity: 100 lbs. per caster level.","link":""},"unseen servant":{"name":"Unseen Servant","level":"1","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"0","duration":"6 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"3” radius around caster","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Unseen Servant\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 6 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” radius around caster\nThis spell creates an invisible servant, a non-visible valet or butler-like force that fetches, opens doors, holds chairs, cleans, and mends. It is not strong, but obeys the caster’s commands. It can carry light items: up to 200 gold pieces suspended, or twice that across a relatively friction-free surface such as smooth stone or wood. It can open only normal doors, drawers, lids, and similar objects. It cannot fight or be killed, since it is a force rather than a creature. It can be dispelled or eliminated after taking 6 hit points of magical damage. Material Components: A piece of string and a bit of wood.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"ventriloquism":{"name":"Ventriloquism","level":"1","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"1” per level, maximum 6”","duration":"2 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"One object","components":"V, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Ventriloquism\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 1” per level, maximum 6”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 2 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One object\nThis spell allows the magic-user to make their voice, another voice, or a similar sound seem to issue from somewhere else, such as another creature, statue, behind a door, or down a passage. The caster may make the voice sound like a different creature, provided the language is known or the sound can normally be made by the caster. A hearer has a 10% chance per point of Intelligence above 12 to recognize the ruse. Material Component: A small cone of parchment.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"write":{"name":"Write","level":"1","school":"Evocation","range":"0","duration":"1 hour per level","aoe":"One magical spell inscription","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Write\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 hour per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One magical spell inscription\nThis spell may allow the magic-user to inscribe a spell they cannot yet understand into their spellbook or other spell compilation. The caster must make a saving throw versus magic to attempt the writing: +2 if the spell is only up to 1 level higher than the caster can currently use, no modifier if it is 2 levels higher, and -1 per level from 3 levels higher onward. If the save fails, the magic-user takes 1d4 damage per level of the spell being transcribed and is knocked unconscious for the same number of turns. This damage, if not fatal, heals only at 1d4 points per day. Transcription takes 1 hour per spell level, during which the magic-user is in a trance and can always be surprised. Material Component: A writing surface and fine ink made from rare substances, costing at least 200 gp per bottle if available.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 2nd Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"audible glamour":{"name":"Audible Glamour","level":"2","school":"School: Illusion","range":"60 ft. + 10 ft./level","duration":"2 rounds/level","aoe":"Within hearing distance of a chosen point","components":"V, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Special (see below)","save_type":"","description":"This spell creates illusory sounds issuing from a point in space within range (the “focal point”). The caster determines the nature of the sounds, but their maximum loudness is limited by caster level.\nNotes:\n    The caster may move the focal point at will (so long as it remains within range) until the spell ends.\n    Any type of sound may be created. A 3rd-level caster can produce noise equivalent to four people shouting (or less). Each additional caster level adds the equivalent of four more people.\n    As a benchmark, the sound of an explosion or landslide generally requires about an 8th-level caster.\n    Saving throws are allowed only if a listener has reason to doubt the sound. Players must declare disbelief; the referee determines disbelief for monsters and NPCs based on circumstances and plausibility.","notes":"This spell creates illusory sounds issuing from a point in space within range (the “focal point”). The caster determines the nature of the sounds, but their maximum loudness is limited by caster level.\nNotes:\n    The caster may move the focal point at will (so long as it remains within range) until the spell ends.\n    Any type of sound may be created. A 3rd-level caster can produce noise equivalent to four people shouting (or less). Each additional caster level adds the equivalent of four more people.\n    As a benchmark, the sound of an explosion or landslide generally requires about an 8th-level caster.\n    Saving throws are allowed only if a listener has reason to doubt the sound. Players must declare disbelief; the referee determines disbelief for monsters and NPCs based on circumstances and plausibility.","link":""},"continual light":{"name":"Continual Light","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"6”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"6” radius globe","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Continual Light\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6” radius globe\nThis spell is the same as the 3rd-level cleric spell continual light, except that its range is 6” instead of 12”, and the caster cannot reverse it.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"detect evil":{"name":"Detect Evil","level":"2","school":"Divination","range":"6”","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"1” path","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Evil\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Detect Good\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” path\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 1st-level cleric spell detect evil.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"detect invisibility":{"name":"Detect Invisibility","level":"2","school":"Divination","range":"1” per level","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"1” path","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Invisibility\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” path\nThis spell allows the magic-user to clearly see invisible objects, as well as astral, ethereal, hidden, invisible, or out-of-phase creatures. Detection occurs in the caster’s line of sight along a 1” wide path to the range limit. Material Components: A pinch of talc and a small sprinkling of powdered silver.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"esp":{"name":"ESP","level":"2","school":"Divination","range":"½” per level, maximum 9”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"One creature per probe","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"ESP\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level, maximum 9”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature per probe\nThis spell allows the caster to detect the surface thoughts of creatures in range, except creatures with no mind as we understand it, such as undead. ESP is blocked by 2 or more feet of rock, 2 or more inches of any metal other than lead, or a thin sheet of lead foil. The caster may probe the surface thoughts of 1 creature per turn, receiving simple instinctual thoughts from lower creatures. Probes may continue on the same creature from round to round. The spell can help determine whether a creature lurks behind a door, though it will not always reveal what sort of creature it is. Material Component: A copper piece.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"fool s gold":{"name":"Fool’S Gold","level":"2","school":"School: Transmutation","range":"10 ft.","duration":"6 turns/level","aoe":"1 cubic foot/level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Transmutes base metal into a metal closely resembling gold (about 1 cubic foot per caster level—roughly 2,000 copper coins).\nNotes:\n    Observers may detect the fraud: if d20 + caster level is ≤ observer’s Intelligence, the deception is noticed. (The referee may choose or roll Intelligence for creatures as needed.)\n    Expensive material components may improve believability, at the referee’s discretion.\n    Mundane tests may reveal the effect; e.g., striking with cold iron may have a 10% chance to revert the metal (exact methods are referee-determined).","notes":"Transmutes base metal into a metal closely resembling gold (about 1 cubic foot per caster level—roughly 2,000 copper coins).\nNotes:\n    Observers may detect the fraud: if d20 + caster level is ≤ observer’s Intelligence, the deception is noticed. (The referee may choose or roll Intelligence for creatures as needed.)\n    Expensive material components may improve believability, at the referee’s discretion.\n    Mundane tests may reveal the effect; e.g., striking with cold iron may have a 10% chance to revert the metal (exact methods are referee-determined).","link":""},"forget":{"name":"Forget","level":"2","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"3”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"2” × 2”","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Forget\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 2” × 2”\nThis spell causes creatures in the area to forget events of the previous round, meaning the previous 1 minute before the spell is uttered. For every 3 caster levels, another minute of past time is forgotten. The spell does not negate charm, suggestion, geas, quest, or similar magic, but the creature who caused such magic might be forgotten. The caster may affect 1d4 creatures. If only 1 creature is affected, it saves versus magic at -2. If 2 are affected, each saves at -1. If 3 or 4 are affected, saves are normal. A clerical heal or restoration spell specially cast for this purpose restores the lost memories, as does wish; other means do not.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"invisibility":{"name":"Invisibility","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Invisibility\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell causes the recipient to vanish from sight and become undetectable by normal vision or infravision. The invisible creature is not magically silenced. The spell lasts until magically broken or dispelled, cancelled by the caster or recipient, or until the recipient attacks any creature. The recipient may open doors, talk, eat, climb stairs, and so on, but attacking immediately makes them visible, though the first attack benefits from prior invisibility. Even allies cannot see the invisible creature or gear unless they can normally see invisible things or use magic to do so. Highly intelligent creatures with 10 or more Hit Dice, levels, or equivalent intelligence have a chance to automatically detect invisible objects. Material Components: An eyelash encased in gum arabic.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"false trap":{"name":"False Trap","level":"2","school":"School: Illusion","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Creates an illusory trap on an object, convincing to normal inspection (including a thief’s examination).\nNotes:\n    Any examiner has an 80% chance to find and believe the false trap.\n    For thieves, reduce this chance by 3% per level of experience.\n    If a thief attempts to remove the “trap,” there is only a 20% chance the illusion is dispelled or exposed; otherwise the thief typically concludes the attempt failed.\n    Only one false trap may exist within a 50 ft. radius. If two such objects come within 50 ft. of each other, both illusions are dispelled.","notes":"Creates an illusory trap on an object, convincing to normal inspection (including a thief’s examination).\nNotes:\n    Any examiner has an 80% chance to find and believe the false trap.\n    For thieves, reduce this chance by 3% per level of experience.\n    If a thief attempts to remove the “trap,” there is only a 20% chance the illusion is dispelled or exposed; otherwise the thief typically concludes the attempt failed.\n    Only one false trap may exist within a 50 ft. radius. If two such objects come within 50 ft. of each other, both illusions are dispelled.","link":""},"knock":{"name":"Knock","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"6”","duration":"Special","aoe":"10 square feet per level","components":"V","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Knock\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10 square feet per level\nThis spell opens stuck, held, wizard-locked, barred, otherwise locked, or trick-opening doors, boxes, and chests. It also opens secret doors and loosens shackles or chains. If used on a wizard-locked door, the spell does not remove wizard lock, but suspends it for 1 turn. In all other cases, knock permanently opens locks or welds, though locks may later be closed and locked again. The spell does not raise bars or similar impediments such as a portcullis. The spell performs two functions, so a door that is locked, barred, and held requires two knock spells.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"levitate":{"name":"Levitate","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"2” per level","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Levitate\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the magic-user to levitate themselves or another creature. Maximum weight is 1,000 gold pieces per caster level; for example, a 3rd-level magic-user can levitate up to 3,000 gold pieces, or 300 pounds. If cast on the caster, vertical movement is 20 feet per round. If cast on another creature, the caster may move it vertically up to 10 feet per round. The spell grants no horizontal movement, though the recipient may push along a cliff face or similar surface to move laterally. The caster may cancel the spell at will. An unwilling target receives a saving throw. Material Component: A small leather loop or a piece of golden wire bent into a cup shape with a long shank.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"locate object":{"name":"Locate Object","level":"2","school":"Divination","range":"2” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Locate Object\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Obscure Object\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is the same as the 3rd-level cleric spell locate object, except that its range differs.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic mouth":{"name":"Magic Mouth","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"Special","duration":"Special","aoe":"One object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Magic Mouth\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One object\nThis spell gives an object an enchanted mouth that appears and speaks a message when a specified event occurs. The message may be up to 25 words in a language known by the caster and must be delivered within 1 turn. The mouth cannot speak magical spells. It moves as it speaks; if placed on a statue, the statue’s mouth appears to move. The spell may be placed on a tree, rock, door, or almost any object, but not on intelligent animal or vegetable creatures. The triggering condition may be general or specific, such as “speak to the first creature that touches you” or “speak only when an octogenarian female human carrying a sack of groat clusters sits cross-legged within 1 foot.” The command range is ½” per caster level. For example, a 6th-level magic-user can set the mouth to speak when a winged creature comes within 3”. Until the condition is fulfilled, the spell remains active. Magic mouth cannot distinguish invisible creatures, alignment, level, Hit Dice, or class except by external garb. Material Component: A small bit of honeycomb.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"mirror image":{"name":"Mirror Image","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"6-foot radius around caster","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mirror Image\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6-foot radius around caster\nThis spell creates 1d4 exact duplicates of the caster around them. The images do exactly what the magic-user does, and the spell creates blurring and slight distortion, making it impossible for opponents to know which is real. When an image is struck by any weapon, magical or mundane, it disappears. Other images remain until struck or until the spell ends. The images shift from round to round, so even if the real caster is struck one round, they cannot be distinguished the next. To determine the number of images, roll percentile dice and add 1 per caster level: 25 or less creates 1 image, 26–50 creates 2, 51–75 creates 3, and 76 or more creates 4. All images vanish when the spell expires.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"pyrotechnics":{"name":"Pyrotechnics","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"12”","duration":"Special","aoe":"10 or 100 times the fire source used","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Pyrotechnics\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10 or 100 times the fire source used\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level druid spell pyrotechnics.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"ray of enfeeblement":{"name":"Ray Of Enfeeblement","level":"2","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1” + ¼” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Ray Of Enfeeblement\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” + ¼” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell weakens an opponent, reducing Strength and attacks based on Strength by 25% or more. For each caster level beyond 3rd, the Strength reduction increases by 2%; for example, at 4th level the reduction is 27%. Range and duration also depend on caster level. A creature struck by the ray loses the appropriate percentage of damage dealt by physical attacks, including missiles, weapons, bites, claws, gores, kicks, and constriction. The referee determines any other appropriate reductions. A successful saving throw negates the spell.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"rope trick":{"name":"Rope Trick","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"2 turns per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Rope Trick\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 2 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is cast on a rope 5 to 30 feet long. One end rises into the air until the rope hangs perpendicular, as if fastened above. The upper end is actually fixed in an extra-dimensional space. The caster and up to 5 others may climb the rope and disappear into this safe space, where no creature can find them. The rope cannot be taken into the extra-dimensional space if 6 people have climbed it, but otherwise it may be pulled up. If not pulled up, it hangs in the air and may be removed by another creature. Those inside must climb down before the spell ends or fall from the height they originally climbed when the spell expires. Only one person can climb the rope at a time. The spell also permits climbers to reach a normal place if they do not climb all the way to the upper end. Material Components: Powdered corn extract and a twisted loop of parchment.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"scare":{"name":"Scare","level":"2","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1”","duration":"3d4 rounds","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Scare\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 3d4 rounds\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell affects a creature with fewer than 6 levels or Hit Dice. If the target fails its saving throw versus magic, it falls into trembling fear. The creature does not drop held items unless encumbered. If cornered, it fights at -1 on “to hit” rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws. The spell has no effect on elves, half-elves, undead such as skeletons, zombies, ghouls, shadows, ghasts, wights, and wraiths, larvae, lemures, manes, or clerics of any sort. Material Component: A bit of bone from an undead skeleton, zombie, ghoul, ghast, or mummy.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"shatter":{"name":"Shatter","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"6”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Shatter\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One object\nThis spell affects nonmagical objects made of crystal, glass, ceramic, or porcelain, such as vials, bottles, flasks, jugs, windows, and mirrors. Such objects are shattered into dozens of pieces. Objects weighing more than 100 gold pieces per caster level are unaffected. All other objects of the appropriate material must save versus crushing blow or be shattered. Material Component: A chip of mica.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"stinking cloud":{"name":"Stinking Cloud","level":"2","school":"Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"2” × 2” × 2” cloud","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Stinking Cloud\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 2” × 2” × 2” cloud\nThis spell creates a billowing mass of nauseous vapors up to 3” from the caster. Any creature caught in the cloud must save versus poison or become helpless with nausea for 1d4+1 rounds. Creatures that save are helpless only while they remain in the cloud and for 1 round after emerging, due to irritation of the eyes and nose. Material Component: A rotten egg or several skunk cabbage leaves.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"strength":{"name":"Strength","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"Person touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Strength\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Person touched\nThis spell increases the touched character’s Strength by an amount based on class, subject to normal race, sex, and class restrictions. Clerics gain 1d6 Strength, fighters gain 1d8, magic-users gain 1d4, thieves gain 1d6, and monks gain 1d4. If a fighter, paladin, or ranger already has Strength 18, the spell adds 10% to 80% to extraordinary Strength. Strength additions above 18 are treated as +10% extraordinary Strength per point. Material Component: A few hairs or a pinch of dung from a strong animal, such as an ape, bear, or ox.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"web":{"name":"Web","level":"2","school":"Evocation","range":"½” per level","duration":"2 turns per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates or half","save_type":"","description":"Web\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 2 turns per level\nSaving Throw: Negates or half\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a many-layered mass of strong, sticky strands like giant spider webs. The webs must be anchored to two or more diametrically opposed points, such as floor and ceiling or opposite walls. The spell covers up to 8 cubic inches, and the webs must be at least 1” thick. Creatures caught in or touching the webs become stuck. Creatures with Strength below 13 remain trapped until freed or until the spell ends. For every full turn trapped, a creature has a cumulative 5% chance of suffocating. Creatures with Strength 13–17 can break through 1 foot of webs per turn. Creatures with Strength 18 or greater break through 1 foot per round. Strong and huge creatures break through 1 foot per segment. Web strands are flammable. Fire burns them away in 1 round, dealing 2d4 damage to creatures caught in the webs, though creatures freed from the strands are not harmed. If the saving throw is made and there is room to escape, the creature jumps free. If there is no room to escape, the webs are only half strength. Material Component: A bit of spider web.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"wizard lock":{"name":"Wizard Lock","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"30 square feet per level","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wizard Lock\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 30 square feet per level\nThis spell magically locks a door, chest, or portal. The wizard-locked object can be opened only by breaking it, by dispel magic, by knock, or by a magic-user at least 4 levels higher than the caster. Knock and the higher-level magic-user method do not remove the wizard lock; they only negate it briefly. Extra-dimensional creatures do not affect wizard lock as they do hold portal.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 3rd Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"clairaudience":{"name":"Clairaudience","level":"3","school":"Divination","range":"Special","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Clairaudience\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the magic-user to concentrate on a known or obvious location and hear sounds within a 6” radius of that point. Distance is not a factor, but the location must be familiar or obvious, such as behind a door, around a corner, or in a copse of woods. Only sounds normally detectable by the caster can be heard. Metal sheeting or magical protection blocks the spell. It functions only on the plane where the caster is located. Material Component: A small silver horn worth at least 100 gp, which disappears when the spell is cast.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"clairvoyance":{"name":"Clairvoyance","level":"3","school":"Divination","range":"Special","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Clairvoyance\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is similar to clairaudience, but allows the magic-user to see in their mind whatever lies within sight range from the chosen location. Distance is not a factor, but the location must be familiar or obvious. Light conditions matter. If the area is dark, only a 1” radius from the spell’s center can be seen; otherwise, vision extends to normal sight range. Metal sheeting or magical protection blocks the spell. It functions only on the caster’s current plane. Material Component: A pinch of powdered pineal gland from a human or humanoid creature.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"dispel magic":{"name":"Dispel Magic","level":"3","school":"Abjuration","range":"12”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"3” cube","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Dispel Magic\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” cube\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level cleric spell dispel magic.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"explosive runes":{"name":"Explosive Runes","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"1” radius","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Explosive Runes\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: 1” radius\nThe magic-user traces mystic runes on a book, map, scroll, or similar written object to prevent unauthorized reading. The runes are difficult to detect, with a 5% chance per reader level; thieves have only a 5% chance in any case. When read, the runes explode, dealing 6d4+6 damage to the reader with no saving throw. Other creatures within the blast radius take the same damage, or half with a successful saving throw. The caster and any magic-users instructed by the caster can read the protected writing without triggering the runes. The caster may remove the runes at will. Otherwise, they can be removed only by dispel magic and last until triggered. The object bearing the runes is destroyed by the explosion unless it is not normally subject to destruction by magical fire.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"feign death":{"name":"Feign Death","level":"3","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"6 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Feign Death\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 6 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell places the caster or another willing creature into a cataleptic state indistinguishable from death, provided the target’s levels or Hit Dice do not exceed the caster’s level. The affected creature can smell, hear, and understand what is happening, but cannot see or feel anything. Wounding or mistreatment causes no reaction and deals only half normal damage. Paralysis, poison, and energy drain do not affect the creature while the spell lasts, though poison introduced into the body takes effect when the spell ends, with a saving throw allowed. Only a willing creature can be affected. The caster may end the spell at any time, but bodily functions require 1 full round to resume.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"fireball":{"name":"Fireball","level":"3","school":"Evocation","range":"10” + 1” per level","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"2” radius sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Fireball\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 10” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: 2” radius sphere\nThis spell creates an explosive burst of flame that detonates with a low roar and deals 1d6 damage per caster level. Wands of fireball produce 6d6 fireballs, staves produce 8d6 fireballs, and scrolls produce 5d6 to 10d6 fireballs. The burst creates little pressure and generally conforms to the shape of the area, filling a volume equal to its normal spherical volume. It ignites combustibles and melts soft metals such as gold, copper, silver, and similar metals. Exposed items must save to avoid damage, though items carried by a creature that saves are considered unaffected. The caster points and states the distance and height where the fireball is to burst. A streak flashes from the pointing finger and blossoms into the fireball unless it strikes a material body first. Creatures that fail their saves take full damage; those that save take half. Material Component: A tiny ball of bat guano and sulfur.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"flame arrow":{"name":"Flame Arrow","level":"3","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Touch","duration":"1 segment per level","aoe":"Each arrow or bolt touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Flame Arrow\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 segment per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Each arrow or bolt touched\nAfter casting this spell, the magic-user may touch one arrow or crossbow bolt per segment for the spell’s duration. Each missile becomes magical, though it gains no bonus “to hit.” Each missile must be fired within 1 round, or flame consumes it and the magic is lost. Fiery missiles have normal chances to ignite materials, and creatures especially subject to fire damage take +1 damage from any flame arrow that hits. Material Components: A drop of oil and a small piece of flint.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"fly":{"name":"Fly","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per level + 1d6 turns","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Fly\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level + 1d6 turns\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell grants magical flight. The affected creature may move vertically or horizontally at 12” per move, half speed while ascending, and double speed while diving downward. The exact duration is unknown to the caster because the 1d6 turn variable addition is secretly determined by the Dungeon Master. Material Component: A wing feather from any bird.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"gust of wind":{"name":"Gust Of Wind","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 segment","aoe":"1” wide path, 1” long per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Gust Of Wind\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 segment\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” wide path, 1” long per level\nThis spell creates a strong puff of air from the magic-user in the direction faced. The gust extinguishes candles, torches, and similar unprotected flames. Protected flames, such as lanterns, dance wildly and have a 5% chance per caster level to be extinguished. Large fires are fanned outward 1d6 feet in the wind’s direction. Small flying creatures are forced back 1d6 inches, man-sized flying creatures moving into the gust are held motionless, and large flying creatures are slowed by 50% for 1 round. The gust also blows over light objects. Its path is 1” wide and 1” long per caster level. Material Component: A legume seed.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"haste":{"name":"Haste","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"6”","duration":"3 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"4” × 4” area, one creature per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Haste\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 3 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4” × 4” area, one creature per level\nThis spell causes affected creatures to move and attack at double their normal rates. A creature with movement 6” and one attack per round would move at 12” and attack twice per round. Spellcasting is not accelerated. The spell affects one creature per caster level, choosing the closest creatures to the caster first, provided all are within the area of effect. Haste negates slow. The spell ages recipients because of accelerated metabolic processes. Material Component: A shaving of licorice root.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"hold person":{"name":"Hold Person","level":"3","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"12”","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"One to four persons","components":"V","ct":"3 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Hold Person\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One to four persons\nThis spell is similar to the 2nd-level cleric spell hold person, immobilizing designated persons within range. If three or four persons are targeted, their saves are normal. If two are targeted, saves are made at -1. If one is targeted, the save is made at -3. Partial negation, such as from a ring of spell turning, causes the spell to function as slow unless the saving throw succeeds. Affected creatures include brownies, dryads, dwarves, elves, gnolls, gnomes, goblins, half-elves, halflings, half-orcs, hobgoblins, humans, kobolds, lizard men, nixies, orcs, pixies, sprites, and troglodytes.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"infravision":{"name":"Infravision","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"12 turns + 6 turns per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Infravision\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 12 turns + 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell allows the recipient to see light in the infrared spectrum, detecting heat radiation differences up to 6”. Strong infrared sources, such as fire, lanterns, and torches, tend to blind or cast “shadows” much as bright light affects normal vision, reducing the spell’s effectiveness. Invisible creatures are not usually detected by infravision, because invisibility affects infrared as well as ultraviolet and normal light. Material Component: A pinch of dried carrot or an agate.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"leomund s tiny hut":{"name":"Leomund’s Tiny Hut","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"10-foot diameter sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Leomund’s Tiny Hut\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10-foot diameter sphere\nThis spell creates an opaque sphere of force around the caster, with half above the ground or floor and half below. The interior remains 70°F in outside cold down to 0°F and outside heat up to 105°F. Colder or hotter temperatures change the interior temperature degree for degree beyond those limits. The hut withstands winds up to 50 miles per hour; stronger winds destroy it. The caster may dimly illuminate or darken the interior on command. The field is opaque from outside but transparent from inside. It does not protect against missiles, weapons, spells, or similar attacks. Up to 6 other man-sized creatures can fit inside with the caster and may pass in and out freely. If the caster leaves, the spell dissipates. Material Component: A small crystal bead that shatters when the spell ends or the hut is dispelled.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"lightning bolt":{"name":"Lightning Bolt","level":"3","school":"Evocation","range":"4” + 1” per level","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Lightning Bolt\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 4” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell releases a powerful stroke of electrical energy dealing 1d6 damage per caster level, or half damage to creatures that save. The spell’s range determines where the stroke begins, and the bolt then extends outward from that point. It can ignite combustibles, sunder wooden doors, splinter up to 1 foot of stone, and melt low-melting metals such as lead, gold, copper, silver, and bronze. Objects struck by the full force must save. The caster chooses either a forked bolt 1” wide and 4” long or a single bolt ½” wide and 8” long. If a solid nonconducting barrier blocks the bolt before its full length is reached, the bolt rebounds toward the caster, continuing until its full length is spent. Material Components: A bit of fur and an amber, crystal, or glass rod.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"monster summoning i":{"name":"Monster Summoning I","level":"3","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"3”","duration":"2 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Monster Summoning I\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nWithin 1d4 rounds after casting, this spell summons 2d4 1st-level monsters, chosen randomly by the referee. The monsters appear within range at the caster’s desired location and attack the caster’s opponents to the best of their ability until ordered to stop, the spell ends, or they are slain. If no opponents are present, and communication is possible, the monsters may perform other physically possible services for the caster. Material Components: A tiny bag and a small candle, which need not be lit.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"phantasmal force":{"name":"Phantasmal Force","level":"3","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"8” + 1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"8 square inches + 1 square inch per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Phantasmal Force\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 8 square inches + 1 square inch per level\nThis spell creates a visual illusion affecting all believing creatures that view it, even causing apparent damage from phantasmal missiles or from falling into an illusory pit. Sound is not part of the illusion. The illusion lasts until struck by an opponent, unless the caster makes it react appropriately, or until the caster stops concentrating due to choice, movement, or a successful damaging attack. Creatures that disbelieve may save versus spell. Success reveals the illusion for what it is and grants +4 to associates’ saves if that knowledge can be communicated. Creatures not observing the effect are immune until they view it. The spell may create any object, creature, or force within the area of effect, and the area may move within range. Material Component: A bit of fleece.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"protection from normal missiles":{"name":"Protection From Normal Missiles","level":"3","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Protection From Normal Missiles\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell grants total immunity to hurled and projected normal missiles, such as arrows, axes, bolts, javelins, small stones, and spears. It also reduces damage by 1 point per die from large or magical missiles, such as ballista missiles, catapult stones, magical arrows, magical bolts, and magical javelins. It does not protect against fireball, lightning bolt, magic missile, or similar magical attacks. Material Component: A piece of tortoise or turtle shell.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"slow":{"name":"Slow","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"9” + 1” per level","duration":"3 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"4” × 4” area, one creature per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Slow\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 9” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 3 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4” × 4” area, one creature per level\nThis spell causes affected creatures to move and attack at half normal or current rate. It negates haste, has cumulative effects on already slowed creatures, and affects magically sped or slowed creatures. The spell affects one creature per caster level within the designated 4” × 4” area. Material Component: A drop of treacle.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"suggestion":{"name":"Suggestion","level":"3","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"3”","duration":"6 turns + 6 turns per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Suggestion\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 6 turns + 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell influences the chosen creature’s actions through a few words, phrases, or one or two sentences suggesting a course of action. The target must understand the caster’s language. The suggestion must sound reasonable. Obviously harmful instructions, such as stabbing oneself or jumping onto a spear, negate the spell. However, a suggestion that acid is pure water and a quick dip would be refreshing, or that a red dragon could gain treasure elsewhere through cooperation, may be effective. The suggested action can continue for a long duration. If the target saves, the spell has no effect. A highly reasonable suggestion may impose a saving throw penalty at the Dungeon Master’s discretion. Undead are unaffected. Material Components: A snake’s tongue and either a bit of honeycomb or a drop of sweet oil.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"tongues":{"name":"Tongues","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"6” diameter circle","components":"V, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Tongues\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Confuse Languages\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6” diameter circle\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 4th-level cleric spell tongues. Material Component: A small clay model of a ziggurat, which shatters when the spell is cast.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"babble":{"name":"Babble","level":"3","school":"Transmutation/Alteration","range":"Nil","duration":"1 round/magic-user level","aoe":"30-ft. radius","components":"V, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell makes any verbal communication impossible for any person (not just the caster) in the spell’s area, or it may be used to cancel out the effects of the tongues spell (whether cast by a cleric or by a magic-user).\nDetails:\nAlthough spoken words become meaningless in the area of effect, creatures can still gesture, write, and otherwise communicate. Note: Creatures in the area of effect can’t cast spells that have a verbal component until the spell ends.","notes":"This spell makes any verbal communication impossible for any person (not just the caster) in the spell’s area, or it may be used to cancel out the effects of the tongues spell (whether cast by a cleric or by a magic-user).\nDetails:\nAlthough spoken words become meaningless in the area of effect, creatures can still gesture, write, and otherwise communicate. Note: Creatures in the area of effect can’t cast spells that have a verbal component until the spell ends.","link":""},"water breathing":{"name":"Water Breathing","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"3 turns per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Water Breathing\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Air Breathing\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 3 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nExcept as noted above, and except that the material component is a short reed or piece of straw, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level druid spell water breathing.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 4th Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"air breathing":{"name":"Air Breathing","level":"3","school":"Transmutation/Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"3 turns/magic-user level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell allows a water-breathing creature to breathe air for the spell’s duration. The recipient does not lose the ability to breathe underwater.","notes":"This spell allows a water-breathing creature to breathe air for the spell’s duration. The recipient does not lose the ability to breathe underwater.","link":""},"charm monster":{"name":"Charm Monster","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"6”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Charm Monster\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is similar to charm person, but it can affect any living creature, or several lower-level creatures. Affected creatures regard the caster as friendly, treating them as an ally or companion to be guarded from harm. If communication is possible, the charmed creature follows reasonable requests, instructions, or orders. The charm eventually breaks, with the chance depending on the creature’s level or Hit Dice: 1st level or up to 2 HD, 5% per week; 2nd level or up to 3+2 HD, 10%; 3rd level or up to 4+4 HD, 15%; 4th level or up to 6 HD, 25%; 5th level or up to 7+2 HD, 35%; 6th level or up to 8+4 HD, 45%; 7th level or up to 10 HD, 60%; 8th level or up to 12 HD, 75%; 9th level or over 12 HD, 90%. Overt hostility by the caster automatically breaks the spell or at least allows a new saving throw. The spell affects 2d4 1st-level creatures, 1d4 2nd-level creatures, 1 or 2 3rd-level creatures, or 1 creature of 4th level or higher.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"confusion":{"name":"Confusion","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"12”","duration":"2 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Up to 6” × 6”","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Confusion\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Up to 6” × 6”\nExcept as noted above, this spell is identical to the 7th-level druid spell confusion. It affects a base 2d8 creatures. Material Component: A set of three nut shells.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"dig":{"name":"Dig","level":"4","school":"Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"5-foot cube per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Dig\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 5-foot cube per level\nThis spell excavates 125 cubic feet of earth, sand, or mud per round, creating a 5-foot cube-shaped hole each round. Excavated material scatters evenly around the pit. If the caster continues digging below 5 feet, the pit may collapse: 15% per additional 5 feet in earth, 35% per additional 5 feet in sand, and 55% per additional 5 feet in mud. A creature at the edge, within 1 foot, uses Dexterity as a saving throw to avoid falling in; rolling equal to or below Dexterity avoids the fall. A creature moving rapidly toward the pit falls in unless it saves versus magic. A creature caught in the center of a newly dug pit always falls in. Material Components: A miniature shovel and tiny bucket, which must be held while each pit is excavated.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"dimension door":{"name":"Dimension Door","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Spellcaster","components":"V","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Dimension Door\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Spellcaster\nThis spell instantly transports the magic-user up to 3” per caster level. This precise teleportation has no chance of error, and the caster arrives exactly where desired, either by visualizing a place within range or by stating direction and distance. If the destination is occupied by a solid body, the caster remains in the Astral Plane until located by someone who casts dispel magic on them. While stranded, the caster is stunned and cannot successfully cast spells. If the caster appears in mid-air, falling damage applies unless further magic intervenes. The caster’s worn and carried gear travels with them, up to 5,000 gold pieces of nonliving matter or half that weight of living matter. Recovery from the spell requires 7 segments.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"enchanted weapon":{"name":"Enchanted Weapon","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"Weapon or weapons touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Enchanted Weapon\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Disenchant Weapon\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Weapon or weapons touched\nThis spell turns an ordinary weapon into a magical one. The weapon counts as equivalent to +1 for purposes of striking creatures requiring magic weapons, but it gains no actual bonus. Two small weapons, such as arrows, bolts, or daggers, or one large weapon, such as an axe, bow, hammer, mace, or sword, can be affected. A successful hit by an enchanted missile weapon breaks the spell on that missile. Otherwise, the spell lasts until its duration expires. Material Components: Powdered lime and carbon.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"extension i":{"name":"Extension I","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Extension I\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell extends the duration of a previously cast 1st-, 2nd-, or 3rd-level spell by 50%. For example, levitate may last 1½ turns per level, and hold person may last 3 rounds per level. The spell affects only spells where duration is meaningful.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"fear":{"name":"Fear","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"6” long cone, 3” diameter at end, ½ foot at base","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Fear\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 6” long cone, 3” diameter at end, ½ foot at base\nThis spell sends forth an invisible ray that causes creatures in its area to flee from the caster in panic. Affected creatures may drop held items immediately. The base chance is 60% for 1st-level or 1-Hit-Die creatures, reduced by 5% per level or Hit Die above 1st. Thus, at 10th level the chance is 15%, and at 13th level it is 0%. Affected creatures flee at their fastest rate for a number of rounds equal to the caster’s level. Panic begins on the round after casting, though item dropping occurs immediately. Creatures that save are unaffected. Material Component: The heart of a hen or a white feather.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"fire charm":{"name":"Fire Charm","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1”","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"30-foot diameter of fire","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Fire Charm\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 30-foot diameter of fire\nThis spell causes a normal fire source, such as a brazier, torch, or bonfire, to become a magical agent. A gossamer veil of multicolored flame circles 5 feet from the fire. Creatures observing the fire or veil must save versus magic or remain motionless, gazing transfixed at the flames. While charmed, they are subject to suggestion spells of 12 or fewer words, saving against them at -3. The charm breaks if the creature is physically attacked, if a solid object blocks its view of the flames, or when the spell ends. The veil is not magical fire, and passing through it deals the same damage as passing through the original fire source. Material Component: A very thin piece of multicolored silk thrown into the fire source.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"fire shield":{"name":"Fire Shield","level":"4","school":"Evocation-Alteration","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Personal","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Fire Shield\n\nSchool: Evocation-Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Personal\nThis spell makes the magic-user appear to be engulfed in thin, wispy flames that shed dim light in a 15-foot radius. The flames are blue or green for the hot-flame version, and violet or blue for the cold-flame version. Any creature striking the caster with body or hand-held weapons deals normal damage to the caster but takes double that damage in return. With the hot-flame version, cold-based attacks are saved against at +2 and deal half or no damage, while fire-based attacks affect the caster normally and deal double damage if the caster fails any required save. With the cold-flame version, fire-based attacks are saved against at +2 and deal half or no damage, while cold-based attacks affect the caster normally and deal double damage if the caster fails any required save. Material Component: For the hot-flame version, a bit of phosphorus. For the cold-flame version, a live firefly or glowworm, or the tail portions of four dead ones.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"fire trap":{"name":"Fire Trap","level":"4","school":"Evocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent until discharged","aoe":"Object touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 rounds","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Fire Trap\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: Permanent until discharged\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: Object touched\nThis spell traps any closable item, such as a book, box, bottle, chest, coffer, coffin, door, or drawer. The trapped item cannot also reliably receive hold portal or wizard lock. If fire trap and hold portal are attempted together, only the first spell works, or both fail if simultaneous. If fire trap is cast after wizard lock, fire trap is negated; if simultaneous, both are negated; if wizard lock is cast after fire trap, there is a 50% chance both are negated. Knock does not affect fire trap; touching or entering the trapped object triggers the explosion. The caster may use the object safely. When discharged, the trap explodes in a 5-foot radius, dealing 1d4 damage plus 1 point per caster level, or half damage on a successful save versus magic. The trapped item is not harmed. A fire trap has only half the normal chance to be detected, and failing to remove it detonates it immediately. Material Component: Sulfur or saltpeter used to trace the closure.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"fumble":{"name":"Fumble","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Fumble\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell makes the target suddenly clumsy and awkward. Running creatures trip and fall, creatures reaching for items fumble and drop them, and creatures using weapons awkwardly drop them. Recovering from a fall or dropped item usually requires the whole next melee round. Fragile dropped items may break. If the victim saves, the spell merely causes them to operate at half normal efficiency, as with slow. Material Component: A dab of solidified milk fat.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"hallucinatory terrain":{"name":"Hallucinatory Terrain","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"2” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"1” × 1” square per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Hallucinatory Terrain\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2” per level\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” × 1” square per level\nThis spell creates an illusion that hides the actual terrain within the area. Open fields or roads may appear as swamp, hills, crevasses, or other difficult terrain. A pond may appear as meadow, a precipice as a gentle slope, or a rocky gully as a wide smooth road. The illusion persists until dispel magic is cast on the area or until an intelligent creature contacts it. Each caster level increases the affected area; for example, a 10th-level caster can affect up to a 10” × 10” square. Material Components: A stone, a twig, and a green plant fragment such as a leaf or blade of grass.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"ice storm":{"name":"Ice Storm","level":"4","school":"Evocation","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Ice Storm\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates either hail or sleet. The hail version pounds a 4” diameter area with great hailstones, dealing 3d10 damage to creatures in the area. The sleet version creates driving sleet in an 8” diameter area, blinding creatures within it for the spell’s duration and icing the ground, which slows movement by 50% and gives moving creatures a 50% chance to slip and fall. This spell negates heat metal, though the hail version also deals damage in the process. Material Components: A pinch of dust and a few drops of water.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"massmorph":{"name":"Massmorph","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"11-foot × 1” square per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Massmorph\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 11-foot × 1” square per level\nThis spell makes willing man-sized or smaller creatures appear as normal trees. Up to 10 creatures per caster level can be affected, allowing a group to appear as a copse, grove, or orchard. Other creatures can pass through and touch the apparent trees without revealing the illusion. However, blows reveal the truth, as affected creatures take damage and bleed. Affected creatures must be within the spell’s area. Unwilling creatures are unaffected. The spell lasts until the caster commands it to end or until dispel magic is cast on the creatures. Material Component: A handful of bark chips.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"minor globe of invulnerability":{"name":"Minor Globe Of Invulnerability","level":"4","school":"Abjuration","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"1” diameter sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Minor Globe Of Invulnerability\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” diameter sphere\nThis spell creates a magical sphere around the caster that prevents 1st-, 2nd-, and 3rd-level spells from penetrating. The area of effect of such spells does not include the globe’s interior. Spells may still be cast outward from within the globe. Fourth-level and higher spells are unaffected. Dispel magic can bring down the globe. Material Component: A glass or crystal bead.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"monster summoning ii":{"name":"Monster Summoning II","level":"4","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"4”","duration":"3 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Monster Summoning II\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 4”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 3 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is similar to monster summoning I, except that it summons 1d6 2nd-level monsters. There is a 1d4-round delay before they appear. Material Components: The same as monster summoning I: a tiny bag and a small candle.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"plant growth":{"name":"Plant Growth","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1” × 1” square per level","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Plant Growth\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” × 1” square per level\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level druid spell plant growth.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"polymorph other":{"name":"Polymorph Other","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"½” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Polymorph Other\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell completely changes the form and abilities of one creature, and may also change personality and mentality. Creatures of lower Intelligence cannot be polymorphed into forms with higher Intelligence, though the reverse is possible. The target must make a system shock roll to survive. If successful, it gains the form and abilities of the new creature. There is a base 100% chance that the creature’s personality and mentality also become those of the new form. Subtract 5% for each point of the original creature’s Intelligence. Adjust by ±5% per Hit Die difference between original and new form, adding for a higher-Hit-Die new form and subtracting for a lower-Hit-Die new form. This chance is checked daily until the change occurs. The creature may retain former knowledge if personality and mentality do not change. The new form may be stronger than it appears, such as a mummy changed into a puppy or a brontosaurus changed into an ant. Dispel magic can restore the creature, but this requires another system shock roll. Material Component: A caterpillar cocoon.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"polymorph self":{"name":"Polymorph Self","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"2 turns per level","aoe":"The magic-user","components":"V","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Polymorph Self\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 2 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The magic-user\nThis spell allows the magic-user to assume the form of any creature from wren-sized to hippopotamus-sized, including that creature’s form of movement. It does not grant the creature’s attacks, magic, or special abilities, and it does not risk changing the caster’s personality or mentality. No system shock roll is needed. Thus, a caster changed into an owl can fly but retains human vision, and a caster changed into a black pudding can move under doors or along halls and ceilings but does not gain the pudding’s attacks or defenses. The assumed form must be strong enough for normal movement. The caster may change form as often as desired during the spell, requiring 5 segments per change. Damage to the polymorphed form is treated as damage to the caster, but when the caster returns to normal form, 1d12 hit points are restored.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"rary s mnemonic enhancement":{"name":"Rary’S Mnemonic Enhancement","level":"4","school":"Range: Caster","range":"","duration":"24 hours","aoe":"Caster","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell enhances your precision of memory, allowing you to retain up to three additional spell levels in your mind (3 first level, 1 first and one second level, or 1 third level).\nDetails:\nThe spell may be used during memorisation to “create” additional spell slots, or may be used to hold onto the memory of a spell you have just cast. In the second case, you would have to cast the mnemonic enhancement immediately after casting the spell you wish to retain in memory.\nThe spell components are expensive, costing at least 100 gp, and might not be available in rural communities.","notes":"This spell enhances your precision of memory, allowing you to retain up to three additional spell levels in your mind (3 first level, 1 first and one second level, or 1 third level).\nDetails:\nThe spell may be used during memorisation to “create” additional spell slots, or may be used to hold onto the memory of a spell you have just cast. In the second case, you would have to cast the mnemonic enhancement immediately after casting the spell you wish to retain in memory.\nThe spell components are expensive, costing at least 100 gp, and might not be available in rural communities.","link":""},"remove curse":{"name":"Remove Curse","level":"4","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Remove Curse\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Bestow Curse\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level cleric spell remove curse.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"wall of fire":{"name":"Wall Of Fire","level":"4","school":"Evocation","range":"6”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wall Of Fire\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell differs from the 5th-level druid spell wall of fire as follows: the flame color is violet or reddish blue, base damage is 2d6 plus 1 point per caster level, the radius of the ring-shaped wall is 1” plus ¼” per caster level, and the material component is phosphorus.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"wall of ice":{"name":"Wall Of Ice","level":"4","school":"Evocation","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wall Of Ice\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a sheet of strong, flexible ice. The wall is mainly defensive, stopping pursuers and similar threats. It is 1 inch thick per caster level and covers a 1” square area per caster level. For example, a 10th-level caster can make a wall 10” long and 1” high, 5” long and 2” high, and so on. A creature breaking through takes 2 damage per inch of wall thickness. Fire-using creatures take 3 damage per inch, and cold-using creatures take only 1 damage per inch. If cast horizontally to fall on opponents, the wall has the same effect as the hailstone version of ice storm over the area where it falls. Magical fires such as fireball and fiery dragon breath melt the wall in 1 round, creating a great cloud of steamy fog lasting 1 turn. Normal fires and lesser magical fires do not hasten melting. Material Component: A small piece of quartz or similar rock crystal.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"wizard eye":{"name":"Wizard Eye","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wizard Eye\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates an invisible sensory organ that sends visual information to the magic-user. The wizard eye travels at 3” per round while viewing ahead as a human would, or 1” per round while examining ceilings, walls, and floors. It can see with infravision to 10 feet, or see up to 60 feet in brightly lit areas. It can travel in any direction while the spell lasts. Material Component: A bit of bat fur.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"airy water":{"name":"Airy Water","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"2” diameter sphere or 4” diameter hemisphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Airy Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2” diameter sphere or 4” diameter hemisphere\nThis spell turns normal liquid, such as water or water-based infusions or solutions, into a less dense, breathable substance. A magic-user entering an underwater place may step into the water, cast the spell, and sink downward in a globe of bubbling water. The caster and any companions within the area of effect may move freely and breathe as if the water were air. The globe moves with the caster. Water-breathing creatures avoid the sphere or hemisphere of airy water. Intelligent water-breathers can enter it if they can move by means other than swimming, but no water-breather can breathe inside the affected area. Material Component: A small handful of alkaline or bromine salts.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"animal growth":{"name":"Animal Growth","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"6”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Up to 8 animals in a 2” square area","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Animal Growth\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Reduce Animal\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Up to 8 animals in a 2” square area\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 5th-level druid spell animal growth. Material Component: A pinch of powdered bone.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"reduce animal":{"name":"Reduce Animal","level":"5","school":"Range: 60 ft.","range":"","duration":"1 round/magic-user level","aoe":"Up to 8 animals in a 20-ft. square area","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell causes up to 8 animals in the area of effect to shrink to half normal size, halving their hit dice and the damage they inflict.\nDetails:\nThe spell does not influence the animals’ attitude toward you, but if they are hostile, at least they are a lot smaller than they were. Creatures with magical abilities are not affected by this spell, which affects only ordinary creatures and giant versions of them. Humans, demi-humans, and humanoids are not considered animals.","notes":"This spell causes up to 8 animals in the area of effect to shrink to half normal size, halving their hit dice and the damage they inflict.\nDetails:\nThe spell does not influence the animals’ attitude toward you, but if they are hostile, at least they are a lot smaller than they were. Creatures with magical abilities are not affected by this spell, which affects only ordinary creatures and giant versions of them. Humans, demi-humans, and humanoids are not considered animals.","link":""},"animate dead":{"name":"Animate Dead","level":"5","school":"Necromantic","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Animate Dead\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 5 rounds\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level cleric spell animate dead.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"biccby s interposing hand":{"name":"Biccby’S Interposing Hand","level":"5","school":"Range: 10 ft./magic-user level","range":"","duration":"1 round/magic-user level","aoe":"Magical disembodied hand","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell creates a magical hand with the same number of hit points as your (uninjured) hit points. You can cause the hand to be as small as your own, or as large as a shield. You select a foe, and the hand places itself between you and that particular enemy, moving so rapidly that it cannot be avoided. It is strong enough to hold back any creature weighing 200 lbs or less, and will slow heavier opponents to half movement.\nDetails:\nThe movement rates of opponents of truly massive size (such as dragons) will be adjudicated by the GM, either being slowed by a quarter movement rate or pushing the hand aside entirely.","notes":"This spell creates a magical hand with the same number of hit points as your (uninjured) hit points. You can cause the hand to be as small as your own, or as large as a shield. You select a foe, and the hand places itself between you and that particular enemy, moving so rapidly that it cannot be avoided. It is strong enough to hold back any creature weighing 200 lbs or less, and will slow heavier opponents to half movement.\nDetails:\nThe movement rates of opponents of truly massive size (such as dragons) will be adjudicated by the GM, either being slowed by a quarter movement rate or pushing the hand aside entirely.","link":""},"cloudkill":{"name":"Cloudkill","level":"5","school":"Evocation","range":"1”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"4” wide, 2” high, 2” deep cloud","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cloudkill\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4” wide, 2” high, 2” deep cloud\nThis spell creates a billowing cloud of ghastly yellow-green vapors. The cloud slays creatures with fewer than 4+1 Hit Dice. Creatures with 4+1 to 5+1 Hit Dice must save versus poison at -4 or die. Creatures up to and including 6 Hit Dice must save versus poison normally or die. The cloud moves away from the caster at 1” per round, rolling along the ground. Wind alters its course but never moves it back toward the caster. A strong wind breaks it up in 4 rounds, and stronger wind prevents the spell from being used. Very thick vegetation disperses the cloud in 2 rounds, or after it moves 2” through such growth. Since the vapors are heavier than air, they sink to the lowest available level and may pour into dens, sinkholes, or similar openings.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"cone of cold":{"name":"Cone Of Cold","level":"5","school":"Evocation","range":"0","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Cone Of Cold\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a cone-shaped area of cold originating at the magic-user’s hand and extending outward ½” per caster level. It drains heat and deals 1d4+1 damage per caster level. For example, a 10th-level magic-user casts a cone of cold dealing 10d4+10 damage. Material Component: A very small crystal or glass cone.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"conjure elemental":{"name":"Conjure Elemental","level":"5","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"6”","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Conjure Elemental\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the magic-user to conjure one air, earth, fire, or water elemental, provided the proper material component and element source are available. Fire elementals require a considerable fire source within range, and water elementals require a large amount of water. The elemental type must be chosen before the spell is memorized. Conjured elementals are typically very strong, usually 16 Hit Dice. The magic-user must concentrate to control the elemental and command its actions. If concentration is broken, the elemental turns on the caster and attacks, though it does not leave an existing combat to do so and avoids other creatures while seeking its conjurer. Wounding or grappling the magic-user breaks concentration. At the end of the second and each succeeding round, there is always a 5% chance the elemental turns on its conjurer regardless of concentration. The elemental may be controlled at a distance of up to 3” per caster level. It remains until destroyed or until the spell duration expires. Water elementals are destroyed if they move more than 6” from a body of water. Special protection from uncontrolled elementals may be gained through a pentacle, pentagram, thaumaturgic triangle, magic circle, or protection from evil. Material Components: In addition to the required element source, air elemental requires burning incense; earth elemental requires soft clay; fire elemental requires sulfur and phosphorus; water elemental requires water and sand.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"contact other plane":{"name":"Contact Other Plane","level":"5","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Contact Other Plane\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell sends the magic-user’s mind to another plane to seek advice and information from powers there. Such powers are found at random and resent the contact, so answers are brief, such as “yes,” “no,” “maybe,” “never,” or “irrelevant.” The caster may ask one question for every 2 experience levels. Contacting planes farther removed increases the chance of insanity or death, but also increases the chance that the contacted power knows the answer and tells the truth.\n\nPlane Contacted\tChance of Insanity\tChance of Knowledge\tChance of Truth\nElemental\t20%\t90%\t75%\n1 plane removed\t5%\t60%\t65%\n2 planes removed\t10%\t65%\t67%\n3 planes removed\t15%\t70%\t70%\n4 planes removed\t20%\t75%\t73%\n5 planes removed\t25%\t80%\t75%\n6 planes removed\t30%\t85%\t78%\n7 planes removed\t35%\t90%\t81%\n8 planes removed\t40%\t95%\t85%\n9 or more planes removed\t50%\t98%\t90%\n\nFor every point of Intelligence above 15, the caster reduces the chance of insanity by 5%. If the answer is unknown and truth is not indicated, the being answers definitely but falsely. If truth is indicated, the being answers “unknown.” Elemental contact assumes knowledge of questions concerning the appropriate Elemental Plane. Insanity begins as soon as one question is asked and lasts 1 week per plane removed, to a maximum of 10 weeks. There is a 1% chance per plane removed that the magic-user dies before recovering unless remove curse is cast on them.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"distance distortion":{"name":"Distance Distortion","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"100 square “ per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Distance Distortion\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 100 square “ per level\nThis spell can be cast only when the magic-user has conjured an earth elemental. The elemental does not react hostilely to cooperating if the caster announces the intent to cast distance distortion. The spell places the earth elemental in the area of effect, and the elemental distorts the area’s dimensions in one of two ways: the area effectively becomes half the distance to those traveling across it, or it becomes twice the distance. Thus, a 10-foot by 100-foot corridor could seem 5 feet wide and 50 feet long, or 20 feet wide and 200 feet long. When the duration ends, the elemental returns to its own plane. The true nature of the distortion is undetectable to creatures traveling through the area, though it radiates a dim dweomer, and true seeing reveals the earth elemental spread throughout the area. Material Component: A small lump of soft clay.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"extension ii":{"name":"Extension II","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Extension II\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is the same as extension I, except it extends the duration of 1st- through 4th-level spells by 50%.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"feeblemind":{"name":"Feeblemind","level":"5","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Feeblemind\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 6th-level druid spell feeblemind. Material Component: A handful of small clay, crystal, glass, or mineral spheres.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"hold monster":{"name":"Hold Monster","level":"5","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"One to four creatures","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Hold Monster\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One to four creatures\nThis spell immobilizes 1 to 4 creatures of any type within range and line of sight. If three or four creatures are targeted, each saving throw is normal. If two are targeted, each saves at -1. If only one is targeted, the save is at -3. Partially negated hold monster effects are equivalent to slow. Material Component: One hard metal bar or rod for each monster to be held, which may be as small as a three-penny nail.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"leomund s secret chest":{"name":"Leomund’s Secret Chest","level":"5","school":"Alteration, Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Special","duration":"60 days","aoe":"One chest, about 2’ × 2’ × 3’","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Leomund’s Secret Chest\n\nSchool: Alteration, Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 60 days\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One chest, about 2’ × 2’ × 3’\nTo cast this spell, the magic-user must have an exceptionally well-crafted and expensive chest made by master craftsmen. If made primarily of wood, it must be ebony, rosewood, sandalwood, teak, or similar fine wood, with platinum fittings, nails, and hardware. If made of ivory, its fittings may be gold; if made of bronze, copper, or silver, its fittings may be electrum or silver. The chest costs at least 5,000 gp. A perfect miniature replica of the same materials must also be made. A magic-user may have only one such pair of chests at a time, with no exception even by wish. While touching the chest and holding the miniature, the caster chants the spell, causing the large chest to vanish into the Ethereal Plane. The chest can contain 1 cubic foot of material per caster level, regardless of its apparent size. Living matter creates a 75% chance the spell fails. As long as the caster possesses the miniature, they can recall the large chest. If the miniature is lost or destroyed, even wish cannot return the large chest. While on the Ethereal Plane, there is a cumulative 1% chance per week that some creature or being finds the chest. If found, there is a 10% chance it is ignored, 10% chance something is added, 30% chance contents are exchanged, 30% chance something is stolen, and 20% chance it is emptied. When the chest is recalled, an ethereal window opens for 5 hours, slowly diminishing. There is a 5% chance an ethereal monster is drawn through, reduced by 1% cumulatively each hour. No creature on the Prime Material Plane can locate the chest, even with gem of seeing, true seeing, or similar magic. If the chest is not retrieved before the spell expires, there is a cumulative 5% chance per day it is lost forever, starting at 5% on day 61, 10% on day 62, and so on.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic jar":{"name":"Magic Jar","level":"5","school":"Possession","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Magic Jar\n\nSchool: Possession\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis unusual spell allows the magic-user to transfer their life force into a special container, the magic jar, and from there attempt to take over a victim’s mind and control that creature’s body. If the body is human or humanoid, the caster may even use their own known spells. The possessor can access only rudimentary knowledge of the possessed body, not real knowledge such as languages or spells. The life force receptacle must be within spell range of the caster’s body when the spell is cast. From the jar, the caster’s life force can sense and attack any creature within range, though it cannot determine exactly what the creature is. Possession succeeds only if the victim fails its saving throw. A failed possession attempt leaves the caster’s life force in the jar. Each possession attempt requires 1 round. If the caster’s body is destroyed, the life force in the jar is unharmed. If the jar is destroyed, the life force is extinguished. Returning to the caster’s own body requires 1 round and can only be done if the jar is within spell range of the body. The saving throw is modified by comparing the combined Intelligence and Wisdom of caster and victim; for non-human or non-humanoid victims, compare Intelligence only.\n\nDifference\tSaving Throw Modifier\nVictim higher by 9 or more\t+4\nVictim higher by 6–8\t+3\nVictim higher by 3–5\t+2\nVictim higher by 0–2\t+1\nCaster higher by 1–4\t0\nCaster higher by 5–8\t-1\nCaster higher by 9–12\t-2\nCaster higher by 13 or more\t-3\n\nA negative difference means the caster’s score is lower and the victim gains a saving throw bonus. A possessed creature with any negative difference, or a positive difference below 5, receives a saving throw each round to regain control. A positive difference of 5–8 grants a saving throw each turn; 9–12 grants one each day; 13 or more grants one each week. If the possessed creature regains control, the caster is trapped until they can possess the victim again or escape. Material Component: The magic jar itself.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"monster summoning iii":{"name":"Monster Summoning III","level":"5","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"5”","duration":"4 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Monster Summoning III\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 5”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons 1d4 3rd-level monsters, which arrive in 1d4 rounds. See monster summoning I for other details.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"murkenvain s faithful hound":{"name":"MUrkenvain’S Faithful Hound","level":"5","school":"Range: 10 ft.","range":"","duration":"2 rounds/magic-user level","aoe":"See below","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell summons an invisible watchdog to guard an area. The “hound” is invisible to all but the caster, who may order it to keep watch over a particular area. The area must be close to you; if you move more than 30 ft. from the area the “hound” is guarding, it returns to the spirit realm.\nDetails:\nThe “hound” can detect virtually any creature that enters the area: it can detect invisibility (which includes creatures on the astral and ethereal planes), can see creatures that are moving between dimensions, and can detect virtually any other method that might be employed to sneak into an area.\nIf any creature larger than a cat or small dog enters the area, the “hound” begins baying with an echoing, supernatural bark.\nMoreover, it will seek to attack intruders from behind (it does not make frontal assaults) and can attack as a monster of 10 HD for 3d6 damage, even if the opponent requires up to a +3 magical weapon to be hit.\nThe “hound” cannot be harmed by any means other than by dispelling it. These spirits don’t look like dogs. Most magic-users who can cast the spell avoid the topic of what the “hounds” actually look like.","notes":"This spell summons an invisible watchdog to guard an area. The “hound” is invisible to all but the caster, who may order it to keep watch over a particular area. The area must be close to you; if you move more than 30 ft. from the area the “hound” is guarding, it returns to the spirit realm.\nDetails:\nThe “hound” can detect virtually any creature that enters the area: it can detect invisibility (which includes creatures on the astral and ethereal planes), can see creatures that are moving between dimensions, and can detect virtually any other method that might be employed to sneak into an area.\nIf any creature larger than a cat or small dog enters the area, the “hound” begins baying with an echoing, supernatural bark.\nMoreover, it will seek to attack intruders from behind (it does not make frontal assaults) and can attack as a monster of 10 HD for 3d6 damage, even if the opponent requires up to a +3 magical weapon to be hit.\nThe “hound” cannot be harmed by any means other than by dispelling it. These spirits don’t look like dogs. Most magic-users who can cast the spell avoid the topic of what the “hounds” actually look like.","link":""},"passwall":{"name":"Passwall","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"3”","duration":"6 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Passwall\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 6 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell opens a passage through wooden, plaster, or stone walls. The opening is 5 feet wide, 8 feet high, and 10 feet deep. Multiple passwall spells can form a continuous passage through very thick walls. Material Component: A pinch of sesame seeds.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"stone shape":{"name":"Stone Shape","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1 cubic foot per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Stone Shape\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per level\nThis spell allows the magic-user to form an existing piece of stone into a desired shape. It can create a stone weapon, fashion a trapdoor, sculpt an idol, reshape a stone door to escape imprisonment, form stone coffers, or make secret doors, provided the volume affected is within the spell limit. Fine detail is limited. Material Component: Soft clay worked into roughly the desired shape and touched to the stone when the spell is uttered.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"telekinesis":{"name":"Telekinesis","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"2 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"250 gp weight per level","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Telekinesis\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 250 gp weight per level\nThis spell allows the magic-user to move objects by willpower while concentrating. Objects may move vertically or horizontally. Movement is 2” on the first round, 4” on the second, 8” on the third, 16” on the fourth, and so on, doubling each round until a maximum speed of 1,024” per round is reached. Heavy objects traveling at high speed can be deadly weapons. The spell can move opponents within its weight limit, though simple countermeasures such as enlarge may increase a target’s weight beyond the limit. Ambulation or another motive force can counter telekinesis if velocity has not yet reached 16” per round. Bigby’s hand spells and many other magics may also counter it.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"teleport":{"name":"Teleport","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Teleport\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell instantly transports the magic-user, along with weight touched or carried, to a known destination. Distance is irrelevant, but interplanar travel is not possible. The caster can teleport up to 2,500 gp weight, plus 1,500 gp weight per level above 10th. For example, a 13th-level magic-user can teleport up to 7,000 gp weight, or 700 pounds. The chance of arriving accurately depends on familiarity.\n\nDestination Familiarity\tHigh\tOn Target\tLow\nVery familiar\t01–02\t03–99\t00\nStudied carefully\t01–04\t05–98\t99–00\nSeen casually\t01–08\t09–96\t97–00\nViewed once\t01–16\t17–92\t93–00\nNever seen\t01–32\t33–84\t85–00\n\nA “high” result means the caster arrives 1” above the ground for every 1% below the lowest “On Target” probability, from 2” high for a very familiar destination to 32” high for a never-seen destination. A “low” result means instant death if the caster arrives inside solid matter. The spell cannot teleport the caster to empty space; there must be a substantial surface such as wood floor, stone floor, or natural ground.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"transmute rock to mud":{"name":"Transmute Rock To Mud","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"2 cubic “ per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Transmute Rock To Mud\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Transmute Mud To Rock\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2 cubic “ per level\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 5th-level druid spell transmute rock to mud. Material Components: Clay and water; or sand, lime, and water for the reverse.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"transmute mud to rock":{"name":"Transmute MUd to Rock","level":"5","school":"Range: 10 ft./magic-user level","range":"","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"20-ft. cube/magic-user level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell transforms mud into sandstone or a similar sedimentary rock.","notes":"This spell transforms mud into sandstone or a similar sedimentary rock.","link":""},"wall of force":{"name":"Wall Of Force","level":"5","school":"Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"1 turn + 1 round per level","aoe":"20 square feet per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wall Of Force\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 turn + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 20 square feet per level\nThis spell creates an invisible, immobile barrier at the location desired, within range. It is unaffected by all spells except disintegrate, which destroys it immediately. It is also unaffected by dispel magic, blows, missiles, cold, heat, electricity, and similar effects. Spells and breath weapons cannot pass through it in either direction. The caster may shape it as a wall, hemisphere, or sphere, up to 20 square feet per caster level. Material Component: A pinch of powdered diamond.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"wall of iron":{"name":"Wall Of Iron","level":"5","school":"Evocation","range":"½” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wall Of Iron\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes a vertical iron wall to spring into being. It is typically used to seal a passage or close a breach, inserting itself into surrounding material if its area is sufficient. The wall is ¼ inch thick per caster level. The caster may create 15 square feet of wall per level, so a 12th-level caster can create 180 square feet. If created without support, the wall falls and crushes creatures beneath it. The wall is permanent unless removed by dispel magic, but is otherwise subject to normal forces affecting iron, such as rust and perforation. Material Component: A small piece of sheet iron.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"wall of stone":{"name":"Wall Of Stone","level":"5","school":"Evocation","range":"½” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wall Of Stone\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a granite wall that merges into adjoining stone surfaces if enough area is available. It is typically used to close passages, portals, or breaches. The wall is ¼ foot thick and 20 square feet in area per caster level. Thus, a 12th-level magic-user creates a wall 3 feet thick and 240 square feet in surface area, such as a 12-foot-wide by 20-foot-high wall. The wall need not be vertical or rest on a firm foundation, but it must merge with existing stone. It can be used as a bridge or ramp. It is permanent unless destroyed by dispel magic, disintegrate, or normal breaking and chipping. Material Component: A small block of granite.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 6th Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"anti magic shell":{"name":"Anti-Magic Shell","level":"6","school":"Abjuration","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"1 foot per level diameter sphere","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Anti-Magic Shell\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 foot per level diameter sphere\nThis spell surrounds the magic-user with an invisible barrier that moves with the caster. The barrier is impervious to all magic and magical spell effects, including breath weapons, gaze weapons, and voice weapons. It prevents spells and magical effects from entering, and prevents magical items or spells inside it from functioning. Charmed, summoned, and conjured creatures cannot enter. Normal creatures can pass through the shell, and normal missiles are unaffected. A magic sword loses its magical function inside the shell, but remains a sword.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"bigby s forceful hand":{"name":"Bigby’s Forceful Hand","level":"6","school":"Evocation","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Bigby’s Forceful Hand\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is a stronger version of Bigby’s interposing hand. In addition to interposing itself, it pushes creatures away from the caster. It can push away creatures weighing 500 pounds or less, slow creatures weighing 500 to 2,000 pounds to 1” movement per round, and reduce movement by 50% for creatures weighing up to 8,000 pounds. It takes as much damage to destroy as its creator has hit points. Material Component: A glove.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"control weather":{"name":"Control Weather","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"4–24 hours","aoe":"4–16 square miles","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Control Weather\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 4–24 hours\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4–16 square miles\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 7th-level cleric spell control weather. Material Components: Burning incense, plus bits of earth and wood mixed in water.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"death spell":{"name":"Death Spell","level":"6","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1” per level","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"½” square per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Death Spell\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: ½” square per level\nThis spell instantly and irrevocably slays creatures in the area of effect. The number slain depends on their Hit Dice.\n\nVictim Hit Dice\tMaximum Number Affected\nLess than 2\t4d20\n2 to 4\t3d10\n4+1 to 6+3\t2d4\n6+4 to 8+3\t1d4\n\nFor mixed groups, roll the dice for creatures under 2 Hit Dice, kill those first, then use the conversion table to determine higher-Hit-Die deaths. This process may also be reversed, applying the effect to higher-Hit-Die creatures first.\n\nCreature Hit Dice\tEquals Less Than 2 HD\tEquals 2–4 HD\tEquals 4+1 to 6+3 HD\tEquals 6+4 to 8+3 HD\n6+4 to 8+3\t10\t5\t2\t—\n4+1 to 6+3\t8\t3\t—\t0.5\n2 to 4\t4\t—\t0.125\t0.05\n\nFor example, if 4d20 produces 53, then 20 points can kill one 6+4 to 8+3 Hit Dice creature, 16 points can kill two 4+1 to 6+3 Hit Dice creatures, 12 points can kill three 2 to 4 Hit Dice creatures, and 5 remaining points can kill five creatures under 2 Hit Dice. The spell does not affect lycanthropes, undead, or creatures from planes other than the Prime Material Plane. Material Component: A crushed black pearl worth at least 1,000 gp.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"disintegrate":{"name":"Disintegrate","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"½” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Disintegrate\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes matter to vanish. It can affect magical matter or energy, such as Bigby’s forceful hand, but not globe of invulnerability or anti-magic shell. Disintegration is instantaneous and permanent. It can affect any living thing, including undead, or obliterate up to 1 cubic inch of nonliving matter. Only one creature or object may be targeted. Creatures and magical material with a saving throw are unaffected if the save succeeds. Material Components: A lodestone and a pinch of dust.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"enchant an item":{"name":"Enchant An Item","level":"6","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"One item","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Enchant An Item\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One item\nThis spell prepares an object to receive magic. The item must be sound and undamaged, made of the finest possible materials and workmanship, and usually have raw material cost above 100 gp. Items such as rope, leather, cloth, or pottery must be embroidered, jeweled, tooled, carved, or engraved if such work can be added without weakening their function. The caster must continuously touch the item while casting. Casting requires a base 16 hours plus 8–64 additional hours. Since a magic-user may work no more than 8 hours per day, this means 2 days plus 1–8 days. The work must be uninterrupted. During rest periods, the item must remain within 1 foot of the caster, and the caster may perform no other magic and must remain quiet and isolated. At the end, the caster knows the item is ready for final testing. The caster speaks the final syllable, and the item makes a saving throw versus magic as if it were the caster. The caster’s saving throw bonuses apply up to +3. A natural roll of 1 always fails. If the spell succeeds, the caster may begin placing the desired dweomer on the item. The next spell must be cast within 24 hours, or the preparation fades. Each later spell cast onto the item requires 4 hours plus 4–8 additional hours per spell level, with the same touching and proximity requirements. Each successive dweomer must begin within 24 hours of the previous one, even if a prior spell failed. No magic placed into an item is permanent unless permanency is used. Charged items, such as rods, staves, wands, javelins of lightning, and rings of wishes, can never be made permanent. Scrolls and magic devices cannot be used to enchant an item or place magic on a prepared object. Material Components: These vary by item and intended enchantments, as determined by the Dungeon Master.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"extension iii":{"name":"Extension III","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Extension III\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is like extension I, except it doubles the duration of 1st- through 3rd-level spells and extends 4th- or 5th-level spells by 50%.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"geas":{"name":"Geas","level":"6","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Geas\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell places a magical command on an intelligent, conscious creature acting under its own will. The command may require a service or forbid an action. A geas cannot compel suicide or acts certain to cause death, but it can require almost any other course of action. The creature follows the instructions until the geas is completed. Failure causes the creature to grow sick and die within 1d4 weeks. Deviation or twisting of the instructions causes corresponding Strength loss until the deviation stops. A wish can remove a geas, but dispel magic and remove curse cannot. An improperly cast geas is immediately null and void.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"glasseye":{"name":"Glasseye","level":"6","school":"RANGE: Touch","range":"","duration":"1 round/level","aoe":"See below","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell causes opaque materials to become transparent, either to you alone or to anyone, at your option.\nDetails: The dimensions of the transparent area are 3 ft. × 2 ft., and the depth depends upon the nature of the substance being made transparent. Lead and gold, being the base and pure metals respectively, are not affected by the spell at all. Only four inches of any other metal can be made transparent, but stone can be seen through to a distance of 6 ft., and wood to a distance of 20 ft.","notes":"This spell causes opaque materials to become transparent, either to you alone or to anyone, at your option.\nDetails: The dimensions of the transparent area are 3 ft. × 2 ft., and the depth depends upon the nature of the substance being made transparent. Lead and gold, being the base and pure metals respectively, are not affected by the spell at all. Only four inches of any other metal can be made transparent, but stone can be seen through to a distance of 6 ft., and wood to a distance of 20 ft.","link":""},"globe of invulnerability":{"name":"Globe Of Invulnerability","level":"6","school":"Abjuration","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"1” diameter sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Globe Of Invulnerability\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” diameter sphere\nThis spell is the same as minor globe of invulnerability, except that it prevents 1st- through 4th-level spells from functioning against the magic-user within the globe. The caster may still cast spells outward through the globe.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"guards and wards":{"name":"Guards And Wards","level":"6","school":"Evocation, Alteration, Enchantment/Charm","range":"0","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"1” radius per level, extending from a 2” diameter sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 turns","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Guards And Wards\n\nSchool: Evocation, Alteration, Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 turns\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” radius per level, extending from a 2” diameter sphere\nThis powerful spell is usually used to defend a magic-user’s stronghold. When cast, the following effects occur in the area: all corridors become misty, reducing visibility to 10 feet; all doors are wizard locked; one door per caster level is covered by an illusion making it appear to be a plain wall; stairs are filled with webs from top to bottom; wherever there are choices in direction, such as a side passage or crossing, a minor confusion effect creates a 50% chance intruders believe they are going in the exact opposite direction; and the whole area radiates magic. The caster may also place one additional effect: dancing lights in four corridors, magic mouth in two places, stinking cloud in two places, gust of wind in one corridor or room, or suggestion in one place. Door illusions and the additional effect function only if the caster is completely familiar with the area. Each dispel magic removes one random effect. Remove curse does not work. Material Components: Burning incense, a small measure of sulfur and oil, a knotted string, a small amount of umber hulk blood, and a small silver rod.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"invisible stalker":{"name":"Invisible Stalker","level":"6","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Invisible Stalker\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons an invisible stalker from the Elemental Plane of Air. The 8-Hit-Die creature obeys and serves the caster in performing assigned tasks, but it serves because it is bound, not from loyalty. It resents prolonged missions and complex tasks and attempts to pervert instructions accordingly. It follows instructions even over hundreds or thousands of miles. Material Components: Burning incense and a piece of horn carved into a crescent shape.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"legend lore":{"name":"Legend Lore","level":"6","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Legend Lore\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell reveals information about a known person, place, or thing, provided the subject is noteworthy or legendary. If the person or thing is present, or the caster is in the place in question, casting takes only 1d4 turns and is more likely to produce results. If detailed information is known, casting takes 1d10 days. If only rumors are known, casting takes 2d6 weeks. During casting, the magic-user may do only routine activities such as eating and sleeping. When complete, the spell reveals whether legendary material exists. It often reveals where that material can be found, by place name, rhyme, or riddle. Sometimes, especially when the subject is present, it gives information in cryptic form, such as rhyme, riddle, anagram, cipher, or sign. Material Components: Incense and ivory strips formed into a rectangle, plus a sacrifice such as a potion, magic scroll, magic item, creature, or similar offering.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"lower water":{"name":"Lower Water","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"8”","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"½” × ½” square per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Lower Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Raise Water\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: ½” × ½” square per level\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 4th-level cleric spell lower water. The reverse raises water only ½ foot per caster level. Material Components: A small vial of water and a small vial of dust.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"monster summoning iv":{"name":"Monster Summoning IV","level":"6","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"6”","duration":"5 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Monster Summoning IV\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 5 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons 1d3 4th-level monsters, which appear within 1d3 rounds. See monster summoning I for other details.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"move earth":{"name":"Move Earth","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Move Earth\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell moves dirt, clay, loam, sand, and similar earth. It can collapse embankments, shift hillocks, move dunes, and similar effects. Casting time depends on the area: each 4” square area requires 1 turn of casting. If terrain features are to be moved, rather than simply collapsing banks or walls of earth, an earth elemental must also be summoned to assist. All spellcasting and summoning must be completed before any effects occur. Rock formations cannot be collapsed or moved. Material Components: A mixture of soils, such as clay, loam, and sand, in a small bag, plus an iron blade.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"otiluke s freezing sphere":{"name":"Otiluke’s Freezing Sphere","level":"6","school":"Alteration-Evocation","range":"Special","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Otiluke’s Freezing Sphere\n\nSchool: Alteration-Evocation\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell has three possible forms. First, it can create a globe of absolute-zero matter that spreads on contact with water or mainly water-based liquid, freezing it 6 inches deep over an area of 100 square feet per caster level. This ice lasts 1 round per caster level. Second, it can create a thin ray of cold from the caster’s hand with range 1” per caster level. The ray deals 4 damage per caster level to the creature struck. A successful saving throw versus magic negates all damage, meaning the ray missed, though the ray’s path is still traced to full distance and anything else in that path must save or suffer appropriate damage. Third, it can create a small globe about the size of a sling stone, cool but harmless to the touch. The globe may be thrown or slung and shatters on impact, dealing 4d6 cold damage to all creatures within 10 feet, or half damage on a successful saving throw. If not thrown or slung within 1 round per caster level, it shatters automatically and deals damage as above. Material Components: For the first form, a thin crystal sheet about 1 inch square; for the second, a white sapphire worth at least 1,000 gp; for the third, a diamond worth at least 1,000 gp. All components are lost when cast.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"part water":{"name":"Part Water","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Part Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 6th-level cleric spell part water. Material Components: Two small sheets of crystal or glass.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"project image":{"name":"Project Image","level":"6","school":"Alteration, Illusion/Phantasm","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Project Image\n\nSchool: Alteration, Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a nonmaterial duplicate of the magic-user projected to any desired spot within range. The image performs actions identical to the caster as directed, including walking, speaking, and spellcasting. A special channel connects the image and caster, so spells cast by the caster originate from the image. The image can be dispelled only by dispel magic or by the caster’s command; attacks do not affect it. The image must remain within the caster’s sight. If the caster’s sight is obstructed, the spell ends. Material Component: A small replica or doll of the magic-user.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"reincarnation":{"name":"Reincarnation","level":"6","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Person touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Reincarnation\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Person touched\nThis spell is similar to the 7th-level druid spell reincarnate. It requires no system shock or resurrection survival saving throw. The corpse is touched, and a new incarnation appears nearby in 1d6 turns, provided the person has not been dead longer than 1 day per caster level.\n\nDie Roll\tIncarnation\n01–05\tBugbear\n06–11\tDwarf\n12–18\tElf\n19–23\tGnoll\n24–28\tGnome\n29–33\tGoblin\n34–40\tHalf-Elf\n41–47\tHalfling\n48–54\tHalf-Orc\n55–59\tHobgoblin\n60–73\tHuman\n74–79\tKobold\n80–85\tOrc\n86–90\tOgre\n91–95\tOgre Mage\n96–00\tTroll\n\nVery good or very evil persons will not be reincarnated as creatures whose general alignment is opposite. Material Components: A small drum and a drop of blood.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"repulsion":{"name":"Repulsion","level":"6","school":"Abjuration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round per 2 levels","aoe":"1” path","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Repulsion\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 round per 2 levels\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” path\nThis spell causes all creatures in the area of effect path to move away from the magic-user. Repulsion occurs at 3” per round, or at the motive speed of the creature trying to move toward the caster. A repelled creature continues moving away for the remainder of a full move, even if this carries it beyond spell range. Material Component: A pair of small magnetized iron bars attached to two small canine statuettes, one ivory and one ebony.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"spirit rack":{"name":"Spirit Rack","level":"6","school":"RANGE: 10 ft. + 1 ft./level","range":"","duration":"See below","aoe":"One fiend","components":"V, M","ct":"8d6 hours","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell is used to utterly banish a particular demon, devil, or the like to its home plane of existence for a number of years equal to your magic-user level. The spell is normally used as a bargaining chip to force a devil or demon to cooperate with your plans or give you information.\nDetails: To cast the spell, you must know the fiendish creature’s name, and inscribe it into a scroll, the preparation of which requires 8d6 hours and the expenditure of at least 5,000 gp. Once the spell is cast, if you read the scroll aloud in the fiend’s presence it will have the effects described below. You can create no more than one scroll for any particular fiend and can only keep three such scrolls in existence at any one time; the magic of one will fade if a fourth is created.\nWhen you speak the first words of the scroll in the fiend’s presence, the demon is immediately held in place (unless its innate magic resistance allows it to escape this effect). Even if the fiend’s magic resistance protects it, the words of the scroll cause considerable agony, and if the creature has the ability to escape it is only 10% likely to remain and try to stop the final reading (0% likelihood if it has no means of attacking you, gaining possession of the scroll, or otherwise influencing events in its favor).\nAfter one full minute of reading the scroll (i.e., in the second round), the fiend loses 1 hp/HD from pain. In the third round, the fiend loses 50% of its remaining hit points from the agony caused by the words of the scroll. After the third round of reading, the fiend is banished to its home plane, where it writhes in agony for a period of years equal to the caster’s level.\nObviously, any fiend caught with this ritual will seek to negotiate its way out; the GM will determine probabilities based on the fiend’s goals and personality, but the base likelihood will be roughly 25% per round that the fiend will agree to perform a task for the caster in exchange for nothing more than the cessation of the ritual.","notes":"This spell is used to utterly banish a particular demon, devil, or the like to its home plane of existence for a number of years equal to your magic-user level. The spell is normally used as a bargaining chip to force a devil or demon to cooperate with your plans or give you information.\nDetails: To cast the spell, you must know the fiendish creature’s name, and inscribe it into a scroll, the preparation of which requires 8d6 hours and the expenditure of at least 5,000 gp. Once the spell is cast, if you read the scroll aloud in the fiend’s presence it will have the effects described below. You can create no more than one scroll for any particular fiend and can only keep three such scrolls in existence at any one time; the magic of one will fade if a fourth is created.\nWhen you speak the first words of the scroll in the fiend’s presence, the demon is immediately held in place (unless its innate magic resistance allows it to escape this effect). Even if the fiend’s magic resistance protects it, the words of the scroll cause considerable agony, and if the creature has the ability to escape it is only 10% likely to remain and try to stop the final reading (0% likelihood if it has no means of attacking you, gaining possession of the scroll, or otherwise influencing events in its favor).\nAfter one full minute of reading the scroll (i.e., in the second round), the fiend loses 1 hp/HD from pain. In the third round, the fiend loses 50% of its remaining hit points from the agony caused by the words of the scroll. After the third round of reading, the fiend is banished to its home plane, where it writhes in agony for a period of years equal to the caster’s level.\nObviously, any fiend caught with this ritual will seek to negotiate its way out; the GM will determine probabilities based on the fiend’s goals and personality, but the base likelihood will be roughly 25% per round that the fiend will agree to perform a task for the caster in exchange for nothing more than the cessation of the ritual.","link":""},"stone to flesh":{"name":"Stone To Flesh","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Stone To Flesh\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Flesh To Stone\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell turns stone into flesh. If the stone object was formerly living, the spell restores life and possessions, though the creature must survive the usual system shock roll. Any formerly living creature, regardless of size, can be returned to flesh. Ordinary stone can also be turned into flesh, affecting up to 9 cubic feet per caster level. The reverse, flesh to stone, turns flesh and all possessions on the creature to stone. The victim receives a saving throw. Material Components: For stone to flesh, a pinch of earth and a drop of blood. For flesh to stone, lime, water, and earth.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"tenser s transformation":{"name":"Tenser’s Transformation","level":"6","school":"Alteration-Evocation","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Personal","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Tenser’s Transformation\n\nSchool: Alteration-Evocation\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Personal\nThis spell transforms the magic-user into a berserk fighter of heroic size and strength. The caster’s hit points double, and damage is taken first from these magical hit points. If damage does not exceed the caster’s original hit points, no actual damage is suffered; damage beyond the added amount counts double. The caster’s Armor Class improves by 4, such as AC 10 becoming AC 6, AC 9 becoming AC 5, and so on. The caster attacks as a fighter of the same level, using the fighter combat table. The caster may attack only with a dagger, but gains +2 damage and makes 2 attacks per round. Once cast, the spell must run its full course. The magic-user keeps attacking until all opponents are slain, the caster is killed, the magic is dispelled, or the duration expires. Material Component: A potion of heroism or superheroism, which the caster must drink during the spell.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"bigby s grasping hand":{"name":"Bigby’s Grasping Hand","level":"7","school":"Evocation","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Bigby’s Grasping Hand\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is a superior version of Bigby’s forceful hand. It can hold motionless a creature or object weighing up to 1,000 pounds, or move creatures with double the strength of Bigby’s forceful hand. Material Component: A leather glove.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"cacodemon":{"name":"Cacodemon","level":"7","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Creature summoned","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Cacodemon\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Creature summoned\nThis dangerous spell summons a powerful type IV, V, or VI demon, depending on the name known to the magic-user. The spell cannot summon greater demons, and lesser demons are not called because they have no known names. The caster must know the exact name of the demon being summoned. The summoned demon is angry and evil-disposed. The caster must be within a circle of protection, or a thaumaturgic triangle with protection from evil, and the demon must be confined within a pentagram, or the caster risks being slain or carried off. The caster may deal with the demon in several ways. First, the caster may force service by threatening it with spiritwrack, releasing it only when the service is fulfilled and requiring the demon to pledge its word; this is extremely dangerous, since even a minor bargaining error may let the demon twist the result or kill the summoner, and the demon becomes a lasting enemy. Second, the caster may bargain with fresh human blood and promised sacrifices, though the demon may reject the offer or exploit the exact wording of the agreement. Third, the demon may be trapped with trap the soul. A trapped demon remains imprisoned until its prison is broken, at which point it owes one service to the liberator if the liberator demands one immediately. If no service is demanded when the demon asks what is required, it is free to slay the liberator. Any required service must be limited in duration unless the demon willingly agrees to more. An impossible or excessive task has a 50% chance to free the demon from obligation and allow vengeance. A freed demon can remain on the summoning plane for up to 666 days. The summoned demon is exceptionally strong, having 8 hit points per Hit Die. Casting time is 1 hour per demon type number, such as 4 hours for type IV. Any interruption during casting causes failure. Interruption while the demon is summoned creates a 10% chance, cumulative each round, that it escapes its boundaries and attacks. The demon receives a saving throw against summoning. If a roll higher than the caster’s level is made on 3d6, or on 2d10 for type VI demons, the spell fails to summon that demon, meaning the name was incorrect or the demon is imprisoned or destroyed. Material Components: Five flaming black candles; a brazier of hot coals burning sulfur, bat hair, lard, soot, mercuric-nitric acid crystals, mandrake root, alcohol, and a parchment bearing the demon’s name in runes inside a pentacle; plus a dish of mammal blood, preferably human, placed where the demon is to be confined.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"charm plants":{"name":"Charm Plants","level":"7","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"3”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Charm Plants\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell brings vegetable life forms under the caster’s command and allows communication with them. The plants obey instructions to the best of their ability. The spell charms plants in a 3” × 1” area. It does not give plants new powers, but it allows them to use whatever abilities they already possess to carry out the caster’s instructions. Intelligent plants receive a saving throw at -4. Material Components: A pinch of humus, a drop of water, and a twig or leaf.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"delayed blast fireball":{"name":"Delayed Blast Fireball","level":"7","school":"Evocation","range":"10” + 1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"2” radius globe","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Delayed Blast Fireball\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 10” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: 2” radius globe\nThis spell creates a fireball that deals +1 damage on each die and delays detonation for 1 to 50 segments, or 1/10 round to 5 rounds, according to the caster’s command. Otherwise, it functions as the 3rd-level fireball spell.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"dramijar s instant summons":{"name":"Dramijar’S Instant Summons","level":"7","school":"RANGE: See below","range":"","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Fast","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell calls a specific, desired object into your hand from wherever it might be.\nDetails: The object must be prepared ahead of time, with the first part of the spell being cast upon it at that time—all but the final word of the incantation. The item is then touched with another item, the spell’s focus, which must be of at least 5,000 gp in value (usually a gem). When you seek to summon the item by means of this spell, you must hold the focus item in your hand and speak the final word of the spell. The focus item will disappear, and the summoned item will appear in its place. The summoned item cannot be heavier than 8 lbs. or the spell will not function. Moreover, if the item is in the possession (not necessarily in the hand) of another creature, the spell will fail. However, in this instance, you will learn the item’s location, and some details about the owner, as determined by the GM. The spell will function across the planes.","notes":"This spell calls a specific, desired object into your hand from wherever it might be.\nDetails: The object must be prepared ahead of time, with the first part of the spell being cast upon it at that time—all but the final word of the incantation. The item is then touched with another item, the spell’s focus, which must be of at least 5,000 gp in value (usually a gem). When you seek to summon the item by means of this spell, you must hold the focus item in your hand and speak the final word of the spell. The focus item will disappear, and the summoned item will appear in its place. The summoned item cannot be heavier than 8 lbs. or the spell will not function. Moreover, if the item is in the possession (not necessarily in the hand) of another creature, the spell will fail. However, in this instance, you will learn the item’s location, and some details about the owner, as determined by the GM. The spell will function across the planes.","link":""},"duo dimension":{"name":"Duo-Dimension","level":"7","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"3 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Personal","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Duo-Dimension\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 3 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Personal\nThis spell gives the caster only two dimensions, height and width but no depth. When the caster turns sideways, they become invisible except to true seeing or similar magic. The caster can pass through the thinnest spaces, provided the space has enough height for their actual length, such as slipping between a door and its frame. The caster can act normally, turning invisible, moving while invisible, appearing the next round to cast a spell, and disappearing again afterward. While turned sideways, the caster cannot be affected by attacks. While visible, the caster takes triple normal damage from attacks. A portion of the caster’s existence is on the Astral Plane while the spell lasts, so astral creatures may notice the caster. If noticed, there is a 25% chance an astral creature’s attack pulls the caster entirely onto the Astral Plane. Material Components: A thin, flat ivory likeness of the caster, finely made, gold-filigreed, enameled, and gem-studded, costing 5,000–10,000 gp, and a strip of parchment. During casting, the parchment is twisted into a loop, the figurine is passed through it, and both vanish.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"limited wish":{"name":"Limited Wish","level":"7","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Unlimited","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"Special","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Limited Wish\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: Unlimited\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell partially or temporarily fulfills the caster’s spoken wish. It can alter past, present, or future reality in a limited way, though possibly only for the caster unless carefully worded. It cannot substantially change major realities, nor can it simply grant wealth or experience. It may restore some hit points, or all hit points for a limited duration, reduce enemy hit probabilities or damage, extend a magical effect, cause a creature to be favorably disposed toward the caster, or provide a minor clue to treasure or a magic item. Greedy wishes usually end in disaster. Casting time equals the actual number of seconds needed to phrase the wish, at 6 seconds per segment.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"mass invisibility":{"name":"Mass Invisibility","level":"7","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mass Invisibility\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is the same as invisibility, except it can hide creatures in a 3” × 3” area, up to 300–400 man-sized creatures, 30–40 giants, or 6–8 large dragons.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"monster summoning v":{"name":"Monster Summoning V","level":"7","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"7”","duration":"6 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Monster Summoning V\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 7”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 6 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons 1d2 5th-level monsters, which appear in 1d3 rounds. See monster summoning I for other details.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"murkenvain s sword":{"name":"MUrkenvain’S Sword","level":"7","school":"RANGE: 30 ft.","range":"","duration":"1 round/MU level","aoe":"Summoned sword","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"You evoke a magical sword into being, and can wield it by exerting your willpower (you do not need to wield the sword; it flies and attacks where you direct). While using the sword, you cannot cast spells, use magic items, or move, although the spell does not end if your concentration is broken; the sword simply does not attack during that round.\nDetails: The sword attacks as a fighter one-half your magic user level, always hits on a natural 19 or 20, and can hit creatures that can ordinarily be hit only with magic weapons (up to +3). It can attack creatures in the astral or ethereal planes of existence. The sword inflicts 5d4 hit points of slashing or piercing damage (you choose) against Tiny to Medium size creatures, and 5d6 hit points against creatures larger than Medium. The material components for the spell cost 500 gp or more.","notes":"You evoke a magical sword into being, and can wield it by exerting your willpower (you do not need to wield the sword; it flies and attacks where you direct). While using the sword, you cannot cast spells, use magic items, or move, although the spell does not end if your concentration is broken; the sword simply does not attack during that round.\nDetails: The sword attacks as a fighter one-half your magic user level, always hits on a natural 19 or 20, and can hit creatures that can ordinarily be hit only with magic weapons (up to +3). It can attack creatures in the astral or ethereal planes of existence. The sword inflicts 5d4 hit points of slashing or piercing damage (you choose) against Tiny to Medium size creatures, and 5d6 hit points against creatures larger than Medium. The material components for the spell cost 500 gp or more.","link":""},"phase door":{"name":"Phase Door","level":"7","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"One use per 2 levels","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Phase Door\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: One use per 2 levels\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell attunes the caster’s body and affects a section of wall as if by passwall. The phase door is invisible to all creatures except the caster, and only the caster can use the created passage, disappearing when entering and reappearing when exiting. The door lasts for one use per 2 caster levels. It can be dispelled only by a higher-level magic-user’s dispel magic, or by several lower-level magic-users casting together whose combined levels are more than double the original caster’s level.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"power word stun":{"name":"Power Word, Stun","level":"7","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"½” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Power Word, Stun\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nWhen this spell is uttered, one chosen creature within range is stunned, reeling and unable to think coherently or act. The caster must face the creature. Duration depends on the creature’s current hit points. A creature with 1–30 hit points is stunned for 4d4 rounds. A creature with 31–60 hit points is stunned for 2d4 rounds. A creature with 61–90 hit points is stunned for 1d4 rounds. Creatures with more than 90 hit points are unaffected. Current hit points, not normal maximum hit points, determine the effect.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"reverse gravity":{"name":"Reverse Gravity","level":"7","school":"Alteration","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 segment","aoe":"3” × 3” square area","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Reverse Gravity\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 segment\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” × 3” square area\nThis spell reverses gravity in the area of effect, causing all unfixed objects and creatures within it to fall upward. Reverse gravity lasts 1 second, or 1/6 segment, during which affected objects and creatures fall 16 feet upward. If they strike a solid object, impact is handled as a normal downward fall. When the spell ends, affected objects and creatures fall downward. Since the spell affects an area, objects or creatures high in the air can also be affected. Material Components: A lodestone and iron filings.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"simulacrum":{"name":"Simulacrum","level":"7","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Simulacrum\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell creates a duplicate of any creature. The duplicate appears exactly like the original, but has only 51%–60% of the original’s hit points, has personality differences, lacks some areas of knowledge, and is instantly revealed as a simulacrum by detect magic or true seeing. The simulacrum is under the absolute command of its creator, though there is no telepathic link, so commands must be given normally. The spell creates only the creature’s form, which is initially zombie-like. A reincarnation spell must provide vital force, and a limited wish must give the duplicate 40%–65% of the original’s knowledge and personality. If the original had levels, the simulacrum has 20%–50% of those levels. The duplicate is formed from ice or snow, and a piece of the creature to be copied must be placed inside the form. The spell also requires powdered ruby. The simulacrum cannot grow more powerful or increase its levels or abilities.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"statue":{"name":"Statue","level":"7","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Statue\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell makes the caster or touched creature appear to turn to solid stone, along with worn or carried gear. The initial transformation requires 1 full round after casting. Thereafter, the creature can withstand inspection and appears to be a stone statue, though faint magic is detectable. While in statue form, the subject can see, hear, and smell normally. Feeling is limited to sensations that affect the granite-hard body; chipping is like a slight wound, while breaking off an arm is far more serious. The subject can return to normal in 1/6 segment, and can return to statue form just as quickly while the spell lasts. During the initial transformation, the subject must make a system shock roll of 82% or less, modified by subtracting 1 from the die roll for each point of Constitution; Constitution 18 means automatic success. Failure means death from system shock. Material Components: Lime, sand, and a drop of water stirred with an iron bar, nail, or spike.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"vanish":{"name":"Vanish","level":"7","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Vanish\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes an object to vanish. The caster may teleport the object if it weighs up to 500 gp per caster level; for example, a 14th-level magic-user can vanish and reappear an object weighing up to 7,000 gp. Larger objects can be made to vanish, but they are placed on the Ethereal Plane and replaced by stone. Thus, a vanished door is replaced by a stone wall 1 foot thick, or as thick as the door, whichever is greater. The maximum affected volume is 3 cubic feet per caster level, so both weight and volume limit the spell. A successful dispel magic returns vanished objects from the Ethereal Plane.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 8th Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"antipathy sympathy":{"name":"Antipathy/Sympathy","level":"8","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"3”","duration":"12 turns per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 turns","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Antipathy/Sympathy\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 6 turns\nDuration: 12 turns per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell sets vibrations that repel or attract a specific kind of living, intelligent creature or characters of a specific alignment. The caster must choose the effect and target creature or alignment type before casting. The spell cannot be cast on living creatures. Antipathy causes the specified creature or alignment type to feel an overwhelming urge to leave the area or avoid touching the object. If the saving throw succeeds, the creature may remain or touch the item but feels very uncomfortable, suffering a persistent itching that causes the loss of 1 Dexterity per round, to a maximum loss of 4 Dexterity. If the saving throw fails, the creature or alignment type abandons the area or item, shuns it permanently, and never willingly enters or touches it until the spell is removed or expires. Sympathy causes the specified creature or alignment type to feel elated and pleased to be in the area or to touch or possess the object. The desire is overpowering unless a saving throw versus magic succeeds. If the save succeeds, the creature is released from the enchantment, but must save again 1d6 turns later or return to the area or object. The specific creature type or alignment must be named, such as red dragons, hill giants, wererats, vampires, chaotic evil, lawful neutral, or neutral. If cast on an area, the spell affects a 10-foot cube per caster level. If cast on an object, only that object is enchanted, and affected creatures save at -2. Material Components: For antipathy, a lump of alum soaked in vinegar. For sympathy, 1,000 gp worth of crushed pearls and a drop of honey.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"biccby s clenched fist":{"name":"Biccby’S Clenched Fist","level":"8","school":"RANGE 5ft/MU level","range":"","duration":"1 round/MU level","aoe":"Enchanted hand","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"As with Biccby’s other hand spells, Biccby’s clenched fist evokes a magical hand, but in this case the hand is always at least as large as a giant’s and is curled into a fist rather than held open. The clenched fist strikes one of your enemies per round, never missing, for so long as you maintain concentration.\nDetails\nNo other activity is possible while concentrating, and breaking the caster’s concentration ends the spell. The fist rolls a d20 to determine damage (it hits automatically):\n• On a roll of 1–12, it deals 1d6 hp of damage.\n• On a 13–15, it deals 2d6 hit points.\n• On a roll of 16–19 it deals 3d6 hit points and stuns the opponent for one round.\n• On a roll of 20+ it deals 4d6 hit points and stuns the opponent for 3 rounds.\nIf the opponent has already been stunned, the d20 roll receives a +4 bonus. As with the other Biccby’s hand spells, the hand has as many hit points as the caster’s full hit points.","notes":"As with Biccby’s other hand spells, Biccby’s clenched fist evokes a magical hand, but in this case the hand is always at least as large as a giant’s and is curled into a fist rather than held open. The clenched fist strikes one of your enemies per round, never missing, for so long as you maintain concentration.\nDetails\nNo other activity is possible while concentrating, and breaking the caster’s concentration ends the spell. The fist rolls a d20 to determine damage (it hits automatically):\n• On a roll of 1–12, it deals 1d6 hp of damage.\n• On a 13–15, it deals 2d6 hit points.\n• On a roll of 16–19 it deals 3d6 hit points and stuns the opponent for one round.\n• On a roll of 20+ it deals 4d6 hit points and stuns the opponent for 3 rounds.\nIf the opponent has already been stunned, the d20 roll receives a +4 bonus. As with the other Biccby’s hand spells, the hand has as many hit points as the caster’s full hit points.","link":""},"clone":{"name":"Clone","level":"8","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Clone\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a duplicate of a person. The clone is identical to the original as the person was when the flesh sample was taken, including level, experience, memories, and similar traits. Later knowledge, experience, and possessions are not copied. If the original and clone exist at the same time, each knows of the other and each wants to destroy the other, since such an alter ego is unbearable. If one cannot destroy the other, within 1 week one is 95% likely to go insane and destroy itself, with the clone 75% likely to be the one affected; there is also a 5% chance both become mad and commit suicide. The clone requires 2d4 months to grow, and dual existence is established only after that time. Material Component: A small piece of flesh from the person to be duplicated.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"glass steel":{"name":"Glass-Steel","level":"8","school":"RANGE Touch","range":"","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell grants a glass object the strength of steel, while retaining its transparent properties. The weight of the object can be no more than 10 lbs per caster level.\nDetails\nIn most cases, the object will make item saving throws on the more favourable of the glass or metal tables.","notes":"This spell grants a glass object the strength of steel, while retaining its transparent properties. The weight of the object can be no more than 10 lbs per caster level.\nDetails\nIn most cases, the object will make item saving throws on the more favourable of the glass or metal tables.","link":""},"incendiary cloud":{"name":"Incendiary Cloud","level":"8","school":"Alteration-Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"4 rounds + 1d6 rounds","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Incendiary Cloud\n\nSchool: Alteration-Evocation\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds + 1d6 rounds\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell resembles the smoke effect of pyrotechnics, except the cloud’s minimum dimensions are 10 feet high by 20 feet long by 20 feet wide. The dense vapor cloud billows forth, and on the 3rd round begins to flame, dealing ½ hit point per caster level. On the 4th round, it deals 1 hit point per caster level. On the 5th round, damage drops again to ½ hit point per caster level as the flames burn out. Later rounds are harmless smoke that obscures vision. Creatures in the cloud need make only one saving throw if successful; if they fail the first, they roll again on the 4th and 5th rounds if necessary to reduce damage by half. Material Components: An available fire source, as with pyrotechnics, scrapings from beneath a dung pile, and a pinch of dust.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"otho s irresistible dance":{"name":"Otho’S Irresistible Dance","level":"8","school":"RANGE Touch","range":"","duration":"1d4 +1 rounds","aoe":"One creature","components":"V","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"The creature touched (requiring a successful “to hit” roll) flies into an uncontrollable, twitching tarantella, dancing wildly.\nDetails\nThe creature’s armour class is penalised by 4 points, and it will fail any and all saving throws during the spell’s duration. It cannot act in any way, or gain benefit from a shield.","notes":"The creature touched (requiring a successful “to hit” roll) flies into an uncontrollable, twitching tarantella, dancing wildly.\nDetails\nThe creature’s armour class is penalised by 4 points, and it will fail any and all saving throws during the spell’s duration. It cannot act in any way, or gain benefit from a shield.","link":""},"mass charm":{"name":"Mass Charm","level":"8","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"½” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"8 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Mass Charm\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell affects persons or monsters as charm person or charm monster does, but affects a number of creatures whose combined levels or Hit Dice do not exceed twice the caster’s level. All targets must be within range and within a 3” × 3” area. Target saving throws are not affected by the number of creatures, but all targets save at -2 because of the spell’s efficiency and power.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"maze":{"name":"Maze","level":"8","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"½” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Maze\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell traps the recipient in an extradimensional labyrinth of force planes. The duration depends entirely on the creature’s Intelligence. Minotaurs are unaffected.\n\nIntelligence\tTime Trapped\nUnder 3\t2d4 turns\n3–5\t1d4 turns\n6–8\t5d4 rounds\n9–11\t4d4 rounds\n12–14\t3d4 rounds\n15–17\t2d4 rounds\n18+\t1d4 rounds","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"mind blank":{"name":"Mind Blank","level":"8","school":"Abjuration","range":"3”","duration":"1 day","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mind Blank\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 day\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell completely protects the recipient from devices and spells that detect, influence, or read emotions or thoughts. It blocks augury, charm, command, confusion, divination, empathy effects, ESP, fear, feeblemind, mass suggestion, phantasmal killer, possession, rulership, soul trapping, suggestion, and telepathy. It also prevents discovery or information-gathering by crystal balls and other scrying devices, clairaudience, clairvoyance, commune, contact other plane, wish, limited wish, and alter reality. Extremely powerful deities may penetrate the protection. It also protects against psionic detection and influence, including domination, mass domination, hypnosis, psionic invisibility, precognition, and similar powers.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"monster summoning vi":{"name":"Monster Summoning VI","level":"8","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"8”","duration":"7 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Monster Summoning VI\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 7 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons 1 or 2 6th-level monsters, which appear in 1d3 rounds. See monster summoning I for other details.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"permanency":{"name":"Permanency","level":"8","school":"Alteration","range":"Special","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Permanency\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 2 rounds\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell makes certain spell effects permanent. For personal use, it may make permanent: comprehend languages, detect evil, detect invisibility, detect magic, infravision, protection from evil, protection from normal missiles, read magic, tongues, and unseen servant. The magic-user casts the desired spell and then permanency. Each permanency lowers the magic-user’s Constitution by 1 point. The caster cannot use these personal permanent effects on others. The spell can also make certain object, creature, or area effects permanent: enlarge, fear, gust of wind, invisibility, magic mouth, prismatic sphere, stinking cloud, wall of fire, wall of force, and web. Personal permanency can be dispelled only by a magic-user of higher level than the original caster. Other permanent effects can be dispelled normally, negating the whole effect.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"polymorph object":{"name":"Polymorph Object","level":"8","school":"RANGE 5ft/MU level","range":"","duration":"FACTOR — DURATION — EXAMPLE","aoe":"One object or creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"This spell allows you to transform one thing, living or not, into another sort of thing. If the spell is used simply to duplicate the effects of a polymorph other spell or a stone to flesh spell, it will function in the same manner as these spells but with a -4 penalty to the victim’s saving throw. Otherwise, the spell’s duration depends upon the degree of change involved in the transformation. The calculation is made using a “duration factor” found on table 1, and the explanation of the resulting duration factor is found on table 2.\nDetails\nPOLYMORPH OBJECT—TABLE 1 (MAGIC USER LEVEL 8)\nCHANGED SUBJECT IS: — INCREASE TO DURATION FACTOR\nSame kingdom (animal, vegetable, mineral) — +5\nSame class (mammals, fungi, metals, etc.) — +2\nSame size — +2\nRelated (twig is to tree, wolf fur is to wolf, etc.) — +2\nSame or lower intelligence — +2\nAdd all that apply. Look up the total on the next table.\nExample 1: Changing a dog to a wolf. Same kingdom (+5), the same class (+2), possibly not the same size, but related (+2) and the same intelligence (+2). The duration factor would be 11.\nExample 2: Changing a mushroom into a dragon. Different kingdom, different class, different size, unrelated, and higher intelligence. There are no bonuses, so the duration factor is 0 for this change.\nPOLYMORPH OBJECT—TABLE 2 (MAGIC USER LEVEL 8)\n0 — 20 rounds — Pebble to human\n2 — 1 hour — Marionette to human\n4 — 3 hours — Human to marionette\n5 — 12 hours — Lizard to manticore\n6 — 48 hours — Sheep to woolen cloak\n7 — 1 week — Shrew to manticore\n9+ — Permanent — Manticore to shrew\nLiving creatures subjected to this spell must make a system shock check (See Table 1.1.4a).","notes":"This spell allows you to transform one thing, living or not, into another sort of thing. If the spell is used simply to duplicate the effects of a polymorph other spell or a stone to flesh spell, it will function in the same manner as these spells but with a -4 penalty to the victim’s saving throw. Otherwise, the spell’s duration depends upon the degree of change involved in the transformation. The calculation is made using a “duration factor” found on table 1, and the explanation of the resulting duration factor is found on table 2.\nDetails\nPOLYMORPH OBJECT—TABLE 1 (MAGIC USER LEVEL 8)\nCHANGED SUBJECT IS: — INCREASE TO DURATION FACTOR\nSame kingdom (animal, vegetable, mineral) — +5\nSame class (mammals, fungi, metals, etc.) — +2\nSame size — +2\nRelated (twig is to tree, wolf fur is to wolf, etc.) — +2\nSame or lower intelligence — +2\nAdd all that apply. Look up the total on the next table.\nExample 1: Changing a dog to a wolf. Same kingdom (+5), the same class (+2), possibly not the same size, but related (+2) and the same intelligence (+2). The duration factor would be 11.\nExample 2: Changing a mushroom into a dragon. Different kingdom, different class, different size, unrelated, and higher intelligence. There are no bonuses, so the duration factor is 0 for this change.\nPOLYMORPH OBJECT—TABLE 2 (MAGIC USER LEVEL 8)\n0 — 20 rounds — Pebble to human\n2 — 1 hour — Marionette to human\n4 — 3 hours — Human to marionette\n5 — 12 hours — Lizard to manticore\n6 — 48 hours — Sheep to woolen cloak\n7 — 1 week — Shrew to manticore\n9+ — Permanent — Manticore to shrew\nLiving creatures subjected to this spell must make a system shock check (See Table 1.1.4a).","link":""},"power word blind":{"name":"Power Word, Blind","level":"8","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"½” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"3” diameter","components":"V","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Power Word, Blind\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” diameter\nThis spell temporarily blinds one or more creatures within range and area of effect. It affects up to 100 total hit points of creatures. If 50 or fewer hit points are affected, blindness lasts 1d4+1 turns. If 51 or more hit points are affected, blindness lasts 1d4+1 rounds. The caster must identify the creatures to affect and designate one as the center before results are determined. Creatures with more than 100 hit points are unaffected. Blindness can be removed by cure blindness or dispel magic.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"siartan s spell immunity":{"name":"Siartan’S Spell Immunity","level":"8","school":"RANGE Touch","range":"","duration":"1 turn/level, divided among recipients","aoe":"One creature/4 MU levels","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round/recipient","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"A creature warded by this spell gains a +8 bonus to saving throws against any magical attack that affects the mind.\nDetails\nYou may divide the spell’s duration among as many recipients as your caster level divided by four. The material component for this spell is a gem of any kind or size (but at least 25gp).","notes":"A creature warded by this spell gains a +8 bonus to saving throws against any magical attack that affects the mind.\nDetails\nYou may divide the spell’s duration among as many recipients as your caster level divided by four. The material component for this spell is a gem of any kind or size (but at least 25gp).","link":""},"symbol":{"name":"Symbol","level":"8","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Symbol\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates magical runes that affect creatures that pass over, touch, read, or pass through a portal bearing the symbol. The caster chooses one symbol when casting. Death: Slays one or more creatures whose total hit points do not exceed 80. Discord: Affects all creatures, causing loud bickering and arguing. There is a 50% chance creatures of different alignment attack one another. Bickering lasts 5d4 rounds, and fighting lasts 2d4 rounds. Fear: Functions as an especially strong fear spell, causing creatures to save at -4 or panic and flee. Hopelessness: Affects all creatures, forcing them to turn back in dejection unless they save. Affected creatures submit to opponent demands, such as surrendering or leaving. The effect lasts 3d4 turns; during that time, each round there is a 25% chance an affected creature takes no action and a 25% chance a creature attempting action turns back or retires from battle. Insanity: One or more creatures whose total hit points do not exceed 120 become insane and act as if under confusion until heal, restoration, or wish removes the madness. Pain: All creatures suffer wracking pain, causing -2 Dexterity and -4 on attack rolls for 2d10 turns. Sleep: All creatures under 8+1 Hit Dice fall into catatonic slumber and cannot be awakened for 1d12+4 turns. Stunning: One or more creatures whose total hit points do not exceed 160 are stunned and reeling for 3d4 rounds, dropping anything held. The type of symbol cannot be recognized without reading it, which activates it. Material Components: Powdered black opal and diamond dust worth at least 5,000 gp each.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"trap the soul":{"name":"Trap The Soul","level":"8","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent until broken","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special + 1 segment","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Trap The Soul\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: Special + 1 segment\nDuration: Permanent until broken\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell is similar to magic jar, but forces the subject’s life force and material body, if any, into a specially prepared magical prison. The caster must see the subject and know its true name when the final word is spoken. Before casting, the magic-user must prepare the soul prison: a gem worth 1,000 gp per Hit Die or level of the target, enchanted with enchant an item and then filled with a maze spell. The soul may be trapped in two ways. First, the caster may speak the final word while the target is within range; the target may apply magic resistance and receives a saving throw versus magic, and if the save succeeds, the gem shatters. Second, the caster may trick the victim into accepting a trigger object inscribed with the final spell word. If this method is used, the trigger item must be named when the prison gem is enchanted, and sympathy may be placed on it. When the target picks up or accepts the trigger item, its soul is automatically transferred to the gem. The gem holds the soul indefinitely, or until broken. If a powerful creature from another plane is trapped, it may be required to perform one service immediately upon release. Otherwise, the creature goes free when the gem is broken.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 9th Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"astral spell":{"name":"Astral Spell","level":"9","school":"Evocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Astral Spell\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 7th-level cleric spell astral spell.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"biccby s crushing hand":{"name":"Biccby’S Crushing Hand","level":"9","school":"RANGE 5ft/MU level","range":"","duration":"1 round/MU level","aoe":"See below","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"This spell calls into existence a large, floating hand much like that summoned by the other hand spells. The crushing hand attacks any foe you direct it to, grabbing it and squeezing with great power.\nDetails\nThe hand does not need to make an attack roll, and there is no saving throw. The hand inflicts 1d10 points of blunt damage in the first round, 2d10 points of damage in the second and third round, and 4d10 points of damage per round thereafter. You can direct the hand to change targets, but if you do, the damage it inflicts starts over at 1d10 in the first round. As with the other hand spells, the hand has as many hit points as its caster. The caster cannot engage in any other activity while directing the hand.","notes":"This spell calls into existence a large, floating hand much like that summoned by the other hand spells. The crushing hand attacks any foe you direct it to, grabbing it and squeezing with great power.\nDetails\nThe hand does not need to make an attack roll, and there is no saving throw. The hand inflicts 1d10 points of blunt damage in the first round, 2d10 points of damage in the second and third round, and 4d10 points of damage per round thereafter. You can direct the hand to change targets, but if you do, the damage it inflicts starts over at 1d10 in the first round. As with the other hand spells, the hand has as many hit points as its caster. The caster cannot engage in any other activity while directing the hand.","link":""},"gate":{"name":"Gate","level":"9","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"3”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Gate\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 7th-level cleric spell gate.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"imprisonment":{"name":"Imprisonment","level":"9","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Imprisonment\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Freedom\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell entombs the touched victim in suspended animation inside a small sphere far below the earth’s surface. The victim remains there unless the reverse, freedom, is cast with the creature’s name and background. Magical searches such as crystal balls, locate object, or similar means do not reveal that the creature is imprisoned. Freedom returns the victim to the spot where they were entombed and sunk into the earth. If the caster does not perfectly know the name and background of the creature to be freed, there is a 10% chance that 1d100 other imprisoned creatures are freed at the same time. The spell works only if the victim’s name and background are known.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"meteor swarm":{"name":"Meteor Swarm","level":"9","school":"Evocation","range":"4” + 1” per level","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Meteor Swarm\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 4” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spectacular spell resembles fireball in many respects. The caster creates either four 2-foot-diameter spheres or eight 1-foot-diameter spheres that streak in straight lines from the caster’s outstretched hand to the chosen range. Any creature directly in a meteor’s path takes the missile’s full effect with no saving throw. Each meteor leaves a fiery trail and bursts like a fireball. The four large meteors each deal 10d4 damage and burst in a diamond or box pattern. Each has a 3” diameter area of effect, and each sphere is 2” from the others along the pattern’s sides, creating overlapping blast areas. The center is exposed to all four blasts. The eight small meteors each deal 5d4 damage with a 1½” diameter area. They burst in a box-within-diamond or diamond-within-box pattern, with outer sides 2” long and inner sides 1” long. The center has four overlapping areas, and many peripheral areas have two overlapping areas. Creatures in each blast area save separately for half damage, except for direct missile impacts.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"monster summoning vii":{"name":"Monster Summoning VII","level":"9","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"9”","duration":"8 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Monster Summoning VII\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 9”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 8 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons 1 or 2 7th-level monsters, which appear 1 round after casting, or one 8th-level monster, which appears 2 rounds after casting. See monster summoning I for other details.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"power word kill":{"name":"Power Word, Kill","level":"9","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"¼” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"2” diameter","components":"V","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Power Word, Kill\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V\nRange: ¼” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2” diameter\nWhen this spell is uttered, one or more creatures within range and area are slain. The spell can kill one creature with up to 60 hit points, or kill multiple creatures with 10 or fewer hit points each, up to a combined maximum of 120 hit points. The caster must state whether the spell is being used against one creature or multiple creatures, along with the range and area center.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"prismatic sphere":{"name":"Prismatic Sphere","level":"9","school":"Abjuration, Conjuration/Summoning","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"2” diameter sphere","components":"V","ct":"7 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Prismatic Sphere\n\nSchool: Abjuration, Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 2” diameter sphere\nThis spell surrounds the caster with an opaque globe of shimmering, multicolored light that protects against all forms of attack. The sphere flashes all seven colors of the visible spectrum, each with a different power. Creatures with fewer than 8 Hit Dice are blinded by the colors for 2d4 turns. The sphere is immobile, and only the caster can pass through it safely. Usually only the upper hemisphere is visible because the caster stands at the center and the lower half is hidden by the floor. Anything entering the sphere is subject to every globe in order: 70 total damage plus possible death, petrification, insanity, and/or transportation to another plane. Only the latter four effects allow saving throws. A rod of cancellation destroys the whole sphere. Otherwise, individual globes must be destroyed in order, from red through violet.\n\nColor\tOrder\tEffect\tNegated By\nRed\t1st\tPrevents all nonmagical missiles; inflicts 10 damage\tCone of cold\nOrange\t2nd\tPrevents all magical missiles; inflicts 20 damage\tGust of wind\nYellow\t3rd\tPrevents poison, gases, and petrification; inflicts 40 damage\tDisintegrate\nGreen\t4th\tPrevents all breath weapons; save vs. poison or die\tPasswall\nBlue\t5th\tPrevents location, detection, and psionics; save vs. petrification or turn to stone\tMagic missile\nIndigo\t6th\tPrevents all magical spells; save vs. wand or become insane\tContinual light\nViolet\t7th\tForce field protection; save vs. magic or be sent to another plane\tDispel magic","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"shape change":{"name":"Shape Change","level":"9","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"The spellcaster","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Shape Change\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The spellcaster\nThis spell allows the magic-user to assume the form of nearly any creature short of a demigod, greater devil, demon prince, unique dragon, greater demon, or similar being. The caster gains all abilities of the new form except those dependent on Intelligence, since the caster retains their own mind. The caster may change repeatedly during the duration, with each change requiring 1 segment. No system shock roll is required. The caster keeps their own current hit points in each form. For example, the caster may become a will-o’-wisp, then a stone golem, then a flea, then a bush, then a dragon or pool of water. Material Component: A jade circlet worth at least 5,000 gp, which shatters when the spell ends. If it shatters early, the spell is dispelled.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"temporal stasis":{"name":"Temporal Stasis","level":"9","school":"Alteration","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Temporal Stasis\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Temporal Reinstatement\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell places the recipient in suspended animation. Time stops for the creature, so it does not age and its bodily functions virtually cease. The state persists until removed by dispel magic or by the reverse, temporal reinstatement. The reverse requires only a single word and no somatic or material components. Material Component: A powder made from diamond, emerald, ruby, and sapphire dust, requiring one stone of each type.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"time stop":{"name":"Time Stop","level":"9","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"½ segment per level + 1d8 segments","aoe":"3” diameter sphere","components":"V","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Time Stop\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: ½ segment per level + 1d8 segments\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” diameter sphere\nThis spell stops time within the area of effect. Outside the sphere, the area merely seems to shimmer for an instant. During the subjective duration, the caster may move and act freely inside the stopped area, while all other creatures there are frozen between ticks of time. Any creature entering the area is also stopped. If the caster leaves the area, the spell immediately ends. When the duration expires, the caster returns to normal time.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"wish":{"name":"Wish","level":"9","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Unlimited","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"Special","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Wish\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V\nRange: Unlimited\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is a more powerful version of limited wish. Using it to alter reality with respect to hit points sustained by a party, bring a dead character back to life, or escape a difficult situation by moving the caster and party elsewhere does not harm the caster. Other wishes make the caster weak, imposing -3 Strength, and require 2d4 days of bed rest because of the stress placed on time, space, and the caster’s body. The exact wording of the wish is likely to be fulfilled literally, and the referee interprets the result to preserve game balance. For example, wishing another character dead might instead send the caster to a future time when that character is no longer alive.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"augury":{"name":"Augury","level":"2","school":"Divine divination","range":"Caster","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Caster","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Augury\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 2 rounds\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nThe cleric casting an augury spell seeks to divine whether an action in the immediate future, within 3 turns, will benefit or harm the party. The base chance for correctly divining the augury is 70%, plus 1% per caster level. For example, the chance is 71% at 1st level, 72% at 2nd level, and so on. The referee determines any adjustments based on the conditions of the augury. For example, if a party is considering destroying a weird seal that closes a portal, augury may be used to determine whether weal or woe will result for the party. Material Component: A set of gem-inlaid sticks, dragon bones, similar tokens, or wet infusion leaves left in a container after the infused brew is consumed. If the infusion method is used, a crushed pearl worth at least 100 g.p. must be added before the brew is consumed.","notes":"Your instruments of divination respond to a question about what might happen in the near future, based on a proposed course of action. The results are vague, and there is a chance of an inaccurate reading.\nDetails:\n    When you finish casting, the GM secretly rolls to see if you interpret the omen correctly. Your chance of success is 70% + 1% per cleric level. If you fail, the GM provides a random inaccurate answer instead of the accurate one.\n    You must have instruments of divination worth at least 100 gp (e.g., dragon-bone or gold sticks, crystal ball, entrails of a sacrifice, tarot cards, or other culturally/religiously appropriate means approved by the GM).\n    You must ask about a specific course of action you plan to take within the next 30 minutes. The response is one of:\n        Weal (generally favourable)\n        Woe (generally unfavourable)\n        Weal and woe (mixed results)\n        Nothing (not especially favourable or unfavourable)\n    The worlds of OSRIC aren’t deterministic; divination reveals what is likely, not what is certain.","link":""},"chant":{"name":"Chant","level":"2","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Nil","duration":"Continuing","aoe":"30 ft radius around the point where you were standing when you finished casting","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Chant\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Time of chanting\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” radius\nBy means of chant, the cleric brings special favor upon themselves and their party while causing harm to enemies. Once the spell is completed, all attacks, damage rolls, and saving throws made by friendly creatures in the area of effect gain a +1 bonus, while those made by the cleric’s enemies suffer a -1 penalty. This bonus and penalty continue as long as the cleric remains stationary and continues chanting the mystic syllables. Any interruption, such as a successful damaging attack, grappling, or magical silence, breaks the spell.","notes":"You chant holy words and prayers. After the first round (casting time), and for as long as you remain stationary and continue chanting, your allies receive minor divine assistance and enemies are obstructed.\nDetails:\n    The chanting makes a moderate amount of sound: heard within 30 ft, and heard as far as 60 ft on a 1d6 roll of 5–6.\n    The spell’s effects are cumulative with prayer.\n    While the spell continues, the following apply within the area:\n        You and your allies may choose to gain +1 to attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws.\n        Enemies suffer -1 to attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws.","link":""},"conceal alignment":{"name":"Conceal Alignment","level":"2","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"depends on number of targets:","aoe":"1 to 10 creatures, objects, or places","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"You obscure the alignments of a number of targets, causing detect evil, detect good, and know alignment to perceive them as neutral.\nDetails:\n    Also fools special abilities that detect alignment (e.g., monsters with such abilities, a paladin’s detect evil).\nTargets\tDuration\n1\t1 turn\n2\t5 rounds\n3\t3 rounds\n4–5\t2 rounds\n6–10\t1 round","notes":"You obscure the alignments of a number of targets, causing detect evil, detect good, and know alignment to perceive them as neutral.\nDetails:\n    Also fools special abilities that detect alignment (e.g., monsters with such abilities, a paladin’s detect evil).\nTargets\tDuration\n1\t1 turn\n2\t5 rounds\n3\t3 rounds\n4–5\t2 rounds\n6–10\t1 round","link":""},"conceal charm":{"name":"Conceal Charm","level":"2","school":"Divine enchantment","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 turn","aoe":"One creature within range","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Until this spell ends, detect charm, detect magic, and other magical divinations do not reveal this or any other enchantment spells that you cast on the target. Such divinations still reveal enchantments cast by others.\nDetails:\n    This spell hides your enchantments from magical detection; non-magical questioning/testing is unaffected.\n    The concealment can be cast before or after the actual charm, but the duration begins immediately even if the charm has not yet been cast.\n    Psychic/psionic mind-reading may or may not count as “magical” (GM’s decision).","notes":"Until this spell ends, detect charm, detect magic, and other magical divinations do not reveal this or any other enchantment spells that you cast on the target. Such divinations still reveal enchantments cast by others.\nDetails:\n    This spell hides your enchantments from magical detection; non-magical questioning/testing is unaffected.\n    The concealment can be cast before or after the actual charm, but the duration begins immediately even if the charm has not yet been cast.\n    Psychic/psionic mind-reading may or may not count as “magical” (GM’s decision).","link":""},"detect charm":{"name":"Detect Charm","level":"2","school":"Divine divination","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 turn","aoe":"Up to 10 creatures within range","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"Detect Charm\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Protect From Charm Detection\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 turn\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nWhen used by a cleric, this spell detects whether a person or monster is under the influence of a charm spell. Up to 10 creatures may be checked before the spell ends. The reverse protects against such detection, but only one creature may be shielded.","notes":"An aura, visible only to you, forms around any creature in the area of effect that is being magically influenced or controlled. In some cases, a saving throw applies.\nDetails:\n    This spell reveals magical control or influence; it does not detect non-magical persuasion, propaganda, or deception.\n    If the target is affected by a charm spell, there is no saving throw.\n    If the target is dominated by a monster ability other than a charm, the target may attempt a saving throw vs spells; on a success, the influence is not revealed.\n    Psychic/psionic domination may or may not count as “magical” (GM’s decision).\n    If a creature is invisible, you know its location but not details. Attack rolls against it halve the normal invisible-target penalty (usually -2 instead of -4).\nReversible as Conceal Charm:","link":""},"find traps":{"name":"Find Traps","level":"2","school":"Divine divination","range":"30 ft","duration":"3 turns","aoe":"10 ft wide path originating from you","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Find Traps\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 3 turns\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” path\nWhen a cleric casts find traps, all traps, whether normally concealed, magically concealed, magical, or mechanical, become visible to the cleric. This spell is directional, so the caster must face the desired direction to determine whether a trap lies that way.","notes":"This spell reveals the presence of magical and mechanical traps within the area of effect. Only you perceive the exact location of each trap (and its trigger if within the area). You also learn the basic threat the trap represents.\nDetails:\n    For this spell, a “trap” is anything non-creature that would have an unexpected and undesirable effect (GM adjudication). Examples: poison needle in a lock, tripwire to a bell, a weak floor, glyph of warding.\n    Only the basic nature is revealed; specifics (poison type, pit depth, etc.) are up to the GM.\n    If the trap is magical or concealed by magic, there is a 10% chance per cleric level you can detect the involved school of magic.\n    The spell does not detect creatures and does not teach disarming/avoidance.","link":""},"know alignment":{"name":"Know Alignment","level":"2","school":"Divination","range":"1”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"One creature per 2 rounds","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Know Alignment\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Yes\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature per 2 rounds\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 2nd-level clerical spell of the same name. If a target is examined for only 1 round, only its ethical alignment, law or chaos, is discerned.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"resist fire":{"name":"Resist Fire","level":"2","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per cleric level","aoe":"1 creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Resist Fire\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell toughens the recipient’s body against heat, making boiling temperatures comfortable. The recipient can even stand amid very hot or magical fires, such as red-hot charcoal, large amounts of burning oil, flaming swords, fire storms, fire balls, meteor swarms, or red dragon breath, though such effects still harm the creature to some extent. The recipient gains a +3 bonus on saving throws against such attacks. Fire damage is reduced by 50%, so a failed saving throw results in half damage, and a successful saving throw results in one-quarter damage. The spell lasts 1 turn per caster level. Material Component: A drop of mercury.","notes":"Protects the target against fire damage and heat.\nDetails:\n    Safe from non-magical fire (e.g., torches).\n    Immune to ill effects of normal heat (up to boiling).\n    Against magical or extremely hot fire, grants:\n        Provides Saving Throw: May attempt a saving throw against any magical fire effect even if none is normally allowed (typically vs spells and other magical effects).\n        Improves Saving Throw: If already allowed a save vs fire damage, may choose to add +3.\n        Reduces Damage: Fire damage is halved; if already halved (e.g., successful save), halve again. Round down.","link":""},"silence 15 ft radius":{"name":"Silence 15 Ft Radius","level":"2","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"120 ft","duration":"2 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"15 ft radius sphere around the target","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"Silence, 15’ Radius\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 30’ diameter sphere\nWhen this spell is cast, complete silence fills the area of effect. All sound stops, conversation becomes impossible, spells cannot be cast, and no noise issues from the affected area. The spell may be cast into the air or upon an object. It lasts 2 rounds per caster level: 2 rounds at 1st level, 4 at 2nd level, 6 at 3rd level, 8 at 4th level, and so on. The spell may also be cast upon a creature, causing the silence to radiate from and move with that creature. If the creature is unwilling, it receives a saving throw. If the save succeeds, the spell effect is centered about 1 foot behind the target creature.","notes":"Creates a zone of silence centred on a creature, object, or point in space. Within the area:\n    No sound can be produced; and\n    No sound can be heard, even from outside the zone.\nDetails:\n    Objects and points in space receive no saving throw.\n    A creature target may choose a saving throw vs spells and other magical effects:\n        Success: the target becomes the 5 ft square the creature is standing in (the creature can move out).\n        Failure: the creature remains the target; the silence moves with it.\n    Combat effects:\n        No one can cast spells with a verbal component within the area.\n        Attempts to sneak or move quietly always succeed if the creature is within the area.\n        Echolocation-dependent creatures (e.g., bats, dolphins) are blinded and suffer -4 “to hit”.","link":""},"slow poison":{"name":"Slow Poison","level":"2","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns per cleric level","aoe":"1 creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Fast","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Slow Poison\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 hour per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nWhen cast upon a poisoned individual, this spell greatly slows the effects of venom. It can even temporarily restore life to a supposedly dead victim if cast within a number of turns after poisoning equal to or less than the cleric’s level. For example, a victim poisoned up to 10 turns earlier could be temporarily saved by a 10th-level or higher cleric. The spell does not neutralize the venom, but it prevents substantial harm for the spell’s duration. Each turn, the poisoned creature loses 1 hit point from the venom, though the victim will never fall below 1 hit point while the spell lasts. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol and a bud of garlic, which must be crushed and smeared on the victim’s bare feet.","notes":"Slows the effects of poison to keep someone alive until the poison can be neutralised (e.g., antidote or neutralise poison).\nDetails:\nPoison is often treated as “save or die,” but death is not instantaneous. This spell can slow poison and keep a victim alive within a time window determined by cleric level.\n    Target poisoned but not dead:\n    Record poison damage taken at the moment of casting; this is “slowed damage.”\n    Slowed damage is healed immediately when the spell is cast.\n    During the duration, the creature takes 1 hp poison damage every 10 rounds, but cannot be reduced below 1 hp by this poison damage until the spell ends.\n    Other (non-poison) damage applies normally.\n    Target recently dead from poison:\n    A creature counts as “recently died of poison” if it died from poison damage or from failing a save vs poison within a number of turns equal to your cleric level.\n    The creature is restored to life at the hit points it had before the poison affected it.\n    During the duration, it takes 1 hp poison damage every 10 rounds, but cannot be reduced below 1 hp by this poison damage until the spell ends.\n    Other damage applies normally.\nAdditional poison during duration:\n    Additional poison damage is not applied immediately; record it as additional slowed damage.\n    If the creature fails further saves vs poison, those poison effects are also delayed until the spell ends.\n    If the poison is not cured by the time the spell expires, all slowed poisons take full effect immediately, including the full amount of slowed damage.","link":""},"snake charm":{"name":"Snake Charm","level":"2","school":"Divine enchantment","range":"30 ft","duration":"2 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"One animal within range","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Snake Charm\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nWhen this spell is cast, it creates a hypnotic pattern that causes one or more snakes to cease all activity except a semi-erect swaying motion. If the snakes are charmed while torpid, the spell lasts 3 to 6 turns, or d4 + 2. If the snakes are not torpid but are also not aroused or angry, the charm lasts 1 to 3 turns. If the snakes are angry and/or attacking, the charm lasts 5 to 8 melee rounds, or d4 + 4. The cleric may charm snakes whose total hit points are less than or equal to the cleric’s own hit points. The hit points may belong to one snake or several snakes, but the total may not exceed the cleric’s hit points.","notes":"Affects snakes, serpents, couatls, nagas, and other ophidian/serpentine creatures: they rear up and sway without otherwise moving, taking no actions and not attacking until the spell ends. When it ends, they forget what occurred while affected.\nDetails:\n    Total hit points of affected creatures cannot exceed your uninjured hit points. If you target more, the GM decides (or randomly determines) which are unaffected until the total affected hp is within your limit.\n    If in doubt, affected creatures include those listed above and other reptilian creatures that had no limbs when hatched. Not affected: dragons, demons, devils, wyverns.\n        Asleep/unconscious: 1d4 + 2 turns\n        Alert: 1d3 turns\n        Angry/attacking: 1d4 + 4 rounds\n    Attacking a charmed snake breaks the charm on that snake only.\nSPEAK WITH ANIMALS\nClerical transmutation, level 2\nAllows communication with a nearby animal.\nDetails:\n    You speak in Common; the animal understands magically. The animal communicates in its natural way; meaning is translated into your mind (others do not hear the translation).\n    You may attempt persuasion, deception, or bargaining for services.\n    Affects normal non-fantastic animals (wolves, badgers, bears) and giant versions without additional fantastic abilities (e.g., giant lizard yes; basilisk no).\n    Mindless animals (INT “non” or 0) are not affected. The animal must have intelligence of animal, semi-, or low.\n    Humans are not animals for this spell.\n    The spell does not compel truth, and it does not force the animal to stop fighting if you/your allies attacked it, though it usually won’t initiate combat while the spell is in effect.","link":""},"speak with animals":{"name":"Speak With Animals","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"One animal within 3” radius of cleric","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Speak With Animals\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One animal within 3” radius of cleric\nThis spell allows the cleric to comprehend and communicate with any warm- or cold-blooded animal that is not mindless, such as an amoeba. The cleric may ask questions, receive answers, and generally remain on amicable terms with the animal. The ability lasts 2 melee rounds per caster level. Even if the animal’s bent is opposite to the cleric’s, such as evil/good or good/evil, it and others of its kind will not attack while the spell lasts. If the animal is neutral or of the same general bent as the cleric, such as evil/evil or good/good, it may perform some favor or service. The referee determines this possibility using a special reaction chart, with the cleric’s charisma and actions as major factors. This spell differs from speak with monsters, because it allows conversation only with basically normal, non-fantastic creatures such as apes, bears, cats, dogs, and elephants.","notes":"","link":""},"spiritual weapon":{"name":"Spiritual Weapon","level":"2","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"30 ft radius around you","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Spiritual Hammer\n\nSchool: Invocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One opponent\nBy calling upon their deity, the cleric creates a hammer-shaped field of force. As long as the cleric concentrates, the force may strike any opponent within range as desired. The force strikes as a magical weapon equal to +1 per 3 caster levels for purposes of hitting creatures that require magical weapons, though it gains no magical bonuses “to hit.” It deals the same damage as a normal war hammer: 1d6 against man-sized or smaller opponents, and 1d4 against larger opponents. The hammer attacks at the cleric’s own level, as if the cleric were personally wielding it. When the cleric stops concentrating, the hammer is dispelled. If the cleric is behind an opponent, the force may strike from that position, gaining applicable bonuses and negating defensive protections such as shield and Dexterity. Material Component: A normal war hammer, which the cleric hurls toward opponents while uttering a plea to their deity. The hammer disappears when the spell is cast.","notes":"Creates a magical force shaped like a weapon (usually a hammer; may match your deity’s sacred weapon). It cannot move more than 30 ft from you, but within that radius it attacks where you direct it.\nDetails:\n    Each round until the spell ends, you may attack one creature within range using the spiritual weapon. Roll to hit as if using a regular weapon.\n    On a hit, it deals 1d6 magical damage (not blunt/piercing/slashing; can harm creatures immune to mundane weapons, and isn’t treated as a “weapon” for those purposes).\n    The weapon is not physical and can pass through obstacles (including walls) as long as it stays within the area.\n    If you direct it to attack a target you can’t see, you are effectively blinded with respect to that target.\n    If it attacks from behind, it gains the normal rear-attack bonus (usually +2).\n    You must concentrate to maintain the spell, or it ends (see Concentration rules).","link":""},"bestow curse":{"name":"Bestow Curse","level":"3","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"1 creature","components":"V, S","ct":"6 segments","save":"Yes (negates effect)","save_type":"","description":"Remove Curse\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Bestow Curse\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell usually removes a curse from an object, person, undesired sending, or evil presence. It does not affect a cursed shield, weapon, or suit of armor directly, though it typically enables the afflicted person to get rid of such an item. The reverse, bestow curse, is not permanent and lasts 1 turn per caster level. It lowers one randomly selected ability score to 3 half the time; reduces the victim’s “to hit” and saving throw probabilities by -4 one-quarter of the time; or gives the victim a 50% chance each turn to drop whatever they are holding, or do nothing if not using tools, one-quarter of the time. A cleric may devise another curse of similar power, subject to the referee. The target must be touched and receives a saving throw; success negates the curse.","notes":"Places a curse on the target.\nDetails:\n    A creature can only be affected by one instance of this spell at a time.\n    Many good-aligned religions forbid this spell; others allow it only in dire need.\n    On a successful curse, roll 1d8:\nRoll\tEffect\n1–4\tOne ability score reduced to 3\n5–6\t-4 to attack rolls and saving throws\n7–8\tClumsy: each round, 50% chance to drop each held object; if holding nothing, 50% chance it can’t act that round\nThe curse remains until removed by remove curse, dispelled, or revoked by the caster.\nOptional rule: some religions may have alternative curses (cult secrets, lost secrets, forbidden secrets), learned through donations, service, research, extraplanar consultation, or major quests (GM decides availability and effects).","link":""},"cause blindness":{"name":"Cause Blindness","level":"3","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"8 segments","save":"Yes (negates effect)","save_type":"","description":"Cure Blindness\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Cause Blindness\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nBy touching the afflicted creature, the cleric can permanently cure most forms of blindness. The reverse, cause blindness, requires a successful touch upon the victim. If the victim then makes the saving throw, the effect is negated.","notes":"Causes a target to become blind until removed by the caster, dispelled, or cured by cure blindness.\nDetails:\n    If you miss the to-hit roll, the spell is lost.\n    Affects only living creatures (not undead) and has no effect on creatures that do not rely on vision.\n    Many good-aligned religions forbid this spell; others allow it only in dire need.","link":""},"cause disease":{"name":"Cause Disease","level":"3","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"10 rounds","save":"Negates effect","save_type":"","description":"Cure Disease\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Cause Disease\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThe cleric cures most diseases, including parasitic, bacterial, and viral diseases, by placing their hand upon the diseased creature. The affliction rapidly disappears thereafter, making the creature whole and well in from 1 turn to 1 week, depending on the disease and its advancement when cured. The reverse, cause disease, requires the cleric to touch the intended victim, who must then fail a saving throw. The disease begins to affect the victim in 1d6 turns, causing the creature to lose 1 hit point per turn and 1 point of Strength per hour until reduced to 10% of original hit points and Strength, at which point the creature is weak and virtually helpless.","notes":"Infects the target with a disease.\nDetails:\n    Requires touch (to-hit roll if resisting and not immobilised). Even on a successful touch, the target saves vs spells; success negates.\n    Affects only normally living creatures; no effect on constructs, elementals, golems, undead.\n    Takes effect 1d6 turns after casting. After it takes effect:\n        The target takes 1 hp disease damage every turn (10 rounds). Each time it takes this damage, its maximum hp is reduced by 1. This damage cannot reduce it below 1 hp, and cannot reduce maximum hp below 8 hp.\n        Every hour after it takes effect, the target suffers -1 cumulative to attack rolls and damage rolls (cannot reduce damage below 1).\n    You may end the spell at any time; if you die, the target is cured.\n    Many good-aligned religions forbid this spell; others allow it only in dire need.","link":""},"continual darkness":{"name":"Continual Darkness","level":"3","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"120 ft","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Globe, 60 ft radius","components":"V, S","ct":"6 segments","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"Continual Light\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Continual Darkness\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6” radius globe\nThis spell is similar to light, except it lasts until negated by continual darkness or dispel magic, and its brightness is very great, nearly equal to full daylight. It may be cast into the air, onto an object, or at a creature. If cast at a creature and the creature makes its saving throw, the spell affects the space about 1 foot behind the creature. This spell can blind a creature if successfully cast upon the visual organs. The reverse causes complete absence of light.","notes":"Creates divine darkness emanating from the target (creature, object, or point in space). Light—including sunlight—does not illuminate anything within 60 ft of the target.\nDetails:\n    If cast into an area of magical light (e.g., within a light spell radius), both spells are cancelled.\n    Darkness is stationary unless cast on a moving creature/object, in which case it moves with the target.\n    You may target a creature’s eyes or other sense organs. If it fails its save (or declines to save), it is blinded for the duration. The creature applies its Dexterity save modifier (if any) to the saving throw.\n        Success: Darkness appears as a stationary point just behind the target instead of affecting it.\n    Same limitations as continual light (max 3 concurrent instances; monthly 1-in-12 chance to end).\n    Optional rule: some GMs allow infravision to see through divine darkness (cleric-slot darkness only).","link":""},"create food and water":{"name":"Create Food and Water","level":"3","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"10 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"See below","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Create Food & Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per level\nWhen this spell is cast, the cleric causes food and/or water to appear. The food is highly nourishing, and each cubic foot sustains three human-sized creatures or one horse-sized creature for a full day. The spell creates 1 cubic foot of food and/or water per caster level. For example, a 2nd-level cleric creates 2 cubic feet, a 3rd-level cleric creates 3 cubic feet, a 4th-level cleric creates 4 cubic feet, and so on. The created volume may be divided between food and water.","notes":"Conjures basic food and water from thin air. You choose the form of the food, but it is plain fare.\nDetails:\n    Food is safe when conjured but spoils normally thereafter.\n    For each cleric level, you conjure up to one day’s rations for one human-sized creature.\n    The target point can’t be inside a creature.","link":""},"cure blindness":{"name":"Cure Blindness","level":"3","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Blindness\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Cause Blindness\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nBy touching the afflicted creature, the cleric can permanently cure most forms of blindness. The reverse, cause blindness, requires a successful touch upon the victim. If the victim then makes the saving throw, the effect is negated.","notes":"Cures blindness in one living creature, subject to limitations. Typically only effective for magically induced blindness (e.g., curses, cause blindness).\nDetails:\n    Restores sight only to the extent the creature’s eyes allow; it does not repair destroyed/damaged eyes. A creature whose eyes were put out gains no benefit.\n    Does not cure blindness that exists in the mind (e.g., believing it is blind due to an illusion); does not remove hallucinations from false seeing.\n    Does not remove environmental obstruction (fog/darkness), though it does remove light or continual light cast on the eyes.\nReversible as Cause Blindness:","link":""},"cure disease":{"name":"Cure Disease","level":"3","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Disease\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Cause Disease\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThe cleric cures most diseases, including parasitic, bacterial, and viral diseases, by placing their hand upon the diseased creature. The affliction rapidly disappears thereafter, making the creature whole and well in from 1 turn to 1 week, depending on the disease and its advancement when cured. The reverse, cause disease, requires the cleric to touch the intended victim, who must then fail a saving throw. The disease begins to affect the victim in 1d6 turns, causing the creature to lose 1 hit point per turn and 1 point of Strength per hour until reduced to 10% of original hit points and Strength, at which point the creature is weak and virtually helpless.","notes":"Cures all diseases affecting the target (see details). Full recovery may take up to a week.\nDetails:\n    Stops the “will die in X days” progression immediately; the target is no longer at risk of dying from disease, even if not yet back to full strength.\n    Cures physical pathologies and removes physical parasites. Does not cure genetic conditions/birth defects; affects mental health only insofar as curing underlying pathology/parasites helps.\n    Affects only normally living creatures; no effect on constructs, elementals, golems, undead.\n    Cures lycanthropy only if cast before the first transformation. After first change, lycanthropy becomes a mixed disease/curse/magical alteration.\n    The target may choose a saving throw vs spells and other effects; on a success, one or more diseases of its choice are not cured.\n    Has certain special uses that cure non-disease effects in specific OSRIC creature/object entries.\nReversible as Cause Disease:","link":""},"glyph of warding":{"name":"Glyph of Warding","level":"3","school":"Divine evocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Until discharged","aoe":"Up to 25 sq. ft per cleric level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment per sq. ft protected","save":"When activated (save for half)","save_type":"","description":"Glyph of Warding\n\nSchool: Abjuration-Evocation\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Permanent until discharged\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 25 square feet per caster level\nA glyph of warding is a powerful magical inscription that prevents unauthorized or hostile creatures from passing, entering, or opening. It can guard a small bridge, ward an entry, or trap a chest or box. When cast, the cleric weaves faintly glowing lines around the warding sigil. Each square foot of protected area requires 1 segment to trace, plus the initial segment for tracing the sigil itself. A maximum area of 5’ × 5’ per caster level may be warded. When complete, the glyph and tracery become invisible. Any creature touching the protected area without first speaking the glyph’s name is subject to the stored magic. Saving throws either reduce the effect by half or negate it, depending on the glyph. Material Components: Incense for tracing the spell, plus powdered diamond worth at least 2,000 g.p. if the protected area exceeds 50 square feet. Typical glyphs shock for 2 points of electrical damage per caster level, explode for the same amount of fire damage, paralyze, blind, or even drain one life energy level if the cleric is high enough level to cast such a glyph.","notes":"You inscribe an invisible glyph on a solid surface. It remains invisible unless detect magic is used. A “forbidden creature” (as defined at casting) discharges the glyph when it performs a defined triggering action.\nDetails:\n    You must define:\n        A forbidden creature (e.g., “any living being,” “anyone but myself,” “a dwarf,” “Richard the Necrophage,” etc.).\n        A triggering action (typically opening a warded door or passing through a warded area).\n        The exact area to be warded.\n    When triggered, each creature in the area may save vs spells/spell-like effects:\n        Success: half damage and may disregard other glyph effects (if any).\n    You must know the specific glyph you’re using. Fire/lightning/ice/acid glyphs are secrets of clerical orders; blindness/paralysis are lost secrets; drain/petrify/banish are long-lost and widely forbidden, requiring major effort/quests to learn.\n    If warding more than 50 sq. ft, gems worth 2,000 gp must be destroyed as a material component.\n    You can only use glyph types permitted by your cleric level:\nMinimum Cleric Level\tGlyph\tNoise\tEffect\n3\tFire\tNoisy\t2 hp fire damage per cleric level\n5\tLightning\tLoud\t2 hp lightning damage per cleric level\n7\tIce\tQuiet\t2 hp cold damage per cleric level\n9\tAcid\tQuiet\t2 hp corrosion damage per cleric level\n11\tBlindness\tSilent\tSave or blinded for 3d6 rounds\n13\tParalysis\tSilent\tSave or paralysed for 2d6 rounds\n15\tDrain\tSilent\tSave or lose 1 life energy level\n17\tPetrify\tSilent\tSave or turned to stone\n20\tBanish\tSilent\tSave or sent to deity-associated plane","link":""},"prayer":{"name":"Prayer","level":"3","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Nil","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"60 ft radius","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Prayer\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6” radius\nThis spell duplicates the effects of chant regarding bonuses and penalties: friendly creatures gain +1 on attacks and saving throws, while enemies suffer -1 on similar rolls. Unlike chant, once prayer is uttered, the cleric may do other things and need not continue chanting. Material Component: A silver holy symbol, prayer beads, or a similar device.","notes":"The target location is where you stand when casting completes. Until the spell ends, within the area:\n    You and your allies may choose to gain +1 to attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws.\n    Enemies suffer -1 to attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws.\nDetails:\n    Cumulative with chant despite similarity.","link":""},"speak with dead":{"name":"Speak With Dead","level":"3","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"10 ft","duration":"Varies (see table)","aoe":"One corpse","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Speak With Dead\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell allows the cleric to ask several questions of a dead creature within a set period and receive answers according to the creature’s knowledge. The cleric must be able to converse in the language the dead creature used in life. The length of time the creature has been dead, the number of questions allowed, and the time available for questioning depend on the cleric’s level. Up to 7th level: dead up to 1 week, questioned for 1 round, 2 questions. 7th–8th level: dead up to 1 month, questioned for 3 rounds, 3 questions. 9th–12th level: dead up to 1 year, questioned for 1 turn, 4 questions. 13th–15th level: dead up to 10 years, questioned for 2 turns, 5 questions. 16th–20th level: dead up to 100 years, questioned for 3 turns, 6 questions. 21st level and up: dead up to 1,000 years, questioned for 6 turns, 7 questions. Material Components: A holy symbol and burning incense, cast upon the body, remains, or portion thereof.","notes":"Compels a corpse to answer questions aloud (others can hear). Duration, question limit, and maximum corpse age depend on your cleric level.\nLimitations by cleric level:\nCleric Level\tDuration\tMax Questions\tMax Time Since Death\n5–6\t1 round\t2\t1 week\n7–8\t3 rounds\t3\t1 month\n9–12\t1 turn\t4\t1 year\n13–15\t2 turns\t5\t1 decade\n16–19\t3 turns\t6\t1 century\n20\t1 hour\t7\t1 aeon\nDetails:\n    The corpse can only tell what it knew in life.\n    It only speaks languages it knew in life. If it doesn’t understand a question, it can say “I don’t understand,” and this still consumes one question.\n    The spell does not make it friendly. If it was hostile (especially if you killed it), it answers briefly and with minimal information.\n    Multi-part questions get only one part answered (corpse chooses which).\n    Ambiguous questions may be interpreted in any reasonable way (GM adjudication).\n    If the target is undead, it does not have to stop fighting while answering.","link":""},"blither":{"name":"Blither","level":"4","school":"Divine enchantment","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"Yes (negates effect)","save_type":"","description":"Noise: Casting quiet; effect quiet\nRenders a creature’s spoken words meaningless for the duration; it cannot communicate via speech.\nDetails:\n    Target may add its Wisdom saving throw modifier to the saving throw.\n    On failure, it can still gesture, write, and otherwise communicate.\n    The affected creature cannot cast spells with verbal components until the spell ends.","notes":"Noise: Casting quiet; effect quiet\nRenders a creature’s spoken words meaningless for the duration; it cannot communicate via speech.\nDetails:\n    Target may add its Wisdom saving throw modifier to the saving throw.\n    On failure, it can still gesture, write, and otherwise communicate.\n    The affected creature cannot cast spells with verbal components until the spell ends.","link":""},"cause serious wounds":{"name":"Cause Serious Wounds","level":"4","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Serious Wounds\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Cause Serious Wounds\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is a more potent version of cure light wounds. By laying a hand upon a creature, the cleric heals 3 to 17 hit points, or 2d8 + 1, of wound or injury damage. The healing affects only creatures listed in the cure light wounds explanation. The reverse, cause serious wounds, works similarly to cause light wounds: the victim must first be touched, and a successful touch inflicts 3 to 17 hit points of damage.","notes":"The touched target takes 2d8+1 hit points of magical damage, even if it can only be hit by magical weapons. Touching the target requires a successful to-hit roll; no saving throw is allowed.\nDetails:\nIf you miss the to-hit roll, no damage is inflicted and the spell is lost. This spell affects only naturally living creatures and does not affect golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.","link":""},"cure serious wounds":{"name":"Cure Serious Wounds","level":"4","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Serious Wounds\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Cause Serious Wounds\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is a more potent version of cure light wounds. By laying a hand upon a creature, the cleric heals 3 to 17 hit points, or 2d8 + 1, of wound or injury damage. The healing affects only creatures listed in the cure light wounds explanation. The reverse, cause serious wounds, works similarly to cause light wounds: the victim must first be touched, and a successful touch inflicts 3 to 17 hit points of damage.","notes":"The target regains 2d8+1 hit points, up to its normal maximum. Any healing beyond the normal maximum is wasted.\nDetails:\nThis spell cannot cure disease, reattach limbs, raise the dead, or heal afflictions not measured in hit points; such effects require stronger magic. It generally affects only normally living creatures and has no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.\nReversible as Cause Serious Wounds:","link":""},"detect lie":{"name":"Detect Lie","level":"4","school":"Divine divination","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"One creature you designate","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Lie\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Undetectable Lie\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One person\nWhen the cleric casts detect lie, the recipient can immediately determine whether truth is being spoken. The spell lasts 1 round per caster level. The reverse, undetectable lie, makes direct untruths seem reasonable or counters detect lie. Material Component: Gold dust for detect lie; brass dust for undetectable lie.","notes":"Cast upon a specific creature. For the duration, when that creature speaks, you know whether it is saying something it does not believe to be true.\nDetails:\nYour awareness of lies is not detectable by others. The spell affects only speech, not telepathy or writing. You can only detect lies you can hear. Lies spoken in languages you do not know are still detected as lies, but you will not know what was actually said.\nReversible as Glibness:","link":""},"divination":{"name":"Divination","level":"4","school":"Divine divination","range":"Caster","duration":"1 round","aoe":"Caster","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Divination\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nSimilar to augury, this spell determines information about a known area, such as a small woods, large building, or section of a dungeon level. The spell reveals the relative strength of creatures in the area, whether treasure there is rich, moderate, or poor, and the relative chances of incurring the wrath of evil or good supernatural or super-powerful beings if the area is invaded and attacked. The base chance for correct divination is 60% plus 1% per caster level, such as 65% at 5th level and 66% at 6th level. The Dungeon Master adjusts this chance based on the facts of the area. If the result is not correct, inaccurate information is obtained. Material Components: A sacrificial creature, incense, and the cleric’s holy symbol. For unusually potent divinations, especially valuable gems, jewelry, and/or magic items may be required.","notes":"Gives information about a place via divination (bones, yarrow stalks, tea leaves, entrails, etc.). You may misinterpret the reading.\nDetails:\n    The divination must be about a place. You do not need to be there; you need only its approximate location. It cannot be about an object unless it is so large it counts as a place (e.g., a building).\n    The GM secretly rolls 1d6:\n        1–4: You interpret correctly.\n        5–6: You interpret incorrectly.\n    If you sacrifice a magical item as part of the divination, it is destroyed and the GM’s d6 roll is modified by -1. Artifacts, relics, and equivalent items cannot be sacrificed or destroyed by this spell.\n    The GM provides your character’s interpretation of:\n        Whether the place is sacred to a god/demigod/power, and which;\n        Whether creatures inhabit it;\n        Whether those creatures are weak/equivalent/strong compared to you;\n        Whether treasure is present; and\n        Whether the treasure is poor/medium/rich.\n    If you misinterpret, the GM answers randomly with a mixture of correct and incorrect information.\n    Some legendary places are specially warded; divination always misinterprets those places.","link":""},"exorcise":{"name":"Exorcise","level":"4","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"10 ft","duration":"Instantaneous (or continuing; see below)","aoe":"One creature, object, or place","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds, continuing","save":"Depends on use (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Exorcise\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1\nCasting Time: 1–100+ turns\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature or object\nThis spell negates possession of a creature or object by an outside or supernatural force. This includes control of a creature by a force in an object, possession by magic jar, demonic possession, curse, and even charm, since exorcise is similar to dispel magic. It may also affect a magical item if that item is the object of the exorcism. A successfully exorcised soul object causes the creature’s life force to wholly inhabit its nearest material body. Once begun, exorcise cannot be interrupted or it is spoiled and useless. The base chance for success is a random 1% to 100%. Each turn of exorcism, dice are rolled; if the base chance number or less is rolled, the spell succeeds. The base chance is modified by -1% for each level of difference when the cleric’s level is lower than the possessor or possessing magic, or +1% cumulatively when the cleric’s level is higher. The referee may determine the base chance according to circumstances. Material Components: The cleric’s holy object and holy water, or unholy object and unholy water for evil clerics. A religious artifact or relic may increase the chance of success by 1% to 50%, depending on its power.","notes":"A multi-purpose ritual to cast out a supernatural creature or influence (fiend, ghost, etc.) possessing a creature/object. It can also remove a curse or end a charm/enchantment. The casting and effect are loud.\nDetails:\nUsing the spell to remove curses / end charm or enchantment:\n    Automatically succeeds when you finish the first turn of casting.\n    Unwilling targets do not receive a saving throw for this use.\nUsing the spell to cast out supernatural creatures and influences:\n    On a good-aligned outer plane: automatically succeeds after the first turn.\n    On an evil-aligned outer plane: automatically fails.\n    Otherwise, each turn you continue casting, the creature/influence rolls a special saving throw on d20; failure means it is exorcised.\nSaving throws versus exorcism (base target numbers):\nCreature/Influence Strength\tBase Saving Throw\nWeak influence, dretch, spiked devil\t10\nModerate influence, class A demon, shub demon, bearded devil, erinyes, scaly devil\t8\nClass B demon, uduk demon, ekivu demon, ghost, succubus, barbed devil\t7\nClass C demon, babau demon, bone devil\t6\nStrong influence, class D demon, horned devil\t5\nClass E demon, ice devil, night hag\t4\nClass F demon, pit fiend, shaitan devil\t3\nModifiers:\n    Apply -1 to the creature’s saving throw for each cleric level you have above 8.\n    If you hold a relevant artifact/relic, the GM may assign an additional -1 to -4 modifier (based on strength/aptitude/inclination).\n    Magic resistance does not apply.\n    On a natural 20 on its saving throw, you suffer an ill effect (e.g., curse or loss of 1 point from a random ability score).\n    Cannot exorcise artifacts, relics, deities, or equivalent powers.\nEffect of exorcism:\nThe cast-out creature returns to its own body (or nearest body if it has several). If bodiless, it appears on the Prime Material Plane adjacent to the formerly possessed target (GM chooses or randomises if multiple possible).","link":""},"glibness":{"name":"Glibness","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Counters detect lie on the target; if detect lie is not in effect, the target’s lies become more convincing.\nDetails:\n    A creature can only be affected by one instance of this spell at a time.\n    As with most targeted spells, you can cast it on yourself or another creature.\n    Lies are only believed if the listener can hear and understand them.\n    The GM determines plausibility; each listener then rolls a special saving throw on a d20 (optionally adding their Wisdom save modifier).\nSaving throw targets for Glibness:\nPlausibility\tSaving Throw Target\nLikely\t20\nPlausible\t18\nPossible\t15\nSurprising\t11\nUnlikely\t7\nObviously false\t2\nIf the listener passes, they do not believe the lie.","notes":"Counters detect lie on the target; if detect lie is not in effect, the target’s lies become more convincing.\nDetails:\n    A creature can only be affected by one instance of this spell at a time.\n    As with most targeted spells, you can cast it on yourself or another creature.\n    Lies are only believed if the listener can hear and understand them.\n    The GM determines plausibility; each listener then rolls a special saving throw on a d20 (optionally adding their Wisdom save modifier).\nSaving throw targets for Glibness:\nPlausibility\tSaving Throw Target\nLikely\t20\nPlausible\t18\nPossible\t15\nSurprising\t11\nUnlikely\t7\nObviously false\t2\nIf the listener passes, they do not believe the lie.","link":""},"neutralise poison":{"name":"Neutralise Poison","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"1 ft cube per 2 cleric levels, or one creature","components":"V, S","ct":"7 segments","save":"Depends on use (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Neutralize Poison\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Poison\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched or 1 cubic foot of substance per 2 levels\nBy means of neutralize poison, the cleric detoxifies any venom in the creature or substance touched. An unwilling opponent, such as a poisonous reptile, snake, or envenomed weapon’s wielder, requires the cleric to score a melee touch hit. The effect is permanent only for poison present at the time of the touch; creatures or objects that generate new poison are not permanently detoxified. The reverse, poison, also requires a successful touch attack. The victim then receives a saving throw versus poison; if unsuccessful, the victim is killed.","notes":"Purges venom/toxin/contaminant, rendering it harmless. Can potentially revive someone who has recently “died” from poison.\nDetails:\n    Does not affect disease-based contamination.\n    Gods/demigods/artifacts/relics/equivalent are not affected (GM may allow some derivative effects to be affected).\n    If targeting a toxic place, all toxins/contaminants are purged from the area.\nUsing the spell to de-venom an opponent:\n    If the target is a creature, it may choose a saving throw vs spells and other magical effects.\n        Success: not affected.\n        Failure: if it has a venomous attack, the venom component is nullified until dawn the next day.\nUsing the spell to revive someone “dead by poison”:\n    If the target is poisoned, all toxins are purged, but poison damage already taken remains.\n    Also works on creatures that have recently died of poison: death from poison damage or failed save vs poison within a number of turns equal to your cleric level.\nReversible as Poison:","link":""},"poison":{"name":"Poison","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"1 ft cube per 2 cleric levels, including no more than one creature","components":"V, S","ct":"7 segments","save":"Depends on use (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Neutralize Poison\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Poison\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched or 1 cubic foot of substance per 2 levels\nBy means of neutralize poison, the cleric detoxifies any venom in the creature or substance touched. An unwilling opponent, such as a poisonous reptile, snake, or envenomed weapon’s wielder, requires the cleric to score a melee touch hit. The effect is permanent only for poison present at the time of the touch; creatures or objects that generate new poison are not permanently detoxified. The reverse, poison, also requires a successful touch attack. The victim then receives a saving throw versus poison; if unsuccessful, the victim is killed.","notes":"Your touch becomes deadly poison, or you can make an edible/potable substance poisonous. In either case, you must touch the target.\nDetails:\n    If targeting a creature, it may attempt a saving throw vs poison; success negates.\n    Creatures immune to poison are unaffected.\n    Gods/demigods/artifacts/relics/equivalent are unaffected.\n    If a creature fails its save: it dies.\n    If an edible/potable is poisoned: the first creature to consume must save vs poison or die (unless immune). After that save is resolved, remaining poison is nullified.","link":""},"protection from evil 10 ft radius":{"name":"Protection from Evil 10 Ft Radius","level":"4","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"10 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"10 ft radius around the creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Protection From Evil, 10’ Radius\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Protection From Good, 10’ Radius\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 20’ diameter sphere\nThis spell is identical to protection from evil, except it covers a much larger area and lasts longer. Material Component: The cleric must trace a 20-foot diameter circle using holy water or blood, incense or smoldering dung, according to the protection from evil spell.","notes":"Creates a 10 ft radius invisible barrier against evil and summoned creatures around the protected creature.\nDetails:\n    Cast on yourself or another willing creature; not on hostile creatures, objects, or places.\n    A creature can only be affected by one instance at a time. If already warded by the 1st-level protection from evil, this spell has no effect on it.\n    Effects within the warded area:\n        Evil creatures: -2 to attack rolls into the warded area; anyone inside gains +2 on saving throws caused by evil creatures or their effects.\n        Evil effects (rare): effects explicitly described as evil/fiendish/demonic/devilish allow +2 to saving throws.\n        Summoned/conjured creatures: cannot attack into the warded area by touch (claws, teeth, etc.), regardless of alignment. They only suffer the -2 penalty in (1) if they are evil. (A non-evil summoned creature could still attack with a long weapon if it can reach.)\n    Ghouls: additionally “kept at bay” (cannot reduce distance to the warded area), but if the warded area moves toward them, they need not retreat. Some GMs extend “kept at bay” beyond ghouls.\nReversible as Protection from Good 10 ft Radius:","link":""},"protection from good 10 ft radius":{"name":"Protection from Good 10 Ft Radius","level":"4","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"10 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"10 ft radius around the creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Protection From Evil, 10’ Radius\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Protection From Good, 10’ Radius\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 20’ diameter sphere\nThis spell is identical to protection from evil, except it covers a much larger area and lasts longer. Material Component: The cleric must trace a 20-foot diameter circle using holy water or blood, incense or smoldering dung, according to the protection from evil spell.","notes":"Creates a 10 ft radius barrier against good-aligned and summoned creatures around the protected creature.\nDetails:\n    Same targeting limits and stacking limits as the evil version (and does not affect a creature already warded by 1st-level protection from good).\n    Effects:\n        Good creatures: -2 to attack rolls into the warded area; anyone inside gains +2 on saving throws caused by good creatures or their effects.\n        Holy effects (rare): effects explicitly described as “holy” allow +2 to saving throws.\n        Summoned/conjured creatures: cannot attack into the warded area by touch, regardless of alignment; only take the -2 penalty if actually good-aligned. (A non-good summoned creature could still attack with a long weapon if it can reach.)","link":""},"raise water":{"name":"Raise Water","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"120 ft","duration":"1 turn per cleric level","aoe":"Up to 10 ft square of surface area per cleric level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Lower Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Raise Water\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” × 1” square per level\nThe cleric causes water or similar fluid in the area of effect to sink away. The lowering is 5% of the original effect per caster level: 40% at 8th level, 45% at 9th, 50% at 10th, and so on. The spell lasts 1 turn per caster level. The area of effect also increases by level: an 8th-level cleric affects an 8” × 8” area, a 9th-level cleric affects a 9” × 9” area, and so forth. The reverse causes water or similar fluid to return to its normal highest level, plus 1 foot per caster level. Material Components: The cleric’s religious symbol and a pinch of dust.","notes":"Water in the affected area rises by 5 ft. If you can affect the same area multiple times, you may raise it an additional 5 ft per iteration.\nDetails:\nAdditional water comes from the Elemental Plane of Water for the duration and returns when the spell ends (about room temperature). Target liquid must be non-magical and roughly water-like viscosity. If the target is a water creature (water weird/elemental), it is affected as if by an enlarge spell.","link":""},"snakes to sticks":{"name":"Snakes to Sticks","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"30 ft","duration":"2 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"10 ft cube","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"Yes (negates effect)","save_type":"","description":"Sticks To Snakes\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Snakes To Sticks\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic “\nThis spell allows the cleric to change 1 stick into a snake per caster level. For example, a 9th-level cleric can change 9 sticks into 9 snakes. The snakes attack as commanded by the cleric. There must be sticks or similar wood pieces, such as torches or spears, to transform. Magical items such as enchanted staves and spears are not affected. Only sticks within the area of effect are changed. The probability that each snake is venomous is 5% per caster level, such as 55% for an 11th-level cleric and 60% for a 12th-level cleric. The effect lasts 2 melee rounds per caster level. The reverse changes snakes to sticks for the appropriate duration or negates sticks to snakes according to the level of the countering cleric. For example, a 10th-level cleric casting the reverse can turn only 10 snakes back into sticks. Material Components: A small piece of bark and several snake scales.","notes":"Transforms ophidian creatures into sticks temporarily. Affects snakes, serpents, couatls, nagas, and similar; maximum of one creature per cleric level.\nDetails:\n    Targets may save vs spells and other magical effects; success negates.\n    If unclear, affected creatures include those listed above and other reptilian creatures that lacked limbs when hatched. Dragons, demons, devils, and wyverns are not “snakes” for this spell.\n    Some ophidian creatures are too large to fit in the area and cannot be affected.\n    While wood, snakes can be broken/burned/destroyed; if destroyed, they are dead when the spell ends.","link":""},"speak with plants":{"name":"Speak With Plants","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"One plant within range","components":"V, S","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Speak With Plants\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6” diameter circle\nThis spell enables the cleric to converse in rudimentary terms with all sorts of living vegetation. The cleric can question plants about whether creatures have passed through them, cause thickets to part for passage, require vines to entangle pursuers, and similar things. The spell does not animate non-ambulatory vegetation. Its power lasts 1 melee round per caster level, and all vegetation within the area of effect is under the spell’s command. Material Components: A drop of water, a pinch of dung, and a flame.","notes":"Lets you communicate with a nearby plant and understand its “speech.”\nDetails:\n    Only you hear the magical translation.\n    You speak in Common; the plant understands. It replies in its natural mode; the spell translates into your mind.\n    Some plants may be mobile/dangerous; you can bargain/persuade/deceive as appropriate.\n    GM decides what counts as a “plant.”\n    The plant usually won’t start combat until the spell ends, but if you/your allies attacked it in the last turn, it is not required to stop fighting.\n    Does not compel truth.","link":""},"sticks to snakes":{"name":"Sticks to Snakes","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"30 ft","duration":"2 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"10 ft cube; max 1 stick per cleric level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Sticks To Snakes\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Snakes To Sticks\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic “\nThis spell allows the cleric to change 1 stick into a snake per caster level. For example, a 9th-level cleric can change 9 sticks into 9 snakes. The snakes attack as commanded by the cleric. There must be sticks or similar wood pieces, such as torches or spears, to transform. Magical items such as enchanted staves and spears are not affected. Only sticks within the area of effect are changed. The probability that each snake is venomous is 5% per caster level, such as 55% for an 11th-level cleric and 60% for a 12th-level cleric. The effect lasts 2 melee rounds per caster level. The reverse changes snakes to sticks for the appropriate duration or negates sticks to snakes according to the level of the countering cleric. For example, a 10th-level cleric casting the reverse can turn only 10 snakes back into sticks. Material Components: A small piece of bark and several snake scales.","notes":"Transforms dead wood into serpents. The serpents do not understand speech, but obey mental commands to attack a target.\nFor each snake created, roll 1d20: if the result is ≤ your cleric level, the snake is venomous; otherwise it is a constrictor.\nDetails:\n    Affects roughly cylindrical dead-wood objects, up to a maximum number equal to your cleric level. Targets cannot be magical.\n    If you aren’t in a forest, bring your own sticks.\nVenomous Snake: AC 6, MV 90 ft, HD 2, #AT 1, Dmg 1 piercing, SA poison (save vs poison or die; apply CON modifier to save), Size S, AL N.\nConstrictor Snake: AC 6, MV 90 ft, HD 2, #AT 1, Dmg 1 blunt, SA constrict (on hit: constricts until it releases or is killed; one target at a time; may deal 1d4 blunt damage on its initiative instead of attacking), Size S, AL N.\nNo XP is awarded for killing/defeating snakes created by this spell.\nReversible as Snakes to Sticks:","link":""},"atonement":{"name":"Atonement","level":"5","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Atonement\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One person\nThis spell removes the onus of unwilling or unknown deeds from the subject of the atonement. It also removes the effects of magical alignment change. The person receiving atonement must be either truly repentant or not in command of their own will so as to be capable of repentance. The referee judges this requirement and notes any past uses of the spell upon the person. Deliberate misdeeds and knowing, willful acts cannot be atoned for with this spell. Material Components: The cleric’s religious symbol, prayer beads, prayer wheel or prayer book, and burning incense.","notes":"You request forgiveness for the target’s past sins and transgressions. Any punishments imposed by gods or spirits are removed (see details). The spell can only be cast on a willing creature.\nDetails:\nThe spell ends without effect if:\n    Your alignment is chaotic and the target’s is lawful;\n    Your alignment is lawful and the target’s is chaotic;\n    Your alignment is good and the target’s is evil; or\n    Your alignment is evil and the target’s is good.\nIf the target’s transgressions were involuntary, unwilling, or unwitting, and the target is truly sorry, punishments are lifted unconditionally.\nIf the transgressions were involuntary, unwilling, or unwitting, and the target is not truly sorry, the gods/spirits assign a penance or quest; punishments are lifted when it is completed.\nIf the transgressions occurred while the target’s mind/brain was disturbed (charm, domination, mind control, possession), and the disturbance is ongoing, punishments are lifted unconditionally regardless of remorse, and the disturbance ends.\nIf the transgressions were voluntary but the target honestly believed they were for the greater good, the GM determines whether the repentance is accepted. If accepted, a penance/quest is assigned; punishments are lifted when it is completed.","link":""},"cause critical wounds":{"name":"Cause Critical Wounds","level":"5","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Critical Wounds\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Cause Critical Wounds\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is a very potent version of cure light wounds. The cleric lays their hand upon a creature and heals 6 to 27 hit points, or 3d8 + 3, of wound or injury damage. The spell does not affect creatures excluded in the cure light wounds explanation. The reverse, cause critical wounds, works like other cause wounds spells and requires a successful touch to inflict 6 to 27 hit points of damage. Caused wounds heal as normal wounds do.","notes":"The touched target takes 3d8+3 magical damage, even if it can only be hit by magical weapons. Requires a successful to-hit roll; no saving throw allowed.\nDetails:\nIf you miss the to-hit roll, no damage is inflicted and the spell is lost. Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.","link":""},"commune":{"name":"Commune","level":"5","school":"Divine divination","range":"Self","duration":"3 rounds","aoe":"You","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Commune\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nBy using commune, the cleric contacts their divinity or agents thereof and requests information in the form of questions answerable by “yes” or “no.” The cleric may ask one such question per caster level. The answers are correct. The referee will probably limit commune to once per adventure, once per week, or even once per month, since the gods dislike frequent interruptions. Material Components: The cleric’s religious symbol, holy or unholy water, and incense.","notes":"You pray for enlightenment; an invisible divine power answers your questions.\nDetails:\nGods/spirits that are pestered too often may choose not to respond.\nThe divine emissary knows what the gods/spirits you petition know. It is not omniscient, but its knowledge of the Prime Material Plane is likely excellent. It never lies.\nYou may ask one question per cleric level. Each must be asked promptly and respectfully or the emissary departs, ending the spell without further effect. Each answer is:\n“O [adjective] mortal, the answer to your question is…” followed by “yes”, “no”, “I don’t know”, or “it’s complicated”. The emissary may add an adjective before “mortal” (commonly “puny” or “insignificant”, but possibly “annoying”, “stupid”, etc. if patience wears thin).\nOnly you can hear the responses.","link":""},"cure critical wounds":{"name":"Cure Critical Wounds","level":"5","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Critical Wounds\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Cause Critical Wounds\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is a very potent version of cure light wounds. The cleric lays their hand upon a creature and heals 6 to 27 hit points, or 3d8 + 3, of wound or injury damage. The spell does not affect creatures excluded in the cure light wounds explanation. The reverse, cause critical wounds, works like other cause wounds spells and requires a successful touch to inflict 6 to 27 hit points of damage. Caused wounds heal as normal wounds do.","notes":"The target regains 3d8+3 hp, up to its normal maximum. Healing beyond maximum is wasted.\nDetails:\nDoes not cure disease, reattach limbs, raise the dead, or heal afflictions not measured in hit points. Generally affects only normally living creatures; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.\nReversible as Cause Critical Wounds:","link":""},"dispel evil":{"name":"Dispel Evil","level":"5","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Yes (lessened effect)","save_type":"","description":"Dispel Evil\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Dispel Good\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell causes summoned creatures of evil nature, or monsters enchanted and caused to perform evil deeds, to return to their own plane or place. Examples include aerial servants, demons, devils, djinn, efreet, elementals, and invisible stalkers. While the spell lasts, creatures that could be affected by it attack the caster at a -7 penalty on “to hit” rolls. The reverse, dispel good, works against summoned or enchanted creatures of good alignment or creatures sent to aid good. Material Components: The cleric’s religious object and holy or unholy water.","notes":"Banishes an evil-aligned extraplanar creature. It disappears with an audible “pop”.\nDetails:\nTarget applies its Wisdom save modifier (if any) to the saving throw.\n    Fail save: banished to its home plane.\n    Pass save: not banished, but for the spell’s duration, whenever it attacks you with melee/missile/touch, you may choose to apply -7 to its attack roll.\nWorks only on evil creatures from other planes (demons, devils, efreets, etc.). The banished creature takes its carried/worn items, but no other creatures go with it even if it is carrying them.\nReversible as Dispel Good:","link":""},"dispel good":{"name":"Dispel Good","level":"5","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Yes (lessened effect)","save_type":"","description":"Dispel Evil\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Dispel Good\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell causes summoned creatures of evil nature, or monsters enchanted and caused to perform evil deeds, to return to their own plane or place. Examples include aerial servants, demons, devils, djinn, efreet, elementals, and invisible stalkers. While the spell lasts, creatures that could be affected by it attack the caster at a -7 penalty on “to hit” rolls. The reverse, dispel good, works against summoned or enchanted creatures of good alignment or creatures sent to aid good. Material Components: The cleric’s religious object and holy or unholy water.","notes":"Banishes a good-aligned extraplanar creature; it disappears with an audible “pop”.\nDetails:\nTarget applies its Wisdom save modifier (if any) to the saving throw.\n    Fail save: banished to its home plane.\n    Pass save: not banished, but for the spell’s duration, whenever it attacks you with melee/missile/touch, you may choose to apply -7 to its attack roll.\nWorks only on good extraplanar creatures (celestials, genies, etc.). The banished creature takes carried/worn items only.","link":""},"false seeing":{"name":"False Seeing","level":"5","school":"Divine divination","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"120 ft radius around the touched creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Yes (negates effect)","save_type":"","description":"True Seeing\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: False Seeing\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 12” sight range\nWhen the cleric uses this spell, all things within the area of true seeing appear as they actually are. Secret doors become plain. The exact location of displaced things is obvious. Invisible, astral, and ethereal things become visible. Illusions and apparitions are seen through. Polymorphed, changed, or magicked things are apparent. Even creature auras become visible, allowing the cleric to know whether they are good, evil, or between. The reverse, false seeing, causes the recipient to see things falsely, such as rich as poor, rough as smooth, or beautiful as ugly. Material Component: For true seeing, an eye ointment made from very rare mushroom powder, saffron, and fat. For false seeing, an ointment made from oil, poppy dust, and pink orchid essence. Both ointments must be aged for 1d6 months.","notes":"Affects one creature: it suffers wild hallucinations, is blinded for the duration, and must make a morale check each round or flee screaming in a random direction.\nDetails:\nTarget adds its Wisdom save modifier to the saving throw.","link":""},"flame strike":{"name":"Flame Strike","level":"5","school":"Divine evocation","range":"60 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Column, 5 ft radius; 30 ft high","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Yes (half damage)","save_type":"","description":"Flame Strike\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 1 segment\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: 1” diameter by 3” high column\nWhen the cleric calls down flame strike, a column of fire roars downward at the exact location chosen by the caster. Any creature within the area of effect must make a saving throw. Failure means the creature takes 6d8 damage, or 6 to 48 hit points. Success means the creature takes 3d8 damage, or 3 to 24 hit points. Material Component: A pinch of sulphur.","notes":"Cast at a visible target point on the ground. A pillar of flame strikes; extremely loud (heard within 300 ft).\nDetails:\nCreatures in the area take 6d8 fire damage. If any fiends or celestials are in the area, they instead take 6d8 magical damage (not fire).\nCreatures may save vs spells/magical effects:\n    Pass: half damage; worn/carried items are undamaged.\n    Fail/decline: full damage; roll item saves vs fire for worn/carried objects.\nGM rolls saves vs fire for unattended objects in the area. In 5 ft squares, can hit up to 4 squares (target an intersection). Afterward, the area is charred/sooty with a lingering scent appropriate to the invoked power (incense, brimstone, etc.).","link":""},"insect plague":{"name":"Insect Plague","level":"5","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"360 ft","duration":"10 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"Column, 180 ft radius; 60 ft high","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Insect Plague\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 36”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 36” diameter, 6” high cloud\nThis spell summons a horde of creeping, hopping, and flying insects in a thick cloud. The insects obscure vision, limiting it to 3”. Creatures within the plague take 1 hit point of damage each melee round from bites and stings, regardless of armor class. The referee causes all creatures with fewer than 5 Hit Dice to check morale. Creatures with 2 or fewer Hit Dice automatically move at maximum speed in a straight line in a random direction until at least 24” away from the insect cloud. Creatures with fewer than 5 Hit Dice that fail morale behave likewise. Heavy smoke drives off insects within its bounds. Fire also drives insects away; a ring-shaped wall of fire keeps the plague outside its confines, but a fireball clears insects from its blast area for only 1 turn. Lightning and cold or ice act similarly. The plague lasts 1 turn per caster level, after which the insects disperse. The insects swarm in an area centered on a summoning point up to 36” from the cleric and do not move thereafter. The spell can be countered by casting dispel magic upon the summoning point. A cube of force keeps insects away from a character seeking the swarm’s center, but invisibility gives no protection. Material Components: A few grains of sugar, some kernels of grain, and a smear of fat.","notes":"Conjures a swarm of biting/stinging insects from a visible target point on the ground.\nDetails:\nIf you are level 18 or lower: mundane insects (wasps, clegs, midges, mosquitoes, biting locusts). Each round, at the start of the round, each creature in the area:\n    Takes 1 point piercing damage; and\n    Level 2 / 2 HD or less: must flee until at least 240 ft from the plague’s edge.\n    Level 4 / 4 HD or less: must check morale; on failure, flee until at least 120 ft from the edge.\nIf you are level 19 or higher: may conjure extraplanar insects. Each round, at the start of the round, each creature in the area:\n    Takes 2 points piercing damage; and\n    Level 4 / 4 HD or less: must flee until at least 240 ft from the edge.\n    Level 7 / 7 HD or less: must check morale; on failure, flee until at least 120 ft from the edge.\nOther details:\n    Fire/smoke holds back insects while it lasts (e.g., wall of fire works; fireball/flame strike only clears briefly).\n    Insects can pass through tiny spaces but not impenetrable barriers (can pass through blade barrier/wall of thorns; not wall of force).\n    Insects will not enter water; fully submerged creatures at start of round take no damage.\n    Creatures immune to mundane weapons are unaffected, regardless of HD.\n    Visibility inside is 30 ft.","link":""},"plane shift":{"name":"Plane Shift","level":"5","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creatures touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Depends on use (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Plane Shift\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched, special\nWhen plane shift is cast, the cleric moves themselves or another creature to another plane of existence. The recipient remains on the new plane until sent away by similar means. If several persons link hands in a circle, up to seven can be affected at once. An unwilling victim must be touched and receives a saving throw; success negates the spell. Material Component: A small, forked metal rod whose exact size and metal type determine the plane reached, as determined by the referee.","notes":"Transports either:\n    One unwilling creature, or\n    Up to 7 willing creatures holding hands in a circle, plus optionally the caster,\n    to an Outer Plane.\nIf the creature is native to an Outer Plane, it returns to its origin plane; otherwise the caster chooses which Outer Plane it is sent to.\nDetails:\nIf you touch an unwilling creature, it may attempt a saving throw vs spells/magical effects, adding its Wisdom save modifier. On success, the spell does not affect it.","link":""},"quest":{"name":"Quest","level":"5","school":"Divine enchantment","range":"60 ft","duration":"Until completed","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Yes (negates effect)","save_type":"","description":"Quest\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Until fulfilled\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell requires the affected creature to perform a service and return to the cleric with proof of completion. A quest may require locating and returning an important or valuable object, rescuing a notable person, freeing a creature, capturing a stronghold, slaying a person, delivering an item, and similar deeds. If the quest is not properly followed because of disregard, delay, or perversion, the affected creature loses 1 from saving throw dice for each day of such action. This penalty is not removed until the quest is properly discharged or the cleric cancels it. Certain circumstances may temporarily suspend, discharge, or cancel a quest, as determined by the Dungeon Master. Material Component: The cleric’s religious symbol.","notes":"Sets a quest a target creature is compelled to perform. Target must be human, demi-human, or humanoid.\nDetails:\nTarget may save vs spells/other effects, adding Wisdom save modifier. On success, spell ends without effect.\nQuest limitations:\n    Cannot be one that would change the target’s alignment if completed.\n    Must be within the target’s power.\n    Must be possible to complete within a year and a day.\nEnding conditions:\n    You can end it at any time.\n    Any cleric higher level than you can end it by touching the target and willing it to end.\n    Ends when the target returns with proof of completion (or, if it doesn’t know where you are, to the casting location), or when the target dies, or when completion becomes impossible (target of assassination dies; object to retrieve is destroyed; etc.).\nPenalty for procrastination:\nFor each 24 hours the target avoids the quest, it takes a cumulative -1 to all saving throws (periods need not be continuous). Normal daily maintenance is allowed as long as it is acting in good faith toward the quest.","link":""},"raise dead":{"name":"Raise Dead","level":"5","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"30 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One corpse or undead creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"Depends on use (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Raise Dead\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Slay Living\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One person\nThis spell restores life to a dwarf, gnome, half-elf, halfling, or human. The time since death matters: the cleric can raise a person dead up to 1 day per caster level, such as up to 9 days for a 9th-level cleric. The body must be whole; missing parts remain missing when the person is restored. The raised person must make a special saving throw to survive the ordeal, based on Constitution. The raised person is weak and helpless and must rest in bed for 1 full day per day they were dead. The reverse, slay living, allows the victim a saving throw. If successful, the victim takes only the damage of cause serious wounds, or 3 to 17 hit points. Evil clerics may freely use the reverse. Good clerics must use extreme caution and be absolutely certain the victim is evil and that death is necessary and for good, or the cleric’s alignment will be sharply changed. Newly made undead, excluding skeletons, that fall within the allowed death-time limit are affected by raise dead. The spell causes them to become resurrected dead if Constitution permits survival; otherwise, they are simply dead. Somatic Component: A pointed finger.","notes":"Returns a recently killed person to life, or can be used to kill some undead with physical bodies (works on zombies, not ghosts).\nDetails:\n    Can only raise if death occurred within 1 day per cleric level. (You can still use it to kill an undead that died longer ago.)\n    Body must be sufficiently intact (missing head/heart causes failure).\n    The slain creature must pass a Resurrection Success roll based on Constitution (table 1.1.4a). Failure means no return.\n    Returned creature remembers dying but not the time spent dead.\n    Unless the GM rules otherwise: works on humans, half-elves, gnomes, dwarfs, halflings; not elves or half-orcs.\n    Returned creature has 1 hp, is weak/sick, and cannot fight/cast/work until bed rest of 1 full day per day dead.\n    Missing body parts remain missing.\nIf the target is an undead creature (with a physical body):\nIt saves vs spells/other magical effects.\n    Pass: takes 2d8+1 corrosion damage; no other effect.\n    Fail: returned to life if it died recently enough; otherwise it crumbles to dust.\n    A lich, or a vampire older than a century, automatically passes this saving throw.\nReversible as Slay Living:","link":""},"slay living":{"name":"Slay Living","level":"5","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"30 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Yes (negates effect)","save_type":"","description":"Raise Dead\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Slay Living\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One person\nThis spell restores life to a dwarf, gnome, half-elf, halfling, or human. The time since death matters: the cleric can raise a person dead up to 1 day per caster level, such as up to 9 days for a 9th-level cleric. The body must be whole; missing parts remain missing when the person is restored. The raised person must make a special saving throw to survive the ordeal, based on Constitution. The raised person is weak and helpless and must rest in bed for 1 full day per day they were dead. The reverse, slay living, allows the victim a saving throw. If successful, the victim takes only the damage of cause serious wounds, or 3 to 17 hit points. Evil clerics may freely use the reverse. Good clerics must use extreme caution and be absolutely certain the victim is evil and that death is necessary and for good, or the cleric’s alignment will be sharply changed. Newly made undead, excluding skeletons, that fall within the allowed death-time limit are affected by raise dead. The spell causes them to become resurrected dead if Constitution permits survival; otherwise, they are simply dead. Somatic Component: A pointed finger.","notes":"You speak an Abominable Word and point at a creature. Target may save vs spells/magical effects.\n    Pass: takes 2d8+1 corrosion damage; no other effect.\n    Fail: dies instantly.\nDetails:\nIn some campaigns, Abominable Words are lost secrets obtainable only through ancient lore, extraplanar consultation, or certain liches. Unless the GM rules otherwise, works on humans, half-elves, gnomes, dwarfs, halflings; not elves or half-orcs.","link":""},"true seeing":{"name":"True Seeing","level":"5","school":"Divine divination","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"120 ft radius around the touched creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"True Seeing\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: False Seeing\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 12” sight range\nWhen the cleric uses this spell, all things within the area of true seeing appear as they actually are. Secret doors become plain. The exact location of displaced things is obvious. Invisible, astral, and ethereal things become visible. Illusions and apparitions are seen through. Polymorphed, changed, or magicked things are apparent. Even creature auras become visible, allowing the cleric to know whether they are good, evil, or between. The reverse, false seeing, causes the recipient to see things falsely, such as rich as poor, rough as smooth, or beautiful as ugly. Material Component: For true seeing, an eye ointment made from very rare mushroom powder, saffron, and fat. For false seeing, an ointment made from oil, poppy dust, and pink orchid essence. Both ointments must be aged for 1d6 months.","notes":"Target sees things as they truly are within the area: detects illusions/displacements (and may choose to see through them), perceives astral/ethereal beings, hidden/secret things, sees alignment auras, recognizes polymorph/shapechange (and may choose to see true or altered form), and sees through darkness/bright light/fog/mist.\nDetails:\nGods and god-like beings, artifacts, and relics may produce effects immune to this spell.\nReversible as False Seeing:","link":""},"aerial servant":{"name":"Aerial Servant","level":"6","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"10 ft","duration":"1 day per cleric level","aoe":"Nil","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Aerial Servant\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 1 day per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons an invisible aerial servant to do the cleric’s bidding. The creature does not fight, but it obeys commands to find and return with a described object or creature, provided it can physically bring that object or creature to the cleric or the cleric’s assign. The spell lasts up to 1 day per caster level. The aerial servant returns to its own plane when the spell ends, its duty is fulfilled, it is dispelled, the cleric releases it, or the cleric is slain. The cleric must have protection from evil, be within a magic circle, thaumaturgic triangle, or pentagram, or have a religious symbol, artifact, or relic to control the servant. Otherwise, the creature slays its summoner and returns to its plane. On a mission, the aerial servant attacks by complete surprise and gains 4 free melee rounds unless the target can detect invisible objects. If the target can detect invisible objects, roll 1d6: 1 = 1 free round, 2 = 2 free rounds, 3 = 3 free rounds, 4 = 4 free rounds, and 5–6 = no free rounds. Each round, the aerial servant must roll to hit. A hit means it has grabbed the item or creature it was sent to retrieve. If a creature is grabbed, compare the aerial servant’s Strength to the creature’s Strength. If the creature has no Strength rating, roll the appropriate Hit Dice for both; the higher total is stronger.","notes":"Summons an aerial servant (invisible elemental being) and binds it to your service. Unless you or it travels to another plane, it magically knows the direction and distance to both the summoning location and your current location.\nDetails:\n    Spell fails unless you are on the Prime Material, Elemental Plane of Air, Ethereal, or Astral plane.\n    It cannot speak and knows no languages, but understands your spoken commands via the spell.\n    It hates being controlled; the spell compels strict obedience.\n    It does not have to obey:\n        commands that are obviously self-destructive, or\n        commands to attack a creature.\n    The servant is dismissed (spell ends) when: it is killed; you are killed; you dismiss it; you leave the plane of casting; or it leaves that plane.\n    Not evil, but it cannot cross Protection from Evil or a magic circle, and must recoil from a holy symbol held out by a cleric or paladin.\n    Nothing prevents it from attacking you; best practice is to stand protected until commands are complete.\n    If its mission can’t be completed, the spell ends; it is no longer commanded and will usually return and attack you.","link":""},"animate object":{"name":"Animate Object","level":"6","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"One object up to 1 cubic foot per cleric level","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Animate Object\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per level\nThis spell imbues inanimate objects with mobility and a semblance of life. The animated object or objects attack whomever or whatever the cleric first designates. Objects may be made of any material: wood, metal, stone, fabric, leather, ceramic, glass, and so on. Movement speed depends on propulsion and weight. A heavy wooden table may move quickly on its legs; a rug slithers; a jar rolls. Examples include a large stone pedestal rocking forward at 1” per round, a stone statue moving at 4” per round, a wooden statue at 8” per round, and a light ivory stool at 12” per round. Slithering movement is about 1” to 2” per round, and rolling movement is 3” to 6” per round. Damage depends on form and composition. Light, supple objects can obscure vision, obstruct movement, bind, trip, smother, and similar effects. Light, hard objects can fall or strike for 1–2 hit points of damage, or obstruct and trip. Hard, medium-weight objects can crush or strike for 2–8 damage, with larger and heavier objects dealing 3–12, 4–16, or even 5–20 damage. Attack frequency depends on locomotion, appendages, and attack method, ranging from once every 5 melee rounds to once per melee round. Armor class depends on material and movement ability. Damage taken depends on the weapon and object struck: sharp cutting weapons work well against fabric, leather, wood, and similar substances, while heavy smashing and crushing weapons are useful against wood, stone, and metal objects. The referee determines these factors and how much damage the object can sustain before destruction. The cleric may animate 1 cubic foot of material per caster level. For example, a 14th-level cleric can animate one or more objects whose total solid volume does not exceed 14 cubic feet, such as a large statue, two rugs, three chairs, or a dozen average crocks.","notes":"Infuses a spirit into an inanimate object, which becomes a temporary creature that obeys you. When the spell ends, it becomes inanimate again; damage it took remains.\nDetails:\n    No self-preservation; obeys all commands even if self-destructive.\n    Statblock is “animated object” in the OSRIC GM Guide.\n    If the object is too large, spell ends without effect and the slot is still used.\n    Cannot speak/knows no languages; understands your spoken commands via the spell.\n    Spell ends if the animated object is killed; you are killed; you dismiss it; or you leave the plane of casting.\n    Commanding it does not take your combat action, but in any round you give it a command you can’t cast spells with a verbal component.","link":""},"blade barrier":{"name":"Blade Barrier","level":"6","school":"Divine evocation","range":"30 ft","duration":"3 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"Sphere of radius 5/10/15/20 ft around a visible target point","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Blade Barrier\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 3 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a wall of circling, razor-sharp blades that whirl and flash around an immobile point. Any creature attempting to pass through the blade barrier takes 8d8 damage, or 8 to 64 hit points. The barrier remains for 3 melee rounds per caster level. It can cover an area as small as 5 feet square or as large as 2” square, meaning 20’ × 20’ underground or 60’ × 60’ outdoors.","notes":"Creates a stationary sphere of whirling blades around the target point; radius chosen at casting and cannot be changed.\nDetails:\n    Blades cannot penetrate rock or brick; they do not appear in those portions of the area.\n    Ends if you are killed or you dismiss it.\n    Blades are not magical; creatures only hittable by magical weapons take no damage.\n    Contact damage: 8d8 slashing, no attack roll, no save. Triggered when:\n        a creature enters or reaches through from either side,\n        the barrier appears on a creature,\n        a creature remains in it (damage at start of each round).\n    Barrier is narrow; standing adjacent is safe, but melee attacks through it cause damage.\n    Physical missiles/projectiles through it: -3 to attack roll. Magical/energy attacks do not take this penalty.","link":""},"conjure animals":{"name":"Conjure Animals","level":"6","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"30 ft","duration":"2 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"Up to 1 creature per cleric level (varies by strength chosen)","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Conjure Animals\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons one or more mammals to the cleric’s locale to attack the cleric’s opponents. The conjured animals remain for 2 melee rounds per caster level or until slain. The cleric may call one or more mammals whose total Hit Dice do not exceed the cleric’s level. For example, a 12th-level cleric may conjure one 12-Hit-Die mammal, two 6-Hit-Die mammals, three 4-Hit-Die mammals, four 3-Hit-Die mammals, six 2-Hit-Die mammals, or twelve 1-Hit-Die mammals. For every +1 hit point in a creature’s Hit Dice, count ¼ Hit Die; thus, a 4 + 3 Hit Dice creature counts as 4¾ Hit Dice. The summoned creatures unfailingly attack the opponents of the cleric who cast the spell.","notes":"Conjures animal allies at a visible target point. You choose desired strength (Weak/Medium/Strong/Mighty); stronger types yield fewer animals. GM rolls/chooses what appears.\nWeak — 1 per cleric level\n1–3 Baboon; 4–9 Dog; 10–16 Giant rat; 17–20 Jackal\nMedium — 1 per 2 cleric levels (round down)\n1–4 Badger; 5–14 Herd animal; 15–20 Horse\nStrong — 1 per 3 cleric levels (round down)\n1–2 Boar; 3–5 Camel; 6–7 Giant goat; 8–9 Horse; 10–11 Hyena; 12–13 Leopard; 14–15 Phorusrhacid (Axe Beak); 16–17 Stag; 18–20 Wolf\nMighty — 1 per 4 cleric levels (round down)\n1–3 Ape; 4–5 Bear; 6–7 Boar; 8–9 Bull; 10–12 Dire wolf; 13–14 Leopard; 15–16 Lion; 17–18 Sabretooth tiger; 19–20 Tiger\nDetails:\n    Spell fails unless on the Prime Material Plane.\n    Animals understand your spoken commands; need not obey self-destructive commands.\n    Ends when all are killed; you are killed; you dismiss them; you leave the plane of casting; or they leave that plane.\n    No XP for defeating them.\n    VTT spacing: GM may place; typical approach is one per unoccupied square in/adjacent to the target point. If no space, an animal appears later when space opens; duration extends accordingly for late arrivals.","link":""},"find the path":{"name":"Find The Path","level":"6","school":"Divine divination","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per cleric level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Find The Path\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Lose The Path\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell enables the cleric to find the shortest and most direct route sought, whether to, from, or out of a locale. The locale may be outdoors, underground, a trap, or even a maze spell. The spell enables the cleric to choose the correct direction, exact path, or necessary actions, and this knowledge remains for 1 turn per caster level. The spell frees the cleric and companions from a maze spell in a single melee round and continues to do so while it lasts. The reverse, lose the path, makes the touched creature totally lost and unable to find its way for the duration, though it can still be led. Material Component: A set of divination counters favored by the cleric, such as bones, ivory counters, sticks, carved runes, or similar items.","notes":"Touched creature magically knows the route to one specific destination you choose. If multiple routes exist, only the shortest is known. If none exists, you learn that and the spell ends.\nDetails:\nKnows the route, not precise distances/directions; cannot draw an accurate map. Learns nothing about hazards on the route.\nReversible as Hide the Path:","link":""},"harm":{"name":"Harm","level":"6","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"Yes (negates)","save_type":"","description":"Heal\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Harm\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis powerful spell wipes away disease and injury in the recipient. It completely cures all diseases and/or blindness and heals all hit point damage from wounds or injury except 1d4 points. It also dispels feeblemind. Later wounds, injuries, or diseases can negate its benefits. The reverse, harm, infects the victim with disease and causes the loss of all hit points except 1d4 if a successful touch is inflicted. For creatures not affected by heal or harm, see cure light wounds.","notes":"You speak an Abominable Word and attempt to touch the target. If it fails a save vs spells, it takes enough magical damage to reduce its hit points to 1d4.\nDetails:\nIn some campaigns, Abominable Words are lost secrets. Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, undead.","link":""},"heal":{"name":"Heal","level":"6","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Heal\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Harm\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis powerful spell wipes away disease and injury in the recipient. It completely cures all diseases and/or blindness and heals all hit point damage from wounds or injury except 1d4 points. It also dispels feeblemind. Later wounds, injuries, or diseases can negate its benefits. The reverse, harm, infects the victim with disease and causes the loss of all hit points except 1d4 if a successful touch is inflicted. For creatures not affected by heal or harm, see cure light wounds.","notes":"Target regains almost all lost hit points: up to normal total minus 1d4. Cures blindness, deafness, diseases, madnesses, and poisons completely. Ends feeblemind.\nDetails:\nDoes not raise the dead and does not remove lycanthropy. Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, undead.\nReversible as Harm:","link":""},"hide the path":{"name":"Hide the Path","level":"6","school":"Divine enchantment","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per cleric level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 rounds","save":"Yes (negates)","save_type":"","description":"Find The Path\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Lose The Path\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell enables the cleric to find the shortest and most direct route sought, whether to, from, or out of a locale. The locale may be outdoors, underground, a trap, or even a maze spell. The spell enables the cleric to choose the correct direction, exact path, or necessary actions, and this knowledge remains for 1 turn per caster level. The spell frees the cleric and companions from a maze spell in a single melee round and continues to do so while it lasts. The reverse, lose the path, makes the touched creature totally lost and unable to find its way for the duration, though it can still be led. Material Component: A set of divination counters favored by the cleric, such as bones, ivory counters, sticks, carved runes, or similar items.","notes":"Touched creature loses sense of direction; if it tries to move, its heading is randomly determined.\nDetails:\nIt can still attack and cast spells normally; only directional movement becomes random.","link":""},"speak with monsters":{"name":"Speak With Monsters","level":"6","school":"Divine divination","range":"Caster","duration":"1 turn","aoe":"30 ft radius around you","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Speak With Monsters\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3” radius\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen cast, this spell allows the cleric to converse with any type of creature that has any form of communicative ability. The creature understands the intent of what the cleric says. The referee checks the creature’s reaction. All creatures of the same type as the one chosen by the cleric can likewise understand if they are within range. The spell lasts 1 melee round per caster level, and during that duration conversation can occur as the monster is able and desires.","notes":"Universal translator for any creature or plant intelligent enough to communicate. Translates their “speech” into a language you understand and translates your spoken words for them within the area.\nDetails:\n    Intelligence < animal (1) cannot communicate meaningfully even with this spell.\n    Does not make hostile creatures friendly.\n    Translation is per-language; different species may not understand each other without repetition, though you can understand all of them.","link":""},"stone tell":{"name":"Stone Tell","level":"6","school":"Divine divination","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn","aoe":"Up to 10 cubic feet","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Stone Tell\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 turn\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One cubic yard of stone\nWhen the cleric casts stone tell upon an area, the stones speak and tell the caster who or what has touched them, as well as what is covered, concealed, or behind them. The stones provide complete descriptions as required. Material Components: A drop of mercury and a bit of clay.","notes":"Gives stone the ability to hear your questions and mentally reply with brief, truthful answers to the best of its knowledge.\nDetails:\nOnly you hear replies. Stone only knows what occurred within 20 ft of it (making area of effect relevant).","link":""},"word of recall":{"name":"Word of Recall","level":"6","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Caster","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"You plus creatures/objects up to 25 lb per cleric level","components":"V","ct":"Fast","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Word Of Recall\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell instantly returns the cleric to their sanctuary when the word is uttered. The sanctuary must be specifically designated in advance and must be a well-known place, but it may be any distance from the cleric, above or below ground. Transportation by word of recall is infallibly safe. In addition to themselves, the cleric may transport 250 gold pieces weight per caster level. For example, a 15th-level cleric may transport themselves plus 3,750 gold pieces weight, or 375 pounds, of additional matter, including equipment, treasure, or living material such as another person.","notes":"Teleports you (and possibly others) to a prepared sanctuary. Before using, you must designate a sanctuary by standing there and praying privately for 10 minutes.\nDetails:\n    Only one sanctuary at a time; designating a new one replaces the old.\n    Transports willing creatures only; unwilling creatures are unaffected.\n    Worn/held/carried gear is transported. Weight limit cannot be exploited to bring additional “creatures” unless very small (≈ 30 lb or less).","link":""},"earthquake":{"name":"Earthquake","level":"7","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"360 ft","duration":"1 round","aoe":"Contiguous stone area up to 5 ft diameter per cleric level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Earthquake\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: ½” diameter per level\nWhen cast, this spell creates a strong local tremor that rips the ground. The shock lasts 1 melee round and affects terrain, vegetation, structures, and creatures in the area. The area is circular, with a diameter of ½” per caster level; for example, a 20th-level cleric creates a 10” diameter earthquake. Terrain effects: caves and caverns collapse their roofs; cliffs crumble and cause landslides; ground cracks open, causing creatures to fall in and be killed on a 1-in-4 chance for Size S, 1-in-6 for Size M, and 1-in-8 for Size L; marsh drains water and becomes muddy rough ground; tunnels cave in. Vegetation effects: small growth is unaffected; 1 in 3 trees are uprooted and fall. Structure effects: all structures sustain 5d12 structural damage, and those taking full damage are thrown down into rubble. Creature effects are as listed by the referee’s table. Material Components: A pinch of dirt, a piece of rock, and a lump of clay.","notes":"Creates a minor earthquake; cracks open with a chance to swallow creatures.\nDetails:\n    Non-material creatures and creatures flying/levitating do not fall in.\n    GM may rule extremely large creatures are too large to fall in.\n    Elementals survive the fall and can return after 3d6 rounds.\n    Chance to fall (no saving throw):\n        Small: 1 in 4\n        Medium: 1 in 6\n        Large: 1 in 8\n    Creatures swallowed take 12d10 blunt damage.","link":""},"energy drain":{"name":"Energy Drain","level":"9","school":"Evocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Energy Drain\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell opens a channel between the caster’s plane and the Negative Material Plane, with the caster acting as conductor. When the caster touches a living creature, requiring a hit in melee if applicable, the victim loses two energy levels as if struck by a spectre. A monster permanently loses two Hit Dice, affecting hit points and attack ability. A character permanently loses levels, Hit Dice, hit points, and abilities until regained through adventuring, if applicable. The caster prepares for 3 segments, casts forth the material component, then speaks the triggering word upon touching the victim. There is always a 5% chance the caster is also affected, losing one energy level while the victim loses two. Humans or humanoids reduced to zero energy level by this spell become juju zombies. Material Component: Essence of spectre or vampire dust.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"holy word":{"name":"Holy Word","level":"7","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"Nil","duration":"Varies","aoe":"30 ft radius","components":"V","ct":"Fast","save":"None (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Holy Word / Unholy Word\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” radius\nThe utterance of a holy word or unholy word has tremendous power. It drives off evil or good creatures from other planes, forcing them to return to their own planes of existence. It also affects creatures of differing alignment within the 6” diameter area of effect centered on the cleric. Creatures with fewer than 4 Hit Dice or levels are killed. Creatures with 4 to 7+ Hit Dice or levels are paralyzed for 1d4 turns. Creatures with 8 to 11+ Hit Dice or levels are stunned for 2d4 rounds, move at -50%, and attack at -4. Creatures with 12 or more Hit Dice or levels are deafened for 1d4 rounds, move at -25%, attack at -2, and have a 50% chance of spell failure.","notes":"Utter a holy word; all non-good-aligned creatures in the area suffer severe effects.\nDetails:\n    All fiends and evil-aligned elementals are instantly banished to their home plane.\n    Other non-good creatures suffer based on level/HD:\n        < 4: Killed (instant)\n        4–7: Paralyzed for 10d4 rounds\n        8–11: Move halved; -4 to attacks for 2d4 rounds\n            11: Move -10 ft; -2 to attacks for 1d4 rounds\n    Deities/similar power unaffected.\n    Does not work in the Lower Outer Planes.\n    Alignment interpretation is GM-facing: some tables apply it to any non-good; others only to evil.\nReversible as Unholy Word.","link":""},"regenerate":{"name":"Regenerate","level":"7","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Regenerate\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Wither\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell causes body members, bones, or organs to grow back, including fingers, toes, hands, feet, arms, legs, tails, and even the heads of multi-headed creatures. Regeneration takes 1 round if the severed member is present and touching the creature, or 2d8 turns otherwise. The reverse, wither, causes the touched member or organ to shrivel and stop functioning in 1 round, then drop off into dust in 2d8 turns. As usual, the target must be touched for the harmful effect. Material Components: A prayer device and holy or unholy water.","notes":"Regrows or reattaches a lost body part; also heals organ damage or injuries not addressed by Heal/Cure spells (e.g., can restore sight to damaged eyes).\nDetails:\n    Target must be alive. Cannot restore head or brain; if missing, spell fails.\n    If severed part is present: instantly reattached.\n    If missing/destroyed: regrows over 2d4 combat rounds.\n    Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, undead.\nReversible as Wither.","link":""},"restoration":{"name":"Restoration","level":"7","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Restoration\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Energy Drain\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell raises the recipient’s life energy level upward by one, restoring a previous life energy level drained by a force or monster. For example, if a 10th-level character was struck by a wight and drained to 9th level, restoration restores the character to exactly the number of experience points needed for 10th level, with additional Hit Dice or hit points and level functions restored accordingly. Restoration works only if cast within 1 day per caster level after the life energy loss. The reverse, energy drain, removes one life energy level and requires the victim to be touched. Restoration also restores the Intelligence of a creature affected by feeblemind.","notes":"Restores one lost level from undead level drain (or similar). Also has broader restorative effects at GM discretion.\nDetails:\n    Must be cast within one day per your cleric level of the level loss; outside that window it cannot restore.\n    Target gains enough XP to be at the start of the restored level.\n    Ends feeblemind or similar mind-damaging effects.\nReversible as Energy Drain.","link":""},"resurrection":{"name":"Resurrection","level":"7","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"The piece of flesh or bone you choose","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"Only when used vs undead","save_type":"","description":"Resurrection\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Destruction\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Person touched\nThis spell restores life and complete strength to the person touched. The person may have been dead up to 10 years per caster level, so a 19th-level cleric can resurrect the bones of a person dead up to 190 years. See raise dead for limitations on what persons can be raised. The reverse, destruction, causes the victim to die instantly and turn to dust. Destruction requires a touch, in combat or otherwise. Using this spell makes it impossible for the cleric to cast further spells or engage in combat until they have had 1 day of bed rest per level of the person brought back to life or destroyed. Material Components: The cleric’s religious symbol and holy or unholy water.","notes":"Returns the dead to life by returning a soul to a portion of its body and regrowing the rest if needed. Target remembers dying but not the interval while dead.\nDetails:\n    If successful: returns with full hit points; retains prepared spells/unused slots it had at death.\n    Missing parts are restored.\n    Default ancestry limitation (unless GM says otherwise): works on humans, half-elves, gnomes, dwarfs, halflings; not elves or half-orcs (souls vs spirits rationale).\n    Death must be within 10 years per your cleric level (but can still be used against older-dead undead).\n    Requires at least 1 ounce of flesh/bone (not fingernail/hair).\n    Target must be deceased (cannot clone from a living body part).\n    Target must pass a Resurrection Success roll (by CON). Failure makes the target forever dead to further resurrection/raise dead.\nAgainst undead:\n    Undead saves vs spells/magical effects.\n        Pass: takes 5d8+5 corrosion damage; no other effect. (Lich or vampire > century gets +4 on this save.)\n        Fail: returned to life if within time limit; otherwise crumbles to dust.\nReversible as Surcease.","link":""},"surcease":{"name":"Surcease","level":"7","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"Yes (lessened effect)","save_type":"","description":"Kills the target on a failed save; damages on a successful save. Involves an Abominable Word that prevents future raising/resurrection of the body (except by a deity/similar power).\nDetails:\n    Abominable Words may be lost secrets in some campaigns.\n    Default ancestry limitation (unless GM says otherwise): humans, half-elves, gnomes, dwarfs, halflings; not elves/half-orcs.\n    Requires touch (may require to-hit roll). Target may save vs spells/magical effects:\n        Pass: takes 5d8+5 corrosion damage.\n        Fail: dies instantly and cannot be raised/resurrected except by deity-level intervention.","notes":"Kills the target on a failed save; damages on a successful save. Involves an Abominable Word that prevents future raising/resurrection of the body (except by a deity/similar power).\nDetails:\n    Abominable Words may be lost secrets in some campaigns.\n    Default ancestry limitation (unless GM says otherwise): humans, half-elves, gnomes, dwarfs, halflings; not elves/half-orcs.\n    Requires touch (may require to-hit roll). Target may save vs spells/magical effects:\n        Pass: takes 5d8+5 corrosion damage.\n        Fail: dies instantly and cannot be raised/resurrected except by deity-level intervention.","link":""},"unholy word":{"name":"Unholy Word","level":"7","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"Nil","duration":"Varies","aoe":"30 ft radius","components":"V","ct":"Fast","save":"None (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Holy Word / Unholy Word\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” radius\nThe utterance of a holy word or unholy word has tremendous power. It drives off evil or good creatures from other planes, forcing them to return to their own planes of existence. It also affects creatures of differing alignment within the 6” diameter area of effect centered on the cleric. Creatures with fewer than 4 Hit Dice or levels are killed. Creatures with 4 to 7+ Hit Dice or levels are paralyzed for 1d4 turns. Creatures with 8 to 11+ Hit Dice or levels are stunned for 2d4 rounds, move at -50%, and attack at -4. Creatures with 12 or more Hit Dice or levels are deafened for 1d4 rounds, move at -25%, attack at -2, and have a 50% chance of spell failure.","notes":"Utter an unholy word; all non-evil-aligned creatures in the area suffer severe effects.\nDetails:\n    All celestials and good-aligned elementals are instantly banished to their home plane.\n    Other non-evil creatures suffer based on level/HD (same table structure as Holy Word):\n        < 4: Killed (instant)\n        4–7: Paralyzed for 10d4 rounds\n        8–11: Move halved; -4 to attacks for 2d4 rounds\n            11: Move -10 ft; -2 to attacks for 1d4 rounds\n    Deities/similar power unaffected.\n    Does not work in the Upper Outer Planes.","link":""},"wind walk":{"name":"Wind Walk","level":"7","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Caster","duration":"1 hour per cleric level","aoe":"Creatures of your choice within 20 ft radius of you","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wind Walk\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell enables the cleric, and possibly one or two others, to transform their bodies into cloud-like vapors. A magical wind carries the cleric at a speed from 6” to 60” per turn, as the caster wills. The spell lasts as long as the cleric desires, up to 6 turns, or 1 hour, per caster level. For every 8 levels of experience the cleric has, up to 24, they may touch and carry one additional person, up to two persons total. Wind-walking persons are not invisible, but appear misty and transparent. If fully clothed in white, they are 80% likely to be mistaken for clouds, fog, vapors, or similar forms. Material Components: Fire and holy or unholy water.","notes":"Turns you and designated creatures into magical vapor (cloud/steam). In this form you can fly and pass through any gap wider than ½ inch.\nDetails:\n    Must affect you. Also includes up to 1 human-sized creature per 8 cleric levels.\n    Only willing creatures affected; any affected creature may end the spell on itself at any time.\n    Movement: 60 ft per round.\n    If the spell ends while flying: creature falls immediately.\n    If the spell ends while in a narrow space: takes 6d6 blunt damage, then appears prone in the nearest unoccupied space.","link":""},"wither":{"name":"Wither","level":"7","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None (but see below)","save_type":"","description":"Regenerate\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Wither\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell causes body members, bones, or organs to grow back, including fingers, toes, hands, feet, arms, legs, tails, and even the heads of multi-headed creatures. Regeneration takes 1 round if the severed member is present and touching the creature, or 2d8 turns otherwise. The reverse, wither, causes the touched member or organ to shrivel and stop functioning in 1 round, then drop off into dust in 2d8 turns. As usual, the target must be touched for the harmful effect. Material Components: A prayer device and holy or unholy water.","notes":"Degenerates living tissue (opposite of Regenerate).\nDetails:\n    On a successful touch, target may save vs spells; on success takes half damage.\n    Damage: 8d12+32 corrosion, or 4d12+16 on a successful save.\n    If you touched a limb and it failed its save, the limb withers.\n    Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, undead.","link":""},"bless":{"name":"Bless","level":"1","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"60 ft","duration":"6 rounds","aoe":"Cube, 50 ft × 50 ft × 50 ft","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Bless\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nReversible: Curse\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 6 melee rounds\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 5” × 5”\nUpon uttering the bless spell, the caster raises the morale of friendly creatures by +1 and gives them a +1 bonus to “to hit” rolls. A bless spell affects only creatures not already engaged in melee combat. The spell may be reversed as curse, lowering enemies’ morale and “to hit” rolls by -1. The caster determines the range, up to 6”, and the spell affects all creatures in a 5” square area centered on the chosen point. Material Component: Bless requires holy water. Curse requires specially polluted water.","notes":"The selected creatures in the area of effect may choose to gain +1 to “to hit” rolls in combat and +5% to morale checks.\n\nDetails:\n\nThis spell can target creatures within the area of effect that aren’t in melee when the spell is cast (they must be 10 ft distant from enemies).\n\nWhen you cast the spell, you can choose any number of creatures and decide they aren’t affected.\n\nThis spell is normally used as a blessing on your allies (and yourself), granting bonuses in combat and morale checks.\n\nAlternatively, you may bless an object or a place, even if you memorised the spell for blessing creatures. This usually has no direct game-mechanical effect, but can influence events outside the ordinary rules.","link":""},"ceremony":{"name":"Ceremony","level":"1","school":"Invocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature, one item, or area","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 hour","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Ceremony\n\nSchool: Invocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 hour\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature, one item, or area\nCeremony has several religious applications, depending on the cleric’s level. The spell does not leave behind a magical aura, though in some cases an aura of good or evil may be present and detectable. The specific ceremonies vary by religion, but usually include: 1st-level cleric: coming of age, burial, marriage; 3rd-level cleric: dedication, investiture, consecrate item; 5th-level cleric: ordination, special vows; 7th-level cleric: consecrate ground; 9th-level cleric: anathematize. Each ceremony requires a cleric of the indicated level or higher. Except for anathematize, no saving throw is required because the recipient is either inanimate or presumed willing; if the recipient is unwilling, the ceremony simply fails. Coming of age is a limited bless cast upon a young person, often around age 12. The recipient gains a +1 bonus to any single saving throw, usable at any time after the ceremony. In some cultures, this rite has symbolic importance and grants the rights and privileges of adulthood. Burial magically protects a corpse and grants it the blessing of the religious organization. The body is protected for one week as if by protection from evil, and anyone trying to disinter it during that time must save versus spell or stop and flee in fear for 1 turn. Marriage has no tangible magical after-effect and does not guarantee happiness or harmony, but usually has moral or legal significance. Dedication admits the recipient into the casting cleric’s religion, making them a sanctioned worshiper of the cleric’s deity. The dedication is permanent unless the worshiper changes allegiance to another deity. A previous dedication can be overridden by a new dedication cast by a cleric of higher level than the one who performed the earlier rite. Investiture must be performed on an aspiring cleric before the character can become a 1st-level cleric. Consecrate item must be performed on any object placed on an altar or within a religious edifice. Holy or unholy water must be kept in a properly consecrated container to prevent loss of potency. Ordination must be performed on a cleric before the character can become priest of a congregation, assume similar duties, gain followers, or establish a following. The cleric performing the ordination must be higher level than the recipient. Special vows may be received by a would-be cavalier or paladin before beginning that profession. The effects last until the character gains enough experience to reach the upper limit of their current level. The vows may then be renewed during training between levels or while advancing through the next level. A cavalier or paladin under special vows is immune to bestow curse spells, though not cursed items, while the vows remain in effect. The subject is also more susceptible to any quest spell cast by a cleric of the same alignment as the caster of the vows, suffering a -4 saving throw penalty. Consecrate ground should be performed before any holy or unholy structure is built on a site. A religious edifice built on unconsecrated ground slowly and irrevocably falls into disrepair and has a cumulative 1% chance per year of collapsing. The spell must be cast before the area is altered or construction materials are brought to the site; it has no effect if done afterward. Consecrated ground may also be used for a graveyard, in which case the graveyard automatically turns undead each round as a 3rd-level cleric. If performed by an evil cleric, undead in the area are treated as protected and controlled by an evil 3rd-level cleric. Anathematize is excommunication that brands the offender on the cheek, forehead, arm, or hand with a symbol, sigil, or sign identifying the subject as someone who has committed a serious offense against their deity. An unwilling subject may save versus spell at -4 to avoid the effect. If the recipient is not truly deserving, the spell fails. A successful atonement causes the brand to fade and possibly vanish. If the offense was caused magically or by an external force, the brand disappears completely. If the actions were natural, the brand cannot be fully removed. Material Component: The cleric’s holy symbol is always involved, though other components vary by religion. Standard costs are: coming of age, 5–15 sp; burial, 5–50 gp; marriage, 1–20 gp; dedication, 1–10 sp or sometimes free; investiture, 1–100 gp or sometimes free; item consecration, usually free; ordination, usually free but possibly up to 200 gp; special vows, 1–100 gp or sometimes free; consecrate ground, 100–600 gp depending on area and caster level; anathematize, always free.","notes":"Coming of age, burial, marriage, dedication, investiture, consecrate item, ordination, special vows, consecrate ground, and anathematize are all covered by this spell depending on cleric level. Material component always involves the cleric’s holy symbol.","link":""},"combine":{"name":"Combine","level":"1","school":"Evocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"The circle of clerics","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Combine\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The circle of clerics\nThis spell allows three to five clerics to combine their abilities and empower one of their number to cast a spell or turn undead with greater efficacy. The highest-level cleric, or one of them if tied, stands in the center while the others join hands in a surrounding circle. All participating clerics cast combine together. The central cleric temporarily functions as if higher level, gaining one level for each encircling cleric. The maximum gain is 4 levels, and the maximum duration is 3 turns. The increase applies to effective level for turning undead and for spell details that vary by caster level. The encircling clerics must concentrate to maintain the effect. They gain no Armor Class bonuses from shield or Dexterity, and attackers gain a +4 bonus on “to hit” rolls against them. The central cleric gains no additional spells, but may cast previously memorized spells, often with improved effects.","notes":"Three to five clerics combine power; the central cleric gains one effective level per supporting cleric, up to +4 levels, for up to 3 turns.","link":""},"command":{"name":"Command","level":"1","school":"Divine enchantment","range":"10 ft","duration":"1 round","aoe":"One creature","components":"V","ct":"Fast","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"Command\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell allows the cleric to issue a single-word command. The command must be spoken in a language the target can understand. The target obeys to the best of its ability, but only if the command is absolutely clear and unequivocal. For example, “Suicide!” could be interpreted as a noun and would be ignored. “Die!” causes the target to fall into a faint or cataleptic state for 1 round, after which the creature is alive and well. Typical command words include: back, halt, flee, run, stop, fall, fly, go, leave, surrender, sleep, and rest. Undead are unaffected. Creatures with Intelligence 13 or higher, or creatures with 6 or more Hit Dice or experience levels, receive a saving throw versus magic. A creature that meets both conditions does not receive two saving throws.","notes":"You issue a one-word command to the target creature, and it may be forced to obey for one round. The command must be very clear (unambiguous), so only a few commands are normally used.\n\nDetails:\n\nThe creature must be able to hear you, and it doesn’t have to obey unless the command is in a language it understands.\n\nThis spell is considered a charm and a form of mental domination, so many creatures—such as golems, constructs, elementals, and undead—are immune.\n\nThe target creature doesn’t have to obey unless the command is a verb.","link":""},"create water":{"name":"Create Water","level":"1","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"10 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"See below","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Create Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Destroy Water\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Up to 27 cubic feet\nThis spell creates 4 gallons of clean, drinkable water per caster level. For example, a 2nd-level cleric creates 8 gallons, a 3rd-level cleric creates 12 gallons, and so on. The reverse, destroy water, obliterates an equal quantity of water without leaving vapor, mist, fog, or steam. Created water remains until normally used, evaporated, spilled, or otherwise lost. The water may be created or destroyed in an area just large enough to contain it, up to a maximum area of 27 cubic feet, or one cubic yard. Material Component: A drop of water is required to create water. A pinch of dust is required to destroy water. Water cannot be created inside a living thing.","notes":"For each level you have in the cleric class, you conjure up to sixteen litres of water from the Elemental Plane of Water at a targeted point. You may limit the amount created.\n\nDetails:\n\nUnless the target point is inside a receptacle, the water immediately spills.\n\nThe target point can’t be inside a creature.","link":""},"cure light wounds":{"name":"Cure Light Wounds","level":"1","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Light Wounds\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Cause Light Wounds\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Character touched\nBy laying a hand upon a creature, the cleric heals 1d8 hit points of wound or injury damage. This healing does not affect creatures without corporeal bodies, nonliving creatures, or creatures that can only be harmed by iron, silver, and/or magical weapons. The reverse, cause light wounds, deals 1d8 points of damage. If the target avoids the touch, the cleric must make a melee “to hit” roll to determine whether the touch succeeds. Healed wounds remain healed unless the creature takes further damage. Caused wounds heal naturally or may be cured as normal injuries.","notes":"The target regains 1d8 hit points, up to its normal maximum. Healing beyond the target’s normal maximum is wasted. You must be able to see and touch the target.\n\nDetails:\n\nThis spell can’t cure disease, reattach limbs, raise the dead, or heal afflictions not measured in hit points.\n\nIn general, the spell affects only normally living creatures. It has no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.","link":""},"endure cold/heat":{"name":"Endure Cold/Heat","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"9 turns/level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"The recipient of this spell is protected from normal extremes of cold or heat, depending upon which application is used. He or she can stand unclothed in temperatures as low as -30°F or as high as 130°F without ill effect. A temperature extreme beyond those limits causes 1 hit point of exposure damage per hour for every degree above or below the limit. Without such protection, exposure damage is 1 hit point per turn for each degree of temperature. The spell lasts for the stated duration, or until the recipient is affected by any form of magical cold or magical heat. The recipient does not suffer damage from the magical heat or cold during the round in which the spell is broken, but is vulnerable to all such attacks beginning on the following round. The spell is also cancelled instantly if either resist fire or resist cold is cast upon the recipient.","notes":"Reversible. Protects from normal heat or cold, but ends when magical heat or cold affects the subject.","link":""},"invisibility to undead":{"name":"Invisibility to Undead","level":"1","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"6 rounds","aoe":"One individual","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Invisibility To Undead\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 6 rounds\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One individual\nThis spell is similar to sanctuary, but affects only undead of 4 or fewer Hit Dice. A saving throw versus spell is made for each type of undead within 30 feet of the caster. If the save fails, all undead of that type ignore the caster completely for the duration. This negates later attempts by the caster to turn those undead. If the saving throw succeeds, all undead of that type attack the caster in preference to any other target. The spell ends if the caster attacks or attempts to cast another spell. If the caster is morally neutral with respect to good and evil, the undead save at -2. Material Component: The cleric’s holy symbol.","notes":"Material component: the cleric’s holy symbol. Affects undead of 4 HD or fewer only.","link":""},"magic stone":{"name":"Magic Stone","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"2”","duration":"6 rounds or until used","aoe":"One small stone or pebble","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Magic Stone\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 2”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 6 rounds or until used\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One small stone or pebble\nTo cast this spell, the cleric picks up a small stone or pebble and places a magical aura upon it. The spell cannot affect stones that are already magical. The magic stone may be thrown at a target up to 4” away, assuming no obstacles and enough headroom. It acts as a +1 weapon for “to hit” determination, and a hit deals 1 point of damage. Ranges are 2”/3”/4”, with standard range modifiers. If the stone travels more than 4” from the thrower or misses, it loses its dweomer and falls harmlessly to the ground. The stone must be thrown within 6 rounds after casting or it becomes ordinary again. A hit breaks a spellcaster’s concentration only if the victim fails a saving throw versus spell. Targets with innate magic resistance cannot be affected. A shield spell, brooch of shielding, protection from normal missiles, minor globe of invulnerability, or similar stronger magic protects against the stone. A 6th- through 10th-level cleric may enchant 2 stones; an 11th- through 15th-level cleric may enchant 3 stones; and one additional stone is allowed for every 5 caster levels beyond 11th. The cleric may give enchanted stones to another character to throw. Some religions may forbid this spell because it allows the cleric to use a missile weapon of sorts.","notes":"Creates one or more +1 stones that inflict 1 point of damage on a hit and may disrupt casting.","link":""},"penetrate disguise":{"name":"Penetrate Disguise","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"12”","duration":"1 round","aoe":"One individual","components":"V, S","ct":"2 rounds","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Penetrate Disguise\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 2 rounds\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One individual\nThis spell allows the cleric to see through a disguise made only of makeup or altered clothing. It does not reveal the target’s true class, profession, or actual appearance; it merely shows that the figure is posing as someone or something else. The spell does not detect actual rank or status, reveal illusions, or detect alignment deception, though it can detect whether a figure is affected by a friends spell. The target receives a saving throw versus spell. If the save succeeds, the disguise is enhanced in the cleric’s eyes, causing the caster to believe the target is exactly what they claim to be. A bless spell, magic armor, or protective magic item such as a cloak or ring grants the target an appropriate saving throw bonus.","notes":"Detects only non-magical disguises made with makeup or clothing. A successful save actually enhances the disguise in the caster’s eyes.","link":""},"portent":{"name":"Portent","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Spellcaster or figure touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Portent\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Spellcaster or figure touched\nThis spell allows the cleric to glimpse something of the recipient’s future “luck.” The luck modifies a future “to hit” roll or saving throw, though the affected roll is unknown to the character. After casting, the Dungeon Master secretly rolls 1d12 to determine which future roll is affected, and 1d6 to determine the modifier: 1 = -3, 2 = -2, 3 = -1, 4 = +1, 5 = +2, 6 = +3. Based on the 1d6 result, the DM tells the cleric whether the portent is good, fair, or poor; the recipient is usually also told. The d12 result is the number of qualifying “to hit” rolls or saving throws that must occur before the portent applies. For example, if 12 is rolled, the 12th such roll is affected. Only rolls made in life-or-death situations, such as combat or peril, count. Attempts to sidestep the portent by forcing harmless saves do not count. Qualifying rolls include saving throws made in combat or against magical effects, “to hit” rolls made by the character, and “to hit” rolls made by an opponent against the character. When the designated roll occurs, it is adjusted up or down by the d6 result, making the character more or less likely to hit, be hit, or succeed on a saving throw. Material Component: A numbered wheel or tea leaves.","notes":"The DM secretly determines when the portent applies and whether it is favorable or unfavorable.","link":""},"precipitation":{"name":"Precipitation","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 segment per level","aoe":"3” diameter cylinder up to 12” high","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None and special","save_type":"","description":"Precipitation\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 segment per level\nSaving Throw: None and special\nArea of Effect: 3” diameter cylinder up to 12” high\nThis spell is identical to the 1st-level clerical spell precipitation, except that a holy symbol is not part of the material component.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"purify food & drink":{"name":"Purify Food & Drink","level":"1","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"30 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"1 cubic foot per cleric level","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Purify Food & Drink\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Putrefy Food & Drink\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per level, within a 1” square area\nThis spell makes spoiled, rotten, poisonous, or otherwise contaminated food and water pure and suitable for consumption. Up to 1 cubic foot of food and/or drink per caster level may be purified. The reverse, putrefy food & drink, spoils food and drink, including holy water. Unholy water is spoiled by purify water.","notes":"You detoxify a volume of food and drink, removing spoilage, disease, and poisons. This spell also neutralises unholy water.\n\nDetails:\n\nThis spell affects objects, not creatures.\n\nIt makes substances safe for you.","link":""},"remove fear":{"name":"Remove Fear","level":"1","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn, or instantaneous (see below)","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Remove Fear\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Cause Fear\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nBy touch, the cleric instills courage in the recipient, granting a +4 bonus to saving throws against magical fear for 1 turn. If the recipient has already failed a saving throw against fear, the touch allows another saving throw. This new save gains a bonus of +1 per caster level. A “to hit” roll is required to touch an unwilling recipient. The reverse, cause fear, causes the target to flee in panic at maximum movement speed away from the caster for 1 round per cleric level. Cause fear may be countered by remove fear, and vice versa.","notes":"This spell bolsters courage: it either grants new saving throws versus existing fear effects or provides a bonus to future saving throws against fear.\n\nDetails:\n\nIf the target is already affected by fear, the spell is instantaneous and grants one new saving throw.\n\nIf the target is not already affected by fear, duration is 1 turn and the target gains +4 on each saving throw against fear.","link":""},"resist cold":{"name":"Resist Cold","level":"1","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per cleric level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Resist Cold\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell protects the recipient’s body against cold. The recipient can withstand temperatures down to 0°F without discomfort, even while completely nude. Against greater cold, such as that from a sword of cold, ice storm, cold wand, or white dragon breath, the recipient receives a +3 bonus on saving throws. Cold damage is reduced as follows: failed saving throw, half damage; successful saving throw, one-quarter damage. The spell lasts 1 turn per caster level. Material Component: A pinch of sulphur.","notes":"This spell protects you or one creature from cold, including special protections against magical cold in combat.\n\nDetails:\n\nThe warded creature is safe from non-magical cold.\n\nAll cold damage is halved. If already halved, halve it again.","link":""},"sanctuary":{"name":"Sanctuary","level":"1","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"2 rounds + 1 round per cleric level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"Sanctuary\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nWhen the cleric casts sanctuary, any opponent attempting to strike or attack the protected cleric must make a saving throw versus magic. If the saving throw fails, the opponent ignores the cleric and attacks another target instead. If the saving throw succeeds, the opponent may attack the cleric normally, including attack rolls, saving throws, and damage. This spell does not protect against area attacks such as fireball or ice storm. While protected by sanctuary, the cleric may not take offensive action. The cleric may still cast non-attack spells or act in non-offensive ways, such as healing wounds, casting bless, performing an augury, chanting, or casting light in an area, but not upon an opponent. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol and a small silver mirror.","notes":"You ward yourself or one other creature so that enemies perceive the protected creature as a low-priority target.\n\nFor the duration, any creature attempting an attack or targeted spell against the protected creature must first attempt a saving throw vs spells.\n\nDetails:\n\nIf the protected creature makes a weapon attack or uses a spell that affects an enemy, the spell ends.","link":""},"endure cold endure heat":{"name":"Endure Cold / Endure Heat","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"9 turns per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Endure Cold / Endure Heat\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Endure Heat / Endure Cold\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 9 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell protects the recipient from normal extremes of cold or heat, depending on the version cast. The recipient can stand unclothed in temperatures as low as -30°F or as high as 130°F with no ill effect. Temperatures beyond those limits cause 1 hit point of exposure damage per hour for each degree beyond the limit. Without such protection, exposure damage is 1 hit point per turn per degree. The spell lasts for its duration or until the recipient is affected by any magical cold or magical heat, including white dragon breath. The spell is cancelled regardless of which version was used and regardless of whether magical heat or cold strikes the recipient. The recipient takes no damage from the magical heat or cold during the round in which the spell is broken, but is vulnerable starting the following round. The spell is instantly cancelled if resist fire or resist cold is cast on the recipient.","notes":"","link":""},"endure cold heat":{"name":"Endure Cold/Heat","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"9 turns per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Endure Cold / Endure Heat\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Endure Heat / Endure Cold\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 9 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell protects the recipient from normal extremes of cold or heat, depending on the version cast. The recipient can stand unclothed in temperatures as low as -30°F or as high as 130°F with no ill effect. Temperatures beyond those limits cause 1 hit point of exposure damage per hour for each degree beyond the limit. Without such protection, exposure damage is 1 hit point per turn per degree. The spell lasts for its duration or until the recipient is affected by any magical cold or magical heat, including white dragon breath. The spell is cancelled regardless of which version was used and regardless of whether magical heat or cold strikes the recipient. The recipient takes no damage from the magical heat or cold during the round in which the spell is broken, but is vulnerable starting the following round. The spell is instantly cancelled if resist fire or resist cold is cast on the recipient.","notes":"","link":""},"aid":{"name":"Aid","level":"2","school":"Necromantic-Conjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round + 1 round per level","aoe":"One person","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Aid\n\nSchool: Necromantic-Conjuration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One person\nThe recipient gains the benefit of a bless spell and a special blessing of 1d8 additional hit points. The bless effect and added hit points last for the duration of aid. The added hit points can raise the recipient above their normal maximum. Damage taken while aid is active is subtracted from the temporary hit points before regular hit points are lost. Temporary hit points granted by aid that are lost cannot be restored by curative magic. For example, a 1st-level fighter with 8 hit points who has taken 2 damage receives aid granting 6 temporary hit points. The fighter now has 12 hit points, 6 temporary. If then hit for 7 damage, all 6 temporary hit points and 1 regular hit point are lost. Material Components: A tiny strip of white cloth with sticky substance such as tree sap on the ends, plus the cleric’s holy symbol.","notes":"","link":""},"detect life":{"name":"Detect Life","level":"2","school":"Divination","range":"10’ per level","duration":"5 rounds","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Life\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 10’ per level\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 5 rounds\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell allows the cleric to determine whether a target creature is alive. It detects life in a recipient of feign death, a creature in a coma, deathlike trance, or suspended animation, and the body of a creature engaged in astral travel. It works on plants and plant creatures as well as animals. The spell’s range is reduced if more than 1 inch of wood or stone lies between the cleric and subject; each inch of wood or stone counts as 10 feet of open space. Any thickness of metal causes the spell to fail and be ruined. Any mental protection, whether psionic or magical, likewise ruins the spell without detection. The spell detects the first living creature along the cleric’s line of sight within range, or the first creature that crosses that line before the duration expires.","notes":"","link":""},"dust devil":{"name":"Dust Devil","level":"2","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Dust Devil\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell conjures a weak air elemental called a dust devil. It has AC 4, 2 Hit Dice, MV 18”, one attack for 1d4 damage, and can be hit by normal weapons. Magic weapons of any type deal double damage to it. The dust devil appears as a small whirlwind 5 feet across at its base, 15 feet tall, and 10 feet across at the top. It moves as directed by the cleric, but is dispelled if ordered farther than 3” from the caster. Its winds can hold a gas cloud or gaseous creature at bay or push it away from the caster, though they cannot damage or dispel such a cloud. The winds can extinguish torches, small campfires, exposed lanterns, and other small nonmagical open flames. If moving across loose dust, sand, or ash, the dust devil creates a 30-foot-diameter cloud centered on itself. Normal vision is impossible through the cloud, and creatures caught in it are effectively blinded until 1 round after leaving. Spellcasting is nearly impossible within the cloud or the dust devil itself; even if the dust devil deals no damage, a spellcaster must save versus spell to maintain concentration. Any creature native to the Elemental Plane of Air can dismiss a dust devil at will from 3” or less. Creatures not native to the caster’s plane are unaffected. The dust devil is automatically dispelled if it contacts a creature with innate magic resistance, but only after it has a chance to hit and deal damage.","notes":"","link":""},"enthrall":{"name":"Enthrall","level":"2","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"3”","duration":"Special","aoe":"90’ radius","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Enthrall\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 90’ radius\nThis spell allows the cleric to bind and enthrall an audience that fully understands the cleric’s language. Listeners of the same race as the cleric may save versus spell. Listeners of a different race generally unfriendly to the cleric’s race save at +4. Creatures with more than 4 levels or Hit Dice, or Wisdom greater than 15, cannot be enthralled. The caster must speak without interruption for 1 full round. Thereafter, the enchantment lasts as long as the cleric continues speaking, up to 6 turns. Those who fail their saves view the cleric as if the cleric had Charisma 21, with loyalty base +70% and reaction adjustment +50%. They stand and listen, but do not act as if under a suggestion. When the cleric stops talking, the spell ends and listeners regain control. Any attack on the cleric or any attempt by the cleric to cast another spell or take another action cancels the spell. Audience members who save successfully view the cleric as having Charisma 3 and may, with a 50% chance, hoot and jeer, allowing new saving throws for other listeners. If the cleric abuses the spell by preaching a religion or alignment opposed to the audience’s beliefs, each offended listener gets a new saving throw at +5.","notes":"","link":""},"holy symbol":{"name":"Holy Symbol","level":"2","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Holy Symbol\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One object\nThis spell prepares a cleric’s holy symbol or creates a new one to replace a lost or damaged symbol. The new symbol, which is the spell’s material component and is not consumed, must be made of appropriate material and proper shape and design for the religion or deity. A cleric cannot make just any object into a holy symbol. A cleric may possess two holy symbols at once, and this spell can create a spare. No cleric can create a holy symbol for a deity or religion other than their own. A good or evil cleric’s holy symbol radiates a faint aura of good or evil, but is not a magical object. A morally neutral cleric’s holy symbol has no such aura.","notes":"","link":""},"messenger":{"name":"Messenger","level":"2","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"2” per level","duration":"1 hour per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Messenger\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2” per level\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 hour per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell allows the cleric to call upon a Small creature of at least animal intelligence to act as a messenger. It does not affect giant creatures, creatures with Intelligence 4 or higher, or creatures with low intelligence or better. If the creature is within range, the cleric may use desirable food as a lure to call it. The animal receives a saving throw versus spell; success causes the spell to fail. If the save fails, the animal approaches the cleric and awaits bidding. The cleric can communicate crudely with it, directing it to a certain place, though directions must be simple. The caster may attach a small item or note to the animal. If instructed, the animal waits at the location until the spell ends. If the intended recipient is not expecting an animal messenger, the carrier may be ignored. When the duration ends, the animal returns to normal activity. The intended receiver gains no communication ability.","notes":"","link":""},"withdraw":{"name":"Withdraw","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"The cleric","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Withdraw\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The cleric\nThis spell alters time’s flow with respect to the cleric. While only 1 segment passes for others, the cleric experiences 1 round for contemplation. The base duration is 2 segments, or 2 rounds from the cleric’s perspective, plus 1 additional increment per caster level. Thus, a 5th-level cleric may spend up to 6 rounds thinking while only 6 segments pass for everyone else. The Dungeon Master must allow the player 1 minute of real time per segment to ponder a problem or question. Discussion with unaffected characters is not permitted. While under withdraw, the cleric may only think, read, or cast augury, curing or healing spells, or informational spells, and such spells may only be cast on the cleric. Casting them differently, such as curing a companion, ends withdraw. The cleric cannot walk, run, become invisible, or take other actions. The cleric can still be affected by others, and any successful attack against the cleric breaks the spell.","notes":"","link":""},"wyvern watch":{"name":"Wyvern Watch","level":"2","school":"Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"8 hours or until strike","aoe":"10’ diameter sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Wyvern Watch\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 8 hours or until strike\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 10’ diameter sphere\nThis spell creates an insubstantial haze vaguely resembling a wyvern and is commonly used to guard an area. Any creature approaching within 1” of the guarded area is subject to attack by the spell force. The “wyvern” strikes, and the target must save versus spell or stand paralyzed for 1 round per caster level, or until freed by the caster, dispel magic, or remove paralysis. A successful save means the wyvern-form missed, and the spell remains in place. Once a creature is successfully struck and paralyzed, the spell dissipates. It also dissipates if no intruder is struck within 8 hours. A creature approaching the guarded space may detect the presence of the wyvern-form before coming close enough to be attacked: 90% in bright light, 30% in twilight, and 0% in darkness. Material Component: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol.\n\nCleric Spells, 3rd Level","notes":"","link":""},"cloudburst":{"name":"Cloudburst","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round","aoe":"3” diameter cylinder up to 6” high","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None and special","save_type":"","description":"Cloudburst\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: None and special\nArea of Effect: 3” diameter cylinder up to 6” high\nThis spell is identical to the 3rd-level clerical spell cloudburst, except that a holy symbol is not part of the material component.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"death s door":{"name":"Death’s Door","level":"3","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"1 hour per level","aoe":"One human or demi-human","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Death’s Door\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 hour per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One human or demi-human\nThis spell allows the cleric to touch a human or demi-human who is unconscious and “at death’s door,” meaning at -1 to -9 hit points. The spell immediately brings the individual to 0 hit points. While the subject remains unconscious, bleeding and deterioration stop for the spell’s duration. Because the subject is now at 0 hit points, they may be restored to consciousness and healed by cure light wounds, cure serious wounds, healing potions, extra-healing potions, or other magical healing. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol, a bit of white linen, and any form of unguent.","notes":"","link":""},"flame walk":{"name":"Flame Walk","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn + 1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Flame Walk\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 turn + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the caster or another man-sized creature of comparable mass to withstand nonmagical fires up to 2,000°F. It also grants a +2 bonus on saving throws against magical fires. For each caster level above the minimum required to cast the spell, the cleric may affect one additional man-sized creature. This allows multiple individuals or larger creatures to be affected. For example, an 11th-level caster could affect both themselves and a horse, allowing mounted travel through molten lava. A horse counts as 6 humans for this spell; halfling-sized creatures count as ½ human, and pixie-sized creatures count as ¼ human. Material Components: At least 500 gp worth of powdered ruby and the cleric’s holy or unholy symbol.","notes":"","link":""},"magical vestment":{"name":"Magical Vestment","level":"3","school":"Conjuration/Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 rounds per level","aoe":"The cleric","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Magical Vestment\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 6 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The cleric\nThis spell enchants the caster’s vestment, providing protection equivalent to armor. It functions only while the cleric is on ground consecrated to their deity. If armor or another protective device is worn during the spell, the vestment protects as normal chain mail. If no other protection is worn, the vestment gains a +1 enchantment for every 4 caster levels, to a maximum of chain mail +4, or base AC 1. The spell lasts 6 rounds per caster level, or until the caster loses consciousness or leaves the consecrated area. Material Components: The vestment to be enchanted and the cleric’s holy or unholy symbol.","notes":"","link":""},"meld into stone":{"name":"Meld Into Stone","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"8 rounds + 1d8 rounds","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Meld Into Stone\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 8 rounds + 1d8 rounds\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the cleric to merge their body and worn or carried possessions into a large stone. The cleric must stand next to a stone large enough to contain their body in all three dimensions while holding a small sample of the same type of stone. When casting is complete, the cleric and up to 100 pounds of nonliving gear blend into the stone. Magical artifacts and relics are unaffected. If the stone is too small or the cleric carries more than 100 pounds of gear, the spell fails and is wasted. The spell lasts 9–16 rounds, with the variable portion secretly rolled by the DM. Before the duration expires, the cleric may step out through the same surface used to enter. The spell does not allow movement through stone as passwall or phase door would. If the duration ends before the cleric exits, the cleric is expelled and takes 4d8 damage, and each affected item must save versus petrification or turn to stone. While inside the stone, the cleric is aware of time passing but cannot see or hear outside events. Certain spells harm the cleric if cast on the occupied stone: stone to flesh expels the cleric and deals 4d8 damage, but items need not save; stone shape deals 4d4 damage without expelling the cleric; transmute rock to mud expels the cleric and kills them instantly unless they save versus spell.","notes":"","link":""},"negative plane protection":{"name":"Negative Plane Protection","level":"3","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"One Prime Material Plane creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Negative Plane Protection\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One Prime Material Plane creature\nThis spell partially protects the caster or another touched creature from undead with existence on the Negative Material Plane, such as shadows, wights, wraiths, spectres, and vampires. The spell opens a channel to the Positive Material Plane, offsetting the undead attack. If the recipient is touched or attacked by such an undead creature, the recipient may save versus death magic. Success means the recipient takes normal hit point damage but suffers no experience drain; the undead creature also takes 2d6 damage from Positive Plane energy. The magic protects against only one such attack and then dissipates whether the saving throw succeeds or fails. If the saving throw fails, the recipient takes double normal physical damage in addition to the usual experience loss. The spell also protects against a magic-user’s energy drain, though the magic-user is not harmed. Contact between Positive and Negative Planes causes a bright flash and thunderclap sound, but neither causes damage. The spell lasts 1 turn per caster level or until triggered by a successful undead attack. This spell cannot be cast on the Negative Material Plane.","notes":"","link":""},"remove paralysis":{"name":"Remove Paralysis","level":"3","school":"Abjuration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1–4 creatures in a 2” × 2” area","components":"V, S","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Remove Paralysis\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Cause Paralysis\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1–4 creatures in a 2” × 2” area\nThis spell frees creatures from paralysis or similar forces, such as a hold spell. The cleric casts the spell and points in the proper direction, affecting up to 4 creatures within range and area of effect. There must be no physical or magical barrier between caster and targets, or the spell fails and is wasted. Each target receives a new saving throw versus paralysis, with a +3 bonus if one creature is affected, +2 if two creatures are affected, and +1 if three or four creatures are affected. The reverse, cause paralysis, affects one touched target. The cleric must touch the victim with a successful “to hit” roll using the holy or unholy symbol. If the victim fails a saving throw versus spell, paralysis lasts 1d6 rounds plus 1 round per caster level. Good-aligned clerics should be discerning in using cause paralysis, and some good-aligned orders may prohibit it.","notes":"","link":""},"water walk":{"name":"Water Walk","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn + 1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Water Walk\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 turn + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the caster or another man-sized creature of comparable mass to walk on water as if it were firm, grassy ground. For each caster level above the minimum required to create the dweomer, the cleric may affect one additional man-sized creature. This allows multiple individuals or larger creatures to be affected. For example, an 11th-level caster could also affect a horse, allowing mounted travel atop waves. A horse counts as 6 humans for this spell. Material Components: A piece of cork and the cleric’s holy or unholy symbol.\n\nCleric Spells, 4th Level","notes":"","link":""},"abjure":{"name":"Abjure","level":"4","school":"Abjuration","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Abjure\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Implore\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell attempts to return a creature from another plane to its own plane. The cleric must know the exact name of the creature type, and if the creature has a proper name, that name must also be known and used. The cleric compares their level to the creature’s level or Hit Dice as with dispel magic: base 50% chance of success, adjusted by the level or Hit Dice difference. If the percentile roll is equal to or less than the chance to abjure, the creature is instantly sent back to its plane. Otherwise, the spell fails. The creature may not wish to remain on the caster’s plane and could be appreciative. The reverse, implore, entreats a like-aligned creature from another plane to come to the cleric. Success is determined the same way, and the caster must know the creature type’s exact name and proper name if any. If implore succeeds, there is no guarantee the summoned creature is favorably disposed. Neither version works on deities, though it may affect their servants or minions. Material Components: For abjure, a holy or unholy symbol, holy or unholy water, and often something inimical to the creature. For implore, the same components are used except the last must be something the implored creature craves or respects.","notes":"","link":""},"cloak of fear":{"name":"Cloak of Fear","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"The cleric","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Cloak Of Fear\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nReversible: Cloak Of Bravery\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: The cleric\nThis spell causes the cleric to radiate a personal aura of fear to a 30-foot radius. Any creature or character entering the aura must save versus spell or flee in fear for 6 rounds. The spell remains until one creature fails its save, at which point the dweomer dissipates. The spell has no effect on creatures that radiate fear or undead of any sort, and contact with such creatures does not dissipate it. It also remains if an intruder saves successfully, but expires after 1 turn per caster level if not triggered earlier. Members of the cleric’s party are not immune. The cleric may cancel the aura before the duration ends. The reverse, cloak of bravery, may be cast on the cleric or another willing creature. The recipient gains a +3 bonus on a saving throw against magical fear. The spell works only once and only for one figure, and is dispelled whether or not the recipient succeeds. It does not negate a creature’s innate fear aura, so that creature can still affect others nearby. Material Components: For cloak of fear, a miniature quiver and a chicken feather. For cloak of bravery, a drop of alcohol and the brain of a newt.","notes":"","link":""},"giant insect":{"name":"Giant Insect","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"2”","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"One or more insects","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Giant Insect\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Shrink Insect\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2”\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One or more insects\nThis spell transforms one or more normal insects into larger forms resembling giant insects. The number and total Hit Dice depend on caster level: at 7th–9th level, one insect and 3 total Hit Dice; at 10th–11th level, two insects and 4 total Hit Dice; at 12th–13th level, three insects and 5 total Hit Dice; at 14th level or higher, four insects and 6 total Hit Dice. The spell affects only one type of insect per casting. Casting time is 1 round per Hit Die of the resulting giant creature or creatures; if interrupted, the insects die and the spell is ruined. A created monster has as many attacks per round as its standard giant version, but deals full damage only if it has as many Hit Dice as that usual form. It can never exceed the listed damage for the standard giant form. For example, a 14th-level cleric can enlarge a wasp to 6 Hit Dice, instead of the usual 4 Hit Dice, but its damage remains 2d8/1d4. A 7th-level cleric could create a 3-Hit-Die giant wasp dealing 2d6/1d3, or three-fourths normal damage. The spell works only on true insects, not arachnids, crustaceans, or other small creatures. Created giant insects do not gain the special attacks or defenses of standard giant forms, though armor class, movement, and physical characteristics are as listed. Created insects do not attack the cleric, but the cleric’s control is limited to simple commands such as attack, defend, or guard. They cannot be directed to attack a specific creature or guard against a particular event. Unless commanded otherwise, they attack whatever is nearby. The reverse, shrink insect, reduces standard giant insects or insects created by this spell. Reduction is 1 Hit Die per 4 caster levels, to a maximum reduction of 6 Hit Dice and a minimum of 1/8 Hit Die or 1 hit point. Special attacks are retained at weaker level, allowing saving throw bonuses. For example, a 9th-level cleric can reduce a 4-Hit-Die giant wasp to 1 Hit Die; it retains poison, but saves against it gain at least +3, and normal damage is reduced to one-fourth. Material Component: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol.","notes":"","link":""},"imbue with spell ability":{"name":"Imbue With Spell Ability","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"One individual","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Imbue With Spell Ability\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One individual\nThis spell allows the cleric to bestow the ability to cast a particular spell on a character normally unable to cast spells. It works only on thieves, fighters, cavaliers, assassins, monks, rangers below 8th level, and paladins below 9th level. It does not work on other classes or subclasses, monsters, or individuals with less than one full Hit Die. The transferred spells must be spells the cleric currently has prepared, and they must be informational or defensive spells, or cure light wounds. Attempting to transfer any other spell causes the whole spell to fail, even if allowable spells were also chosen. Up to three spells may be imbued: one 2nd-level spell and one or two 1st-level spells. To receive any spell, the recipient must have Wisdom 9 or higher. A single 1st-level spell may be imbued in any eligible recipient. The recipient must be at least 3rd level to receive two 1st-level spells, and at least 5th level to receive a 2nd-level spell. If transferred spell characteristics vary by caster level, the recipient casts them at their own level. All other spell details, such as casting time and components, apply normally. When the cleric casts this spell, the transferred spells are lost from the cleric’s repertoire, and the cleric cannot memorize more spells until the recipient uses all transferred spells. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol, plus a minor borrowed item symbolic of the recipient’s profession, such as a lock pick for a thief or dagger for an assassin. The borrowed item is consumed.","notes":"","link":""},"spell immunity":{"name":"Spell Immunity","level":"4","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"One individual","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Spell Immunity\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One individual\nThis spell makes the cleric or touched creature immune to the effects of one specified spell of 4th level or lower that the cleric has directly experienced. For example, if the cleric has previously been struck by fireball, the spell can protect someone from fireball. It cannot affect a recipient already magically protected by a spell or other temporary effect. The spell protects only against actual cast spells, not magic item effects or innate spell-like abilities, but immunity lasts for the full duration. Only one spell immunity may affect a creature at a time; later applications have no effect until the first ends. The immunity does not extend to carried items, which must still save normally if applicable. Protection applies only to one specific spell, not to a class or group of similar spells. Thus, immunity to lightning bolt does not protect against shocking grasp. Material Component: The same component, if any, as the spell being protected against.","notes":"","link":""},"spike growth":{"name":"Spike Growth","level":"4","school":"Alteration/Enchantment","range":"6”","duration":"1d6 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"10’ square per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Spike Growth\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enchantment\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1d6 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10’ square per caster level\nThis spell works wherever moderate-size or dense plant growth is present. It causes ground-covering vegetation, roots, or rootlets to become very hard and sharply pointed. The ground appears unchanged but acts as if strewn with caltrops. In bare ground or earthen pits, roots and rootlets function the same way. Without true seeing, similar magic, or special detection such as detect traps, the affected area is undetectable until a victim enters and takes damage. Even then, the creature cannot determine the area’s extent without magical detection. For each 1” of movement through the area, a victim suffers 2 attacks from the spike growth. Hit probability is as if the spellcaster were attacking, and each hit deals 1d4 damage. Spells that control or harm vegetation, or dispel magic, negate the area. Material Components: The cleric’s holy symbol and either seven sharp thorns or seven small twigs sharpened to points.\n\nCleric Spells, 5th Level","notes":"","link":""},"air walk":{"name":"Air Walk","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Air Walk\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 6 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell allows the cleric to walk on air as if it were solid ground. Moving upward is like walking uphill. Ascending at a 45-degree angle halves movement, ascending at 60 degrees reduces movement to one-quarter, and moving straight up is at one-eighth normal movement. Descending is faster by the inverse proportions, so straight downward movement can be up to eight times normal speed, or slower if desired. An air-walking creature always controls its movement rate and can stop suddenly to avoid crashing. If gust of wind is active in the area, movement into the gust is at half normal rate, while movement with the gust is at double normal rate. The spell can be placed on any touched creature up to giant size. For example, it may be cast on a trained horse and ridden through the air, though an untrained animal would panic. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol and a bit of thistledown.","notes":"","link":""},"animate dead monsters":{"name":"Animate Dead Monsters","level":"5","school":"Necromantic","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Animate Dead Monsters\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the caster to animate one humanoid or semi-humanoid skeleton or corpse for every 2 caster levels. The animated remains obey commands. Direct commands or instructions of up to about 12 words are followed. Monster types that can be animated include apes, carnivorous apes, giant apes, bugbears, ettins, giants of all kinds, ogres, and trolls of all kinds. In general, the remains must be bipedal monsters of more than 3 Hit Dice with endoskeletons similar to humans, except larger than 7 feet tall. Corpses animated by this spell are treated as monster zombies, or as normal living creatures of the same form if that creature type normally has fewer than 6 Hit Dice. Skeletons animated by this spell are treated as monsters with half the normal Hit Dice, rounded up. Animated monsters receive normal physical attacks, but no special attacks or defenses other than those typical of monster zombies or skeletons. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol and a small specimen of the type of creature to be animated.","notes":"","link":""},"golem":{"name":"Golem","level":"5","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Golem\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nTo cast this spell, the cleric must first personally construct the form of the golem and place a prayer spell upon it. All golems must be man-shaped and approximately man-sized, though they may be as small as 3 feet or as large as 7 feet tall. The type of lesser golem depends on material and caster level. At 9th level or higher, the cleric may create a straw golem. Construction time is 1 hour, duration is 1 hour per caster level, and it has AC 10, MV 12”, HD 2+4, 20 hp, 2 attacks, 1d2/1d2 damage, immunity to piercing weapons, half damage from blunt weapons, and 30-pound carrying capacity; it takes double damage from flame. At 11th level or higher, the cleric may create a rope golem. Construction time is 3 hours, duration is 3 hours per caster level, and it has AC 8, MV 9”, HD 3+6, 30 hp, 1 attack, 1d6 damage plus strangulation for 6 damage per round after a hit until destroyed or released, immunity to blunt weapons, half damage from piercing weapons, and 40-pound carrying capacity. At 13th level or higher, the cleric may create a leather golem. Construction time is 9 hours, duration is 6 hours per caster level, and it has AC 6, MV 6”, HD 4+8, 40 hp, 2 attacks, 1d6/1d6 damage, requires +1 or better magic weapon to hit, takes half damage from blunt weapons, and has 50-pound carrying capacity. At 15th level or higher, the cleric may create a wood golem. Construction time is 27 hours, duration is 12 hours per caster level, and it has AC 4, MV 3”, HD 5+10, 50 hp, 1 attack, 3d4 damage, requires +1 or better magic weapon to hit, is immune to blunt and piercing weapons, and has 60-pound carrying capacity. These creations are lesser golems, distinct from Monster Manual golems. They have no minds, so charm, fear, hold, sleep, and similar spells do not affect them. A lesser golem saves as a cleric of the creator’s level. Lesser golems cannot speak, but understand and obey simple instructions of no more than about 12 words.","notes":"","link":""},"magic font":{"name":"Magic Font","level":"5","school":"Divination","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 turns","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Magic Font\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 5 turns\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes a holy or unholy water font to serve as a scrying device. It works only if the cleric is in good standing with their deity. The basin of holy or unholy water becomes similar to a crystal ball. For each vial of capacity in the font basin, the cleric may scry for 1 round, so the spell’s duration depends directly on the font’s size. Detection chances for scrying are handled as with a crystal ball and the magic mirror spell. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol and the font with its trappings; these are not consumed.","notes":"","link":""},"rainbow":{"name":"Rainbow","level":"5","school":"Evocation/Alteration","range":"12”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Rainbow\n\nSchool: Evocation/Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nTo cast this spell, the cleric must see a rainbow or have a special substitute component. The spell has four possible applications chosen at casting. Bow: The spell creates a shimmering, multi-layered rainbow bow. It is light and easy to draw, so anyone with Strength 6 or better can use it. It is magical, and each missile counts as a +3 weapon. There is no non-proficiency penalty, but only a character class normally permitted to use bows may use it. The bow fires 7 missiles before disappearing, once or twice per round as desired. Each shot releases one color, and that color leaves the bow. Each arrow deals double damage to certain targets: red against fire dwellers or users; orange against earth elementals; yellow against vegetable targets including fungus creatures, shambling mounds, and treants; green against aquatic creatures and water elementals; blue against aerial creatures, electricity-using creatures, and air elementals; indigo against acid-using or poison-using creatures; violet against metallic or regenerating creatures. When drawn, an arrow of the selected color appears. If no color is chosen, or a used color is requested, the next color in spectrum order appears. Bridge: The rainbow forms a seven-colored bridge. The bridge is as many feet wide as the cleric has levels and can bear weight in hundreds of pounds equal to the cleric’s level. It is at least 20 feet long and may be up to 120 feet long, as desired. If its weight limit is exceeded, it disappears. Otherwise, it lasts for the spell duration or until dismissed. Elevator: The rainbow lifts the cleric and all creatures within 10 feet skyward. It carries them along an arc as high as the cleric desires, and down again if desired. The cleric must reach safety before the duration expires, or the elevator disappears. Movement along the elevator is 12”, and the rainbow arc trails 12” behind the travelers. Flagon: The rainbow condenses into a seven-colored vessel holding seven measures of pure water. Each measure poured out mixes with one hue and becomes a magical draught. Unused measures disappear when the spell ends. Draught effects are: red, cure light wounds; orange, resist fire; yellow, cure blindness; green, slow poison; blue, cure disease; indigo, resist cold; violet, remove paralysis. Each draught functions as if cast by a 12th-level cleric, and the effects persist after the spell ends. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol and a vial of holy or unholy water. If no rainbow is nearby, the cleric may substitute a diamond worth at least 1,000 gp, specially prepared in sight of a rainbow by casting bless and prayer on it. Only the holy symbol remains after casting.","notes":"","link":""},"spike stones":{"name":"Spike Stones","level":"5","school":"Alteration/Enchantment","range":"3”","duration":"3d4 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"1” square per level, 1 spike per 10’ square","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Spike Stones\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enchantment\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 3d4 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” square per level, 1 spike per 10’ square\nThis spell causes rock to form long, sharp points that tend to blend into the background. It works on both natural rock and worked stone. The spike stones impede movement and inflict damage. If carefully observed, each observer has a 25% chance to notice the sharp rock points. Otherwise, creatures entering the area suffer 1d4 damage from each spike stone that hits, with attacks made as if by the caster. Creatures entering the area are attacked immediately upon setting foot in it and on each step afterward. The first step reveals the danger only if the initial attack hits; otherwise, movement continues and the stones remain unnoticed until damage occurs. Charging or running victims suffer 2 attacks per 1” of movement rate over the area after initial damage before they can stop. Others suffer only 1 additional attack-like check. Creatures falling into pits affected by spike stones suffer 6 such attack checks, each with +2 “to hit” per 10 feet fallen and +2 damage per 10 feet fallen, in addition to normal falling damage. Material Component: Four tiny stalactites.\n\nCleric Spells, 6th Level","notes":"","link":""},"forbiddance":{"name":"Forbiddance","level":"6","school":"Abjuration","range":"3”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"6 cubic “ per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 rounds","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Forbiddance\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 6 rounds\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 6 cubic “ per level\nThis spell may be used only to secure a consecrated area. The effect on creatures entering depends on their ethics and morals compared to the caster’s. Creatures with identical morals and ethics cannot enter unless they know the password, with no saving throw. Creatures with different ethics must save versus spell to enter; failure causes 2d12 damage. Creatures with different morals must save versus spell to enter; failure causes 4d6 damage. Effects are cumulative, so multiple saving throws may be required. Once a creature fails a saving throw, it can never enter the forbidden area until the spell ends. The caster is immune to the spell. Intruders who enter by succeeding on saves still feel uneasy and tense. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol, holy or unholy water, silver or dung, and iron or sulfur.","notes":"","link":""},"heroes feast":{"name":"Heroes’ Feast","level":"6","school":"Evocation","range":"1”","duration":"1 hour","aoe":"One individual per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Heroes’ Feast\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 hour\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One individual per caster level\nThis spell creates a great feast serving as many creatures as the cleric has levels. It creates a magnificent table, chairs, service, and all necessary food and drink. Those who partake are cured of all diseases, immune to poison for 12 hours, and healed of 5d4 damage after drinking the nectar-like beverage. The ambrosia-like food grants an effect equal to bless for 12 hours. During the same period, participants are immune to fear, hopelessness, and panic. The feast takes 1 full hour to consume, and benefits begin only after that hour. If interrupted for any reason, the spell is ruined and all effects are negated. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol and specially fermented honey taken from cells of bee larvae destined for royal status.\n\nCleric Spells, 7th Level","notes":"","link":""},"exaction":{"name":"Exaction","level":"7","school":"Evocation-Alteration","range":"1”","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Exaction\n\nSchool: Evocation-Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell allows the cleric to confront a powerful creature from another plane, such as a deva or powerful named demon, but not a demigod or deity, and require a duty or quest. The creature cannot be ethically or morally opposed to the cleric; for example, it cannot be evil if the cleric is good, or chaotic if the cleric is lawful. A true neutral creature is considered greatly opposed to both good and evil, and to both law and chaos. The caster must know something about the creature to exact service from it, or else offer fair trade. If the cleric knows the creature has received a favor from someone of the cleric’s alignment, this may be named as cause; otherwise, a valuable gift or service must be pledged in return. The service must be reasonable relative to the past or promised favor or reward. The spell acts as a quest upon the creature. When the service is completed, the creature is transported to the cleric’s vicinity, and the cleric must immediately return the promised reward, whether by cancelling a debt, granting a service, or giving material reward. Once this is done, the creature is freed to return to its plane. Failure to fulfill the promise exactly subjects the cleric to exaction by the creature or its superior at minimum. At worst, the creature may attack the cleric with complete immunity to that cleric’s spell powers. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol, matter or substance from the creature’s plane, and written knowledge of the creature’s nature or actions on a parchment leaf, which is burned to seal the bargain.","notes":"","link":""},"succor":{"name":"Succor","level":"9","school":"Alteration/Enchantment","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"One individual","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1–4 days","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Succor\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enchantment\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1–4 days\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One individual\nThis spell is essentially the same as the 7th-level cleric spell succor. A magic-user’s succor teleports without error the individual who breaks the enchanted object and speaks the command word. If the reverse is used, the archmage is brought to the individual’s presence. Unlike the cleric version, the summoned archmage has no choice but to answer the summons, making this version rare. Intervening planes have a cumulative 1% chance each of causing irrevocable loss of the individual or spellcaster involved in the succor. Material Component: Gem material worth at least 5,000 gp. It may be faceted or unfaceted. Components can be enchanted only once per month, usually on the night of a clear full moon. At that time, the object is set for the type of succor and final destination, either the casting location or an area well known to the mage.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"purify food drink":{"name":"Purify Food & Drink","level":"1","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"30 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"1 cubic foot per cleric level","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Purify Food & Drink\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Putrefy Food & Drink\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per level, within a 1” square area\nThis spell makes spoiled, rotten, poisonous, or otherwise contaminated food and water pure and suitable for consumption. Up to 1 cubic foot of food and/or drink per caster level may be purified. The reverse, putrefy food & drink, spoils food and drink, including holy water. Unholy water is spoiled by purify water.","notes":"You detoxify a volume of food and drink, removing spoilage, disease, and poisons. This spell also neutralises unholy water.\n\nDetails:\n\nThis spell affects objects, not creatures.\n\nIt makes substances safe for you.","link":""},"silence 15 radius":{"name":"Silence 15’ Radius","level":"2","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"120 ft","duration":"2 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"15 ft radius sphere around the target","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"Silence, 15’ Radius\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 30’ diameter sphere\nWhen this spell is cast, complete silence fills the area of effect. All sound stops, conversation becomes impossible, spells cannot be cast, and no noise issues from the affected area. The spell may be cast into the air or upon an object. It lasts 2 rounds per caster level: 2 rounds at 1st level, 4 at 2nd level, 6 at 3rd level, 8 at 4th level, and so on. The spell may also be cast upon a creature, causing the silence to radiate from and move with that creature. If the creature is unwilling, it receives a saving throw. If the save succeeds, the spell effect is centered about 1 foot behind the target creature.","notes":"Creates a zone of silence centred on a creature, object, or point in space. Within the area:\n    No sound can be produced; and\n    No sound can be heard, even from outside the zone.\nDetails:\n    Objects and points in space receive no saving throw.\n    A creature target may choose a saving throw vs spells and other magical effects:\n        Success: the target becomes the 5 ft square the creature is standing in (the creature can move out).\n        Failure: the creature remains the target; the silence moves with it.\n    Combat effects:\n        No one can cast spells with a verbal component within the area.\n        Attempts to sneak or move quietly always succeed if the creature is within the area.\n        Echolocation-dependent creatures (e.g., bats, dolphins) are blinded and suffer -4 “to hit”.","link":""},"spiritual hammer":{"name":"Spiritual Hammer","level":"2","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"30 ft radius around you","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Spiritual Hammer\n\nSchool: Invocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One opponent\nBy calling upon their deity, the cleric creates a hammer-shaped field of force. As long as the cleric concentrates, the force may strike any opponent within range as desired. The force strikes as a magical weapon equal to +1 per 3 caster levels for purposes of hitting creatures that require magical weapons, though it gains no magical bonuses “to hit.” It deals the same damage as a normal war hammer: 1d6 against man-sized or smaller opponents, and 1d4 against larger opponents. The hammer attacks at the cleric’s own level, as if the cleric were personally wielding it. When the cleric stops concentrating, the hammer is dispelled. If the cleric is behind an opponent, the force may strike from that position, gaining applicable bonuses and negating defensive protections such as shield and Dexterity. Material Component: A normal war hammer, which the cleric hurls toward opponents while uttering a plea to their deity. The hammer disappears when the spell is cast.","notes":"Creates a magical force shaped like a weapon (usually a hammer; may match your deity’s sacred weapon). It cannot move more than 30 ft from you, but within that radius it attacks where you direct it.\nDetails:\n    Each round until the spell ends, you may attack one creature within range using the spiritual weapon. Roll to hit as if using a regular weapon.\n    On a hit, it deals 1d6 magical damage (not blunt/piercing/slashing; can harm creatures immune to mundane weapons, and isn’t treated as a “weapon” for those purposes).\n    The weapon is not physical and can pass through obstacles (including walls) as long as it stays within the area.\n    If you direct it to attack a target you can’t see, you are effectively blinded with respect to that target.\n    If it attacks from behind, it gains the normal rear-attack bonus (usually +2).\n    You must concentrate to maintain the spell, or it ends (see Concentration rules).","link":""},"create food water":{"name":"Create Food & Water","level":"3","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"10 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"See below","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Create Food & Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per level\nWhen this spell is cast, the cleric causes food and/or water to appear. The food is highly nourishing, and each cubic foot sustains three human-sized creatures or one horse-sized creature for a full day. The spell creates 1 cubic foot of food and/or water per caster level. For example, a 2nd-level cleric creates 2 cubic feet, a 3rd-level cleric creates 3 cubic feet, a 4th-level cleric creates 4 cubic feet, and so on. The created volume may be divided between food and water.","notes":"Conjures basic food and water from thin air. You choose the form of the food, but it is plain fare.\nDetails:\n    Food is safe when conjured but spoils normally thereafter.\n    For each cleric level, you conjure up to one day’s rations for one human-sized creature.\n    The target point can’t be inside a creature.","link":""},"neutralize poison":{"name":"Neutralize Poison","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"1 ft cube per 2 cleric levels, or one creature","components":"V, S","ct":"7 segments","save":"Depends on use (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Neutralize Poison\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Poison\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched or 1 cubic foot of substance per 2 levels\nBy means of neutralize poison, the cleric detoxifies any venom in the creature or substance touched. An unwilling opponent, such as a poisonous reptile, snake, or envenomed weapon’s wielder, requires the cleric to score a melee touch hit. The effect is permanent only for poison present at the time of the touch; creatures or objects that generate new poison are not permanently detoxified. The reverse, poison, also requires a successful touch attack. The victim then receives a saving throw versus poison; if unsuccessful, the victim is killed.","notes":"Purges venom/toxin/contaminant, rendering it harmless. Can potentially revive someone who has recently “died” from poison.\nDetails:\n    Does not affect disease-based contamination.\n    Gods/demigods/artifacts/relics/equivalent are not affected (GM may allow some derivative effects to be affected).\n    If targeting a toxic place, all toxins/contaminants are purged from the area.\nUsing the spell to de-venom an opponent:\n    If the target is a creature, it may choose a saving throw vs spells and other magical effects.\n        Success: not affected.\n        Failure: if it has a venomous attack, the venom component is nullified until dawn the next day.\nUsing the spell to revive someone “dead by poison”:\n    If the target is poisoned, all toxins are purged, but poison damage already taken remains.\n    Also works on creatures that have recently died of poison: death from poison damage or failed save vs poison within a number of turns equal to your cleric level.\nReversible as Poison:","link":""},"protection from evil 10 radius":{"name":"Protection From Evil, 10’ Radius","level":"3","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"10-foot radius sphere around creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Protection From Evil, 10’ Radius\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Protection From Good, 10’ Radius\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10-foot radius sphere around creature touched\nThis spell is the same as protection from evil, except for its larger area of effect. See the 1st-level cleric spell protection from evil for general details.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"holy unholy word":{"name":"Holy (Unholy) Word","level":"7","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"Nil","duration":"Varies","aoe":"30 ft radius","components":"V","ct":"Fast","save":"None (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Holy Word / Unholy Word\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” radius\nThe utterance of a holy word or unholy word has tremendous power. It drives off evil or good creatures from other planes, forcing them to return to their own planes of existence. It also affects creatures of differing alignment within the 6” diameter area of effect centered on the cleric. Creatures with fewer than 4 Hit Dice or levels are killed. Creatures with 4 to 7+ Hit Dice or levels are paralyzed for 1d4 turns. Creatures with 8 to 11+ Hit Dice or levels are stunned for 2d4 rounds, move at -50%, and attack at -4. Creatures with 12 or more Hit Dice or levels are deafened for 1d4 rounds, move at -25%, attack at -2, and have a 50% chance of spell failure.","notes":"Utter a holy word; all non-good-aligned creatures in the area suffer severe effects.\nDetails:\n    All fiends and evil-aligned elementals are instantly banished to their home plane.\n    Other non-good creatures suffer based on level/HD:\n        < 4: Killed (instant)\n        4–7: Paralyzed for 10d4 rounds\n        8–11: Move halved; -4 to attacks for 2d4 rounds\n            11: Move -10 ft; -2 to attacks for 1d4 rounds\n    Deities/similar power unaffected.\n    Does not work in the Lower Outer Planes.\n    Alignment interpretation is GM-facing: some tables apply it to any non-good; others only to evil.\nReversible as Unholy Word.","link":""},"druid animal friendship":{"name":"Animal Friendship","level":"1","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One animal","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 turns","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Animal Friendship\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 6 turns\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One animal\nThis spell allows the druid to show any animal of at least animal intelligence, but not above semi-intelligent rating, that the druid is disposed to be its friend. If the animal fails its saving throw versus magic when the spell begins, it stands quietly while the druid finishes the spell. Thereafter, it follows the druid, who may teach it 3 specific tricks or tasks for each point of Intelligence it has. Typical tasks are like those taught to a dog or similar pet and cannot be complex. Training each trick requires 1 week, and all training must be completed within 3 months of acquiring the creature. During training, the animal will not harm the druid, but if left alone for more than 3 days, it reverts to its natural state. The druid may use this spell to attract up to 2 Hit Dice of animals per caster level. The druid can never have more Hit Dice of animals attracted and trained than twice their experience level. Only neutral animals can be attracted, befriended, and trained. Material Components: Mistletoe and food attractive to the animal.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Animal Friendship","class":"Druid"},"druid detect magic":{"name":"Detect Magic","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"12 rounds","aoe":"1” path, 4” long","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Magic\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 12 rounds\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” path, 4” long\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 1st-level cleric spell detect magic.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Detect Magic","class":"Druid"},"druid detect snares pits":{"name":"Detect Snares & Pits","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"4 rounds per level","aoe":"1” path, 4” long","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Snares & Pits\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” path, 4” long\nThis spell allows the druid to detect snares and pits along a 1” wide by 4” long path and avoid such deadfalls. Underground, only simple pits are detected, not all traps. Outdoors, the spell detects all forms of traps, including deadfalls, missile trips, snares, and similar hazards. The spell lasts 4 melee rounds per caster level: 4 rounds at 1st level, 8 rounds at 2nd level, 12 rounds at 3rd level, and so on.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Detect Snares & Pits","class":"Druid"},"druid entangle":{"name":"Entangle","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"8”","duration":"1 turn","aoe":"4” diameter","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Entangle\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 turn\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 4” diameter\nThis spell causes plants in the area of effect to entangle creatures within the area. Grasses, weeds, bushes, and even trees wrap, twist, and entwine around creatures, holding them fast for the duration. A creature that makes its saving throw is instead slowed by 50% for the spell duration.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Entangle","class":"Druid"},"druid faerie fire":{"name":"Faerie Fire","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"8”","duration":"4 rounds per level","aoe":"12 linear feet per level within a 4” radius","components":"V","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Faerie Fire\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 12 linear feet per level within a 4” radius\nThis spell outlines an object or creature with pale glowing light. The completeness of the outline depends on how many linear feet the druid can affect, about 12 feet per level, enough for one 6-foot man or two 3-foot kobolds. If enough power is available, multiple objects or creatures may be outlined, but each must be fully outlined before the next begins, and all must be within the area of effect. Outlined objects and creatures, including invisible ones, are visible at 8” in darkness or 4” near a bright light source. Outlined creatures are easier to strike, granting opponents +2 on “to hit” rolls. The light may be blue, green, or violet, chosen by the druid at casting. Faerie fire causes no harm.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Faerie Fire","class":"Druid"},"druid invisibility to animals":{"name":"Invisibility To Animals","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn + 1 round per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Invisibility To Animals\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 turn + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThe recipient becomes totally undetectable to normal animals with Intelligence under 6. Normal animals include giant-sized varieties, but not animals with magical abilities or powers. The affected individual may walk among animals or pass through them as if they did not exist. For example, the recipient could stand before a hungry lion or tyrannosaurus rex and not be noticed or molested. A nightmare, hell hound, or winter wolf would still be aware of the recipient. Material Component: Holly rubbed over the individual.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Invisibility To Animals","class":"Druid"},"druid locate animals":{"name":"Locate Animals","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"2” path, 2” long per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Locate Animals\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2” path, 2” long per level\nThis spell allows the druid to determine the direction and distance of a desired animal type within the area of effect. The animal sought may be any sort, but the druid must concentrate on that type. The druid faces a direction, thinks of the desired animal, and knows whether such an animal is within range. During each round of the spell, the druid may face only one direction, so only one 2” wide path can be checked. The spell lasts 1 round per caster level, and the path extends 2” per caster level.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Locate Animals","class":"Druid"},"druid pass without trace":{"name":"Pass Without Trace","level":"1","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Pass Without Trace\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThe recipient can move through any terrain, including mud, snow, and dust, while leaving neither footprints nor scent. Tracking the affected creature is impossible. The area passed over radiates a dweomer for 6d6 turns after the creature passes. Material Components: A mistletoe leaf, which must be burned and scattered as powdered ashes, and a sprig of pine or evergreen.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Pass Without Trace","class":"Druid"},"druid predict weather":{"name":"Predict Weather","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"2 hours per level","aoe":"Nine square miles","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Predict Weather\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 2 hours per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Nine square miles\nThis spell gives the druid 100% accurate knowledge of the weather, including sky, temperature, and precipitation, in a nine-square-mile area centered on the druid. The druid can forecast 2 hours ahead per caster level. Thus, a 1st-level druid knows the weather for the next 2 hours, a 2nd-level druid for the next 4 hours, and so on.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Predict Weather","class":"Druid"},"druid purify water":{"name":"Purify Water","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"4”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1 cubic foot per level, 1” square area","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Purify Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Contaminate Water\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 4”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per level, 1” square area\nThis spell makes dirty or contaminated water clean, pure, and suitable for consumption. It purifies up to 1 cubic foot of water per caster level. The reverse, contaminate water, works the same way and can spoil even holy or unholy water.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Purify Water","class":"Druid"},"druid shillelagh":{"name":"Shillelagh","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"One normal oaken club","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Shillelagh\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One normal oaken club\nThis spell changes the druid’s own oaken cudgel into a magical weapon. The shillelagh is +1 to hit and deals 2d4 damage against opponents up to man-sized, or 2d3 damage against larger opponents. The druid must wield the shillelagh. Material Components: An oaken club, any mistletoe, and a shamrock leaf.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Shillelagh","class":"Druid"},"druid speak with animals":{"name":"Speak With Animals","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"One animal type within 4” radius of druid","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Speak With Animals\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One animal type within 4” radius of druid\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 2nd-level cleric spell speak with animals.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Speak With Animals","class":"Druid"},"druid charm person or mammal":{"name":"Charm Person Or Mammal","level":"2","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"","components":"V, S, M","ct":"","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Charm Person Or Mammal\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nSaving Throw: Negates\nIf the druid harms or attempts to harm the charmed creature by some overt action, or if dispel magic is successfully cast upon the charmed creature, the charm is automatically broken. The spell affects all mammalian animals and persons. “Person” includes all bipedal human and humanoid creatures of approximately man-size or smaller, including those affected by hold person. If the recipient makes its saving throw versus spell, the effect is negated.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Charm Person Or Mammal","class":"Druid"},"druid create water":{"name":"Create Water","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1 cubic foot per level","components":"V, S","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Create Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per level\nThe druid creates pure, drinkable water. The spell creates 1 cubic foot of water per caster level, at a maximum distance of 1” from the druid.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Create Water","class":"Druid"},"druid cure light wounds":{"name":"Cure Light Wounds","level":"2","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Character touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Light Wounds\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Cause Light Wounds\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Character touched\nExcept that the druid must have mistletoe of any sort to cast it, this spell is the same as the 1st-level cleric spell cure light wounds.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Cure Light Wounds","class":"Druid"},"druid feign death":{"name":"Feign Death","level":"2","school":"Necromantic","range":"1”","duration":"4 rounds + 2 rounds per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Feign Death\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds + 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level magic-user spell feign death. Material Component: A piece of dead oak leaf, in addition to mistletoe.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Feign Death","class":"Druid"},"druid fire trap":{"name":"Fire Trap","level":"2","school":"Evocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent until discharged","aoe":"Object touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Fire Trap\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent until discharged\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: Object touched\nThis spell is the same as the 4th-level magic-user spell fire trap, except as noted above. Material Components: Holly berries and a stick of charcoal used to trace the outline of the closure.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Fire Trap","class":"Druid"},"druid heat metal":{"name":"Heat Metal","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"4”","duration":"7 rounds","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Heat Metal\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Chill Metal\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 4”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 7 rounds\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell excites the molecules of ferrous metal, including iron, iron alloys, and steel, causing the affected metal to become hot. On the first and last rounds, the metal becomes very warm and uncomfortable to touch. On the second and sixth rounds, it becomes hot enough to cause blisters and damage. On the third, fourth, and fifth rounds, the metal becomes searing hot, causing disability and damage to exposed flesh. Very warm metal causes no damage or disability. Hot metal causes 1d4 damage per round. Searing metal causes 2d8 damage per round and may disable hands or feet for 2d8 days, cause head exposure to result in unconsciousness for 1d4 turns, or body exposure to cause disability for 1d4 days. Wood, leather, or flammable cloth exposed to searing metal smolders and burns, then causes searing damage to exposed flesh on the next round. Fire resistance, such as a potion or ring, or protection from fire, completely negates heat metal. Immersion in water or snow, or exposure to cold or ice storm, also negates it. For each caster level, the druid can affect the metal worn or carried by one man-sized creature, or one mass of metal equal to 500 gold pieces in weight, cumulative. The reverse, chill metal, counters heat metal or causes metal to become cold, icy, and freezing. Cold metal causes no damage or disability. Icy metal causes 1d2 damage per round. Freezing metal causes 1d4 damage per round and may cause amputation of fingers, toes, nose, or ears. Chill metal is countered by resist cold or by great heat, such as proximity to a blazing fire, a magical flaming sword, or wall of fire.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Heat Metal","class":"Druid"},"druid locate plants":{"name":"Locate Plants","level":"2","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"1” diameter per level circle","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Locate Plants\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” diameter per level circle\nThis spell allows the druid to locate any desired type of plant within the area of effect. The plant type must be singular and concentrated upon. The area of effect is centered on, and moves with, the druid.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Locate Plants","class":"Druid"},"druid obscurement":{"name":"Obscurement","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"4 rounds per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Obscurement\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes a misty vapor to arise around the druid. The vapor persists for 4 rounds per caster level and reduces all visibility, including infravision, to 2d4 feet. The area of effect is a cubic progression based on druid level: 1” cube at 1st level, 2” cube at 2nd level, 3” cube at 3rd level, and so on. Underground, the vapor’s height is restricted to 1”, though length and breadth are not so limited. A strong wind reduces the spell’s duration by 75%.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Obscurement","class":"Druid"},"druid produce flame":{"name":"Produce Flame","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Produce Flame\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nA bright flame, equal to torchlight, springs from the druid’s palm. The flame lasts 2 melee rounds per caster level. It does not harm the druid, but it is hot and ignites flammable materials such as paper, cloth, dry wood, and oil. The druid may hurl the flame as a missile with a range of 4”. On impact, it flashes, ignites combustibles within a 3-foot diameter of the impact point, and then extinguishes itself. The druid may extinguish the produced flame at will, but cannot thereby extinguish fires caused by it.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Produce Flame","class":"Druid"},"druid trip":{"name":"Trip","level":"2","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"One 10-foot-long object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Trip\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One 10-foot-long object\nThe caster enchants a length of vine, stick, pole, rope, or similar object. The object rises slightly from the ground or floor and trips creatures crossing it if they fail a saving throw versus magic. Only as many creatures can be tripped as are actually stepping across the object; for example, a 3-foot rope can trip only one man-sized creature. Creatures moving very rapidly, such as running, take 1d6 damage and are stunned for 1d4+1 rounds if they fall on a very hard surface. On turf or non-hard ground, they are stunned for only 1d4+1 segments. Very large creatures, such as elephants, are unaffected. The enchanted object continues to trip creatures, including the caster, for the spell’s duration. Creatures aware of the object and its danger gain +4 on their saving throw when crossing it. The object is 80% undetectable without magical detection.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Trip","class":"Druid"},"druid warp wood":{"name":"Warp Wood","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Warp Wood\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes a volume of wood to bend and warp, permanently destroying its straightness, form, and strength. It affects about a 15-inch shaft of wood up to 1 inch in diameter per caster level. At 1st level, a druid might warp a hand axe handle or four crossbow bolts. At 5th level, the druid could warp the shaft of a typical magic spear. Boards and planks can also be affected, causing a door to spring or a boat or ship to leak.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Warp Wood","class":"Druid"},"druid call lightning":{"name":"Call Lightning","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"72” diameter","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Call Lightning\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: 72” diameter\nThis spell requires a storm of some sort in the area, such as a rain shower, clouds and wind, hot cloudy conditions, or even a tornado. The druid may then call down lightning bolts from sky to ground. Each bolt deals 2d8 damage plus 1d8 per caster level. Thus, a 4th-level druid calls down a 6d8 bolt. The bolt strikes perpendicularly at a point chosen by the caster, up to the maximum 36” radial distance. Any creature within 1” of the bolt’s path or strike point takes full damage, or half damage on a successful saving throw. The druid may call one bolt every 10 melee rounds, or 1 turn, up to one bolt per caster level. This spell is normally usable outdoors only.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Call Lightning","class":"Druid"},"druid cure disease":{"name":"Cure Disease","level":"3","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Disease\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Cause Disease\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is the same as the 3rd-level cleric spell cure disease, except that the druid must have mistletoe to cast it. It is reversible as cause disease.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Cure Disease","class":"Druid"},"druid hold animal":{"name":"Hold Animal","level":"3","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"8”","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"One to four animals","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Hold Animal\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One to four animals\nThis spell holds one to four animals rigid. Affected animals are normal or giant-sized mammals, birds, or reptiles, but not monsters such as centaurs, gorgons, harpies, or nagas. Examples include apes, bears, crocodiles, dogs, eagles, foxes, giant beavers, and similar animals. The spell lasts 2 melee rounds per caster level. The druid chooses how many animals to affect, but the more targets chosen, the better their chances to resist. The maximum body weight affected is 400 pounds per caster level for mammals, or 100 pounds per caster level for non-mammals such as birds or reptiles. For example, an 8th-level druid can affect up to four 3,200-pound mammals or four 800-pound non-mammals. Each animal receives a saving throw. If one animal is targeted, it saves at -4. If two are targeted, each saves at -2. If three are targeted, each saves at -1. If four are targeted, each saves normally.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Hold Animal","class":"Druid"},"druid neutralize poison":{"name":"Neutralize Poison","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Neutralize Poison\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Poison\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is the same as the 4th-level cleric spell neutralize poison.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Neutralize Poison","class":"Druid"},"druid plant growth":{"name":"Plant Growth","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"16”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"2” × 2” square area per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Plant Growth\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 16”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2” × 2” square area per level\nThis spell causes normal vegetation to grow, entwine, and entangle into a thicket or jungle that creatures must hack or force their way through at a movement rate of 1”, or 2” for larger-than-man-sized creatures. The area must contain brush and trees for the spell to function. Briars, bushes, creepers, lianas, roots, saplings, thistles, thorns, trees, vines, and weeds become thick and overgrown enough to form a barrier. The area of effect is 2” × 2” square per caster level, arranged in any square or rectangular shape the druid chooses. Thus, an 8th-level druid can affect a maximum area of 16” × 16”, a 32” × 8” rectangle, a 64” × 4” rectangle, a 128” × 2” rectangle, and so on. The effects persist until cleared by labor, fire, or magical means such as dispel magic.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Plant Growth","class":"Druid"},"druid protection from fire":{"name":"Protection From Fire","level":"3","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Protection From Fire\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell’s effect depends on whether the recipient is the druid or another creature. If cast on the druid, it grants complete invulnerability to normal fires and to magical fires such as demon fire, burning hands, fiery dragon breath, fireball, fire seeds, fire storm, flame strike, hell hound breath, meteor swarm, and pyrohydra breath, until it absorbs 12 hit points of potential damage per caster level, at which point the spell is negated. Otherwise, it lasts 1 turn per caster level. If cast on another creature, it grants invulnerability to normal fire, a +4 bonus on saving throws against fire attacks, and a 50% reduction in damage from magical fire.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Protection From Fire","class":"Druid"},"druid pyrotechnics":{"name":"Pyrotechnics","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"16”","duration":"Special","aoe":"10 or 100 times the fire source","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Pyrotechnics\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 16”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10 or 100 times the fire source\nThis spell produces one of two effects. It may create flashing, fiery, glowing, colored aerial fireworks lasting 1 segment per caster level, temporarily blinding creatures in the area of effect, under it, or within 12” of it if they have unobstructed line of sight. Alternatively, it may create a thick, writhing stream of smoke from the fire source, forming a choking cloud that lasts 1 round per caster level and totally obscures vision beyond 2 feet. The spell requires a fire source within range. The area is 10 times the fire source’s volume for fireworks, or 100 times for smoke. In either case, the fire source is immediately extinguished.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Pyrotechnics","class":"Druid"},"druid snare":{"name":"Snare","level":"3","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent until triggered","aoe":"2-foot diameter circle plus 1/6 foot per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Snare\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: Permanent until triggered\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2-foot diameter circle plus 1/6 foot per caster level\nThis spell allows the druid to make a snare that is 90% undetectable without magical aid. The snare may be made from any supple vine, thong, or rope. Once enchanted, the cord blends with the background. One end is tied in a loop that contracts around one or more limbs of any creature stepping inside the circle; even the head of a worm or snake may be ensnared. If a strong, supple tree is nearby, the snare fastens to it, and the spell causes the tree to bend and then snap upright when the loop is triggered, dealing 1d6 damage and lifting the trapped creature by the trapped member or strangling it if the head or neck triggered the snare. If no such tree is available, the cord tightens around the limb or limbs and wraps the entire creature, dealing no damage but binding it tightly. For 1 hour, the magical snare can be broken only by storm giant or greater Strength, meaning 23. Each hour afterward, it becomes easier to break by 1 Strength point: 22 after 2 hours, 21 after 3 hours, 20 after 4 hours, and so on until 6 full hours have passed, when Strength 18 can break it. After 12 hours, the snare loses all magic and opens, freeing anything it held. Material Components: A snake skin and sinew from a strong animal woven into the cord, plus mistletoe.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Snare","class":"Druid"},"druid stone shape":{"name":"Stone Shape","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"3 cubic feet plus 1 cubic foot per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Stone Shape\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3 cubic feet plus 1 cubic foot per level\nThis spell is exactly the same as the 5th-level magic-user spell stone shape, except as noted above and with mistletoe required as an additional component.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Stone Shape","class":"Druid"},"druid summon insects":{"name":"Summon Insects","level":"3","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Summon Insects\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell attracts flying insects 70% of the time. If flying insects are indicated, the insects are bees, biting flies, hornets, or wasps. Otherwise, they are biting ants or pinching beetles. A cloud of flying insects or swarm of crawling insects appears and attacks any creature the druid points to. The target takes 2 hit points of damage per melee round and can do nothing but fend off the insects while attacked. The insects may be redirected to another opponent, but there is at least a 1-round delay while they leave the former target and attack the new one. Crawling insects move only about 12 feet per round over smooth ground. Underground, the druid may possibly summon 1d4 giant ants, but the chance is only 30% unless giant ants are nearby. Material Components: Mistletoe, a flower petal, and a bit of mud or wet clay.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Summon Insects","class":"Druid"},"druid tree":{"name":"Tree","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"6 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"Personal","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Tree\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 6 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Personal\nThis spell allows the druid to assume the form of a small living tree or shrub, or a large dead tree trunk with only a few limbs. Even close inspection does not reveal that the plant is actually a druid; for all normal tests, the druid is a tree or shrub. The druid can observe everything around them as if in human form. The caster may end the spell at any time, instantly returning to human form with full ability to act normally. Clothing and carried gear change with the druid. Material Components: Mistletoe and a twig from a tree.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Tree","class":"Druid"},"druid water breathing":{"name":"Water Breathing","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Water Breathing\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Air Breathing\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThe recipient can breathe freely underwater for 6 turns per caster level. The reverse, air breathing, allows water-breathing creatures to survive comfortably in the atmosphere for the same duration.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Water Breathing","class":"Druid"},"druid animal summoning i":{"name":"Animal Summoning I","level":"4","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"4” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Animal Summoning I\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 4” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell calls up to 8 animals of whatever sort the druid names, provided such animals are within range. The animals may have no more than 4 Hit Dice each. Summoned animals aid the druid by whatever means they possess and remain until a fight is over, a specific mission is completed, the druid is safe, or the druid sends them away. The druid may try three times to summon three different animal types. For example, if wild dogs are unavailable, the druid may next call hawks, and then wild horses. The referee determines probabilities if the presence of a summoned animal type is unknown. Other than various giant animals, fantastic animals and monsters cannot be summoned; for example, no chimerae, dragons, gorgons, or manticores.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Animal Summoning I","class":"Druid"},"druid call woodland beings":{"name":"Call Woodland Beings","level":"4","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"12” + 1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Call Woodland Beings\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 12” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons certain woodland creatures to the druid’s location. It works only outdoors, though not necessarily only in wooded areas. The druid begins the incantation and must continue uninterrupted until a called creature appears or 2 turns pass. Only one type of being may be summoned, and only if within range: 2d4 brownies, 1d4 centaurs, 1d4 dryads, 1d8 pixies, 1d4 satyrs, 1d6 sprites, 1 treant, or 1 unicorn. The referee consults the outdoor map or determines the probability based on the area. Called creatures receive a saving throw versus magic at -4 to avoid the summons. Woodland beings that answer are favorably disposed and give whatever aid they can. However, if the caller or party members are evil, the creatures receive another saving throw versus magic at +4 when they come within 1” of the druid or other evil character, and they immediately try to escape if successful. If the druid asks the summoned creatures to fight, they must make a loyalty reaction check based on the druid’s Charisma and prior dealings. Material Components: A pinecone and 8 holly berries.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Call Woodland Beings","class":"Druid"},"druid control temperature 10 radius":{"name":"Control Temperature, 10’ Radius","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"4 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"20-foot diameter sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Control Temperature, 10’ Radius\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 4 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 20-foot diameter sphere\nThis spell alters the temperature around the druid by up to 9°F per caster level, either upward or downward. For example, a 10th-level druid can raise or lower the surrounding temperature by 1°F to 90°F. The spell lasts 4 turns plus 1 turn per caster level, so a 10th-level druid’s spell lasts 14 turns.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Control Temperature, 10’ Radius","class":"Druid"},"druid cure serious wounds":{"name":"Cure Serious Wounds","level":"4","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Serious Wounds\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Cause Serious Wounds\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is the same as the 4th-level cleric spell cure serious wounds, except that it requires mistletoe of any sort.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Cure Serious Wounds","class":"Druid"},"druid dispel magic":{"name":"Dispel Magic","level":"4","school":"Abjuration","range":"8”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"4” cube","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Dispel Magic\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4” cube\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level cleric spell dispel magic.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Dispel Magic","class":"Druid"},"druid hallucinatory forest":{"name":"Hallucinatory Forest","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"8”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"4” square per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Hallucinatory Forest\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nReversible: Dispel Hallucinatory Forest\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4” square per level\nThis spell creates the appearance of a hallucinatory forest. The illusory forest appears completely natural and is indistinguishable from a real forest. Other druids and creatures such as centaurs, dryads, green dragons, nymphs, satyrs, and treants recognize it for what it is. All other creatures believe it is real, and movement and order of march are affected accordingly. The forest remains until magically dispelled by the reverse of the spell or by dispel magic. Its shape is generally square or rectangular, at least 4” deep, and appears wherever the druid desires, with one edge up to 8” away from the druid. The druid may create a forest smaller than the maximum area.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Hallucinatory Forest","class":"Druid"},"druid hold plant":{"name":"Hold Plant","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"8”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Hold Plant\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell affects vegetable matter in three ways: it causes ambulatory vegetation to stop moving; prevents vegetable matter from entwining, grasping, closing, or growing; and prevents vegetable matter from making any sound or movement not caused by wind. It applies to all forms of vegetation, including parasitic and fungoid types, as well as magically animated or empowered vegetation. It affects creatures such as green slime, molds, shambling mounds, shriekers, and treants. The duration is 1 melee round per caster level. The spell affects 1 to 4 plants, or 4 to 16 square yards of small ground growth such as grass or mold. If one plant or 4 square yards is targeted, the save is at -4. If two plants or 8 square yards are targeted, saves are at -2. If three plants or 12 square yards are targeted, saves are at -1. If four plants or 16 square yards are targeted, saves are normal.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Hold Plant","class":"Druid"},"druid plant door":{"name":"Plant Door","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Plant Door\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell opens a magical portal or passageway through trees, undergrowth, thickets, or similar growth, including magical growth. The portal is open only to the casting druid, higher-level druids, or dryads. It can also allow the druid to enter a solid tree trunk and remain hidden until the spell ends. If the tree is cut down or burned, the druid must leave before the tree falls or is consumed, or the druid is killed. The spell lasts 1 turn per caster level. If the druid remains inside an oak, the duration is 9 times longer; inside an ash tree, it is 3 times longer. The passage may be up to 4 feet wide, 8 feet high, and 12 feet per caster level long.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Plant Door","class":"Druid"},"druid produce fire":{"name":"Produce Fire","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"4”","duration":"1 round","aoe":"12-foot square","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Produce Fire\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Quench Fire\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 4”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 12-foot square\nThis spell creates a common-type fire in an area up to 12 feet per side. Though it lasts only 1 round, the fire deals 1d4 damage to creatures in the area and ignites combustible materials such as cloth, oil, paper, parchment, and wood, causing continued burning. The reverse, quench fire, extinguishes any normal fire, such as coals, oil, tallow, wax, or wood, within the area.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Produce Fire","class":"Druid"},"druid protection from lightning":{"name":"Protection From Lightning","level":"4","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Protection From Lightning\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is exactly the same as the 3rd-level druid spell protection from fire, except it applies to electrical and lightning attacks.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Protection From Lightning","class":"Druid"},"druid repel insects":{"name":"Repel Insects","level":"4","school":"Abjuration/Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"10-foot radius around the caster","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Repel Insects\n\nSchool: Abjuration/Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10-foot radius around the caster\nThis spell creates an invisible barrier against true insects. Normal insects will not approach within 10 feet of the druid while the spell lasts. Giant insects with 2 or more Hit Dice may cross the barrier if they make a saving throw versus magic, but even if successful, they take 1d6 damage from passing through. The spell does not affect arachnids, myriapods, or similar creatures. Material Components: Mistletoe and one of the following: several crushed marigold flowers, a whole crushed leek, 7 crushed stinging nettle leaves, or a small lump of resin from a camphor tree.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Repel Insects","class":"Druid"},"druid speak with plants":{"name":"Speak With Plants","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"8” diameter circle","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Speak With Plants\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 8” diameter circle\nExcept as noted above, and except that the material component is typically druidic mistletoe, this spell is the same as the 4th-level cleric spell speak with plants.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Speak With Plants","class":"Druid"},"druid animal growth":{"name":"Animal Growth","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"8”","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"Up to 8 animals in a 2” square area","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Animal Growth\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Reduce Animal\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Up to 8 animals in a 2” square area\nThis spell causes up to 8 animals within a 2” square area to grow to twice normal size. The effects include doubled Hit Dice, improved attack potential, and doubled combat damage. The spell lasts 2 melee rounds per caster level. It is especially useful with charm person or animal or speak with animals. The reverse reduces animals to half size and similarly reduces Hit Dice, attack damage, and related statistics.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Animal Growth","class":"Druid"},"druid animal summoning ii":{"name":"Animal Summoning II","level":"5","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"6” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Animal Summoning II\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6” per level\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is the same in duration and effect as animal summoning I, except that it may call up to 6 animals of no more than 8 Hit Dice each, or 12 animals of no more than 4 Hit Dice each.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Animal Summoning II","class":"Druid"},"druid anti plant shell":{"name":"Anti-Plant Shell","level":"5","school":"Abjuration","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"16-foot diameter hemisphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Anti-Plant Shell\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 16-foot diameter hemisphere\nThis spell creates an invisible barrier that keeps out all creatures or missiles of living vegetable material. The druid and creatures within the shell are protected from attacking plants and vegetable creatures such as shambling mounds and treants. The spell lasts 1 turn per caster level.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Anti-Plant Shell","class":"Druid"},"druid commune with nature":{"name":"Commune With Nature","level":"5","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Commune With Nature\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the druid to become one with nature in the area, gaining knowledge of the surrounding territory. For each caster level, the druid may know one fact, such as the ground ahead, left, or right; the plants ahead, left, or right; the minerals ahead, left, or right; watercourses or bodies of water ahead, left, or right; people dwelling ahead, left, or right; and similar information. The spell works only outdoors and operates in a radius of ½ mile per caster level.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Commune With Nature","class":"Druid"},"druid control winds":{"name":"Control Winds","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"4” per level radius hemisphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Control Winds\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4” per level radius hemisphere\nThis spell allows the druid to alter wind force in the area. For each caster level, the druid may increase or decrease wind speed by 3 miles per hour. Winds over 30 miles per hour drive small flying creatures, eagle-sized and smaller, from the sky and severely inhibit missile fire. Winds over 45 miles per hour drive even man-sized flying creatures from the sky. Winds over 60 miles per hour drive all flying creatures from the sky, uproot small trees, knock down wooden structures, tear off roofs, and similar effects. Winds over 75 miles per hour are hurricane force and devastate all but the strongest stone constructions. Winds above 30 miles per hour make sailing difficult, above 45 miles per hour cause minor ship damage, above 60 miles per hour endanger ships, and above 75 miles per hour sink ships. There is a calm “eye” of 4” radius around the druid. A higher-level druid can use control winds to counter the effects of a like spell cast by a lower-level druid. The spell lasts 1 turn per caster level. Once cast, wind force changes by 3 miles per hour per round until the maximum speed is reached. When the spell expires, wind force diminishes at the same rate. Underground, the eye shrinks in proportion to confinement. For example, if the area of effect is a 48” radius but the confined space allows only 46”, the eye is 2” radius; any space under 44” radius eliminates the eye and subjects the caster to the wind.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Control Winds","class":"Druid"},"druid insect plague":{"name":"Insect Plague","level":"5","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"32”","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"32” diameter, 4” high cloud","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Insect Plague\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 32”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 32” diameter, 4” high cloud\nExcept as noted above, and except that the required material component is mistletoe or a holly or oak leaf substitute, this spell is the same as the 5th-level cleric spell insect plague.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Insect Plague","class":"Druid"},"druid pass plant":{"name":"Pass Plant","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Pass Plant\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the druid to enter a tree and move from inside it to another tree of the same type in approximately the desired direction, within range. The entered tree and destination tree must be the same type, living, and at least as large in girth as the druid. If the desired direction does not contain a matching tree but another valid tree is in range elsewhere, the druid passes to that tree instead. For example, if the druid enters an ash and wishes to pass north as far as possible, but the only suitable ash is south, the druid passes to the southern ash. The movement takes 1 segment. The druid may remain within the destination tree for up to 1 round per caster level or step out immediately. If no matching tree is in range, the druid remains in the original tree and must step out within the applicable number of rounds. Tree ranges are: oak 60”, ash 54”, yew 48”, elm 42”, linden 36”, deciduous 30”, coniferous 24”, and other 18”. See plant door for the effects of chopping or burning an occupied tree.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Pass Plant","class":"Druid"},"druid sticks to snakes":{"name":"Sticks To Snakes","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"4”","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"1” cube","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Sticks To Snakes\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Snakes To Sticks\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 4”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” cube\nExcept as noted above, and except that the material component is typical for druids, this spell is the same as the 4th-level cleric spell sticks to snakes.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Sticks To Snakes","class":"Druid"},"druid transmute rock to mud":{"name":"Transmute Rock To Mud","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"16”","duration":"Special","aoe":"2” cube per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Transmute Rock To Mud\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Transmute Mud To Rock\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 16”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2” cube per level\nThis spell turns natural rock of any sort into an equal volume of mud. The mud’s depth can never exceed one-half its length and/or breadth. If cast on a rock, the affected rock collapses into mud. Creatures unable to levitate, fly, or otherwise escape sink and suffocate, except lightweight creatures that could normally pass across such ground. The mud remains until dispel magic or the reverse, mud to rock, restores its substance, though not necessarily its form. Evaporation turns the mud into normal dirt, requiring 1d6 days per cubic 1”, depending on exposure to sun, wind, and drainage. The reverse permanently hardens normal mud into soft stone, such as sandstone, unless magically changed.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Transmute Rock To Mud","class":"Druid"},"druid wall of fire":{"name":"Wall Of Fire","level":"5","school":"Evocation","range":"8”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wall Of Fire\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a blazing curtain of magical fire in shimmering druidic colors, yellow-green or amber. Any creature passing through the wall takes 4d4 damage plus 1 damage per caster level. Creatures within 1” of the wall take 2d4 damage, and those within 2” take 1d4 damage. Creatures especially vulnerable to fire may take additional damage, and undead always take double damage. Only the side of the wall away from the caster deals damage. The opaque wall lasts as long as the druid concentrates, or 1 round per caster level if the druid does not concentrate. The spell creates either a sheet of flame up to 2” square per caster level, which is stationary, or a ring with radius up to ½” per caster level from the druid to its flames and height of 2”, which moves with the druid.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Wall Of Fire","class":"Druid"},"druid animal summoning iii":{"name":"Animal Summoning III","level":"6","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"8” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Animal Summoning III\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8” per level\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is the same in duration and effect as animal summoning I, except that it may summon up to 4 animals of no more than 16 Hit Dice each, 8 animals of no more than 8 Hit Dice each, or 16 creatures of no more than 4 Hit Dice each.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Animal Summoning III","class":"Druid"},"druid anti animal shell":{"name":"Anti-Animal Shell","level":"6","school":"Abjuration","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"20-foot diameter hemisphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Anti-Animal Shell\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 20-foot diameter hemisphere\nThis spell creates a hemispherical force field that prevents the entrance of animal matter of normal, nonmagical nature. Thus, a giant would be kept out, but undead could pass through, as could creatures such as aerial servants, demons, and devils. The spell lasts 1 turn per caster level.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Anti-Animal Shell","class":"Druid"},"druid conjure fire elemental":{"name":"Conjure Fire Elemental","level":"6","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"8”","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Conjure Fire Elemental\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nReversible: Dismiss Fire Elemental\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 6 rounds\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell opens a special gate to the Elemental Plane of Fire and summons a powerful fire creature. There is an 85% chance that a 16-Hit-Die fire elemental appears, a 9% chance that 2d4 salamanders appear, a 4% chance that an efreeti appears, and a 2% chance that a huge 21–24 Hit Die fire elemental appears. Because of druids’ relationship to natural and elemental forces, the summoned elemental force does not turn on the druid, and neither concentration nor a magic circle is required. The summoned creature helps the druid however possible, including attacking opponents. It remains for up to 1 turn per caster level, or until sent back by attack, dispel magic, or the reverse spell. Only a druid can dismiss summoned salamanders, efreeti, or ultra-powerful elementals.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Conjure Fire Elemental","class":"Druid"},"druid cure critical wounds":{"name":"Cure Critical Wounds","level":"6","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Critical Wounds\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Cause Critical Wounds\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is the same as the 5th-level cleric spell cure critical wounds, except that it requires mistletoe of any sort.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Cure Critical Wounds","class":"Druid"},"druid feeblemind":{"name":"Feeblemind","level":"6","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"16”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"8 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Feeblemind\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 16”\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell is used only against persons or creatures who use magic spells. Feeblemind causes the victim’s brain to become like that of a moronic child. The victim remains in this state until heal, restoration, or wish removes the effect. The spell is especially effective against spellcasters, and saving throw adjustments apply: cleric +1, druid -1, human magic-user -4, illusionist -5, combination or non-human spellcaster -2. The spell has no material component.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Feeblemind","class":"Druid"},"druid transport via plants":{"name":"Transport Via Plants","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Transport Via Plants\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the druid to enter any large living plant and pass in a single round to a plant of the same species at any distance. The destination plant need not be familiar but must be alive. If the druid is uncertain of the destination plant, the druid may specify direction and distance, and the spell moves the druid as near as possible to the desired location. There is a base 20% chance, reduced by 1% per caster level, that the transport delivers the druid to an allied plant species 1d100 miles from the desired destination plant. If a specific destination plant is desired but is not alive, the spell fails, and the druid must exit the entrance plant within 24 hours. Harm to a plant containing a druid may affect the druid, as described under plant door.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Transport Via Plants","class":"Druid"},"druid turn wood":{"name":"Turn Wood","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"4 rounds per level","aoe":"12” wide path, 2” long per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Turn Wood\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 12” wide path, 2” long per level\nThis spell sends waves of force from the druid in the direction faced, pushing all wooden objects in the path away to the limit of the area of effect. Wooden objects over 3 inches in diameter that are firmly fixed are unaffected, but loose objects such as movable mantlets or siege towers are pushed back. Fixed objects under 3 inches in diameter splinter and break, and the pieces move with the force. Wooden shields, spears, weapon shafts and hafts, arrows, and bolts are pushed back, dragging those carrying them. A planted spear used to resist the force splinters. The spell lasts 4 rounds per caster level, and the force continues to sweep down the set path. Wooden objects move back at 4” per melee round. The path is 12” wide and 2” long per caster level; for example, a 14th-level druid creates a 12” by 28” path lasting 56 rounds. After casting, the path is fixed, and the druid may act normally or leave without affecting the spell.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Turn Wood","class":"Druid"},"druid wall of thorns":{"name":"Wall Of Thorns","level":"6","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"8”","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"10” cube per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wall Of Thorns\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10” cube per level\nThis spell creates a barrier of tough, pliable green tangled brush with needle-sharp thorns as long as a person’s finger. Any creature breaking through or impacting the wall takes 8 damage plus additional damage equal to its Armor Class, with negative Armor Class subtracting from the base 8 damage. Any creature within the area when the spell is cast is considered to have impacted the wall and must break through to move. Damage is based on each 1” thickness of barrier. If the wall is chopped, cutting a path through 1” thickness takes at least 4 turns. Normal fire does not harm the barrier, but magical fire burns it away in 2 turns, creating a wall of fire effect while doing so. The nearest edge appears up to 8” away from the druid, as desired. The wall lasts 1 turn per caster level and covers 10 cubic inches per caster level in whatever form the druid chooses. For example, a 14th-level druid could create a wall 7” long by 2” high by 1” deep, a 1” high by 1” wide by 14” long wall to block a dungeon passage, or another suitable shape.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Wall Of Thorns","class":"Druid"},"druid fire seeds":{"name":"Fire Seeds","level":"6","school":"Conjuration","range":"4”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round per seed","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Fire Seeds\n\nSchool: Conjuration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 4”\nCasting Time: 1 round per seed\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates special missiles or timed incendiaries that burn with great heat. Acorns become missile fire seeds, while holly berries become timed incendiaries. The druid may create up to 4 acorn fire seeds or 8 holly berry fire seeds. Acorns may be hurled up to 4” and burst on impact, dealing 2d8 damage and igniting combustibles within a 1” diameter of the impact point. Holly berries are too light to be effective missiles, but may be placed or tossed up to 6 feet away, then ignited by command word. Each berry bursts into flame, dealing 1d8 damage to any creature in a ½” diameter burst and igniting combustibles in that area. Command range for holly berry fire seeds is 4”. All fire seeds lose power after 1 turn per caster level. Targets of acorn fire seeds must be struck by the missile. Creatures within the burst area take half damage on a successful saving throw, but creatures struck directly always take full damage. No mistletoe or components other than acorns or holly berries are required.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Fire Seeds","class":"Druid"},"druid weather summoning":{"name":"Weather Summoning","level":"6","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Weather Summoning\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is similar to the clerical control weather spell. The druid calls forth weather appropriate to the climate and season of the area. In spring, the druid may summon a tornado, thunderstorm, cold, sleet storm, or hot weather. In summer, torrential rain, heat wave, hail storm, and similar conditions may be called. In autumn, hot or cold weather, fog, sleet, and similar weather may appear. In winter, great cold, blizzard, or thaw conditions may be summoned. Hurricane-force winds may be summoned near coastal regions in late winter or early spring. The summoned weather is not under the druid’s control. It may last a single turn, such as a tornado, or hours or days in other cases. The area of effect varies from about 1 square mile to 100 or more square miles. Several druids may work together to greatly affect weather, controlling winds and jointly summoning extreme conditions. Within 4 turns after casting, the trend of the coming weather becomes apparent, such as clearing skies, warm gusts, a chill breeze, or overcast skies. The weather arrives 1d12+5 turns after casting. Anything less than greater mistletoe sharply limits the desired weather extremes.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Weather Summoning","class":"Druid"},"druid animate rock":{"name":"Animate Rock","level":"7","school":"Alteration","range":"4”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"2 cubic feet per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Animate Rock\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 4”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2 cubic feet per level\nThis spell animates a separate stone object up to the listed size. The object must be separate, not part of a huge boulder or similar mass. The animated rock follows the druid’s spoken desire, such as attacking, breaking objects, or blocking, while the spell lasts. It has no intelligence or will of its own and follows instructions exactly as spoken. Only one brief set of instructions for one action, about 12 words or fewer, may be given. The rock remains animated for 1 melee round per caster level. The volume animated is 2 cubic feet per caster level; for example, a 12th-level druid can animate 24 cubic feet of stone.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Animate Rock","class":"Druid"},"druid chariot of sustarre":{"name":"Chariot Of Sustarre","level":"7","school":"Evocation","range":"1”","duration":"6 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Chariot Of Sustarre\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 6 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell brings forth a large flaming chariot pulled by two fiery horses, appearing in a clap of thunder amid cloud-like smoke. The vehicle moves at 24” on the ground or 48” flying. It can carry the druid and up to 8 other man-sized creatures whom the druid first touches to enable them to ride aboard. Creatures other than the druid and designated passengers take damage equal to a wall of fire spell if they come within 5 feet of the horses or chariot, voluntarily or involuntarily. The druid controls the chariot by verbal command, causing the fiery steeds to stop, go, walk, trot, run, fly, or turn left or right. The chariot is a physical manifestation and can take damage. The vehicle and steeds are struck only by magical weapons or by water, with one quart of water causing 1 hit point of damage. They are Armor Class 2, and each requires 30 hit points of damage to dispel. Fire has no effect on the vehicle or steeds, though magical fires can affect exposed riders other than the chariot’s own flames. Material Components: Mistletoe, a small piece of wood, 2 holly berries, and a fire source at least equal to a torch.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Chariot Of Sustarre","class":"Druid"},"druid confusion":{"name":"Confusion","level":"7","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"8”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Up to 4” by 4”","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Confusion\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Up to 4” by 4”\nThis spell causes confusion in one or more creatures within range. Confused creatures act according to a percentile roll: 01–10, wander away for 1 turn; 11–60, stand confused for 1 round; 61–80, attack the nearest creature for 1 round; 81–00, attack the druid or the druid’s party for 1 round. The spell lasts 1 melee round per caster level. It affects 2d4 creatures, plus a possible additional number determined by subtracting the level or Hit Dice of the strongest opponent within range and area from the druid’s level. If the result is positive, add it to the number of affected creatures; if negative, ignore it. Affected creatures are those closest to the druid within the area. Each affected creature makes a saving throw each round unless it is caused to wander away for 1 turn, in which case it moves as far from the druid as possible in 1 turn of normal movement, as conditions permit. All saving throws are at -2. Saving throws and actions are checked at the beginning of each round.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Confusion","class":"Druid"},"druid conjure earth elemental":{"name":"Conjure Earth Elemental","level":"7","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"4”","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Conjure Earth Elemental\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nReversible: Dismiss Earth Elemental\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 4”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons a 16-Hit-Die earth elemental to do the druid’s bidding. The druid need only command it and may then act normally, because the elemental does not regard the summoning druid with enmity. The elemental remains until destroyed, dispelled, or sent away by dismissal.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Conjure Earth Elemental","class":"Druid"},"druid control weather":{"name":"Control Weather","level":"7","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"8–96 hours","aoe":"4–32 square miles","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Control Weather\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 8–96 hours\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4–32 square miles\nThe druidic version of control weather is more powerful than the clerical spell of the same name. If greater mistletoe is used, the druid can change weather by two places from prevailing conditions. Otherwise, it functions as the 7th-level cleric spell control weather.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Control Weather","class":"Druid"},"druid creeping doom":{"name":"Creeping Doom","level":"7","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"0","duration":"4 rounds per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Creeping Doom\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell calls forth a mass of 500 to 1,000 venomous, biting, and stinging arachnids, insects, and myriapods. The carpet-like swarm covers a 2” square area and, on command, creeps forth at 1” per round toward prey within 8”, moving in the direction the druid commands. The swarm can slay any creature subject to normal attacks, with each small horror inflicting 1 hit point of damage and then dying after its attack. Thus, up to 1,000 hit points of damage may be inflicted on creatures in the path of the creeping doom. If the swarm moves beyond 8” from the summoner, it loses 50 creatures for each 1” beyond 8”; for example, at 10”, its number has shrunk by 100. Various obvious methods may thwart or destroy the swarm.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Creeping Doom","class":"Druid"},"druid finger of death":{"name":"Finger Of Death","level":"7","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"6”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Finger Of Death\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell causes the victim’s heart to stop. The druid utters the incantation and points an index finger at the creature to be slain. Unless the victim succeeds on the appropriate saving throw, death occurs. A successful saving throw negates the spell.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Finger Of Death","class":"Druid"},"druid fire storm":{"name":"Fire Storm","level":"7","school":"Evocation","range":"16”","duration":"1 round","aoe":"2” cube per level, minimum 16 cubic “","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Fire Storm\n\nSchool: Evocation\nReversible: Fire Quench\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 16”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: 2” cube per level, minimum 16 cubic “\nThis spell fills an area with sheets of roaring flame equivalent to a wall of fire. Creatures within the area and within 1” or less from its edge take 2d8 damage plus 1 point per caster level, or half damage on a successful saving throw. The area of effect is 2 cubic inches per caster level; for example, a 13th-level druid can create a fire storm measuring 13” by 2” by 1”. The storm’s height is 1” or 2”, with the remainder of its area in length and width. The reverse, fire quench, smothers double the area of effect of fire storm for normal fires. Against magical fires, it has a 5% chance per caster level to extinguish magical fire, such as fire storm, up to the normal area of effect of the unreversed spell.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Fire Storm","class":"Druid"},"druid reincarnate":{"name":"Reincarnate","level":"7","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Person touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Reincarnate\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Person touched\nThis spell allows the druid to bring back the dead in another body if death occurred no more than one week before casting. The reincarnated person recalls most of their former life and form, but their new class, if any, may be different. Abilities and speech are often changed. Any sort of player character may be reincarnated. If an elf, gnome, or human is indicated, the character must be created. When the corpse is touched, the new incarnation appears in the area within 1d6 turns.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Reincarnate","class":"Druid"},"druid transmute metal to wood":{"name":"Transmute Metal To Wood","level":"7","school":"Alteration","range":"8”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One metal object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Transmute Metal To Wood\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One metal object\nThis spell changes a metal object into wood. The volume of metal affected equals a maximum weight of 80 gold pieces per caster level. Magical metal objects are only 10% likely to be affected. Even dispel magic will not reverse the effect. Thus, a metal door changed to wood remains wooden permanently.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Transmute Metal To Wood","class":"Druid"},"druid ceremony":{"name":"Ceremony, Druid","level":"1","school":"Invocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature, item, or area","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 hour","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Ceremony\n\nSchool: Invocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 hour\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature, item, or area\nThe druidic ceremony spell is similar to the clerical spell of the same name and has several applications within the druidic hierarchy. The spell does not leave behind a magical aura, though know alignment or similar magic might reveal the force of true neutrality involved. Druidic ceremonies include: 1st-level druid: coming of age, rest eternal, marriage; 3rd-level druid: dedication, investiture; 7th-level druid: initiation, special vows; 9th-level druid: hallowed ground; 12th-level druid: cast out. Coming of age is performed upon young people in druidic societies, usually at age 14, and symbolizes entry into adulthood. Its effects are the same as the clerical version, granting a +1 bonus to one saving throw. Rest eternal is cast upon a deceased being’s body, hastening the soul or spirit to its final resting place. Raise dead and resurrection cannot restore life to a creature affected by this spell, though wish can. Marriage is essentially identical to the clerical ceremony of the same name. Dedication admits the recipient into the ranks of the druid’s followers or worshipers, provided the recipient is true neutral. The recipient is charged with preserving and protecting nature and the balance of forces in the world. Otherwise, it is similar to the clerical ceremony. Investiture must be performed before a character can become an Aspirant, or 1st-level druid. It grants no other benefit. Initiation grants the druid the shape-changing and immunity to woodland charm powers gained at 7th level. It must be performed immediately after the druid begins advancing through 7th level. If cast earlier, it fails, and the druid does not gain those powers until properly initiated. Usually, a druid must seek another druid of 7th level or higher to perform the rite, though in unusual cases a druid may cast it upon themselves. Special vows functions like the clerical rite of the same name. It does not work on paladins, but works on cavaliers of any alignment. Hallowed ground is cast on the druid’s permanent grove. It enchants the grove’s trees so they are never affected by disease or natural disasters. The ground remains hallowed as long as the druid maintains the grove as a permanent base. Cast out is a form of excommunication or punishment used against someone who has committed sacrilege against nature or violated druidic principles. Its effects may later be lessened by a reversed version of the ceremony cast by the same druid or another druid of at least equal level, but it can only be completely neutralized by a Hierophant Druid. A cast-out character exudes a powerful negative aura, causing natural creatures to react negatively, including normal animals, woodland monsters, domesticated beasts, druids, and druidic followers. This punishment requires permission from the druid’s Archdruid; an Archdruid needs permission from the Great Druid, and the Great Druid from the Grand Druid. The Grand Druid needs no permission, but a Hierophant Druid may reverse the action at any time. A druid who wrongly seeks or performs this punishment may themselves be punished by higher-ranking druids. An unwilling recipient saves versus spell at -4 to negate the effect. Material Components: Druidic ceremony always requires mistletoe and must be performed in a druid grove or another natural, healthy forested area. Such ceremonies are normally conducted at dawn or dusk, when night and day are in balance.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Ceremony, Druid","class":"Druid"},"ceremony druid":{"name":"Ceremony, Druid","level":"1","school":"Invocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature, item, or area","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 hour","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Ceremony\n\nSchool: Invocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 hour\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature, item, or area\nThe druidic ceremony spell is similar to the clerical spell of the same name and has several applications within the druidic hierarchy. The spell does not leave behind a magical aura, though know alignment or similar magic might reveal the force of true neutrality involved. Druidic ceremonies include: 1st-level druid: coming of age, rest eternal, marriage; 3rd-level druid: dedication, investiture; 7th-level druid: initiation, special vows; 9th-level druid: hallowed ground; 12th-level druid: cast out. Coming of age is performed upon young people in druidic societies, usually at age 14, and symbolizes entry into adulthood. Its effects are the same as the clerical version, granting a +1 bonus to one saving throw. Rest eternal is cast upon a deceased being’s body, hastening the soul or spirit to its final resting place. Raise dead and resurrection cannot restore life to a creature affected by this spell, though wish can. Marriage is essentially identical to the clerical ceremony of the same name. Dedication admits the recipient into the ranks of the druid’s followers or worshipers, provided the recipient is true neutral. The recipient is charged with preserving and protecting nature and the balance of forces in the world. Otherwise, it is similar to the clerical ceremony. Investiture must be performed before a character can become an Aspirant, or 1st-level druid. It grants no other benefit. Initiation grants the druid the shape-changing and immunity to woodland charm powers gained at 7th level. It must be performed immediately after the druid begins advancing through 7th level. If cast earlier, it fails, and the druid does not gain those powers until properly initiated. Usually, a druid must seek another druid of 7th level or higher to perform the rite, though in unusual cases a druid may cast it upon themselves. Special vows functions like the clerical rite of the same name. It does not work on paladins, but works on cavaliers of any alignment. Hallowed ground is cast on the druid’s permanent grove. It enchants the grove’s trees so they are never affected by disease or natural disasters. The ground remains hallowed as long as the druid maintains the grove as a permanent base. Cast out is a form of excommunication or punishment used against someone who has committed sacrilege against nature or violated druidic principles. Its effects may later be lessened by a reversed version of the ceremony cast by the same druid or another druid of at least equal level, but it can only be completely neutralized by a Hierophant Druid. A cast-out character exudes a powerful negative aura, causing natural creatures to react negatively, including normal animals, woodland monsters, domesticated beasts, druids, and druidic followers. This punishment requires permission from the druid’s Archdruid; an Archdruid needs permission from the Great Druid, and the Great Druid from the Grand Druid. The Grand Druid needs no permission, but a Hierophant Druid may reverse the action at any time. A druid who wrongly seeks or performs this punishment may themselves be punished by higher-ranking druids. An unwilling recipient saves versus spell at -4 to negate the effect. Material Components: Druidic ceremony always requires mistletoe and must be performed in a druid grove or another natural, healthy forested area. Such ceremonies are normally conducted at dawn or dusk, when night and day are in balance.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Ceremony","class":"Druid"},"druid detect balance":{"name":"Detect Balance","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"6”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"One object or creature per round","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Balance\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One object or creature per round\nThis spell allows the druid to determine whether non-neutral forces and alignments are at work in the object or creature being scanned. A partly neutral alignment, such as neutral good, radiates a mild aura. An alignment with no neutral component, such as chaotic good, gives off a strong aura. The spell does not reveal exact alignment; it only tells whether the subject is something other than true neutral. Thus, a paladin and a chaotic evil thief radiate the same strength of aura. The spell does not work on nonliving items without a natural aura, such as a vial of poison, but it works on objects such as aligned magical swords. Creatures under unknowable alignment or similar magic radiate no aura. A true neutral subject produces a smooth, well-balanced aura identifiable as neutrality.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Detect Balance","class":"Druid"},"druid detect poison":{"name":"Detect Poison","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Poison\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the druid to determine whether an object, creature, or area contains poison or has been poisoned. The spell can examine about 1 cubic yard of space, so it cannot determine whether an entire pond is poisoned, but it can check a portion of it. There is a 5% chance per caster level that the spell also reveals the type of poison: contact, ingestive, or respirative gas. More than one area can be scanned during the spell’s duration, but attempting to determine poison type for multiple areas is difficult. Any single failure on the 5% per level roll makes the spell useless for identifying poison type for the rest of that casting. Material Components: Mistletoe and a yew leaf. The yew leaf turns brown if poison is present, so several may be needed to use the whole duration.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Detect Poison","class":"Druid"},"druid precipitation":{"name":"Precipitation","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 segment per level","aoe":"3” diameter cylinder up to 12” high","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None and special","save_type":"","description":"Precipitation\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 segment per level\nSaving Throw: None and special\nArea of Effect: 3” diameter cylinder up to 12” high\nThis spell is identical to the 1st-level clerical spell precipitation, except the druid requires mistletoe as an additional material component.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Precipitation","class":"Druid"},"druid flame blade":{"name":"Flame Blade","level":"2","school":"Evocation","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"3-foot-long sword-like blade","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Flame Blade\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3-foot-long sword-like blade\nThis spell causes a blazing ray of red-hot fire to spring from the druid’s hand. The blade-like ray is wielded as a scimitar. On a successful hit, it deals 5–8 damage, with a +2 damage bonus against undead or creatures especially vulnerable to fire, or a -2 damage penalty against creatures protected from fire. It deals no damage to fire-dwellers or creatures that use fire as an attack form. The blade ignites combustible materials such as parchment, straw, dry sticks, and cloth. It is not a magical weapon in the normal sense except against undead, so creatures hit only by magical weapons are not harmed unless they are undead. Material Components: Mistletoe and a sumac leaf.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Flame Blade","class":"Druid"},"druid goodberry":{"name":"Goodberry","level":"2","school":"Alteration-Evocation","range":"Touch","duration":"1 day + 1 day per level","aoe":"2–8 fresh berries","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Goodberry\n\nSchool: Alteration-Evocation\nReversible: Badberry\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 day + 1 day per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2–8 fresh berries\nWhen cast upon freshly picked berries, this spell makes 2d4 of them magical. The casting druid and any other druid of 3rd level or higher can immediately identify which berries were affected. Detect magic also reveals them. Each enchanted berry either nourishes a hungry man-sized creature as a full normal meal or cures 1 point of physical damage from wounds or similar causes. A creature may receive no more than 8 points of such healing in any 24-hour period. The reverse, badberry, causes rotten berries to appear wholesome, but each deals 1 point of poison damage with no saving throw if eaten. Material Component: Mistletoe passed over freshly picked edible berries, such as blueberries, blackberries, raspberries, currants, or gooseberries.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Goodberry","class":"Druid"},"druid reflecting pool":{"name":"Reflecting Pool","level":"2","school":"Evocation-Divination","range":"1”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 hours","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Reflecting Pool\n\nSchool: Evocation-Divination\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 2 hours\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes a pool of normal water in a natural setting to function as a scrying device. The pool may be no wider than 2 feet per caster level. It becomes similar to a crystal ball, much like magic mirror or magic font. The scrying can reach only planes coexistent with or bordering the Prime Material Plane, such as the Inner Planes, Para-Elemental Planes, and Plane of Shadow. Penalties for scrying beyond the druid’s own plane apply as with a crystal ball. The following spells may be cast through the pool, with a 5% chance per caster level of operating correctly: detect magic, detect snares and pits, and detect poison. Infravision and ultravision work normally through the pool, as do starshine and moonbeam. Material Components: Mistletoe and oil extracted from nuts such as hickory or walnut, refined and dropped in three measures upon the pool’s surface. A measure may be as little as one ounce.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Reflecting Pool","class":"Druid"},"druid slow poison":{"name":"Slow Poison, Druid","level":"2","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"1 hour per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Slow Poison\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 hour per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is identical to the 2nd-level clerical spell slow poison, except that if the druid can determine the poison was made from a living plant, they have a 5% chance per caster level of knowing an herbal antidote that neutralizes the poison. If the Dungeon Master does not identify the exact poison, a successful detect poison type result indicates an organic poison that can be countered. A successful roll equal to or less than the druid’s chance means the antidote neutralizes the poison. Material Components: Mistletoe and crushed garlic rubbed on the recipient’s feet. Antidotes must be obtained from green vegetables outdoors or from an herbalist or similar source.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Slow Poison, Druid","class":"Druid"},"slow poison druid":{"name":"Slow Poison, Druid","level":"2","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"1 hour per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Slow Poison\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 hour per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is identical to the 2nd-level clerical spell slow poison, except that if the druid can determine the poison was made from a living plant, they have a 5% chance per caster level of knowing an herbal antidote that neutralizes the poison. If the Dungeon Master does not identify the exact poison, a successful detect poison type result indicates an organic poison that can be countered. A successful roll equal to or less than the druid’s chance means the antidote neutralizes the poison. Material Components: Mistletoe and crushed garlic rubbed on the recipient’s feet. Antidotes must be obtained from green vegetables outdoors or from an herbalist or similar source.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Slow Poison","class":"Druid"},"druid cloudburst":{"name":"Cloudburst","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round","aoe":"3” diameter cylinder up to 6” high","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None and special","save_type":"","description":"Cloudburst\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: None and special\nArea of Effect: 3” diameter cylinder up to 6” high\nThis spell is essentially the same as the 3rd-level clerical spell cloudburst, with the following additions: lightning cannot be called by cloudburst, and call lightning cannot be used in the same area at the same time. Material Component: Mistletoe is required as an additional component.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Cloudburst","class":"Druid"},"druid know alignment":{"name":"Know Alignment","level":"3","school":"Divination","range":"1”","duration":"5 rounds","aoe":"One creature per round","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Know Alignment\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 5 rounds\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature per round\nThis spell is essentially the same as the 2nd-level clerical spell know alignment, except as noted above. Because of the shorter duration, only 5 creatures can be examined. The druidic version cannot be reversed.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Know Alignment","class":"Druid"},"druid spike growth":{"name":"Spike Growth","level":"3","school":"Alteration/Enchantment","range":"6”","duration":"3–12 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"10-foot square per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Spike Growth\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enchantment\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 3–12 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10-foot square per caster level\nThis spell is essentially the same as the 4th-level clerical spell spike growth, except as noted above. The affected area radiates magic, and detect snares and pits reveals the location of the spike growth. Material Components: Mistletoe, replacing the cleric’s holy symbol, plus seven small twigs or thorns.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Spike Growth","class":"Druid"},"druid starshine":{"name":"Starshine","level":"3","school":"Evocation-Illusion","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"10-foot square per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Starshine\n\nSchool: Evocation-Illusion\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10-foot square per caster level\nThis spell softly illuminates an area as if it were under a clear night sky full of stars. Regardless of the height of the open area in which it is cast, the area beneath is lit by starshine. Vision is clear up to 30 feet, indistinct out to 60 feet, and beyond that only gleams and glimmers are visible. Starshine allows shadows. It enhances ultravision to full potential but does not affect infravision. The spell makes the area appear to be a night sky, but disbelief merely reveals that the “stars” are evoked lights. Material Components: Several stalks from an amaryllis, especially Hypoxis, and several holly berries.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Starshine","class":"Druid"},"druid moonbeam":{"name":"Moonbeam","level":"5","school":"Evocation-Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"1” diameter sphere plus special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Moonbeam\n\nSchool: Evocation-Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” diameter sphere plus special\nThis spell causes a beam of soft, pale moonlight to strike downward from overhead and illuminate the area the druid points at. The light is exactly like moonlight, so colors other than shades of black, gray, and white cannot be determined. The caster can move the moonbeam to any visible area they can point to, making it useful for spotlighting something, such as an opponent. The beam allows shadows, but a creature centered in it is clearly under observation. Reflected light allows dim visual perception 1” beyond the area of effect. The light does not adversely affect infravision and enhances ultravision to its greatest potential. Material Components: Several seeds from any moonseed plant and a piece of opalescent feldspar, or moonstone.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Moonbeam","class":"Druid"},"druid spike stones":{"name":"Spike Stones","level":"5","school":"Alteration/Enhancement","range":"3”","duration":"3–12 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"1” square per level, 1 spike per 10-foot square","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Spike Stones\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enhancement\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 3–12 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” square per level, 1 spike per 10-foot square\nThis spell is the same as the 5th-level clerical spell spike stones.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Spike Stones","class":"Druid"},"druid liveoak":{"name":"Liveoak","level":"6","school":"Enchantment","range":"Touch","duration":"1 day per level","aoe":"One oak tree","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Liveoak\n\nSchool: Enchantment\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 day per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One oak tree\nThis spell allows the druid to enchant a healthy oak tree to serve as a protector. Only one liveoak spell by a particular druid may be active at once. The chosen tree must be within 10 feet of the druid’s dwelling, within a sacred place, or within 10” of something the druid wishes to guard. The spell can be cast on a healthy oak of small, medium, or large size. The druid sets a triggering phrase of up to one word per caster level. For example, “Attack any persons who come near without first saying ‘sacred mistletoe’” is an 11-word trigger usable by an 11th-level or higher druid. When triggered, the oak becomes a treant of appropriate size and attack capability, as described in the Monster Manual, but with only 3” movement. An enchanted oak radiates magic and can be returned to normal by dispel magic or by the druid who enchanted it. Material Component: Mistletoe.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Liveoak","class":"Druid"},"druid transmute water to dust":{"name":"Transmute Water To Dust","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"6”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1 cubic “ per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None and special","save_type":"","description":"Transmute Water To Dust\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Transmute Dust To Water\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None and special\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic “ per level\nThis spell instantly changes liquid in the subject area into powdery dust. If the water is already muddy, the area of effect is doubled; if wet mud is affected, the area is quadrupled. If water remains in contact with the transmuted dust, it quickly permeates the dust and turns it into silty mud if enough water is present, or dampens it otherwise. Only liquid present in the area at the moment of casting is affected. Liquids that are only partly water are affected only as to their water content, though potions containing water are rendered useless. Living creatures are unaffected except those native to the Elemental Plane of Water. Such creatures receive a saving throw versus spell, and only one such creature can be affected by a single casting regardless of size or area. The reverse is a very powerful create water spell requiring a pinch of normal dust as an additional material component. Material Components: Diamond dust worth at least 500 gp, a bit of seashell, and mistletoe.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Transmute Water To Dust","class":"Druid"},"druid changestaff":{"name":"Changestaff","level":"7","school":"Evocation-Enchantment","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"The druid’s staff","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Changestaff\n\nSchool: Evocation-Enchantment\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The druid’s staff\nThis spell changes the druid’s staff from dead wood into a largest-size treant. To cast it, the druid must first find a tree struck by lightning within the past 24 hours, with a 1%–5% chance for any given tree depending on storm severity. The druid must select a sound limb, remove it, and prepare a specially cured section. The staff must be ash, oak, or yew. Sun-drying and special smoke curing require 28 days, and shaping, carving, smoothing, and polishing require another 28 days. The druid cannot adventure or do strenuous activity during either period. The finished staff is engraved with woodland scenes, rubbed with holly berry juice, and thrust into the earth of the druid’s grove while the druid uses speak with plants to call upon the staff for aid in time of need. The staff is then charged with magic that lasts through many transformations. The staff/treant begins as a largest-size treant with 12 Hit Dice and 96 hit points. Every 8 points of accumulated damage reduces it by 1 Hit Die: 11 HD and 88 hp, 10 HD and 80 hp, 9 HD and 72 hp, and so on. As it loses Hit Dice, it becomes smaller and loses attack power. If reduced below 7 Hit Dice, it crumbles into sawdust and is lost. It cannot regain Hit Dice or hit points except by wish, which restores it fully. A new staff may be prepared to begin again. When the druid plants the staff in the ground and speaks a special command prayer and invocation, it becomes a treant. It defends and obeys the druid, but is not a true treant and cannot converse with real treants. The transformation lasts for 1 turn per caster level, until the druid commands it to return to staff form, or until destroyed. Material Component: Mistletoe or leaves of ash, oak, or yew matching the staff.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Changestaff","class":"Druid"},"druid sunray":{"name":"Sunray","level":"7","school":"Evocation-Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round","aoe":"1” diameter sphere plus special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Sunray\n\nSchool: Evocation-Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 1” diameter sphere plus special\nThis spell evokes a burning beam of light similar to true sunlight. All creatures within the main area of effect are blinded for 1d3 rounds unless they save versus spell. Creatures using ultravision may be blinded for 2d4 rounds. Creatures for whom sunlight is harmful or unnatural suffer permanent blindness unless they save, in which case blindness lasts 2d6 rounds. Creatures within the main area and within 2” of its perimeter lose infravision for 2d4+1 rounds. Undead, including vampires, caught in the main area must save versus spell, taking 8d6 damage on a failed save or half damage on success. Undead within the secondary area, up to 2” from the perimeter, take 3d6 damage or none on a successful save. The ultraviolet light damages fungoid creatures and subterranean fungi as if they were undead, but they receive no saving throw. Material Components: An aster seed and a piece of aventurine feldspar, or sunstone.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Druid: Sunray","class":"Druid"},"magic user affect normal fires":{"name":"Affect Normal Fires","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"3-foot diameter fire","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Affect Normal Fires\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3-foot diameter fire\nThis spell allows the magic-user to affect small fires, from a torch or lantern up to a normal bonfire no more than 3 feet in diameter. The caster may reduce the fire’s size and light until it becomes match-like, or increase its light until it is as bright as a light spell. Reducing the fire halves fuel consumption, while increasing the fire doubles fuel consumption. Heat output is not changed.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Affect Normal Fires","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user burning hands":{"name":"Burning Hands","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 round","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Burning Hands\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nWhen this spell is cast, jets of searing flame shoot from the magic-user’s fingertips. The hands must be held with thumbs touching and fingers spread, producing a fan-like sheet of flame. The flame extends 3 feet in a horizontal arc of about 120 degrees in front of the caster. Any creature in the area takes 1 point of damage per caster level, with no saving throw. Flammable materials touched by the fire, such as cloth, paper, parchment, and thin wood, ignite.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Burning Hands","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user charm person":{"name":"Charm Person","level":"1","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"12”","duration":"Special","aoe":"One person","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Charm Person\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One person\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 2nd-level druid spell charm person or mammal, but the magic-user can charm only persons. This includes brownies, dwarves, elves, gnolls, gnomes, goblins, half-elves, halflings, half-orcs, hobgoblins, humans, kobolds, lizard men, nixies, orcs, pixies, sprites, and troglodytes. All other comments regarding the spell’s effects apply to persons.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Charm Person","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user comprehend languages":{"name":"Comprehend Languages","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"One written object or speaking creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Comprehend Languages\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Confuse Languages\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One written object or speaking creature\nThis spell allows the magic-user to read an otherwise incomprehensible written message, such as a treasure map, or understand the language of a speaking creature. It does not allow magical writing to be read, except to recognize it as magical. The caster must touch the writing or creature. The spell does not enable the caster to write or speak the language. The reverse, confuse languages, prevents comprehension or cancels comprehend languages. Material Components: A pinch of soot and a few grains of salt.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Comprehend Languages","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user dancing lights":{"name":"Dancing Lights","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"4” + 1” per level","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Dancing Lights\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 4” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates, at the caster’s option, 1 to 4 lights resembling torches or lanterns, glowing spheres like will-o-wisps, or one faintly glowing, vaguely man-like shape similar to a creature from the Elemental Plane of Fire. The lights move as the caster desires: forward, backward, straight, or around corners, without concentration. The spell ends if range or duration is exceeded. Material Component: A bit of phosphorus, wytchwood, or a glowworm.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Dancing Lights","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user detect magic":{"name":"Detect Magic","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"1” path, 6” long","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Magic\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” path, 6” long\nThis spell is the same as the 1st-level cleric spell detect magic, except as noted above: it has a different duration and area of effect, and it requires no material component.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Detect Magic","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user enlarge":{"name":"Enlarge","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Enlarge\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Reduce\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes instant growth of one creature or object, increasing both size and weight. The target must be visible. Living creatures increase by 20% per caster level, to a maximum additional growth of 200%. Objects increase by 10% per caster level, to a maximum additional growth of 100%. The maximum initial volume affected is 10 cubic feet of living material per caster level, or 5 cubic feet of nonliving matter per caster level. Magical properties are not increased, but weight, mass, and strength are. For example, a table blocking a door becomes heavier and more effective; a hurled stone becomes more massive if enlarged just before impact; chains become more massive; doors become thicker; a thin line becomes a sizable rope; a 12-foot person is comparable to an ogre; and an 18-foot person is effectively a giant for the spell’s duration. The reverse, reduce, negates enlarge or makes creatures and objects smaller by the same ratios. Unwilling targets receive a saving throw; success means the spell has no effect and is wasted. Material Component: A pinch of powdered iron.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Enlarge","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user erase":{"name":"Erase","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"3”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One scroll or two facing pages","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Erase\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One scroll or two facing pages\nThis spell removes magical or mundane writing from a scroll, or from one or two pages or sheets of paper, parchment, or similar surfaces. It does not remove explosive runes or a symbol. The base chance of success is 50%, plus 2% per caster level for magical writing, or plus 4% per caster level for mundane writing. This chance represents the saving throw; a percentile roll above the adjusted chance means the spell fails.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Erase","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user feather fall":{"name":"Feather Fall","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 segment per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, M","ct":"1/10 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Feather Fall\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1/10 segment\nDuration: 1 segment per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes affected falling creatures or objects to assume the mass of a feathery piece of down. Their falling rate immediately changes to 2 feet per second, or 12 feet per segment, and they take no damage on landing while the spell is active. When the spell ends, normal falling resumes. The spell may affect the caster, another creature, or an object within range. It affects an area of 1 cubic inch, and the total maximum weight is 2,000 gold pieces plus 2,000 gold pieces per caster level. For example, a 2nd-level magic-user has a 2” range, 2-segment duration, and 6,000 gold piece, or 600-pound, weight maximum. The spell works only on free-falling or propelled objects. It does not affect a sword blow or charging creature, but it can affect a missile. Material Component: A small feather or piece of down somewhere on the caster’s person.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Feather Fall","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user find familiar":{"name":"Find Familiar","level":"1","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1 mile per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"As spell range","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1–24 hours","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Find Familiar\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1 mile per level\nCasting Time: 1–24 hours\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: As spell range\nThis spell summons a familiar, which benefits a magic-user by adding to the caster’s hit points, conveying sensory powers, conversing with the caster, and serving as guard, scout, or spy. The magic-user has no control over what type of creature answers, or whether any creature comes. The spell may be attempted only once per year. To cast it, the magic-user must burn charcoal in a brass brazier, then add 100 gp worth of incense, herbs, and fat. The herbs must include basil, savory, and catnip. The incantation continues until the familiar arrives or the casting time ends. The referee secretly determines all results.\n\nFamiliar Table\nd20 Roll\tFamiliar\tSensory Powers\n1–4\tBlack cat\tExcellent night vision and superior hearing\n5–6\tCrow\tExcellent vision\n7–8\tHawk\tVery superior distance vision\n9–10\tScreech owl\tNight vision equal to human daylight vision and superior hearing\n11–12\tToad\tWide-angle vision\n13–14\tWeasel\tSuperior hearing and very superior smell\n15\tSpecial\tSee special familiar table\n16–20\tNo familiar available\tNone\n\nSubtract 1 from the die roll for each 3 caster levels. If the modified score is 15 or less, roll again using d16; if a 16 is rolled, that result is final.\n\nSpecial Familiar Table\nMagic-User Alignment\tSpecial Familiar\nChaotic evil or chaotic neutral\tQuasit\nChaotic good, neutral, or neutral good\tPseudo-dragon\nLawful neutral or lawful good\tBrownie\nLawful evil or neutral evil\tImp\n\nNormal familiars have 2–4 hit points and Armor Class 7 due to size and speed. Each is unusually intelligent and totally faithful to the magic-user. The familiar’s hit points are added to the caster’s hit point total while it is within 12” of its master. If the familiar is killed, the magic-user permanently loses double that number of hit points. Special familiars have powers described in the Monster Manual, except for the brownie. A brownie familiar becomes a friend and companion; the magic-user gains Dexterity 18, cannot be surprised, and gains +2 on all saving throws. Special familiars receive a saving throw versus magic when summoned. If successful, they ignore the spell, and no familiar is available that year. A familiar fights for the magic-user’s life only in a life-or-death situation, and imps and quasits are 90% likely not to do so if risking their own lives.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Find Familiar","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user friends":{"name":"Friends","level":"1","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"1” + 1” per level radius sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Friends\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 1” + 1” per level radius sphere\nThis spell temporarily increases the magic-user’s Charisma by 2d4 points or lowers it by 1d4 points, depending on whether creatures in the area fail or make their saving throws versus magic. Creatures that fail are impressed by the caster and strongly desire to be friendly and helpful. Creatures that save are uneasy around the caster and tend to find them irritating. This spell has no effect on creatures of animal intelligence or lower. Material Components: Chalk or white flour, lampblack or soot, and vermillion applied to the face before casting.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Friends","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user hold portal":{"name":"Hold Portal","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"2” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"80 square feet per level","components":"V","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Hold Portal\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V\nRange: 2” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 80 square feet per level\nThis spell magically bars a door, gate, or valve of wood, metal, or stone. The closure holds fast as if securely stopped and locked. Any extra-dimensional creature, such as a demon, devil, or elemental, shatters such a held portal. A magic-user at least 4 experience levels higher than the caster can open the portal at will. Knock or dispel magic negates the spell. Held portals can also be broken or battered down.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Hold Portal","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user identify":{"name":"Identify","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"1 segment per level","aoe":"One item","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Identify\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 segment per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One item\nThis spell allows the magic-user to touch and handle one item to possibly determine its magical properties. The item must be held or worn in the normal manner, such as a bracelet on the wrist, helm on the head, boots on the feet, cloak worn, dagger held, and so on. Any consequences of using the item fall fully on the magic-user, though any normal saving throw still applies. For each segment the spell remains in force, there is a 15% chance plus 5% per caster level that one property becomes known, including the possibility that the item has no true properties and is a ruse, such as Nystul’s magic aura or magic mouth. Each time a property might be learned, the referee secretly checks the caster’s saving throw versus magic. If successful, the property is known. If the save is missed by 1 point, a false power is revealed. If missed by more than 1, no information is gained. Exact bonuses to hit or damage are never revealed, though the caster may learn whether the item has few or many such bonuses. If the item has charges, the exact number is never revealed, but the caster senses a number within 25% of the actual total. The item must be examined within 1 hour per caster level after discovery, or impressions become blended with those of later possessors. After casting and learning what can be learned, the magic-user loses 8 Constitution points and must rest 6 turns per point to regain them. If this loss drops Constitution below 3, the caster falls unconscious and does not awaken until full Constitution is restored 24 hours later. Material Components: A pearl worth at least 100 gp and an owl feather steeped in wine, with the infusion drunk and a live miniature carp swallowed whole before casting. If a luckstone is powdered and added to the infusion, the probability increases by 25%, and all saving throws are made at +4.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Identify","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user jump":{"name":"Jump","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Jump\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell allows the recipient to leap up to 30 feet forward, 10 feet backward, or 10 feet straight upward. Horizontal leaps have only a slight arc, about 2 feet per 10 feet traveled. The spell does not ensure safe landing or grasping at the end of the leap. For every 3 caster levels beyond 1st, the caster grants one additional leap: 2 leaps at 4th level, 3 leaps at 7th level, and so on. All leaps must be completed within 1 turn after casting. Material Component: One grasshopper hind leg for each leap, broken when the leap is made.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Jump","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user light":{"name":"Light","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"6”","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"2” radius globe","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Light\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2” radius globe\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 1st-level cleric spell light.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Light","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user magic missile":{"name":"Magic Missile","level":"1","school":"Evocation","range":"6” + 1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"One or more creatures in a 10-square-foot area","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Magic Missile\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One or more creatures in a 10-square-foot area\nThis spell creates one or more magical missiles that dart from the magic-user’s fingertip and unerringly strike their target. Each missile deals 1d4 + 1 damage. If the caster has multiple missiles, they may strike one creature or several creatures as desired. Range is 6” plus 1” per caster level. The caster gains one additional missile for every 2 levels of experience: 2 missiles at 3rd level, 3 at 5th level, 4 at 7th level, and so on.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Magic Missile","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user mending":{"name":"Mending","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"3”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mending\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One object\nThis spell repairs small breaks in objects. It can weld a broken ring, chain link, medallion, or slender dagger, provided there is only one break. Ceramic or wooden objects with multiple breaks can be invisibly rejoined and made as strong as new. A hole in a leather sack or wineskin is completely sealed. The spell does not repair magic items. Material Components: Two small magnets, likely lodestones, or two burrs.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Mending","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user message":{"name":"Message","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"6” + 1” per level","duration":"5 segments + 1 segment per level","aoe":"¼” path","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Message\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 5 segments + 1 segment per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: ¼” path\nWhen this spell is cast, the magic-user whispers a message and secretly or openly points at the intended recipient. The whispered message travels in a straight line and is audible to the creature pointed at. The message must fit within the spell’s duration. If time remains, the recipient may whisper a reply that the caster hears. There must be an open, unobstructed path between caster and recipient. Material Component: A short piece of finely drawn copper.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Message","class":"Magic-User"},"nystul s magic aura":{"name":"Nystul’s Magic Aura","level":"1","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"1 day per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Nystul’s Magic Aura\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 day per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell gives one item a false magical aura detectable by detect magic. The item may weigh up to 50 gold pieces per caster level. If the detecting creature actually holds the item, it receives a saving throw versus magic. Success reveals that the aura was placed to mislead the unwary. Otherwise, the aura simply appears magical, but no amount of testing reveals what the magic is. Material Component: A small square of silk passed over the item.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user nystul s magic aura":{"name":"Nystul’s Magic Aura","level":"1","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"1 day per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Nystul’s Magic Aura\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 day per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell gives one item a false magical aura detectable by detect magic. The item may weigh up to 50 gold pieces per caster level. If the detecting creature actually holds the item, it receives a saving throw versus magic. Success reveals that the aura was placed to mislead the unwary. Otherwise, the aura simply appears magical, but no amount of testing reveals what the magic is. Material Component: A small square of silk passed over the item.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Nystul’s Magic Aura","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user protection from evil":{"name":"Protection From Evil","level":"1","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Protection From Evil\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Protection From Good\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 1st-level cleric spell protection from evil. The magic-user version requires powdered iron and silver as material components for tracing the protective circle.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Protection From Evil","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user push":{"name":"Push","level":"1","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1” + ¼” per level","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Push\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” + ¼” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates an invisible force that strikes the object or creature the magic-user points at. The force is slight, equal to 1 foot-pound per caster level. It can move small objects up to 1 foot directly away from the caster, topple an object under proper conditions, or cause a creature to lose balance. For example, a creature attacking may lose balance and be unable to attack that round if it fails its saving throw. The creature’s mass cannot exceed the force of the push by more than a factor of 50; a 1st-level magic-user cannot effectively push a creature weighing more than 50 pounds. Used against an object held by a creature, the spell subtracts its force in foot-pounds from the creature’s chance to hit, or adds to opponent saving throws as applicable, if the holder fails its saving throw versus magic. Material Component: A small pinch of powdered brass blown from the palm before pointing.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Push","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user read magic":{"name":"Read Magic","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Read Magic\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Unreadable Magic\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the magic-user to read magical inscriptions on objects such as books, scrolls, and weapons that would otherwise be unintelligible. The caster’s own spellbooks and works already read by magic are already intelligible. Deciphering does not normally invoke the magic in the writing, though it may do so with a cursed scroll. Once the spell has been used to read a particular inscription, the magic-user can read that writing thereafter without using read magic. The reverse, unreadable magic, makes magical writing unreadable to any creature, even with read magic, until the spell ends or is dispelled. Material Component: For read magic, a clear crystal or mineral prism, not consumed by casting. For unreadable magic, a pinch of dirt and a drop of water.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Read Magic","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user shocking grasp":{"name":"Shocking Grasp","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"One touch","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Shocking Grasp\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: One touch\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell gives the magic-user a powerful electrical charge. The touched creature takes 1d8 damage plus 1 point per caster level. For example, a 2nd-level magic-user deals 1d8 + 2 damage. The caster need only touch the opponent’s body or an electrical conductor touching the opponent. A touch from the opponent does not discharge the spell.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Shocking Grasp","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user shield":{"name":"Shield","level":"1","school":"Evocation","range":"0","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Shield\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates an invisible barrier in front of the magic-user. It completely negates magic missile attacks. It provides Armor Class 2 against hand-hurled missiles such as axes, darts, javelins, and spears; Armor Class 3 against small device-propelled missiles such as arrows, bolts, bullets, manticore spikes, and sling stones; and Armor Class 4 against all other attacks. The shield also grants +1 on saving throws against attacks that are basically frontal. These benefits apply only to attacks from the caster’s front, where the shield can interpose itself.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Shield","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user sleep":{"name":"Sleep","level":"1","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"3” + 1” per level","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Sleep\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell usually causes one or more creatures to fall into comatose slumber, excluding undead and certain other creatures specifically immune to the spell. All affected creatures must be within a 3” diameter circle. The number affected depends on Hit Dice or life energy levels.\n\nCreature Hit Dice\tNumber Affected\nUp to 1\t4d4\n1+1 to 2\t2d4\n2+1 to 3\t1d4\n3+1 to 4\t1d2\n4+1 to 4+4\t0–1, affected on d4 roll of 3 or 4\n\nThe caster determines the center of the area within range. Slapping or wounding awakens affected creatures, but noise does not. Awakening requires 1 complete melee round. Sleeping creatures can be slain automatically at a rate of 1 per slayer per melee round. Material Component: A pinch of fine sand, rose petals, or a live cricket.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Sleep","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user spider climb":{"name":"Spider Climb","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round + 1 round per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Spider Climb\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell allows the recipient to climb and travel on vertical surfaces like a giant spider, at 3” movement rate, and even hang upside down from ceilings. The creature must have bare hands and feet to climb this way. During the spell, the recipient cannot handle objects weighing less than 50 gold pieces, since such objects stick to their hands and feet. A magic-user under spider climb will find spellcasting virtually impossible. Material Components: A drop of bitumen and a live spider, both eaten by the recipient.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Spider Climb","class":"Magic-User"},"tenser s floating disc":{"name":"Tenser’s Floating Disc","level":"1","school":"Evocation","range":"2”","duration":"3 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Tenser’s Floating Disc\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 3 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates Tenser’s floating disc, a circular plane of null-gravity named for the famed wizard. The disc is concave, 3 feet in diameter, and holds 1,000 gold pieces of weight per caster level. It floats about 3 feet above the ground and remains level. If not otherwise commanded, it maintains a constant 6-foot distance from the caster. It may otherwise move within range and accompany the caster at a rate of 6”. If the caster moves beyond range or the duration expires, the disc disappears and anything it supported falls to the surface below. Material Component: A drop of mercury.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user tenser s floating disc":{"name":"Tenser’s Floating Disc","level":"1","school":"Evocation","range":"2”","duration":"3 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Tenser’s Floating Disc\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 3 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates Tenser’s floating disc, a circular plane of null-gravity named for the famed wizard. The disc is concave, 3 feet in diameter, and holds 1,000 gold pieces of weight per caster level. It floats about 3 feet above the ground and remains level. If not otherwise commanded, it maintains a constant 6-foot distance from the caster. It may otherwise move within range and accompany the caster at a rate of 6”. If the caster moves beyond range or the duration expires, the disc disappears and anything it supported falls to the surface below. Material Component: A drop of mercury.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Tenser’s Floating Disc","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user unseen servant":{"name":"Unseen Servant","level":"1","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"0","duration":"6 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"3” radius around caster","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Unseen Servant\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 6 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” radius around caster\nThis spell creates an invisible servant, a non-visible valet or butler-like force that fetches, opens doors, holds chairs, cleans, and mends. It is not strong, but obeys the caster’s commands. It can carry light items: up to 200 gold pieces suspended, or twice that across a relatively friction-free surface such as smooth stone or wood. It can open only normal doors, drawers, lids, and similar objects. It cannot fight or be killed, since it is a force rather than a creature. It can be dispelled or eliminated after taking 6 hit points of magical damage. Material Components: A piece of string and a bit of wood.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Unseen Servant","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user ventriloquism":{"name":"Ventriloquism","level":"1","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"1” per level, maximum 6”","duration":"2 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"One object","components":"V, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Ventriloquism\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 1” per level, maximum 6”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 2 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One object\nThis spell allows the magic-user to make their voice, another voice, or a similar sound seem to issue from somewhere else, such as another creature, statue, behind a door, or down a passage. The caster may make the voice sound like a different creature, provided the language is known or the sound can normally be made by the caster. A hearer has a 10% chance per point of Intelligence above 12 to recognize the ruse. Material Component: A small cone of parchment.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Ventriloquism","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user write":{"name":"Write","level":"1","school":"Evocation","range":"0","duration":"1 hour per level","aoe":"One magical spell inscription","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Write\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 hour per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One magical spell inscription\nThis spell may allow the magic-user to inscribe a spell they cannot yet understand into their spellbook or other spell compilation. The caster must make a saving throw versus magic to attempt the writing: +2 if the spell is only up to 1 level higher than the caster can currently use, no modifier if it is 2 levels higher, and -1 per level from 3 levels higher onward. If the save fails, the magic-user takes 1d4 damage per level of the spell being transcribed and is knocked unconscious for the same number of turns. This damage, if not fatal, heals only at 1d4 points per day. Transcription takes 1 hour per spell level, during which the magic-user is in a trance and can always be surprised. Material Component: A writing surface and fine ink made from rare substances, costing at least 200 gp per bottle if available.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 2nd Level","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Write","class":"Magic-User"},"audible glamer":{"name":"Audible Glamer","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"6” + 1” per level","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"Hearing range","components":"V, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Audible Glamer\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 6” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Hearing range\nThis spell creates sound at any desired point within range. The sound may seem to recede, approach, or remain fixed. The volume depends on caster level, with 3rd level as the minimum casting level producing sound equal to 4 people. Each additional caster level adds the same volume, so a 4th-level caster can create sound equal to 8 people. The spell can create talking, singing, shouting, walking, marching, running, or similar noises. The sound may be virtually any type, but its volume must match the caster’s level. A horde of squeaking, running rats is about equal to 8 people running and shouting. A roaring lion equals the volume of 16 people, and a roaring dragon equals at least 24 people. If a character states disbelief, they receive a saving throw. Success means they hear nothing or only a faint sound. This spell is especially effective with phantasmal force. Material Component: A bit of wool or a small lump of wax.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user audible glamer":{"name":"Audible Glamer","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"6” + 1” per level","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"Hearing range","components":"V, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Audible Glamer\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 6” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Hearing range\nThis spell creates sound at any desired point within range. The sound may seem to recede, approach, or remain fixed. The volume depends on caster level, with 3rd level as the minimum casting level producing sound equal to 4 people. Each additional caster level adds the same volume, so a 4th-level caster can create sound equal to 8 people. The spell can create talking, singing, shouting, walking, marching, running, or similar noises. The sound may be virtually any type, but its volume must match the caster’s level. A horde of squeaking, running rats is about equal to 8 people running and shouting. A roaring lion equals the volume of 16 people, and a roaring dragon equals at least 24 people. If a character states disbelief, they receive a saving throw. Success means they hear nothing or only a faint sound. This spell is especially effective with phantasmal force. Material Component: A bit of wool or a small lump of wax.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Audible Glamer","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user continual light":{"name":"Continual Light","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"6”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"6” radius globe","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Continual Light\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6” radius globe\nThis spell is the same as the 3rd-level cleric spell continual light, except that its range is 6” instead of 12”, and the caster cannot reverse it.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Continual Light","class":"Magic-User"},"darkness 15 radius":{"name":"Darkness, 15’ Radius","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 turn + 1 round per level","aoe":"1½” radius globe","components":"V, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Darkness, 15’ Radius\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 turn + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1½” radius globe\nThis spell creates total, impenetrable darkness in its area. Infravision and ultravision are useless. Neither normal nor magical light works unless a light or continual light spell is used. A light spell negates darkness, and vice versa. Material Components: A bit of bat fur and either a drop of pitch or a piece of coal.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user darkness 15 radius":{"name":"Darkness, 15’ Radius","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 turn + 1 round per level","aoe":"1½” radius globe","components":"V, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Darkness, 15’ Radius\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 turn + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1½” radius globe\nThis spell creates total, impenetrable darkness in its area. Infravision and ultravision are useless. Neither normal nor magical light works unless a light or continual light spell is used. A light spell negates darkness, and vice versa. Material Components: A bit of bat fur and either a drop of pitch or a piece of coal.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Darkness, 15’ Radius","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user detect evil":{"name":"Detect Evil","level":"2","school":"Divination","range":"6”","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"1” path","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Evil\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Detect Good\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” path\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 1st-level cleric spell detect evil.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Detect Evil","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user detect invisibility":{"name":"Detect Invisibility","level":"2","school":"Divination","range":"1” per level","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"1” path","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Invisibility\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” path\nThis spell allows the magic-user to clearly see invisible objects, as well as astral, ethereal, hidden, invisible, or out-of-phase creatures. Detection occurs in the caster’s line of sight along a 1” wide path to the range limit. Material Components: A pinch of talc and a small sprinkling of powdered silver.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Detect Invisibility","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user esp":{"name":"ESP","level":"2","school":"Divination","range":"½” per level, maximum 9”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"One creature per probe","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"ESP\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level, maximum 9”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature per probe\nThis spell allows the caster to detect the surface thoughts of creatures in range, except creatures with no mind as we understand it, such as undead. ESP is blocked by 2 or more feet of rock, 2 or more inches of any metal other than lead, or a thin sheet of lead foil. The caster may probe the surface thoughts of 1 creature per turn, receiving simple instinctual thoughts from lower creatures. Probes may continue on the same creature from round to round. The spell can help determine whether a creature lurks behind a door, though it will not always reveal what sort of creature it is. Material Component: A copper piece.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: ESP","class":"Magic-User"},"fools gold":{"name":"Fools Gold","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"1”","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"1 cubic foot per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Fools Gold\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per level\nThis spell temporarily changes copper coins into gold pieces, or brass items into solid gold, for the spell’s duration. For this spell, 4,000 gold pieces equal 1 cubic foot. Any creature viewing the false gold receives a detection roll equal to or less than its Intelligence, but it must add 1 to the die roll per caster level, making high-level castings difficult to detect. If the false gold is struck hard by cold-wrought iron, there is a chance it reverts depending on the component used: 30% if a 50 gp citrine was powdered and sprinkled over the metal, 25% if a 100 gp amber stone was powdered, 10% if a 500 gp topaz was powdered, or 1% if a 1,000 gp oriental corundum topaz was powdered.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user fools gold":{"name":"Fools Gold","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"1”","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"1 cubic foot per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Fools Gold\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per level\nThis spell temporarily changes copper coins into gold pieces, or brass items into solid gold, for the spell’s duration. For this spell, 4,000 gold pieces equal 1 cubic foot. Any creature viewing the false gold receives a detection roll equal to or less than its Intelligence, but it must add 1 to the die roll per caster level, making high-level castings difficult to detect. If the false gold is struck hard by cold-wrought iron, there is a chance it reverts depending on the component used: 30% if a 50 gp citrine was powdered and sprinkled over the metal, 25% if a 100 gp amber stone was powdered, 10% if a 500 gp topaz was powdered, or 1% if a 1,000 gp oriental corundum topaz was powdered.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Fools Gold","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user forget":{"name":"Forget","level":"2","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"3”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"2” × 2”","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Forget\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 2” × 2”\nThis spell causes creatures in the area to forget events of the previous round, meaning the previous 1 minute before the spell is uttered. For every 3 caster levels, another minute of past time is forgotten. The spell does not negate charm, suggestion, geas, quest, or similar magic, but the creature who caused such magic might be forgotten. The caster may affect 1d4 creatures. If only 1 creature is affected, it saves versus magic at -2. If 2 are affected, each saves at -1. If 3 or 4 are affected, saves are normal. A clerical heal or restoration spell specially cast for this purpose restores the lost memories, as does wish; other means do not.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Forget","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user invisibility":{"name":"Invisibility","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Invisibility\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell causes the recipient to vanish from sight and become undetectable by normal vision or infravision. The invisible creature is not magically silenced. The spell lasts until magically broken or dispelled, cancelled by the caster or recipient, or until the recipient attacks any creature. The recipient may open doors, talk, eat, climb stairs, and so on, but attacking immediately makes them visible, though the first attack benefits from prior invisibility. Even allies cannot see the invisible creature or gear unless they can normally see invisible things or use magic to do so. Highly intelligent creatures with 10 or more Hit Dice, levels, or equivalent intelligence have a chance to automatically detect invisible objects. Material Components: An eyelash encased in gum arabic.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Invisibility","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user knock":{"name":"Knock","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"6”","duration":"Special","aoe":"10 square feet per level","components":"V","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Knock\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10 square feet per level\nThis spell opens stuck, held, wizard-locked, barred, otherwise locked, or trick-opening doors, boxes, and chests. It also opens secret doors and loosens shackles or chains. If used on a wizard-locked door, the spell does not remove wizard lock, but suspends it for 1 turn. In all other cases, knock permanently opens locks or welds, though locks may later be closed and locked again. The spell does not raise bars or similar impediments such as a portcullis. The spell performs two functions, so a door that is locked, barred, and held requires two knock spells.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Knock","class":"Magic-User"},"leomund s trap":{"name":"Leomund’s Trap","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Object touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Leomund’s Trap\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Object touched\nThis false trap is designed to fool dwarves or thieves attempting to steal or tamper with the caster’s goods. The magic-user places a dweomer on a small mechanism or device, such as a lock, hinge, hasp, screw-on cap, or ratchet. A trap-detecting character has an 80% chance to notice Leomund’s trap and believe it real, reduced by 4% per level of the examiner beyond 1st. If the supposed trap is then removed, the remover is only 20% likely to believe they succeeded, plus 4% per level. The spell is illusory; nothing happens if the trap is ignored. Its purpose is to frighten thieves away or waste their time. Only one Leomund’s trap may be placed within a 50-foot by 50-foot area. Material Component: A piece of iron pyrite touched to the object.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user leomund s trap":{"name":"Leomund’s Trap","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Object touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Leomund’s Trap\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Object touched\nThis false trap is designed to fool dwarves or thieves attempting to steal or tamper with the caster’s goods. The magic-user places a dweomer on a small mechanism or device, such as a lock, hinge, hasp, screw-on cap, or ratchet. A trap-detecting character has an 80% chance to notice Leomund’s trap and believe it real, reduced by 4% per level of the examiner beyond 1st. If the supposed trap is then removed, the remover is only 20% likely to believe they succeeded, plus 4% per level. The spell is illusory; nothing happens if the trap is ignored. Its purpose is to frighten thieves away or waste their time. Only one Leomund’s trap may be placed within a 50-foot by 50-foot area. Material Component: A piece of iron pyrite touched to the object.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Leomund’s Trap","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user levitate":{"name":"Levitate","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"2” per level","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Levitate\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the magic-user to levitate themselves or another creature. Maximum weight is 1,000 gold pieces per caster level; for example, a 3rd-level magic-user can levitate up to 3,000 gold pieces, or 300 pounds. If cast on the caster, vertical movement is 20 feet per round. If cast on another creature, the caster may move it vertically up to 10 feet per round. The spell grants no horizontal movement, though the recipient may push along a cliff face or similar surface to move laterally. The caster may cancel the spell at will. An unwilling target receives a saving throw. Material Component: A small leather loop or a piece of golden wire bent into a cup shape with a long shank.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Levitate","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user locate object":{"name":"Locate Object","level":"2","school":"Divination","range":"2” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Locate Object\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Obscure Object\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is the same as the 3rd-level cleric spell locate object, except that its range differs.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Locate Object","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user magic mouth":{"name":"Magic Mouth","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"Special","duration":"Special","aoe":"One object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Magic Mouth\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One object\nThis spell gives an object an enchanted mouth that appears and speaks a message when a specified event occurs. The message may be up to 25 words in a language known by the caster and must be delivered within 1 turn. The mouth cannot speak magical spells. It moves as it speaks; if placed on a statue, the statue’s mouth appears to move. The spell may be placed on a tree, rock, door, or almost any object, but not on intelligent animal or vegetable creatures. The triggering condition may be general or specific, such as “speak to the first creature that touches you” or “speak only when an octogenarian female human carrying a sack of groat clusters sits cross-legged within 1 foot.” The command range is ½” per caster level. For example, a 6th-level magic-user can set the mouth to speak when a winged creature comes within 3”. Until the condition is fulfilled, the spell remains active. Magic mouth cannot distinguish invisible creatures, alignment, level, Hit Dice, or class except by external garb. Material Component: A small bit of honeycomb.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Magic Mouth","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user mirror image":{"name":"Mirror Image","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"6-foot radius around caster","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mirror Image\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6-foot radius around caster\nThis spell creates 1d4 exact duplicates of the caster around them. The images do exactly what the magic-user does, and the spell creates blurring and slight distortion, making it impossible for opponents to know which is real. When an image is struck by any weapon, magical or mundane, it disappears. Other images remain until struck or until the spell ends. The images shift from round to round, so even if the real caster is struck one round, they cannot be distinguished the next. To determine the number of images, roll percentile dice and add 1 per caster level: 25 or less creates 1 image, 26–50 creates 2, 51–75 creates 3, and 76 or more creates 4. All images vanish when the spell expires.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Mirror Image","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user pyrotechnics":{"name":"Pyrotechnics","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"12”","duration":"Special","aoe":"10 or 100 times the fire source used","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Pyrotechnics\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10 or 100 times the fire source used\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level druid spell pyrotechnics.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Pyrotechnics","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user ray of enfeeblement":{"name":"Ray Of Enfeeblement","level":"2","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1” + ¼” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Ray Of Enfeeblement\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” + ¼” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell weakens an opponent, reducing Strength and attacks based on Strength by 25% or more. For each caster level beyond 3rd, the Strength reduction increases by 2%; for example, at 4th level the reduction is 27%. Range and duration also depend on caster level. A creature struck by the ray loses the appropriate percentage of damage dealt by physical attacks, including missiles, weapons, bites, claws, gores, kicks, and constriction. The referee determines any other appropriate reductions. A successful saving throw negates the spell.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Ray Of Enfeeblement","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user rope trick":{"name":"Rope Trick","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"2 turns per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Rope Trick\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 2 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is cast on a rope 5 to 30 feet long. One end rises into the air until the rope hangs perpendicular, as if fastened above. The upper end is actually fixed in an extra-dimensional space. The caster and up to 5 others may climb the rope and disappear into this safe space, where no creature can find them. The rope cannot be taken into the extra-dimensional space if 6 people have climbed it, but otherwise it may be pulled up. If not pulled up, it hangs in the air and may be removed by another creature. Those inside must climb down before the spell ends or fall from the height they originally climbed when the spell expires. Only one person can climb the rope at a time. The spell also permits climbers to reach a normal place if they do not climb all the way to the upper end. Material Components: Powdered corn extract and a twisted loop of parchment.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Rope Trick","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user scare":{"name":"Scare","level":"2","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1”","duration":"3d4 rounds","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Scare\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 3d4 rounds\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell affects a creature with fewer than 6 levels or Hit Dice. If the target fails its saving throw versus magic, it falls into trembling fear. The creature does not drop held items unless encumbered. If cornered, it fights at -1 on “to hit” rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws. The spell has no effect on elves, half-elves, undead such as skeletons, zombies, ghouls, shadows, ghasts, wights, and wraiths, larvae, lemures, manes, or clerics of any sort. Material Component: A bit of bone from an undead skeleton, zombie, ghoul, ghast, or mummy.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Scare","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user shatter":{"name":"Shatter","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"6”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Shatter\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One object\nThis spell affects nonmagical objects made of crystal, glass, ceramic, or porcelain, such as vials, bottles, flasks, jugs, windows, and mirrors. Such objects are shattered into dozens of pieces. Objects weighing more than 100 gold pieces per caster level are unaffected. All other objects of the appropriate material must save versus crushing blow or be shattered. Material Component: A chip of mica.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Shatter","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user stinking cloud":{"name":"Stinking Cloud","level":"2","school":"Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"2” × 2” × 2” cloud","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Stinking Cloud\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 2” × 2” × 2” cloud\nThis spell creates a billowing mass of nauseous vapors up to 3” from the caster. Any creature caught in the cloud must save versus poison or become helpless with nausea for 1d4+1 rounds. Creatures that save are helpless only while they remain in the cloud and for 1 round after emerging, due to irritation of the eyes and nose. Material Component: A rotten egg or several skunk cabbage leaves.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Stinking Cloud","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user strength":{"name":"Strength","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"Person touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Strength\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Person touched\nThis spell increases the touched character’s Strength by an amount based on class, subject to normal race, sex, and class restrictions. Clerics gain 1d6 Strength, fighters gain 1d8, magic-users gain 1d4, thieves gain 1d6, and monks gain 1d4. If a fighter, paladin, or ranger already has Strength 18, the spell adds 10% to 80% to extraordinary Strength. Strength additions above 18 are treated as +10% extraordinary Strength per point. Material Component: A few hairs or a pinch of dung from a strong animal, such as an ape, bear, or ox.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Strength","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user web":{"name":"Web","level":"2","school":"Evocation","range":"½” per level","duration":"2 turns per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates or half","save_type":"","description":"Web\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 2 turns per level\nSaving Throw: Negates or half\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a many-layered mass of strong, sticky strands like giant spider webs. The webs must be anchored to two or more diametrically opposed points, such as floor and ceiling or opposite walls. The spell covers up to 8 cubic inches, and the webs must be at least 1” thick. Creatures caught in or touching the webs become stuck. Creatures with Strength below 13 remain trapped until freed or until the spell ends. For every full turn trapped, a creature has a cumulative 5% chance of suffocating. Creatures with Strength 13–17 can break through 1 foot of webs per turn. Creatures with Strength 18 or greater break through 1 foot per round. Strong and huge creatures break through 1 foot per segment. Web strands are flammable. Fire burns them away in 1 round, dealing 2d4 damage to creatures caught in the webs, though creatures freed from the strands are not harmed. If the saving throw is made and there is room to escape, the creature jumps free. If there is no room to escape, the webs are only half strength. Material Component: A bit of spider web.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Web","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user wizard lock":{"name":"Wizard Lock","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"30 square feet per level","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wizard Lock\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 30 square feet per level\nThis spell magically locks a door, chest, or portal. The wizard-locked object can be opened only by breaking it, by dispel magic, by knock, or by a magic-user at least 4 levels higher than the caster. Knock and the higher-level magic-user method do not remove the wizard lock; they only negate it briefly. Extra-dimensional creatures do not affect wizard lock as they do hold portal.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 3rd Level","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Wizard Lock","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user blink":{"name":"Blink","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Personal","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Blink\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Personal\nThis spell causes the magic-user’s material form to blink out and back into the current plane at random times and directions each round. The segment in which the caster blinks is determined by 2d4. The caster reappears 2 feet from the previous position in a random direction: 1 = right ahead, 2 = right, 3 = right behind, 4 = behind, 5 = left behind, 6 = left, 7 = left ahead, 8 = ahead. If the destination is occupied, the caster is displaced away from the starting position by the shortest distance needed to appear in empty space, up to 10 additional feet. If no empty space is available, the caster is trapped on the Ethereal Plane. During and after the blink segment, the caster can only be attacked by effects that strike both locations at once, such as breath weapons or fireball. Other attacks can hit only if made before the blink segment. The caster is only 75% likely to perform actions other than physical attacks with hand-held weapons correctly while the spell lasts; spell, device, or item use may fail or be misdirected at the referee’s discretion.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Blink","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user clairaudience":{"name":"Clairaudience","level":"3","school":"Divination","range":"Special","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Clairaudience\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the magic-user to concentrate on a known or obvious location and hear sounds within a 6” radius of that point. Distance is not a factor, but the location must be familiar or obvious, such as behind a door, around a corner, or in a copse of woods. Only sounds normally detectable by the caster can be heard. Metal sheeting or magical protection blocks the spell. It functions only on the plane where the caster is located. Material Component: A small silver horn worth at least 100 gp, which disappears when the spell is cast.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Clairaudience","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user clairvoyance":{"name":"Clairvoyance","level":"3","school":"Divination","range":"Special","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Clairvoyance\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is similar to clairaudience, but allows the magic-user to see in their mind whatever lies within sight range from the chosen location. Distance is not a factor, but the location must be familiar or obvious. Light conditions matter. If the area is dark, only a 1” radius from the spell’s center can be seen; otherwise, vision extends to normal sight range. Metal sheeting or magical protection blocks the spell. It functions only on the caster’s current plane. Material Component: A pinch of powdered pineal gland from a human or humanoid creature.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Clairvoyance","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user dispel magic":{"name":"Dispel Magic","level":"3","school":"Abjuration","range":"12”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"3” cube","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Dispel Magic\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” cube\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level cleric spell dispel magic.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Dispel Magic","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user explosive runes":{"name":"Explosive Runes","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"1” radius","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Explosive Runes\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: 1” radius\nThe magic-user traces mystic runes on a book, map, scroll, or similar written object to prevent unauthorized reading. The runes are difficult to detect, with a 5% chance per reader level; thieves have only a 5% chance in any case. When read, the runes explode, dealing 6d4+6 damage to the reader with no saving throw. Other creatures within the blast radius take the same damage, or half with a successful saving throw. The caster and any magic-users instructed by the caster can read the protected writing without triggering the runes. The caster may remove the runes at will. Otherwise, they can be removed only by dispel magic and last until triggered. The object bearing the runes is destroyed by the explosion unless it is not normally subject to destruction by magical fire.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Explosive Runes","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user feign death":{"name":"Feign Death","level":"3","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"6 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Feign Death\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 6 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell places the caster or another willing creature into a cataleptic state indistinguishable from death, provided the target’s levels or Hit Dice do not exceed the caster’s level. The affected creature can smell, hear, and understand what is happening, but cannot see or feel anything. Wounding or mistreatment causes no reaction and deals only half normal damage. Paralysis, poison, and energy drain do not affect the creature while the spell lasts, though poison introduced into the body takes effect when the spell ends, with a saving throw allowed. Only a willing creature can be affected. The caster may end the spell at any time, but bodily functions require 1 full round to resume.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Feign Death","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user fireball":{"name":"Fireball","level":"3","school":"Evocation","range":"10” + 1” per level","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"2” radius sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Fireball\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 10” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: 2” radius sphere\nThis spell creates an explosive burst of flame that detonates with a low roar and deals 1d6 damage per caster level. Wands of fireball produce 6d6 fireballs, staves produce 8d6 fireballs, and scrolls produce 5d6 to 10d6 fireballs. The burst creates little pressure and generally conforms to the shape of the area, filling a volume equal to its normal spherical volume. It ignites combustibles and melts soft metals such as gold, copper, silver, and similar metals. Exposed items must save to avoid damage, though items carried by a creature that saves are considered unaffected. The caster points and states the distance and height where the fireball is to burst. A streak flashes from the pointing finger and blossoms into the fireball unless it strikes a material body first. Creatures that fail their saves take full damage; those that save take half. Material Component: A tiny ball of bat guano and sulfur.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Fireball","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user flame arrow":{"name":"Flame Arrow","level":"3","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Touch","duration":"1 segment per level","aoe":"Each arrow or bolt touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Flame Arrow\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 segment per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Each arrow or bolt touched\nAfter casting this spell, the magic-user may touch one arrow or crossbow bolt per segment for the spell’s duration. Each missile becomes magical, though it gains no bonus “to hit.” Each missile must be fired within 1 round, or flame consumes it and the magic is lost. Fiery missiles have normal chances to ignite materials, and creatures especially subject to fire damage take +1 damage from any flame arrow that hits. Material Components: A drop of oil and a small piece of flint.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Flame Arrow","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user fly":{"name":"Fly","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per level + 1d6 turns","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Fly\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level + 1d6 turns\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell grants magical flight. The affected creature may move vertically or horizontally at 12” per move, half speed while ascending, and double speed while diving downward. The exact duration is unknown to the caster because the 1d6 turn variable addition is secretly determined by the Dungeon Master. Material Component: A wing feather from any bird.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Fly","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user gust of wind":{"name":"Gust Of Wind","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 segment","aoe":"1” wide path, 1” long per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Gust Of Wind\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 segment\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” wide path, 1” long per level\nThis spell creates a strong puff of air from the magic-user in the direction faced. The gust extinguishes candles, torches, and similar unprotected flames. Protected flames, such as lanterns, dance wildly and have a 5% chance per caster level to be extinguished. Large fires are fanned outward 1d6 feet in the wind’s direction. Small flying creatures are forced back 1d6 inches, man-sized flying creatures moving into the gust are held motionless, and large flying creatures are slowed by 50% for 1 round. The gust also blows over light objects. Its path is 1” wide and 1” long per caster level. Material Component: A legume seed.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Gust Of Wind","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user haste":{"name":"Haste","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"6”","duration":"3 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"4” × 4” area, one creature per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Haste\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 3 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4” × 4” area, one creature per level\nThis spell causes affected creatures to move and attack at double their normal rates. A creature with movement 6” and one attack per round would move at 12” and attack twice per round. Spellcasting is not accelerated. The spell affects one creature per caster level, choosing the closest creatures to the caster first, provided all are within the area of effect. Haste negates slow. The spell ages recipients because of accelerated metabolic processes. Material Component: A shaving of licorice root.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Haste","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user hold person":{"name":"Hold Person","level":"3","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"12”","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"One to four persons","components":"V","ct":"3 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Hold Person\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One to four persons\nThis spell is similar to the 2nd-level cleric spell hold person, immobilizing designated persons within range. If three or four persons are targeted, their saves are normal. If two are targeted, saves are made at -1. If one is targeted, the save is made at -3. Partial negation, such as from a ring of spell turning, causes the spell to function as slow unless the saving throw succeeds. Affected creatures include brownies, dryads, dwarves, elves, gnolls, gnomes, goblins, half-elves, halflings, half-orcs, hobgoblins, humans, kobolds, lizard men, nixies, orcs, pixies, sprites, and troglodytes.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Hold Person","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user infravision":{"name":"Infravision","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"12 turns + 6 turns per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Infravision\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 12 turns + 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell allows the recipient to see light in the infrared spectrum, detecting heat radiation differences up to 6”. Strong infrared sources, such as fire, lanterns, and torches, tend to blind or cast “shadows” much as bright light affects normal vision, reducing the spell’s effectiveness. Invisible creatures are not usually detected by infravision, because invisibility affects infrared as well as ultraviolet and normal light. Material Component: A pinch of dried carrot or an agate.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Infravision","class":"Magic-User"},"invisibility 10 radius":{"name":"Invisibility, 10’ Radius","level":"3","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"10-foot radius around creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Invisibility, 10’ Radius\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10-foot radius around creature touched\nThis spell is essentially the same as invisibility. Affected creatures cannot see one another. If an affected creature attacks, only that creature’s invisibility is negated unless the original spell recipient causes the spell to break.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user invisibility 10 radius":{"name":"Invisibility, 10’ Radius","level":"3","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"10-foot radius around creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Invisibility, 10’ Radius\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10-foot radius around creature touched\nThis spell is essentially the same as invisibility. Affected creatures cannot see one another. If an affected creature attacks, only that creature’s invisibility is negated unless the original spell recipient causes the spell to break.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Invisibility, 10’ Radius","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user leomund s tiny hut":{"name":"Leomund’s Tiny Hut","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"10-foot diameter sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Leomund’s Tiny Hut\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10-foot diameter sphere\nThis spell creates an opaque sphere of force around the caster, with half above the ground or floor and half below. The interior remains 70°F in outside cold down to 0°F and outside heat up to 105°F. Colder or hotter temperatures change the interior temperature degree for degree beyond those limits. The hut withstands winds up to 50 miles per hour; stronger winds destroy it. The caster may dimly illuminate or darken the interior on command. The field is opaque from outside but transparent from inside. It does not protect against missiles, weapons, spells, or similar attacks. Up to 6 other man-sized creatures can fit inside with the caster and may pass in and out freely. If the caster leaves, the spell dissipates. Material Component: A small crystal bead that shatters when the spell ends or the hut is dispelled.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Leomund’s Tiny Hut","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user lightning bolt":{"name":"Lightning Bolt","level":"3","school":"Evocation","range":"4” + 1” per level","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Lightning Bolt\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 4” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell releases a powerful stroke of electrical energy dealing 1d6 damage per caster level, or half damage to creatures that save. The spell’s range determines where the stroke begins, and the bolt then extends outward from that point. It can ignite combustibles, sunder wooden doors, splinter up to 1 foot of stone, and melt low-melting metals such as lead, gold, copper, silver, and bronze. Objects struck by the full force must save. The caster chooses either a forked bolt 1” wide and 4” long or a single bolt ½” wide and 8” long. If a solid nonconducting barrier blocks the bolt before its full length is reached, the bolt rebounds toward the caster, continuing until its full length is spent. Material Components: A bit of fur and an amber, crystal, or glass rod.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Lightning Bolt","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user monster summoning i":{"name":"Monster Summoning I","level":"3","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"3”","duration":"2 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Monster Summoning I\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nWithin 1d4 rounds after casting, this spell summons 2d4 1st-level monsters, chosen randomly by the referee. The monsters appear within range at the caster’s desired location and attack the caster’s opponents to the best of their ability until ordered to stop, the spell ends, or they are slain. If no opponents are present, and communication is possible, the monsters may perform other physically possible services for the caster. Material Components: A tiny bag and a small candle, which need not be lit.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Monster Summoning I","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user phantasmal force":{"name":"Phantasmal Force","level":"3","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"8” + 1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"8 square inches + 1 square inch per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Phantasmal Force\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 8 square inches + 1 square inch per level\nThis spell creates a visual illusion affecting all believing creatures that view it, even causing apparent damage from phantasmal missiles or from falling into an illusory pit. Sound is not part of the illusion. The illusion lasts until struck by an opponent, unless the caster makes it react appropriately, or until the caster stops concentrating due to choice, movement, or a successful damaging attack. Creatures that disbelieve may save versus spell. Success reveals the illusion for what it is and grants +4 to associates’ saves if that knowledge can be communicated. Creatures not observing the effect are immune until they view it. The spell may create any object, creature, or force within the area of effect, and the area may move within range. Material Component: A bit of fleece.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Phantasmal Force","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user protection from evil 10 radius":{"name":"Protection From Evil, 10’ Radius","level":"3","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"10-foot radius sphere around creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Protection From Evil, 10’ Radius\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Protection From Good, 10’ Radius\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10-foot radius sphere around creature touched\nThis spell is the same as protection from evil, except for its larger area of effect. See the 1st-level cleric spell protection from evil for general details.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Protection From Evil, 10’ Radius","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user protection from normal missiles":{"name":"Protection From Normal Missiles","level":"3","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Protection From Normal Missiles\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell grants total immunity to hurled and projected normal missiles, such as arrows, axes, bolts, javelins, small stones, and spears. It also reduces damage by 1 point per die from large or magical missiles, such as ballista missiles, catapult stones, magical arrows, magical bolts, and magical javelins. It does not protect against fireball, lightning bolt, magic missile, or similar magical attacks. Material Component: A piece of tortoise or turtle shell.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Protection From Normal Missiles","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user slow":{"name":"Slow","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"9” + 1” per level","duration":"3 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"4” × 4” area, one creature per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Slow\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 9” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 3 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4” × 4” area, one creature per level\nThis spell causes affected creatures to move and attack at half normal or current rate. It negates haste, has cumulative effects on already slowed creatures, and affects magically sped or slowed creatures. The spell affects one creature per caster level within the designated 4” × 4” area. Material Component: A drop of treacle.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Slow","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user suggestion":{"name":"Suggestion","level":"3","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"3”","duration":"6 turns + 6 turns per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Suggestion\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 6 turns + 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell influences the chosen creature’s actions through a few words, phrases, or one or two sentences suggesting a course of action. The target must understand the caster’s language. The suggestion must sound reasonable. Obviously harmful instructions, such as stabbing oneself or jumping onto a spear, negate the spell. However, a suggestion that acid is pure water and a quick dip would be refreshing, or that a red dragon could gain treasure elsewhere through cooperation, may be effective. The suggested action can continue for a long duration. If the target saves, the spell has no effect. A highly reasonable suggestion may impose a saving throw penalty at the Dungeon Master’s discretion. Undead are unaffected. Material Components: A snake’s tongue and either a bit of honeycomb or a drop of sweet oil.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Suggestion","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user tongues":{"name":"Tongues","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"6” diameter circle","components":"V, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Tongues\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Confuse Languages\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6” diameter circle\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 4th-level cleric spell tongues. Material Component: A small clay model of a ziggurat, which shatters when the spell is cast.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Tongues","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user water breathing":{"name":"Water Breathing","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"3 turns per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Water Breathing\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Air Breathing\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 3 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nExcept as noted above, and except that the material component is a short reed or piece of straw, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level druid spell water breathing.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 4th Level","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Water Breathing","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user charm monster":{"name":"Charm Monster","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"6”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Charm Monster\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is similar to charm person, but it can affect any living creature, or several lower-level creatures. Affected creatures regard the caster as friendly, treating them as an ally or companion to be guarded from harm. If communication is possible, the charmed creature follows reasonable requests, instructions, or orders. The charm eventually breaks, with the chance depending on the creature’s level or Hit Dice: 1st level or up to 2 HD, 5% per week; 2nd level or up to 3+2 HD, 10%; 3rd level or up to 4+4 HD, 15%; 4th level or up to 6 HD, 25%; 5th level or up to 7+2 HD, 35%; 6th level or up to 8+4 HD, 45%; 7th level or up to 10 HD, 60%; 8th level or up to 12 HD, 75%; 9th level or over 12 HD, 90%. Overt hostility by the caster automatically breaks the spell or at least allows a new saving throw. The spell affects 2d4 1st-level creatures, 1d4 2nd-level creatures, 1 or 2 3rd-level creatures, or 1 creature of 4th level or higher.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Charm Monster","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user confusion":{"name":"Confusion","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"12”","duration":"2 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Up to 6” × 6”","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Confusion\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Up to 6” × 6”\nExcept as noted above, this spell is identical to the 7th-level druid spell confusion. It affects a base 2d8 creatures. Material Component: A set of three nut shells.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Confusion","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user dig":{"name":"Dig","level":"4","school":"Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"5-foot cube per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Dig\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 5-foot cube per level\nThis spell excavates 125 cubic feet of earth, sand, or mud per round, creating a 5-foot cube-shaped hole each round. Excavated material scatters evenly around the pit. If the caster continues digging below 5 feet, the pit may collapse: 15% per additional 5 feet in earth, 35% per additional 5 feet in sand, and 55% per additional 5 feet in mud. A creature at the edge, within 1 foot, uses Dexterity as a saving throw to avoid falling in; rolling equal to or below Dexterity avoids the fall. A creature moving rapidly toward the pit falls in unless it saves versus magic. A creature caught in the center of a newly dug pit always falls in. Material Components: A miniature shovel and tiny bucket, which must be held while each pit is excavated.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Dig","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user dimension door":{"name":"Dimension Door","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Spellcaster","components":"V","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Dimension Door\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Spellcaster\nThis spell instantly transports the magic-user up to 3” per caster level. This precise teleportation has no chance of error, and the caster arrives exactly where desired, either by visualizing a place within range or by stating direction and distance. If the destination is occupied by a solid body, the caster remains in the Astral Plane until located by someone who casts dispel magic on them. While stranded, the caster is stunned and cannot successfully cast spells. If the caster appears in mid-air, falling damage applies unless further magic intervenes. The caster’s worn and carried gear travels with them, up to 5,000 gold pieces of nonliving matter or half that weight of living matter. Recovery from the spell requires 7 segments.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Dimension Door","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user enchanted weapon":{"name":"Enchanted Weapon","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"Weapon or weapons touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Enchanted Weapon\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Disenchant Weapon\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Weapon or weapons touched\nThis spell turns an ordinary weapon into a magical one. The weapon counts as equivalent to +1 for purposes of striking creatures requiring magic weapons, but it gains no actual bonus. Two small weapons, such as arrows, bolts, or daggers, or one large weapon, such as an axe, bow, hammer, mace, or sword, can be affected. A successful hit by an enchanted missile weapon breaks the spell on that missile. Otherwise, the spell lasts until its duration expires. Material Components: Powdered lime and carbon.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Enchanted Weapon","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user extension i":{"name":"Extension I","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Extension I\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell extends the duration of a previously cast 1st-, 2nd-, or 3rd-level spell by 50%. For example, levitate may last 1½ turns per level, and hold person may last 3 rounds per level. The spell affects only spells where duration is meaningful.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Extension I","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user fear":{"name":"Fear","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"6” long cone, 3” diameter at end, ½ foot at base","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Fear\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 6” long cone, 3” diameter at end, ½ foot at base\nThis spell sends forth an invisible ray that causes creatures in its area to flee from the caster in panic. Affected creatures may drop held items immediately. The base chance is 60% for 1st-level or 1-Hit-Die creatures, reduced by 5% per level or Hit Die above 1st. Thus, at 10th level the chance is 15%, and at 13th level it is 0%. Affected creatures flee at their fastest rate for a number of rounds equal to the caster’s level. Panic begins on the round after casting, though item dropping occurs immediately. Creatures that save are unaffected. Material Component: The heart of a hen or a white feather.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Fear","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user fire charm":{"name":"Fire Charm","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1”","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"30-foot diameter of fire","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Fire Charm\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 30-foot diameter of fire\nThis spell causes a normal fire source, such as a brazier, torch, or bonfire, to become a magical agent. A gossamer veil of multicolored flame circles 5 feet from the fire. Creatures observing the fire or veil must save versus magic or remain motionless, gazing transfixed at the flames. While charmed, they are subject to suggestion spells of 12 or fewer words, saving against them at -3. The charm breaks if the creature is physically attacked, if a solid object blocks its view of the flames, or when the spell ends. The veil is not magical fire, and passing through it deals the same damage as passing through the original fire source. Material Component: A very thin piece of multicolored silk thrown into the fire source.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Fire Charm","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user fire shield":{"name":"Fire Shield","level":"4","school":"Evocation-Alteration","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Personal","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Fire Shield\n\nSchool: Evocation-Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Personal\nThis spell makes the magic-user appear to be engulfed in thin, wispy flames that shed dim light in a 15-foot radius. The flames are blue or green for the hot-flame version, and violet or blue for the cold-flame version. Any creature striking the caster with body or hand-held weapons deals normal damage to the caster but takes double that damage in return. With the hot-flame version, cold-based attacks are saved against at +2 and deal half or no damage, while fire-based attacks affect the caster normally and deal double damage if the caster fails any required save. With the cold-flame version, fire-based attacks are saved against at +2 and deal half or no damage, while cold-based attacks affect the caster normally and deal double damage if the caster fails any required save. Material Component: For the hot-flame version, a bit of phosphorus. For the cold-flame version, a live firefly or glowworm, or the tail portions of four dead ones.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Fire Shield","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user fire trap":{"name":"Fire Trap","level":"4","school":"Evocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent until discharged","aoe":"Object touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 rounds","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Fire Trap\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: Permanent until discharged\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: Object touched\nThis spell traps any closable item, such as a book, box, bottle, chest, coffer, coffin, door, or drawer. The trapped item cannot also reliably receive hold portal or wizard lock. If fire trap and hold portal are attempted together, only the first spell works, or both fail if simultaneous. If fire trap is cast after wizard lock, fire trap is negated; if simultaneous, both are negated; if wizard lock is cast after fire trap, there is a 50% chance both are negated. Knock does not affect fire trap; touching or entering the trapped object triggers the explosion. The caster may use the object safely. When discharged, the trap explodes in a 5-foot radius, dealing 1d4 damage plus 1 point per caster level, or half damage on a successful save versus magic. The trapped item is not harmed. A fire trap has only half the normal chance to be detected, and failing to remove it detonates it immediately. Material Component: Sulfur or saltpeter used to trace the closure.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Fire Trap","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user fumble":{"name":"Fumble","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Fumble\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell makes the target suddenly clumsy and awkward. Running creatures trip and fall, creatures reaching for items fumble and drop them, and creatures using weapons awkwardly drop them. Recovering from a fall or dropped item usually requires the whole next melee round. Fragile dropped items may break. If the victim saves, the spell merely causes them to operate at half normal efficiency, as with slow. Material Component: A dab of solidified milk fat.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Fumble","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user hallucinatory terrain":{"name":"Hallucinatory Terrain","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"2” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"1” × 1” square per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Hallucinatory Terrain\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2” per level\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” × 1” square per level\nThis spell creates an illusion that hides the actual terrain within the area. Open fields or roads may appear as swamp, hills, crevasses, or other difficult terrain. A pond may appear as meadow, a precipice as a gentle slope, or a rocky gully as a wide smooth road. The illusion persists until dispel magic is cast on the area or until an intelligent creature contacts it. Each caster level increases the affected area; for example, a 10th-level caster can affect up to a 10” × 10” square. Material Components: A stone, a twig, and a green plant fragment such as a leaf or blade of grass.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Hallucinatory Terrain","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user ice storm":{"name":"Ice Storm","level":"4","school":"Evocation","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Ice Storm\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates either hail or sleet. The hail version pounds a 4” diameter area with great hailstones, dealing 3d10 damage to creatures in the area. The sleet version creates driving sleet in an 8” diameter area, blinding creatures within it for the spell’s duration and icing the ground, which slows movement by 50% and gives moving creatures a 50% chance to slip and fall. This spell negates heat metal, though the hail version also deals damage in the process. Material Components: A pinch of dust and a few drops of water.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Ice Storm","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user massmorph":{"name":"Massmorph","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"11-foot × 1” square per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Massmorph\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 11-foot × 1” square per level\nThis spell makes willing man-sized or smaller creatures appear as normal trees. Up to 10 creatures per caster level can be affected, allowing a group to appear as a copse, grove, or orchard. Other creatures can pass through and touch the apparent trees without revealing the illusion. However, blows reveal the truth, as affected creatures take damage and bleed. Affected creatures must be within the spell’s area. Unwilling creatures are unaffected. The spell lasts until the caster commands it to end or until dispel magic is cast on the creatures. Material Component: A handful of bark chips.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Massmorph","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user minor globe of invulnerability":{"name":"Minor Globe Of Invulnerability","level":"4","school":"Abjuration","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"1” diameter sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Minor Globe Of Invulnerability\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” diameter sphere\nThis spell creates a magical sphere around the caster that prevents 1st-, 2nd-, and 3rd-level spells from penetrating. The area of effect of such spells does not include the globe’s interior. Spells may still be cast outward from within the globe. Fourth-level and higher spells are unaffected. Dispel magic can bring down the globe. Material Component: A glass or crystal bead.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Minor Globe Of Invulnerability","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user monster summoning ii":{"name":"Monster Summoning II","level":"4","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"4”","duration":"3 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Monster Summoning II\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 4”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 3 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is similar to monster summoning I, except that it summons 1d6 2nd-level monsters. There is a 1d4-round delay before they appear. Material Components: The same as monster summoning I: a tiny bag and a small candle.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Monster Summoning II","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user plant growth":{"name":"Plant Growth","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1” × 1” square per level","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Plant Growth\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” × 1” square per level\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level druid spell plant growth.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Plant Growth","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user polymorph other":{"name":"Polymorph Other","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"½” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Polymorph Other\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell completely changes the form and abilities of one creature, and may also change personality and mentality. Creatures of lower Intelligence cannot be polymorphed into forms with higher Intelligence, though the reverse is possible. The target must make a system shock roll to survive. If successful, it gains the form and abilities of the new creature. There is a base 100% chance that the creature’s personality and mentality also become those of the new form. Subtract 5% for each point of the original creature’s Intelligence. Adjust by ±5% per Hit Die difference between original and new form, adding for a higher-Hit-Die new form and subtracting for a lower-Hit-Die new form. This chance is checked daily until the change occurs. The creature may retain former knowledge if personality and mentality do not change. The new form may be stronger than it appears, such as a mummy changed into a puppy or a brontosaurus changed into an ant. Dispel magic can restore the creature, but this requires another system shock roll. Material Component: A caterpillar cocoon.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Polymorph Other","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user polymorph self":{"name":"Polymorph Self","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"2 turns per level","aoe":"The magic-user","components":"V","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Polymorph Self\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 2 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The magic-user\nThis spell allows the magic-user to assume the form of any creature from wren-sized to hippopotamus-sized, including that creature’s form of movement. It does not grant the creature’s attacks, magic, or special abilities, and it does not risk changing the caster’s personality or mentality. No system shock roll is needed. Thus, a caster changed into an owl can fly but retains human vision, and a caster changed into a black pudding can move under doors or along halls and ceilings but does not gain the pudding’s attacks or defenses. The assumed form must be strong enough for normal movement. The caster may change form as often as desired during the spell, requiring 5 segments per change. Damage to the polymorphed form is treated as damage to the caster, but when the caster returns to normal form, 1d12 hit points are restored.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Polymorph Self","class":"Magic-User"},"rary s mnemonic enhancer":{"name":"Rary’s Mnemonic Enhancer","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 day","aoe":"The magic-user","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Rary’s Mnemonic Enhancer\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 day\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The magic-user\nThis spell allows the magic-user to memorize or retain three additional spell levels: three 1st-level spells, one 1st-level and one 2nd-level spell, or one 3rd-level spell. The caster may immediately memorize additional spells or retain memory of a spell cast through the enhancer. Material Components: A piece of string, an ivory plaque worth at least 100 gp, and ink made from squid secretion plus either black dragon blood or giant slug digestive juice. All components vanish when cast.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user rary s mnemonic enhancer":{"name":"Rary’s Mnemonic Enhancer","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 day","aoe":"The magic-user","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Rary’s Mnemonic Enhancer\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 day\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The magic-user\nThis spell allows the magic-user to memorize or retain three additional spell levels: three 1st-level spells, one 1st-level and one 2nd-level spell, or one 3rd-level spell. The caster may immediately memorize additional spells or retain memory of a spell cast through the enhancer. Material Components: A piece of string, an ivory plaque worth at least 100 gp, and ink made from squid secretion plus either black dragon blood or giant slug digestive juice. All components vanish when cast.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Rary’s Mnemonic Enhancer","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user remove curse":{"name":"Remove Curse","level":"4","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Remove Curse\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Bestow Curse\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level cleric spell remove curse.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Remove Curse","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user wall of fire":{"name":"Wall Of Fire","level":"4","school":"Evocation","range":"6”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wall Of Fire\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell differs from the 5th-level druid spell wall of fire as follows: the flame color is violet or reddish blue, base damage is 2d6 plus 1 point per caster level, the radius of the ring-shaped wall is 1” plus ¼” per caster level, and the material component is phosphorus.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Wall Of Fire","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user wall of ice":{"name":"Wall Of Ice","level":"4","school":"Evocation","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wall Of Ice\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a sheet of strong, flexible ice. The wall is mainly defensive, stopping pursuers and similar threats. It is 1 inch thick per caster level and covers a 1” square area per caster level. For example, a 10th-level caster can make a wall 10” long and 1” high, 5” long and 2” high, and so on. A creature breaking through takes 2 damage per inch of wall thickness. Fire-using creatures take 3 damage per inch, and cold-using creatures take only 1 damage per inch. If cast horizontally to fall on opponents, the wall has the same effect as the hailstone version of ice storm over the area where it falls. Magical fires such as fireball and fiery dragon breath melt the wall in 1 round, creating a great cloud of steamy fog lasting 1 turn. Normal fires and lesser magical fires do not hasten melting. Material Component: A small piece of quartz or similar rock crystal.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Wall Of Ice","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user wizard eye":{"name":"Wizard Eye","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wizard Eye\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates an invisible sensory organ that sends visual information to the magic-user. The wizard eye travels at 3” per round while viewing ahead as a human would, or 1” per round while examining ceilings, walls, and floors. It can see with infravision to 10 feet, or see up to 60 feet in brightly lit areas. It can travel in any direction while the spell lasts. Material Component: A bit of bat fur.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Wizard Eye","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user airy water":{"name":"Airy Water","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"2” diameter sphere or 4” diameter hemisphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Airy Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2” diameter sphere or 4” diameter hemisphere\nThis spell turns normal liquid, such as water or water-based infusions or solutions, into a less dense, breathable substance. A magic-user entering an underwater place may step into the water, cast the spell, and sink downward in a globe of bubbling water. The caster and any companions within the area of effect may move freely and breathe as if the water were air. The globe moves with the caster. Water-breathing creatures avoid the sphere or hemisphere of airy water. Intelligent water-breathers can enter it if they can move by means other than swimming, but no water-breather can breathe inside the affected area. Material Component: A small handful of alkaline or bromine salts.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Airy Water","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user animal growth":{"name":"Animal Growth","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"6”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Up to 8 animals in a 2” square area","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Animal Growth\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Reduce Animal\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Up to 8 animals in a 2” square area\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 5th-level druid spell animal growth. Material Component: A pinch of powdered bone.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Animal Growth","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user animate dead":{"name":"Animate Dead","level":"5","school":"Necromantic","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Animate Dead\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 5 rounds\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level cleric spell animate dead.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Animate Dead","class":"Magic-User"},"bigby s interposing hand":{"name":"Bigby’s Interposing Hand","level":"5","school":"Evocation","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Bigby’s Interposing Hand\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a large to huge magical hand that appears between the caster and one chosen opponent. The disembodied hand remains between them regardless of what the caster does afterward or how the opponent tries to get around it. The caster determines the hand’s size, from human-sized to titan-sized. It has as many hit points as the magic-user who cast it. Any creature weighing less than 2,000 pounds that tries to push past the hand is slowed to half normal movement. Material Component: A glove.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user bigby s interposing hand":{"name":"Bigby’s Interposing Hand","level":"5","school":"Evocation","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Bigby’s Interposing Hand\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a large to huge magical hand that appears between the caster and one chosen opponent. The disembodied hand remains between them regardless of what the caster does afterward or how the opponent tries to get around it. The caster determines the hand’s size, from human-sized to titan-sized. It has as many hit points as the magic-user who cast it. Any creature weighing less than 2,000 pounds that tries to push past the hand is slowed to half normal movement. Material Component: A glove.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Bigby’s Interposing Hand","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user cloudkill":{"name":"Cloudkill","level":"5","school":"Evocation","range":"1”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"4” wide, 2” high, 2” deep cloud","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cloudkill\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4” wide, 2” high, 2” deep cloud\nThis spell creates a billowing cloud of ghastly yellow-green vapors. The cloud slays creatures with fewer than 4+1 Hit Dice. Creatures with 4+1 to 5+1 Hit Dice must save versus poison at -4 or die. Creatures up to and including 6 Hit Dice must save versus poison normally or die. The cloud moves away from the caster at 1” per round, rolling along the ground. Wind alters its course but never moves it back toward the caster. A strong wind breaks it up in 4 rounds, and stronger wind prevents the spell from being used. Very thick vegetation disperses the cloud in 2 rounds, or after it moves 2” through such growth. Since the vapors are heavier than air, they sink to the lowest available level and may pour into dens, sinkholes, or similar openings.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Cloudkill","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user conjure elemental":{"name":"Conjure Elemental","level":"5","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"6”","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Conjure Elemental\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the magic-user to conjure one air, earth, fire, or water elemental, provided the proper material component and element source are available. Fire elementals require a considerable fire source within range, and water elementals require a large amount of water. The elemental type must be chosen before the spell is memorized. Conjured elementals are typically very strong, usually 16 Hit Dice. The magic-user must concentrate to control the elemental and command its actions. If concentration is broken, the elemental turns on the caster and attacks, though it does not leave an existing combat to do so and avoids other creatures while seeking its conjurer. Wounding or grappling the magic-user breaks concentration. At the end of the second and each succeeding round, there is always a 5% chance the elemental turns on its conjurer regardless of concentration. The elemental may be controlled at a distance of up to 3” per caster level. It remains until destroyed or until the spell duration expires. Water elementals are destroyed if they move more than 6” from a body of water. Special protection from uncontrolled elementals may be gained through a pentacle, pentagram, thaumaturgic triangle, magic circle, or protection from evil. Material Components: In addition to the required element source, air elemental requires burning incense; earth elemental requires soft clay; fire elemental requires sulfur and phosphorus; water elemental requires water and sand.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Conjure Elemental","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user cone of cold":{"name":"Cone Of Cold","level":"5","school":"Evocation","range":"0","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Cone Of Cold\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a cone-shaped area of cold originating at the magic-user’s hand and extending outward ½” per caster level. It drains heat and deals 1d4+1 damage per caster level. For example, a 10th-level magic-user casts a cone of cold dealing 10d4+10 damage. Material Component: A very small crystal or glass cone.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Cone Of Cold","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user contact other plane":{"name":"Contact Other Plane","level":"5","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Contact Other Plane\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell sends the magic-user’s mind to another plane to seek advice and information from powers there. Such powers are found at random and resent the contact, so answers are brief, such as “yes,” “no,” “maybe,” “never,” or “irrelevant.” The caster may ask one question for every 2 experience levels. Contacting planes farther removed increases the chance of insanity or death, but also increases the chance that the contacted power knows the answer and tells the truth.\n\nPlane Contacted\tChance of Insanity\tChance of Knowledge\tChance of Truth\nElemental\t20%\t90%\t75%\n1 plane removed\t5%\t60%\t65%\n2 planes removed\t10%\t65%\t67%\n3 planes removed\t15%\t70%\t70%\n4 planes removed\t20%\t75%\t73%\n5 planes removed\t25%\t80%\t75%\n6 planes removed\t30%\t85%\t78%\n7 planes removed\t35%\t90%\t81%\n8 planes removed\t40%\t95%\t85%\n9 or more planes removed\t50%\t98%\t90%\n\nFor every point of Intelligence above 15, the caster reduces the chance of insanity by 5%. If the answer is unknown and truth is not indicated, the being answers definitely but falsely. If truth is indicated, the being answers “unknown.” Elemental contact assumes knowledge of questions concerning the appropriate Elemental Plane. Insanity begins as soon as one question is asked and lasts 1 week per plane removed, to a maximum of 10 weeks. There is a 1% chance per plane removed that the magic-user dies before recovering unless remove curse is cast on them.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Contact Other Plane","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user distance distortion":{"name":"Distance Distortion","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"100 square “ per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Distance Distortion\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 100 square “ per level\nThis spell can be cast only when the magic-user has conjured an earth elemental. The elemental does not react hostilely to cooperating if the caster announces the intent to cast distance distortion. The spell places the earth elemental in the area of effect, and the elemental distorts the area’s dimensions in one of two ways: the area effectively becomes half the distance to those traveling across it, or it becomes twice the distance. Thus, a 10-foot by 100-foot corridor could seem 5 feet wide and 50 feet long, or 20 feet wide and 200 feet long. When the duration ends, the elemental returns to its own plane. The true nature of the distortion is undetectable to creatures traveling through the area, though it radiates a dim dweomer, and true seeing reveals the earth elemental spread throughout the area. Material Component: A small lump of soft clay.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Distance Distortion","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user extension ii":{"name":"Extension II","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Extension II\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is the same as extension I, except it extends the duration of 1st- through 4th-level spells by 50%.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Extension II","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user feeblemind":{"name":"Feeblemind","level":"5","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Feeblemind\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 6th-level druid spell feeblemind. Material Component: A handful of small clay, crystal, glass, or mineral spheres.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Feeblemind","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user hold monster":{"name":"Hold Monster","level":"5","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"One to four creatures","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Hold Monster\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One to four creatures\nThis spell immobilizes 1 to 4 creatures of any type within range and line of sight. If three or four creatures are targeted, each saving throw is normal. If two are targeted, each saves at -1. If only one is targeted, the save is at -3. Partially negated hold monster effects are equivalent to slow. Material Component: One hard metal bar or rod for each monster to be held, which may be as small as a three-penny nail.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Hold Monster","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user leomund s secret chest":{"name":"Leomund’s Secret Chest","level":"5","school":"Alteration, Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Special","duration":"60 days","aoe":"One chest, about 2’ × 2’ × 3’","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Leomund’s Secret Chest\n\nSchool: Alteration, Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 60 days\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One chest, about 2’ × 2’ × 3’\nTo cast this spell, the magic-user must have an exceptionally well-crafted and expensive chest made by master craftsmen. If made primarily of wood, it must be ebony, rosewood, sandalwood, teak, or similar fine wood, with platinum fittings, nails, and hardware. If made of ivory, its fittings may be gold; if made of bronze, copper, or silver, its fittings may be electrum or silver. The chest costs at least 5,000 gp. A perfect miniature replica of the same materials must also be made. A magic-user may have only one such pair of chests at a time, with no exception even by wish. While touching the chest and holding the miniature, the caster chants the spell, causing the large chest to vanish into the Ethereal Plane. The chest can contain 1 cubic foot of material per caster level, regardless of its apparent size. Living matter creates a 75% chance the spell fails. As long as the caster possesses the miniature, they can recall the large chest. If the miniature is lost or destroyed, even wish cannot return the large chest. While on the Ethereal Plane, there is a cumulative 1% chance per week that some creature or being finds the chest. If found, there is a 10% chance it is ignored, 10% chance something is added, 30% chance contents are exchanged, 30% chance something is stolen, and 20% chance it is emptied. When the chest is recalled, an ethereal window opens for 5 hours, slowly diminishing. There is a 5% chance an ethereal monster is drawn through, reduced by 1% cumulatively each hour. No creature on the Prime Material Plane can locate the chest, even with gem of seeing, true seeing, or similar magic. If the chest is not retrieved before the spell expires, there is a cumulative 5% chance per day it is lost forever, starting at 5% on day 61, 10% on day 62, and so on.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Leomund’s Secret Chest","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user magic jar":{"name":"Magic Jar","level":"5","school":"Possession","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Magic Jar\n\nSchool: Possession\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis unusual spell allows the magic-user to transfer their life force into a special container, the magic jar, and from there attempt to take over a victim’s mind and control that creature’s body. If the body is human or humanoid, the caster may even use their own known spells. The possessor can access only rudimentary knowledge of the possessed body, not real knowledge such as languages or spells. The life force receptacle must be within spell range of the caster’s body when the spell is cast. From the jar, the caster’s life force can sense and attack any creature within range, though it cannot determine exactly what the creature is. Possession succeeds only if the victim fails its saving throw. A failed possession attempt leaves the caster’s life force in the jar. Each possession attempt requires 1 round. If the caster’s body is destroyed, the life force in the jar is unharmed. If the jar is destroyed, the life force is extinguished. Returning to the caster’s own body requires 1 round and can only be done if the jar is within spell range of the body. The saving throw is modified by comparing the combined Intelligence and Wisdom of caster and victim; for non-human or non-humanoid victims, compare Intelligence only.\n\nDifference\tSaving Throw Modifier\nVictim higher by 9 or more\t+4\nVictim higher by 6–8\t+3\nVictim higher by 3–5\t+2\nVictim higher by 0–2\t+1\nCaster higher by 1–4\t0\nCaster higher by 5–8\t-1\nCaster higher by 9–12\t-2\nCaster higher by 13 or more\t-3\n\nA negative difference means the caster’s score is lower and the victim gains a saving throw bonus. A possessed creature with any negative difference, or a positive difference below 5, receives a saving throw each round to regain control. A positive difference of 5–8 grants a saving throw each turn; 9–12 grants one each day; 13 or more grants one each week. If the possessed creature regains control, the caster is trapped until they can possess the victim again or escape. Material Component: The magic jar itself.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Magic Jar","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user monster summoning iii":{"name":"Monster Summoning III","level":"5","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"5”","duration":"4 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Monster Summoning III\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 5”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons 1d4 3rd-level monsters, which arrive in 1d4 rounds. See monster summoning I for other details.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Monster Summoning III","class":"Magic-User"},"mordenkainen s faithful hound":{"name":"Mordenkainen’s Faithful Hound","level":"5","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1”","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mordenkainen’s Faithful Hound\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons a phantom watchdog visible only to the caster. The caster may command it to guard a passage, room, door, or similar space or portal. The hound immediately barks loudly if any creature larger than a cat approaches its guarded area. It can detect invisible, astral, ethereal, out-of-phase, duo-dimensional, or similarly unseen creatures. If an intruder exposes its back to the phantom watchdog, the hound attacks as a 10-Hit-Die monster, dealing 3d6 damage and striking even opponents normally hit only by +3 or better magical weapons. The faithful hound cannot be attacked, but it can be dispelled. If the caster moves more than 3” from the guarded area, the spell is automatically dispelled. Material Components: A tiny silver whistle, a piece of bone, and a thread.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user mordenkainen s faithful hound":{"name":"Mordenkainen’s Faithful Hound","level":"5","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1”","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mordenkainen’s Faithful Hound\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons a phantom watchdog visible only to the caster. The caster may command it to guard a passage, room, door, or similar space or portal. The hound immediately barks loudly if any creature larger than a cat approaches its guarded area. It can detect invisible, astral, ethereal, out-of-phase, duo-dimensional, or similarly unseen creatures. If an intruder exposes its back to the phantom watchdog, the hound attacks as a 10-Hit-Die monster, dealing 3d6 damage and striking even opponents normally hit only by +3 or better magical weapons. The faithful hound cannot be attacked, but it can be dispelled. If the caster moves more than 3” from the guarded area, the spell is automatically dispelled. Material Components: A tiny silver whistle, a piece of bone, and a thread.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Mordenkainen’s Faithful Hound","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user passwall":{"name":"Passwall","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"3”","duration":"6 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Passwall\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 6 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell opens a passage through wooden, plaster, or stone walls. The opening is 5 feet wide, 8 feet high, and 10 feet deep. Multiple passwall spells can form a continuous passage through very thick walls. Material Component: A pinch of sesame seeds.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Passwall","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user stone shape":{"name":"Stone Shape","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1 cubic foot per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Stone Shape\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per level\nThis spell allows the magic-user to form an existing piece of stone into a desired shape. It can create a stone weapon, fashion a trapdoor, sculpt an idol, reshape a stone door to escape imprisonment, form stone coffers, or make secret doors, provided the volume affected is within the spell limit. Fine detail is limited. Material Component: Soft clay worked into roughly the desired shape and touched to the stone when the spell is uttered.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Stone Shape","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user telekinesis":{"name":"Telekinesis","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"2 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"250 gp weight per level","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Telekinesis\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 250 gp weight per level\nThis spell allows the magic-user to move objects by willpower while concentrating. Objects may move vertically or horizontally. Movement is 2” on the first round, 4” on the second, 8” on the third, 16” on the fourth, and so on, doubling each round until a maximum speed of 1,024” per round is reached. Heavy objects traveling at high speed can be deadly weapons. The spell can move opponents within its weight limit, though simple countermeasures such as enlarge may increase a target’s weight beyond the limit. Ambulation or another motive force can counter telekinesis if velocity has not yet reached 16” per round. Bigby’s hand spells and many other magics may also counter it.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Telekinesis","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user teleport":{"name":"Teleport","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Teleport\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell instantly transports the magic-user, along with weight touched or carried, to a known destination. Distance is irrelevant, but interplanar travel is not possible. The caster can teleport up to 2,500 gp weight, plus 1,500 gp weight per level above 10th. For example, a 13th-level magic-user can teleport up to 7,000 gp weight, or 700 pounds. The chance of arriving accurately depends on familiarity.\n\nDestination Familiarity\tHigh\tOn Target\tLow\nVery familiar\t01–02\t03–99\t00\nStudied carefully\t01–04\t05–98\t99–00\nSeen casually\t01–08\t09–96\t97–00\nViewed once\t01–16\t17–92\t93–00\nNever seen\t01–32\t33–84\t85–00\n\nA “high” result means the caster arrives 1” above the ground for every 1% below the lowest “On Target” probability, from 2” high for a very familiar destination to 32” high for a never-seen destination. A “low” result means instant death if the caster arrives inside solid matter. The spell cannot teleport the caster to empty space; there must be a substantial surface such as wood floor, stone floor, or natural ground.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Teleport","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user transmute rock to mud":{"name":"Transmute Rock To Mud","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"2 cubic “ per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Transmute Rock To Mud\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Transmute Mud To Rock\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2 cubic “ per level\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 5th-level druid spell transmute rock to mud. Material Components: Clay and water; or sand, lime, and water for the reverse.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Transmute Rock To Mud","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user wall of force":{"name":"Wall Of Force","level":"5","school":"Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"1 turn + 1 round per level","aoe":"20 square feet per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wall Of Force\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 turn + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 20 square feet per level\nThis spell creates an invisible, immobile barrier at the location desired, within range. It is unaffected by all spells except disintegrate, which destroys it immediately. It is also unaffected by dispel magic, blows, missiles, cold, heat, electricity, and similar effects. Spells and breath weapons cannot pass through it in either direction. The caster may shape it as a wall, hemisphere, or sphere, up to 20 square feet per caster level. Material Component: A pinch of powdered diamond.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Wall Of Force","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user wall of iron":{"name":"Wall Of Iron","level":"5","school":"Evocation","range":"½” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wall Of Iron\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes a vertical iron wall to spring into being. It is typically used to seal a passage or close a breach, inserting itself into surrounding material if its area is sufficient. The wall is ¼ inch thick per caster level. The caster may create 15 square feet of wall per level, so a 12th-level caster can create 180 square feet. If created without support, the wall falls and crushes creatures beneath it. The wall is permanent unless removed by dispel magic, but is otherwise subject to normal forces affecting iron, such as rust and perforation. Material Component: A small piece of sheet iron.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Wall Of Iron","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user wall of stone":{"name":"Wall Of Stone","level":"5","school":"Evocation","range":"½” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wall Of Stone\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a granite wall that merges into adjoining stone surfaces if enough area is available. It is typically used to close passages, portals, or breaches. The wall is ¼ foot thick and 20 square feet in area per caster level. Thus, a 12th-level magic-user creates a wall 3 feet thick and 240 square feet in surface area, such as a 12-foot-wide by 20-foot-high wall. The wall need not be vertical or rest on a firm foundation, but it must merge with existing stone. It can be used as a bridge or ramp. It is permanent unless destroyed by dispel magic, disintegrate, or normal breaking and chipping. Material Component: A small block of granite.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 6th Level","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Wall Of Stone","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user anti magic shell":{"name":"Anti-Magic Shell","level":"6","school":"Abjuration","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"1 foot per level diameter sphere","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Anti-Magic Shell\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 foot per level diameter sphere\nThis spell surrounds the magic-user with an invisible barrier that moves with the caster. The barrier is impervious to all magic and magical spell effects, including breath weapons, gaze weapons, and voice weapons. It prevents spells and magical effects from entering, and prevents magical items or spells inside it from functioning. Charmed, summoned, and conjured creatures cannot enter. Normal creatures can pass through the shell, and normal missiles are unaffected. A magic sword loses its magical function inside the shell, but remains a sword.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Anti-Magic Shell","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user bigby s forceful hand":{"name":"Bigby’s Forceful Hand","level":"6","school":"Evocation","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Bigby’s Forceful Hand\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is a stronger version of Bigby’s interposing hand. In addition to interposing itself, it pushes creatures away from the caster. It can push away creatures weighing 500 pounds or less, slow creatures weighing 500 to 2,000 pounds to 1” movement per round, and reduce movement by 50% for creatures weighing up to 8,000 pounds. It takes as much damage to destroy as its creator has hit points. Material Component: A glove.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Bigby’s Forceful Hand","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user control weather":{"name":"Control Weather","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"4–24 hours","aoe":"4–16 square miles","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Control Weather\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 4–24 hours\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4–16 square miles\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 7th-level cleric spell control weather. Material Components: Burning incense, plus bits of earth and wood mixed in water.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Control Weather","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user death spell":{"name":"Death Spell","level":"6","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1” per level","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"½” square per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Death Spell\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: ½” square per level\nThis spell instantly and irrevocably slays creatures in the area of effect. The number slain depends on their Hit Dice.\n\nVictim Hit Dice\tMaximum Number Affected\nLess than 2\t4d20\n2 to 4\t3d10\n4+1 to 6+3\t2d4\n6+4 to 8+3\t1d4\n\nFor mixed groups, roll the dice for creatures under 2 Hit Dice, kill those first, then use the conversion table to determine higher-Hit-Die deaths. This process may also be reversed, applying the effect to higher-Hit-Die creatures first.\n\nCreature Hit Dice\tEquals Less Than 2 HD\tEquals 2–4 HD\tEquals 4+1 to 6+3 HD\tEquals 6+4 to 8+3 HD\n6+4 to 8+3\t10\t5\t2\t—\n4+1 to 6+3\t8\t3\t—\t0.5\n2 to 4\t4\t—\t0.125\t0.05\n\nFor example, if 4d20 produces 53, then 20 points can kill one 6+4 to 8+3 Hit Dice creature, 16 points can kill two 4+1 to 6+3 Hit Dice creatures, 12 points can kill three 2 to 4 Hit Dice creatures, and 5 remaining points can kill five creatures under 2 Hit Dice. The spell does not affect lycanthropes, undead, or creatures from planes other than the Prime Material Plane. Material Component: A crushed black pearl worth at least 1,000 gp.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Death Spell","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user disintegrate":{"name":"Disintegrate","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"½” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Disintegrate\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes matter to vanish. It can affect magical matter or energy, such as Bigby’s forceful hand, but not globe of invulnerability or anti-magic shell. Disintegration is instantaneous and permanent. It can affect any living thing, including undead, or obliterate up to 1 cubic inch of nonliving matter. Only one creature or object may be targeted. Creatures and magical material with a saving throw are unaffected if the save succeeds. Material Components: A lodestone and a pinch of dust.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Disintegrate","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user enchant an item":{"name":"Enchant An Item","level":"6","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"One item","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Enchant An Item\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One item\nThis spell prepares an object to receive magic. The item must be sound and undamaged, made of the finest possible materials and workmanship, and usually have raw material cost above 100 gp. Items such as rope, leather, cloth, or pottery must be embroidered, jeweled, tooled, carved, or engraved if such work can be added without weakening their function. The caster must continuously touch the item while casting. Casting requires a base 16 hours plus 8–64 additional hours. Since a magic-user may work no more than 8 hours per day, this means 2 days plus 1–8 days. The work must be uninterrupted. During rest periods, the item must remain within 1 foot of the caster, and the caster may perform no other magic and must remain quiet and isolated. At the end, the caster knows the item is ready for final testing. The caster speaks the final syllable, and the item makes a saving throw versus magic as if it were the caster. The caster’s saving throw bonuses apply up to +3. A natural roll of 1 always fails. If the spell succeeds, the caster may begin placing the desired dweomer on the item. The next spell must be cast within 24 hours, or the preparation fades. Each later spell cast onto the item requires 4 hours plus 4–8 additional hours per spell level, with the same touching and proximity requirements. Each successive dweomer must begin within 24 hours of the previous one, even if a prior spell failed. No magic placed into an item is permanent unless permanency is used. Charged items, such as rods, staves, wands, javelins of lightning, and rings of wishes, can never be made permanent. Scrolls and magic devices cannot be used to enchant an item or place magic on a prepared object. Material Components: These vary by item and intended enchantments, as determined by the Dungeon Master.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Enchant An Item","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user extension iii":{"name":"Extension III","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Extension III\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is like extension I, except it doubles the duration of 1st- through 3rd-level spells and extends 4th- or 5th-level spells by 50%.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Extension III","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user geas":{"name":"Geas","level":"6","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Geas\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell places a magical command on an intelligent, conscious creature acting under its own will. The command may require a service or forbid an action. A geas cannot compel suicide or acts certain to cause death, but it can require almost any other course of action. The creature follows the instructions until the geas is completed. Failure causes the creature to grow sick and die within 1d4 weeks. Deviation or twisting of the instructions causes corresponding Strength loss until the deviation stops. A wish can remove a geas, but dispel magic and remove curse cannot. An improperly cast geas is immediately null and void.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Geas","class":"Magic-User"},"glassee":{"name":"Glassee","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Glassee\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the magic-user to make metal, stone, or wood transparent to their gaze, or to create a transparent one-way window in the material. Normally, the caster can see through up to 4 inches of metal, 6 feet of stone, or 20 feet of wood. The spell does not work on lead, gold, or platinum. The caster may either make the effect apply only to themselves, using it up to once per round during the duration, or create an actual transparent area. In either case, the viewing area is 3 feet wide by 2 feet high. Material Component: A small piece of crystal or glass.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user glassee":{"name":"Glassee","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Glassee\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the magic-user to make metal, stone, or wood transparent to their gaze, or to create a transparent one-way window in the material. Normally, the caster can see through up to 4 inches of metal, 6 feet of stone, or 20 feet of wood. The spell does not work on lead, gold, or platinum. The caster may either make the effect apply only to themselves, using it up to once per round during the duration, or create an actual transparent area. In either case, the viewing area is 3 feet wide by 2 feet high. Material Component: A small piece of crystal or glass.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Glassee","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user globe of invulnerability":{"name":"Globe Of Invulnerability","level":"6","school":"Abjuration","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"1” diameter sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Globe Of Invulnerability\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” diameter sphere\nThis spell is the same as minor globe of invulnerability, except that it prevents 1st- through 4th-level spells from functioning against the magic-user within the globe. The caster may still cast spells outward through the globe.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Globe Of Invulnerability","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user guards and wards":{"name":"Guards And Wards","level":"6","school":"Evocation, Alteration, Enchantment/Charm","range":"0","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"1” radius per level, extending from a 2” diameter sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 turns","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Guards And Wards\n\nSchool: Evocation, Alteration, Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 turns\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” radius per level, extending from a 2” diameter sphere\nThis powerful spell is usually used to defend a magic-user’s stronghold. When cast, the following effects occur in the area: all corridors become misty, reducing visibility to 10 feet; all doors are wizard locked; one door per caster level is covered by an illusion making it appear to be a plain wall; stairs are filled with webs from top to bottom; wherever there are choices in direction, such as a side passage or crossing, a minor confusion effect creates a 50% chance intruders believe they are going in the exact opposite direction; and the whole area radiates magic. The caster may also place one additional effect: dancing lights in four corridors, magic mouth in two places, stinking cloud in two places, gust of wind in one corridor or room, or suggestion in one place. Door illusions and the additional effect function only if the caster is completely familiar with the area. Each dispel magic removes one random effect. Remove curse does not work. Material Components: Burning incense, a small measure of sulfur and oil, a knotted string, a small amount of umber hulk blood, and a small silver rod.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Guards And Wards","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user invisible stalker":{"name":"Invisible Stalker","level":"6","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Invisible Stalker\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons an invisible stalker from the Elemental Plane of Air. The 8-Hit-Die creature obeys and serves the caster in performing assigned tasks, but it serves because it is bound, not from loyalty. It resents prolonged missions and complex tasks and attempts to pervert instructions accordingly. It follows instructions even over hundreds or thousands of miles. Material Components: Burning incense and a piece of horn carved into a crescent shape.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Invisible Stalker","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user legend lore":{"name":"Legend Lore","level":"6","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Legend Lore\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell reveals information about a known person, place, or thing, provided the subject is noteworthy or legendary. If the person or thing is present, or the caster is in the place in question, casting takes only 1d4 turns and is more likely to produce results. If detailed information is known, casting takes 1d10 days. If only rumors are known, casting takes 2d6 weeks. During casting, the magic-user may do only routine activities such as eating and sleeping. When complete, the spell reveals whether legendary material exists. It often reveals where that material can be found, by place name, rhyme, or riddle. Sometimes, especially when the subject is present, it gives information in cryptic form, such as rhyme, riddle, anagram, cipher, or sign. Material Components: Incense and ivory strips formed into a rectangle, plus a sacrifice such as a potion, magic scroll, magic item, creature, or similar offering.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Legend Lore","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user lower water":{"name":"Lower Water","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"8”","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"½” × ½” square per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Lower Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Raise Water\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: ½” × ½” square per level\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 4th-level cleric spell lower water. The reverse raises water only ½ foot per caster level. Material Components: A small vial of water and a small vial of dust.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Lower Water","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user monster summoning iv":{"name":"Monster Summoning IV","level":"6","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"6”","duration":"5 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Monster Summoning IV\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 5 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons 1d3 4th-level monsters, which appear within 1d3 rounds. See monster summoning I for other details.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Monster Summoning IV","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user move earth":{"name":"Move Earth","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Move Earth\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell moves dirt, clay, loam, sand, and similar earth. It can collapse embankments, shift hillocks, move dunes, and similar effects. Casting time depends on the area: each 4” square area requires 1 turn of casting. If terrain features are to be moved, rather than simply collapsing banks or walls of earth, an earth elemental must also be summoned to assist. All spellcasting and summoning must be completed before any effects occur. Rock formations cannot be collapsed or moved. Material Components: A mixture of soils, such as clay, loam, and sand, in a small bag, plus an iron blade.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Move Earth","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user otiluke s freezing sphere":{"name":"Otiluke’s Freezing Sphere","level":"6","school":"Alteration-Evocation","range":"Special","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Otiluke’s Freezing Sphere\n\nSchool: Alteration-Evocation\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell has three possible forms. First, it can create a globe of absolute-zero matter that spreads on contact with water or mainly water-based liquid, freezing it 6 inches deep over an area of 100 square feet per caster level. This ice lasts 1 round per caster level. Second, it can create a thin ray of cold from the caster’s hand with range 1” per caster level. The ray deals 4 damage per caster level to the creature struck. A successful saving throw versus magic negates all damage, meaning the ray missed, though the ray’s path is still traced to full distance and anything else in that path must save or suffer appropriate damage. Third, it can create a small globe about the size of a sling stone, cool but harmless to the touch. The globe may be thrown or slung and shatters on impact, dealing 4d6 cold damage to all creatures within 10 feet, or half damage on a successful saving throw. If not thrown or slung within 1 round per caster level, it shatters automatically and deals damage as above. Material Components: For the first form, a thin crystal sheet about 1 inch square; for the second, a white sapphire worth at least 1,000 gp; for the third, a diamond worth at least 1,000 gp. All components are lost when cast.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Otiluke’s Freezing Sphere","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user part water":{"name":"Part Water","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"5 rounds per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Part Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 5 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 6th-level cleric spell part water. Material Components: Two small sheets of crystal or glass.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Part Water","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user project image":{"name":"Project Image","level":"6","school":"Alteration, Illusion/Phantasm","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Project Image\n\nSchool: Alteration, Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a nonmaterial duplicate of the magic-user projected to any desired spot within range. The image performs actions identical to the caster as directed, including walking, speaking, and spellcasting. A special channel connects the image and caster, so spells cast by the caster originate from the image. The image can be dispelled only by dispel magic or by the caster’s command; attacks do not affect it. The image must remain within the caster’s sight. If the caster’s sight is obstructed, the spell ends. Material Component: A small replica or doll of the magic-user.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Project Image","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user reincarnation":{"name":"Reincarnation","level":"6","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Person touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Reincarnation\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Person touched\nThis spell is similar to the 7th-level druid spell reincarnate. It requires no system shock or resurrection survival saving throw. The corpse is touched, and a new incarnation appears nearby in 1d6 turns, provided the person has not been dead longer than 1 day per caster level.\n\nDie Roll\tIncarnation\n01–05\tBugbear\n06–11\tDwarf\n12–18\tElf\n19–23\tGnoll\n24–28\tGnome\n29–33\tGoblin\n34–40\tHalf-Elf\n41–47\tHalfling\n48–54\tHalf-Orc\n55–59\tHobgoblin\n60–73\tHuman\n74–79\tKobold\n80–85\tOrc\n86–90\tOgre\n91–95\tOgre Mage\n96–00\tTroll\n\nVery good or very evil persons will not be reincarnated as creatures whose general alignment is opposite. Material Components: A small drum and a drop of blood.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Reincarnation","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user repulsion":{"name":"Repulsion","level":"6","school":"Abjuration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round per 2 levels","aoe":"1” path","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Repulsion\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 round per 2 levels\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” path\nThis spell causes all creatures in the area of effect path to move away from the magic-user. Repulsion occurs at 3” per round, or at the motive speed of the creature trying to move toward the caster. A repelled creature continues moving away for the remainder of a full move, even if this carries it beyond spell range. Material Component: A pair of small magnetized iron bars attached to two small canine statuettes, one ivory and one ebony.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Repulsion","class":"Magic-User"},"spiritwrack":{"name":"Spiritwrack","level":"6","school":"Evocation/Abjuration","range":"1” + 1 foot per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, M","ct":"Special","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Spiritwrack\n\nSchool: Evocation/Abjuration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 1” + 1 foot per level\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is a powerful protection and punishment against powerful creatures of the nether planes, such as the Abyss, Hades, or Hell. The caster must know the true name of the being targeted. Before casting, the magic-user must personally prepare an illuminated vellum document inscribed with the being’s name in special inks made from powdered rubies and the ichor of a slain type I, II, or III demon, bordered continuously with gold leaf. Preparing the document requires 8–32 hours and costs 1,000 gp for vellum, pens, gold leaf, and related materials, plus at least 5,000 gp in powdered rubies. If the named demon, devil, or other nether-planar being is present in some form and is not merely possessing another body, the caster may begin reading the document. When the reading begins, the named being is rooted in place unless it makes its magic resistance roll, adjusted for caster level, as a saving throw. Even if it succeeds, it feels great discomfort and, if not magically forced to remain, is 90% likely to retreat to its own or another plane. While the caster reads, the being is powerless to attack the caster. The first round of reading increases the being’s discomfort. During the second round, the being suffers acute pain and loses 1 hit point per Hit Die it possesses. During the third and final round, the being loses 50% of its current hit points, suffers horrible pain, and is consigned to a confined space on its own plane for a number of years equal to the caster’s level. A being affected this way becomes the caster’s sworn enemy forever. Because of this, casters often use the spell as a threat rather than finish it. Each round of reading gives the being a cumulative 25% chance to concede even without additional offerings or payment.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user spiritwrack":{"name":"Spiritwrack","level":"6","school":"Evocation/Abjuration","range":"1” + 1 foot per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, M","ct":"Special","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Spiritwrack\n\nSchool: Evocation/Abjuration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 1” + 1 foot per level\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is a powerful protection and punishment against powerful creatures of the nether planes, such as the Abyss, Hades, or Hell. The caster must know the true name of the being targeted. Before casting, the magic-user must personally prepare an illuminated vellum document inscribed with the being’s name in special inks made from powdered rubies and the ichor of a slain type I, II, or III demon, bordered continuously with gold leaf. Preparing the document requires 8–32 hours and costs 1,000 gp for vellum, pens, gold leaf, and related materials, plus at least 5,000 gp in powdered rubies. If the named demon, devil, or other nether-planar being is present in some form and is not merely possessing another body, the caster may begin reading the document. When the reading begins, the named being is rooted in place unless it makes its magic resistance roll, adjusted for caster level, as a saving throw. Even if it succeeds, it feels great discomfort and, if not magically forced to remain, is 90% likely to retreat to its own or another plane. While the caster reads, the being is powerless to attack the caster. The first round of reading increases the being’s discomfort. During the second round, the being suffers acute pain and loses 1 hit point per Hit Die it possesses. During the third and final round, the being loses 50% of its current hit points, suffers horrible pain, and is consigned to a confined space on its own plane for a number of years equal to the caster’s level. A being affected this way becomes the caster’s sworn enemy forever. Because of this, casters often use the spell as a threat rather than finish it. Each round of reading gives the being a cumulative 25% chance to concede even without additional offerings or payment.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Spiritwrack","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user stone to flesh":{"name":"Stone To Flesh","level":"6","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Stone To Flesh\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Flesh To Stone\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell turns stone into flesh. If the stone object was formerly living, the spell restores life and possessions, though the creature must survive the usual system shock roll. Any formerly living creature, regardless of size, can be returned to flesh. Ordinary stone can also be turned into flesh, affecting up to 9 cubic feet per caster level. The reverse, flesh to stone, turns flesh and all possessions on the creature to stone. The victim receives a saving throw. Material Components: For stone to flesh, a pinch of earth and a drop of blood. For flesh to stone, lime, water, and earth.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Stone To Flesh","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user tenser s transformation":{"name":"Tenser’s Transformation","level":"6","school":"Alteration-Evocation","range":"0","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Personal","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Tenser’s Transformation\n\nSchool: Alteration-Evocation\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Personal\nThis spell transforms the magic-user into a berserk fighter of heroic size and strength. The caster’s hit points double, and damage is taken first from these magical hit points. If damage does not exceed the caster’s original hit points, no actual damage is suffered; damage beyond the added amount counts double. The caster’s Armor Class improves by 4, such as AC 10 becoming AC 6, AC 9 becoming AC 5, and so on. The caster attacks as a fighter of the same level, using the fighter combat table. The caster may attack only with a dagger, but gains +2 damage and makes 2 attacks per round. Once cast, the spell must run its full course. The magic-user keeps attacking until all opponents are slain, the caster is killed, the magic is dispelled, or the duration expires. Material Component: A potion of heroism or superheroism, which the caster must drink during the spell.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Tenser’s Transformation","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user bigby s grasping hand":{"name":"Bigby’s Grasping Hand","level":"7","school":"Evocation","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Bigby’s Grasping Hand\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is a superior version of Bigby’s forceful hand. It can hold motionless a creature or object weighing up to 1,000 pounds, or move creatures with double the strength of Bigby’s forceful hand. Material Component: A leather glove.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Bigby’s Grasping Hand","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user cacodemon":{"name":"Cacodemon","level":"7","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Creature summoned","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Cacodemon\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Creature summoned\nThis dangerous spell summons a powerful type IV, V, or VI demon, depending on the name known to the magic-user. The spell cannot summon greater demons, and lesser demons are not called because they have no known names. The caster must know the exact name of the demon being summoned. The summoned demon is angry and evil-disposed. The caster must be within a circle of protection, or a thaumaturgic triangle with protection from evil, and the demon must be confined within a pentagram, or the caster risks being slain or carried off. The caster may deal with the demon in several ways. First, the caster may force service by threatening it with spiritwrack, releasing it only when the service is fulfilled and requiring the demon to pledge its word; this is extremely dangerous, since even a minor bargaining error may let the demon twist the result or kill the summoner, and the demon becomes a lasting enemy. Second, the caster may bargain with fresh human blood and promised sacrifices, though the demon may reject the offer or exploit the exact wording of the agreement. Third, the demon may be trapped with trap the soul. A trapped demon remains imprisoned until its prison is broken, at which point it owes one service to the liberator if the liberator demands one immediately. If no service is demanded when the demon asks what is required, it is free to slay the liberator. Any required service must be limited in duration unless the demon willingly agrees to more. An impossible or excessive task has a 50% chance to free the demon from obligation and allow vengeance. A freed demon can remain on the summoning plane for up to 666 days. The summoned demon is exceptionally strong, having 8 hit points per Hit Die. Casting time is 1 hour per demon type number, such as 4 hours for type IV. Any interruption during casting causes failure. Interruption while the demon is summoned creates a 10% chance, cumulative each round, that it escapes its boundaries and attacks. The demon receives a saving throw against summoning. If a roll higher than the caster’s level is made on 3d6, or on 2d10 for type VI demons, the spell fails to summon that demon, meaning the name was incorrect or the demon is imprisoned or destroyed. Material Components: Five flaming black candles; a brazier of hot coals burning sulfur, bat hair, lard, soot, mercuric-nitric acid crystals, mandrake root, alcohol, and a parchment bearing the demon’s name in runes inside a pentacle; plus a dish of mammal blood, preferably human, placed where the demon is to be confined.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Cacodemon","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user charm plants":{"name":"Charm Plants","level":"7","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"3”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Charm Plants\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell brings vegetable life forms under the caster’s command and allows communication with them. The plants obey instructions to the best of their ability. The spell charms plants in a 3” × 1” area. It does not give plants new powers, but it allows them to use whatever abilities they already possess to carry out the caster’s instructions. Intelligent plants receive a saving throw at -4. Material Components: A pinch of humus, a drop of water, and a twig or leaf.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Charm Plants","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user delayed blast fireball":{"name":"Delayed Blast Fireball","level":"7","school":"Evocation","range":"10” + 1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"2” radius globe","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Delayed Blast Fireball\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 10” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: 2” radius globe\nThis spell creates a fireball that deals +1 damage on each die and delays detonation for 1 to 50 segments, or 1/10 round to 5 rounds, according to the caster’s command. Otherwise, it functions as the 3rd-level fireball spell.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Delayed Blast Fireball","class":"Magic-User"},"drawmij s instant summons":{"name":"Drawmij’s Instant Summons","level":"7","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Infinite plus special","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One small object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Drawmij’s Instant Summons\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Infinite plus special\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One small object\nThis spell teleports a specific desired item from virtually any location directly to the caster’s hand. The object must be singular, nonliving, no larger than a sword, and no heavier than a shield, about 75 gp weight. To prepare the spell, the magic-user holds a gem worth at least 5,000 gp and speaks all but the final word of the conjuration. The same gem must be available when casting the spell. The caster then utters the final word while crushing the gem, and the named item appears in the desired hand. The item must have been touched during the original incantation and specifically named. If another creature possesses the item, the spell fails, but the caster learns who possesses it and roughly where they are. Items can be summoned from other planes only if not possessed by another creature. For each level above 14th, the caster can summon from one plane farther removed: one plane at 14th level, two at 15th, three at 16th, and so on.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user drawmij s instant summons":{"name":"Drawmij’s Instant Summons","level":"7","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Infinite plus special","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One small object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Drawmij’s Instant Summons\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Infinite plus special\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One small object\nThis spell teleports a specific desired item from virtually any location directly to the caster’s hand. The object must be singular, nonliving, no larger than a sword, and no heavier than a shield, about 75 gp weight. To prepare the spell, the magic-user holds a gem worth at least 5,000 gp and speaks all but the final word of the conjuration. The same gem must be available when casting the spell. The caster then utters the final word while crushing the gem, and the named item appears in the desired hand. The item must have been touched during the original incantation and specifically named. If another creature possesses the item, the spell fails, but the caster learns who possesses it and roughly where they are. Items can be summoned from other planes only if not possessed by another creature. For each level above 14th, the caster can summon from one plane farther removed: one plane at 14th level, two at 15th, three at 16th, and so on.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Drawmij’s Instant Summons","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user duo dimension":{"name":"Duo-Dimension","level":"7","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"3 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Personal","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Duo-Dimension\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 3 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Personal\nThis spell gives the caster only two dimensions, height and width but no depth. When the caster turns sideways, they become invisible except to true seeing or similar magic. The caster can pass through the thinnest spaces, provided the space has enough height for their actual length, such as slipping between a door and its frame. The caster can act normally, turning invisible, moving while invisible, appearing the next round to cast a spell, and disappearing again afterward. While turned sideways, the caster cannot be affected by attacks. While visible, the caster takes triple normal damage from attacks. A portion of the caster’s existence is on the Astral Plane while the spell lasts, so astral creatures may notice the caster. If noticed, there is a 25% chance an astral creature’s attack pulls the caster entirely onto the Astral Plane. Material Components: A thin, flat ivory likeness of the caster, finely made, gold-filigreed, enameled, and gem-studded, costing 5,000–10,000 gp, and a strip of parchment. During casting, the parchment is twisted into a loop, the figurine is passed through it, and both vanish.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Duo-Dimension","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user limited wish":{"name":"Limited Wish","level":"7","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Unlimited","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"Special","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Limited Wish\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: Unlimited\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell partially or temporarily fulfills the caster’s spoken wish. It can alter past, present, or future reality in a limited way, though possibly only for the caster unless carefully worded. It cannot substantially change major realities, nor can it simply grant wealth or experience. It may restore some hit points, or all hit points for a limited duration, reduce enemy hit probabilities or damage, extend a magical effect, cause a creature to be favorably disposed toward the caster, or provide a minor clue to treasure or a magic item. Greedy wishes usually end in disaster. Casting time equals the actual number of seconds needed to phrase the wish, at 6 seconds per segment.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Limited Wish","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user mass invisibility":{"name":"Mass Invisibility","level":"7","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mass Invisibility\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is the same as invisibility, except it can hide creatures in a 3” × 3” area, up to 300–400 man-sized creatures, 30–40 giants, or 6–8 large dragons.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Mass Invisibility","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user monster summoning v":{"name":"Monster Summoning V","level":"7","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"7”","duration":"6 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Monster Summoning V\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 7”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 6 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons 1d2 5th-level monsters, which appear in 1d3 rounds. See monster summoning I for other details.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Monster Summoning V","class":"Magic-User"},"mordenkainen s sword":{"name":"Mordenkainen’s Sword","level":"7","school":"Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mordenkainen’s Sword\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a shimmering sword-like plane of force. The caster mentally wields it, excluding all activities except movement, causing it to move and strike as if used by a fighter. Its chance to hit is equal to that of a fighter half the caster’s level. For example, a 14th-level magic-user creates a sword that attacks as a 7th-level fighter. The sword has no magical bonus “to hit,” but can strike any opponent, including those normally hit only by +3 weapons or those astral, ethereal, or out of phase. It hits any Armor Class on a roll of 19 or 20. It deals 5d4 damage to man-sized or smaller opponents and 5d6 damage to larger opponents. It can be used to subdue. The sword lasts until the spell ends, until dispelled, or until the caster no longer desires it. Material Component: A miniature platinum sword with copper and zinc grip and pommel, costing 500 gp, which disappears when the spell is completed.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user mordenkainen s sword":{"name":"Mordenkainen’s Sword","level":"7","school":"Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mordenkainen’s Sword\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a shimmering sword-like plane of force. The caster mentally wields it, excluding all activities except movement, causing it to move and strike as if used by a fighter. Its chance to hit is equal to that of a fighter half the caster’s level. For example, a 14th-level magic-user creates a sword that attacks as a 7th-level fighter. The sword has no magical bonus “to hit,” but can strike any opponent, including those normally hit only by +3 weapons or those astral, ethereal, or out of phase. It hits any Armor Class on a roll of 19 or 20. It deals 5d4 damage to man-sized or smaller opponents and 5d6 damage to larger opponents. It can be used to subdue. The sword lasts until the spell ends, until dispelled, or until the caster no longer desires it. Material Component: A miniature platinum sword with copper and zinc grip and pommel, costing 500 gp, which disappears when the spell is completed.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Mordenkainen’s Sword","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user phase door":{"name":"Phase Door","level":"7","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"One use per 2 levels","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Phase Door\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: One use per 2 levels\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell attunes the caster’s body and affects a section of wall as if by passwall. The phase door is invisible to all creatures except the caster, and only the caster can use the created passage, disappearing when entering and reappearing when exiting. The door lasts for one use per 2 caster levels. It can be dispelled only by a higher-level magic-user’s dispel magic, or by several lower-level magic-users casting together whose combined levels are more than double the original caster’s level.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Phase Door","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user power word stun":{"name":"Power Word, Stun","level":"7","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"½” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Power Word, Stun\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nWhen this spell is uttered, one chosen creature within range is stunned, reeling and unable to think coherently or act. The caster must face the creature. Duration depends on the creature’s current hit points. A creature with 1–30 hit points is stunned for 4d4 rounds. A creature with 31–60 hit points is stunned for 2d4 rounds. A creature with 61–90 hit points is stunned for 1d4 rounds. Creatures with more than 90 hit points are unaffected. Current hit points, not normal maximum hit points, determine the effect.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Power Word, Stun","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user reverse gravity":{"name":"Reverse Gravity","level":"7","school":"Alteration","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 segment","aoe":"3” × 3” square area","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Reverse Gravity\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 segment\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” × 3” square area\nThis spell reverses gravity in the area of effect, causing all unfixed objects and creatures within it to fall upward. Reverse gravity lasts 1 second, or 1/6 segment, during which affected objects and creatures fall 16 feet upward. If they strike a solid object, impact is handled as a normal downward fall. When the spell ends, affected objects and creatures fall downward. Since the spell affects an area, objects or creatures high in the air can also be affected. Material Components: A lodestone and iron filings.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Reverse Gravity","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user simulacrum":{"name":"Simulacrum","level":"7","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Simulacrum\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell creates a duplicate of any creature. The duplicate appears exactly like the original, but has only 51%–60% of the original’s hit points, has personality differences, lacks some areas of knowledge, and is instantly revealed as a simulacrum by detect magic or true seeing. The simulacrum is under the absolute command of its creator, though there is no telepathic link, so commands must be given normally. The spell creates only the creature’s form, which is initially zombie-like. A reincarnation spell must provide vital force, and a limited wish must give the duplicate 40%–65% of the original’s knowledge and personality. If the original had levels, the simulacrum has 20%–50% of those levels. The duplicate is formed from ice or snow, and a piece of the creature to be copied must be placed inside the form. The spell also requires powdered ruby. The simulacrum cannot grow more powerful or increase its levels or abilities.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Simulacrum","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user statue":{"name":"Statue","level":"7","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Statue\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell makes the caster or touched creature appear to turn to solid stone, along with worn or carried gear. The initial transformation requires 1 full round after casting. Thereafter, the creature can withstand inspection and appears to be a stone statue, though faint magic is detectable. While in statue form, the subject can see, hear, and smell normally. Feeling is limited to sensations that affect the granite-hard body; chipping is like a slight wound, while breaking off an arm is far more serious. The subject can return to normal in 1/6 segment, and can return to statue form just as quickly while the spell lasts. During the initial transformation, the subject must make a system shock roll of 82% or less, modified by subtracting 1 from the die roll for each point of Constitution; Constitution 18 means automatic success. Failure means death from system shock. Material Components: Lime, sand, and a drop of water stirred with an iron bar, nail, or spike.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Statue","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user vanish":{"name":"Vanish","level":"7","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Vanish\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes an object to vanish. The caster may teleport the object if it weighs up to 500 gp per caster level; for example, a 14th-level magic-user can vanish and reappear an object weighing up to 7,000 gp. Larger objects can be made to vanish, but they are placed on the Ethereal Plane and replaced by stone. Thus, a vanished door is replaced by a stone wall 1 foot thick, or as thick as the door, whichever is greater. The maximum affected volume is 3 cubic feet per caster level, so both weight and volume limit the spell. A successful dispel magic returns vanished objects from the Ethereal Plane.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 8th Level","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Vanish","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user antipathy sympathy":{"name":"Antipathy/Sympathy","level":"8","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"3”","duration":"12 turns per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 turns","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Antipathy/Sympathy\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 6 turns\nDuration: 12 turns per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell sets vibrations that repel or attract a specific kind of living, intelligent creature or characters of a specific alignment. The caster must choose the effect and target creature or alignment type before casting. The spell cannot be cast on living creatures. Antipathy causes the specified creature or alignment type to feel an overwhelming urge to leave the area or avoid touching the object. If the saving throw succeeds, the creature may remain or touch the item but feels very uncomfortable, suffering a persistent itching that causes the loss of 1 Dexterity per round, to a maximum loss of 4 Dexterity. If the saving throw fails, the creature or alignment type abandons the area or item, shuns it permanently, and never willingly enters or touches it until the spell is removed or expires. Sympathy causes the specified creature or alignment type to feel elated and pleased to be in the area or to touch or possess the object. The desire is overpowering unless a saving throw versus magic succeeds. If the save succeeds, the creature is released from the enchantment, but must save again 1d6 turns later or return to the area or object. The specific creature type or alignment must be named, such as red dragons, hill giants, wererats, vampires, chaotic evil, lawful neutral, or neutral. If cast on an area, the spell affects a 10-foot cube per caster level. If cast on an object, only that object is enchanted, and affected creatures save at -2. Material Components: For antipathy, a lump of alum soaked in vinegar. For sympathy, 1,000 gp worth of crushed pearls and a drop of honey.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Antipathy/Sympathy","class":"Magic-User"},"bigby s clenched fist":{"name":"Bigby’s Clenched Fist","level":"8","school":"Evocation","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Bigby’s Clenched Fist\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a huge disembodied fist under the caster’s mental control. The caster may cause it to strike one opponent each round. No other spellcasting or magical activity may be undertaken while controlling the fist. The fist never misses, but the impact varies each round: 1–12, glancing blow for 1d6 damage; 13–16, solid punch for 2d6 damage; 17–19, hard punch for 3d6 damage and the opponent is stunned next round; 20, crushing blow for 4d6 damage and the opponent is stunned for the next 3 rounds. Against a stunned opponent, the caster adds +4 to the die roll to determine the fist’s result. The fist is destroyed if it takes damage equal to the caster’s hit points. Material Components: A leather glove and a small device of four connected rings in a slight curve attached to an “I”-shaped base, made from copper-zinc alloy.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user bigby s clenched fist":{"name":"Bigby’s Clenched Fist","level":"8","school":"Evocation","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Bigby’s Clenched Fist\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a huge disembodied fist under the caster’s mental control. The caster may cause it to strike one opponent each round. No other spellcasting or magical activity may be undertaken while controlling the fist. The fist never misses, but the impact varies each round: 1–12, glancing blow for 1d6 damage; 13–16, solid punch for 2d6 damage; 17–19, hard punch for 3d6 damage and the opponent is stunned next round; 20, crushing blow for 4d6 damage and the opponent is stunned for the next 3 rounds. Against a stunned opponent, the caster adds +4 to the die roll to determine the fist’s result. The fist is destroyed if it takes damage equal to the caster’s hit points. Material Components: A leather glove and a small device of four connected rings in a slight curve attached to an “I”-shaped base, made from copper-zinc alloy.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Bigby’s Clenched Fist","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user clone":{"name":"Clone","level":"8","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Clone\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a duplicate of a person. The clone is identical to the original as the person was when the flesh sample was taken, including level, experience, memories, and similar traits. Later knowledge, experience, and possessions are not copied. If the original and clone exist at the same time, each knows of the other and each wants to destroy the other, since such an alter ego is unbearable. If one cannot destroy the other, within 1 week one is 95% likely to go insane and destroy itself, with the clone 75% likely to be the one affected; there is also a 5% chance both become mad and commit suicide. The clone requires 2d4 months to grow, and dual existence is established only after that time. Material Component: A small piece of flesh from the person to be duplicated.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Clone","class":"Magic-User"},"glassteel":{"name":"Glassteel","level":"8","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Object touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Glassteel\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Object touched\nThis spell turns crystal or glass into a transparent substance with the tensile strength and unbreakability of steel. It affects one whole object with maximum weight of 10 pounds per caster level. Material Components: A small piece of glass and a small piece of steel.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user glassteel":{"name":"Glassteel","level":"8","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Object touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Glassteel\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Object touched\nThis spell turns crystal or glass into a transparent substance with the tensile strength and unbreakability of steel. It affects one whole object with maximum weight of 10 pounds per caster level. Material Components: A small piece of glass and a small piece of steel.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Glassteel","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user incendiary cloud":{"name":"Incendiary Cloud","level":"8","school":"Alteration-Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"4 rounds + 1d6 rounds","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Incendiary Cloud\n\nSchool: Alteration-Evocation\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds + 1d6 rounds\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell resembles the smoke effect of pyrotechnics, except the cloud’s minimum dimensions are 10 feet high by 20 feet long by 20 feet wide. The dense vapor cloud billows forth, and on the 3rd round begins to flame, dealing ½ hit point per caster level. On the 4th round, it deals 1 hit point per caster level. On the 5th round, damage drops again to ½ hit point per caster level as the flames burn out. Later rounds are harmless smoke that obscures vision. Creatures in the cloud need make only one saving throw if successful; if they fail the first, they roll again on the 4th and 5th rounds if necessary to reduce damage by half. Material Components: An available fire source, as with pyrotechnics, scrapings from beneath a dung pile, and a pinch of dust.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Incendiary Cloud","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user mass charm":{"name":"Mass Charm","level":"8","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"½” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"8 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Mass Charm\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell affects persons or monsters as charm person or charm monster does, but affects a number of creatures whose combined levels or Hit Dice do not exceed twice the caster’s level. All targets must be within range and within a 3” × 3” area. Target saving throws are not affected by the number of creatures, but all targets save at -2 because of the spell’s efficiency and power.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Mass Charm","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user maze":{"name":"Maze","level":"8","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"½” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Maze\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell traps the recipient in an extradimensional labyrinth of force planes. The duration depends entirely on the creature’s Intelligence. Minotaurs are unaffected.\n\nIntelligence\tTime Trapped\nUnder 3\t2d4 turns\n3–5\t1d4 turns\n6–8\t5d4 rounds\n9–11\t4d4 rounds\n12–14\t3d4 rounds\n15–17\t2d4 rounds\n18+\t1d4 rounds","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Maze","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user mind blank":{"name":"Mind Blank","level":"8","school":"Abjuration","range":"3”","duration":"1 day","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mind Blank\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 day\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell completely protects the recipient from devices and spells that detect, influence, or read emotions or thoughts. It blocks augury, charm, command, confusion, divination, empathy effects, ESP, fear, feeblemind, mass suggestion, phantasmal killer, possession, rulership, soul trapping, suggestion, and telepathy. It also prevents discovery or information-gathering by crystal balls and other scrying devices, clairaudience, clairvoyance, commune, contact other plane, wish, limited wish, and alter reality. Extremely powerful deities may penetrate the protection. It also protects against psionic detection and influence, including domination, mass domination, hypnosis, psionic invisibility, precognition, and similar powers.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Mind Blank","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user monster summoning vi":{"name":"Monster Summoning VI","level":"8","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"8”","duration":"7 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Monster Summoning VI\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 7 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons 1 or 2 6th-level monsters, which appear in 1d3 rounds. See monster summoning I for other details.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Monster Summoning VI","class":"Magic-User"},"otto s irresistible dance":{"name":"Otto’s Irresistible Dance","level":"8","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"Touch","duration":"2–5 rounds","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Otto’s Irresistible Dance\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 2–5 rounds\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell forces the touched creature to dance, shuffling and tapping its feet. The victim can do nothing except caper and prance. The dance worsens the creature’s Armor Class by 4, makes saving throws impossible, and negates any benefit from a shield. The caster must touch the target, possibly requiring an attack roll in combat.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user otto s irresistible dance":{"name":"Otto’s Irresistible Dance","level":"8","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"Touch","duration":"2–5 rounds","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Otto’s Irresistible Dance\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 2–5 rounds\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell forces the touched creature to dance, shuffling and tapping its feet. The victim can do nothing except caper and prance. The dance worsens the creature’s Armor Class by 4, makes saving throws impossible, and negates any benefit from a shield. The caster must touch the target, possibly requiring an attack roll in combat.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Otto’s Irresistible Dance","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user permanency":{"name":"Permanency","level":"8","school":"Alteration","range":"Special","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Permanency\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 2 rounds\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell makes certain spell effects permanent. For personal use, it may make permanent: comprehend languages, detect evil, detect invisibility, detect magic, infravision, protection from evil, protection from normal missiles, read magic, tongues, and unseen servant. The magic-user casts the desired spell and then permanency. Each permanency lowers the magic-user’s Constitution by 1 point. The caster cannot use these personal permanent effects on others. The spell can also make certain object, creature, or area effects permanent: enlarge, fear, gust of wind, invisibility, magic mouth, prismatic sphere, stinking cloud, wall of fire, wall of force, and web. Personal permanency can be dispelled only by a magic-user of higher level than the original caster. Other permanent effects can be dispelled normally, negating the whole effect.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Permanency","class":"Magic-User"},"polymorph any object":{"name":"Polymorph Any Object","level":"8","school":"Alteration","range":"½” per level","duration":"Variable","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Polymorph Any Object\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Variable\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell changes one object, living or otherwise, into another. Used as polymorph other or stone to flesh, it functions as a more powerful version, with saves made at -4. For other transformations, duration depends on how radically the original differs from the new form, including kingdom, class, relationship, size, shape, and intelligence. Changes across one kingdom last hours; changes across two kingdoms last turns. For example, changing a lion into an androsphinx is permanent, turning a turnip into a purple worm lasts hours, turning a tusk into an elephant is permanent, and turning a twig into a sword lasts several turns. Polymorphed objects radiate strong magic, and dispel magic returns them to natural form. Stone to flesh and its reverse affect objects under this spell. System shock applies to living creatures, as do the restrictions of polymorph other and stone to flesh. Material Components: Mercury, gum arabic, and smoke.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user polymorph any object":{"name":"Polymorph Any Object","level":"8","school":"Alteration","range":"½” per level","duration":"Variable","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Polymorph Any Object\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Variable\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell changes one object, living or otherwise, into another. Used as polymorph other or stone to flesh, it functions as a more powerful version, with saves made at -4. For other transformations, duration depends on how radically the original differs from the new form, including kingdom, class, relationship, size, shape, and intelligence. Changes across one kingdom last hours; changes across two kingdoms last turns. For example, changing a lion into an androsphinx is permanent, turning a turnip into a purple worm lasts hours, turning a tusk into an elephant is permanent, and turning a twig into a sword lasts several turns. Polymorphed objects radiate strong magic, and dispel magic returns them to natural form. Stone to flesh and its reverse affect objects under this spell. System shock applies to living creatures, as do the restrictions of polymorph other and stone to flesh. Material Components: Mercury, gum arabic, and smoke.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Polymorph Any Object","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user power word blind":{"name":"Power Word, Blind","level":"8","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"½” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"3” diameter","components":"V","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Power Word, Blind\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” diameter\nThis spell temporarily blinds one or more creatures within range and area of effect. It affects up to 100 total hit points of creatures. If 50 or fewer hit points are affected, blindness lasts 1d4+1 turns. If 51 or more hit points are affected, blindness lasts 1d4+1 rounds. The caster must identify the creatures to affect and designate one as the center before results are determined. Creatures with more than 100 hit points are unaffected. Blindness can be removed by cure blindness or dispel magic.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Power Word, Blind","class":"Magic-User"},"serten s spell immunity":{"name":"Serten’s Spell Immunity","level":"8","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Creature or creatures touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round per recipient","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Serten’s Spell Immunity\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round per recipient\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature or creatures touched\nThis spell gives virtual immunity to certain spells and magical attacks. For every 4 caster levels, one creature can be protected, but duration is divided among additional recipients. For example, a 16th-level caster can protect one creature for 16 turns, two creatures for 8 turns, or four creatures for 4 turns. The spell grants the following saving throw bonuses: +9 against beguiling, charm, and suggestion; +7 against command, domination, fear, hold, and scare; and +5 against geas and quest. Material Components: A diamond crushed and sprinkled over the recipients, and each recipient must also carry an intact diamond of any size.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user serten s spell immunity":{"name":"Serten’s Spell Immunity","level":"8","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"Creature or creatures touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round per recipient","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Serten’s Spell Immunity\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round per recipient\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature or creatures touched\nThis spell gives virtual immunity to certain spells and magical attacks. For every 4 caster levels, one creature can be protected, but duration is divided among additional recipients. For example, a 16th-level caster can protect one creature for 16 turns, two creatures for 8 turns, or four creatures for 4 turns. The spell grants the following saving throw bonuses: +9 against beguiling, charm, and suggestion; +7 against command, domination, fear, hold, and scare; and +5 against geas and quest. Material Components: A diamond crushed and sprinkled over the recipients, and each recipient must also carry an intact diamond of any size.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Serten’s Spell Immunity","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user symbol":{"name":"Symbol","level":"8","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Symbol\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates magical runes that affect creatures that pass over, touch, read, or pass through a portal bearing the symbol. The caster chooses one symbol when casting. Death: Slays one or more creatures whose total hit points do not exceed 80. Discord: Affects all creatures, causing loud bickering and arguing. There is a 50% chance creatures of different alignment attack one another. Bickering lasts 5d4 rounds, and fighting lasts 2d4 rounds. Fear: Functions as an especially strong fear spell, causing creatures to save at -4 or panic and flee. Hopelessness: Affects all creatures, forcing them to turn back in dejection unless they save. Affected creatures submit to opponent demands, such as surrendering or leaving. The effect lasts 3d4 turns; during that time, each round there is a 25% chance an affected creature takes no action and a 25% chance a creature attempting action turns back or retires from battle. Insanity: One or more creatures whose total hit points do not exceed 120 become insane and act as if under confusion until heal, restoration, or wish removes the madness. Pain: All creatures suffer wracking pain, causing -2 Dexterity and -4 on attack rolls for 2d10 turns. Sleep: All creatures under 8+1 Hit Dice fall into catatonic slumber and cannot be awakened for 1d12+4 turns. Stunning: One or more creatures whose total hit points do not exceed 160 are stunned and reeling for 3d4 rounds, dropping anything held. The type of symbol cannot be recognized without reading it, which activates it. Material Components: Powdered black opal and diamond dust worth at least 5,000 gp each.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Symbol","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user trap the soul":{"name":"Trap The Soul","level":"8","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent until broken","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special + 1 segment","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Trap The Soul\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: Special + 1 segment\nDuration: Permanent until broken\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell is similar to magic jar, but forces the subject’s life force and material body, if any, into a specially prepared magical prison. The caster must see the subject and know its true name when the final word is spoken. Before casting, the magic-user must prepare the soul prison: a gem worth 1,000 gp per Hit Die or level of the target, enchanted with enchant an item and then filled with a maze spell. The soul may be trapped in two ways. First, the caster may speak the final word while the target is within range; the target may apply magic resistance and receives a saving throw versus magic, and if the save succeeds, the gem shatters. Second, the caster may trick the victim into accepting a trigger object inscribed with the final spell word. If this method is used, the trigger item must be named when the prison gem is enchanted, and sympathy may be placed on it. When the target picks up or accepts the trigger item, its soul is automatically transferred to the gem. The gem holds the soul indefinitely, or until broken. If a powerful creature from another plane is trapped, it may be required to perform one service immediately upon release. Otherwise, the creature goes free when the gem is broken.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 9th Level","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Trap The Soul","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user astral spell":{"name":"Astral Spell","level":"9","school":"Evocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Astral Spell\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 7th-level cleric spell astral spell.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Astral Spell","class":"Magic-User"},"bigby s crushing hand":{"name":"Bigby’s Crushing Hand","level":"9","school":"Evocation","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Bigby’s Crushing Hand\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a huge disembodied hand similar to Bigby’s forceful hand and Bigby’s clenched fist. The caster mentally controls the hand and can make it grasp and squeeze an opponent. Constriction damage depends on duration: 1st round, 1d10 damage; 2nd and 3rd rounds, 2d10 damage; 4th round and beyond, 4d10 damage. The hand can sustain damage equal to the caster’s hit points before being dispelled. Material Components: A snakeskin glove and an eggshell.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user bigby s crushing hand":{"name":"Bigby’s Crushing Hand","level":"9","school":"Evocation","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Bigby’s Crushing Hand\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a huge disembodied hand similar to Bigby’s forceful hand and Bigby’s clenched fist. The caster mentally controls the hand and can make it grasp and squeeze an opponent. Constriction damage depends on duration: 1st round, 1d10 damage; 2nd and 3rd rounds, 2d10 damage; 4th round and beyond, 4d10 damage. The hand can sustain damage equal to the caster’s hit points before being dispelled. Material Components: A snakeskin glove and an eggshell.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Bigby’s Crushing Hand","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user gate":{"name":"Gate","level":"9","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"3”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Gate\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 7th-level cleric spell gate.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Gate","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user imprisonment":{"name":"Imprisonment","level":"9","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Imprisonment\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Freedom\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell entombs the touched victim in suspended animation inside a small sphere far below the earth’s surface. The victim remains there unless the reverse, freedom, is cast with the creature’s name and background. Magical searches such as crystal balls, locate object, or similar means do not reveal that the creature is imprisoned. Freedom returns the victim to the spot where they were entombed and sunk into the earth. If the caster does not perfectly know the name and background of the creature to be freed, there is a 10% chance that 1d100 other imprisoned creatures are freed at the same time. The spell works only if the victim’s name and background are known.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Imprisonment","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user meteor swarm":{"name":"Meteor Swarm","level":"9","school":"Evocation","range":"4” + 1” per level","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"Half","save_type":"","description":"Meteor Swarm\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 4” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spectacular spell resembles fireball in many respects. The caster creates either four 2-foot-diameter spheres or eight 1-foot-diameter spheres that streak in straight lines from the caster’s outstretched hand to the chosen range. Any creature directly in a meteor’s path takes the missile’s full effect with no saving throw. Each meteor leaves a fiery trail and bursts like a fireball. The four large meteors each deal 10d4 damage and burst in a diamond or box pattern. Each has a 3” diameter area of effect, and each sphere is 2” from the others along the pattern’s sides, creating overlapping blast areas. The center is exposed to all four blasts. The eight small meteors each deal 5d4 damage with a 1½” diameter area. They burst in a box-within-diamond or diamond-within-box pattern, with outer sides 2” long and inner sides 1” long. The center has four overlapping areas, and many peripheral areas have two overlapping areas. Creatures in each blast area save separately for half damage, except for direct missile impacts.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Meteor Swarm","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user monster summoning vii":{"name":"Monster Summoning VII","level":"9","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"9”","duration":"8 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Monster Summoning VII\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 9”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 8 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons 1 or 2 7th-level monsters, which appear 1 round after casting, or one 8th-level monster, which appears 2 rounds after casting. See monster summoning I for other details.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Monster Summoning VII","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user power word kill":{"name":"Power Word, Kill","level":"9","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"¼” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"2” diameter","components":"V","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Power Word, Kill\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V\nRange: ¼” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2” diameter\nWhen this spell is uttered, one or more creatures within range and area are slain. The spell can kill one creature with up to 60 hit points, or kill multiple creatures with 10 or fewer hit points each, up to a combined maximum of 120 hit points. The caster must state whether the spell is being used against one creature or multiple creatures, along with the range and area center.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Power Word, Kill","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user prismatic sphere":{"name":"Prismatic Sphere","level":"9","school":"Abjuration, Conjuration/Summoning","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"2” diameter sphere","components":"V","ct":"7 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Prismatic Sphere\n\nSchool: Abjuration, Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 2” diameter sphere\nThis spell surrounds the caster with an opaque globe of shimmering, multicolored light that protects against all forms of attack. The sphere flashes all seven colors of the visible spectrum, each with a different power. Creatures with fewer than 8 Hit Dice are blinded by the colors for 2d4 turns. The sphere is immobile, and only the caster can pass through it safely. Usually only the upper hemisphere is visible because the caster stands at the center and the lower half is hidden by the floor. Anything entering the sphere is subject to every globe in order: 70 total damage plus possible death, petrification, insanity, and/or transportation to another plane. Only the latter four effects allow saving throws. A rod of cancellation destroys the whole sphere. Otherwise, individual globes must be destroyed in order, from red through violet.\n\nColor\tOrder\tEffect\tNegated By\nRed\t1st\tPrevents all nonmagical missiles; inflicts 10 damage\tCone of cold\nOrange\t2nd\tPrevents all magical missiles; inflicts 20 damage\tGust of wind\nYellow\t3rd\tPrevents poison, gases, and petrification; inflicts 40 damage\tDisintegrate\nGreen\t4th\tPrevents all breath weapons; save vs. poison or die\tPasswall\nBlue\t5th\tPrevents location, detection, and psionics; save vs. petrification or turn to stone\tMagic missile\nIndigo\t6th\tPrevents all magical spells; save vs. wand or become insane\tContinual light\nViolet\t7th\tForce field protection; save vs. magic or be sent to another plane\tDispel magic","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Prismatic Sphere","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user shape change":{"name":"Shape Change","level":"9","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"The spellcaster","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Shape Change\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The spellcaster\nThis spell allows the magic-user to assume the form of nearly any creature short of a demigod, greater devil, demon prince, unique dragon, greater demon, or similar being. The caster gains all abilities of the new form except those dependent on Intelligence, since the caster retains their own mind. The caster may change repeatedly during the duration, with each change requiring 1 segment. No system shock roll is required. The caster keeps their own current hit points in each form. For example, the caster may become a will-o’-wisp, then a stone golem, then a flea, then a bush, then a dragon or pool of water. Material Component: A jade circlet worth at least 5,000 gp, which shatters when the spell ends. If it shatters early, the spell is dispelled.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Shape Change","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user temporal stasis":{"name":"Temporal Stasis","level":"9","school":"Alteration","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Temporal Stasis\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Temporal Reinstatement\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell places the recipient in suspended animation. Time stops for the creature, so it does not age and its bodily functions virtually cease. The state persists until removed by dispel magic or by the reverse, temporal reinstatement. The reverse requires only a single word and no somatic or material components. Material Component: A powder made from diamond, emerald, ruby, and sapphire dust, requiring one stone of each type.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Temporal Stasis","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user time stop":{"name":"Time Stop","level":"9","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"½ segment per level + 1d8 segments","aoe":"3” diameter sphere","components":"V","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Time Stop\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: ½ segment per level + 1d8 segments\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” diameter sphere\nThis spell stops time within the area of effect. Outside the sphere, the area merely seems to shimmer for an instant. During the subjective duration, the caster may move and act freely inside the stopped area, while all other creatures there are frozen between ticks of time. Any creature entering the area is also stopped. If the caster leaves the area, the spell immediately ends. When the duration expires, the caster returns to normal time.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Time Stop","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user wish":{"name":"Wish","level":"9","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Unlimited","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"Special","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Wish\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V\nRange: Unlimited\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is a more powerful version of limited wish. Using it to alter reality with respect to hit points sustained by a party, bring a dead character back to life, or escape a difficult situation by moving the caster and party elsewhere does not harm the caster. Other wishes make the caster weak, imposing -3 Strength, and require 2d4 days of bed rest because of the stress placed on time, space, and the caster’s body. The exact wording of the wish is likely to be fulfilled literally, and the referee interprets the result to preserve game balance. For example, wishing another character dead might instead send the caster to a future time when that character is no longer alive.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Wish","class":"Magic-User"},"cleric augury":{"name":"Augury","level":"2","school":"Divine divination","range":"Caster","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Caster","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Augury\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 2 rounds\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nThe cleric casting an augury spell seeks to divine whether an action in the immediate future, within 3 turns, will benefit or harm the party. The base chance for correctly divining the augury is 70%, plus 1% per caster level. For example, the chance is 71% at 1st level, 72% at 2nd level, and so on. The referee determines any adjustments based on the conditions of the augury. For example, if a party is considering destroying a weird seal that closes a portal, augury may be used to determine whether weal or woe will result for the party. Material Component: A set of gem-inlaid sticks, dragon bones, similar tokens, or wet infusion leaves left in a container after the infused brew is consumed. If the infusion method is used, a crushed pearl worth at least 100 g.p. must be added before the brew is consumed.","notes":"Your instruments of divination respond to a question about what might happen in the near future, based on a proposed course of action. The results are vague, and there is a chance of an inaccurate reading.\nDetails:\n    When you finish casting, the GM secretly rolls to see if you interpret the omen correctly. Your chance of success is 70% + 1% per cleric level. If you fail, the GM provides a random inaccurate answer instead of the accurate one.\n    You must have instruments of divination worth at least 100 gp (e.g., dragon-bone or gold sticks, crystal ball, entrails of a sacrifice, tarot cards, or other culturally/religiously appropriate means approved by the GM).\n    You must ask about a specific course of action you plan to take within the next 30 minutes. The response is one of:\n        Weal (generally favourable)\n        Woe (generally unfavourable)\n        Weal and woe (mixed results)\n        Nothing (not especially favourable or unfavourable)\n    The worlds of OSRIC aren’t deterministic; divination reveals what is likely, not what is certain.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Augury"},"cleric chant":{"name":"Chant","level":"2","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Nil","duration":"Continuing","aoe":"30 ft radius around the point where you were standing when you finished casting","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Chant\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Time of chanting\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” radius\nBy means of chant, the cleric brings special favor upon themselves and their party while causing harm to enemies. Once the spell is completed, all attacks, damage rolls, and saving throws made by friendly creatures in the area of effect gain a +1 bonus, while those made by the cleric’s enemies suffer a -1 penalty. This bonus and penalty continue as long as the cleric remains stationary and continues chanting the mystic syllables. Any interruption, such as a successful damaging attack, grappling, or magical silence, breaks the spell.","notes":"You chant holy words and prayers. After the first round (casting time), and for as long as you remain stationary and continue chanting, your allies receive minor divine assistance and enemies are obstructed.\nDetails:\n    The chanting makes a moderate amount of sound: heard within 30 ft, and heard as far as 60 ft on a 1d6 roll of 5–6.\n    The spell’s effects are cumulative with prayer.\n    While the spell continues, the following apply within the area:\n        You and your allies may choose to gain +1 to attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws.\n        Enemies suffer -1 to attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Chant"},"cleric conceal alignment":{"name":"Conceal Alignment","level":"2","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"depends on number of targets:","aoe":"1 to 10 creatures, objects, or places","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"You obscure the alignments of a number of targets, causing detect evil, detect good, and know alignment to perceive them as neutral.\nDetails:\n    Also fools special abilities that detect alignment (e.g., monsters with such abilities, a paladin’s detect evil).\nTargets\tDuration\n1\t1 turn\n2\t5 rounds\n3\t3 rounds\n4–5\t2 rounds\n6–10\t1 round","notes":"You obscure the alignments of a number of targets, causing detect evil, detect good, and know alignment to perceive them as neutral.\nDetails:\n    Also fools special abilities that detect alignment (e.g., monsters with such abilities, a paladin’s detect evil).\nTargets\tDuration\n1\t1 turn\n2\t5 rounds\n3\t3 rounds\n4–5\t2 rounds\n6–10\t1 round","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Conceal Alignment"},"cleric conceal charm":{"name":"Conceal Charm","level":"2","school":"Divine enchantment","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 turn","aoe":"One creature within range","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Until this spell ends, detect charm, detect magic, and other magical divinations do not reveal this or any other enchantment spells that you cast on the target. Such divinations still reveal enchantments cast by others.\nDetails:\n    This spell hides your enchantments from magical detection; non-magical questioning/testing is unaffected.\n    The concealment can be cast before or after the actual charm, but the duration begins immediately even if the charm has not yet been cast.\n    Psychic/psionic mind-reading may or may not count as “magical” (GM’s decision).","notes":"Until this spell ends, detect charm, detect magic, and other magical divinations do not reveal this or any other enchantment spells that you cast on the target. Such divinations still reveal enchantments cast by others.\nDetails:\n    This spell hides your enchantments from magical detection; non-magical questioning/testing is unaffected.\n    The concealment can be cast before or after the actual charm, but the duration begins immediately even if the charm has not yet been cast.\n    Psychic/psionic mind-reading may or may not count as “magical” (GM’s decision).","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Conceal Charm"},"cleric detect charm":{"name":"Detect Charm","level":"2","school":"Divine divination","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 turn","aoe":"Up to 10 creatures within range","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"Detect Charm\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Protect From Charm Detection\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 turn\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nWhen used by a cleric, this spell detects whether a person or monster is under the influence of a charm spell. Up to 10 creatures may be checked before the spell ends. The reverse protects against such detection, but only one creature may be shielded.","notes":"An aura, visible only to you, forms around any creature in the area of effect that is being magically influenced or controlled. In some cases, a saving throw applies.\nDetails:\n    This spell reveals magical control or influence; it does not detect non-magical persuasion, propaganda, or deception.\n    If the target is affected by a charm spell, there is no saving throw.\n    If the target is dominated by a monster ability other than a charm, the target may attempt a saving throw vs spells; on a success, the influence is not revealed.\n    Psychic/psionic domination may or may not count as “magical” (GM’s decision).\n    If a creature is invisible, you know its location but not details. Attack rolls against it halve the normal invisible-target penalty (usually -2 instead of -4).\nReversible as Conceal Charm:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Detect Charm"},"cleric find traps":{"name":"Find Traps","level":"2","school":"Divine divination","range":"30 ft","duration":"3 turns","aoe":"10 ft wide path originating from you","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Find Traps\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 3 turns\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” path\nWhen a cleric casts find traps, all traps, whether normally concealed, magically concealed, magical, or mechanical, become visible to the cleric. This spell is directional, so the caster must face the desired direction to determine whether a trap lies that way.","notes":"This spell reveals the presence of magical and mechanical traps within the area of effect. Only you perceive the exact location of each trap (and its trigger if within the area). You also learn the basic threat the trap represents.\nDetails:\n    For this spell, a “trap” is anything non-creature that would have an unexpected and undesirable effect (GM adjudication). Examples: poison needle in a lock, tripwire to a bell, a weak floor, glyph of warding.\n    Only the basic nature is revealed; specifics (poison type, pit depth, etc.) are up to the GM.\n    If the trap is magical or concealed by magic, there is a 10% chance per cleric level you can detect the involved school of magic.\n    The spell does not detect creatures and does not teach disarming/avoidance.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Find Traps"},"cleric hold person":{"name":"Hold Person","level":"2","school":"Divine enchantment","range":"60 ft","duration":"4 rounds + 1 round per cleric level","aoe":"1, 2, or 3 creatures of your choice within range","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Hold Person\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One to three creatures\nThis spell holds immobile and freezes in place 1 to 3 humans or humanoid creatures for 5 or more melee rounds. The cleric’s level determines the duration: 5 melee rounds at 1st level, 6 rounds at 2nd level, 7 rounds at 3rd level, and so on. If the spell is cast at three targets, each saves normally. If cast at two targets, each saves at -1. If cast at one target, the saving throw is made at -2. Creatures that make their saving throws are unaffected. Affected creatures include brownies, dryads, dwarves, elves, gnolls, gnomes, goblins, half-elves, halflings, half-orcs, hobgoblins, humans, kobolds, lizard men, nixies, orcs, pixies, sprites, and troglodytes. Material Component: A small, straight piece of iron.","notes":"Targets must save vs spells or be paralysed. The saving throw modifier depends on how many creatures you affect.\nDetails:\n    Only affects bipedal (human/demi-human/humanoid-like) creatures of Medium size or smaller.\n    Each target saves vs spells and applies its Wisdom save modifier (if any), plus a modifier based on targets chosen:\n        1 target: saves at -2\n        2 targets: no modifier\n        3 targets: each saves at +2\n    Held creatures cannot move voluntary muscles, but may keep breathing and heartbeat continues. Psychic/psionic powers usable without voluntary movement may still function.\nCombat effects (paralysis reminder):\n    Held creatures are physically helpless. If you have a hand weapon and are not in melee, you can automatically kill one held creature each round.\n    If you have rope/chain/bindings and are not in melee, you may bind one held creature each round instead of attacking.\n    You may choose normal attacks instead (e.g., still in melee, multiple attacks, touch spell).\n    Any weapon/unarmed/touch attack against a held creature hits automatically unless you choose to miss. On a hit with a weapon/unarmed attack, you may deal maximum damage instead of rolling. If every creature you attack is held, your number of attacks is doubled that round.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Hold Person"},"cleric know alignment":{"name":"Know Alignment","level":"2","school":"Divine divination","range":"Caster","duration":"1 turn","aoe":"1 creature, object, or place per round","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Know Alignment\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Obscure Alignment\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 turn\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature per round\nThis spell allows the cleric to exactly read the aura of a human, semi-human, or non-human creature, revealing that creature’s exact alignment. Up to 10 creatures may be examined. The reverse totally obscures alignment, even from this spell, for one creature for 1 turn, two creatures for 5 rounds, and so on. Certain magical devices negate the ability to know alignment.","notes":"After casting, you may focus on one target per round within 10 ft and learn its alignment.\nDetails:\n    Reveals alignment, not danger; it won’t necessarily reveal traps or poison.\n    Does not necessarily detect curses, though some horrific curses can make an item inherently evil (typically neutral evil).\n    Opaque materials interfere: penetrates metal up to 1 inch, and brick/stone up to 1 foot.\n    Most places do not have alignments, except certain sites (e.g., temples, desecrated temples, outer-planar portals, and places specifically described as good/evil/holy/unholy).\nReversible as Conceal Alignment:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Know Alignment"},"cleric resist fire":{"name":"Resist Fire","level":"2","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per cleric level","aoe":"1 creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Resist Fire\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell toughens the recipient’s body against heat, making boiling temperatures comfortable. The recipient can even stand amid very hot or magical fires, such as red-hot charcoal, large amounts of burning oil, flaming swords, fire storms, fire balls, meteor swarms, or red dragon breath, though such effects still harm the creature to some extent. The recipient gains a +3 bonus on saving throws against such attacks. Fire damage is reduced by 50%, so a failed saving throw results in half damage, and a successful saving throw results in one-quarter damage. The spell lasts 1 turn per caster level. Material Component: A drop of mercury.","notes":"Protects the target against fire damage and heat.\nDetails:\n    Safe from non-magical fire (e.g., torches).\n    Immune to ill effects of normal heat (up to boiling).\n    Against magical or extremely hot fire, grants:\n        Provides Saving Throw: May attempt a saving throw against any magical fire effect even if none is normally allowed (typically vs spells and other magical effects).\n        Improves Saving Throw: If already allowed a save vs fire damage, may choose to add +3.\n        Reduces Damage: Fire damage is halved; if already halved (e.g., successful save), halve again. Round down.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Resist Fire"},"cleric silence 15 ft radius":{"name":"Silence 15 Ft Radius","level":"2","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"120 ft","duration":"2 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"15 ft radius sphere around the target","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"Silence, 15’ Radius\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 30’ diameter sphere\nWhen this spell is cast, complete silence fills the area of effect. All sound stops, conversation becomes impossible, spells cannot be cast, and no noise issues from the affected area. The spell may be cast into the air or upon an object. It lasts 2 rounds per caster level: 2 rounds at 1st level, 4 at 2nd level, 6 at 3rd level, 8 at 4th level, and so on. The spell may also be cast upon a creature, causing the silence to radiate from and move with that creature. If the creature is unwilling, it receives a saving throw. If the save succeeds, the spell effect is centered about 1 foot behind the target creature.","notes":"Creates a zone of silence centred on a creature, object, or point in space. Within the area:\n    No sound can be produced; and\n    No sound can be heard, even from outside the zone.\nDetails:\n    Objects and points in space receive no saving throw.\n    A creature target may choose a saving throw vs spells and other magical effects:\n        Success: the target becomes the 5 ft square the creature is standing in (the creature can move out).\n        Failure: the creature remains the target; the silence moves with it.\n    Combat effects:\n        No one can cast spells with a verbal component within the area.\n        Attempts to sneak or move quietly always succeed if the creature is within the area.\n        Echolocation-dependent creatures (e.g., bats, dolphins) are blinded and suffer -4 “to hit”.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Silence 15 Ft Radius"},"cleric slow poison":{"name":"Slow Poison","level":"2","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns per cleric level","aoe":"1 creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Fast","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Slow Poison\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 hour per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nWhen cast upon a poisoned individual, this spell greatly slows the effects of venom. It can even temporarily restore life to a supposedly dead victim if cast within a number of turns after poisoning equal to or less than the cleric’s level. For example, a victim poisoned up to 10 turns earlier could be temporarily saved by a 10th-level or higher cleric. The spell does not neutralize the venom, but it prevents substantial harm for the spell’s duration. Each turn, the poisoned creature loses 1 hit point from the venom, though the victim will never fall below 1 hit point while the spell lasts. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol and a bud of garlic, which must be crushed and smeared on the victim’s bare feet.","notes":"Slows the effects of poison to keep someone alive until the poison can be neutralised (e.g., antidote or neutralise poison).\nDetails:\nPoison is often treated as “save or die,” but death is not instantaneous. This spell can slow poison and keep a victim alive within a time window determined by cleric level.\n    Target poisoned but not dead:\n    Record poison damage taken at the moment of casting; this is “slowed damage.”\n    Slowed damage is healed immediately when the spell is cast.\n    During the duration, the creature takes 1 hp poison damage every 10 rounds, but cannot be reduced below 1 hp by this poison damage until the spell ends.\n    Other (non-poison) damage applies normally.\n    Target recently dead from poison:\n    A creature counts as “recently died of poison” if it died from poison damage or from failing a save vs poison within a number of turns equal to your cleric level.\n    The creature is restored to life at the hit points it had before the poison affected it.\n    During the duration, it takes 1 hp poison damage every 10 rounds, but cannot be reduced below 1 hp by this poison damage until the spell ends.\n    Other damage applies normally.\nAdditional poison during duration:\n    Additional poison damage is not applied immediately; record it as additional slowed damage.\n    If the creature fails further saves vs poison, those poison effects are also delayed until the spell ends.\n    If the poison is not cured by the time the spell expires, all slowed poisons take full effect immediately, including the full amount of slowed damage.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Slow Poison"},"cleric snake charm":{"name":"Snake Charm","level":"2","school":"Divine enchantment","range":"30 ft","duration":"2 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"One animal within range","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Snake Charm\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nWhen this spell is cast, it creates a hypnotic pattern that causes one or more snakes to cease all activity except a semi-erect swaying motion. If the snakes are charmed while torpid, the spell lasts 3 to 6 turns, or d4 + 2. If the snakes are not torpid but are also not aroused or angry, the charm lasts 1 to 3 turns. If the snakes are angry and/or attacking, the charm lasts 5 to 8 melee rounds, or d4 + 4. The cleric may charm snakes whose total hit points are less than or equal to the cleric’s own hit points. The hit points may belong to one snake or several snakes, but the total may not exceed the cleric’s hit points.","notes":"Affects snakes, serpents, couatls, nagas, and other ophidian/serpentine creatures: they rear up and sway without otherwise moving, taking no actions and not attacking until the spell ends. When it ends, they forget what occurred while affected.\nDetails:\n    Total hit points of affected creatures cannot exceed your uninjured hit points. If you target more, the GM decides (or randomly determines) which are unaffected until the total affected hp is within your limit.\n    If in doubt, affected creatures include those listed above and other reptilian creatures that had no limbs when hatched. Not affected: dragons, demons, devils, wyverns.\n        Asleep/unconscious: 1d4 + 2 turns\n        Alert: 1d3 turns\n        Angry/attacking: 1d4 + 4 rounds\n    Attacking a charmed snake breaks the charm on that snake only.\nSPEAK WITH ANIMALS\nClerical transmutation, level 2\nAllows communication with a nearby animal.\nDetails:\n    You speak in Common; the animal understands magically. The animal communicates in its natural way; meaning is translated into your mind (others do not hear the translation).\n    You may attempt persuasion, deception, or bargaining for services.\n    Affects normal non-fantastic animals (wolves, badgers, bears) and giant versions without additional fantastic abilities (e.g., giant lizard yes; basilisk no).\n    Mindless animals (INT “non” or 0) are not affected. The animal must have intelligence of animal, semi-, or low.\n    Humans are not animals for this spell.\n    The spell does not compel truth, and it does not force the animal to stop fighting if you/your allies attacked it, though it usually won’t initiate combat while the spell is in effect.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Snake Charm"},"cleric speak with animals":{"name":"Speak With Animals","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"One animal within 3” radius of cleric","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Speak With Animals\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One animal within 3” radius of cleric\nThis spell allows the cleric to comprehend and communicate with any warm- or cold-blooded animal that is not mindless, such as an amoeba. The cleric may ask questions, receive answers, and generally remain on amicable terms with the animal. The ability lasts 2 melee rounds per caster level. Even if the animal’s bent is opposite to the cleric’s, such as evil/good or good/evil, it and others of its kind will not attack while the spell lasts. If the animal is neutral or of the same general bent as the cleric, such as evil/evil or good/good, it may perform some favor or service. The referee determines this possibility using a special reaction chart, with the cleric’s charisma and actions as major factors. This spell differs from speak with monsters, because it allows conversation only with basically normal, non-fantastic creatures such as apes, bears, cats, dogs, and elephants.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Speak With Animals"},"cleric spiritual weapon":{"name":"Spiritual Weapon","level":"2","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"30 ft radius around you","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Spiritual Hammer\n\nSchool: Invocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One opponent\nBy calling upon their deity, the cleric creates a hammer-shaped field of force. As long as the cleric concentrates, the force may strike any opponent within range as desired. The force strikes as a magical weapon equal to +1 per 3 caster levels for purposes of hitting creatures that require magical weapons, though it gains no magical bonuses “to hit.” It deals the same damage as a normal war hammer: 1d6 against man-sized or smaller opponents, and 1d4 against larger opponents. The hammer attacks at the cleric’s own level, as if the cleric were personally wielding it. When the cleric stops concentrating, the hammer is dispelled. If the cleric is behind an opponent, the force may strike from that position, gaining applicable bonuses and negating defensive protections such as shield and Dexterity. Material Component: A normal war hammer, which the cleric hurls toward opponents while uttering a plea to their deity. The hammer disappears when the spell is cast.","notes":"Creates a magical force shaped like a weapon (usually a hammer; may match your deity’s sacred weapon). It cannot move more than 30 ft from you, but within that radius it attacks where you direct it.\nDetails:\n    Each round until the spell ends, you may attack one creature within range using the spiritual weapon. Roll to hit as if using a regular weapon.\n    On a hit, it deals 1d6 magical damage (not blunt/piercing/slashing; can harm creatures immune to mundane weapons, and isn’t treated as a “weapon” for those purposes).\n    The weapon is not physical and can pass through obstacles (including walls) as long as it stays within the area.\n    If you direct it to attack a target you can’t see, you are effectively blinded with respect to that target.\n    If it attacks from behind, it gains the normal rear-attack bonus (usually +2).\n    You must concentrate to maintain the spell, or it ends (see Concentration rules).","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Spiritual Weapon"},"cleric animate dead":{"name":"Animate Dead","level":"3","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"10 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Up to 1 corpse per cleric level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Animate Dead\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates the lowest undead monsters, skeletons or zombies, from the bones or bodies of dead humans. The remains become animated and obey the cleric’s commands. The skeletons or zombies may follow, remain in an area, attack any creature or specific type of creature entering a place, and so on. The spell animates them until they are destroyed or the magic is dispelled. The cleric may animate 1 skeleton or 1 zombie per caster level. For example, a 2nd-level cleric may animate 2 such monsters, a 3rd-level cleric may animate 3, and so on. The act of animating dead is not basically good, and clerics of good alignment must use it with careful consideration and good reason. Material Components: A drop of blood, a piece of human flesh, and a pinch of bone powder or a bone shard.","notes":"You animate dead bodies to serve you. The undead created are skeletons or zombies, depending on decomposition. Larger undead can be created, but doing so reduces the total number of “corpses” you can affect (see below).\nDetails:\n    The undead obey simple verbal commands. They understand any spoken language. Control cannot be delegated (you can’t order them to follow someone else’s orders), though you can specify actions that trigger when another person says something.\n    You can’t animate a corpse that is already undead.\n    If not commanded, undead do nothing. They feel no pain or fear, have no self-preservation, and do not defend themselves while idle.\n    Commands must be loud, clear, completely unambiguous, and require no deduction or interpretation. Example: “Attack the elf in the blue robe” works; “Attack the wizard” may not (too much deduction). If the command is ambiguous (e.g., two elves in blue robes), they do nothing.\n    Animated undead cannot perceive creatures more than 60 ft away.\n    After completing a command, they do nothing until commanded again.\n    If you issue no commands for 7 consecutive days, they become free-willed skeletons/zombies. Free-willed undead defend themselves and typically attack any living creatures larger than an insect they can perceive. Over time, they drift toward dark places and sites of evil deeds.\nMonster type:\n    Human / demi-human / humanoid corpses: Rise as zombies, or as skeletons if bones are mostly exposed. They fight as standard zombies/skeletons. They can use hand weapons if available. Zombies cannot use bows/crossbows/slings, but can use thrown weapons. Skeletons can use missile weapons without restriction.\n    Roughly human-sized but not human-like in shape: Rise as animal skeletons/zombies. They cannot use weapons and can only move by walking (no flight, even if the corpse had wings).\n    Human-like but larger than human: Rise as mighty skeletons/zombies with the hit dice they had in life. Each additional hit die beyond 1 counts as an additional “corpse” for this spell’s limit. Example: at cleric level 9, you could raise an 8 HD hill giant zombie plus one other human-sized corpse.\n    Larger than human and not human-like in shape: Cannot be animated by this spell (e.g., dragon skeleton).\nSetting note: Many good-aligned religions forbid this spell; others allow it only in dire need. In most civilised lands, casting it and controlling undead are criminal acts.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Animate Dead"},"cleric bestow curse":{"name":"Bestow Curse","level":"3","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"1 creature","components":"V, S","ct":"6 segments","save":"Yes (negates effect)","save_type":"","description":"Remove Curse\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Bestow Curse\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell usually removes a curse from an object, person, undesired sending, or evil presence. It does not affect a cursed shield, weapon, or suit of armor directly, though it typically enables the afflicted person to get rid of such an item. The reverse, bestow curse, is not permanent and lasts 1 turn per caster level. It lowers one randomly selected ability score to 3 half the time; reduces the victim’s “to hit” and saving throw probabilities by -4 one-quarter of the time; or gives the victim a 50% chance each turn to drop whatever they are holding, or do nothing if not using tools, one-quarter of the time. A cleric may devise another curse of similar power, subject to the referee. The target must be touched and receives a saving throw; success negates the curse.","notes":"Places a curse on the target.\nDetails:\n    A creature can only be affected by one instance of this spell at a time.\n    Many good-aligned religions forbid this spell; others allow it only in dire need.\n    On a successful curse, roll 1d8:\nRoll\tEffect\n1–4\tOne ability score reduced to 3\n5–6\t-4 to attack rolls and saving throws\n7–8\tClumsy: each round, 50% chance to drop each held object; if holding nothing, 50% chance it can’t act that round\nThe curse remains until removed by remove curse, dispelled, or revoked by the caster.\nOptional rule: some religions may have alternative curses (cult secrets, lost secrets, forbidden secrets), learned through donations, service, research, extraplanar consultation, or major quests (GM decides availability and effects).","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Bestow Curse"},"cleric cause blindness":{"name":"Cause Blindness","level":"3","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"8 segments","save":"Yes (negates effect)","save_type":"","description":"Cure Blindness\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Cause Blindness\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nBy touching the afflicted creature, the cleric can permanently cure most forms of blindness. The reverse, cause blindness, requires a successful touch upon the victim. If the victim then makes the saving throw, the effect is negated.","notes":"Causes a target to become blind until removed by the caster, dispelled, or cured by cure blindness.\nDetails:\n    If you miss the to-hit roll, the spell is lost.\n    Affects only living creatures (not undead) and has no effect on creatures that do not rely on vision.\n    Many good-aligned religions forbid this spell; others allow it only in dire need.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Cause Blindness"},"cleric cause disease":{"name":"Cause Disease","level":"3","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"10 rounds","save":"Negates effect","save_type":"","description":"Cure Disease\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Cause Disease\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThe cleric cures most diseases, including parasitic, bacterial, and viral diseases, by placing their hand upon the diseased creature. The affliction rapidly disappears thereafter, making the creature whole and well in from 1 turn to 1 week, depending on the disease and its advancement when cured. The reverse, cause disease, requires the cleric to touch the intended victim, who must then fail a saving throw. The disease begins to affect the victim in 1d6 turns, causing the creature to lose 1 hit point per turn and 1 point of Strength per hour until reduced to 10% of original hit points and Strength, at which point the creature is weak and virtually helpless.","notes":"Infects the target with a disease.\nDetails:\n    Requires touch (to-hit roll if resisting and not immobilised). Even on a successful touch, the target saves vs spells; success negates.\n    Affects only normally living creatures; no effect on constructs, elementals, golems, undead.\n    Takes effect 1d6 turns after casting. After it takes effect:\n        The target takes 1 hp disease damage every turn (10 rounds). Each time it takes this damage, its maximum hp is reduced by 1. This damage cannot reduce it below 1 hp, and cannot reduce maximum hp below 8 hp.\n        Every hour after it takes effect, the target suffers -1 cumulative to attack rolls and damage rolls (cannot reduce damage below 1).\n    You may end the spell at any time; if you die, the target is cured.\n    Many good-aligned religions forbid this spell; others allow it only in dire need.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Cause Disease"},"cleric continual darkness":{"name":"Continual Darkness","level":"3","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"120 ft","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Globe, 60 ft radius","components":"V, S","ct":"6 segments","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"Continual Light\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Continual Darkness\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6” radius globe\nThis spell is similar to light, except it lasts until negated by continual darkness or dispel magic, and its brightness is very great, nearly equal to full daylight. It may be cast into the air, onto an object, or at a creature. If cast at a creature and the creature makes its saving throw, the spell affects the space about 1 foot behind the creature. This spell can blind a creature if successfully cast upon the visual organs. The reverse causes complete absence of light.","notes":"Creates divine darkness emanating from the target (creature, object, or point in space). Light—including sunlight—does not illuminate anything within 60 ft of the target.\nDetails:\n    If cast into an area of magical light (e.g., within a light spell radius), both spells are cancelled.\n    Darkness is stationary unless cast on a moving creature/object, in which case it moves with the target.\n    You may target a creature’s eyes or other sense organs. If it fails its save (or declines to save), it is blinded for the duration. The creature applies its Dexterity save modifier (if any) to the saving throw.\n        Success: Darkness appears as a stationary point just behind the target instead of affecting it.\n    Same limitations as continual light (max 3 concurrent instances; monthly 1-in-12 chance to end).\n    Optional rule: some GMs allow infravision to see through divine darkness (cleric-slot darkness only).","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Continual Darkness"},"cleric continual light":{"name":"Continual Light","level":"3","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"120 ft","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Globe, 60 ft radius","components":"V, S","ct":"6 segments","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"Continual Light\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Continual Darkness\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6” radius globe\nThis spell is similar to light, except it lasts until negated by continual darkness or dispel magic, and its brightness is very great, nearly equal to full daylight. It may be cast into the air, onto an object, or at a creature. If cast at a creature and the creature makes its saving throw, the spell affects the space about 1 foot behind the creature. This spell can blind a creature if successfully cast upon the visual organs. The reverse causes complete absence of light.","notes":"Creates divine light illuminating the target (creature, object, or point in space) and a 60 ft radius around it.\nDetails:\n    If cast into an area of magical darkness, both light and darkness are cancelled.\n    Light is stationary unless cast on a moving creature/object, in which case it moves with the target.\n    If targeted on a creature’s eyes or other sense organs, the creature may save vs spells, applying its Dexterity save modifier (if any).\n        Success: Light appears as a stationary glow just behind the target instead of affecting it.\n        Failure: Target is effectively blinded until the spell ends or is dispelled.\n    You cannot have more than three instances of continual light active at once. Casting again ends your earliest still-active instance.\n    At the end of every complete month the spell has been running, there is a 1-in-12 chance it ends.\nReversible as Continual Darkness:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Continual Light"},"cleric create food and water":{"name":"Create Food and Water","level":"3","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"10 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"See below","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Create Food & Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per level\nWhen this spell is cast, the cleric causes food and/or water to appear. The food is highly nourishing, and each cubic foot sustains three human-sized creatures or one horse-sized creature for a full day. The spell creates 1 cubic foot of food and/or water per caster level. For example, a 2nd-level cleric creates 2 cubic feet, a 3rd-level cleric creates 3 cubic feet, a 4th-level cleric creates 4 cubic feet, and so on. The created volume may be divided between food and water.","notes":"Conjures basic food and water from thin air. You choose the form of the food, but it is plain fare.\nDetails:\n    Food is safe when conjured but spoils normally thereafter.\n    For each cleric level, you conjure up to one day’s rations for one human-sized creature.\n    The target point can’t be inside a creature.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Create Food and Water"},"cleric cure blindness":{"name":"Cure Blindness","level":"3","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Blindness\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Cause Blindness\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nBy touching the afflicted creature, the cleric can permanently cure most forms of blindness. The reverse, cause blindness, requires a successful touch upon the victim. If the victim then makes the saving throw, the effect is negated.","notes":"Cures blindness in one living creature, subject to limitations. Typically only effective for magically induced blindness (e.g., curses, cause blindness).\nDetails:\n    Restores sight only to the extent the creature’s eyes allow; it does not repair destroyed/damaged eyes. A creature whose eyes were put out gains no benefit.\n    Does not cure blindness that exists in the mind (e.g., believing it is blind due to an illusion); does not remove hallucinations from false seeing.\n    Does not remove environmental obstruction (fog/darkness), though it does remove light or continual light cast on the eyes.\nReversible as Cause Blindness:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Cure Blindness"},"cleric cure disease":{"name":"Cure Disease","level":"3","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Disease\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Cause Disease\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThe cleric cures most diseases, including parasitic, bacterial, and viral diseases, by placing their hand upon the diseased creature. The affliction rapidly disappears thereafter, making the creature whole and well in from 1 turn to 1 week, depending on the disease and its advancement when cured. The reverse, cause disease, requires the cleric to touch the intended victim, who must then fail a saving throw. The disease begins to affect the victim in 1d6 turns, causing the creature to lose 1 hit point per turn and 1 point of Strength per hour until reduced to 10% of original hit points and Strength, at which point the creature is weak and virtually helpless.","notes":"Cures all diseases affecting the target (see details). Full recovery may take up to a week.\nDetails:\n    Stops the “will die in X days” progression immediately; the target is no longer at risk of dying from disease, even if not yet back to full strength.\n    Cures physical pathologies and removes physical parasites. Does not cure genetic conditions/birth defects; affects mental health only insofar as curing underlying pathology/parasites helps.\n    Affects only normally living creatures; no effect on constructs, elementals, golems, undead.\n    Cures lycanthropy only if cast before the first transformation. After first change, lycanthropy becomes a mixed disease/curse/magical alteration.\n    The target may choose a saving throw vs spells and other effects; on a success, one or more diseases of its choice are not cured.\n    Has certain special uses that cure non-disease effects in specific OSRIC creature/object entries.\nReversible as Cause Disease:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Cure Disease"},"cleric dispel magic":{"name":"Dispel Magic","level":"3","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"60 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"30 ft radius sphere","components":"V, S","ct":"6 segments","save":"No (but see below for failure chance)","save_type":"","description":"Dispel Magic\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” cube\nWhen a cleric casts dispel magic, it neutralizes or negates magic it contacts. It does not affect specially enchanted items such as scrolls, rings, wands, rods, staves, miscellaneous magic items, magic weapons, magic shields, or magic armor. It destroys magic potions, which are treated as 12th level for this spell, removes spells cast upon persons or objects, and counters spellcasting within the area of effect. The base chance of success is 50%. For each caster level above the level of the creature or object whose magic is being dispelled, the chance increases by 5%, up to 100% at a 10-level difference. For each caster level below the target’s level or efficiency level, the chance is reduced by 2%. This spell can be very effective against charmed or similarly beguiled creatures. It automatically negates the caster’s own magic.","notes":"Removes or suppresses magical effects in the area. The centre point may be a creature, object, place, or point in space within range.\nDetails:\n    Gods, demigods, artifacts, relics, and equivalent powers are not affected.\n    Psychic/psionic powers are not magical and are not affected.\n    When casting completes:\n        Any ongoing spell effects in the area that you personally cast end.\n        If a creature in the area is currently casting a spell, that spell is interrupted.\n    Then, for each dispellable magical effect in the area, the GM rolls d100 (often in secret). Success chance depends on caster levels:\n        If your cleric level is ≥ the effect’s caster level: 50% + 5% per level difference.\n        If your cleric level is < the effect’s caster level: 50% - 2% per level difference.\n        For potions/scrolls, caster level is 12 unless creation required higher; then use the minimum level to create it (e.g., time stop scroll is caster level 18).\n    On a successful dispel of an effect:\n        Spell effects wholly within the area end (including innate spell-like powers and item-cast spell effects).\n        If only partly overlapped, the spell does not end, but the overlapped portion is suppressed for 1 hour.\n        Potions/scrolls are denatured (potions become inert liquid; scrolls become blank).\n        Permanent magic items have their powers suppressed for 1 round (become non-magical for that round).\n        Constructs/elementals/golems/summoned creatures are not banished, but may temporarily lose spell/spell-like powers; such powers return after 1d6 rounds.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Dispel Magic"},"cleric feign death":{"name":"Feign Death","level":"3","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"10 rounds + 1 round per cleric level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Fast","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Feign Death\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 turn + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One person\nExcept as noted, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level magic-user spell feign death. A character of any level may be affected by the cleric version. Material Components: A pinch of graveyard dirt and the cleric’s holy or unholy symbol.","notes":"The target becomes corpse-like, enabling it to “play dead,” and gains protection from certain harms.\nDetails:\n    Only affects willing creatures. You or the target may end the spell at any time.\n    While affected:\n        No need to eat, drink, breathe, or sleep.\n        Can hear, smell, and think, but is blinded and loses sense of touch. Feels no pain and does not know when injured.\n        Immune to undead touch attacks; cannot be poisoned; cannot contract disease. Existing poison is suspended during the spell and returns afterward.\n        Damage from other sources is halved (round down).\n    When the spell ends, the target needs 1 round to stand and recover.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Feign Death"},"cleric glyph of warding":{"name":"Glyph of Warding","level":"3","school":"Divine evocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Until discharged","aoe":"Up to 25 sq. ft per cleric level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment per sq. ft protected","save":"When activated (save for half)","save_type":"","description":"Glyph of Warding\n\nSchool: Abjuration-Evocation\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Permanent until discharged\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 25 square feet per caster level\nA glyph of warding is a powerful magical inscription that prevents unauthorized or hostile creatures from passing, entering, or opening. It can guard a small bridge, ward an entry, or trap a chest or box. When cast, the cleric weaves faintly glowing lines around the warding sigil. Each square foot of protected area requires 1 segment to trace, plus the initial segment for tracing the sigil itself. A maximum area of 5’ × 5’ per caster level may be warded. When complete, the glyph and tracery become invisible. Any creature touching the protected area without first speaking the glyph’s name is subject to the stored magic. Saving throws either reduce the effect by half or negate it, depending on the glyph. Material Components: Incense for tracing the spell, plus powdered diamond worth at least 2,000 g.p. if the protected area exceeds 50 square feet. Typical glyphs shock for 2 points of electrical damage per caster level, explode for the same amount of fire damage, paralyze, blind, or even drain one life energy level if the cleric is high enough level to cast such a glyph.","notes":"You inscribe an invisible glyph on a solid surface. It remains invisible unless detect magic is used. A “forbidden creature” (as defined at casting) discharges the glyph when it performs a defined triggering action.\nDetails:\n    You must define:\n        A forbidden creature (e.g., “any living being,” “anyone but myself,” “a dwarf,” “Richard the Necrophage,” etc.).\n        A triggering action (typically opening a warded door or passing through a warded area).\n        The exact area to be warded.\n    When triggered, each creature in the area may save vs spells/spell-like effects:\n        Success: half damage and may disregard other glyph effects (if any).\n    You must know the specific glyph you’re using. Fire/lightning/ice/acid glyphs are secrets of clerical orders; blindness/paralysis are lost secrets; drain/petrify/banish are long-lost and widely forbidden, requiring major effort/quests to learn.\n    If warding more than 50 sq. ft, gems worth 2,000 gp must be destroyed as a material component.\n    You can only use glyph types permitted by your cleric level:\nMinimum Cleric Level\tGlyph\tNoise\tEffect\n3\tFire\tNoisy\t2 hp fire damage per cleric level\n5\tLightning\tLoud\t2 hp lightning damage per cleric level\n7\tIce\tQuiet\t2 hp cold damage per cleric level\n9\tAcid\tQuiet\t2 hp corrosion damage per cleric level\n11\tBlindness\tSilent\tSave or blinded for 3d6 rounds\n13\tParalysis\tSilent\tSave or paralysed for 2d6 rounds\n15\tDrain\tSilent\tSave or lose 1 life energy level\n17\tPetrify\tSilent\tSave or turned to stone\n20\tBanish\tSilent\tSave or sent to deity-associated plane","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Glyph of Warding"},"cleric locate object":{"name":"Locate Object","level":"3","school":"Divine divination","range":"Caster","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"Path 10 ft wide originating from you; length 60 ft + 10 ft per cleric level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Locate Object\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Obscure Object\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell helps locate a known or familiar object. The cleric casts the spell, slowly turns, and knows when they are facing the direction of the object, provided it is within range: 7” for a 1st-level cleric, 8” for a 2nd-level cleric, 9” for a 3rd-level cleric, and so on. The spell can locate objects such as apparel, jewelry, furniture, tools, weapons, ladders, or stairways. The reverse, obscure object, hides an object from detection by spell, crystal ball, or similar means. Neither version affects living creatures. Material Component: A piece of lodestone.","notes":"You visualise an object (general or specific). If an object fitting the description is within the pathway-shaped area of effect (often after turning in place), you learn the exact distance to the nearest matching object. Once located, the spell ends.\nDetails:\n    Opaque materials do not interfere; you can perceive the target through solid rock.\n    Target must be an object, not a creature or place.\n    Only locates the nearest matching object; does not locate objects on other planes.\n    Provides location/distance, not safe route or terrain details.\n    You must be able to visualise the object: you are “familiar” with its form, function, and material.\n    Requires concentration; if broken, the spell ends.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Locate Object"},"cleric prayer":{"name":"Prayer","level":"3","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Nil","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"60 ft radius","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Prayer\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6” radius\nThis spell duplicates the effects of chant regarding bonuses and penalties: friendly creatures gain +1 on attacks and saving throws, while enemies suffer -1 on similar rolls. Unlike chant, once prayer is uttered, the cleric may do other things and need not continue chanting. Material Component: A silver holy symbol, prayer beads, or a similar device.","notes":"The target location is where you stand when casting completes. Until the spell ends, within the area:\n    You and your allies may choose to gain +1 to attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws.\n    Enemies suffer -1 to attack rolls, damage rolls, and saving throws.\nDetails:\n    Cumulative with chant despite similarity.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Prayer"},"cleric remove curse":{"name":"Remove Curse","level":"3","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One creature, object, or place","components":"V, S","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Remove Curse\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Bestow Curse\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell usually removes a curse from an object, person, undesired sending, or evil presence. It does not affect a cursed shield, weapon, or suit of armor directly, though it typically enables the afflicted person to get rid of such an item. The reverse, bestow curse, is not permanent and lasts 1 turn per caster level. It lowers one randomly selected ability score to 3 half the time; reduces the victim’s “to hit” and saving throw probabilities by -4 one-quarter of the time; or gives the victim a 50% chance each turn to drop whatever they are holding, or do nothing if not using tools, one-quarter of the time. A cleric may devise another curse of similar power, subject to the referee. The target must be touched and receives a saving throw; success negates the curse.","notes":"Ends one curse on a target creature, object, or place.\nDetails:\n    Curses from gods/demigods/artifacts/relics are not affected.\n    Does not cure vampirism or lycanthropy.\n    If the target is a creature with multiple curses, you choose which curse ends.\n    If the target is a cursed object, the curse does not end, but a creature holding it is allowed to drop it and be free of it.\nReversible as Bestow Curse:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Remove Curse"},"cleric speak with dead":{"name":"Speak With Dead","level":"3","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"10 ft","duration":"Varies (see table)","aoe":"One corpse","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Speak With Dead\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell allows the cleric to ask several questions of a dead creature within a set period and receive answers according to the creature’s knowledge. The cleric must be able to converse in the language the dead creature used in life. The length of time the creature has been dead, the number of questions allowed, and the time available for questioning depend on the cleric’s level. Up to 7th level: dead up to 1 week, questioned for 1 round, 2 questions. 7th–8th level: dead up to 1 month, questioned for 3 rounds, 3 questions. 9th–12th level: dead up to 1 year, questioned for 1 turn, 4 questions. 13th–15th level: dead up to 10 years, questioned for 2 turns, 5 questions. 16th–20th level: dead up to 100 years, questioned for 3 turns, 6 questions. 21st level and up: dead up to 1,000 years, questioned for 6 turns, 7 questions. Material Components: A holy symbol and burning incense, cast upon the body, remains, or portion thereof.","notes":"Compels a corpse to answer questions aloud (others can hear). Duration, question limit, and maximum corpse age depend on your cleric level.\nLimitations by cleric level:\nCleric Level\tDuration\tMax Questions\tMax Time Since Death\n5–6\t1 round\t2\t1 week\n7–8\t3 rounds\t3\t1 month\n9–12\t1 turn\t4\t1 year\n13–15\t2 turns\t5\t1 decade\n16–19\t3 turns\t6\t1 century\n20\t1 hour\t7\t1 aeon\nDetails:\n    The corpse can only tell what it knew in life.\n    It only speaks languages it knew in life. If it doesn’t understand a question, it can say “I don’t understand,” and this still consumes one question.\n    The spell does not make it friendly. If it was hostile (especially if you killed it), it answers briefly and with minimal information.\n    Multi-part questions get only one part answered (corpse chooses which).\n    Ambiguous questions may be interpreted in any reasonable way (GM adjudication).\n    If the target is undead, it does not have to stop fighting while answering.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Speak With Dead"},"cleric blither":{"name":"Blither","level":"4","school":"Divine enchantment","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"Yes (negates effect)","save_type":"","description":"Noise: Casting quiet; effect quiet\nRenders a creature’s spoken words meaningless for the duration; it cannot communicate via speech.\nDetails:\n    Target may add its Wisdom saving throw modifier to the saving throw.\n    On failure, it can still gesture, write, and otherwise communicate.\n    The affected creature cannot cast spells with verbal components until the spell ends.","notes":"Noise: Casting quiet; effect quiet\nRenders a creature’s spoken words meaningless for the duration; it cannot communicate via speech.\nDetails:\n    Target may add its Wisdom saving throw modifier to the saving throw.\n    On failure, it can still gesture, write, and otherwise communicate.\n    The affected creature cannot cast spells with verbal components until the spell ends.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Blither"},"cleric cause serious wounds":{"name":"Cause Serious Wounds","level":"4","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Serious Wounds\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Cause Serious Wounds\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is a more potent version of cure light wounds. By laying a hand upon a creature, the cleric heals 3 to 17 hit points, or 2d8 + 1, of wound or injury damage. The healing affects only creatures listed in the cure light wounds explanation. The reverse, cause serious wounds, works similarly to cause light wounds: the victim must first be touched, and a successful touch inflicts 3 to 17 hit points of damage.","notes":"The touched target takes 2d8+1 hit points of magical damage, even if it can only be hit by magical weapons. Touching the target requires a successful to-hit roll; no saving throw is allowed.\nDetails:\nIf you miss the to-hit roll, no damage is inflicted and the spell is lost. This spell affects only naturally living creatures and does not affect golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Cause Serious Wounds"},"cleric cure serious wounds":{"name":"Cure Serious Wounds","level":"4","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Serious Wounds\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Cause Serious Wounds\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is a more potent version of cure light wounds. By laying a hand upon a creature, the cleric heals 3 to 17 hit points, or 2d8 + 1, of wound or injury damage. The healing affects only creatures listed in the cure light wounds explanation. The reverse, cause serious wounds, works similarly to cause light wounds: the victim must first be touched, and a successful touch inflicts 3 to 17 hit points of damage.","notes":"The target regains 2d8+1 hit points, up to its normal maximum. Any healing beyond the normal maximum is wasted.\nDetails:\nThis spell cannot cure disease, reattach limbs, raise the dead, or heal afflictions not measured in hit points; such effects require stronger magic. It generally affects only normally living creatures and has no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.\nReversible as Cause Serious Wounds:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Cure Serious Wounds"},"cleric detect lie":{"name":"Detect Lie","level":"4","school":"Divine divination","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"One creature you designate","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Lie\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Undetectable Lie\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One person\nWhen the cleric casts detect lie, the recipient can immediately determine whether truth is being spoken. The spell lasts 1 round per caster level. The reverse, undetectable lie, makes direct untruths seem reasonable or counters detect lie. Material Component: Gold dust for detect lie; brass dust for undetectable lie.","notes":"Cast upon a specific creature. For the duration, when that creature speaks, you know whether it is saying something it does not believe to be true.\nDetails:\nYour awareness of lies is not detectable by others. The spell affects only speech, not telepathy or writing. You can only detect lies you can hear. Lies spoken in languages you do not know are still detected as lies, but you will not know what was actually said.\nReversible as Glibness:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Detect Lie"},"cleric divination":{"name":"Divination","level":"4","school":"Divine divination","range":"Caster","duration":"1 round","aoe":"Caster","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Divination\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nSimilar to augury, this spell determines information about a known area, such as a small woods, large building, or section of a dungeon level. The spell reveals the relative strength of creatures in the area, whether treasure there is rich, moderate, or poor, and the relative chances of incurring the wrath of evil or good supernatural or super-powerful beings if the area is invaded and attacked. The base chance for correct divination is 60% plus 1% per caster level, such as 65% at 5th level and 66% at 6th level. The Dungeon Master adjusts this chance based on the facts of the area. If the result is not correct, inaccurate information is obtained. Material Components: A sacrificial creature, incense, and the cleric’s holy symbol. For unusually potent divinations, especially valuable gems, jewelry, and/or magic items may be required.","notes":"Gives information about a place via divination (bones, yarrow stalks, tea leaves, entrails, etc.). You may misinterpret the reading.\nDetails:\n    The divination must be about a place. You do not need to be there; you need only its approximate location. It cannot be about an object unless it is so large it counts as a place (e.g., a building).\n    The GM secretly rolls 1d6:\n        1–4: You interpret correctly.\n        5–6: You interpret incorrectly.\n    If you sacrifice a magical item as part of the divination, it is destroyed and the GM’s d6 roll is modified by -1. Artifacts, relics, and equivalent items cannot be sacrificed or destroyed by this spell.\n    The GM provides your character’s interpretation of:\n        Whether the place is sacred to a god/demigod/power, and which;\n        Whether creatures inhabit it;\n        Whether those creatures are weak/equivalent/strong compared to you;\n        Whether treasure is present; and\n        Whether the treasure is poor/medium/rich.\n    If you misinterpret, the GM answers randomly with a mixture of correct and incorrect information.\n    Some legendary places are specially warded; divination always misinterprets those places.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Divination"},"cleric exorcise":{"name":"Exorcise","level":"4","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"10 ft","duration":"Instantaneous (or continuing; see below)","aoe":"One creature, object, or place","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds, continuing","save":"Depends on use (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Exorcise\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1\nCasting Time: 1–100+ turns\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature or object\nThis spell negates possession of a creature or object by an outside or supernatural force. This includes control of a creature by a force in an object, possession by magic jar, demonic possession, curse, and even charm, since exorcise is similar to dispel magic. It may also affect a magical item if that item is the object of the exorcism. A successfully exorcised soul object causes the creature’s life force to wholly inhabit its nearest material body. Once begun, exorcise cannot be interrupted or it is spoiled and useless. The base chance for success is a random 1% to 100%. Each turn of exorcism, dice are rolled; if the base chance number or less is rolled, the spell succeeds. The base chance is modified by -1% for each level of difference when the cleric’s level is lower than the possessor or possessing magic, or +1% cumulatively when the cleric’s level is higher. The referee may determine the base chance according to circumstances. Material Components: The cleric’s holy object and holy water, or unholy object and unholy water for evil clerics. A religious artifact or relic may increase the chance of success by 1% to 50%, depending on its power.","notes":"A multi-purpose ritual to cast out a supernatural creature or influence (fiend, ghost, etc.) possessing a creature/object. It can also remove a curse or end a charm/enchantment. The casting and effect are loud.\nDetails:\nUsing the spell to remove curses / end charm or enchantment:\n    Automatically succeeds when you finish the first turn of casting.\n    Unwilling targets do not receive a saving throw for this use.\nUsing the spell to cast out supernatural creatures and influences:\n    On a good-aligned outer plane: automatically succeeds after the first turn.\n    On an evil-aligned outer plane: automatically fails.\n    Otherwise, each turn you continue casting, the creature/influence rolls a special saving throw on d20; failure means it is exorcised.\nSaving throws versus exorcism (base target numbers):\nCreature/Influence Strength\tBase Saving Throw\nWeak influence, dretch, spiked devil\t10\nModerate influence, class A demon, shub demon, bearded devil, erinyes, scaly devil\t8\nClass B demon, uduk demon, ekivu demon, ghost, succubus, barbed devil\t7\nClass C demon, babau demon, bone devil\t6\nStrong influence, class D demon, horned devil\t5\nClass E demon, ice devil, night hag\t4\nClass F demon, pit fiend, shaitan devil\t3\nModifiers:\n    Apply -1 to the creature’s saving throw for each cleric level you have above 8.\n    If you hold a relevant artifact/relic, the GM may assign an additional -1 to -4 modifier (based on strength/aptitude/inclination).\n    Magic resistance does not apply.\n    On a natural 20 on its saving throw, you suffer an ill effect (e.g., curse or loss of 1 point from a random ability score).\n    Cannot exorcise artifacts, relics, deities, or equivalent powers.\nEffect of exorcism:\nThe cast-out creature returns to its own body (or nearest body if it has several). If bodiless, it appears on the Prime Material Plane adjacent to the formerly possessed target (GM chooses or randomises if multiple possible).","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Exorcise"},"cleric glibness":{"name":"Glibness","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Counters detect lie on the target; if detect lie is not in effect, the target’s lies become more convincing.\nDetails:\n    A creature can only be affected by one instance of this spell at a time.\n    As with most targeted spells, you can cast it on yourself or another creature.\n    Lies are only believed if the listener can hear and understand them.\n    The GM determines plausibility; each listener then rolls a special saving throw on a d20 (optionally adding their Wisdom save modifier).\nSaving throw targets for Glibness:\nPlausibility\tSaving Throw Target\nLikely\t20\nPlausible\t18\nPossible\t15\nSurprising\t11\nUnlikely\t7\nObviously false\t2\nIf the listener passes, they do not believe the lie.","notes":"Counters detect lie on the target; if detect lie is not in effect, the target’s lies become more convincing.\nDetails:\n    A creature can only be affected by one instance of this spell at a time.\n    As with most targeted spells, you can cast it on yourself or another creature.\n    Lies are only believed if the listener can hear and understand them.\n    The GM determines plausibility; each listener then rolls a special saving throw on a d20 (optionally adding their Wisdom save modifier).\nSaving throw targets for Glibness:\nPlausibility\tSaving Throw Target\nLikely\t20\nPlausible\t18\nPossible\t15\nSurprising\t11\nUnlikely\t7\nObviously false\t2\nIf the listener passes, they do not believe the lie.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Glibness"},"cleric lower water":{"name":"Lower Water","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"120 ft","duration":"1 turn per cleric level","aoe":"Up to 10 ft square of surface area per cleric level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Lower Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Raise Water\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” × 1” square per level\nThe cleric causes water or similar fluid in the area of effect to sink away. The lowering is 5% of the original effect per caster level: 40% at 8th level, 45% at 9th, 50% at 10th, and so on. The spell lasts 1 turn per caster level. The area of effect also increases by level: an 8th-level cleric affects an 8” × 8” area, a 9th-level cleric affects a 9” × 9” area, and so forth. The reverse causes water or similar fluid to return to its normal highest level, plus 1 foot per caster level. Material Components: The cleric’s religious symbol and a pinch of dust.","notes":"Water in the affected area sinks by 5 ft. If you can affect the same area multiple times, you may lower it an additional 5 ft per iteration.\nExample: A 30 ft × 30 ft pool: you can affect a 30 ft square once per 3 cleric levels. At level 7–8 you can lower by 10 ft; 9–11 by 15 ft; 12–14 by 20 ft; etc.\nDisplaced water is held in a magical interdimensional space for the spell’s duration and returns when the spell ends (slightly chilled).\nDetails:\nTarget liquid must be non-magical and roughly water-like viscosity (blood might work; lava would not). If the target is a water creature (water weird/elemental), it is considered held unless the monster description says otherwise.\nReversible as Raise Water:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Lower Water"},"cleric neutralise poison":{"name":"Neutralise Poison","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"1 ft cube per 2 cleric levels, or one creature","components":"V, S","ct":"7 segments","save":"Depends on use (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Neutralize Poison\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Poison\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched or 1 cubic foot of substance per 2 levels\nBy means of neutralize poison, the cleric detoxifies any venom in the creature or substance touched. An unwilling opponent, such as a poisonous reptile, snake, or envenomed weapon’s wielder, requires the cleric to score a melee touch hit. The effect is permanent only for poison present at the time of the touch; creatures or objects that generate new poison are not permanently detoxified. The reverse, poison, also requires a successful touch attack. The victim then receives a saving throw versus poison; if unsuccessful, the victim is killed.","notes":"Purges venom/toxin/contaminant, rendering it harmless. Can potentially revive someone who has recently “died” from poison.\nDetails:\n    Does not affect disease-based contamination.\n    Gods/demigods/artifacts/relics/equivalent are not affected (GM may allow some derivative effects to be affected).\n    If targeting a toxic place, all toxins/contaminants are purged from the area.\nUsing the spell to de-venom an opponent:\n    If the target is a creature, it may choose a saving throw vs spells and other magical effects.\n        Success: not affected.\n        Failure: if it has a venomous attack, the venom component is nullified until dawn the next day.\nUsing the spell to revive someone “dead by poison”:\n    If the target is poisoned, all toxins are purged, but poison damage already taken remains.\n    Also works on creatures that have recently died of poison: death from poison damage or failed save vs poison within a number of turns equal to your cleric level.\nReversible as Poison:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Neutralise Poison"},"cleric poison":{"name":"Poison","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"1 ft cube per 2 cleric levels, including no more than one creature","components":"V, S","ct":"7 segments","save":"Depends on use (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Neutralize Poison\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Poison\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched or 1 cubic foot of substance per 2 levels\nBy means of neutralize poison, the cleric detoxifies any venom in the creature or substance touched. An unwilling opponent, such as a poisonous reptile, snake, or envenomed weapon’s wielder, requires the cleric to score a melee touch hit. The effect is permanent only for poison present at the time of the touch; creatures or objects that generate new poison are not permanently detoxified. The reverse, poison, also requires a successful touch attack. The victim then receives a saving throw versus poison; if unsuccessful, the victim is killed.","notes":"Your touch becomes deadly poison, or you can make an edible/potable substance poisonous. In either case, you must touch the target.\nDetails:\n    If targeting a creature, it may attempt a saving throw vs poison; success negates.\n    Creatures immune to poison are unaffected.\n    Gods/demigods/artifacts/relics/equivalent are unaffected.\n    If a creature fails its save: it dies.\n    If an edible/potable is poisoned: the first creature to consume must save vs poison or die (unless immune). After that save is resolved, remaining poison is nullified.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Poison"},"cleric protection from evil 10 ft radius":{"name":"Protection from Evil 10 Ft Radius","level":"4","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"10 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"10 ft radius around the creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Protection From Evil, 10’ Radius\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Protection From Good, 10’ Radius\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 20’ diameter sphere\nThis spell is identical to protection from evil, except it covers a much larger area and lasts longer. Material Component: The cleric must trace a 20-foot diameter circle using holy water or blood, incense or smoldering dung, according to the protection from evil spell.","notes":"Creates a 10 ft radius invisible barrier against evil and summoned creatures around the protected creature.\nDetails:\n    Cast on yourself or another willing creature; not on hostile creatures, objects, or places.\n    A creature can only be affected by one instance at a time. If already warded by the 1st-level protection from evil, this spell has no effect on it.\n    Effects within the warded area:\n        Evil creatures: -2 to attack rolls into the warded area; anyone inside gains +2 on saving throws caused by evil creatures or their effects.\n        Evil effects (rare): effects explicitly described as evil/fiendish/demonic/devilish allow +2 to saving throws.\n        Summoned/conjured creatures: cannot attack into the warded area by touch (claws, teeth, etc.), regardless of alignment. They only suffer the -2 penalty in (1) if they are evil. (A non-evil summoned creature could still attack with a long weapon if it can reach.)\n    Ghouls: additionally “kept at bay” (cannot reduce distance to the warded area), but if the warded area moves toward them, they need not retreat. Some GMs extend “kept at bay” beyond ghouls.\nReversible as Protection from Good 10 ft Radius:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Protection from Evil 10 Ft Radius"},"cleric protection from good 10 ft radius":{"name":"Protection from Good 10 Ft Radius","level":"4","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"10 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"10 ft radius around the creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Protection From Evil, 10’ Radius\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Protection From Good, 10’ Radius\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 20’ diameter sphere\nThis spell is identical to protection from evil, except it covers a much larger area and lasts longer. Material Component: The cleric must trace a 20-foot diameter circle using holy water or blood, incense or smoldering dung, according to the protection from evil spell.","notes":"Creates a 10 ft radius barrier against good-aligned and summoned creatures around the protected creature.\nDetails:\n    Same targeting limits and stacking limits as the evil version (and does not affect a creature already warded by 1st-level protection from good).\n    Effects:\n        Good creatures: -2 to attack rolls into the warded area; anyone inside gains +2 on saving throws caused by good creatures or their effects.\n        Holy effects (rare): effects explicitly described as “holy” allow +2 to saving throws.\n        Summoned/conjured creatures: cannot attack into the warded area by touch, regardless of alignment; only take the -2 penalty if actually good-aligned. (A non-good summoned creature could still attack with a long weapon if it can reach.)","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Protection from Good 10 Ft Radius"},"cleric raise water":{"name":"Raise Water","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"120 ft","duration":"1 turn per cleric level","aoe":"Up to 10 ft square of surface area per cleric level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Lower Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Raise Water\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” × 1” square per level\nThe cleric causes water or similar fluid in the area of effect to sink away. The lowering is 5% of the original effect per caster level: 40% at 8th level, 45% at 9th, 50% at 10th, and so on. The spell lasts 1 turn per caster level. The area of effect also increases by level: an 8th-level cleric affects an 8” × 8” area, a 9th-level cleric affects a 9” × 9” area, and so forth. The reverse causes water or similar fluid to return to its normal highest level, plus 1 foot per caster level. Material Components: The cleric’s religious symbol and a pinch of dust.","notes":"Water in the affected area rises by 5 ft. If you can affect the same area multiple times, you may raise it an additional 5 ft per iteration.\nDetails:\nAdditional water comes from the Elemental Plane of Water for the duration and returns when the spell ends (about room temperature). Target liquid must be non-magical and roughly water-like viscosity. If the target is a water creature (water weird/elemental), it is affected as if by an enlarge spell.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Raise Water"},"cleric snakes to sticks":{"name":"Snakes to Sticks","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"30 ft","duration":"2 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"10 ft cube","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"Yes (negates effect)","save_type":"","description":"Sticks To Snakes\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Snakes To Sticks\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic “\nThis spell allows the cleric to change 1 stick into a snake per caster level. For example, a 9th-level cleric can change 9 sticks into 9 snakes. The snakes attack as commanded by the cleric. There must be sticks or similar wood pieces, such as torches or spears, to transform. Magical items such as enchanted staves and spears are not affected. Only sticks within the area of effect are changed. The probability that each snake is venomous is 5% per caster level, such as 55% for an 11th-level cleric and 60% for a 12th-level cleric. The effect lasts 2 melee rounds per caster level. The reverse changes snakes to sticks for the appropriate duration or negates sticks to snakes according to the level of the countering cleric. For example, a 10th-level cleric casting the reverse can turn only 10 snakes back into sticks. Material Components: A small piece of bark and several snake scales.","notes":"Transforms ophidian creatures into sticks temporarily. Affects snakes, serpents, couatls, nagas, and similar; maximum of one creature per cleric level.\nDetails:\n    Targets may save vs spells and other magical effects; success negates.\n    If unclear, affected creatures include those listed above and other reptilian creatures that lacked limbs when hatched. Dragons, demons, devils, and wyverns are not “snakes” for this spell.\n    Some ophidian creatures are too large to fit in the area and cannot be affected.\n    While wood, snakes can be broken/burned/destroyed; if destroyed, they are dead when the spell ends.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Snakes to Sticks"},"cleric speak with plants":{"name":"Speak With Plants","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"One plant within range","components":"V, S","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Speak With Plants\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6” diameter circle\nThis spell enables the cleric to converse in rudimentary terms with all sorts of living vegetation. The cleric can question plants about whether creatures have passed through them, cause thickets to part for passage, require vines to entangle pursuers, and similar things. The spell does not animate non-ambulatory vegetation. Its power lasts 1 melee round per caster level, and all vegetation within the area of effect is under the spell’s command. Material Components: A drop of water, a pinch of dung, and a flame.","notes":"Lets you communicate with a nearby plant and understand its “speech.”\nDetails:\n    Only you hear the magical translation.\n    You speak in Common; the plant understands. It replies in its natural mode; the spell translates into your mind.\n    Some plants may be mobile/dangerous; you can bargain/persuade/deceive as appropriate.\n    GM decides what counts as a “plant.”\n    The plant usually won’t start combat until the spell ends, but if you/your allies attacked it in the last turn, it is not required to stop fighting.\n    Does not compel truth.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Speak With Plants"},"cleric sticks to snakes":{"name":"Sticks to Snakes","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"30 ft","duration":"2 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"10 ft cube; max 1 stick per cleric level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Sticks To Snakes\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Snakes To Sticks\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic “\nThis spell allows the cleric to change 1 stick into a snake per caster level. For example, a 9th-level cleric can change 9 sticks into 9 snakes. The snakes attack as commanded by the cleric. There must be sticks or similar wood pieces, such as torches or spears, to transform. Magical items such as enchanted staves and spears are not affected. Only sticks within the area of effect are changed. The probability that each snake is venomous is 5% per caster level, such as 55% for an 11th-level cleric and 60% for a 12th-level cleric. The effect lasts 2 melee rounds per caster level. The reverse changes snakes to sticks for the appropriate duration or negates sticks to snakes according to the level of the countering cleric. For example, a 10th-level cleric casting the reverse can turn only 10 snakes back into sticks. Material Components: A small piece of bark and several snake scales.","notes":"Transforms dead wood into serpents. The serpents do not understand speech, but obey mental commands to attack a target.\nFor each snake created, roll 1d20: if the result is ≤ your cleric level, the snake is venomous; otherwise it is a constrictor.\nDetails:\n    Affects roughly cylindrical dead-wood objects, up to a maximum number equal to your cleric level. Targets cannot be magical.\n    If you aren’t in a forest, bring your own sticks.\nVenomous Snake: AC 6, MV 90 ft, HD 2, #AT 1, Dmg 1 piercing, SA poison (save vs poison or die; apply CON modifier to save), Size S, AL N.\nConstrictor Snake: AC 6, MV 90 ft, HD 2, #AT 1, Dmg 1 blunt, SA constrict (on hit: constricts until it releases or is killed; one target at a time; may deal 1d4 blunt damage on its initiative instead of attacking), Size S, AL N.\nNo XP is awarded for killing/defeating snakes created by this spell.\nReversible as Snakes to Sticks:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Sticks to Snakes"},"cleric tongues":{"name":"Tongues","level":"4","school":"Divine divination","range":"Caster","duration":"1 turn","aoe":"30 ft radius around you","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Tongues\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Confuse Languages\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 turn\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6” diameter circle\nThis spell enables the cleric to speak the language of any creature inside the spell area, whether a racial tongue or alignment language. The reverse cancels tongues or confuses verbal communication of any sort within the area of effect.","notes":"Magically translates spoken language for you and translates your words for other creatures within the area.\nDetails:\n    Only you hear the translation of others’ speech, and only if spoken within the area.\n    Everyone in the area hears the translation of your words.\n    Spoken words only; writing and non-verbal communication are unaffected.\n    Creatures only understand you if they naturally speak at least one language.\nReversible as Blither:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Tongues"},"cleric atonement":{"name":"Atonement","level":"5","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Atonement\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One person\nThis spell removes the onus of unwilling or unknown deeds from the subject of the atonement. It also removes the effects of magical alignment change. The person receiving atonement must be either truly repentant or not in command of their own will so as to be capable of repentance. The referee judges this requirement and notes any past uses of the spell upon the person. Deliberate misdeeds and knowing, willful acts cannot be atoned for with this spell. Material Components: The cleric’s religious symbol, prayer beads, prayer wheel or prayer book, and burning incense.","notes":"You request forgiveness for the target’s past sins and transgressions. Any punishments imposed by gods or spirits are removed (see details). The spell can only be cast on a willing creature.\nDetails:\nThe spell ends without effect if:\n    Your alignment is chaotic and the target’s is lawful;\n    Your alignment is lawful and the target’s is chaotic;\n    Your alignment is good and the target’s is evil; or\n    Your alignment is evil and the target’s is good.\nIf the target’s transgressions were involuntary, unwilling, or unwitting, and the target is truly sorry, punishments are lifted unconditionally.\nIf the transgressions were involuntary, unwilling, or unwitting, and the target is not truly sorry, the gods/spirits assign a penance or quest; punishments are lifted when it is completed.\nIf the transgressions occurred while the target’s mind/brain was disturbed (charm, domination, mind control, possession), and the disturbance is ongoing, punishments are lifted unconditionally regardless of remorse, and the disturbance ends.\nIf the transgressions were voluntary but the target honestly believed they were for the greater good, the GM determines whether the repentance is accepted. If accepted, a penance/quest is assigned; punishments are lifted when it is completed.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Atonement"},"cleric cause critical wounds":{"name":"Cause Critical Wounds","level":"5","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Critical Wounds\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Cause Critical Wounds\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is a very potent version of cure light wounds. The cleric lays their hand upon a creature and heals 6 to 27 hit points, or 3d8 + 3, of wound or injury damage. The spell does not affect creatures excluded in the cure light wounds explanation. The reverse, cause critical wounds, works like other cause wounds spells and requires a successful touch to inflict 6 to 27 hit points of damage. Caused wounds heal as normal wounds do.","notes":"The touched target takes 3d8+3 magical damage, even if it can only be hit by magical weapons. Requires a successful to-hit roll; no saving throw allowed.\nDetails:\nIf you miss the to-hit roll, no damage is inflicted and the spell is lost. Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Cause Critical Wounds"},"cleric commune":{"name":"Commune","level":"5","school":"Divine divination","range":"Self","duration":"3 rounds","aoe":"You","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Commune\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nBy using commune, the cleric contacts their divinity or agents thereof and requests information in the form of questions answerable by “yes” or “no.” The cleric may ask one such question per caster level. The answers are correct. The referee will probably limit commune to once per adventure, once per week, or even once per month, since the gods dislike frequent interruptions. Material Components: The cleric’s religious symbol, holy or unholy water, and incense.","notes":"You pray for enlightenment; an invisible divine power answers your questions.\nDetails:\nGods/spirits that are pestered too often may choose not to respond.\nThe divine emissary knows what the gods/spirits you petition know. It is not omniscient, but its knowledge of the Prime Material Plane is likely excellent. It never lies.\nYou may ask one question per cleric level. Each must be asked promptly and respectfully or the emissary departs, ending the spell without further effect. Each answer is:\n“O [adjective] mortal, the answer to your question is…” followed by “yes”, “no”, “I don’t know”, or “it’s complicated”. The emissary may add an adjective before “mortal” (commonly “puny” or “insignificant”, but possibly “annoying”, “stupid”, etc. if patience wears thin).\nOnly you can hear the responses.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Commune"},"cleric cure critical wounds":{"name":"Cure Critical Wounds","level":"5","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Critical Wounds\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Cause Critical Wounds\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is a very potent version of cure light wounds. The cleric lays their hand upon a creature and heals 6 to 27 hit points, or 3d8 + 3, of wound or injury damage. The spell does not affect creatures excluded in the cure light wounds explanation. The reverse, cause critical wounds, works like other cause wounds spells and requires a successful touch to inflict 6 to 27 hit points of damage. Caused wounds heal as normal wounds do.","notes":"The target regains 3d8+3 hp, up to its normal maximum. Healing beyond maximum is wasted.\nDetails:\nDoes not cure disease, reattach limbs, raise the dead, or heal afflictions not measured in hit points. Generally affects only normally living creatures; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.\nReversible as Cause Critical Wounds:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Cure Critical Wounds"},"cleric dispel evil":{"name":"Dispel Evil","level":"5","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Yes (lessened effect)","save_type":"","description":"Dispel Evil\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Dispel Good\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell causes summoned creatures of evil nature, or monsters enchanted and caused to perform evil deeds, to return to their own plane or place. Examples include aerial servants, demons, devils, djinn, efreet, elementals, and invisible stalkers. While the spell lasts, creatures that could be affected by it attack the caster at a -7 penalty on “to hit” rolls. The reverse, dispel good, works against summoned or enchanted creatures of good alignment or creatures sent to aid good. Material Components: The cleric’s religious object and holy or unholy water.","notes":"Banishes an evil-aligned extraplanar creature. It disappears with an audible “pop”.\nDetails:\nTarget applies its Wisdom save modifier (if any) to the saving throw.\n    Fail save: banished to its home plane.\n    Pass save: not banished, but for the spell’s duration, whenever it attacks you with melee/missile/touch, you may choose to apply -7 to its attack roll.\nWorks only on evil creatures from other planes (demons, devils, efreets, etc.). The banished creature takes its carried/worn items, but no other creatures go with it even if it is carrying them.\nReversible as Dispel Good:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Dispel Evil"},"cleric dispel good":{"name":"Dispel Good","level":"5","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Yes (lessened effect)","save_type":"","description":"Dispel Evil\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Dispel Good\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell causes summoned creatures of evil nature, or monsters enchanted and caused to perform evil deeds, to return to their own plane or place. Examples include aerial servants, demons, devils, djinn, efreet, elementals, and invisible stalkers. While the spell lasts, creatures that could be affected by it attack the caster at a -7 penalty on “to hit” rolls. The reverse, dispel good, works against summoned or enchanted creatures of good alignment or creatures sent to aid good. Material Components: The cleric’s religious object and holy or unholy water.","notes":"Banishes a good-aligned extraplanar creature; it disappears with an audible “pop”.\nDetails:\nTarget applies its Wisdom save modifier (if any) to the saving throw.\n    Fail save: banished to its home plane.\n    Pass save: not banished, but for the spell’s duration, whenever it attacks you with melee/missile/touch, you may choose to apply -7 to its attack roll.\nWorks only on good extraplanar creatures (celestials, genies, etc.). The banished creature takes carried/worn items only.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Dispel Good"},"cleric false seeing":{"name":"False Seeing","level":"5","school":"Divine divination","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"120 ft radius around the touched creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Yes (negates effect)","save_type":"","description":"True Seeing\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: False Seeing\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 12” sight range\nWhen the cleric uses this spell, all things within the area of true seeing appear as they actually are. Secret doors become plain. The exact location of displaced things is obvious. Invisible, astral, and ethereal things become visible. Illusions and apparitions are seen through. Polymorphed, changed, or magicked things are apparent. Even creature auras become visible, allowing the cleric to know whether they are good, evil, or between. The reverse, false seeing, causes the recipient to see things falsely, such as rich as poor, rough as smooth, or beautiful as ugly. Material Component: For true seeing, an eye ointment made from very rare mushroom powder, saffron, and fat. For false seeing, an ointment made from oil, poppy dust, and pink orchid essence. Both ointments must be aged for 1d6 months.","notes":"Affects one creature: it suffers wild hallucinations, is blinded for the duration, and must make a morale check each round or flee screaming in a random direction.\nDetails:\nTarget adds its Wisdom save modifier to the saving throw.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: False Seeing"},"cleric flame strike":{"name":"Flame Strike","level":"5","school":"Divine evocation","range":"60 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Column, 5 ft radius; 30 ft high","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Yes (half damage)","save_type":"","description":"Flame Strike\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 1 segment\nSaving Throw: Half\nArea of Effect: 1” diameter by 3” high column\nWhen the cleric calls down flame strike, a column of fire roars downward at the exact location chosen by the caster. Any creature within the area of effect must make a saving throw. Failure means the creature takes 6d8 damage, or 6 to 48 hit points. Success means the creature takes 3d8 damage, or 3 to 24 hit points. Material Component: A pinch of sulphur.","notes":"Cast at a visible target point on the ground. A pillar of flame strikes; extremely loud (heard within 300 ft).\nDetails:\nCreatures in the area take 6d8 fire damage. If any fiends or celestials are in the area, they instead take 6d8 magical damage (not fire).\nCreatures may save vs spells/magical effects:\n    Pass: half damage; worn/carried items are undamaged.\n    Fail/decline: full damage; roll item saves vs fire for worn/carried objects.\nGM rolls saves vs fire for unattended objects in the area. In 5 ft squares, can hit up to 4 squares (target an intersection). Afterward, the area is charred/sooty with a lingering scent appropriate to the invoked power (incense, brimstone, etc.).","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Flame Strike"},"cleric insect plague":{"name":"Insect Plague","level":"5","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"360 ft","duration":"10 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"Column, 180 ft radius; 60 ft high","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Insect Plague\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 36”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 36” diameter, 6” high cloud\nThis spell summons a horde of creeping, hopping, and flying insects in a thick cloud. The insects obscure vision, limiting it to 3”. Creatures within the plague take 1 hit point of damage each melee round from bites and stings, regardless of armor class. The referee causes all creatures with fewer than 5 Hit Dice to check morale. Creatures with 2 or fewer Hit Dice automatically move at maximum speed in a straight line in a random direction until at least 24” away from the insect cloud. Creatures with fewer than 5 Hit Dice that fail morale behave likewise. Heavy smoke drives off insects within its bounds. Fire also drives insects away; a ring-shaped wall of fire keeps the plague outside its confines, but a fireball clears insects from its blast area for only 1 turn. Lightning and cold or ice act similarly. The plague lasts 1 turn per caster level, after which the insects disperse. The insects swarm in an area centered on a summoning point up to 36” from the cleric and do not move thereafter. The spell can be countered by casting dispel magic upon the summoning point. A cube of force keeps insects away from a character seeking the swarm’s center, but invisibility gives no protection. Material Components: A few grains of sugar, some kernels of grain, and a smear of fat.","notes":"Conjures a swarm of biting/stinging insects from a visible target point on the ground.\nDetails:\nIf you are level 18 or lower: mundane insects (wasps, clegs, midges, mosquitoes, biting locusts). Each round, at the start of the round, each creature in the area:\n    Takes 1 point piercing damage; and\n    Level 2 / 2 HD or less: must flee until at least 240 ft from the plague’s edge.\n    Level 4 / 4 HD or less: must check morale; on failure, flee until at least 120 ft from the edge.\nIf you are level 19 or higher: may conjure extraplanar insects. Each round, at the start of the round, each creature in the area:\n    Takes 2 points piercing damage; and\n    Level 4 / 4 HD or less: must flee until at least 240 ft from the edge.\n    Level 7 / 7 HD or less: must check morale; on failure, flee until at least 120 ft from the edge.\nOther details:\n    Fire/smoke holds back insects while it lasts (e.g., wall of fire works; fireball/flame strike only clears briefly).\n    Insects can pass through tiny spaces but not impenetrable barriers (can pass through blade barrier/wall of thorns; not wall of force).\n    Insects will not enter water; fully submerged creatures at start of round take no damage.\n    Creatures immune to mundane weapons are unaffected, regardless of HD.\n    Visibility inside is 30 ft.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Insect Plague"},"cleric plane shift":{"name":"Plane Shift","level":"5","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creatures touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Depends on use (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Plane Shift\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched, special\nWhen plane shift is cast, the cleric moves themselves or another creature to another plane of existence. The recipient remains on the new plane until sent away by similar means. If several persons link hands in a circle, up to seven can be affected at once. An unwilling victim must be touched and receives a saving throw; success negates the spell. Material Component: A small, forked metal rod whose exact size and metal type determine the plane reached, as determined by the referee.","notes":"Transports either:\n    One unwilling creature, or\n    Up to 7 willing creatures holding hands in a circle, plus optionally the caster,\n    to an Outer Plane.\nIf the creature is native to an Outer Plane, it returns to its origin plane; otherwise the caster chooses which Outer Plane it is sent to.\nDetails:\nIf you touch an unwilling creature, it may attempt a saving throw vs spells/magical effects, adding its Wisdom save modifier. On success, the spell does not affect it.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Plane Shift"},"cleric quest":{"name":"Quest","level":"5","school":"Divine enchantment","range":"60 ft","duration":"Until completed","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Yes (negates effect)","save_type":"","description":"Quest\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Until fulfilled\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell requires the affected creature to perform a service and return to the cleric with proof of completion. A quest may require locating and returning an important or valuable object, rescuing a notable person, freeing a creature, capturing a stronghold, slaying a person, delivering an item, and similar deeds. If the quest is not properly followed because of disregard, delay, or perversion, the affected creature loses 1 from saving throw dice for each day of such action. This penalty is not removed until the quest is properly discharged or the cleric cancels it. Certain circumstances may temporarily suspend, discharge, or cancel a quest, as determined by the Dungeon Master. Material Component: The cleric’s religious symbol.","notes":"Sets a quest a target creature is compelled to perform. Target must be human, demi-human, or humanoid.\nDetails:\nTarget may save vs spells/other effects, adding Wisdom save modifier. On success, spell ends without effect.\nQuest limitations:\n    Cannot be one that would change the target’s alignment if completed.\n    Must be within the target’s power.\n    Must be possible to complete within a year and a day.\nEnding conditions:\n    You can end it at any time.\n    Any cleric higher level than you can end it by touching the target and willing it to end.\n    Ends when the target returns with proof of completion (or, if it doesn’t know where you are, to the casting location), or when the target dies, or when completion becomes impossible (target of assassination dies; object to retrieve is destroyed; etc.).\nPenalty for procrastination:\nFor each 24 hours the target avoids the quest, it takes a cumulative -1 to all saving throws (periods need not be continuous). Normal daily maintenance is allowed as long as it is acting in good faith toward the quest.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Quest"},"cleric raise dead":{"name":"Raise Dead","level":"5","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"30 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One corpse or undead creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"Depends on use (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Raise Dead\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Slay Living\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One person\nThis spell restores life to a dwarf, gnome, half-elf, halfling, or human. The time since death matters: the cleric can raise a person dead up to 1 day per caster level, such as up to 9 days for a 9th-level cleric. The body must be whole; missing parts remain missing when the person is restored. The raised person must make a special saving throw to survive the ordeal, based on Constitution. The raised person is weak and helpless and must rest in bed for 1 full day per day they were dead. The reverse, slay living, allows the victim a saving throw. If successful, the victim takes only the damage of cause serious wounds, or 3 to 17 hit points. Evil clerics may freely use the reverse. Good clerics must use extreme caution and be absolutely certain the victim is evil and that death is necessary and for good, or the cleric’s alignment will be sharply changed. Newly made undead, excluding skeletons, that fall within the allowed death-time limit are affected by raise dead. The spell causes them to become resurrected dead if Constitution permits survival; otherwise, they are simply dead. Somatic Component: A pointed finger.","notes":"Returns a recently killed person to life, or can be used to kill some undead with physical bodies (works on zombies, not ghosts).\nDetails:\n    Can only raise if death occurred within 1 day per cleric level. (You can still use it to kill an undead that died longer ago.)\n    Body must be sufficiently intact (missing head/heart causes failure).\n    The slain creature must pass a Resurrection Success roll based on Constitution (table 1.1.4a). Failure means no return.\n    Returned creature remembers dying but not the time spent dead.\n    Unless the GM rules otherwise: works on humans, half-elves, gnomes, dwarfs, halflings; not elves or half-orcs.\n    Returned creature has 1 hp, is weak/sick, and cannot fight/cast/work until bed rest of 1 full day per day dead.\n    Missing body parts remain missing.\nIf the target is an undead creature (with a physical body):\nIt saves vs spells/other magical effects.\n    Pass: takes 2d8+1 corrosion damage; no other effect.\n    Fail: returned to life if it died recently enough; otherwise it crumbles to dust.\n    A lich, or a vampire older than a century, automatically passes this saving throw.\nReversible as Slay Living:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Raise Dead"},"cleric slay living":{"name":"Slay Living","level":"5","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"30 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Yes (negates effect)","save_type":"","description":"Raise Dead\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Slay Living\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One person\nThis spell restores life to a dwarf, gnome, half-elf, halfling, or human. The time since death matters: the cleric can raise a person dead up to 1 day per caster level, such as up to 9 days for a 9th-level cleric. The body must be whole; missing parts remain missing when the person is restored. The raised person must make a special saving throw to survive the ordeal, based on Constitution. The raised person is weak and helpless and must rest in bed for 1 full day per day they were dead. The reverse, slay living, allows the victim a saving throw. If successful, the victim takes only the damage of cause serious wounds, or 3 to 17 hit points. Evil clerics may freely use the reverse. Good clerics must use extreme caution and be absolutely certain the victim is evil and that death is necessary and for good, or the cleric’s alignment will be sharply changed. Newly made undead, excluding skeletons, that fall within the allowed death-time limit are affected by raise dead. The spell causes them to become resurrected dead if Constitution permits survival; otherwise, they are simply dead. Somatic Component: A pointed finger.","notes":"You speak an Abominable Word and point at a creature. Target may save vs spells/magical effects.\n    Pass: takes 2d8+1 corrosion damage; no other effect.\n    Fail: dies instantly.\nDetails:\nIn some campaigns, Abominable Words are lost secrets obtainable only through ancient lore, extraplanar consultation, or certain liches. Unless the GM rules otherwise, works on humans, half-elves, gnomes, dwarfs, halflings; not elves or half-orcs.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Slay Living"},"cleric true seeing":{"name":"True Seeing","level":"5","school":"Divine divination","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"120 ft radius around the touched creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"True Seeing\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: False Seeing\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 12” sight range\nWhen the cleric uses this spell, all things within the area of true seeing appear as they actually are. Secret doors become plain. The exact location of displaced things is obvious. Invisible, astral, and ethereal things become visible. Illusions and apparitions are seen through. Polymorphed, changed, or magicked things are apparent. Even creature auras become visible, allowing the cleric to know whether they are good, evil, or between. The reverse, false seeing, causes the recipient to see things falsely, such as rich as poor, rough as smooth, or beautiful as ugly. Material Component: For true seeing, an eye ointment made from very rare mushroom powder, saffron, and fat. For false seeing, an ointment made from oil, poppy dust, and pink orchid essence. Both ointments must be aged for 1d6 months.","notes":"Target sees things as they truly are within the area: detects illusions/displacements (and may choose to see through them), perceives astral/ethereal beings, hidden/secret things, sees alignment auras, recognizes polymorph/shapechange (and may choose to see true or altered form), and sees through darkness/bright light/fog/mist.\nDetails:\nGods and god-like beings, artifacts, and relics may produce effects immune to this spell.\nReversible as False Seeing:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: True Seeing"},"cleric aerial servant":{"name":"Aerial Servant","level":"6","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"10 ft","duration":"1 day per cleric level","aoe":"Nil","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Aerial Servant\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 1 day per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons an invisible aerial servant to do the cleric’s bidding. The creature does not fight, but it obeys commands to find and return with a described object or creature, provided it can physically bring that object or creature to the cleric or the cleric’s assign. The spell lasts up to 1 day per caster level. The aerial servant returns to its own plane when the spell ends, its duty is fulfilled, it is dispelled, the cleric releases it, or the cleric is slain. The cleric must have protection from evil, be within a magic circle, thaumaturgic triangle, or pentagram, or have a religious symbol, artifact, or relic to control the servant. Otherwise, the creature slays its summoner and returns to its plane. On a mission, the aerial servant attacks by complete surprise and gains 4 free melee rounds unless the target can detect invisible objects. If the target can detect invisible objects, roll 1d6: 1 = 1 free round, 2 = 2 free rounds, 3 = 3 free rounds, 4 = 4 free rounds, and 5–6 = no free rounds. Each round, the aerial servant must roll to hit. A hit means it has grabbed the item or creature it was sent to retrieve. If a creature is grabbed, compare the aerial servant’s Strength to the creature’s Strength. If the creature has no Strength rating, roll the appropriate Hit Dice for both; the higher total is stronger.","notes":"Summons an aerial servant (invisible elemental being) and binds it to your service. Unless you or it travels to another plane, it magically knows the direction and distance to both the summoning location and your current location.\nDetails:\n    Spell fails unless you are on the Prime Material, Elemental Plane of Air, Ethereal, or Astral plane.\n    It cannot speak and knows no languages, but understands your spoken commands via the spell.\n    It hates being controlled; the spell compels strict obedience.\n    It does not have to obey:\n        commands that are obviously self-destructive, or\n        commands to attack a creature.\n    The servant is dismissed (spell ends) when: it is killed; you are killed; you dismiss it; you leave the plane of casting; or it leaves that plane.\n    Not evil, but it cannot cross Protection from Evil or a magic circle, and must recoil from a holy symbol held out by a cleric or paladin.\n    Nothing prevents it from attacking you; best practice is to stand protected until commands are complete.\n    If its mission can’t be completed, the spell ends; it is no longer commanded and will usually return and attack you.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Aerial Servant"},"cleric animate object":{"name":"Animate Object","level":"6","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"One object up to 1 cubic foot per cleric level","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Animate Object\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per level\nThis spell imbues inanimate objects with mobility and a semblance of life. The animated object or objects attack whomever or whatever the cleric first designates. Objects may be made of any material: wood, metal, stone, fabric, leather, ceramic, glass, and so on. Movement speed depends on propulsion and weight. A heavy wooden table may move quickly on its legs; a rug slithers; a jar rolls. Examples include a large stone pedestal rocking forward at 1” per round, a stone statue moving at 4” per round, a wooden statue at 8” per round, and a light ivory stool at 12” per round. Slithering movement is about 1” to 2” per round, and rolling movement is 3” to 6” per round. Damage depends on form and composition. Light, supple objects can obscure vision, obstruct movement, bind, trip, smother, and similar effects. Light, hard objects can fall or strike for 1–2 hit points of damage, or obstruct and trip. Hard, medium-weight objects can crush or strike for 2–8 damage, with larger and heavier objects dealing 3–12, 4–16, or even 5–20 damage. Attack frequency depends on locomotion, appendages, and attack method, ranging from once every 5 melee rounds to once per melee round. Armor class depends on material and movement ability. Damage taken depends on the weapon and object struck: sharp cutting weapons work well against fabric, leather, wood, and similar substances, while heavy smashing and crushing weapons are useful against wood, stone, and metal objects. The referee determines these factors and how much damage the object can sustain before destruction. The cleric may animate 1 cubic foot of material per caster level. For example, a 14th-level cleric can animate one or more objects whose total solid volume does not exceed 14 cubic feet, such as a large statue, two rugs, three chairs, or a dozen average crocks.","notes":"Infuses a spirit into an inanimate object, which becomes a temporary creature that obeys you. When the spell ends, it becomes inanimate again; damage it took remains.\nDetails:\n    No self-preservation; obeys all commands even if self-destructive.\n    Statblock is “animated object” in the OSRIC GM Guide.\n    If the object is too large, spell ends without effect and the slot is still used.\n    Cannot speak/knows no languages; understands your spoken commands via the spell.\n    Spell ends if the animated object is killed; you are killed; you dismiss it; or you leave the plane of casting.\n    Commanding it does not take your combat action, but in any round you give it a command you can’t cast spells with a verbal component.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Animate Object"},"cleric blade barrier":{"name":"Blade Barrier","level":"6","school":"Divine evocation","range":"30 ft","duration":"3 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"Sphere of radius 5/10/15/20 ft around a visible target point","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Blade Barrier\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 3 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a wall of circling, razor-sharp blades that whirl and flash around an immobile point. Any creature attempting to pass through the blade barrier takes 8d8 damage, or 8 to 64 hit points. The barrier remains for 3 melee rounds per caster level. It can cover an area as small as 5 feet square or as large as 2” square, meaning 20’ × 20’ underground or 60’ × 60’ outdoors.","notes":"Creates a stationary sphere of whirling blades around the target point; radius chosen at casting and cannot be changed.\nDetails:\n    Blades cannot penetrate rock or brick; they do not appear in those portions of the area.\n    Ends if you are killed or you dismiss it.\n    Blades are not magical; creatures only hittable by magical weapons take no damage.\n    Contact damage: 8d8 slashing, no attack roll, no save. Triggered when:\n        a creature enters or reaches through from either side,\n        the barrier appears on a creature,\n        a creature remains in it (damage at start of each round).\n    Barrier is narrow; standing adjacent is safe, but melee attacks through it cause damage.\n    Physical missiles/projectiles through it: -3 to attack roll. Magical/energy attacks do not take this penalty.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Blade Barrier"},"cleric conjure animals":{"name":"Conjure Animals","level":"6","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"30 ft","duration":"2 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"Up to 1 creature per cleric level (varies by strength chosen)","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Conjure Animals\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell summons one or more mammals to the cleric’s locale to attack the cleric’s opponents. The conjured animals remain for 2 melee rounds per caster level or until slain. The cleric may call one or more mammals whose total Hit Dice do not exceed the cleric’s level. For example, a 12th-level cleric may conjure one 12-Hit-Die mammal, two 6-Hit-Die mammals, three 4-Hit-Die mammals, four 3-Hit-Die mammals, six 2-Hit-Die mammals, or twelve 1-Hit-Die mammals. For every +1 hit point in a creature’s Hit Dice, count ¼ Hit Die; thus, a 4 + 3 Hit Dice creature counts as 4¾ Hit Dice. The summoned creatures unfailingly attack the opponents of the cleric who cast the spell.","notes":"Conjures animal allies at a visible target point. You choose desired strength (Weak/Medium/Strong/Mighty); stronger types yield fewer animals. GM rolls/chooses what appears.\nWeak — 1 per cleric level\n1–3 Baboon; 4–9 Dog; 10–16 Giant rat; 17–20 Jackal\nMedium — 1 per 2 cleric levels (round down)\n1–4 Badger; 5–14 Herd animal; 15–20 Horse\nStrong — 1 per 3 cleric levels (round down)\n1–2 Boar; 3–5 Camel; 6–7 Giant goat; 8–9 Horse; 10–11 Hyena; 12–13 Leopard; 14–15 Phorusrhacid (Axe Beak); 16–17 Stag; 18–20 Wolf\nMighty — 1 per 4 cleric levels (round down)\n1–3 Ape; 4–5 Bear; 6–7 Boar; 8–9 Bull; 10–12 Dire wolf; 13–14 Leopard; 15–16 Lion; 17–18 Sabretooth tiger; 19–20 Tiger\nDetails:\n    Spell fails unless on the Prime Material Plane.\n    Animals understand your spoken commands; need not obey self-destructive commands.\n    Ends when all are killed; you are killed; you dismiss them; you leave the plane of casting; or they leave that plane.\n    No XP for defeating them.\n    VTT spacing: GM may place; typical approach is one per unoccupied square in/adjacent to the target point. If no space, an animal appears later when space opens; duration extends accordingly for late arrivals.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Conjure Animals"},"cleric find the path":{"name":"Find The Path","level":"6","school":"Divine divination","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per cleric level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Find The Path\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Lose The Path\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell enables the cleric to find the shortest and most direct route sought, whether to, from, or out of a locale. The locale may be outdoors, underground, a trap, or even a maze spell. The spell enables the cleric to choose the correct direction, exact path, or necessary actions, and this knowledge remains for 1 turn per caster level. The spell frees the cleric and companions from a maze spell in a single melee round and continues to do so while it lasts. The reverse, lose the path, makes the touched creature totally lost and unable to find its way for the duration, though it can still be led. Material Component: A set of divination counters favored by the cleric, such as bones, ivory counters, sticks, carved runes, or similar items.","notes":"Touched creature magically knows the route to one specific destination you choose. If multiple routes exist, only the shortest is known. If none exists, you learn that and the spell ends.\nDetails:\nKnows the route, not precise distances/directions; cannot draw an accurate map. Learns nothing about hazards on the route.\nReversible as Hide the Path:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Find The Path"},"cleric harm":{"name":"Harm","level":"6","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"Yes (negates)","save_type":"","description":"Heal\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Harm\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis powerful spell wipes away disease and injury in the recipient. It completely cures all diseases and/or blindness and heals all hit point damage from wounds or injury except 1d4 points. It also dispels feeblemind. Later wounds, injuries, or diseases can negate its benefits. The reverse, harm, infects the victim with disease and causes the loss of all hit points except 1d4 if a successful touch is inflicted. For creatures not affected by heal or harm, see cure light wounds.","notes":"You speak an Abominable Word and attempt to touch the target. If it fails a save vs spells, it takes enough magical damage to reduce its hit points to 1d4.\nDetails:\nIn some campaigns, Abominable Words are lost secrets. Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, undead.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Harm"},"cleric heal":{"name":"Heal","level":"6","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Heal\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Harm\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis powerful spell wipes away disease and injury in the recipient. It completely cures all diseases and/or blindness and heals all hit point damage from wounds or injury except 1d4 points. It also dispels feeblemind. Later wounds, injuries, or diseases can negate its benefits. The reverse, harm, infects the victim with disease and causes the loss of all hit points except 1d4 if a successful touch is inflicted. For creatures not affected by heal or harm, see cure light wounds.","notes":"Target regains almost all lost hit points: up to normal total minus 1d4. Cures blindness, deafness, diseases, madnesses, and poisons completely. Ends feeblemind.\nDetails:\nDoes not raise the dead and does not remove lycanthropy. Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, undead.\nReversible as Harm:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Heal"},"cleric hide the path":{"name":"Hide the Path","level":"6","school":"Divine enchantment","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per cleric level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 rounds","save":"Yes (negates)","save_type":"","description":"Find The Path\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Lose The Path\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell enables the cleric to find the shortest and most direct route sought, whether to, from, or out of a locale. The locale may be outdoors, underground, a trap, or even a maze spell. The spell enables the cleric to choose the correct direction, exact path, or necessary actions, and this knowledge remains for 1 turn per caster level. The spell frees the cleric and companions from a maze spell in a single melee round and continues to do so while it lasts. The reverse, lose the path, makes the touched creature totally lost and unable to find its way for the duration, though it can still be led. Material Component: A set of divination counters favored by the cleric, such as bones, ivory counters, sticks, carved runes, or similar items.","notes":"Touched creature loses sense of direction; if it tries to move, its heading is randomly determined.\nDetails:\nIt can still attack and cast spells normally; only directional movement becomes random.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Hide the Path"},"cleric part water":{"name":"Part Water","level":"6","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"30 ft per cleric level","duration":"1 turn per cleric level","aoe":"Path 10 ft wide; length 30 ft per cleric level; up to 1 mile deep","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Depends on use","save_type":"","description":"Part Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2” per level\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes water or similar liquid to move apart, forming a trough. The trough’s depth and length depend on caster level: per level, it creates a trough 3’ deep by 1’ wide by 2” long, meaning 20’ or 20 yards. For example, at 12th level, the cleric parts water 36’ deep by 12’ wide by 24” long, or 240’/240 yards. The trough remains for the spell’s duration or until the cleric ends it. Material Component: The cleric’s religious symbol.","notes":"Opens a dry pathway through a body of water (≤ 1 mile deep). No saving throw for this use. Can also be used to destroy water elementals.\nDetails:\n    Only bodies of water affected; does not function on the Elemental Plane of Water.\n    If targeted on/including water elementals: each must save vs spells/magical effects.\n        Fail: destroyed.\n        Pass: takes 6d6 raw magical damage.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Part Water"},"cleric speak with monsters":{"name":"Speak With Monsters","level":"6","school":"Divine divination","range":"Caster","duration":"1 turn","aoe":"30 ft radius around you","components":"V, S, M","ct":"9 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Speak With Monsters\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3” radius\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nWhen cast, this spell allows the cleric to converse with any type of creature that has any form of communicative ability. The creature understands the intent of what the cleric says. The referee checks the creature’s reaction. All creatures of the same type as the one chosen by the cleric can likewise understand if they are within range. The spell lasts 1 melee round per caster level, and during that duration conversation can occur as the monster is able and desires.","notes":"Universal translator for any creature or plant intelligent enough to communicate. Translates their “speech” into a language you understand and translates your spoken words for them within the area.\nDetails:\n    Intelligence < animal (1) cannot communicate meaningfully even with this spell.\n    Does not make hostile creatures friendly.\n    Translation is per-language; different species may not understand each other without repetition, though you can understand all of them.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Speak With Monsters"},"cleric stone tell":{"name":"Stone Tell","level":"6","school":"Divine divination","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn","aoe":"Up to 10 cubic feet","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Stone Tell\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 turn\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One cubic yard of stone\nWhen the cleric casts stone tell upon an area, the stones speak and tell the caster who or what has touched them, as well as what is covered, concealed, or behind them. The stones provide complete descriptions as required. Material Components: A drop of mercury and a bit of clay.","notes":"Gives stone the ability to hear your questions and mentally reply with brief, truthful answers to the best of its knowledge.\nDetails:\nOnly you hear replies. Stone only knows what occurred within 20 ft of it (making area of effect relevant).","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Stone Tell"},"cleric word of recall":{"name":"Word of Recall","level":"6","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Caster","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"You plus creatures/objects up to 25 lb per cleric level","components":"V","ct":"Fast","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Word Of Recall\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell instantly returns the cleric to their sanctuary when the word is uttered. The sanctuary must be specifically designated in advance and must be a well-known place, but it may be any distance from the cleric, above or below ground. Transportation by word of recall is infallibly safe. In addition to themselves, the cleric may transport 250 gold pieces weight per caster level. For example, a 15th-level cleric may transport themselves plus 3,750 gold pieces weight, or 375 pounds, of additional matter, including equipment, treasure, or living material such as another person.","notes":"Teleports you (and possibly others) to a prepared sanctuary. Before using, you must designate a sanctuary by standing there and praying privately for 10 minutes.\nDetails:\n    Only one sanctuary at a time; designating a new one replaces the old.\n    Transports willing creatures only; unwilling creatures are unaffected.\n    Worn/held/carried gear is transported. Weight limit cannot be exploited to bring additional “creatures” unless very small (≈ 30 lb or less).","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Word of Recall"},"cleric astral spell":{"name":"Astral Spell","level":"7","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Affected creatures, with objects/equipment worn or carried","components":"V, S","ct":"3 turns","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Astral Spell\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 turns\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the cleric to project their astral body into the Astral Plane, leaving their physical body and material possessions behind on the Prime Material Plane. Only certain magic items with multi-planed existence can be brought into the Astral Plane. Since the Astral Plane touches all first levels of the Outer Planes, the cleric may travel astrally to any of those Outer Planes and then leave the Astral Plane, forming a body on the chosen plane. It is also possible to travel astrally anywhere in the Prime Material Plane, but a second body cannot be formed there. As a general rule, an astrally projected person can be seen only by creatures on the Astral Plane. The astral body remains connected to the material body by a silvery cord. If the cord is broken, the person is killed astrally and materially, though normally only the psychic wind can break it. When a second body is formed on another plane, the silvery cord remains invisibly attached to the new body. If the second body or astral form is slain, the cord returns to the body on the Prime Material Plane, reviving it from suspended animation. Astrally projected persons may function on the Astral Plane, but their actions do not affect creatures outside the Astral Plane. The spell lasts until the cleric ends it or it is ended by outside means, such as dispel magic or destruction of the cleric’s body on the Prime Material Plane. The cleric may take up to five other creatures by linking them in a circle with the cleric. These travelers depend on the cleric and can be stranded. Travel speed in the Astral Plane depends on the cleric’s desire, and the ultimate destination depends on the cleric’s conceptualization.","notes":"Transports astral avatars of you and up to five other creatures to the Astral Plane, leaving physical bodies behind.\nDetails:\n    Only transports willing creatures; unwilling creatures are unaffected.\n    Most magic items are weakened or suppressed on the Astral Plane; some spells work differently.\n    Physical bodies remain on the Prime Material Plane, unconscious and incapacitated until the spell ends.\n    Each avatar is linked to its body by a silver cord (normally invisible and invulnerable), but it can be severed by:\n        deities / similar powers,\n        rare Astral weather effects,\n        a very limited number of special weapons/powers.\n        If severed: avatar disappears and the physical body dies.\n    Avatar can enter other planes from the Astral, but cannot enter a plane where you have a physical body (except returning to the original body).","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Astral Spell"},"cleric control weather":{"name":"Control Weather","level":"7","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"Nil","duration":"4d12 hours","aoe":"Area around target up to 4d4 square miles","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Control Weather\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 4–48 hours\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4–16 square miles\nThis spell allows the cleric to change the weather in the area where the spell is cast. It affects weather for 4d12 hours in an area of 4d4 square miles. Casting requires 1 turn, and the effects are felt after an additional 1d4 turns. The spell cannot radically change temperature, such as from below zero to a 100-degree heat wave. The possible weather changes depend on prevailing conditions. Clear weather may become very clear, light clouds, or hazy. Partly cloudy weather may become clear, cloudy, mist, light rain, small hail, sleet, or light snow. Cloudy weather may become partly cloudy, deep clouds, fog, heavy rain, large hail, driving sleet, or heavy snow. Hot weather may become warm weather or sweltering heat. Warm weather may become hot or cool weather. Cool weather may become warm or cold weather. Cold weather may become cool weather or arctic cold. Calm may become dead calm or light breeze. Light wind may become calm or strong wind. Strong wind may become light wind or gale. Gale may become strong wind or storm. Storm may become gale or hurricane/typhoon. All three aspects—clouds/precipitation, temperature, and wind—may be controlled, but only within the listed limits. Contradictions such as fog and strong wind are not possible. Multiple control weather spells can be used only in succession. Material Components: The cleric’s religious symbol, incense, and prayer beads or similar prayer object. The spell functions only in areas with appropriate climatic conditions.","notes":"Controls precipitation, temperature, and wind speed over a large area. New weather takes 10d4 minutes to reach full strength.\nDetails:\n    Cannot create weather not natural to the region (no snowstorm in tropics; no monsoon in tundra).\n    Works only where “weather exists”: Prime Material, Elemental Plane of Air, Elemental Plane of Water, or GM-approved regions.\n    Cannot affect rare Astral/Ethereal weather; Outer Planes are typically under a power’s direct control.\n    Affects weather only, not geology/astronomy (no earthquake, no eclipse).\n    You can move one step on each of the precipitation and wind speed tracks; temperature change limited to 1d10 + 10 °F.\nPrecipitation track: Clear → Light clouds → Cloudy → Light precipitation → Medium precipitation → Heavy precipitation\nWind speed track: Calm → Light breeze → Wind → Strong wind → Gale","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Control Weather"},"cleric earthquake":{"name":"Earthquake","level":"7","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"360 ft","duration":"1 round","aoe":"Contiguous stone area up to 5 ft diameter per cleric level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"None (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Earthquake\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: ½” diameter per level\nWhen cast, this spell creates a strong local tremor that rips the ground. The shock lasts 1 melee round and affects terrain, vegetation, structures, and creatures in the area. The area is circular, with a diameter of ½” per caster level; for example, a 20th-level cleric creates a 10” diameter earthquake. Terrain effects: caves and caverns collapse their roofs; cliffs crumble and cause landslides; ground cracks open, causing creatures to fall in and be killed on a 1-in-4 chance for Size S, 1-in-6 for Size M, and 1-in-8 for Size L; marsh drains water and becomes muddy rough ground; tunnels cave in. Vegetation effects: small growth is unaffected; 1 in 3 trees are uprooted and fall. Structure effects: all structures sustain 5d12 structural damage, and those taking full damage are thrown down into rubble. Creature effects are as listed by the referee’s table. Material Components: A pinch of dirt, a piece of rock, and a lump of clay.","notes":"Creates a minor earthquake; cracks open with a chance to swallow creatures.\nDetails:\n    Non-material creatures and creatures flying/levitating do not fall in.\n    GM may rule extremely large creatures are too large to fall in.\n    Elementals survive the fall and can return after 3d6 rounds.\n    Chance to fall (no saving throw):\n        Small: 1 in 4\n        Medium: 1 in 6\n        Large: 1 in 8\n    Creatures swallowed take 12d10 blunt damage.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Earthquake"},"cleric energy drain":{"name":"Energy Drain","level":"7","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Restoration\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Energy Drain\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell raises the recipient’s life energy level upward by one, restoring a previous life energy level drained by a force or monster. For example, if a 10th-level character was struck by a wight and drained to 9th level, restoration restores the character to exactly the number of experience points needed for 10th level, with additional Hit Dice or hit points and level functions restored accordingly. Restoration works only if cast within 1 day per caster level after the life energy loss. The reverse, energy drain, removes one life energy level and requires the victim to be touched. Restoration also restores the Intelligence of a creature affected by feeblemind.","notes":"Drains one experience level from the target.\nDetails:\n    Touch required (may require a to-hit roll). No saving throw.\n    Target loses one life energy level; if level 1 or lower (or 1 HD or less), it is killed.\n    Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, undead.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Energy Drain"},"cleric gate":{"name":"Gate","level":"7","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"30 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"2D rectangle 10 ft wide × 20 ft high contiguous with target point","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Gate\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nCasting gate has two effects. First, it creates an ultra-dimensional connection between the cleric’s plane and the plane of a specific powerful being, enabling that being to step through the gate. Second, the spell attracts that being’s attention. When casting the spell, the cleric must name the demon, devil, demi-god, god, or similar being they wish to come through and aid them. There is a 100% certainty that something steps through the gate. The being’s actions depend on many factors, including the cleric’s alignment, the nature of the cleric’s companions, and what opposes or threatens the cleric. The Dungeon Master determines the variables. The gated being either returns immediately, which is very unlikely, or remains to act.","notes":"Draws attention of a specified extraplanar creature (by name or type) and opens a portal at the target point through which it can emerge. The creature is not forced to step through; something will, as determined by the GM.\nDetails:\n    If you know a being’s true name (or one of them), you may attempt to call that specific being; it is still not forced to come.\n    Calling a deity/equivalent: it does not come personally; it sends a minion.\n    Provides no control over the gated creature; it may be hostile if its time is being wasted.\n    Gate orientation is thematically appropriate (celestial above descending; fiend below crawling up, etc.).\n    GM controls the gated creature.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Gate"},"cleric holy word":{"name":"Holy Word","level":"7","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"Nil","duration":"Varies","aoe":"30 ft radius","components":"V","ct":"Fast","save":"None (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Holy Word / Unholy Word\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” radius\nThe utterance of a holy word or unholy word has tremendous power. It drives off evil or good creatures from other planes, forcing them to return to their own planes of existence. It also affects creatures of differing alignment within the 6” diameter area of effect centered on the cleric. Creatures with fewer than 4 Hit Dice or levels are killed. Creatures with 4 to 7+ Hit Dice or levels are paralyzed for 1d4 turns. Creatures with 8 to 11+ Hit Dice or levels are stunned for 2d4 rounds, move at -50%, and attack at -4. Creatures with 12 or more Hit Dice or levels are deafened for 1d4 rounds, move at -25%, attack at -2, and have a 50% chance of spell failure.","notes":"Utter a holy word; all non-good-aligned creatures in the area suffer severe effects.\nDetails:\n    All fiends and evil-aligned elementals are instantly banished to their home plane.\n    Other non-good creatures suffer based on level/HD:\n        < 4: Killed (instant)\n        4–7: Paralyzed for 10d4 rounds\n        8–11: Move halved; -4 to attacks for 2d4 rounds\n            11: Move -10 ft; -2 to attacks for 1d4 rounds\n    Deities/similar power unaffected.\n    Does not work in the Lower Outer Planes.\n    Alignment interpretation is GM-facing: some tables apply it to any non-good; others only to evil.\nReversible as Unholy Word.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Holy Word"},"cleric regenerate":{"name":"Regenerate","level":"7","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Regenerate\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Wither\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell causes body members, bones, or organs to grow back, including fingers, toes, hands, feet, arms, legs, tails, and even the heads of multi-headed creatures. Regeneration takes 1 round if the severed member is present and touching the creature, or 2d8 turns otherwise. The reverse, wither, causes the touched member or organ to shrivel and stop functioning in 1 round, then drop off into dust in 2d8 turns. As usual, the target must be touched for the harmful effect. Material Components: A prayer device and holy or unholy water.","notes":"Regrows or reattaches a lost body part; also heals organ damage or injuries not addressed by Heal/Cure spells (e.g., can restore sight to damaged eyes).\nDetails:\n    Target must be alive. Cannot restore head or brain; if missing, spell fails.\n    If severed part is present: instantly reattached.\n    If missing/destroyed: regrows over 2d4 combat rounds.\n    Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, undead.\nReversible as Wither.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Regenerate"},"cleric restoration":{"name":"Restoration","level":"7","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Restoration\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Energy Drain\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell raises the recipient’s life energy level upward by one, restoring a previous life energy level drained by a force or monster. For example, if a 10th-level character was struck by a wight and drained to 9th level, restoration restores the character to exactly the number of experience points needed for 10th level, with additional Hit Dice or hit points and level functions restored accordingly. Restoration works only if cast within 1 day per caster level after the life energy loss. The reverse, energy drain, removes one life energy level and requires the victim to be touched. Restoration also restores the Intelligence of a creature affected by feeblemind.","notes":"Restores one lost level from undead level drain (or similar). Also has broader restorative effects at GM discretion.\nDetails:\n    Must be cast within one day per your cleric level of the level loss; outside that window it cannot restore.\n    Target gains enough XP to be at the start of the restored level.\n    Ends feeblemind or similar mind-damaging effects.\nReversible as Energy Drain.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Restoration"},"cleric resurrection":{"name":"Resurrection","level":"7","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"The piece of flesh or bone you choose","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"Only when used vs undead","save_type":"","description":"Resurrection\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Destruction\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Person touched\nThis spell restores life and complete strength to the person touched. The person may have been dead up to 10 years per caster level, so a 19th-level cleric can resurrect the bones of a person dead up to 190 years. See raise dead for limitations on what persons can be raised. The reverse, destruction, causes the victim to die instantly and turn to dust. Destruction requires a touch, in combat or otherwise. Using this spell makes it impossible for the cleric to cast further spells or engage in combat until they have had 1 day of bed rest per level of the person brought back to life or destroyed. Material Components: The cleric’s religious symbol and holy or unholy water.","notes":"Returns the dead to life by returning a soul to a portion of its body and regrowing the rest if needed. Target remembers dying but not the interval while dead.\nDetails:\n    If successful: returns with full hit points; retains prepared spells/unused slots it had at death.\n    Missing parts are restored.\n    Default ancestry limitation (unless GM says otherwise): works on humans, half-elves, gnomes, dwarfs, halflings; not elves or half-orcs (souls vs spirits rationale).\n    Death must be within 10 years per your cleric level (but can still be used against older-dead undead).\n    Requires at least 1 ounce of flesh/bone (not fingernail/hair).\n    Target must be deceased (cannot clone from a living body part).\n    Target must pass a Resurrection Success roll (by CON). Failure makes the target forever dead to further resurrection/raise dead.\nAgainst undead:\n    Undead saves vs spells/magical effects.\n        Pass: takes 5d8+5 corrosion damage; no other effect. (Lich or vampire > century gets +4 on this save.)\n        Fail: returned to life if within time limit; otherwise crumbles to dust.\nReversible as Surcease.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Resurrection"},"cleric surcease":{"name":"Surcease","level":"7","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"10 rounds","save":"Yes (lessened effect)","save_type":"","description":"Kills the target on a failed save; damages on a successful save. Involves an Abominable Word that prevents future raising/resurrection of the body (except by a deity/similar power).\nDetails:\n    Abominable Words may be lost secrets in some campaigns.\n    Default ancestry limitation (unless GM says otherwise): humans, half-elves, gnomes, dwarfs, halflings; not elves/half-orcs.\n    Requires touch (may require to-hit roll). Target may save vs spells/magical effects:\n        Pass: takes 5d8+5 corrosion damage.\n        Fail: dies instantly and cannot be raised/resurrected except by deity-level intervention.","notes":"Kills the target on a failed save; damages on a successful save. Involves an Abominable Word that prevents future raising/resurrection of the body (except by a deity/similar power).\nDetails:\n    Abominable Words may be lost secrets in some campaigns.\n    Default ancestry limitation (unless GM says otherwise): humans, half-elves, gnomes, dwarfs, halflings; not elves/half-orcs.\n    Requires touch (may require to-hit roll). Target may save vs spells/magical effects:\n        Pass: takes 5d8+5 corrosion damage.\n        Fail: dies instantly and cannot be raised/resurrected except by deity-level intervention.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Surcease"},"cleric symbol":{"name":"Symbol","level":"7","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per cleric level","aoe":"Each creature within 100 ft that can see the symbol","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"Yes (negates effect)","save_type":"","description":"Symbol\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThe cleric inscribes a glowing symbol in the air or on any surface. The symbol glows for 1 turn per caster level. The cleric chooses the symbol at the time of casting from the following options. Hopelessness: Creatures seeing it must turn back in dejection and/or surrender to capture or attack unless they save versus magic; effects last 3d4 turns. Pain: Affected creatures suffer -4 on “to hit” rolls and -2 Dexterity due to wracking pains; effects last 2d10 turns. Persuasion: Creatures seeing the symbol become the same alignment as, and friendly to, the cleric for 1d20 turns unless they save versus magic. Material Components: Mercury and phosphorus.","notes":"Shapes a glowing symbol in the air. For the duration, any creature that sees it must save or suffer the symbol’s effect. Effects can outlast the symbol’s active duration.\nDetails:\n    Creatures save vs spells/magical effects; on success they still see it but are unaffected.\n    Clerics can use three symbols (choose on casting):\nHopelessness: 3d4 turns; -100 morale; if attacked in melee must flee or surrender (creature chooses).\nPain: 2d10 turns; Dexterity and AC worsen by 2; -4 to attack rolls.\nPersuasion: 1d20 turns; alignment shifts to yours; views you as trusted friend.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Symbol"},"cleric unholy word":{"name":"Unholy Word","level":"7","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"Nil","duration":"Varies","aoe":"30 ft radius","components":"V","ct":"Fast","save":"None (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Holy Word / Unholy Word\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” radius\nThe utterance of a holy word or unholy word has tremendous power. It drives off evil or good creatures from other planes, forcing them to return to their own planes of existence. It also affects creatures of differing alignment within the 6” diameter area of effect centered on the cleric. Creatures with fewer than 4 Hit Dice or levels are killed. Creatures with 4 to 7+ Hit Dice or levels are paralyzed for 1d4 turns. Creatures with 8 to 11+ Hit Dice or levels are stunned for 2d4 rounds, move at -50%, and attack at -4. Creatures with 12 or more Hit Dice or levels are deafened for 1d4 rounds, move at -25%, attack at -2, and have a 50% chance of spell failure.","notes":"Utter an unholy word; all non-evil-aligned creatures in the area suffer severe effects.\nDetails:\n    All celestials and good-aligned elementals are instantly banished to their home plane.\n    Other non-evil creatures suffer based on level/HD (same table structure as Holy Word):\n        < 4: Killed (instant)\n        4–7: Paralyzed for 10d4 rounds\n        8–11: Move halved; -4 to attacks for 2d4 rounds\n            11: Move -10 ft; -2 to attacks for 1d4 rounds\n    Deities/similar power unaffected.\n    Does not work in the Upper Outer Planes.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Unholy Word"},"cleric wind walk":{"name":"Wind Walk","level":"7","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Caster","duration":"1 hour per cleric level","aoe":"Creatures of your choice within 20 ft radius of you","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wind Walk\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell enables the cleric, and possibly one or two others, to transform their bodies into cloud-like vapors. A magical wind carries the cleric at a speed from 6” to 60” per turn, as the caster wills. The spell lasts as long as the cleric desires, up to 6 turns, or 1 hour, per caster level. For every 8 levels of experience the cleric has, up to 24, they may touch and carry one additional person, up to two persons total. Wind-walking persons are not invisible, but appear misty and transparent. If fully clothed in white, they are 80% likely to be mistaken for clouds, fog, vapors, or similar forms. Material Components: Fire and holy or unholy water.","notes":"Turns you and designated creatures into magical vapor (cloud/steam). In this form you can fly and pass through any gap wider than ½ inch.\nDetails:\n    Must affect you. Also includes up to 1 human-sized creature per 8 cleric levels.\n    Only willing creatures affected; any affected creature may end the spell on itself at any time.\n    Movement: 60 ft per round.\n    If the spell ends while flying: creature falls immediately.\n    If the spell ends while in a narrow space: takes 6d6 blunt damage, then appears prone in the nearest unoccupied space.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Wind Walk"},"cleric wither":{"name":"Wither","level":"7","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None (but see below)","save_type":"","description":"Regenerate\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Wither\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell causes body members, bones, or organs to grow back, including fingers, toes, hands, feet, arms, legs, tails, and even the heads of multi-headed creatures. Regeneration takes 1 round if the severed member is present and touching the creature, or 2d8 turns otherwise. The reverse, wither, causes the touched member or organ to shrivel and stop functioning in 1 round, then drop off into dust in 2d8 turns. As usual, the target must be touched for the harmful effect. Material Components: A prayer device and holy or unholy water.","notes":"Degenerates living tissue (opposite of Regenerate).\nDetails:\n    On a successful touch, target may save vs spells; on success takes half damage.\n    Damage: 8d12+32 corrosion, or 4d12+16 on a successful save.\n    If you touched a limb and it failed its save, the limb withers.\n    Affects normally living creatures only; no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, undead.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Wither"},"cleric bless":{"name":"Bless","level":"1","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"60 ft","duration":"6 rounds","aoe":"Cube, 50 ft × 50 ft × 50 ft","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Bless\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nReversible: Curse\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 6 melee rounds\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 5” × 5”\nUpon uttering the bless spell, the caster raises the morale of friendly creatures by +1 and gives them a +1 bonus to “to hit” rolls. A bless spell affects only creatures not already engaged in melee combat. The spell may be reversed as curse, lowering enemies’ morale and “to hit” rolls by -1. The caster determines the range, up to 6”, and the spell affects all creatures in a 5” square area centered on the chosen point. Material Component: Bless requires holy water. Curse requires specially polluted water.","notes":"The selected creatures in the area of effect may choose to gain +1 to “to hit” rolls in combat and +5% to morale checks.\n\nDetails:\n\nThis spell can target creatures within the area of effect that aren’t in melee when the spell is cast (they must be 10 ft distant from enemies).\n\nWhen you cast the spell, you can choose any number of creatures and decide they aren’t affected.\n\nThis spell is normally used as a blessing on your allies (and yourself), granting bonuses in combat and morale checks.\n\nAlternatively, you may bless an object or a place, even if you memorised the spell for blessing creatures. This usually has no direct game-mechanical effect, but can influence events outside the ordinary rules.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Bless"},"cleric ceremony":{"name":"Ceremony","level":"1","school":"Invocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature, one item, or area","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 hour","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Ceremony\n\nSchool: Invocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 hour\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature, one item, or area\nCeremony has several religious applications, depending on the cleric’s level. The spell does not leave behind a magical aura, though in some cases an aura of good or evil may be present and detectable. The specific ceremonies vary by religion, but usually include: 1st-level cleric: coming of age, burial, marriage; 3rd-level cleric: dedication, investiture, consecrate item; 5th-level cleric: ordination, special vows; 7th-level cleric: consecrate ground; 9th-level cleric: anathematize. Each ceremony requires a cleric of the indicated level or higher. Except for anathematize, no saving throw is required because the recipient is either inanimate or presumed willing; if the recipient is unwilling, the ceremony simply fails. Coming of age is a limited bless cast upon a young person, often around age 12. The recipient gains a +1 bonus to any single saving throw, usable at any time after the ceremony. In some cultures, this rite has symbolic importance and grants the rights and privileges of adulthood. Burial magically protects a corpse and grants it the blessing of the religious organization. The body is protected for one week as if by protection from evil, and anyone trying to disinter it during that time must save versus spell or stop and flee in fear for 1 turn. Marriage has no tangible magical after-effect and does not guarantee happiness or harmony, but usually has moral or legal significance. Dedication admits the recipient into the casting cleric’s religion, making them a sanctioned worshiper of the cleric’s deity. The dedication is permanent unless the worshiper changes allegiance to another deity. A previous dedication can be overridden by a new dedication cast by a cleric of higher level than the one who performed the earlier rite. Investiture must be performed on an aspiring cleric before the character can become a 1st-level cleric. Consecrate item must be performed on any object placed on an altar or within a religious edifice. Holy or unholy water must be kept in a properly consecrated container to prevent loss of potency. Ordination must be performed on a cleric before the character can become priest of a congregation, assume similar duties, gain followers, or establish a following. The cleric performing the ordination must be higher level than the recipient. Special vows may be received by a would-be cavalier or paladin before beginning that profession. The effects last until the character gains enough experience to reach the upper limit of their current level. The vows may then be renewed during training between levels or while advancing through the next level. A cavalier or paladin under special vows is immune to bestow curse spells, though not cursed items, while the vows remain in effect. The subject is also more susceptible to any quest spell cast by a cleric of the same alignment as the caster of the vows, suffering a -4 saving throw penalty. Consecrate ground should be performed before any holy or unholy structure is built on a site. A religious edifice built on unconsecrated ground slowly and irrevocably falls into disrepair and has a cumulative 1% chance per year of collapsing. The spell must be cast before the area is altered or construction materials are brought to the site; it has no effect if done afterward. Consecrated ground may also be used for a graveyard, in which case the graveyard automatically turns undead each round as a 3rd-level cleric. If performed by an evil cleric, undead in the area are treated as protected and controlled by an evil 3rd-level cleric. Anathematize is excommunication that brands the offender on the cheek, forehead, arm, or hand with a symbol, sigil, or sign identifying the subject as someone who has committed a serious offense against their deity. An unwilling subject may save versus spell at -4 to avoid the effect. If the recipient is not truly deserving, the spell fails. A successful atonement causes the brand to fade and possibly vanish. If the offense was caused magically or by an external force, the brand disappears completely. If the actions were natural, the brand cannot be fully removed. Material Component: The cleric’s holy symbol is always involved, though other components vary by religion. Standard costs are: coming of age, 5–15 sp; burial, 5–50 gp; marriage, 1–20 gp; dedication, 1–10 sp or sometimes free; investiture, 1–100 gp or sometimes free; item consecration, usually free; ordination, usually free but possibly up to 200 gp; special vows, 1–100 gp or sometimes free; consecrate ground, 100–600 gp depending on area and caster level; anathematize, always free.","notes":"Coming of age, burial, marriage, dedication, investiture, consecrate item, ordination, special vows, consecrate ground, and anathematize are all covered by this spell depending on cleric level. Material component always involves the cleric’s holy symbol.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Ceremony"},"cleric combine":{"name":"Combine","level":"1","school":"Evocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"The circle of clerics","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Combine\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The circle of clerics\nThis spell allows three to five clerics to combine their abilities and empower one of their number to cast a spell or turn undead with greater efficacy. The highest-level cleric, or one of them if tied, stands in the center while the others join hands in a surrounding circle. All participating clerics cast combine together. The central cleric temporarily functions as if higher level, gaining one level for each encircling cleric. The maximum gain is 4 levels, and the maximum duration is 3 turns. The increase applies to effective level for turning undead and for spell details that vary by caster level. The encircling clerics must concentrate to maintain the effect. They gain no Armor Class bonuses from shield or Dexterity, and attackers gain a +4 bonus on “to hit” rolls against them. The central cleric gains no additional spells, but may cast previously memorized spells, often with improved effects.","notes":"Three to five clerics combine power; the central cleric gains one effective level per supporting cleric, up to +4 levels, for up to 3 turns.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Combine"},"cleric command":{"name":"Command","level":"1","school":"Divine enchantment","range":"10 ft","duration":"1 round","aoe":"One creature","components":"V","ct":"Fast","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"Command\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell allows the cleric to issue a single-word command. The command must be spoken in a language the target can understand. The target obeys to the best of its ability, but only if the command is absolutely clear and unequivocal. For example, “Suicide!” could be interpreted as a noun and would be ignored. “Die!” causes the target to fall into a faint or cataleptic state for 1 round, after which the creature is alive and well. Typical command words include: back, halt, flee, run, stop, fall, fly, go, leave, surrender, sleep, and rest. Undead are unaffected. Creatures with Intelligence 13 or higher, or creatures with 6 or more Hit Dice or experience levels, receive a saving throw versus magic. A creature that meets both conditions does not receive two saving throws.","notes":"You issue a one-word command to the target creature, and it may be forced to obey for one round. The command must be very clear (unambiguous), so only a few commands are normally used.\n\nDetails:\n\nThe creature must be able to hear you, and it doesn’t have to obey unless the command is in a language it understands.\n\nThis spell is considered a charm and a form of mental domination, so many creatures—such as golems, constructs, elementals, and undead—are immune.\n\nThe target creature doesn’t have to obey unless the command is a verb.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Command"},"cleric create water":{"name":"Create Water","level":"1","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"10 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"See below","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Create Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Destroy Water\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Up to 27 cubic feet\nThis spell creates 4 gallons of clean, drinkable water per caster level. For example, a 2nd-level cleric creates 8 gallons, a 3rd-level cleric creates 12 gallons, and so on. The reverse, destroy water, obliterates an equal quantity of water without leaving vapor, mist, fog, or steam. Created water remains until normally used, evaporated, spilled, or otherwise lost. The water may be created or destroyed in an area just large enough to contain it, up to a maximum area of 27 cubic feet, or one cubic yard. Material Component: A drop of water is required to create water. A pinch of dust is required to destroy water. Water cannot be created inside a living thing.","notes":"For each level you have in the cleric class, you conjure up to sixteen litres of water from the Elemental Plane of Water at a targeted point. You may limit the amount created.\n\nDetails:\n\nUnless the target point is inside a receptacle, the water immediately spills.\n\nThe target point can’t be inside a creature.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Create Water"},"cleric cure light wounds":{"name":"Cure Light Wounds","level":"1","school":"Divine necromancy","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Cure Light Wounds\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nReversible: Cause Light Wounds\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Character touched\nBy laying a hand upon a creature, the cleric heals 1d8 hit points of wound or injury damage. This healing does not affect creatures without corporeal bodies, nonliving creatures, or creatures that can only be harmed by iron, silver, and/or magical weapons. The reverse, cause light wounds, deals 1d8 points of damage. If the target avoids the touch, the cleric must make a melee “to hit” roll to determine whether the touch succeeds. Healed wounds remain healed unless the creature takes further damage. Caused wounds heal naturally or may be cured as normal injuries.","notes":"The target regains 1d8 hit points, up to its normal maximum. Healing beyond the target’s normal maximum is wasted. You must be able to see and touch the target.\n\nDetails:\n\nThis spell can’t cure disease, reattach limbs, raise the dead, or heal afflictions not measured in hit points.\n\nIn general, the spell affects only normally living creatures. It has no effect on golems, constructs, elementals, or undead.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Cure Light Wounds"},"cleric detect evil":{"name":"Detect Evil","level":"1","school":"Divine divination","range":"Caster","duration":"1 turn, plus 5 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"Path 10 ft wide and 120 ft long","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Evil\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Detect Good\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 turn + ½ turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” path\nThis spell detects emanations of evil, or good if reversed, from any creature or object. For example, evil alignment or an evilly cursed object radiates evil, but a hidden trap or unintelligent viper does not. The spell lasts 1 turn plus ½ turn, or 5 rounds/5 minutes, per caster level. A 1st-level cleric has a duration of 1½ turns, a 2nd-level cleric has 2 turns, a 3rd-level cleric has 2½ turns, and so on. Detection extends in a 1” wide path in the direction the cleric faces. Material Component: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol, held before them.","notes":"You see an aura around each evil-aligned creature, object, or place in the area of effect.\n\nIf the creature, object, or place is invisible, you know where it is, but you can’t see details.\n\nDetails:\n\nOnly the caster sees the aura. This spell reveals evil alignment, not danger.\n\nThe spell doesn’t necessarily detect curses, though some horrific curses may make an item inherently evil.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Detect Evil"},"cleric detect magic":{"name":"Detect Magic","level":"1","school":"Divine divination","range":"Caster","duration":"1 turn","aoe":"Path 10 ft wide and 30 ft long","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Magic\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 turn\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” path, 3” long\nThis spell detects magical radiations in a path 1” wide and up to 3” long in the direction the cleric faces. The caster may turn 60 degrees per round. The spell is blocked by 1 foot or more of stone, 1/12 foot of solid metal, or 3 feet or more of solid wood. Material Component: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol.","notes":"You see an aura around each magical creature, object, or place in the area of effect.\n\nIf the creature, object, or place is invisible, you know where it is, but you still can’t see it.\n\nDetails:\n\nOnly you see the magical auras. The spell reveals enchantments, not powers.\n\nSolid material blocks it: it penetrates metal up to 1 inch thick and brick/stone up to 1 foot thick.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Detect Magic"},"cleric endure cold heat":{"name":"Endure Cold/Heat","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"9 turns per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Endure Cold / Endure Heat\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Endure Heat / Endure Cold\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 9 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell protects the recipient from normal extremes of cold or heat, depending on the version cast. The recipient can stand unclothed in temperatures as low as -30°F or as high as 130°F with no ill effect. Temperatures beyond those limits cause 1 hit point of exposure damage per hour for each degree beyond the limit. Without such protection, exposure damage is 1 hit point per turn per degree. The spell lasts for its duration or until the recipient is affected by any magical cold or magical heat, including white dragon breath. The spell is cancelled regardless of which version was used and regardless of whether magical heat or cold strikes the recipient. The recipient takes no damage from the magical heat or cold during the round in which the spell is broken, but is vulnerable starting the following round. The spell is instantly cancelled if resist fire or resist cold is cast on the recipient.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Endure Cold/Heat"},"cleric invisibility to undead":{"name":"Invisibility to Undead","level":"1","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"6 rounds","aoe":"One individual","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Invisibility To Undead\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 6 rounds\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One individual\nThis spell is similar to sanctuary, but affects only undead of 4 or fewer Hit Dice. A saving throw versus spell is made for each type of undead within 30 feet of the caster. If the save fails, all undead of that type ignore the caster completely for the duration. This negates later attempts by the caster to turn those undead. If the saving throw succeeds, all undead of that type attack the caster in preference to any other target. The spell ends if the caster attacks or attempts to cast another spell. If the caster is morally neutral with respect to good and evil, the undead save at -2. Material Component: The cleric’s holy symbol.","notes":"Material component: the cleric’s holy symbol. Affects undead of 4 HD or fewer only.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Invisibility to Undead"},"cleric light":{"name":"Light","level":"1","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"60 ft","duration":"6 turns + 1 turn per cleric level","aoe":"20 ft radius sphere","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"Light\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Darkness\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 6 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2” radius globe\nThis spell causes molecules to become brightly luminous. The light is equal to torchlight, but limited to a globe 4” in diameter. The spell lasts for the listed duration, 7 turns at 1st level, 8 turns at 2nd level, 9 turns at 3rd level, and so on, or until the caster speaks a word to extinguish it. The reverse, darkness, affects the same area under the same conditions, but lasts only half as long. If cast upon a creature, applicable magic resistance and saving throws apply. If successful, the spell affects the area immediately behind the creature instead. Otherwise, the spell appears where the caster directs, provided there is line of sight or an unobstructed path. Light may spring from air, rock, metal, wood, or similar substances.","notes":"You create magical light centred on a target point, creature, or object. You may extinguish it at will.\n\nIf the target is an area of magical darkness, the darkness is nullified for the duration.\n\nDetails:\n\nThe light is stationary unless cast on a moving creature or object.\n\nIf the target is a creature, it may choose a saving throw vs spells and apply its Dexterity save modifier.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Light"},"cleric magic stone":{"name":"Magic Stone","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"2”","duration":"6 rounds or until used","aoe":"One small stone or pebble","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Magic Stone\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 2”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 6 rounds or until used\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One small stone or pebble\nTo cast this spell, the cleric picks up a small stone or pebble and places a magical aura upon it. The spell cannot affect stones that are already magical. The magic stone may be thrown at a target up to 4” away, assuming no obstacles and enough headroom. It acts as a +1 weapon for “to hit” determination, and a hit deals 1 point of damage. Ranges are 2”/3”/4”, with standard range modifiers. If the stone travels more than 4” from the thrower or misses, it loses its dweomer and falls harmlessly to the ground. The stone must be thrown within 6 rounds after casting or it becomes ordinary again. A hit breaks a spellcaster’s concentration only if the victim fails a saving throw versus spell. Targets with innate magic resistance cannot be affected. A shield spell, brooch of shielding, protection from normal missiles, minor globe of invulnerability, or similar stronger magic protects against the stone. A 6th- through 10th-level cleric may enchant 2 stones; an 11th- through 15th-level cleric may enchant 3 stones; and one additional stone is allowed for every 5 caster levels beyond 11th. The cleric may give enchanted stones to another character to throw. Some religions may forbid this spell because it allows the cleric to use a missile weapon of sorts.","notes":"Creates one or more +1 stones that inflict 1 point of damage on a hit and may disrupt casting.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Magic Stone"},"cleric penetrate disguise":{"name":"Penetrate Disguise","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"12”","duration":"1 round","aoe":"One individual","components":"V, S","ct":"2 rounds","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Penetrate Disguise\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 2 rounds\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One individual\nThis spell allows the cleric to see through a disguise made only of makeup or altered clothing. It does not reveal the target’s true class, profession, or actual appearance; it merely shows that the figure is posing as someone or something else. The spell does not detect actual rank or status, reveal illusions, or detect alignment deception, though it can detect whether a figure is affected by a friends spell. The target receives a saving throw versus spell. If the save succeeds, the disguise is enhanced in the cleric’s eyes, causing the caster to believe the target is exactly what they claim to be. A bless spell, magic armor, or protective magic item such as a cloak or ring grants the target an appropriate saving throw bonus.","notes":"Detects only non-magical disguises made with makeup or clothing. A successful save actually enhances the disguise in the caster’s eyes.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Penetrate Disguise"},"cleric portent":{"name":"Portent","level":"1","school":"Divination","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Spellcaster or figure touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Portent\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Spellcaster or figure touched\nThis spell allows the cleric to glimpse something of the recipient’s future “luck.” The luck modifies a future “to hit” roll or saving throw, though the affected roll is unknown to the character. After casting, the Dungeon Master secretly rolls 1d12 to determine which future roll is affected, and 1d6 to determine the modifier: 1 = -3, 2 = -2, 3 = -1, 4 = +1, 5 = +2, 6 = +3. Based on the 1d6 result, the DM tells the cleric whether the portent is good, fair, or poor; the recipient is usually also told. The d12 result is the number of qualifying “to hit” rolls or saving throws that must occur before the portent applies. For example, if 12 is rolled, the 12th such roll is affected. Only rolls made in life-or-death situations, such as combat or peril, count. Attempts to sidestep the portent by forcing harmless saves do not count. Qualifying rolls include saving throws made in combat or against magical effects, “to hit” rolls made by the character, and “to hit” rolls made by an opponent against the character. When the designated roll occurs, it is adjusted up or down by the d6 result, making the character more or less likely to hit, be hit, or succeed on a saving throw. Material Component: A numbered wheel or tea leaves.","notes":"The DM secretly determines when the portent applies and whether it is favorable or unfavorable.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Portent"},"cleric precipitation":{"name":"Precipitation","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 segment per level","aoe":"3” diameter cylinder up to 12” high","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Precipitation\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 segment per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” diameter cylinder up to 12” high\nThis spell causes all water vapor in the area of effect to precipitate as light rain. Low-level casters will often be within the area of effect. The rain lasts 1 segment per caster level, and about 1/100 inch of rain falls per segment. Thin, light material becomes damp in 1 segment and thoroughly wet thereafter. Twigs and heavy material such as canvas become damp in 2 segments and wet thereafter. Flat, relatively non-porous surfaces such as stone floors, rock, and painted wood become damp in 1 segment and filmed with water thereafter. Semi-porous surfaces become damp on the surface in 2 segments, then dampness progresses inward or downward until fully wet after 5 segments. Porous surfaces absorb rain up to their capacity, which usually exceeds the spell duration. Small flames such as candles are extinguished by 1 segment of rain. Small fires slow and become smoky for 1 round after the spell ends. Large fires are not materially affected. If the temperature is above 90°F, the spell duration is doubled except in arid regions. Between 33°F and 31°F, the precipitation falls as sleet. At 30°F or below, it falls as thick snow, and most dampness effects are negated or delayed until melting. If large-area magical heat such as wall of fire, fireball, or flame strike is applied to the rain, warm fog forms over twice the spell’s area. If magical cold is applied to the spell or remaining water, normal ice forms. Material Component: A pinch of silver dust.\n\nCleric Spells, 2nd Level","notes":"Creates light rain with environmental effects such as dampness, extinguishing small flames, sleet or snow in cold temperatures, and fog or ice when magical heat or cold is applied.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Precipitation"},"cleric protection from evil":{"name":"Protection From Evil","level":"1","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"3 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Protection From Evil\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Protection From Good\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 3 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell surrounds the recipient with a magical protective barrier at a distance of 1 foot. The barrier prevents bodily contact by enchanted or conjured creatures, including aerial servants, demons, devils, djinn, efreet, elementals, imps, invisible stalkers, night hags, quasits, salamanders, water weirds, wind walkers, and xorn. Summoned animals and monsters are similarly kept away. Attacks made by evil creatures against the protected creature suffer a -2 penalty to “to hit” rolls. Saving throws caused by such attacks are made with a +2 bonus. The spell may be reversed as protection from good, though it still keeps out enchanted evil creatures as well. Material Component: The cleric must trace a 3-foot diameter circle with holy water for protection from evil, with blood for protection from good, or in the air using burning incense or smoldering dung, depending on evil/good alignment.","notes":"You create an invisible barrier against evil and summoned creatures, protecting you or one creature you touch.\n\nDetails:\n\nYou can’t cast this spell on a hostile creature, an object, or a place/point in space.\n\nEvil-aligned creatures take -2 on attack rolls vs the warded creature. The warded creature gains +2 on saving throws caused by an evil creature.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Protection From Evil"},"cleric purify food drink":{"name":"Purify Food & Drink","level":"1","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"30 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"1 cubic foot per cleric level","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Purify Food & Drink\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Putrefy Food & Drink\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per level, within a 1” square area\nThis spell makes spoiled, rotten, poisonous, or otherwise contaminated food and water pure and suitable for consumption. Up to 1 cubic foot of food and/or drink per caster level may be purified. The reverse, putrefy food & drink, spoils food and drink, including holy water. Unholy water is spoiled by purify water.","notes":"You detoxify a volume of food and drink, removing spoilage, disease, and poisons. This spell also neutralises unholy water.\n\nDetails:\n\nThis spell affects objects, not creatures.\n\nIt makes substances safe for you.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Purify Food & Drink"},"cleric remove fear":{"name":"Remove Fear","level":"1","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn, or instantaneous (see below)","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Remove Fear\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Cause Fear\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nBy touch, the cleric instills courage in the recipient, granting a +4 bonus to saving throws against magical fear for 1 turn. If the recipient has already failed a saving throw against fear, the touch allows another saving throw. This new save gains a bonus of +1 per caster level. A “to hit” roll is required to touch an unwilling recipient. The reverse, cause fear, causes the target to flee in panic at maximum movement speed away from the caster for 1 round per cleric level. Cause fear may be countered by remove fear, and vice versa.","notes":"This spell bolsters courage: it either grants new saving throws versus existing fear effects or provides a bonus to future saving throws against fear.\n\nDetails:\n\nIf the target is already affected by fear, the spell is instantaneous and grants one new saving throw.\n\nIf the target is not already affected by fear, duration is 1 turn and the target gains +4 on each saving throw against fear.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Remove Fear"},"cleric resist cold":{"name":"Resist Cold","level":"1","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per cleric level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Resist Cold\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell protects the recipient’s body against cold. The recipient can withstand temperatures down to 0°F without discomfort, even while completely nude. Against greater cold, such as that from a sword of cold, ice storm, cold wand, or white dragon breath, the recipient receives a +3 bonus on saving throws. Cold damage is reduced as follows: failed saving throw, half damage; successful saving throw, one-quarter damage. The spell lasts 1 turn per caster level. Material Component: A pinch of sulphur.","notes":"This spell protects you or one creature from cold, including special protections against magical cold in combat.\n\nDetails:\n\nThe warded creature is safe from non-magical cold.\n\nAll cold damage is halved. If already halved, halve it again.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Resist Cold"},"cleric sanctuary":{"name":"Sanctuary","level":"1","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"2 rounds + 1 round per cleric level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"Sanctuary\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nWhen the cleric casts sanctuary, any opponent attempting to strike or attack the protected cleric must make a saving throw versus magic. If the saving throw fails, the opponent ignores the cleric and attacks another target instead. If the saving throw succeeds, the opponent may attack the cleric normally, including attack rolls, saving throws, and damage. This spell does not protect against area attacks such as fireball or ice storm. While protected by sanctuary, the cleric may not take offensive action. The cleric may still cast non-attack spells or act in non-offensive ways, such as healing wounds, casting bless, performing an augury, chanting, or casting light in an area, but not upon an opponent. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol and a small silver mirror.","notes":"You ward yourself or one other creature so that enemies perceive the protected creature as a low-priority target.\n\nFor the duration, any creature attempting an attack or targeted spell against the protected creature must first attempt a saving throw vs spells.\n\nDetails:\n\nIf the protected creature makes a weapon attack or uses a spell that affects an enemy, the spell ends.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Sanctuary"},"cleric endure cold endure heat":{"name":"Endure Cold / Endure Heat","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"9 turns per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Endure Cold / Endure Heat\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Endure Heat / Endure Cold\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 9 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell protects the recipient from normal extremes of cold or heat, depending on the version cast. The recipient can stand unclothed in temperatures as low as -30°F or as high as 130°F with no ill effect. Temperatures beyond those limits cause 1 hit point of exposure damage per hour for each degree beyond the limit. Without such protection, exposure damage is 1 hit point per turn per degree. The spell lasts for its duration or until the recipient is affected by any magical cold or magical heat, including white dragon breath. The spell is cancelled regardless of which version was used and regardless of whether magical heat or cold strikes the recipient. The recipient takes no damage from the magical heat or cold during the round in which the spell is broken, but is vulnerable starting the following round. The spell is instantly cancelled if resist fire or resist cold is cast on the recipient.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Endure Cold / Endure Heat"},"cleric aid":{"name":"Aid","level":"2","school":"Necromantic-Conjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round + 1 round per level","aoe":"One person","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Aid\n\nSchool: Necromantic-Conjuration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One person\nThe recipient gains the benefit of a bless spell and a special blessing of 1d8 additional hit points. The bless effect and added hit points last for the duration of aid. The added hit points can raise the recipient above their normal maximum. Damage taken while aid is active is subtracted from the temporary hit points before regular hit points are lost. Temporary hit points granted by aid that are lost cannot be restored by curative magic. For example, a 1st-level fighter with 8 hit points who has taken 2 damage receives aid granting 6 temporary hit points. The fighter now has 12 hit points, 6 temporary. If then hit for 7 damage, all 6 temporary hit points and 1 regular hit point are lost. Material Components: A tiny strip of white cloth with sticky substance such as tree sap on the ends, plus the cleric’s holy symbol.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Aid"},"cleric detect life":{"name":"Detect Life","level":"2","school":"Divination","range":"10’ per level","duration":"5 rounds","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Life\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 10’ per level\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 5 rounds\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell allows the cleric to determine whether a target creature is alive. It detects life in a recipient of feign death, a creature in a coma, deathlike trance, or suspended animation, and the body of a creature engaged in astral travel. It works on plants and plant creatures as well as animals. The spell’s range is reduced if more than 1 inch of wood or stone lies between the cleric and subject; each inch of wood or stone counts as 10 feet of open space. Any thickness of metal causes the spell to fail and be ruined. Any mental protection, whether psionic or magical, likewise ruins the spell without detection. The spell detects the first living creature along the cleric’s line of sight within range, or the first creature that crosses that line before the duration expires.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Detect Life"},"cleric dust devil":{"name":"Dust Devil","level":"2","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"3 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Dust Devil\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 3 rounds\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell conjures a weak air elemental called a dust devil. It has AC 4, 2 Hit Dice, MV 18”, one attack for 1d4 damage, and can be hit by normal weapons. Magic weapons of any type deal double damage to it. The dust devil appears as a small whirlwind 5 feet across at its base, 15 feet tall, and 10 feet across at the top. It moves as directed by the cleric, but is dispelled if ordered farther than 3” from the caster. Its winds can hold a gas cloud or gaseous creature at bay or push it away from the caster, though they cannot damage or dispel such a cloud. The winds can extinguish torches, small campfires, exposed lanterns, and other small nonmagical open flames. If moving across loose dust, sand, or ash, the dust devil creates a 30-foot-diameter cloud centered on itself. Normal vision is impossible through the cloud, and creatures caught in it are effectively blinded until 1 round after leaving. Spellcasting is nearly impossible within the cloud or the dust devil itself; even if the dust devil deals no damage, a spellcaster must save versus spell to maintain concentration. Any creature native to the Elemental Plane of Air can dismiss a dust devil at will from 3” or less. Creatures not native to the caster’s plane are unaffected. The dust devil is automatically dispelled if it contacts a creature with innate magic resistance, but only after it has a chance to hit and deal damage.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Dust Devil"},"cleric enthrall":{"name":"Enthrall","level":"2","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"3”","duration":"Special","aoe":"90’ radius","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Enthrall\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 90’ radius\nThis spell allows the cleric to bind and enthrall an audience that fully understands the cleric’s language. Listeners of the same race as the cleric may save versus spell. Listeners of a different race generally unfriendly to the cleric’s race save at +4. Creatures with more than 4 levels or Hit Dice, or Wisdom greater than 15, cannot be enthralled. The caster must speak without interruption for 1 full round. Thereafter, the enchantment lasts as long as the cleric continues speaking, up to 6 turns. Those who fail their saves view the cleric as if the cleric had Charisma 21, with loyalty base +70% and reaction adjustment +50%. They stand and listen, but do not act as if under a suggestion. When the cleric stops talking, the spell ends and listeners regain control. Any attack on the cleric or any attempt by the cleric to cast another spell or take another action cancels the spell. Audience members who save successfully view the cleric as having Charisma 3 and may, with a 50% chance, hoot and jeer, allowing new saving throws for other listeners. If the cleric abuses the spell by preaching a religion or alignment opposed to the audience’s beliefs, each offended listener gets a new saving throw at +5.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Enthrall"},"cleric holy symbol":{"name":"Holy Symbol","level":"2","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Holy Symbol\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One object\nThis spell prepares a cleric’s holy symbol or creates a new one to replace a lost or damaged symbol. The new symbol, which is the spell’s material component and is not consumed, must be made of appropriate material and proper shape and design for the religion or deity. A cleric cannot make just any object into a holy symbol. A cleric may possess two holy symbols at once, and this spell can create a spare. No cleric can create a holy symbol for a deity or religion other than their own. A good or evil cleric’s holy symbol radiates a faint aura of good or evil, but is not a magical object. A morally neutral cleric’s holy symbol has no such aura.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Holy Symbol"},"cleric messenger":{"name":"Messenger","level":"2","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"2” per level","duration":"1 hour per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Messenger\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2” per level\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 hour per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell allows the cleric to call upon a Small creature of at least animal intelligence to act as a messenger. It does not affect giant creatures, creatures with Intelligence 4 or higher, or creatures with low intelligence or better. If the creature is within range, the cleric may use desirable food as a lure to call it. The animal receives a saving throw versus spell; success causes the spell to fail. If the save fails, the animal approaches the cleric and awaits bidding. The cleric can communicate crudely with it, directing it to a certain place, though directions must be simple. The caster may attach a small item or note to the animal. If instructed, the animal waits at the location until the spell ends. If the intended recipient is not expecting an animal messenger, the carrier may be ignored. When the duration ends, the animal returns to normal activity. The intended receiver gains no communication ability.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Messenger"},"cleric withdraw":{"name":"Withdraw","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"The cleric","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Withdraw\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The cleric\nThis spell alters time’s flow with respect to the cleric. While only 1 segment passes for others, the cleric experiences 1 round for contemplation. The base duration is 2 segments, or 2 rounds from the cleric’s perspective, plus 1 additional increment per caster level. Thus, a 5th-level cleric may spend up to 6 rounds thinking while only 6 segments pass for everyone else. The Dungeon Master must allow the player 1 minute of real time per segment to ponder a problem or question. Discussion with unaffected characters is not permitted. While under withdraw, the cleric may only think, read, or cast augury, curing or healing spells, or informational spells, and such spells may only be cast on the cleric. Casting them differently, such as curing a companion, ends withdraw. The cleric cannot walk, run, become invisible, or take other actions. The cleric can still be affected by others, and any successful attack against the cleric breaks the spell.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Withdraw"},"cleric wyvern watch":{"name":"Wyvern Watch","level":"2","school":"Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"8 hours or until strike","aoe":"10’ diameter sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Wyvern Watch\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 8 hours or until strike\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 10’ diameter sphere\nThis spell creates an insubstantial haze vaguely resembling a wyvern and is commonly used to guard an area. Any creature approaching within 1” of the guarded area is subject to attack by the spell force. The “wyvern” strikes, and the target must save versus spell or stand paralyzed for 1 round per caster level, or until freed by the caster, dispel magic, or remove paralysis. A successful save means the wyvern-form missed, and the spell remains in place. Once a creature is successfully struck and paralyzed, the spell dissipates. It also dissipates if no intruder is struck within 8 hours. A creature approaching the guarded space may detect the presence of the wyvern-form before coming close enough to be attacked: 90% in bright light, 30% in twilight, and 0% in darkness. Material Component: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol.\n\nCleric Spells, 3rd Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Wyvern Watch"},"cleric cloudburst":{"name":"Cloudburst","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round","aoe":"3” diameter cylinder up to 6” high","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None and special","save_type":"","description":"Cloudburst\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: None and special\nArea of Effect: 3” diameter cylinder up to 6” high\nThis spell causes atmospheric water vapor to precipitate instantly as huge drops of rain, creating a true downburst and drawing more vapor into the area to be precipitated. Everything in the area is drenched within 1 segment, with rain falling at 1/10 inch per segment, or 1 inch in 1 round. All normal fires in the area are extinguished: small fires instantly, medium fires in 3–5 segments, and large fires in 8–10 segments. Magical fires are also extinguished according to general rules. Permanent magical fires relight in 1–2 rounds. Small rekindlable magical fires, such as a flame tongue sword, are affected only during the actual cloudburst. Spells such as produce fire and burning hands are negated. Large-area fire spells such as fireball, flame strike, or wall of fire vaporize the rain as they are extinguished, producing a steam cloud four times as large as the fire spell’s area, up to 12” diameter and 24” high. The steam deals 1d3 damage per round to normal creatures and double that to cold-dwelling or cold-using creatures. The steam lasts 2d4+1 rounds, half that in a breeze, or 1 round in strong wind. In arid regions, cloudburst acts only as a double-strength precipitation spell. In hot and humid areas, the duration extends to 2 rounds. At temperatures from 33°F to 31°F, sleet falls and forms ice and slush. At 30°F or lower, the spell becomes a snowburst, dropping 1 inch of snow per segment. Material Components: Powdered silver, powdered iodine crystals, and the cleric’s holy symbol.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Cloudburst"},"cleric death s door":{"name":"Death’s Door","level":"3","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"1 hour per level","aoe":"One human or demi-human","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Death’s Door\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 hour per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One human or demi-human\nThis spell allows the cleric to touch a human or demi-human who is unconscious and “at death’s door,” meaning at -1 to -9 hit points. The spell immediately brings the individual to 0 hit points. While the subject remains unconscious, bleeding and deterioration stop for the spell’s duration. Because the subject is now at 0 hit points, they may be restored to consciousness and healed by cure light wounds, cure serious wounds, healing potions, extra-healing potions, or other magical healing. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol, a bit of white linen, and any form of unguent.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Death’s Door"},"cleric flame walk":{"name":"Flame Walk","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn + 1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Flame Walk\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 turn + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the caster or another man-sized creature of comparable mass to withstand nonmagical fires up to 2,000°F. It also grants a +2 bonus on saving throws against magical fires. For each caster level above the minimum required to cast the spell, the cleric may affect one additional man-sized creature. This allows multiple individuals or larger creatures to be affected. For example, an 11th-level caster could affect both themselves and a horse, allowing mounted travel through molten lava. A horse counts as 6 humans for this spell; halfling-sized creatures count as ½ human, and pixie-sized creatures count as ¼ human. Material Components: At least 500 gp worth of powdered ruby and the cleric’s holy or unholy symbol.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Flame Walk"},"cleric magical vestment":{"name":"Magical Vestment","level":"3","school":"Conjuration/Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 rounds per level","aoe":"The cleric","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Magical Vestment\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 6 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The cleric\nThis spell enchants the caster’s vestment, providing protection equivalent to armor. It functions only while the cleric is on ground consecrated to their deity. If armor or another protective device is worn during the spell, the vestment protects as normal chain mail. If no other protection is worn, the vestment gains a +1 enchantment for every 4 caster levels, to a maximum of chain mail +4, or base AC 1. The spell lasts 6 rounds per caster level, or until the caster loses consciousness or leaves the consecrated area. Material Components: The vestment to be enchanted and the cleric’s holy or unholy symbol.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Magical Vestment"},"cleric meld into stone":{"name":"Meld Into Stone","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"8 rounds + 1d8 rounds","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Meld Into Stone\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 8 rounds + 1d8 rounds\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the cleric to merge their body and worn or carried possessions into a large stone. The cleric must stand next to a stone large enough to contain their body in all three dimensions while holding a small sample of the same type of stone. When casting is complete, the cleric and up to 100 pounds of nonliving gear blend into the stone. Magical artifacts and relics are unaffected. If the stone is too small or the cleric carries more than 100 pounds of gear, the spell fails and is wasted. The spell lasts 9–16 rounds, with the variable portion secretly rolled by the DM. Before the duration expires, the cleric may step out through the same surface used to enter. The spell does not allow movement through stone as passwall or phase door would. If the duration ends before the cleric exits, the cleric is expelled and takes 4d8 damage, and each affected item must save versus petrification or turn to stone. While inside the stone, the cleric is aware of time passing but cannot see or hear outside events. Certain spells harm the cleric if cast on the occupied stone: stone to flesh expels the cleric and deals 4d8 damage, but items need not save; stone shape deals 4d4 damage without expelling the cleric; transmute rock to mud expels the cleric and kills them instantly unless they save versus spell.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Meld Into Stone"},"cleric negative plane protection":{"name":"Negative Plane Protection","level":"3","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"One Prime Material Plane creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Negative Plane Protection\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One Prime Material Plane creature\nThis spell partially protects the caster or another touched creature from undead with existence on the Negative Material Plane, such as shadows, wights, wraiths, spectres, and vampires. The spell opens a channel to the Positive Material Plane, offsetting the undead attack. If the recipient is touched or attacked by such an undead creature, the recipient may save versus death magic. Success means the recipient takes normal hit point damage but suffers no experience drain; the undead creature also takes 2d6 damage from Positive Plane energy. The magic protects against only one such attack and then dissipates whether the saving throw succeeds or fails. If the saving throw fails, the recipient takes double normal physical damage in addition to the usual experience loss. The spell also protects against a magic-user’s energy drain, though the magic-user is not harmed. Contact between Positive and Negative Planes causes a bright flash and thunderclap sound, but neither causes damage. The spell lasts 1 turn per caster level or until triggered by a successful undead attack. This spell cannot be cast on the Negative Material Plane.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Negative Plane Protection"},"cleric remove paralysis":{"name":"Remove Paralysis","level":"3","school":"Abjuration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1–4 creatures in a 2” × 2” area","components":"V, S","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Remove Paralysis\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Cause Paralysis\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1–4 creatures in a 2” × 2” area\nThis spell frees creatures from paralysis or similar forces, such as a hold spell. The cleric casts the spell and points in the proper direction, affecting up to 4 creatures within range and area of effect. There must be no physical or magical barrier between caster and targets, or the spell fails and is wasted. Each target receives a new saving throw versus paralysis, with a +3 bonus if one creature is affected, +2 if two creatures are affected, and +1 if three or four creatures are affected. The reverse, cause paralysis, affects one touched target. The cleric must touch the victim with a successful “to hit” roll using the holy or unholy symbol. If the victim fails a saving throw versus spell, paralysis lasts 1d6 rounds plus 1 round per caster level. Good-aligned clerics should be discerning in using cause paralysis, and some good-aligned orders may prohibit it.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Remove Paralysis"},"cleric water walk":{"name":"Water Walk","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn + 1 turn per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Water Walk\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 turn + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the caster or another man-sized creature of comparable mass to walk on water as if it were firm, grassy ground. For each caster level above the minimum required to create the dweomer, the cleric may affect one additional man-sized creature. This allows multiple individuals or larger creatures to be affected. For example, an 11th-level caster could also affect a horse, allowing mounted travel atop waves. A horse counts as 6 humans for this spell. Material Components: A piece of cork and the cleric’s holy or unholy symbol.\n\nCleric Spells, 4th Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Water Walk"},"cleric abjure":{"name":"Abjure","level":"4","school":"Abjuration","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Abjure\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Implore\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell attempts to return a creature from another plane to its own plane. The cleric must know the exact name of the creature type, and if the creature has a proper name, that name must also be known and used. The cleric compares their level to the creature’s level or Hit Dice as with dispel magic: base 50% chance of success, adjusted by the level or Hit Dice difference. If the percentile roll is equal to or less than the chance to abjure, the creature is instantly sent back to its plane. Otherwise, the spell fails. The creature may not wish to remain on the caster’s plane and could be appreciative. The reverse, implore, entreats a like-aligned creature from another plane to come to the cleric. Success is determined the same way, and the caster must know the creature type’s exact name and proper name if any. If implore succeeds, there is no guarantee the summoned creature is favorably disposed. Neither version works on deities, though it may affect their servants or minions. Material Components: For abjure, a holy or unholy symbol, holy or unholy water, and often something inimical to the creature. For implore, the same components are used except the last must be something the implored creature craves or respects.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Abjure"},"cleric cloak of fear":{"name":"Cloak of Fear","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"The cleric","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Cloak Of Fear\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nReversible: Cloak Of Bravery\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: The cleric\nThis spell causes the cleric to radiate a personal aura of fear to a 30-foot radius. Any creature or character entering the aura must save versus spell or flee in fear for 6 rounds. The spell remains until one creature fails its save, at which point the dweomer dissipates. The spell has no effect on creatures that radiate fear or undead of any sort, and contact with such creatures does not dissipate it. It also remains if an intruder saves successfully, but expires after 1 turn per caster level if not triggered earlier. Members of the cleric’s party are not immune. The cleric may cancel the aura before the duration ends. The reverse, cloak of bravery, may be cast on the cleric or another willing creature. The recipient gains a +3 bonus on a saving throw against magical fear. The spell works only once and only for one figure, and is dispelled whether or not the recipient succeeds. It does not negate a creature’s innate fear aura, so that creature can still affect others nearby. Material Components: For cloak of fear, a miniature quiver and a chicken feather. For cloak of bravery, a drop of alcohol and the brain of a newt.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Cloak of Fear"},"cleric giant insect":{"name":"Giant Insect","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"2”","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"One or more insects","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Giant Insect\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Shrink Insect\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2”\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One or more insects\nThis spell transforms one or more normal insects into larger forms resembling giant insects. The number and total Hit Dice depend on caster level: at 7th–9th level, one insect and 3 total Hit Dice; at 10th–11th level, two insects and 4 total Hit Dice; at 12th–13th level, three insects and 5 total Hit Dice; at 14th level or higher, four insects and 6 total Hit Dice. The spell affects only one type of insect per casting. Casting time is 1 round per Hit Die of the resulting giant creature or creatures; if interrupted, the insects die and the spell is ruined. A created monster has as many attacks per round as its standard giant version, but deals full damage only if it has as many Hit Dice as that usual form. It can never exceed the listed damage for the standard giant form. For example, a 14th-level cleric can enlarge a wasp to 6 Hit Dice, instead of the usual 4 Hit Dice, but its damage remains 2d8/1d4. A 7th-level cleric could create a 3-Hit-Die giant wasp dealing 2d6/1d3, or three-fourths normal damage. The spell works only on true insects, not arachnids, crustaceans, or other small creatures. Created giant insects do not gain the special attacks or defenses of standard giant forms, though armor class, movement, and physical characteristics are as listed. Created insects do not attack the cleric, but the cleric’s control is limited to simple commands such as attack, defend, or guard. They cannot be directed to attack a specific creature or guard against a particular event. Unless commanded otherwise, they attack whatever is nearby. The reverse, shrink insect, reduces standard giant insects or insects created by this spell. Reduction is 1 Hit Die per 4 caster levels, to a maximum reduction of 6 Hit Dice and a minimum of 1/8 Hit Die or 1 hit point. Special attacks are retained at weaker level, allowing saving throw bonuses. For example, a 9th-level cleric can reduce a 4-Hit-Die giant wasp to 1 Hit Die; it retains poison, but saves against it gain at least +3, and normal damage is reduced to one-fourth. Material Component: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Giant Insect"},"cleric imbue with spell ability":{"name":"Imbue With Spell Ability","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"One individual","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Imbue With Spell Ability\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One individual\nThis spell allows the cleric to bestow the ability to cast a particular spell on a character normally unable to cast spells. It works only on thieves, fighters, cavaliers, assassins, monks, rangers below 8th level, and paladins below 9th level. It does not work on other classes or subclasses, monsters, or individuals with less than one full Hit Die. The transferred spells must be spells the cleric currently has prepared, and they must be informational or defensive spells, or cure light wounds. Attempting to transfer any other spell causes the whole spell to fail, even if allowable spells were also chosen. Up to three spells may be imbued: one 2nd-level spell and one or two 1st-level spells. To receive any spell, the recipient must have Wisdom 9 or higher. A single 1st-level spell may be imbued in any eligible recipient. The recipient must be at least 3rd level to receive two 1st-level spells, and at least 5th level to receive a 2nd-level spell. If transferred spell characteristics vary by caster level, the recipient casts them at their own level. All other spell details, such as casting time and components, apply normally. When the cleric casts this spell, the transferred spells are lost from the cleric’s repertoire, and the cleric cannot memorize more spells until the recipient uses all transferred spells. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol, plus a minor borrowed item symbolic of the recipient’s profession, such as a lock pick for a thief or dagger for an assassin. The borrowed item is consumed.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Imbue With Spell Ability"},"cleric spell immunity":{"name":"Spell Immunity","level":"4","school":"Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"One individual","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Spell Immunity\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One individual\nThis spell makes the cleric or touched creature immune to the effects of one specified spell of 4th level or lower that the cleric has directly experienced. For example, if the cleric has previously been struck by fireball, the spell can protect someone from fireball. It cannot affect a recipient already magically protected by a spell or other temporary effect. The spell protects only against actual cast spells, not magic item effects or innate spell-like abilities, but immunity lasts for the full duration. Only one spell immunity may affect a creature at a time; later applications have no effect until the first ends. The immunity does not extend to carried items, which must still save normally if applicable. Protection applies only to one specific spell, not to a class or group of similar spells. Thus, immunity to lightning bolt does not protect against shocking grasp. Material Component: The same component, if any, as the spell being protected against.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Spell Immunity"},"cleric spike growth":{"name":"Spike Growth","level":"4","school":"Alteration/Enchantment","range":"6”","duration":"1d6 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"10’ square per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Spike Growth\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enchantment\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1d6 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10’ square per caster level\nThis spell works wherever moderate-size or dense plant growth is present. It causes ground-covering vegetation, roots, or rootlets to become very hard and sharply pointed. The ground appears unchanged but acts as if strewn with caltrops. In bare ground or earthen pits, roots and rootlets function the same way. Without true seeing, similar magic, or special detection such as detect traps, the affected area is undetectable until a victim enters and takes damage. Even then, the creature cannot determine the area’s extent without magical detection. For each 1” of movement through the area, a victim suffers 2 attacks from the spike growth. Hit probability is as if the spellcaster were attacking, and each hit deals 1d4 damage. Spells that control or harm vegetation, or dispel magic, negate the area. Material Components: The cleric’s holy symbol and either seven sharp thorns or seven small twigs sharpened to points.\n\nCleric Spells, 5th Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Spike Growth"},"cleric air walk":{"name":"Air Walk","level":"5","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Air Walk\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 6 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell allows the cleric to walk on air as if it were solid ground. Moving upward is like walking uphill. Ascending at a 45-degree angle halves movement, ascending at 60 degrees reduces movement to one-quarter, and moving straight up is at one-eighth normal movement. Descending is faster by the inverse proportions, so straight downward movement can be up to eight times normal speed, or slower if desired. An air-walking creature always controls its movement rate and can stop suddenly to avoid crashing. If gust of wind is active in the area, movement into the gust is at half normal rate, while movement with the gust is at double normal rate. The spell can be placed on any touched creature up to giant size. For example, it may be cast on a trained horse and ridden through the air, though an untrained animal would panic. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol and a bit of thistledown.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Air Walk"},"cleric animate dead monsters":{"name":"Animate Dead Monsters","level":"5","school":"Necromantic","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Animate Dead Monsters\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the caster to animate one humanoid or semi-humanoid skeleton or corpse for every 2 caster levels. The animated remains obey commands. Direct commands or instructions of up to about 12 words are followed. Monster types that can be animated include apes, carnivorous apes, giant apes, bugbears, ettins, giants of all kinds, ogres, and trolls of all kinds. In general, the remains must be bipedal monsters of more than 3 Hit Dice with endoskeletons similar to humans, except larger than 7 feet tall. Corpses animated by this spell are treated as monster zombies, or as normal living creatures of the same form if that creature type normally has fewer than 6 Hit Dice. Skeletons animated by this spell are treated as monsters with half the normal Hit Dice, rounded up. Animated monsters receive normal physical attacks, but no special attacks or defenses other than those typical of monster zombies or skeletons. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol and a small specimen of the type of creature to be animated.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Animate Dead Monsters"},"cleric golem":{"name":"Golem","level":"5","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"8 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Golem\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nTo cast this spell, the cleric must first personally construct the form of the golem and place a prayer spell upon it. All golems must be man-shaped and approximately man-sized, though they may be as small as 3 feet or as large as 7 feet tall. The type of lesser golem depends on material and caster level. At 9th level or higher, the cleric may create a straw golem. Construction time is 1 hour, duration is 1 hour per caster level, and it has AC 10, MV 12”, HD 2+4, 20 hp, 2 attacks, 1d2/1d2 damage, immunity to piercing weapons, half damage from blunt weapons, and 30-pound carrying capacity; it takes double damage from flame. At 11th level or higher, the cleric may create a rope golem. Construction time is 3 hours, duration is 3 hours per caster level, and it has AC 8, MV 9”, HD 3+6, 30 hp, 1 attack, 1d6 damage plus strangulation for 6 damage per round after a hit until destroyed or released, immunity to blunt weapons, half damage from piercing weapons, and 40-pound carrying capacity. At 13th level or higher, the cleric may create a leather golem. Construction time is 9 hours, duration is 6 hours per caster level, and it has AC 6, MV 6”, HD 4+8, 40 hp, 2 attacks, 1d6/1d6 damage, requires +1 or better magic weapon to hit, takes half damage from blunt weapons, and has 50-pound carrying capacity. At 15th level or higher, the cleric may create a wood golem. Construction time is 27 hours, duration is 12 hours per caster level, and it has AC 4, MV 3”, HD 5+10, 50 hp, 1 attack, 3d4 damage, requires +1 or better magic weapon to hit, is immune to blunt and piercing weapons, and has 60-pound carrying capacity. These creations are lesser golems, distinct from Monster Manual golems. They have no minds, so charm, fear, hold, sleep, and similar spells do not affect them. A lesser golem saves as a cleric of the creator’s level. Lesser golems cannot speak, but understand and obey simple instructions of no more than about 12 words.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Golem"},"cleric magic font":{"name":"Magic Font","level":"5","school":"Divination","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 turns","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Magic Font\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 5 turns\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes a holy or unholy water font to serve as a scrying device. It works only if the cleric is in good standing with their deity. The basin of holy or unholy water becomes similar to a crystal ball. For each vial of capacity in the font basin, the cleric may scry for 1 round, so the spell’s duration depends directly on the font’s size. Detection chances for scrying are handled as with a crystal ball and the magic mirror spell. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol and the font with its trappings; these are not consumed.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Magic Font"},"cleric rainbow":{"name":"Rainbow","level":"5","school":"Evocation/Alteration","range":"12”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Rainbow\n\nSchool: Evocation/Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nTo cast this spell, the cleric must see a rainbow or have a special substitute component. The spell has four possible applications chosen at casting. Bow: The spell creates a shimmering, multi-layered rainbow bow. It is light and easy to draw, so anyone with Strength 6 or better can use it. It is magical, and each missile counts as a +3 weapon. There is no non-proficiency penalty, but only a character class normally permitted to use bows may use it. The bow fires 7 missiles before disappearing, once or twice per round as desired. Each shot releases one color, and that color leaves the bow. Each arrow deals double damage to certain targets: red against fire dwellers or users; orange against earth elementals; yellow against vegetable targets including fungus creatures, shambling mounds, and treants; green against aquatic creatures and water elementals; blue against aerial creatures, electricity-using creatures, and air elementals; indigo against acid-using or poison-using creatures; violet against metallic or regenerating creatures. When drawn, an arrow of the selected color appears. If no color is chosen, or a used color is requested, the next color in spectrum order appears. Bridge: The rainbow forms a seven-colored bridge. The bridge is as many feet wide as the cleric has levels and can bear weight in hundreds of pounds equal to the cleric’s level. It is at least 20 feet long and may be up to 120 feet long, as desired. If its weight limit is exceeded, it disappears. Otherwise, it lasts for the spell duration or until dismissed. Elevator: The rainbow lifts the cleric and all creatures within 10 feet skyward. It carries them along an arc as high as the cleric desires, and down again if desired. The cleric must reach safety before the duration expires, or the elevator disappears. Movement along the elevator is 12”, and the rainbow arc trails 12” behind the travelers. Flagon: The rainbow condenses into a seven-colored vessel holding seven measures of pure water. Each measure poured out mixes with one hue and becomes a magical draught. Unused measures disappear when the spell ends. Draught effects are: red, cure light wounds; orange, resist fire; yellow, cure blindness; green, slow poison; blue, cure disease; indigo, resist cold; violet, remove paralysis. Each draught functions as if cast by a 12th-level cleric, and the effects persist after the spell ends. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol and a vial of holy or unholy water. If no rainbow is nearby, the cleric may substitute a diamond worth at least 1,000 gp, specially prepared in sight of a rainbow by casting bless and prayer on it. Only the holy symbol remains after casting.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Rainbow"},"cleric spike stones":{"name":"Spike Stones","level":"5","school":"Alteration/Enchantment","range":"3”","duration":"3d4 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"1” square per level, 1 spike per 10’ square","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Spike Stones\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enchantment\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 3d4 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” square per level, 1 spike per 10’ square\nThis spell causes rock to form long, sharp points that tend to blend into the background. It works on both natural rock and worked stone. The spike stones impede movement and inflict damage. If carefully observed, each observer has a 25% chance to notice the sharp rock points. Otherwise, creatures entering the area suffer 1d4 damage from each spike stone that hits, with attacks made as if by the caster. Creatures entering the area are attacked immediately upon setting foot in it and on each step afterward. The first step reveals the danger only if the initial attack hits; otherwise, movement continues and the stones remain unnoticed until damage occurs. Charging or running victims suffer 2 attacks per 1” of movement rate over the area after initial damage before they can stop. Others suffer only 1 additional attack-like check. Creatures falling into pits affected by spike stones suffer 6 such attack checks, each with +2 “to hit” per 10 feet fallen and +2 damage per 10 feet fallen, in addition to normal falling damage. Material Component: Four tiny stalactites.\n\nCleric Spells, 6th Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Spike Stones"},"cleric forbiddance":{"name":"Forbiddance","level":"6","school":"Abjuration","range":"3”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"6 cubic “ per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 rounds","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Forbiddance\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 6 rounds\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 6 cubic “ per level\nThis spell may be used only to secure a consecrated area. The effect on creatures entering depends on their ethics and morals compared to the caster’s. Creatures with identical morals and ethics cannot enter unless they know the password, with no saving throw. Creatures with different ethics must save versus spell to enter; failure causes 2d12 damage. Creatures with different morals must save versus spell to enter; failure causes 4d6 damage. Effects are cumulative, so multiple saving throws may be required. Once a creature fails a saving throw, it can never enter the forbidden area until the spell ends. The caster is immune to the spell. Intruders who enter by succeeding on saves still feel uneasy and tense. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol, holy or unholy water, silver or dung, and iron or sulfur.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Forbiddance"},"cleric heroes feast":{"name":"Heroes’ Feast","level":"6","school":"Evocation","range":"1”","duration":"1 hour","aoe":"One individual per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Heroes’ Feast\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 1 hour\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One individual per caster level\nThis spell creates a great feast serving as many creatures as the cleric has levels. It creates a magnificent table, chairs, service, and all necessary food and drink. Those who partake are cured of all diseases, immune to poison for 12 hours, and healed of 5d4 damage after drinking the nectar-like beverage. The ambrosia-like food grants an effect equal to bless for 12 hours. During the same period, participants are immune to fear, hopelessness, and panic. The feast takes 1 full hour to consume, and benefits begin only after that hour. If interrupted for any reason, the spell is ruined and all effects are negated. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol and specially fermented honey taken from cells of bee larvae destined for royal status.\n\nCleric Spells, 7th Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Heroes’ Feast"},"cleric exaction":{"name":"Exaction","level":"7","school":"Evocation-Alteration","range":"1”","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Exaction\n\nSchool: Evocation-Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell allows the cleric to confront a powerful creature from another plane, such as a deva or powerful named demon, but not a demigod or deity, and require a duty or quest. The creature cannot be ethically or morally opposed to the cleric; for example, it cannot be evil if the cleric is good, or chaotic if the cleric is lawful. A true neutral creature is considered greatly opposed to both good and evil, and to both law and chaos. The caster must know something about the creature to exact service from it, or else offer fair trade. If the cleric knows the creature has received a favor from someone of the cleric’s alignment, this may be named as cause; otherwise, a valuable gift or service must be pledged in return. The service must be reasonable relative to the past or promised favor or reward. The spell acts as a quest upon the creature. When the service is completed, the creature is transported to the cleric’s vicinity, and the cleric must immediately return the promised reward, whether by cancelling a debt, granting a service, or giving material reward. Once this is done, the creature is freed to return to its plane. Failure to fulfill the promise exactly subjects the cleric to exaction by the creature or its superior at minimum. At worst, the creature may attack the cleric with complete immunity to that cleric’s spell powers. Material Components: The cleric’s holy or unholy symbol, matter or substance from the creature’s plane, and written knowledge of the creature’s nature or actions on a parchment leaf, which is burned to seal the bargain.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Exaction"},"cleric succor":{"name":"Succor","level":"7","school":"Alteration-Enchantment","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"One individual","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 day","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Succor\n\nSchool: Alteration-Enchantment\nReversible: Summon Cleric\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 day\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One individual\nThis spell creates a powerful dweomer in a specially prepared object, such as prayer beads, a small clay tablet, or an ivory baton. The object radiates magic and can instantly transport its possessor to the sanctuary of the cleric who created it. Once the item is enchanted, the cleric must willingly give it to an individual and tell them the command word. To use it, the recipient speaks the command word while rending or breaking the item. The individual and everything worn or carried are instantly transported to the cleric’s sanctuary as if by word of recall. No other creatures can be affected. The reverse allows the cleric to be transported to the immediate vicinity of the item’s possessor when the item is broken and the command word spoken. The cleric may choose not to answer the summons at that instant, but if they refuse, the opportunity is lost forever and the spell is wasted. Material Component: A specially prepared item costing 2,000–5,000 gp.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Succor"},"cleric silence 15 radius":{"name":"Silence 15’ Radius","level":"2","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"120 ft","duration":"2 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"15 ft radius sphere around the target","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"See below","save_type":"","description":"Silence, 15’ Radius\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 12”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 30’ diameter sphere\nWhen this spell is cast, complete silence fills the area of effect. All sound stops, conversation becomes impossible, spells cannot be cast, and no noise issues from the affected area. The spell may be cast into the air or upon an object. It lasts 2 rounds per caster level: 2 rounds at 1st level, 4 at 2nd level, 6 at 3rd level, 8 at 4th level, and so on. The spell may also be cast upon a creature, causing the silence to radiate from and move with that creature. If the creature is unwilling, it receives a saving throw. If the save succeeds, the spell effect is centered about 1 foot behind the target creature.","notes":"Creates a zone of silence centred on a creature, object, or point in space. Within the area:\n    No sound can be produced; and\n    No sound can be heard, even from outside the zone.\nDetails:\n    Objects and points in space receive no saving throw.\n    A creature target may choose a saving throw vs spells and other magical effects:\n        Success: the target becomes the 5 ft square the creature is standing in (the creature can move out).\n        Failure: the creature remains the target; the silence moves with it.\n    Combat effects:\n        No one can cast spells with a verbal component within the area.\n        Attempts to sneak or move quietly always succeed if the creature is within the area.\n        Echolocation-dependent creatures (e.g., bats, dolphins) are blinded and suffer -4 “to hit”.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Silence 15’ Radius"},"cleric spiritual hammer":{"name":"Spiritual Hammer","level":"2","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"30 ft","duration":"1 round per cleric level","aoe":"30 ft radius around you","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Spiritual Hammer\n\nSchool: Invocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One opponent\nBy calling upon their deity, the cleric creates a hammer-shaped field of force. As long as the cleric concentrates, the force may strike any opponent within range as desired. The force strikes as a magical weapon equal to +1 per 3 caster levels for purposes of hitting creatures that require magical weapons, though it gains no magical bonuses “to hit.” It deals the same damage as a normal war hammer: 1d6 against man-sized or smaller opponents, and 1d4 against larger opponents. The hammer attacks at the cleric’s own level, as if the cleric were personally wielding it. When the cleric stops concentrating, the hammer is dispelled. If the cleric is behind an opponent, the force may strike from that position, gaining applicable bonuses and negating defensive protections such as shield and Dexterity. Material Component: A normal war hammer, which the cleric hurls toward opponents while uttering a plea to their deity. The hammer disappears when the spell is cast.","notes":"Creates a magical force shaped like a weapon (usually a hammer; may match your deity’s sacred weapon). It cannot move more than 30 ft from you, but within that radius it attacks where you direct it.\nDetails:\n    Each round until the spell ends, you may attack one creature within range using the spiritual weapon. Roll to hit as if using a regular weapon.\n    On a hit, it deals 1d6 magical damage (not blunt/piercing/slashing; can harm creatures immune to mundane weapons, and isn’t treated as a “weapon” for those purposes).\n    The weapon is not physical and can pass through obstacles (including walls) as long as it stays within the area.\n    If you direct it to attack a target you can’t see, you are effectively blinded with respect to that target.\n    If it attacks from behind, it gains the normal rear-attack bonus (usually +2).\n    You must concentrate to maintain the spell, or it ends (see Concentration rules).","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Spiritual Hammer"},"cleric create food water":{"name":"Create Food & Water","level":"3","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"10 ft","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"See below","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Create Food & Water\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per level\nWhen this spell is cast, the cleric causes food and/or water to appear. The food is highly nourishing, and each cubic foot sustains three human-sized creatures or one horse-sized creature for a full day. The spell creates 1 cubic foot of food and/or water per caster level. For example, a 2nd-level cleric creates 2 cubic feet, a 3rd-level cleric creates 3 cubic feet, a 4th-level cleric creates 4 cubic feet, and so on. The created volume may be divided between food and water.","notes":"Conjures basic food and water from thin air. You choose the form of the food, but it is plain fare.\nDetails:\n    Food is safe when conjured but spoils normally thereafter.\n    For each cleric level, you conjure up to one day’s rations for one human-sized creature.\n    The target point can’t be inside a creature.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Create Food & Water"},"cleric neutralize poison":{"name":"Neutralize Poison","level":"4","school":"Divine transmutation","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"1 ft cube per 2 cleric levels, or one creature","components":"V, S","ct":"7 segments","save":"Depends on use (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Neutralize Poison\n\nSchool: Alteration\nReversible: Poison\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched or 1 cubic foot of substance per 2 levels\nBy means of neutralize poison, the cleric detoxifies any venom in the creature or substance touched. An unwilling opponent, such as a poisonous reptile, snake, or envenomed weapon’s wielder, requires the cleric to score a melee touch hit. The effect is permanent only for poison present at the time of the touch; creatures or objects that generate new poison are not permanently detoxified. The reverse, poison, also requires a successful touch attack. The victim then receives a saving throw versus poison; if unsuccessful, the victim is killed.","notes":"Purges venom/toxin/contaminant, rendering it harmless. Can potentially revive someone who has recently “died” from poison.\nDetails:\n    Does not affect disease-based contamination.\n    Gods/demigods/artifacts/relics/equivalent are not affected (GM may allow some derivative effects to be affected).\n    If targeting a toxic place, all toxins/contaminants are purged from the area.\nUsing the spell to de-venom an opponent:\n    If the target is a creature, it may choose a saving throw vs spells and other magical effects.\n        Success: not affected.\n        Failure: if it has a venomous attack, the venom component is nullified until dawn the next day.\nUsing the spell to revive someone “dead by poison”:\n    If the target is poisoned, all toxins are purged, but poison damage already taken remains.\n    Also works on creatures that have recently died of poison: death from poison damage or failed save vs poison within a number of turns equal to your cleric level.\nReversible as Poison:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Neutralize Poison"},"cleric protection from evil 10 radius":{"name":"Protection From Evil, 10’ Radius","level":"4","school":"Divine abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"10 rounds per cleric level","aoe":"10 ft radius around the creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Protection From Evil, 10’ Radius\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Protection From Good, 10’ Radius\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 20’ diameter sphere\nThis spell is identical to protection from evil, except it covers a much larger area and lasts longer. Material Component: The cleric must trace a 20-foot diameter circle using holy water or blood, incense or smoldering dung, according to the protection from evil spell.","notes":"Creates a 10 ft radius invisible barrier against evil and summoned creatures around the protected creature.\nDetails:\n    Cast on yourself or another willing creature; not on hostile creatures, objects, or places.\n    A creature can only be affected by one instance at a time. If already warded by the 1st-level protection from evil, this spell has no effect on it.\n    Effects within the warded area:\n        Evil creatures: -2 to attack rolls into the warded area; anyone inside gains +2 on saving throws caused by evil creatures or their effects.\n        Evil effects (rare): effects explicitly described as evil/fiendish/demonic/devilish allow +2 to saving throws.\n        Summoned/conjured creatures: cannot attack into the warded area by touch (claws, teeth, etc.), regardless of alignment. They only suffer the -2 penalty in (1) if they are evil. (A non-evil summoned creature could still attack with a long weapon if it can reach.)\n    Ghouls: additionally “kept at bay” (cannot reduce distance to the warded area), but if the warded area moves toward them, they need not retreat. Some GMs extend “kept at bay” beyond ghouls.\nReversible as Protection from Good 10 ft Radius:","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Protection From Evil, 10’ Radius"},"cleric holy unholy word":{"name":"Holy (Unholy) Word","level":"7","school":"Divine conjuration","range":"Nil","duration":"Varies","aoe":"30 ft radius","components":"V","ct":"Fast","save":"None (see below)","save_type":"","description":"Holy Word / Unholy Word\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” radius\nThe utterance of a holy word or unholy word has tremendous power. It drives off evil or good creatures from other planes, forcing them to return to their own planes of existence. It also affects creatures of differing alignment within the 6” diameter area of effect centered on the cleric. Creatures with fewer than 4 Hit Dice or levels are killed. Creatures with 4 to 7+ Hit Dice or levels are paralyzed for 1d4 turns. Creatures with 8 to 11+ Hit Dice or levels are stunned for 2d4 rounds, move at -50%, and attack at -4. Creatures with 12 or more Hit Dice or levels are deafened for 1d4 rounds, move at -25%, attack at -2, and have a 50% chance of spell failure.","notes":"Utter a holy word; all non-good-aligned creatures in the area suffer severe effects.\nDetails:\n    All fiends and evil-aligned elementals are instantly banished to their home plane.\n    Other non-good creatures suffer based on level/HD:\n        < 4: Killed (instant)\n        4–7: Paralyzed for 10d4 rounds\n        8–11: Move halved; -4 to attacks for 2d4 rounds\n            11: Move -10 ft; -2 to attacks for 1d4 rounds\n    Deities/similar power unaffected.\n    Does not work in the Lower Outer Planes.\n    Alignment interpretation is GM-facing: some tables apply it to any non-good; others only to evil.\nReversible as Unholy Word.","link":"","class":"Cleric","select_value":"Cleric: Holy (Unholy) Word"},"cleric ceremony druid":{"name":"Ceremony, Druid","level":"1","school":"Invocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature, item, or area","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 hour","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Ceremony\n\nSchool: Invocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 hour\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature, item, or area\nThe druidic ceremony spell is similar to the clerical spell of the same name and has several applications within the druidic hierarchy. The spell does not leave behind a magical aura, though know alignment or similar magic might reveal the force of true neutrality involved. Druidic ceremonies include: 1st-level druid: coming of age, rest eternal, marriage; 3rd-level druid: dedication, investiture; 7th-level druid: initiation, special vows; 9th-level druid: hallowed ground; 12th-level druid: cast out. Coming of age is performed upon young people in druidic societies, usually at age 14, and symbolizes entry into adulthood. Its effects are the same as the clerical version, granting a +1 bonus to one saving throw. Rest eternal is cast upon a deceased being’s body, hastening the soul or spirit to its final resting place. Raise dead and resurrection cannot restore life to a creature affected by this spell, though wish can. Marriage is essentially identical to the clerical ceremony of the same name. Dedication admits the recipient into the ranks of the druid’s followers or worshipers, provided the recipient is true neutral. The recipient is charged with preserving and protecting nature and the balance of forces in the world. Otherwise, it is similar to the clerical ceremony. Investiture must be performed before a character can become an Aspirant, or 1st-level druid. It grants no other benefit. Initiation grants the druid the shape-changing and immunity to woodland charm powers gained at 7th level. It must be performed immediately after the druid begins advancing through 7th level. If cast earlier, it fails, and the druid does not gain those powers until properly initiated. Usually, a druid must seek another druid of 7th level or higher to perform the rite, though in unusual cases a druid may cast it upon themselves. Special vows functions like the clerical rite of the same name. It does not work on paladins, but works on cavaliers of any alignment. Hallowed ground is cast on the druid’s permanent grove. It enchants the grove’s trees so they are never affected by disease or natural disasters. The ground remains hallowed as long as the druid maintains the grove as a permanent base. Cast out is a form of excommunication or punishment used against someone who has committed sacrilege against nature or violated druidic principles. Its effects may later be lessened by a reversed version of the ceremony cast by the same druid or another druid of at least equal level, but it can only be completely neutralized by a Hierophant Druid. A cast-out character exudes a powerful negative aura, causing natural creatures to react negatively, including normal animals, woodland monsters, domesticated beasts, druids, and druidic followers. This punishment requires permission from the druid’s Archdruid; an Archdruid needs permission from the Great Druid, and the Great Druid from the Grand Druid. The Grand Druid needs no permission, but a Hierophant Druid may reverse the action at any time. A druid who wrongly seeks or performs this punishment may themselves be punished by higher-ranking druids. An unwilling recipient saves versus spell at -4 to negate the effect. Material Components: Druidic ceremony always requires mistletoe and must be performed in a druid grove or another natural, healthy forested area. Such ceremonies are normally conducted at dawn or dusk, when night and day are in balance.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Cleric: Ceremony, Druid","class":"Cleric"},"cleric slow poison druid":{"name":"Slow Poison, Druid","level":"2","school":"Necromantic","range":"Touch","duration":"1 hour per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Slow Poison\n\nSchool: Necromantic\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 hour per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is identical to the 2nd-level clerical spell slow poison, except that if the druid can determine the poison was made from a living plant, they have a 5% chance per caster level of knowing an herbal antidote that neutralizes the poison. If the Dungeon Master does not identify the exact poison, a successful detect poison type result indicates an organic poison that can be countered. A successful roll equal to or less than the druid’s chance means the antidote neutralizes the poison. Material Components: Mistletoe and crushed garlic rubbed on the recipient’s feet. Antidotes must be obtained from green vegetables outdoors or from an herbalist or similar source.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Cleric: Slow Poison, Druid","class":"Cleric"},"magic user bluelight":{"name":"Bluelight","level":"0","school":"Conjuration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"¼' diam. sphere","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip enables the caster to conjure a small sphere of glowing blue radiance. The light has an eerie effect when seen from a distance, but the 3-inch sphere only illuminates an area of 5' around itself. Furthermore, the bluelight does not cast reflections beyond this radius. The light does not affect either infravision or ultravision. When the caster says a rhyme using the words blue and light in any combination, the bluelight appears in his or her open palm and remains aglow until the caster ceases to concentrate on it.","notes":"This cantrip enables the caster to conjure a small sphere of glowing blue radiance. The light has an eerie effect when seen from a distance, but the 3-inch sphere only illuminates an area of 5' around itself. Furthermore, the bluelight does not cast reflections beyond this radius. The light does not affect either infravision or ultravision. When the caster says a rhyme using the words blue and light in any combination, the bluelight appears in his or her open palm and remains aglow until the caster ceases to concentrate on it.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Bluelight"},"magic user bug":{"name":"Bug","level":"0","school":"Summoning","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One bug","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A variation of the bee cantrip, the bug cantrip enables the caster to summon some form of crawling insect. The beetle or bug appears in the same manner as the bee summoned by the cantrip of that name. It will likewise be irritated and will pinch, bite, or otherwise attack the creature it might find itself upon, with appropriate results. Verbal component is the name of the insect desired while the caster’s forefinger makes a sliding and pointing motion at the desired area of the bug’s appearance (up to 1' distant).","notes":"A variation of the bee cantrip, the bug cantrip enables the caster to summon some form of crawling insect. The beetle or bug appears in the same manner as the bee summoned by the cantrip of that name. It will likewise be irritated and will pinch, bite, or otherwise attack the creature it might find itself upon, with appropriate results. Verbal component is the name of the insect desired while the caster’s forefinger makes a sliding and pointing motion at the desired area of the bug’s appearance (up to 1' distant).","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Bug"},"magic user chill":{"name":"Chill","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1 cu. yd. cube","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A cantrip of this nature allows the caster to cause non-living liquid or solid material to become about 40° F. cooler than it was, subject to a minimum temperature of freezing. The chilling effect lasts for but an instant, after which the subject warms slowly back to normal temperature. Verbal component is a soft whistling, somatic is a downward-thrust thumb.","notes":"A cantrip of this nature allows the caster to cause non-living liquid or solid material to become about 40° F. cooler than it was, subject to a minimum temperature of freezing. The chilling effect lasts for but an instant, after which the subject warms slowly back to normal temperature. Verbal component is a soft whistling, somatic is a downward-thrust thumb.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Chill"},"magic user clean":{"name":"Clean","level":"0","school":"Abjuration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"4 sq. yds.","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip enables the caster to remove heavy soil, dirt, and like foreign objects from floors, walls, dishes, windows, etc. The subject surfaces are then spotless, but care must be taken in removal of pigments and the like, so usually only one type of material will be treated in a single application. Verbal component is a low outrush of air, somatic is a circular hand motion.","notes":"This cantrip enables the caster to remove heavy soil, dirt, and like foreign objects from floors, walls, dishes, windows, etc. The subject surfaces are then spotless, but care must be taken in removal of pigments and the like, so usually only one type of material will be treated in a single application. Verbal component is a low outrush of air, somatic is a circular hand motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Clean"},"magic user color":{"name":"Color","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1 cubic yd.","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By use of this cantrip, the caster brings color to an object. It can be used to restore faded hues or to tinge those already colored with a different hue. Thus, dull or faded fabric can be brightened, pigments restored, or even hair or skin changed to another color. The effect must be renewed every 30 days. Verbal component is a humming, somatic is a back-and-forth or wringing hand motion.","notes":"By use of this cantrip, the caster brings color to an object. It can be used to restore faded hues or to tinge those already colored with a different hue. Thus, dull or faded fabric can be brightened, pigments restored, or even hair or skin changed to another color. The effect must be renewed every 30 days. Verbal component is a humming, somatic is a back-and-forth or wringing hand motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Color"},"magic user cough":{"name":"Cough","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One person","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip enables the caster to make the subject individual cough spasmodically. If a saving throw is made, the cough is only a brief hacking which will not usually disturb other activities. Failing the saving throw indicates the victim is affected by a loud and active series of coughs lasting from 1 to 3 seconds. The somatic component is a gagging gesture while a gasp is verbalized.","notes":"This cantrip enables the caster to make the subject individual cough spasmodically. If a saving throw is made, the cough is only a brief hacking which will not usually disturb other activities. Failing the saving throw indicates the victim is affected by a loud and active series of coughs lasting from 1 to 3 seconds. The somatic component is a gagging gesture while a gasp is verbalized.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Cough"},"magic user dampen":{"name":"Dampen","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1 cubic yd.","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"When a cantrip of this sort is cast, the subject area is permeated by a fog-like dampness which leaves all material within it damp to the touch. It is useful for many sorts of things. It is hard on parchment, and it similarly makes it and like substances hard to set aflame. Those within the area of effect of the dampen cantrip will be enwrapped in a light fog, and objects in this fog, while still visible, will lose their detail. Verbal component is a low hooting or a hummed ditty, somatic is a hand gesture upwards with writhing fingers.","notes":"When a cantrip of this sort is cast, the subject area is permeated by a fog-like dampness which leaves all material within it damp to the touch. It is useful for many sorts of things. It is hard on parchment, and it similarly makes it and like substances hard to set aflame. Those within the area of effect of the dampen cantrip will be enwrapped in a light fog, and objects in this fog, while still visible, will lose their detail. Verbal component is a low hooting or a hummed ditty, somatic is a hand gesture upwards with writhing fingers.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Dampen"},"magic user dirty":{"name":"Dirty","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"4 sq. yds.","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"The opposite of a clean cantrip, this enables the caster to soil, spot, and sully walls, floors, dishes, garments, etc. Verbal component is a spitting sound, made while the feet are shuffled and stamped.","notes":"The opposite of a clean cantrip, this enables the caster to soil, spot, and sully walls, floors, dishes, garments, etc. Verbal component is a spitting sound, made while the feet are shuffled and stamped.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Dirty"},"magic user distract":{"name":"Distract","level":"0","school":"Enchantment","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes all who are watching to look at an area of the caster’s choice. The area must be to the right or left of the caster, and the distraction must be within 10 feet of the caster. Thus, the caster can cause viewers to watch his or her right hand and a location a few feet distant where the caster’s finger is pointing, while the caster’s left hand does something unnoticed. Saving throws apply only to individuals above 0 level, or with at least 1 + 1 hit dice and an intelligence rating of greater than low. The distract cantrip has a duration of only 1 segment. The caster speaks an attention-getting word or phrase and gestures to the left or right to effectuate the cantrip.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes all who are watching to look at an area of the caster’s choice. The area must be to the right or left of the caster, and the distraction must be within 10 feet of the caster. Thus, the caster can cause viewers to watch his or her right hand and a location a few feet distant where the caster’s finger is pointing, while the caster’s left hand does something unnoticed. Saving throws apply only to individuals above 0 level, or with at least 1 + 1 hit dice and an intelligence rating of greater than low. The distract cantrip has a duration of only 1 segment. The caster speaks an attention-getting word or phrase and gestures to the left or right to effectuate the cantrip.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Distract"},"magic user dry":{"name":"Dry","level":"0","school":"Abjuration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1 cubic yd.","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip removes dampness and excess moisture from materials within the area of effect. It is useful for cloth, herbs, and cleaning chores. Verbal component is similar to that of the dampen cantrip, and the somatic is a two-handed wringing motion.","notes":"This cantrip removes dampness and excess moisture from materials within the area of effect. It is useful for cloth, herbs, and cleaning chores. Verbal component is similar to that of the dampen cantrip, and the somatic is a two-handed wringing motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Dry"},"magic user dust":{"name":"Dust","level":"0","school":"Abjuration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"10' radius","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A cantrip of this sort removes all fine dust and tiny grit particles from exposed surfaces such as floors, shelves, walls, etc. The material so removed is transported elsewhere, but new dust can accumulate, of course. Verbal component is a continuous in-drawing of breath, somatic is a back-and-forth hand motion.","notes":"A cantrip of this sort removes all fine dust and tiny grit particles from exposed surfaces such as floors, shelves, walls, etc. The material so removed is transported elsewhere, but new dust can accumulate, of course. Verbal component is a continuous in-drawing of breath, somatic is a back-and-forth hand motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Dust"},"magic user dusty":{"name":"Dusty","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"10' radius","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes a film of dust and grime to settle upon all exposed surfaces within the cantrip area of effect. The verbal component is a low humming sound, made while the hands move in shaking motions.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes a film of dust and grime to settle upon all exposed surfaces within the cantrip area of effect. The verbal component is a low humming sound, made while the hands move in shaking motions.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Dusty"},"magic user exterminate":{"name":"Exterminate","level":"0","school":"Abjuration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1 small creature","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"When this cantrip is used, the caster may kill a small pest such as a fly, mouse, rat, beetle, or the like. It is useful for indoor and outdoor applications. If the subject is very small, an area of up to ½ cubic foot can be rid of pests. This cantrip is effective against magical creations and normal-sized creatures magically shrunk to insect-size, but has no effect on polymorphed creatures and similarly enchanted beings. The somatic gesture is a pointed finger, while the caster verbalizes a low zzzt sound.","notes":"When this cantrip is used, the caster may kill a small pest such as a fly, mouse, rat, beetle, or the like. It is useful for indoor and outdoor applications. If the subject is very small, an area of up to ½ cubic foot can be rid of pests. This cantrip is effective against magical creations and normal-sized creatures magically shrunk to insect-size, but has no effect on polymorphed creatures and similarly enchanted beings. The somatic gesture is a pointed finger, while the caster verbalizes a low zzzt sound.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Exterminate"},"magic user firefinger":{"name":"Firefinger","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"½v line","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"The firefinger cantrip enables the caster to cause a jet of flame up to one-half foot in length to shoot forth from his or her finger. The flame is very hot and will ignite combustible materials such as parchment, twigs, kindling, and the like without difficulty, providing the materials are relatively dry. The flame persists for up to 1 segment. To bring about the magic of this cantrip, the caster speaks a word of power over elemental fire (such as ron-son, zip-po, or the much revered word, dun-hill), extends the forefinger, and makes a sideways motion with the thumb.","notes":"The firefinger cantrip enables the caster to cause a jet of flame up to one-half foot in length to shoot forth from his or her finger. The flame is very hot and will ignite combustible materials such as parchment, twigs, kindling, and the like without difficulty, providing the materials are relatively dry. The flame persists for up to 1 segment. To bring about the magic of this cantrip, the caster speaks a word of power over elemental fire (such as ron-son, zip-po, or the much revered word, dun-hill), extends the forefinger, and makes a sideways motion with the thumb.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Firefinger"},"magic user flavor":{"name":"Flavor","level":"0","school":"Enchantment","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip enables the caster to give the subject a superior or better or different flavor. Thus, mush can be made to taste as if it were lobster bisque, but the dweomer will not actually affect quality or wholesomeness. Spoiled food remains spoiled; a poisoned drink would still be deadly (though any tell-tale taste of the poison may be masked in this fashion). The verbal component is a muttered lip-smacking sound; the somatic gesture is a shaking motion.","notes":"This cantrip enables the caster to give the subject a superior or better or different flavor. Thus, mush can be made to taste as if it were lobster bisque, but the dweomer will not actually affect quality or wholesomeness. Spoiled food remains spoiled; a poisoned drink would still be deadly (though any tell-tale taste of the poison may be masked in this fashion). The verbal component is a muttered lip-smacking sound; the somatic gesture is a shaking motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Flavor"},"magic user footfall":{"name":"Footfall","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"When this cantrip is used, the caster creates the aural illusion of footsteps. The sound is as if a human or humanoid was walking. The footfalls can be soft or fairly noisy. They can approach, move away from, follow, or otherwise seem to parallel a person or party. They must begin within 1' of the caster, but they may thereafter move away from him or her up to a 2' distance, or may approach closer than 1'. The caster must softly vocalize sounds similar to footsteps while pointing in the area they are to occur initially and subsequently.","notes":"When this cantrip is used, the caster creates the aural illusion of footsteps. The sound is as if a human or humanoid was walking. The footfalls can be soft or fairly noisy. They can approach, move away from, follow, or otherwise seem to parallel a person or party. They must begin within 1' of the caster, but they may thereafter move away from him or her up to a 2' distance, or may approach closer than 1'. The caster must softly vocalize sounds similar to footsteps while pointing in the area they are to occur initially and subsequently.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Footfall"},"magic user freshen":{"name":"Freshen","level":"0","school":"Enchantment","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster brings new life or freshness to the object desired. The magic applies to food and drink items such as milk, beer, meat, and raw vegetables. It also works with cut vegetables, flowers, herbs, etc. Although it will remove a slight taint of spoilage, restore drooping flowers, and so on, it is not as effective as a purify food & drink spell, and it lasts for but an hour. The subject must be of relatively small size, i.e. a small cask of liquid, a sheep, a bushel of vegetables, etc. If used on a creature that is harmed by magics such as purify food & drink, the cantrip inflicts 1-4 points of damage. The verbal component is an mmmmmm sound, while the hand makes a mystic symbol with thumb and forefinger forming a circle and the other fingers upright and apart.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster brings new life or freshness to the object desired. The magic applies to food and drink items such as milk, beer, meat, and raw vegetables. It also works with cut vegetables, flowers, herbs, etc. Although it will remove a slight taint of spoilage, restore drooping flowers, and so on, it is not as effective as a purify food & drink spell, and it lasts for but an hour. The subject must be of relatively small size, i.e. a small cask of liquid, a sheep, a bushel of vegetables, etc. If used on a creature that is harmed by magics such as purify food & drink, the cantrip inflicts 1-4 points of damage. The verbal component is an mmmmmm sound, while the hand makes a mystic symbol with thumb and forefinger forming a circle and the other fingers upright and apart.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Freshen"},"magic user gather":{"name":"Gather","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1 sq. yd.","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip enables the caster to neatly gather numerous small objects into a stack or pile. For instance, if nails, nuts, coins, papers, or like objects were spilled, the magic would bring them together. It can be used selectively, for instance to separate one type of material from another, but only the selected type would be gathered neatly. The caster verbalizes the type of material to be gathered while making a gathering motion.","notes":"This cantrip enables the caster to neatly gather numerous small objects into a stack or pile. For instance, if nails, nuts, coins, papers, or like objects were spilled, the magic would bring them together. It can be used selectively, for instance to separate one type of material from another, but only the selected type would be gathered neatly. The caster verbalizes the type of material to be gathered while making a gathering motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Gather"},"magic user giggle":{"name":"Giggle","level":"0","school":"Charm","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One person","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes the subject individual to involuntarily giggle. The loudness and length of this reaction depend on the saving throw. If the subject fails to save, the result will be a chuckle or giggle lasting about 2 or 3 seconds. If the save succeeds, only a brief chuckle will be caused. The verbal component is a single word or phrase (known in magical circles as a “punch line”) to be spoken while one finger is moved back and forth rapidly.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes the subject individual to involuntarily giggle. The loudness and length of this reaction depend on the saving throw. If the subject fails to save, the result will be a chuckle or giggle lasting about 2 or 3 seconds. If the save succeeds, only a brief chuckle will be caused. The verbal component is a single word or phrase (known in magical circles as a “punch line”) to be spoken while one finger is moved back and forth rapidly.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Giggle"},"magic user gnats":{"name":"Gnats","level":"0","school":"Summoning","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1 cubic foot","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A cantrip of this nature is similar to the bee and bug cantrips described above, except that when it is used a cloud of gnats is summoned. The swarm will immediately proceed to fly around the head of the nearest living creature (which must be no more than 1' from the caster), and unless this creature makes a successful saving throw versus poison, the cloud of gnats will distract the creature for from 1-4 segments before the gnats fly elsewhere. The verbal component is a high-pitched buzzing sound made with the tongue and upper palate while the caster points a digit at the area in which the gnat cloud is to appear.","notes":"A cantrip of this nature is similar to the bee and bug cantrips described above, except that when it is used a cloud of gnats is summoned. The swarm will immediately proceed to fly around the head of the nearest living creature (which must be no more than 1' from the caster), and unless this creature makes a successful saving throw versus poison, the cloud of gnats will distract the creature for from 1-4 segments before the gnats fly elsewhere. The verbal component is a high-pitched buzzing sound made with the tongue and upper palate while the caster points a digit at the area in which the gnat cloud is to appear.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Gnats"},"magic user groan":{"name":"Groan","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A groan cantrip creates the audible illusion of a wracking cry coming from some location no more than 1' from the caster. Naturally, those creatures within hearing distance are allowed a saving throw versus spell, and if it succeeds, the individual will hear no such noise. The caster makes a soft groaning sound in his or her throat while pointing to the area from which the sound is to appear to come. A container or door will not hamper the range, so that a groaning sound can be made to seem to come from behind a door, in a chest, etc.","notes":"A groan cantrip creates the audible illusion of a wracking cry coming from some location no more than 1' from the caster. Naturally, those creatures within hearing distance are allowed a saving throw versus spell, and if it succeeds, the individual will hear no such noise. The caster makes a soft groaning sound in his or her throat while pointing to the area from which the sound is to appear to come. A container or door will not hamper the range, so that a groaning sound can be made to seem to come from behind a door, in a chest, etc.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Groan"},"magic user hairy":{"name":"Hairy","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"While this cantrip is not actually one of the standard useful ones which apprentices reverse for mischievousness, it is one which is generally used for no good purpose. It causes hair, fur, or hairlike growth to thicken and lengthen. Thus, a head of hair, a peach, a beard, a cat, or whatever could be affected. The growth will cause the subject material to increase from 2-12 inches in length. The subject material must be trimmed or cut to remove the cantrip’s effect. This cantrip can be reversed to shorten growth or effectively shave, but since the effect on short material (growth under 1 inch in length) is complete absence of growth for 2-12 days, it is not often used. The caster verbalizes snicking sounds while making massaging motions for growth, or scissoring motions for removal.","notes":"While this cantrip is not actually one of the standard useful ones which apprentices reverse for mischievousness, it is one which is generally used for no good purpose. It causes hair, fur, or hairlike growth to thicken and lengthen. Thus, a head of hair, a peach, a beard, a cat, or whatever could be affected. The growth will cause the subject material to increase from 2-12 inches in length. The subject material must be trimmed or cut to remove the cantrip’s effect. This cantrip can be reversed to shorten growth or effectively shave, but since the effect on short material (growth under 1 inch in length) is complete absence of growth for 2-12 days, it is not often used. The caster verbalizes snicking sounds while making massaging motions for growth, or scissoring motions for removal.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Hairy"},"magic user hide":{"name":"Hide","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip allows the caster to magically hide an object of virtually any size for a short period of time. The cantrip casts a dweomer over the desired object so that it becomes invisible to all who are in front of the caster. Note that the magic does not affect sound, so that if a crowing rooster were made to seemingly disappear, the noise of its cry would still be heard. Likewise, if an elephant were hidden by the cantrip, the sound of its tread, trumpeting, or even breathing might be heard. The dweomer will not work if viewers are beside or behind the caster. The cantrip lasts for 1 turn on an object of 2 cubic yards or less in volume. The duration is reduced by 1 round for every additional 2 cubic yards of volume made to seemingly disappear, until at 20 cubic yards of volume, the duration is 1 round. At over 20 cubic yards of volume, duration is reduced by 1 segment per 2 additional cubic yards; i.e., the hide cantrip will have a duration of 9 segments if cast on an object of 22 cubic yards volume; 8 segments for 24 cubic yards, 7 segments for 26, 6 for 28, 5 for 30, 4 for 32, 3 for 34, 2 for 36, and 1 segment for 38 cubic yards. Anything over 38 cubic yards in volume will at best momentarily disappear and then reappear again. Verbal component is an activating word such as abracadabra while the hand makes a pass across the forepart of the object. The caster can dispel the cantrip simply by speaking the activating word.","notes":"This cantrip allows the caster to magically hide an object of virtually any size for a short period of time. The cantrip casts a dweomer over the desired object so that it becomes invisible to all who are in front of the caster. Note that the magic does not affect sound, so that if a crowing rooster were made to seemingly disappear, the noise of its cry would still be heard. Likewise, if an elephant were hidden by the cantrip, the sound of its tread, trumpeting, or even breathing might be heard. The dweomer will not work if viewers are beside or behind the caster. The cantrip lasts for 1 turn on an object of 2 cubic yards or less in volume. The duration is reduced by 1 round for every additional 2 cubic yards of volume made to seemingly disappear, until at 20 cubic yards of volume, the duration is 1 round. At over 20 cubic yards of volume, duration is reduced by 1 segment per 2 additional cubic yards; i.e., the hide cantrip will have a duration of 9 segments if cast on an object of 22 cubic yards volume; 8 segments for 24 cubic yards, 7 segments for 26, 6 for 28, 5 for 30, 4 for 32, 3 for 34, 2 for 36, and 1 segment for 38 cubic yards. Anything over 38 cubic yards in volume will at best momentarily disappear and then reappear again. Verbal component is an activating word such as abracadabra while the hand makes a pass across the forepart of the object. The caster can dispel the cantrip simply by speaking the activating word.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Hide"},"magic user knot":{"name":"Knot","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip is a permutation of the tie cantrip. It causes the thread, string, cord, or rope to knot itself in such a manner as to be very difficult to untie, and from 2-8 rounds, minus dexterity bonus for reaction of the individual untying the knot, to undo. It works even on material already affected by a tie cantrip, but not on magical ropes, ropes being held onto by a character or creature, or taut lines such as a bowstring. The caster verbalizes a low zzzz sound while moving the arm forward with a strong wrist motion.","notes":"This cantrip is a permutation of the tie cantrip. It causes the thread, string, cord, or rope to knot itself in such a manner as to be very difficult to untie, and from 2-8 rounds, minus dexterity bonus for reaction of the individual untying the knot, to undo. It works even on material already affected by a tie cantrip, but not on magical ropes, ropes being held onto by a character or creature, or taut lines such as a bowstring. The caster verbalizes a low zzzz sound while moving the arm forward with a strong wrist motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Knot"},"magic user moan":{"name":"Moan","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip is the same as a groan cantrip, except that the sound involved is either a pitiful moaning or else an eerie one. The desired sound is either a low-pitched one for the haunting effect or a high-pitched one for the pitiful effect.","notes":"This cantrip is the same as a groan cantrip, except that the sound involved is either a pitiful moaning or else an eerie one. The desired sound is either a low-pitched one for the haunting effect or a high-pitched one for the pitiful effect.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Moan"},"magic user mouse":{"name":"Mouse","level":"0","school":"Summoning","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One mouse","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Similar to the cantrip which summons a bee or a bug, the mouse cantrip enables the caster to bring forth a mouse up to 1' from his or her position. The animal will be a typical field mouse or as similar a species as possible. When it arrives, the caster will have no control over the mouse, and the animal will behave as would any mouse in the given situation. The caster speaks a summoning word (typically the name of a food desirable by mice) while holding his or her hands in such a way as to resemble mouse ears.","notes":"Similar to the cantrip which summons a bee or a bug, the mouse cantrip enables the caster to bring forth a mouse up to 1' from his or her position. The animal will be a typical field mouse or as similar a species as possible. When it arrives, the caster will have no control over the mouse, and the animal will behave as would any mouse in the given situation. The caster speaks a summoning word (typically the name of a food desirable by mice) while holding his or her hands in such a way as to resemble mouse ears.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Mouse"},"magic user mute":{"name":"MUte","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"The mute cantrip allows the caster to alter the shape of small objects of a mineral nature. The magic is effective against glass, metal, stone, etc. A plane can be altered to a rod, a torus to a sphere, etc. Thus, a coin could be changed to be a ring. Similarly, glass could be changed to crystal, lead to silver, copper to gold, etc. However, the dweomers of magical items are too strong for this cantrip to affect them. The duration of the mute is but 1 round. If another individual actually touches the object affected, the dweomer of the cantrip might be affected: The individual touching it makes a saving throw versus spell, and if it succeeds the cantrip is dispelled. The components for the mute cantrip are similar to those of a change cantrip.","notes":"The mute cantrip allows the caster to alter the shape of small objects of a mineral nature. The magic is effective against glass, metal, stone, etc. A plane can be altered to a rod, a torus to a sphere, etc. Thus, a coin could be changed to be a ring. Similarly, glass could be changed to crystal, lead to silver, copper to gold, etc. However, the dweomers of magical items are too strong for this cantrip to affect them. The duration of the mute is but 1 round. If another individual actually touches the object affected, the dweomer of the cantrip might be affected: The individual touching it makes a saving throw versus spell, and if it succeeds the cantrip is dispelled. The components for the mute cantrip are similar to those of a change cantrip.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: MUte"},"magic user nod":{"name":"Nod","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One person","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip causes the subject to give an involuntary nod of the head due to muscle contraction. The effect is as if the subject were nodding in agreement or as a greeting. A successful saving throw negates the effect. The caster gives a slight nod of the head while pointing his or her small finger at the subject.","notes":"This cantrip causes the subject to give an involuntary nod of the head due to muscle contraction. The effect is as if the subject were nodding in agreement or as a greeting. A successful saving throw negates the effect. The caster gives a slight nod of the head while pointing his or her small finger at the subject.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Nod"},"magic user palm":{"name":"Palm","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One small item","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip enables the caster to secret a small object in his hand without seeming to do so. The dweomer creates an illusory duplicate of the object to be palmed, so that the other can be taken while under a form of hide cantrip (which actually works regardless of viewer position). The illusory duplicate of the palmed object lasts but 1 segment, so it must be covered or screened from view, or else any onlookers will see it wink out of existence. A special word is spoken while a digit points at the object to be palmed. The caster may then pick up the now-invisible actual object while seemingly only touching or handling the illusory duplicate.","notes":"This cantrip enables the caster to secret a small object in his hand without seeming to do so. The dweomer creates an illusory duplicate of the object to be palmed, so that the other can be taken while under a form of hide cantrip (which actually works regardless of viewer position). The illusory duplicate of the palmed object lasts but 1 segment, so it must be covered or screened from view, or else any onlookers will see it wink out of existence. A special word is spoken while a digit points at the object to be palmed. The caster may then pick up the now-invisible actual object while seemingly only touching or handling the illusory duplicate.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Palm"},"magic user polish":{"name":"Polish","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"When this cantrip is used, the caster magically smooths and brings a luster to materials such as wood, metal, stone, leather, or ceramic. Naturally, the desired object must be relatively clean in order for the cantrip to be effective. The object affected must be of reasonable size — a floor of up to 1,000 square feet, an armoire, etc. It works better on smaller objects, of course, such as boots, mirrors, crystal containers, etc. The caster hums a ditty while making a buffing motion.","notes":"When this cantrip is used, the caster magically smooths and brings a luster to materials such as wood, metal, stone, leather, or ceramic. Naturally, the desired object must be relatively clean in order for the cantrip to be effective. The object affected must be of reasonable size — a floor of up to 1,000 square feet, an armoire, etc. It works better on smaller objects, of course, such as boots, mirrors, crystal containers, etc. The caster hums a ditty while making a buffing motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Polish"},"magic user present":{"name":"Present","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One person","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A present cantrip enables the caster to bring any small object or series of objects from within a 2-foot radius of his or her person to his or her hand. The object or objects will appear magically in the caster’s hand as he or she puts the hand upward or outward with a flourish and speaks the key word to begin the dweomer. If an object as large as a tankard is thus presented, the cantrip will be exhausted, but as many as a dozen coins could be brought to the hand before the dweomer failed. The caster must know the exact nature and location of the object or objects to be presented. If they are on the person of another individual, a saving throw versus spell applies to the individual, unless the object or objects are in plain sight.\nPerson-Affecting Cantrips: Belch (Evocation)\nWhen this cantrip is cast, the subject will involuntarily belch. A saving throw is applicable only to see how loud or muffled the burping is, failure indicating a very loud belch, success meaning that the sound is relatively low and muffled. The verbal component is an almost inaudible belch, done at the same time that the caster’s hand presses his or her diaphragm.","notes":"A present cantrip enables the caster to bring any small object or series of objects from within a 2-foot radius of his or her person to his or her hand. The object or objects will appear magically in the caster’s hand as he or she puts the hand upward or outward with a flourish and speaks the key word to begin the dweomer. If an object as large as a tankard is thus presented, the cantrip will be exhausted, but as many as a dozen coins could be brought to the hand before the dweomer failed. The caster must know the exact nature and location of the object or objects to be presented. If they are on the person of another individual, a saving throw versus spell applies to the individual, unless the object or objects are in plain sight.\nPerson-Affecting Cantrips: Belch (Evocation)\nWhen this cantrip is cast, the subject will involuntarily belch. A saving throw is applicable only to see how loud or muffled the burping is, failure indicating a very loud belch, success meaning that the sound is relatively low and muffled. The verbal component is an almost inaudible belch, done at the same time that the caster’s hand presses his or her diaphragm.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Present"},"magic user rattle":{"name":"Rattle","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes the audible illusion of a rattling sound associated with chains. Its direction and distance is the same as for a groan cantrip. The sound will last for up to 2 seconds. All creatures within 1' of the sound are entitled to a saving throw versus spell to determine whether they hear the illusory sound. The spell caster names the rattling device which he or she desires to create the illusion of while shaking one hand vigorously.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes the audible illusion of a rattling sound associated with chains. Its direction and distance is the same as for a groan cantrip. The sound will last for up to 2 seconds. All creatures within 1' of the sound are entitled to a saving throw versus spell to determine whether they hear the illusory sound. The spell caster names the rattling device which he or she desires to create the illusion of while shaking one hand vigorously.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Rattle"},"magic user ravel":{"name":"Ravel","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip is the reverse of a stitch. It will work only if there is a loose or broken thread in the seam or fabric to be affected, except for material magically stitched by the appropriate cantrip. When the latter sort of seam or material is involved, the ravel cantrip will always work except in a case where the subject is otherwise magical, i.e. a bag of holding, a cloak of protection, boots of elvenkind, etc. The name of the cantrip is verbalized while the fingers make a plucking motion.","notes":"This cantrip is the reverse of a stitch. It will work only if there is a loose or broken thread in the seam or fabric to be affected, except for material magically stitched by the appropriate cantrip. When the latter sort of seam or material is involved, the ravel cantrip will always work except in a case where the subject is otherwise magical, i.e. a bag of holding, a cloak of protection, boots of elvenkind, etc. The name of the cantrip is verbalized while the fingers make a plucking motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Ravel"},"magic user salt":{"name":"Salt","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip causes a sprinkling of fine salt to magically appear and descend upon the desired object — a stew, some troublesome weed patch, or a barrel full of stock fish to be preserved. The object must be of a reasonable size — up to perhaps 4 square yards in area or about 30 gallons liquid volume. Care must be taken to avoid over-salting if the object involved is smaller, and if the object is larger, it will not receive much salt. Creatures adversely affected by salt (such as a giant slug) take 1-4 points of damage from this cantrip. The verbal component is a labial smacking, performed while the hand makes a sprinkling motion.","notes":"This cantrip causes a sprinkling of fine salt to magically appear and descend upon the desired object — a stew, some troublesome weed patch, or a barrel full of stock fish to be preserved. The object must be of a reasonable size — up to perhaps 4 square yards in area or about 30 gallons liquid volume. Care must be taken to avoid over-salting if the object involved is smaller, and if the object is larger, it will not receive much salt. Creatures adversely affected by salt (such as a giant slug) take 1-4 points of damage from this cantrip. The verbal component is a labial smacking, performed while the hand makes a sprinkling motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Salt"},"magic user scratch":{"name":"Scratch","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One creature","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A scratch cantrip causes the subject creature to experience an annoying itch on some portion of the body. Unless a saving throw is successful, the subject will involuntarily scratch at this itch. This scratching will take but a second, and will immediately cause the itch to cease. Verbal component is the name of some body pest (flea, louse, etc.), uttered while the area of the itch is pointed to.","notes":"A scratch cantrip causes the subject creature to experience an annoying itch on some portion of the body. Unless a saving throw is successful, the subject will involuntarily scratch at this itch. This scratching will take but a second, and will immediately cause the itch to cease. Verbal component is the name of some body pest (flea, louse, etc.), uttered while the area of the itch is pointed to.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Scratch"},"magic user shine":{"name":"Shine","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Similar to the polish cantrip, this magic allows the caster to remove tarnish, rust, corrosion, and similar substances from the desired object. This cantrip brings about a mirror-bright shine to objects capable of such, causing their surfaces to be smooth and unmarred. A piece of jewelry, for instance, would be made more attractive, and the gems (only) of such a piece might be actually made more valuable: If base value of the gem(s) in a piece of jewelry was originally decreased, and a shine cantrip is used upon the object, then the owner may (if desired) find out whether the value of the gem(s) has been changed. (The DM should roll again on the “Increase or Decrease of Worth Beyond Base Value” table on page 26 of the DMG, with a -1 modifier to the die roll.) No gem can be “re-valued” in this manner more than once. A single object up to about 1 cubic yard in volume can be treated by this cantrip. Its components are similar to those of polish.","notes":"Similar to the polish cantrip, this magic allows the caster to remove tarnish, rust, corrosion, and similar substances from the desired object. This cantrip brings about a mirror-bright shine to objects capable of such, causing their surfaces to be smooth and unmarred. A piece of jewelry, for instance, would be made more attractive, and the gems (only) of such a piece might be actually made more valuable: If base value of the gem(s) in a piece of jewelry was originally decreased, and a shine cantrip is used upon the object, then the owner may (if desired) find out whether the value of the gem(s) has been changed. (The DM should roll again on the “Increase or Decrease of Worth Beyond Base Value” table on page 26 of the DMG, with a -1 modifier to the die roll.) No gem can be “re-valued” in this manner more than once. A single object up to about 1 cubic yard in volume can be treated by this cantrip. Its components are similar to those of polish.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Shine"},"magic user smokepuff":{"name":"Smokepuff","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1' diam. cloud","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"When this cantrip is employed, a puff of actual smoke appears in the desired location, up to 1' distant from the caster, and will ascend as would a normal cloud of smoke, or be dissipated, depending on the prevailing conditions. The caster can cause the smoke to be either white, gray, black, brown, yellow, or green. The caster names the color of smoke desired while moving a hand from an extended horizontal position to a vertical one, meanwhile breathing forth a puff of air.","notes":"When this cantrip is employed, a puff of actual smoke appears in the desired location, up to 1' distant from the caster, and will ascend as would a normal cloud of smoke, or be dissipated, depending on the prevailing conditions. The caster can cause the smoke to be either white, gray, black, brown, yellow, or green. The caster names the color of smoke desired while moving a hand from an extended horizontal position to a vertical one, meanwhile breathing forth a puff of air.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Smokepuff"},"magic user sneeze":{"name":"Sneeze","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One creature","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A cantrip of this nature causes an irritation in the nasal passages of the subject. Unless the subject makes a successful saving throw versus spell, a sneeze will occur. This single sneeze will relieve the irritation. The caster verbalizes the name of an irritant substance while touching his or her nose.","notes":"A cantrip of this nature causes an irritation in the nasal passages of the subject. Unless the subject makes a successful saving throw versus spell, a sneeze will occur. This single sneeze will relieve the irritation. The caster verbalizes the name of an irritant substance while touching his or her nose.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Sneeze"},"magic user sour":{"name":"Sour","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"When this cantrip is used, the caster causes the subject food or drink to take on a sour taste, not unlike vinegar of the appropriate sort. While it is typically used to spoil wine, beer, or some pastry, the sour cantrip can be used to useful purpose. The magic actually causes about a pint (maximum) of vinegar to appear over the subject. This can be an empty container in which such liquid is desired. The caster purses the lips and makes a whoosh sound while clenching the hand.","notes":"When this cantrip is used, the caster causes the subject food or drink to take on a sour taste, not unlike vinegar of the appropriate sort. While it is typically used to spoil wine, beer, or some pastry, the sour cantrip can be used to useful purpose. The magic actually causes about a pint (maximum) of vinegar to appear over the subject. This can be an empty container in which such liquid is desired. The caster purses the lips and makes a whoosh sound while clenching the hand.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Sour"},"magic user spice":{"name":"Spice","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Unlike the flavor cantrip, this magic actually brings a particular spice to the object of food or drink. Thus, ginger, pepper, and like spices can be brought to add zest (or disguise). Herbs such as bay leaf, garlic, parsley, and so forth can likewise be evoked by this cantrip. The quantity is sufficient to spice food or drink for about a dozen people. The spice (or herb) appears over the object vessel as a fine powder or flake, falls upon it, and adds its substance to the dish or drink. A ditty is hummed for the verbal component, while the hand makes a crumbling and sprinkling motion.","notes":"Unlike the flavor cantrip, this magic actually brings a particular spice to the object of food or drink. Thus, ginger, pepper, and like spices can be brought to add zest (or disguise). Herbs such as bay leaf, garlic, parsley, and so forth can likewise be evoked by this cantrip. The quantity is sufficient to spice food or drink for about a dozen people. The spice (or herb) appears over the object vessel as a fine powder or flake, falls upon it, and adds its substance to the dish or drink. A ditty is hummed for the verbal component, while the hand makes a crumbling and sprinkling motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Spice"},"magic user spider":{"name":"Spider","level":"0","school":"Summoning","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One spider","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip, much as does a bee or bug or mouse or gnats cantrip, summons a small, ordinary spider from elsewhere to the location desired by the caster, up to 1' distant from his or her person. The arachnid so summoned will usually be a common garden spider or the like, no larger than an inch or two in diameter, and basically harmless. There is a 5% chance that the creature will turn out to be one with powerful poison (black widow, brown recluse, etc.). Since the spider summoned will be annoyed, the creature upon which it finds itself, if such is the case, will be subject to an immediate bite attack. This will have only a momentary effect, distracting the victim for 1 segment, for a normal spider. If the spider is of the very poisonous sort, the victim must also make a saving throw versus poison at +4. Success indicates 1 point of damage is inflicted. Failure indicates 2 points of damage are inflicted, and the victim will feel sick and be unable to act normally for 1-4 days unless a neutralize poison spell is cast to remove the toxin. (A slow poison will defer the sickness for 1 day.) To cast the cantrip, the caster speaks the word arachnid while spreading his or her fingers and wiggling them.","notes":"This cantrip, much as does a bee or bug or mouse or gnats cantrip, summons a small, ordinary spider from elsewhere to the location desired by the caster, up to 1' distant from his or her person. The arachnid so summoned will usually be a common garden spider or the like, no larger than an inch or two in diameter, and basically harmless. There is a 5% chance that the creature will turn out to be one with powerful poison (black widow, brown recluse, etc.). Since the spider summoned will be annoyed, the creature upon which it finds itself, if such is the case, will be subject to an immediate bite attack. This will have only a momentary effect, distracting the victim for 1 segment, for a normal spider. If the spider is of the very poisonous sort, the victim must also make a saving throw versus poison at +4. Success indicates 1 point of damage is inflicted. Failure indicates 2 points of damage are inflicted, and the victim will feel sick and be unable to act normally for 1-4 days unless a neutralize poison spell is cast to remove the toxin. (A slow poison will defer the sickness for 1 day.) To cast the cantrip, the caster speaks the word arachnid while spreading his or her fingers and wiggling them.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Spider"},"magic user spill":{"name":"Spill","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One container","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"The opposite of a gather cantrip, this enables the caster to cause the contents of a container to spill out. The object container is actually tipped by the cantrip, and since the magic is not powerful, containers of more than about a gallon size, or magical ones, will not be affected by the cantrip. Solids and/or liquids within the object container will spill out, if the container is not securely closed or capped. To bring about the magic, the caster verbalizes an uh-oh sound while making an abrupt hand motion.","notes":"The opposite of a gather cantrip, this enables the caster to cause the contents of a container to spill out. The object container is actually tipped by the cantrip, and since the magic is not powerful, containers of more than about a gallon size, or magical ones, will not be affected by the cantrip. Solids and/or liquids within the object container will spill out, if the container is not securely closed or capped. To bring about the magic, the caster verbalizes an uh-oh sound while making an abrupt hand motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Spill"},"magic user sprout":{"name":"Sprout","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1 cubic yd.","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes acceleration in the growth of plants, particularly with respect to the germination of plant seeds. Upon its casting, the cantrip will cause seeds to shoot forth tiny sprouts, newly sprouted plants to grow an inch or so, buds to flower, etc. Fruits and vegetables can be caused to ripen (or actually go past ripening to spoilage) by this cantrip. A susurrant sound is verbalized while the caster’s hand makes hoeing motions.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes acceleration in the growth of plants, particularly with respect to the germination of plant seeds. Upon its casting, the cantrip will cause seeds to shoot forth tiny sprouts, newly sprouted plants to grow an inch or so, buds to flower, etc. Fruits and vegetables can be caused to ripen (or actually go past ripening to spoilage) by this cantrip. A susurrant sound is verbalized while the caster’s hand makes hoeing motions.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Sprout"},"magic user stitch":{"name":"Stitch","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip magically sews seams in cloth or leather. It will make new ones, or repair old work. About 20 yards of cloth can be thus stitched, but only about 2 yards of leather. The seam thus created is neither stronger nor weaker than a seam done without magic. Usually a brief rhyme is recited as the hand makes a sewing motion.","notes":"This cantrip magically sews seams in cloth or leather. It will make new ones, or repair old work. About 20 yards of cloth can be thus stitched, but only about 2 yards of leather. The seam thus created is neither stronger nor weaker than a seam done without magic. Usually a brief rhyme is recited as the hand makes a sewing motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Stitch"},"magic user sweeten":{"name":"Sweeten","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip is the same as a spice cantrip, except that the result is the evocation of a sweetener — sugar, honey, or even a syrup. Components are a buzzing sound and a stirring motion.","notes":"This cantrip is the same as a spice cantrip, except that the result is the evocation of a sweetener — sugar, honey, or even a syrup. Components are a buzzing sound and a stirring motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Sweeten"},"magic user tangle":{"name":"Tangle","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A permutation of the tie cantrip, this magic allows the caster to cause fine material such as thread, hair, small grass, and the like to become twisted and entwined in a tangle. It will not work on heavy material such as rope. Untangling subject material will take 3-12 rounds, unless it is roughly done — and the material is broken and snapped in the process, torn loose, etc. The cantrip will tangle mixed materials such as grass and string, hair and threads, and so forth. A buzzing is verbalized while the finger makes a stirring motion.","notes":"A permutation of the tie cantrip, this magic allows the caster to cause fine material such as thread, hair, small grass, and the like to become twisted and entwined in a tangle. It will not work on heavy material such as rope. Untangling subject material will take 3-12 rounds, unless it is roughly done — and the material is broken and snapped in the process, torn loose, etc. The cantrip will tangle mixed materials such as grass and string, hair and threads, and so forth. A buzzing is verbalized while the finger makes a stirring motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Tangle"},"magic user tap":{"name":"Tap","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1 sq. ft.","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster is able to evoke an invisible force which will tap or rap against some solid object — a door, lid, floor, table, wall, pane, or whatever. The sound will occur once, twice, or thrice, according to the number of fingers extended by the caster. It is an actual sound; creatures within 1' of the noise will certainly hear it if they are able. Verbal component is a hollow sound created by the tongue against the palate, or a key phrase spoken softly, while the finger makes a tapping motion.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster is able to evoke an invisible force which will tap or rap against some solid object — a door, lid, floor, table, wall, pane, or whatever. The sound will occur once, twice, or thrice, according to the number of fingers extended by the caster. It is an actual sound; creatures within 1' of the noise will certainly hear it if they are able. Verbal component is a hollow sound created by the tongue against the palate, or a key phrase spoken softly, while the finger makes a tapping motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Tap"},"magic user tarnish":{"name":"Tarnish","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"The reverse of a shine cantrip, this causes a covering of rust, corrosion, verdigris, or the like to cover an object normally subject to such tarnishing. The object must be of about 1 cubic yard or less in volume. Verbal component is a spitting sound, while the hand makes a sprinkling motion.","notes":"The reverse of a shine cantrip, this causes a covering of rust, corrosion, verdigris, or the like to cover an object normally subject to such tarnishing. The object must be of about 1 cubic yard or less in volume. Verbal component is a spitting sound, while the hand makes a sprinkling motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Tarnish"},"magic user thump":{"name":"Thump","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"An audible illusion, the thump cantrip causes all creatures within a 1' radius of the area of effect to hear a loud but muffled thumping sound, as if something large just fell from a height of a foot or so. A successful saving throw versus spell nullifies the cantrip’s effect. The caster can cause the sound to seemingly come from any location within a 1' radius of his or her person. The caster swallows loudly while pointing toward the area where the cantrip is to come from, while thinking of the thumping sound.","notes":"An audible illusion, the thump cantrip causes all creatures within a 1' radius of the area of effect to hear a loud but muffled thumping sound, as if something large just fell from a height of a foot or so. A successful saving throw versus spell nullifies the cantrip’s effect. The caster can cause the sound to seemingly come from any location within a 1' radius of his or her person. The caster swallows loudly while pointing toward the area where the cantrip is to come from, while thinking of the thumping sound.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Thump"},"magic user tie":{"name":"Tie","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster can magically cause the object of the magic — thread, string, cord, rope, or even cable — to tightly knot itself to either its other end or an end of a similar object within 1' of it. The resulting knot will be a normal one such as a square knot, half-hitch, running bowline, or whatever other sort is desired. The caster verbalizes the name of the knot while holding up three fingers.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster can magically cause the object of the magic — thread, string, cord, rope, or even cable — to tightly knot itself to either its other end or an end of a similar object within 1' of it. The resulting knot will be a normal one such as a square knot, half-hitch, running bowline, or whatever other sort is desired. The caster verbalizes the name of the knot while holding up three fingers.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Tie"},"magic user tweak":{"name":"Tweak","level":"0","school":"Conjuration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One creature","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes an unseen thumb and forefinger to harmlessly, but annoyingly, tweak some portion of a chosen subject within a 1' radius of the caster. Portions subject to the tweak cantrip are: cheek, nose, ear, beard, moustache, whiskers, or tail. The cantrip’s effects do not disturb spell casting, although the tweaking might distract any creature by causing it to turn to discover the source of the annoyance. A failure to save versus spell (with respect to creatures with an intelligence under 7), or failure to roll a score greater than intelligence on 3d6 (with respect to creatures with intelligence of 7 or greater), indicates a 1-segment distraction. The caster speaks a magic phrase (such as kitchy-kitchy-coo) while making a pinching and pulling motion with thumb and forefinger.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes an unseen thumb and forefinger to harmlessly, but annoyingly, tweak some portion of a chosen subject within a 1' radius of the caster. Portions subject to the tweak cantrip are: cheek, nose, ear, beard, moustache, whiskers, or tail. The cantrip’s effects do not disturb spell casting, although the tweaking might distract any creature by causing it to turn to discover the source of the annoyance. A failure to save versus spell (with respect to creatures with an intelligence under 7), or failure to roll a score greater than intelligence on 3d6 (with respect to creatures with intelligence of 7 or greater), indicates a 1-segment distraction. The caster speaks a magic phrase (such as kitchy-kitchy-coo) while making a pinching and pulling motion with thumb and forefinger.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Tweak"},"magic user twitch":{"name":"Twitch","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One creature","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes a muscle contraction in some portion of the subject creature’s appendages — head, neck, hand, arm, foot, leg, etc. The twitch will be noticeable, but will not cause the subject great discomfort or loss of control or concentration. The cantrip is negated by a successful saving throw. Verbal component is the name of the area to be affected while the caster gazes at the area and makes a twitching motion with the hand.","notes":"By means of this cantrip, the caster causes a muscle contraction in some portion of the subject creature’s appendages — head, neck, hand, arm, foot, leg, etc. The twitch will be noticeable, but will not cause the subject great discomfort or loss of control or concentration. The cantrip is negated by a successful saving throw. Verbal component is the name of the area to be affected while the caster gazes at the area and makes a twitching motion with the hand.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Twitch"},"magic user unlock":{"name":"Unlock","level":"0","school":"Conjuration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip enables the caster to conjure an invisible, key-like force appropriate to the locking mechanism to be opened (or closed). The unlock cantrip will affect only simple locks of the most basic sort — typically those which have closing pressure prongs or bolt and pins, or bolt and spring closures. Locks with tumblers or levers, as well as secret-combination locks, are not subject to this cantrip. Note that simple locks with complex wards to prevent skeleton-key triggering will be subject to an unlock cantrip. While the caster speaks a word or phrase associated with locks (tick-tock-doublelock or yah-el, etc.) he or she makes a twisting motion with fingers held as if to grasp a key.\nHaunting-Sound Cantrips: Creak (Evocation)\nBy means of this cantrip, the caster evokes a noise similar to that of a door with corroded hinges slowly opening, or else a sound as if someone or something were walking across squeaking floorboards. The former sound lasts for 1 /3 segment; the latter noise will last half a segment and seem to traverse up to 10 feet distance. The caster makes a low creaking sound in his or her throat while using a hand to make an opening motion or fingers to make a walking motion.","notes":"This cantrip enables the caster to conjure an invisible, key-like force appropriate to the locking mechanism to be opened (or closed). The unlock cantrip will affect only simple locks of the most basic sort — typically those which have closing pressure prongs or bolt and pins, or bolt and spring closures. Locks with tumblers or levers, as well as secret-combination locks, are not subject to this cantrip. Note that simple locks with complex wards to prevent skeleton-key triggering will be subject to an unlock cantrip. While the caster speaks a word or phrase associated with locks (tick-tock-doublelock or yah-el, etc.) he or she makes a twisting motion with fingers held as if to grasp a key.\nHaunting-Sound Cantrips: Creak (Evocation)\nBy means of this cantrip, the caster evokes a noise similar to that of a door with corroded hinges slowly opening, or else a sound as if someone or something were walking across squeaking floorboards. The former sound lasts for 1 /3 segment; the latter noise will last half a segment and seem to traverse up to 10 feet distance. The caster makes a low creaking sound in his or her throat while using a hand to make an opening motion or fingers to make a walking motion.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Unlock"},"magic user untie":{"name":"Untie","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This permutation of a tie cantrip is simply the reverse of the magic. The caster selects an object — thread, string, cord, etc. — which is knotted or tied. The cantrip removes the knot or tying. Note that the untie cantrip will cause a tangle to be nullified. The cantrip will not remove both a knot and a normal tying (normal knot or one caused by a tie cantrip), but it will cause the former to disappear so that only a normal tying remains. This cantrip has no effect on magical objects. Somatic and verbal components vary according to the desired result. In general, a popping sound is made while the hands are moved apart — either as if a knot were being untied or a cord snapped.","notes":"This permutation of a tie cantrip is simply the reverse of the magic. The caster selects an object — thread, string, cord, etc. — which is knotted or tied. The cantrip removes the knot or tying. Note that the untie cantrip will cause a tangle to be nullified. The cantrip will not remove both a knot and a normal tying (normal knot or one caused by a tie cantrip), but it will cause the former to disappear so that only a normal tying remains. This cantrip has no effect on magical objects. Somatic and verbal components vary according to the desired result. In general, a popping sound is made while the hands are moved apart — either as if a knot were being untied or a cord snapped.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Untie"},"magic user warm":{"name":"Warm","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1 cu. yd. cube","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip is the same as chill, except that the magic brings a warming of the liquid or solid. The temperature will rise at most about 40° F. The cantrip will never cause living creatures to become warmer than their normal body temperature. Components are an aah sound vocalized while the hands are rubbed briskly together.","notes":"This cantrip is the same as chill, except that the magic brings a warming of the liquid or solid. The temperature will rise at most about 40° F. The cantrip will never cause living creatures to become warmer than their normal body temperature. Components are an aah sound vocalized while the hands are rubbed briskly together.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Warm"},"magic user whistle":{"name":"Whistle","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"When this cantrip is cast, the dweomer causes a faint or loud whistling sound. A faint whistling can be heard within 10', a loud one within 30'. The sound can be sharp and normal-seeming or echoing, hollow, and eerie. The caster must whistle softly in a manner similar to the desired sound while he or she looks at the area from which the sound is to come and holds two fingers near his or her mouth.","notes":"When this cantrip is cast, the dweomer causes a faint or loud whistling sound. A faint whistling can be heard within 10', a loud one within 30'. The sound can be sharp and normal-seeming or echoing, hollow, and eerie. The caster must whistle softly in a manner similar to the desired sound while he or she looks at the area from which the sound is to come and holds two fingers near his or her mouth.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Whistle"},"magic user wilt":{"name":"Wilt","level":"0","school":"Enchantment","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A reverse of the freshen cantrip which affects only vegetable material — whether growing or picked. Thus, a plant can be made to wilt (or possibly wither if it is not very healthy), or a bunch of cut flowers sag or droop. Verbal component is a descending hum, while the forefinger is slowly curled from an upright position.\nLegerdemain Cantrips: Change (Alteration)\nBy means of a change cantrip, the caster alters one small object to another, although the change must be within the same kingdom, and only animal and vegetable objects are affected. Thus, a piece of parchment can be changed to a brightly colored cloth square, then the cloth can be changed to a rose by another use of the cantrip. Likewise, a bird can be changed into a bat, the bat to a flying squirrel by another use of the same type of cantrip, and so forth. Each change requires a change cantrip. The cantrip will not cause more than a 50% increase or decrease in size/volume, and the effect will last for a base time of 1 turn. If the change is radical, then the time will be reduced accordingly; i.e., changing a dead object to a live one is a radical change and will last only 1 round. On the other hand, a very slight alteration such as color change or the like will last for 1 or more days. A saving throw against this magic does not apply as long as small, animal-intelligence, non-magical creatures of normal sort are concerned. Typically, a magic word is verbalized while the hand makes a pass over the object to be affected.","notes":"A reverse of the freshen cantrip which affects only vegetable material — whether growing or picked. Thus, a plant can be made to wilt (or possibly wither if it is not very healthy), or a bunch of cut flowers sag or droop. Verbal component is a descending hum, while the forefinger is slowly curled from an upright position.\nLegerdemain Cantrips: Change (Alteration)\nBy means of a change cantrip, the caster alters one small object to another, although the change must be within the same kingdom, and only animal and vegetable objects are affected. Thus, a piece of parchment can be changed to a brightly colored cloth square, then the cloth can be changed to a rose by another use of the cantrip. Likewise, a bird can be changed into a bat, the bat to a flying squirrel by another use of the same type of cantrip, and so forth. Each change requires a change cantrip. The cantrip will not cause more than a 50% increase or decrease in size/volume, and the effect will last for a base time of 1 turn. If the change is radical, then the time will be reduced accordingly; i.e., changing a dead object to a live one is a radical change and will last only 1 round. On the other hand, a very slight alteration such as color change or the like will last for 1 or more days. A saving throw against this magic does not apply as long as small, animal-intelligence, non-magical creatures of normal sort are concerned. Typically, a magic word is verbalized while the hand makes a pass over the object to be affected.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Wilt"},"magic user wink":{"name":"Wink","level":"0","school":"Enchantment","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One person","components":"","ct":"1 /10 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"This cantrip enables the caster to cause the subject individual to wink one eye. A saving throw indicates that the winking is rapid and not greatly noticeable, while failure to save indicates a greatly exaggerated, prolonged winking. The caster speaks a magical phrase (such as twenty-three skidoo) while making an imperceptible winking of his or her eye.","notes":"This cantrip enables the caster to cause the subject individual to wink one eye. A saving throw indicates that the winking is rapid and not greatly noticeable, while failure to save indicates a greatly exaggerated, prolonged winking. The caster speaks a magical phrase (such as twenty-three skidoo) while making an imperceptible winking of his or her eye.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Wink"},"magic user wrap":{"name":"Wrap","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One object","components":"","ct":"1 /6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"When a wrap cantrip is employed, the caster creates a strong and sturdy wrapping around the subject desired — a bit of herbs, a heap of flour, a bundle of cloth, etc. The material of the cantrip is of a suitable type and thickness for the item(s) to be wrapped. Thus, a few ounces of fine powder will be contained in a waxy tissue, gemstones in a felt-like envelope, meal in cloth, and so forth. The wrapping can be undone normally, but the caster can just as easily order it to open, so the cantrip is often used to enfold the material components of a spell. The caster verbalizes a general class of wrapping desired while making folding motions with his hands.\nReversed Cantrips: Curdle (Enchantment)\nThis cantrip is broader than its name, for it affects many food and drink items. The magic curdles milk and hastens spoilage or wilting, but does not putrefy food & drink as per that spell. It has a permanent effect on the object. It is otherwise similar to freshen. The caster verbalizes a retching sound while pointing the thumb downward.","notes":"When a wrap cantrip is employed, the caster creates a strong and sturdy wrapping around the subject desired — a bit of herbs, a heap of flour, a bundle of cloth, etc. The material of the cantrip is of a suitable type and thickness for the item(s) to be wrapped. Thus, a few ounces of fine powder will be contained in a waxy tissue, gemstones in a felt-like envelope, meal in cloth, and so forth. The wrapping can be undone normally, but the caster can just as easily order it to open, so the cantrip is often used to enfold the material components of a spell. The caster verbalizes a general class of wrapping desired while making folding motions with his hands.\nReversed Cantrips: Curdle (Enchantment)\nThis cantrip is broader than its name, for it affects many food and drink items. The magic curdles milk and hastens spoilage or wilting, but does not putrefy food & drink as per that spell. It has a permanent effect on the object. It is otherwise similar to freshen. The caster verbalizes a retching sound while pointing the thumb downward.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Wrap"},"magic user yawn":{"name":"Yawn","level":"0","school":"Evocation","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One bee","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"A yawn cantrip makes the subject creature feel a brief wave of drowsiness which in turn evokes a yawn reaction. If a saving throw versus spell succeeds, the subject creature is totally unaffected by the dweomer of the cantrip. Failure, however, not only forces a yawn to immediately occur, but the subject is then more susceptible to a sleep spell. During the balance of the round in which the yawn cantrip was cast, and during the whole of the following round, the subject will automatically fall into comatose slumber from a sleep spell cast upon it, so 1 additional creature will be vulnerable to the spell if more than 1 creature of 4 or fewer hit dice are subjected to the spell. Further, if creatures of 4 + 1 to 4 + 4 hit dice are involved, there is then a chance that two such creatures will actually be affected by sleep. Even a creature of up to 5 + 2 hit dice can be affected by sleep if previously victimized by a yawn cantrip, but the effect of the sleep spell is rolled for as if the creature had 4 + 1 to 4 + 4 hit dice; i.e., there is a 50% chance that it will not be affected. The caster hums a lullaby for the verbal component while making a rocking motion with cupped hands.\nPersonal Cantrips: Bee (Summoning)\nWhen this cantrip is used, the caster summons a honey bee from someplace — where is of no importance, for the creature appears in seconds. The bee will appear in whatever spot the caster is gazing at, up to 1' distance from him or her. The bee is, of course, annoyed, and it is 90% likely to sting any living creature it finds itself upon. (This will certainly cause the subject to react violently if it would otherwise be so affected by a bee sting.) The verbal component is a low buzzing sound, made while the caster moves a forefinger through flight-like passes.","notes":"A yawn cantrip makes the subject creature feel a brief wave of drowsiness which in turn evokes a yawn reaction. If a saving throw versus spell succeeds, the subject creature is totally unaffected by the dweomer of the cantrip. Failure, however, not only forces a yawn to immediately occur, but the subject is then more susceptible to a sleep spell. During the balance of the round in which the yawn cantrip was cast, and during the whole of the following round, the subject will automatically fall into comatose slumber from a sleep spell cast upon it, so 1 additional creature will be vulnerable to the spell if more than 1 creature of 4 or fewer hit dice are subjected to the spell. Further, if creatures of 4 + 1 to 4 + 4 hit dice are involved, there is then a chance that two such creatures will actually be affected by sleep. Even a creature of up to 5 + 2 hit dice can be affected by sleep if previously victimized by a yawn cantrip, but the effect of the sleep spell is rolled for as if the creature had 4 + 1 to 4 + 4 hit dice; i.e., there is a 50% chance that it will not be affected. The caster hums a lullaby for the verbal component while making a rocking motion with cupped hands.\nPersonal Cantrips: Bee (Summoning)\nWhen this cantrip is used, the caster summons a honey bee from someplace — where is of no importance, for the creature appears in seconds. The bee will appear in whatever spot the caster is gazing at, up to 1' distance from him or her. The bee is, of course, annoyed, and it is 90% likely to sting any living creature it finds itself upon. (This will certainly cause the subject to react violently if it would otherwise be so affected by a bee sting.) The verbal component is a low buzzing sound, made while the caster moves a forefinger through flight-like passes.","link":"","class":"Magic-User","select_value":"Magic-User: Yawn"},"alarm":{"name":"Alarm","level":"1","school":"Evocation","range":"1”","duration":"2d4 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"Up to 20 square feet per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Alarm\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 2d4 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Up to 20 square feet per level\nWhen cast, this spell causes a selected area, such as a portal, section of floor, or stairs, to react to the presence of any living creature larger than a normal rat. When such a creature contacts the area, the spell produces a loud ringing audible within a 60-foot radius, reduced by 10 feet for each interposing door and by 20 feet for each substantial wall. The sound lasts 1 segment. Undead do not trigger the spell, but invisible, flying, levitating, and otherwise living extraplanar creatures do. Ethereal and astrally projected creatures do not. Material Components: A tiny bell and a piece of very fine silver wire.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user alarm":{"name":"Alarm","level":"1","school":"Evocation","range":"1”","duration":"2d4 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"Up to 20 square feet per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Alarm\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 2d4 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Up to 20 square feet per level\nWhen cast, this spell causes a selected area, such as a portal, section of floor, or stairs, to react to the presence of any living creature larger than a normal rat. When such a creature contacts the area, the spell produces a loud ringing audible within a 60-foot radius, reduced by 10 feet for each interposing door and by 20 feet for each substantial wall. The sound lasts 1 segment. Undead do not trigger the spell, but invisible, flying, levitating, and otherwise living extraplanar creatures do. Ethereal and astrally projected creatures do not. Material Components: A tiny bell and a piece of very fine silver wire.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Alarm","class":"Magic-User"},"armor":{"name":"Armor","level":"1","school":"Conjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Armor\n\nSchool: Conjuration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell creates a magical force field equivalent to leather armor, AC 8. If cast on an already armored person, it has no effect. If cast on a creature whose natural Armor Class is already better than 9 because of size, speed, hide, or similar traits, it improves that Armor Class by one step. The spell does not hinder movement, add weight, create encumbrance, or prevent spellcasting. It lasts until dispelled or until the wearer takes cumulative damage greater than 8 points + 1 point per caster level. It does not function with protective magic devices except a ring of protection. Material Component: A piece of finely cured leather blessed by a cleric.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user armor":{"name":"Armor","level":"1","school":"Conjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Armor\n\nSchool: Conjuration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell creates a magical force field equivalent to leather armor, AC 8. If cast on an already armored person, it has no effect. If cast on a creature whose natural Armor Class is already better than 9 because of size, speed, hide, or similar traits, it improves that Armor Class by one step. The spell does not hinder movement, add weight, create encumbrance, or prevent spellcasting. It lasts until dispelled or until the wearer takes cumulative damage greater than 8 points + 1 point per caster level. It does not function with protective magic devices except a ring of protection. Material Component: A piece of finely cured leather blessed by a cleric.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Armor","class":"Magic-User"},"firewater":{"name":"Firewater","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"1”","duration":"1 round","aoe":"1 pint of water per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Firewater\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 pint of water per caster level\nThis spell changes water into a volatile, flammable substance similar to alcohol and lighter than water. If exposed to flame, fire, or even a spark, it bursts into hot flame. Creatures caught in the flame take 2d6 damage. The firewater evaporates and becomes useless within 1 round, even if sealed, so it must be ignited within 10 segments of creation. Material Components: A few grains of sugar and a raisin.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user firewater":{"name":"Firewater","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"1”","duration":"1 round","aoe":"1 pint of water per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Firewater\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 pint of water per caster level\nThis spell changes water into a volatile, flammable substance similar to alcohol and lighter than water. If exposed to flame, fire, or even a spark, it bursts into hot flame. Creatures caught in the flame take 2d6 damage. The firewater evaporates and becomes useless within 1 round, even if sealed, so it must be ignited within 10 segments of creation. Material Components: A few grains of sugar and a raisin.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Firewater","class":"Magic-User"},"grease":{"name":"Grease","level":"1","school":"Evocation","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1 square foot per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Grease\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 1 square foot per caster level\nThis spell covers an area with a slippery fatty substance. Any creature stepping on it must save versus petrification or slip, skid, and fall. If a creature is aware of the area, it may be able to avoid it. The spell may also coat another surface, such as a rope, ladder rungs, or weapon handle. Unattended objects are automatically affected; objects held or used by a creature are affected only if the creature fails a saving throw versus spell. A successful save negates the effect. Material Component: A bit of pork rind, butter, or another greasy substance.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user grease":{"name":"Grease","level":"1","school":"Evocation","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1 square foot per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Grease\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 1 square foot per caster level\nThis spell covers an area with a slippery fatty substance. Any creature stepping on it must save versus petrification or slip, skid, and fall. If a creature is aware of the area, it may be able to avoid it. The spell may also coat another surface, such as a rope, ladder rungs, or weapon handle. Unattended objects are automatically affected; objects held or used by a creature are affected only if the creature fails a saving throw versus spell. A successful save negates the effect. Material Component: A bit of pork rind, butter, or another greasy substance.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Grease","class":"Magic-User"},"melt":{"name":"Melt","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"1 cubic yard of ice or 2 cubic yards of snow per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Melt\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic yard of ice or 2 cubic yards of snow per caster level\nThis spell raises the temperature in the area of effect, melting ice or snow. A 1st-level magic-user can melt a 1-yard cube of solid ice in 1 round, or twice that volume of snow. Against cold-related creatures such as white dragons, winter wolves, yeti, woolly rhinoceroses, creatures of para-elemental ice, and similar beings, melt deals 2 damage per caster level, or 1 damage per caster level if the target saves versus spell. It is generally ineffective against other creatures. Material Components: A few crystals of rock salt and a pinch of soot.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user melt":{"name":"Melt","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"1 cubic yard of ice or 2 cubic yards of snow per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Melt\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic yard of ice or 2 cubic yards of snow per caster level\nThis spell raises the temperature in the area of effect, melting ice or snow. A 1st-level magic-user can melt a 1-yard cube of solid ice in 1 round, or twice that volume of snow. Against cold-related creatures such as white dragons, winter wolves, yeti, woolly rhinoceroses, creatures of para-elemental ice, and similar beings, melt deals 2 damage per caster level, or 1 damage per caster level if the target saves versus spell. It is generally ineffective against other creatures. Material Components: A few crystals of rock salt and a pinch of soot.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Melt","class":"Magic-User"},"mount":{"name":"Mount","level":"1","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1”","duration":"12 turns + 6 turns per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mount\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 12 turns + 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell summons a normal animal to serve willingly as a mount. When the spell ends, the animal disappears and returns to its own place. The mount depends on caster level: 1st–3rd level, mule or light horse; 4th–7th level, draft horse or warhorse; 8th–12th level, camel; 13th level and higher, elephant, with howdah at 18th level. A caster may choose a lower-level mount. A lower-level mount may come with riding gear; for example, a 4th-level magic-user may summon a warhorse without saddle and harness or a light horse with saddle and harness. Material Component: A bit of hair or dung from the animal type to be summoned.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user mount":{"name":"Mount","level":"1","school":"Conjuration/Summoning","range":"1”","duration":"12 turns + 6 turns per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mount\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Summoning\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 12 turns + 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell summons a normal animal to serve willingly as a mount. When the spell ends, the animal disappears and returns to its own place. The mount depends on caster level: 1st–3rd level, mule or light horse; 4th–7th level, draft horse or warhorse; 8th–12th level, camel; 13th level and higher, elephant, with howdah at 18th level. A caster may choose a lower-level mount. A lower-level mount may come with riding gear; for example, a 4th-level magic-user may summon a warhorse without saddle and harness or a light horse with saddle and harness. Material Component: A bit of hair or dung from the animal type to be summoned.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Mount","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user precipitation":{"name":"Precipitation","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 segment per level","aoe":"3” diameter cylinder up to 12” high","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None and special","save_type":"","description":"Precipitation\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 segment per level\nSaving Throw: None and special\nArea of Effect: 3” diameter cylinder up to 12” high\nThis spell is identical to the 1st-level clerical spell precipitation, except that a holy symbol is not part of the material component.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Precipitation","class":"Magic-User"},"run":{"name":"Run","level":"1","school":"Enchantment","range":"Touch","duration":"5–8 hours","aoe":"Humans and demi-humans only","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Run\n\nSchool: Enchantment\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 5–8 hours\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Humans and demi-humans only\nThe recipient can run at full speed, twice normal movement, for 5–8 hours without tiring. Afterward, the recipient must rest for an equal number of hours and consume plenty of liquids and food. For every 2 caster levels, one additional individual can be affected. Only humans and demi-humans in natural form are affected; barbarians with their special running ability are immune. Material Component: An elixir made from dried plum juice boiled in spring water and oil from 5–8 castor beans.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user run":{"name":"Run","level":"1","school":"Enchantment","range":"Touch","duration":"5–8 hours","aoe":"Humans and demi-humans only","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Run\n\nSchool: Enchantment\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 5–8 hours\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Humans and demi-humans only\nThe recipient can run at full speed, twice normal movement, for 5–8 hours without tiring. Afterward, the recipient must rest for an equal number of hours and consume plenty of liquids and food. For every 2 caster levels, one additional individual can be affected. Only humans and demi-humans in natural form are affected; barbarians with their special running ability are immune. Material Component: An elixir made from dried plum juice boiled in spring water and oil from 5–8 castor beans.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Run","class":"Magic-User"},"taunt":{"name":"Taunt","level":"1","school":"Enchantment","range":"3”","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"2 levels or Hit Dice per caster level","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Taunt\n\nSchool: Enchantment\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 2 levels or Hit Dice per caster level\nThis spell lets the caster jape, jeer, insult, and challenge creatures of Intelligence 2 or higher. If affected creatures fail their saves, they rush forward in fury to battle the caster, using body weapons or hand-held weapons rather than ranged attacks if physically possible. An uncrossable or impenetrable barrier, such as a wall of flame or deep chasm, breaks the spell. Only one creature type can be affected by a single casting. The spell affects the nearest eligible creatures first. Troops under a strong leader may gain a +1 