ntent, and erase removes the mark. Material Components: About 50 gp worth of diamond dust and suitable pigments. If the mark is invisible, pigments are still needed, but a stylus is used instead of the caster’s finger.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 2nd Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user wizard mark":{"name":"Wizard Mark","level":"1","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1 square foot","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wizard Mark\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 square foot\nThis spell lets the magic-user inscribe a personal rune or mark, visibly or invisibly, along with up to six smaller characters. The mark can be etched into stone, metal, or softer substances without damaging the material. An invisible mark glows and becomes readable under detect magic. Detect invisibility, true seeing, true sight, a gem of seeing, or a robe of eyes also reveals it. Read magic reveals the maker’s intent, and erase removes the mark. Material Components: About 50 gp worth of diamond dust and suitable pigments. If the mark is invisible, pigments are still needed, but a stylus is used instead of the caster’s finger.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 2nd Level","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Wizard Mark","class":"Magic-User"},"bind":{"name":"Bind","level":"2","school":"Alteration/Enchantment","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Bind\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enchantment\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes a nonliving rope-like object to obey simple commands. It can affect about 50 feet of normal 1-inch rope, plus 5 feet per caster level. Larger diameter reduces length proportionally; half diameter increases length by 50%. Commands include coil, coil and knot, loop, loop and knot, tie and knot, and their reverses. The rope must be within about 1 foot of an object to respond properly, so it must usually be thrown or placed nearby. The rope can act like a normal object for creatures interacting with it. It cannot be used as a garrote, but can be used as a trip line or to entangle one opponent, as the druid spell. It gains no magical properties beyond obeying commands.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user bind":{"name":"Bind","level":"2","school":"Alteration/Enchantment","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Bind\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enchantment\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell causes a nonliving rope-like object to obey simple commands. It can affect about 50 feet of normal 1-inch rope, plus 5 feet per caster level. Larger diameter reduces length proportionally; half diameter increases length by 50%. Commands include coil, coil and knot, loop, loop and knot, tie and knot, and their reverses. The rope must be within about 1 foot of an object to respond properly, so it must usually be thrown or placed nearby. The rope can act like a normal object for creatures interacting with it. It cannot be used as a garrote, but can be used as a trip line or to entangle one opponent, as the druid spell. It gains no magical properties beyond obeying commands.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Bind","class":"Magic-User"},"deeppockets":{"name":"Deeppockets","level":"2","school":"Alteration/Enchantment","range":"Touch","duration":"24 turns + 6 turns per level","aoe":"One garment","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Deeppockets\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enchantment\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 24 turns + 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One garment\nThis spell prepares a high-quality garment, worth at least 300 gp and sewn with at least twelve hand-sized pockets, to hold more than it normally could. One pocket can hold 1,000 gp weight and 5 cubic feet of volume as if it weighed only 100 gp, with no visible bulge. Alternatively, the spell can empower 10 pockets to hold 100 gp weight and ½ cubic foot each. A garment with 100 or more pockets and worth at least 1,000 gp can have 100 pockets each hold 10 gp weight and 1/6 cubic foot. If the spell expires or is dispelled while items are inside, the wearer must save versus spell. Failure sends the contents into astral space, lost forever. Success causes the contents to appear around the wearer and fall to the ground. Material Components: The garment, a tiny golden needle, and a half-twisted strip of fine cloth fastened at the ends.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user deeppockets":{"name":"Deeppockets","level":"2","school":"Alteration/Enchantment","range":"Touch","duration":"24 turns + 6 turns per level","aoe":"One garment","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Deeppockets\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enchantment\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 24 turns + 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One garment\nThis spell prepares a high-quality garment, worth at least 300 gp and sewn with at least twelve hand-sized pockets, to hold more than it normally could. One pocket can hold 1,000 gp weight and 5 cubic feet of volume as if it weighed only 100 gp, with no visible bulge. Alternatively, the spell can empower 10 pockets to hold 100 gp weight and ½ cubic foot each. A garment with 100 or more pockets and worth at least 1,000 gp can have 100 pockets each hold 10 gp weight and 1/6 cubic foot. If the spell expires or is dispelled while items are inside, the wearer must save versus spell. Failure sends the contents into astral space, lost forever. Success causes the contents to appear around the wearer and fall to the ground. Material Components: The garment, a tiny golden needle, and a half-twisted strip of fine cloth fastened at the ends.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Deeppockets","class":"Magic-User"},"flaming sphere":{"name":"Flaming Sphere","level":"2","school":"Alteration/Evocation","range":"1”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"6-foot diameter sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Flaming Sphere\n\nSchool: Alteration/Evocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 6-foot diameter sphere\nThis spell creates a burning globe of normal fire up to 1” from the caster. The sphere rolls in the direction the caster points, even uphill, and can roll over low barriers up to 4 feet tall. Flammable substances ignite on contact. Creatures struck suffer 2d4 damage. Creatures within 5 feet of the sphere’s center must save versus spell or take the damage; a successful save negates the sphere for that creature. The sphere moves 1” per round while the caster points its direction; otherwise, it remains still and burns. It can be extinguished like a normal fire of its size. Material Components: A bit of tallow, a pinch of sulfur, and powdered iron.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user flaming sphere":{"name":"Flaming Sphere","level":"2","school":"Alteration/Evocation","range":"1”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"6-foot diameter sphere","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Flaming Sphere\n\nSchool: Alteration/Evocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 6-foot diameter sphere\nThis spell creates a burning globe of normal fire up to 1” from the caster. The sphere rolls in the direction the caster points, even uphill, and can roll over low barriers up to 4 feet tall. Flammable substances ignite on contact. Creatures struck suffer 2d4 damage. Creatures within 5 feet of the sphere’s center must save versus spell or take the damage; a successful save negates the sphere for that creature. The sphere moves 1” per round while the caster points its direction; otherwise, it remains still and burns. It can be extinguished like a normal fire of its size. Material Components: A bit of tallow, a pinch of sulfur, and powdered iron.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Flaming Sphere","class":"Magic-User"},"irritation":{"name":"Irritation","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Irritation\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell affects the subject’s skin. Creatures with very thick or insensitive hides, such as buffalo, elephants, and scaled creatures, are generally unaffected. The spell has two versions. Itching: The subject feels instant itching. If it does not spend 5–8 segments scratching immediately, it spends the next 3 rounds squirming and twisting, lowering Armor Class by 4 and attack rolls by 2. Spells are ruined during the initial round, but not during the following 3 rounds. Rash: The subject notices nothing for 1d4 rounds, then breaks out in red welts that faintly itch. The rash lasts until removed by cure disease or dispel magic. It lowers Comeliness by 1 point per day for up to 4 days. After 1 week, Dexterity is also lowered by 1 point. Symptoms vanish immediately when the rash is removed. Material Component: Powdered poison ivy, poison oak, or poison sumac leaf.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user irritation":{"name":"Irritation","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Irritation\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell affects the subject’s skin. Creatures with very thick or insensitive hides, such as buffalo, elephants, and scaled creatures, are generally unaffected. The spell has two versions. Itching: The subject feels instant itching. If it does not spend 5–8 segments scratching immediately, it spends the next 3 rounds squirming and twisting, lowering Armor Class by 4 and attack rolls by 2. Spells are ruined during the initial round, but not during the following 3 rounds. Rash: The subject notices nothing for 1d4 rounds, then breaks out in red welts that faintly itch. The rash lasts until removed by cure disease or dispel magic. It lowers Comeliness by 1 point per day for up to 4 days. After 1 week, Dexterity is also lowered by 1 point. Symptoms vanish immediately when the rash is removed. Material Component: Powdered poison ivy, poison oak, or poison sumac leaf.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Irritation","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user know alignment":{"name":"Know Alignment","level":"2","school":"Divination","range":"1”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"One creature per 2 rounds","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Know Alignment\n\nSchool: Divination\nReversible: Yes\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature per 2 rounds\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 2nd-level clerical spell of the same name. If a target is examined for only 1 round, only its ethical alignment, law or chaos, is discerned.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Know Alignment","class":"Magic-User"},"melf s acid arrow":{"name":"Melf’s Acid Arrow","level":"2","school":"Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"Special","aoe":"One target","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Melf’s Acid Arrow\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One target\nThis spell creates a magical arrow that attacks as if fired from a bow by a fighter of the same level as the caster. The arrow counts as a +1 weapon for hit determination. A hit may damage creatures that would not normally be harmed by arrows or +1 weapons because of the acid. The arrow deals 1d4+1 damage, and the acid deals 2d4 damage in a 1-foot diameter area, with applicable item saving throws. The acid lasts longer at higher caster levels: one additional round of damage for every 3 caster levels above 3rd, so a 4th–6th-level caster deals acid damage over 2 rounds unless neutralized. Material Components: A dart, powdered rhubarb leaf, and adder stomach.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user melf s acid arrow":{"name":"Melf’s Acid Arrow","level":"2","school":"Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"Special","aoe":"One target","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Melf’s Acid Arrow\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One target\nThis spell creates a magical arrow that attacks as if fired from a bow by a fighter of the same level as the caster. The arrow counts as a +1 weapon for hit determination. A hit may damage creatures that would not