, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Illusion\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Line of sight, 1” wide and 1” per level long\nThis spell is the same as the 1st-level illusionist spell detect illusion, except as noted above.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Detect Illusion","class":"Magic-User"},"item":{"name":"Item","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns per level, quadrupled for nonliving material","aoe":"2 cubic feet per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Item\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 6 turns per level, quadrupled for nonliving material\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 2 cubic feet per caster level\nThis spell shrinks a normal, nonmagical item to one-twelfth normal size. The caster may also change the shrunken object’s composition to cloth-like material. Only living things receive a saving throw versus spell, and they save at +4. Objects and creatures changed to cloth make normal saving throws against later attacks. Affected objects can be restored to normal size and composition by tossing them onto a solid surface or by the original caster’s command word. The spell can affect fire and its fuel.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user item":{"name":"Item","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns per level, quadrupled for nonliving material","aoe":"2 cubic feet per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Item\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 6 turns per level, quadrupled for nonliving material\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 2 cubic feet per caster level\nThis spell shrinks a normal, nonmagical item to one-twelfth normal size. The caster may also change the shrunken object’s composition to cloth-like material. Only living things receive a saving throw versus spell, and they save at +4. Objects and creatures changed to cloth make normal saving throws against later attacks. Affected objects can be restored to normal size and composition by tossing them onto a solid surface or by the original caster’s command word. The spell can affect fire and its fuel.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Item","class":"Magic-User"},"material":{"name":"Material","level":"3","school":"Evocation/Conjuration","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1 cubic foot per caster level","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Material\n\nSchool: Evocation/Conjuration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per caster level\nThis spell brings common basic materials into being. Stone, earth, soil, wood, water, air, dung, straw, and similar raw, unworked, inorganic or nonliving materials are easy to create. Simple plant life, such as grass, has a base 100% chance of failure, reduced by 1% per caster level. Animal life cannot be created. Worked, refined, or fabricated items cannot be created, nor can rough gems or precious metals. The spell creates only common things of a basic nature.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user material":{"name":"Material","level":"3","school":"Evocation/Conjuration","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1 cubic foot per caster level","components":"V, S","ct":"1 round","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Material\n\nSchool: Evocation/Conjuration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic foot per caster level\nThis spell brings common basic materials into being. Stone, earth, soil, wood, water, air, dung, straw, and similar raw, unworked, inorganic or nonliving materials are easy to create. Simple plant life, such as grass, has a base 100% chance of failure, reduced by 1% per caster level. Animal life cannot be created. Worked, refined, or fabricated items cannot be created, nor can rough gems or precious metals. The spell creates only common things of a basic nature.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Material","class":"Magic-User"},"melf s minute meteors":{"name":"Melf’s Minute Meteors","level":"3","school":"Evocation/Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"One target per missile","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Melf’s Minute Meteors\n\nSchool: Evocation/Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One target per missile\nThis spell lets the caster throw small globes of fire that burst into 1-foot spheres on impact, dealing 1d4 damage to the target or igniting combustibles, even solid planks. Misses are treated as grenade-like missiles. The caster may release one meteor per caster level, until all are fired, the caster stops, or dispel magic succeeds against the caster. The caster chooses one of two firing modes and cannot switch afterward. In the first mode, a missile is discharged every 2 segments after casting until all are released. In the second mode, the caster releases up to one missile each round and may also cast another non-concentration spell in the same round. If the caster loses exact mental count of the remaining missiles, the rest of the spell is involuntarily lost. Material Components: Nitre and sulfur formed into a bead with pine tar, and a tiny hollow gold tube worth at least 1,000 gp, which is reusable unless damaged.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic use