l\nThis spell creates many rubbery black tentacles in the area of effect, springing from the surface underfoot, including water. Each tentacle is 10 feet long, AC 4, and has hit points equal to the caster’s level. The spell creates one tentacle per caster level. Any creature within reach may be attacked. If more than one target is in reach, target probability is determined by die roll. A victim must save versus spell. Success means it takes 1d4 damage from initial contact and the tentacle is destroyed. Failure means it takes 2d4 damage, the tentacle wraps around it, and it takes 3d4 damage on the second and later rounds. Tentacles have no intelligence and may grab objects, continue squeezing dead opponents, or otherwise act blindly. Once grasped, a tentacle holds until destroyed or until the spell ends. Material Component: A piece of tentacle from a giant octopus or giant squid.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Evard’s Black Tentacles","class":"Magic-User"},"leomund s secure shelter":{"name":"Leomund’s Secure Shelter","level":"4","school":"Alteration/Enchantment","range":"2”","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"30 square feet per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 turns","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Leomund’s Secure Shelter\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enchantment\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2”\nCasting Time: 4 turns\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 30 square feet per caster level\nThis spell creates a sturdy cottage or lodge made of common local materials such as stone, timber, or sod. The lodging has 30 square feet of floor area per caster level and a level, clean, dry floor. It resembles a normal cottage, with a strong door, at least two shuttered windows, and a small fireplace. It withstands winds up to 70 miles per hour, is as strong as a stone building regardless of material, resists fire as stone, and is generally impervious to normal missiles, though not siege missiles or giant-thrown projectiles. The door and shutters are wizard locked, the chimney has an iron grate and narrow flue, and these entry points are protected by alarm. An unseen servant is also created to serve the caster. The interior contains crude furnishings as desired, up to 8 bunks, a trestle table and benches, up to 4 chairs or 8 stools, and a writing desk. Material Components: A square chip of stone, crushed lime, grains of sand, water, and wood splinters, plus the components for alarm and unseen servant if those effects are included.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user leomund s secure shelter":{"name":"Leomund’s Secure Shelter","level":"4","school":"Alteration/Enchantment","range":"2”","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"30 square feet per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 turns","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Leomund’s Secure Shelter\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enchantment\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2”\nCasting Time: 4 turns\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 30 square feet per caster level\nThis spell creates a sturdy cottage or lodge made of common local materials such as stone, timber, or sod. The lodging has 30 square feet of floor area per caster level and a level, clean, dry floor. It resembles a normal cottage, with a strong door, at least two shuttered windows, and a small fireplace. It withstands winds up to 70 miles per hour, is as strong as a stone building regardless of material, resists fire as stone, and is generally impervious to normal missiles, though not siege missiles or giant-thrown projectiles. The door and shutters are wizard locked, the chimney has an iron grate and narrow flue, and these entry points are protected by alarm. An unseen servant is also created to serve the caster. The interior contains crude furnishings as desired, up to 8 bunks, a trestle table and benches, up to 4 chairs or 8 stools, and a writing desk. Material Components: A square chip of stone, crushed lime, grains of sand, water, and wood splinters, plus the components for alarm and unseen servant if those effects are included.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Leomund’s Secure Shelter","class":"Magic-User"},"magic mirror":{"name":"Magic Mirror","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Divination","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 hour","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Magic Mirror\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Divination\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 hour\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell turns a normal mirror into a scrying device similar to a crystal ball. The mirror must be finely wrought, highly polished silver worth at least 1,000 gp and is not consumed. The spell follows the crystal ball rules. The following spells can be cast through the mirror: comprehend languages, read magic, tongues, infravision, and ultravision. The following spells have a 5% chance per caster level of working correctly through the mirror: detect magic, detect good/evil, message, and detect illusion. Targets may notice they are being watched as with crystal ball magic; cavaliers have a base 5% chance and barbarians a base 1% chance. Material Components: The silver mirror, plus the eye of a hawk, eagle, or roc, and nitric acid, copper, and zinc.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user magic mirror":{"name":"Magic Mirror","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Divination","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 hour","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Magic Mirror\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Divination\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 hour\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell turns a normal mirror into a scrying device similar to a crystal ball. The mirror must be finely wrought, highly polished silver worth at least 1,000 gp and is not consumed. The spell follows the crystal ball rules. The following spells can be cast through the mirror: comprehend languages, read magic, tongues, infravision, and ultravision. The following spells have a 5% chance per caster level of working correctly through the mirror: detect magic, detect good/evil, message, and detect illusion. Targets may notice they are being watched as with crystal ball magic; cavaliers have a base 5% chance and barbarians a base 1% chance. Material Components: The silver mirror, plus the eye of a hawk, eagle, or roc, and nitric acid, copper, and zinc.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Magic Mirror","class":"Magic-User"},"otiluke s resilient sphere":{"name":"Otiluke’s Resilient Sphere","level":"4","school":"Alteration/Evocation","range":"2”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"1-foot diameter sphere per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Otiluke’s Resilient Sphere\n\nSchool: Alteration/Evocation\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 1-foot diameter sphere per caster level\nThis spell encloses a subject in a globe of shimmering force if the subject fits inside and fails a saving throw versus spell. The sphere contains the subject for the spell’s duration and is immune to damage except from a rod of cancellation, wand of negation, disintegrate, or dispel magic, which destroy the sphere without harming the subject. Nothing passes through the sphere in either direction, but the subject can breathe normally. The subject may struggle, causing the sphere to move; people outside can also move it physically. Material Components: A hemispherical piece of diamond or similar hard clear gem and a matching hemispherical piece of gum arabic.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user otiluke s resilient sphere":{"name":"Otiluke’s Resilient Sphere","level":"4","school":"Alteration/Evocation","range":"2”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"1-foot diameter sphere per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Otiluke’s Resilient Sphere\n\nSchool: Alteration/Evocation\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 1-foot diameter sphere per caster level\nThis spell encloses a subject in a globe of shimmering force if the subject fits inside and fails a saving throw versus spell. The sphere contains the subject for the spell’s duration and is immune to damage except from a rod of cancellation, wand of negation, disintegrate, or dispel magic, which destroy the sphere without harming the subject. Nothing passes through the sphere in either direction, but the subject can breathe normally. The subject may struggle, causing the sphere to move; people outside can also move it physically. Material Components: A hemispherical piece of diamond or similar hard clear gem and a matching hemispherical piece of gum arabic.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Otiluke’s Resilient Sphere","class":"Magic-User"},"shout":{"name":"Shout","level":"4","school":"Evocation","range":"0","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"1” × 3” cone","components":"V, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Shout\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 1” × 3” cone\nThis spell grants the caster tremendous vocal power, releasing an ear-splitting cone of sound from the caster’s mouth. Creatures in the cone are deafened for 2d6 rounds and take 2d6 damage unless they save. Exposed brittle or vibration-sensitive substances, such as a wall of ice, may shatter. The spell can be used only once per day, or the caster risks permanent deafness. Material Components: A drop of honey, a drop of citric acid, and a small cone made from a bull’s or ram’s horn.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user shout":{"name":"Shout","level":"4","school":"Evocation","range":"0","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"1” × 3” cone","components":"V, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Shout\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 1” × 3” cone\nThis spell grants the caster tremendous vocal power, releasing an ear-splitting cone of sound from the caster’s mouth. Creatures in the cone are deafened for 2d6 rounds and take 2d6 damage unless they save. Exposed brittle or vibration-sensitive substances, such as a wall of ice, may shatter. The spell can be used only once per day, or the caster risks permanent deafness. Material Components: A drop of honey, a drop of citric acid, and a small cone made from a bull’s or ram’s horn.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Shout","class":"Magic-User"},"stoneskin":{"name":"Stoneskin","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Stoneskin\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThe recipient gains virtual immunity to one attack by cut, blow, projectile, or similar physical attack. A sword of sharpness, giant-hurled rock, snake strike, and similar attacks have no effect while the spell protects. Magical attacks such as fireball, magic missile, and lightning bolt affect the target normally. Any attack or attack sequence from a single opponent dispels the spell, though the recipient is immune to that attack or sequence. Soft weapon attacks, such as a monk’s hands or an ogrillon’s fist, deal 1d2 damage to the attacker while the spell lasts but do not dispel it. Material Components: Granite and diamond dust sprinkled on the recipient’s skin.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user stoneskin":{"name":"Stoneskin","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Stoneskin\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThe recipient gains virtual immunity to one attack by cut, blow, projectile, or similar physical attack. A sword of sharpness, giant-hurled rock, snake strike, and similar attacks have no effect while the spell protects. Magical attacks such as fireball, magic missile, and lightning bolt affect the target normally. Any attack or attack sequence from a single opponent dispels the spell, though the recipient is immune to that attack or sequence. Soft weapon attacks, such as a monk’s hands or an ogrillon’s fist, deal 1d2 damage to the attacker while the spell lasts but do not dispel it. Material Components: Granite and diamond dust sprinkled on the recipient’s skin.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Stoneskin","class":"Magic-User"},"ultravision":{"name":"Ultravision","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns + 6 turns per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Ultravision\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 6 turns + 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell lets the recipient see ultraviolet radiation. At night, vision is clear as daylight to 100 yards, and shadowy from 100 to 300 yards. Heavy clouds reduce ultravision by 50%. Underground or under more than 6 feet of earth or 3 feet of stone, ultravision provides only dim sight in about a 3-foot radius, unless an ultraviolet source is nearby. Nearby light, including radiance from magic items, tends to spoil ultravision by blinding the eyes to dimmer, more distant areas. Material Component: A crushed amethyst worth at least 500 gp.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user ultravision":{"name":"Ultravision","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns + 6 turns per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Ultravision\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 6 turns + 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell lets the recipient see ultraviolet radiation. At night, vision is clear as daylight to 100 yards, and shadowy from 100 to 300 yards. Heavy clouds reduce ultravision by 50%. Underground or under more than 6 feet of earth or 3 feet of stone, ultravision provides only dim sight in about a 3-foot radius, unless an ultraviolet source is nearby. Nearby light, including radiance from magic items, tends to spoil ultravision by blinding the eyes to dimmer, more distant areas. Material Component: A crushed amethyst worth at least 500 gp.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Ultravision","class":"Magic-User"},"avoidance":{"name":"Avoidance","level":"5","school":"Abjuration/Alteration","range":"1”","duration":"Until dispelled","aoe":"Up to 3” cube","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Avoidance\n\nSchool: Abjuration/Alteration\nReversible: Attraction\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Until dispelled\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Up to 3” cube\nThis spell creates a natural repulsion between the affected object and living things. Any living creature attempting to touch the object is repulsed and cannot come closer than 1”, or the object is repulsed instead, depending on relative mass. A lone halfling trying to touch an iron chest affected by avoidance is thrown back; a dozen halflings cannot approach within 1”; a giant-sized creature causes the chest to skitter away. The spell cannot be cast on living things, and any attempt to cast it on apparel or possessions carried by a living creature allows the subject a saving throw. The reverse, attraction, creates a natural attraction between the affected object and living things. Smaller creatures are drawn to the object, while the object slides toward larger creatures. Once an object adheres to another object or creature, a successful bend bars roll is required to remove it. Material Component: A magnetized needle.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user avoidance":{"name":"Avoidance","level":"5","school":"Abjuration/Alteration","range":"1”","duration":"Until dispelled","aoe":"Up to 3” cube","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Avoidance\n\nSchool: Abjuration/Alteration\nReversible: Attraction\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Until dispelled\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Up to 3” cube\nThis spell creates a natural repulsion between the affected object and living things. Any living creature attempting to touch the object is repulsed and cannot come closer than 1”, or the object is repulsed instead, depending on relative mass. A lone halfling trying to touch an iron chest affected by avoidance is thrown back; a dozen halflings cannot approach within 1”; a giant-sized creature causes the chest to skitter away. The spell cannot be cast on living things, and any attempt to cast it on apparel or possessions carried by a living creature allows the subject a saving throw. The reverse, attraction, creates a natural attraction between the affected object and living things. Smaller creatures are drawn to the object, while the object slides toward larger creatures. Once an object adheres to another object or creature, a successful bend bars roll is required to remove it. Material Component: A magnetized needle.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Avoidance","class":"Magic-User"},"dismissal":{"name":"Dismissal","level":"5","school":"Abjuration","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Dismissal\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Beckon\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell allows a magic-user on the Prime Material Plane to force or allow a creature from another plane to return to its proper plane. The caster must know the creature type’s name, and if it has a given, proper, or surname, that name must also be known and used. Magic resistance is checked immediately. Then the caster’s level is compared to the creature’s level or Hit Dice. If the caster is higher level, the difference is subtracted from the creature’s saving throw score. If the creature is higher level or has more Hit Dice, the difference is added to its saving throw score. If the creature wishes to be dismissed, it makes only an unmodified saving throw. If successful, the creature is instantly sent away, though there is a 20% chance it is sent to a plane other than its own. The reverse, beckon, attempts to conjure a known and named creature from another plane. Success is determined as with dismissal, but magic resistance is checked only if the creature has no known proper name. A successfully beckoned creature is transported to the caster’s plane, but is not automatically friendly or obedient. Protective measures are commonly used, and even careful preparation may produce unwholesome results. The spell does not work on creatures native to the Prime Material Plane that travel to other planes, such as shedu, or on creatures with partial Prime Material ancestry, such as cambions. Material Components: For dismissal, items inimical or distasteful to the creature; for beckon, items pleasing, desirable, or rewarding to the creature.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user dismissal":{"name":"Dismissal","level":"5","school":"Abjuration","range":"1”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Dismissal\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nReversible: Beckon\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell allows a magic-user on the Prime Material Plane to force or allow a creature from another plane to return to its proper plane. The caster must know the creature type’s name, and if it has a given, proper, or surname, that name must also be known and used. Magic resistance is checked immediately. Then the caster’s level is compared to the creature’s level or Hit Dice. If the caster is higher level, the difference is subtracted from the creature’s saving throw score. If the creature is higher level or has more Hit Dice, the difference is added to its saving throw score. If the creature wishes to be dismissed, it makes only an unmodified saving throw. If successful, the creature is instantly sent away, though there is a 20% chance it is sent to a plane other than its own. The reverse, beckon, attempts to conjure a known and named creature from another plane. Success is determined as with dismissal, but magic resistance is checked only if the creature has no known proper name. A successfully beckoned creature is transported to the caster’s plane, but is not automatically friendly or obedient. Protective measures are commonly used, and even careful preparation may produce unwholesome results. The spell does not work on creatures native to the Prime Material Plane that travel to other planes, such as shedu, or on creatures with partial Prime Material ancestry, such as cambions. Material Components: For dismissal, items inimical or distasteful to the creature; for beckon, items pleasing, desirable, or rewarding to the creature.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Dismissal","class":"Magic-User"},"dolor":{"name":"Dolor","level":"5","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1”","duration":"2 rounds","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Dolor\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell attempts to force compliance or obedience from an oppositely aligned or hostile creature from a plane foreign to the caster’s. During the reading, the creature feels unease. On the following round, it becomes nervous and filled with doubts. On the final round, it feels a dull, all-encompassing dolor. The initial effect gives the creature -1 on saving throws versus commands and non-offensive spells, including charms. The secondary effect increases the penalty to -2. The tertiary effect increases it to -3. Afterward, the creature is no longer affected. The verbal component must address the creature’s class and contain as much information as possible about the subject. If the creature has higher Intelligence than the caster, it may mentally assail the caster during the spell. It has a 5% chance per point of superior Intelligence to charm and dominate the magic-user. If the caster is distracted or interrupted during casting, the creature automatically charms and dominates the caster.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user dolor":{"name":"Dolor","level":"5","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1”","duration":"2 rounds","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Dolor\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell attempts to force compliance or obedience from an oppositely aligned or hostile creature from a plane foreign to the caster’s. During the reading, the creature feels unease. On the following round, it becomes nervous and filled with doubts. On the final round, it feels a dull, all-encompassing dolor. The initial effect gives the creature -1 on saving throws versus commands and non-offensive spells, including charms. The secondary effect increases the penalty to -2. The tertiary effect increases it to -3. Afterward, the creature is no longer affected. The verbal component must address the creature’s class and contain as much information as possible about the subject. If the creature has higher Intelligence than the caster, it may mentally assail the caster during the spell. It has a 5% chance per point of superior Intelligence to charm and dominate the magic-user. If the caster is distracted or interrupted during casting, the creature automatically charms and dominates the caster.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Dolor","class":"Magic-User"},"fabricate":{"name":"Fabricate","level":"5","school":"Enchantment/Alteration","range":"½” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1 cubic yard per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Fabricate\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic yard per caster level\nThis spell converts material into a finished product made of basically the same material. The caster can fabricate a wooden bridge from trees, a rope from hemp, clothes from flax or wool, and similar products. Magical or living things cannot be created or altered. The quality of the finished item depends on the quality of the material used. If mineral material is used, the area of effect is reduced by a factor of nine, so 1 cubic yard becomes 1 cubic foot. Items requiring high craftsmanship, such as jewelry, swords, glass, or crystal, cannot be fabricated unless the magic-user actually has great skill in the relevant craft. Casting requires 1 full round per cubic yard, or per cubic foot for mineral material, affected.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user fabricate":{"name":"Fabricate","level":"5","school":"Enchantment/Alteration","range":"½” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"1 cubic yard per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Fabricate\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Alteration\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 cubic yard per caster level\nThis spell converts material into a finished product made of basically the same material. The caster can fabricate a wooden bridge from trees, a rope from hemp, clothes from flax or wool, and similar products. Magical or living things cannot be created or altered. The quality of the finished item depends on the quality of the material used. If mineral material is used, the area of effect is reduced by a factor of nine, so 1 cubic yard becomes 1 cubic foot. Items requiring high craftsmanship, such as jewelry, swords, glass, or crystal, cannot be fabricated unless the magic-user actually has great skill in the relevant craft. Casting requires 1 full round per cubic yard, or per cubic foot for mineral material, affected.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Fabricate","class":"Magic-User"},"leomund s lamentable belabourment":{"name":"Leomund’s Lamentable Belabourment","level":"5","school":"Enchantment/Evocation","range":"1”","duration":"Special","aoe":"One or more creatures in a 1” radius","components":"V","ct":"5 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Leomund’s Lamentable Belabourment\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Evocation\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One or more creatures in a 1” radius\nThis spell causes fascination, confusion, and rage in one or more creatures able to understand the caster’s language. Upon casting, the magic-user begins discussing a topic relevant to the affected creature or creatures. Those failing their saving throw versus spell immediately begin conversing with the caster, agreeing or disagreeing politely. As long as the caster continues the conversation and the subjects are not attacked, they ignore everything else and continue talking and arguing. Creatures with Intelligence 2 or lower are unaffected. Creatures with Intelligence 3–7 save at -1; Intelligence 8–10 save normally; Intelligence 11–14 save at +1; Intelligence 15 or higher save at +2. If maintained for more than 3 rounds, each subject must save again. Failure causes the subject to wander away in confusion for 3d4 rounds, avoiding the caster. Those who save remain fascinated and must continue saving in the 4th, 5th, and 6th rounds, or for as long as the spell continues, to avoid confusion. If maintained for more than 6 rounds, each subject must save to avoid entering a rage. A lone subject attacks itself; multiple subjects attack each other with intent to kill. Rage lasts 2d4+1 rounds. Subjects who save against rage realize they were affected and collapse to the ground, lamenting their foolishness, for 1d4 rounds unless attacked or disturbed. If the caster is attacked or distracted while maintaining the spell, the subjects do not notice. The caster may leave after casting, and the subjects continue as if the caster were still present for 1 full round. In such cases, later saving throws for confusion or rage are not made. The spell is entirely verbal.","notes"