s, the creature is trapped. Any other creatures in the area are also trapped unless they have magic resistance and succeed. The forcecage can be removed only by dispel magic or by expiration of the spell. By special preparation during memorization, this spell may be altered into forcecube. Forcecube has one-eighth the area of effect, a cube 1” on a side, and resembles a cube of force in all respects except those distinguishing a spell from a magic item. Special Component: During memorization, the magic-user must powder a diamond worth at least 1,000 gp and use the dust to trace the outline of the cage or cube desired. The dust is expended when the spell is memorized.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user forcecage":{"name":"Forcecage","level":"7","school":"Evocation","range":"1” per 2 levels","duration":"6 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"2” cube","components":"V, S, special","ct":"3–4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Forcecage\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, special\nRange: 1” per 2 levels\nCasting Time: 3–4 segments\nDuration: 6 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2” cube\nThis spell creates a cube of force with alternating bands of force and ½-foot gaps, making it a cage rather than a solid-walled enclosure. Creatures in the area are trapped unless they can pass through the openings. Spells and breath weapons can pass through the gaps. Creatures with magic resistance may make one attempt to pass through the cage walls. If resistance fails, the creature is trapped. Any other creatures in the area are also trapped unless they have magic resistance and succeed. The forcecage can be removed only by dispel magic or by expiration of the spell. By special preparation during memorization, this spell may be altered into forcecube. Forcecube has one-eighth the area of effect, a cube 1” on a side, and resembles a cube of force in all respects except those distinguishing a spell from a magic item. Special Component: During memorization, the magic-user must powder a diamond worth at least 1,000 gp and use the dust to trace the outline of the cage or cube desired. The dust is expended when the spell is memorized.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Forcecage","class":"Magic-User"},"mordenkainen s magnificent mansion":{"name":"Mordenkainen’s Magnificent Mansion","level":"7","school":"Alteration/Conjuration","range":"1”","duration":"1 hour per level","aoe":"300 square feet per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mordenkainen’s Magnificent Mansion\n\nSchool: Alteration/Conjuration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 7 rounds\nDuration: 1 hour per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 300 square feet per caster level\nThis spell conjures an extradimensional dwelling accessible only through a single point on the plane from which the spell is cast. From outside, observers see only faint shimmering in the air, about 4 feet wide and 8 feet high. The caster controls entry, and the portal shuts and becomes invisible behind the caster when they enter. The caster may reopen it from inside at will. Inside is a magnificent foyer with numerous chambers, furnishings, and enough food to serve a nine-course banquet to as many dozen people as the caster has levels. A staff of near-transparent, obedient, liveried servants attends those within. The air is clean, fresh, and warm. The mansion can be entered only through its portal; outside conditions do not affect it, and interior conditions do not pass outside. Rest and relaxation are normal, but the food is not. It seems excellent and filling while inside, but once outside, its nourishment vanishes and ravenous hunger strikes unless the individual actually ate normal food. For each imaginary meal eaten in the mansion, the individual must spend 1 hour eating normal fare. Failure causes the loss of 1 Strength point per meal. This loss is restored by eating as described, but must be corrected within 6 hours or the Strength loss is permanent. Material Components: A miniature ivory portal, a small piece of polished marble, and a tiny silver spoon, all destroyed when the spell is cast.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user mordenkainen s magnificent mansion":{"name":"Mordenkainen’s Magnificent Mansion","level":"7","school":"Alteration/Conjuration","range":"1”","duration":"1 hour per level","aoe":"300 square feet per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"7 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mordenkainen’s Magnificent Mansion\n\nSchool: Alteration/Conjuration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 7 rounds\nDuration: 1 hour per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 300 square feet per caster level\nThis spell conjures an extradimensional dwelling accessible only through a single point on the plane from which the spell is cast. From outside, observers see only faint shimmering in the air, about 4 feet wide and 8 feet high. The caster controls entry, and the portal shuts and becomes invisible behind the caster when they enter. The caster may reopen it from inside at will. Inside is a magnificent foyer with numerous chambers, furnishings, and enough food to serve a nine-course banquet to as many dozen people as the caster has levels. A staff of near-transparent, obedient, liveried servants attends those within. The air is clean, fresh, and warm. The mansion can be entered only through its portal; outside conditions do not affect it, and interior conditions do not pass outside. Rest and relaxation are normal, but the food is not. It seems excellent and filling while inside, but once outside, its nourishment vanishes and ravenous hunger strikes unless the individual actually ate normal food. For each imaginary meal eaten in the mansion, the individual must spend 1 hour eating normal fare. Failure causes the loss of 1 Strength point per meal. This loss is restored by eating as described, but must be corrected within 6 hours or the Strength loss is permanent. Material Components: A miniature ivory portal, a small piece of polished marble, and a tiny silver spoon, all destroyed when the spell is cast.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Mordenkainen’s Magnificent Mansion","class":"Magic-User"},"sequester":{"name":"Sequester","level":"7","school":"Illusion/Phantasm-Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 week + 1 day per level","aoe":"2” cube per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Sequester\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm-Abjuration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 week + 1 day per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 2” cube per caster level\nThis spell prevents detection and location spells from detecting or locating the affected objects, and also makes them invisible to any form of sight or seeing. It can hide a secret door, treasure vault, or similar subject. It does not prevent tactile discovery or discovery by devices such as a robe of eyes or gem of seeing. If cast on an unwilling creature able to resist, the target receives a normal saving throw versus spell. Living creatures and undead affected by sequester become comatose and remain in suspended animation until the spell ends or is dispelled. Material Components: Basilisk eyelash, gum arabic, and a dram of whitewash.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user sequester":{"name":"Sequester","level":"7","school":"Illusion/Phantasm-Abjuration","range":"Touch","duration":"1 week + 1 day per level","aoe":"2” cube per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Sequester\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm-Abjuration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: 1 week + 1 day per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 2” cube per caster level\nThis spell prevents detection and location spells from detecting or locating the affected objects, and also makes them invisible to any form of sight or seeing. It can hide a secret door, treasure vault, or similar subject. It does not prevent tactile discovery or discovery by devices such as a robe of eyes or gem of seeing. If cast on an unwilling creature able to resist, the target receives a normal saving throw versus spell. Living creatures and undead affected by sequester become comatose and remain in suspended animation until the spell ends or is dispelled. Material Components: Basilisk eyelash, gum arabic, and a dram of whitewash.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Sequester","class":"Magic-User"},"teleport without error":{"name":"Teleport Without Error","level":"7","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Teleport Without Error\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is similar to teleport, but the caster can transport themselves and the weight allowed by teleport to any known location on their home plane with no chance of error. The spell can also transport the caster to other planes, but such destinations are at best treated as “studied carefully.” This assumes the caster has actually been to the plane and carefully examined the destination area. The normal teleport table is used for other-planar travel, using the caster’s knowledge of the destination plane to determine error. The caster can do nothing else in the round they appear from the teleport.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user teleport without error":{"name":"Teleport Without Error","level":"7","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Instantaneous","aoe":"Special","components":"V","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Teleport Without Error\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Instantaneous\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is similar to teleport, but the caster can transport themselves and the weight allowed by teleport to any known location on their home plane with no chance of error. The spell can also transport the caster to other planes, but such destinations are at best treated as “studied carefully.” This assumes the caster has actually been to the plane and carefully examined the destination area. The normal teleport table is used for other-planar travel, using the caster’s knowledge of the destination plane to determine error. The caster can do nothing else in the round they appear from the teleport.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Teleport Without Error","class":"Magic-User"},"torment":{"name":"Torment","level":"7","school":"Evocation/Alteration","range":"1”","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Torment\n\nSchool: Evocation/Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell forces submission and obedience from a captive creature from another plane from whom service is demanded. The creature must be bound in a magic circle, thaumaturgic triangle, or pentagram. If the intended victim has magic resistance, that resistance must fail for torment to affect it. The initial utterance creates a link between caster and captive. The magic-user then continues reading the specially prepared text, and each round worsens the captive’s condition. The first two rounds cause twinges, the third and fourth cause shooting pains, and the fifth and sixth cause aches and cramps. A creature refusing service receives a saving throw versus spell each round, adjusted by the growing intensity: -1 in round 1, -2 in round 2, -3 in round 3, -4 in round 4, -6 in round 5, and -8 in round 6. Failure means the creature agrees to the demand. After round 8, there is no further penalty. If the creature breaks free, the spell still weakens it. It suffers -1 initiative per 2 rounds the spell was active, to a maximum of -4 on round 8. It also suffers -1 to hit and -1 per die of damage after 3 rounds; this penalty increases by -1 per round to -4 in round 6, then decreases back to -1 by round 9. Intelligent creatures with low moral standards are likely to submit once they understand the spell. The forced service is carried out to the letter, but the creature will almost certainly seek revenge. Preparation requires either the secret name of the creature type or the creature’s given name inscribed in the incantation, and the caster must identify themselves. For every point of the creature’s Intelligence above the caster’s, there is a 1% chance the captive gains control, draws the caster into its prison, and carries the caster to its own plane. If the caster is interrupted or distracted during the reading, there is a 5% chance per point of the captive creature’s Intelligence that it gains control. Material Component: A specially prepared scroll written with inks costing at least 1,000 gp per Hit Die of the creature affected.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user torment":{"name":"Torment","level":"7","school":"Evocation/Alteration","range":"1”","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 round","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Torment\n\nSchool: Evocation/Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 round\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell forces submission and obedience from a captive creature from another plane from whom service is demanded. The creature must be bound in a magic circle, thaumaturgic triangle, or pentagram. If the intended victim has magic resistance, that resistance must fail for torment to affect it. The initial utterance creates a link between caster and captive. The magic-user then continues reading the specially prepared text, and each round worsens the captive’s condition. The first two rounds cause twinges, the third and fourth cause shooting pains, and the fifth and sixth cause aches and cramps. A creature refusing service receives a saving throw versus spell each round, adjusted by the growing intensity: -1 in round 1, -2 in round 2, -3 in round 3, -4 in round 4, -6 in round 5, and -8 in round 6. Failure means the creature agrees to the demand. After round 8, there is no further penalty. If the creature breaks free, the spell still weakens it. It suffers -1 initiative per 2 rounds the spell was active, to a maximum of -4 on round 8. It also suffers -1 to hit and -1 per die of damage after 3 rounds; this penalty increases by -1 per round to -4 in round 6, then decreases back to -1 by round 9. Intelligent creatures with low moral standards are likely to submit once they understand the spell. The forced service is carried out to the letter, but the creature will almost certainly seek revenge. Preparation requires either the secret name of the creature type or the creature’s given name inscribed in the incantation, and the caster must identify themselves. For every point of the creature’s Intelligence above the caster’s, there is a 1% chance the captive gains control, draws the caster into its prison, and carries the caster to its own plane. If the caster is interrupted or distracted during the reading, there is a 5% chance per point of the captive creature’s Intelligence that it gains control. Material Component: A specially prepared scroll written with inks costing at least 1,000 gp per Hit Die of the creature affected.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Torment","class":"Magic-User"},"truename":{"name":"Truename","level":"7","school":"Enchantment/Alteration","range":"3”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Thing named","components":"V, S","ct":"Special","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Truename\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Thing named\nThis spell gives the magic-user great power over any living thing whose true name, generic or individual, is known. Common names are not usually true names, and true names are discovered only through hard work, spying, extensive use of legend lore, and difficult sagecraft. Casting requires the magic-user to call out the subject’s true name and recite verse describing the subject’s nature or history. This requires 3 segments. The caster then continues in verse, preferably rhyming or near-rhyming, describing the desired result. Possible effects include: Multiple Suggestion: The verses contain 1 to 4 suggestion effects, each requiring 1 segment to recite. Including the initial reading, 4 suggestions require 7 segments. Weakness and Surrender: Each segment of recitation causes the subject to lose 1 Strength point, imposing -1 to hit, -1 damage, and -1 movement rate. With each point lost, the subject must save versus paralysis or meekly surrender. Strength returns 2d4 rounds after recitation stops, and the subject regains the will to resist as Strength returns. Polymorph: The verses transform the subject as if by polymorph any object, with no system shock roll. Time required depends on how radical the change is: mineral to mineral, 2 verses; vegetable to vegetable, 3; animal to animal, 4; other to human, 5; monster to monster, 6; monster to normal, 7; vegetable to animal, 8; mineral to vegetable, 9; mineral to animal, 10. Reverse cases also apply, and unstated cases use the closest listed case. The subject returns to natural form after 6 turns per caster level, minus 1 turn per verse required. The subject thinks and behaves as a normal creature or object of the new type, but retains original hit points. Transport: The verses transport the subject by teleport without error or similar movement. Required verses depend on distance: same plane within 100 miles, 4 verses; same plane within 500 miles, 5; same plane within 2,000 miles, 6; one plane or world removed, 7; two planes or worlds removed, 8. The subject is automatically altered to physically survive normal conditions at the destination. Willing subjects receive no saving throw, even if they have magic resistance. If the caster is interrupted during recitation, the spell fails and is lost.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user truename":{"name":"Truename","level":"7","school":"Enchantment/Alteration","range":"3”","duration":"Special","aoe":"Thing named","components":"V, S","ct":"Special","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Truename\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Alteration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Thing named\nThis spell gives the magic-user great power over any living thing whose true name, generic or individual, is known. Common names are not usually true names, and true names are discovered only through hard work, spying, extensive use of legend lore, and difficult sagecraft. Casting requires the magic-user to call out the subject’s true name and recite verse describing the subject’s nature or history. This requires 3 segments. The caster then continues in verse, preferably rhyming or near-rhyming, describing the desired result. Possible effects include: Multiple Suggestion: The verses contain 1 to 4 suggestion effects, each requiring 1 segment to recite. Including the initial reading, 4 suggestions require 7 segments. Weakness and Surrender: Each segment of recitation causes the subject to lose 1 Strength point, imposing -1 to hit, -1 damage, and -1 movement rate. With each point lost, the subject must save versus paralysis or meekly surrender. Strength returns 2d4 rounds after recitation stops, and the subject regains the will to resist as Strength returns. Polymorph: The verses transform the subject as if by polymorph any object, with no system shock roll. Time required depends on how radical the change is: mineral to mineral, 2 verses; vegetable to vegetable, 3; animal to animal, 4; other to human, 5; monster to monster, 6; monster to normal, 7; vegetable to animal, 8; mineral to vegetable, 9; mineral to animal, 10. Reverse cases also apply, and unstated cases use the closest listed case. The subject returns to natural form after 6 turns per caster level, minus 1 turn per verse required. The subject thinks and behaves as a normal creature or object of the new type, but retains original hit points. Transport: The verses transport the subject by teleport without error or similar movement. Required verses depend on distance: same plane within 100 miles, 4 verses; same plane within 500 miles, 5; same plane within 2,000 miles, 6; one plane or world removed, 7; two planes or worlds removed, 8. The subject is automatically altered to physically survive normal conditions at the destination. Willing subjects receive no saving throw, even if they have magic resistance. If the caster is interrupted during recitation, the spell fails and is lost.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Truename","class":"Magic-User"},"volley":{"name":"Volley","level":"7","school":"Abjuration","range":"Special","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Volley\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis dangerous spell allows the intended recipient of a spell to turn it back on the original caster. The spell’s range, duration, area of effect, and saving throw depend on the spell being volleyed. For example, if power word kill is cast at a magic-user protected by volley, the spell rebounds toward the original caster. If the original caster fails a saving throw versus spell, power word kill affects them instead. If the original caster saves, the spell returns to the protected magic-user, who must then save or be affected. If the protected magic-user saves, the spell returns again. This continues until one side fails a save or the spell loses power. The whole spell is volleyed; for example, a lightning bolt beginning 10 feet before the volleying magic-user is returned in full, leaving others in the volleying caster’s party unharmed. Each exchange takes 1 second. A spell loses power after exchanges equal to its spell level, counting each volley, not the original casting, as half an exchange. Thus, a 1st-level spell may be cast, volleyed once, possibly return-volleyed, and then dissipates; a 2nd-level spell can undergo four volley portions, or two full exchanges, before exhaustion. Material Component: A bit of bent willow or other flexible wood, crisscrossed with specially prepared gut strands.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 8th Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user volley":{"name":"Volley","level":"7","school":"Abjuration","range":"Special","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Volley\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis dangerous spell allows the intended recipient of a spell to turn it back on the original caster. The spell’s range, duration, area of effect, and saving throw depend on the spell being volleyed. For example, if power word kill is cast at a magic-user protected by volley, the spell rebounds toward the original caster. If the original caster fails a saving throw versus spell, power word kill affects them instead.