ubject’s Hit Dice. Otherwise, the subject receives a saving throw versus spell, modified by the form of binding and by the ratio of caster level to subject Hit Dice. The principal caster’s level is increased by one-third the level of each assisting magic-user of 9th level or higher, and by 1 level for each assistant of 4th to 8th level. No more than six magic-users may assist. Binding forms include: Chaining: The subject is confined by restraints that generate antipathy against all creatures except the caster. Duration is up to 1 year per caster level. The subject remains within the restraining diagram. Slumber: The subject falls into comatose sleep for up to 1 year per caster level. Bound Slumber: Combines chaining and slumber for up to 1 month per caster level. Hedged Prison: The subject is transported or otherwise brought into a confined area it cannot leave until freed. The spell lasts until the magical hedge is broken. Metamorphosis: The subject becomes noncorporeal except for its head or face. The binding is permanent until a prescribed act frees it. Minimus Containment: The subject is shrunk to 1 inch or smaller and held within a gem or similar hedged prison. Minimus containment, metamorphosis, and hedged prison radiate a very faint aura of magic. If applicable, the saving throw is normal for chaining, +1 for slumber, +2 for bound slumber, +3 for hedged prison, +4 for metamorphosis, and +5 for minimus containment. If the subject was first weakened by dolor or torment, the save is adjusted by -1 for dolor, -2 for torment, or -4 for both in succession. A successful save lets the subject burst its bonds. Chaining, slumber, and bound slumber can be renewed. After one year, the subject receives a normal saving throw versus spell; success breaks the binding. If the binding was weakened by contact, magical touching, or similar interference, a normal saving throw applies to renewal.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user binding":{"name":"Binding","l