8","school":"Evocation/Enchantment-Charm","range":"Special","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"1 turn","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Demand\n\nSchool: Evocation/Enchantment-Charm\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell is essentially the same as sending, except the message may include a suggestion. If the subject fails a saving throw versus spell, it does its best to carry out the suggestion in the demand. If the message is impossible or incongruous given the subject’s circumstances, the message is understood but no saving throw is required, and the suggestion is ineffective. Material Components: A pair of cylinders, each open at one end and connected by a thin copper wire, plus a small part of the subject creature, such as a hair or nail clipping.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Demand","class":"Magic-User"},"otiluke s telekinetic sphere":{"name":"Otiluke’s Telekinetic Sphere","level":"8","school":"Evocation/Alteration","range":"2”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"1-foot diameter sphere per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Otiluke’s Telekinetic Sphere\n\nSchool: Evocation/Alteration\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 1-foot diameter sphere per caster level\nThis spell is the same as Otiluke’s resilient sphere, with the additional effect that the interior is virtually weightless. Anything inside weighs only one-sixteenth its normal weight. The caster can telekinetically lift any subject up to 5,000 pounds in the sphere. Range of control extends to 1” per caster level after the sphere encapsulates a subject. Even if more than 5,000 pounds is enclosed, the effective weight is only one-sixteenth normal, so the sphere can be rolled without exceptional effort. The reduced weight makes rapid motion or falling inside the sphere relatively harmless, though danger returns if the sphere vanishes while the subject is high above a hard surface. Material Components: The components for Otiluke’s resilient sphere, plus a pair of small bar magnets.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user otiluke s telekinetic sphere":{"name":"Otiluke’s Telekinetic Sphere","level":"8","school":"Evocation/Alteration","range":"2”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"1-foot diameter sphere per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Otiluke’s Telekinetic Sphere\n\nSchool: Evocation/Alteration\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 1-foot diameter sphere per caster level\nThis spell is the same as Otiluke’s resilient sphere, with the additional effect that the interior is virtually weightless. Anything inside weighs only one-sixteenth its normal weight. The caster can telekinetically lift any subject up to 5,000 pounds in the sphere. Range of control extends to 1” per caster level after the sphere encapsulates a subject. Even if more than 5,000 pounds is enclosed, the effective weight is only one-sixteenth normal, so the sphere can be rolled without exceptional effort. The reduced weight makes rapid motion or falling inside the sphere relatively harmless, though danger returns if the sphere vanishes while the subject is high above a hard surface. Material Components: The components for Otiluke’s resilient sphere, plus a pair of small bar magnets.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Otiluke’s Telekinetic Sphere","class":"Magic-User"},"sink":{"name":"Sink","level":"8","school":"Enchantment/Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature or one object of 1 cubic “ per caster level","components":"V, S","ct":"8 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Sink\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Alteration\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature or one object of 1 cubic “ per caster level\nThe caster chants for 4 uninterrupted segments. At that point, the subject becomes rooted to the spot unless a creature succeeds on a saving throw versus spell, or a magical object succeeds on a saving throw versus disintegration. Nonmagical objects receive no saving throw. The subject also becomes the same density as the surface beneath it if the save fails. The caster may stop at this point, leaving the subject rooted and density-altered for 4 turns before it returns to normal. If the caster continues, the subject begins slowly sinking into the ground. On the 5th segment, it sinks one-quarter of its height; on the 6th, another quarter; on the 7th, another; and on the 8th, it is completely submerged. This entombment places a living subject in stasis-like suspended animation without otherwise harming it. Living or nonliving, the subject remains undamaged within the surface into which it sank, with its uppermost extremity as far beneath the surface as the subject’s height. If surrounding ground is removed, the spell breaks and the subject returns to normal but does not rise. Spells such as dig, transmute rock to mud, and freedom can help recover the subject without harming it. Detect magic cast over the area reveals a faint, undefined dweomer even if the subject is beyond detection range. If the subject is within range, the magic is identified as enchantment-alteration.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 9th Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user sink":{"name":"Sink","level":"8","school":"Enchantment/Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature or one object of 1 cubic “ per caster level","components":"V, S","ct":"8 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Sink\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Alteration\nLevel: 8\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 8 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature or one object of 1 cubic “ per caster level\nThe caster chants for 4 uninterrupted segments. At that point, the subject becomes rooted to the spot unless a creature succeeds on a saving throw versus spell, or a magical object succeeds on a saving throw versus disintegration. Nonmagical objects receive no saving throw. The subject also becomes the same density as the surface beneath it if the save fails. The caster may stop at this point, leaving the subject rooted and density-altered for 4 turns before it returns to normal. If the caster continues, the subject begins slowly sinking into the ground. On the 5th segment, it sinks one-quarter of its height; on the 6th, another quarter; on the 7th, another; and on the 8th, it is completely submerged. This entombment places a living subject in stasis-like suspended animation without otherwise harming it. Living or nonliving, the subject remains undamaged within the surface into which it sank, with its uppermost extremity as far beneath the surface as the subject’s height. If surrounding ground is removed, the spell breaks and the subject returns to normal but does not rise. Spells such as dig, transmute rock to mud, and freedom can help recover the subject without harming it. Detect magic cast over the area reveals a faint, undefined dweomer even if the subject is beyond detection range. If the subject is within range, the magic is identified as enchantment-alteration.\n\nMagic-User Spells, 9th Level","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Sink","class":"Magic-User"},"crystalbrittle":{"name":"Crystalbrittle","level":"9","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"2 cubic feet per caster level","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Crystalbrittle\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 2 cubic feet per caster level\nThis spell turns metal into a crystalline substance as brittle and fragile as crystal, whether the metal is soft gold or hard adamantite. A sword, metal shield, armor, or even an iron golem can become delicate, glass-like material easily shattered by any forceful blow. This change is reversible only by wish; dispel magic does not work. The caster must physically touch the target item, requiring a hit in combat if worn, wielded, or a monster. One single metal item can be affected. For example, armor worn by a subject can be changed, but not both armor and shield. Items gain a saving throw based on their magical bonus or protection. A +1/+3 sword has a 10% chance to save; +5 armor has a 25% chance; an iron golem has a 15% chance because it is hit only by +3 or better magic weapons. Metal artifacts and relics have a 95% chance to be unaffected. Affected items not immediately protected are shattered and permanently destroyed if struck by a normal blow from a metal tool or weighty weapon, including a staff.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user crystalbrittle":{"name":"Crystalbrittle","level":"9","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"2 cubic feet per caster level","components":"V, S","ct":"9 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Crystalbrittle\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 2 cubic feet per caster level\nThis spell turns metal into a crystalline substance as brittle and fragile as crystal, whether the metal is soft gold or hard adamantite. A sword, metal shield, armor, or even an iron golem can become delicate, glass-like material easily shattered by any forceful blow. This change is reversible only by wish; dispel magic does not work. The caster must physically touch the target item, requiring a hit in combat if worn, wielded, or a monster. One single metal item can be affected. For example, armor worn by a subject can be changed, but not both armor and shield. Items gain a saving throw based on their magical bonus or protection. A +1/+3 sword has a 10% chance to save; +5 armor has a 25% chance; an iron golem has a 15% chance because it is hit only by +3 or better magic weapons. Metal artifacts and relics have a 95% chance to be unaffected. Affected items not immediately protected are shattered and permanently destroyed if struck by a normal blow from a metal tool or weighty weapon, including a staff.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Crystalbrittle","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user energy drain":{"name":"Energy Drain","level":"9","school":"Evocation","range":"Touch","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Energy Drain\n\nSchool: Evocation\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell opens a channel between the caster’s plane and the Negative Material Plane, with the caster acting as conductor. When the caster touches a living creature, requiring a hit in melee if applicable, the victim loses two energy levels as if struck by a spectre. A monster permanently loses two Hit Dice, affecting hit points and attack ability. A character permanently loses levels, Hit Dice, hit points, and abilities until regained through adventuring, if applicable. The caster prepares for 3 segments, casts forth the material component, then speaks the triggering word upon touching the victim. There is always a 5% chance the caster is also affected, losing one energy level while the victim loses two. Humans or humanoids reduced to zero energy level by this spell become juju zombies. Material Component: Essence of spectre or vampire dust.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Energy Drain","class":"Magic-User"},"mordenkainen s disjunction":{"name":"Mordenkainen’s Disjunction","level":"9","school":"Alteration/Enchantment","range":"0","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"3” radius","components":"V","ct":"9 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Mordenkainen’s Disjunction\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enchantment\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 3” radius\nThis spell disjoins all magic and magic items within the radius, except those on the caster’s person or being touched by the caster. Spells being cast are separated into their components, usually spoiling the effect as dispel magic would. Permanent and magical items must save, either versus spell if cast on a creature or versus dispel magic otherwise, or become normal items. Artifacts and relics are also subject to the spell, though there is only a 1% chance per caster level of affecting such powerful items. Thus, potions, scrolls, rings, rods, miscellaneous magic items, artifacts, relics, arms, armor, swords, and other magic weapons within 3” of the caster may lose all magical properties. Destroying artifacts is dangerous and is 95% likely to attract the attention of a powerful being connected to the item. If an artifact is destroyed, the caster must save versus spell at -4 or permanently lose all spellcasting abilities.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user mordenkainen s disjunction":{"name":"Mordenkainen’s Disjunction","level":"9","school":"Alteration/Enchantment","range":"0","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"3” radius","components":"V","ct":"9 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Mordenkainen’s Disjunction\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enchantment\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 9 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 3” radius\nThis spell disjoins all magic and magic items within the radius, except those on the caster’s person or being touched by the caster. Spells being cast are separated into their components, usually spoiling the effect as dispel magic would. Permanent and magical items must save, either versus spell if cast on a creature or versus dispel magic otherwise, or become normal items. Artifacts and relics are also subject to the spell, though there is only a 1% chance per caster level of affecting such powerful items. Thus, potions, scrolls, rings, rods, miscellaneous magic items, artifacts, relics, arms, armor, swords, and other magic weapons within 3” of the caster may lose all magical properties. Destroying artifacts is dangerous and is 95% likely to attract the attention of a powerful being connected to the item. If an artifact is destroyed, the caster must save versus spell at -4 or permanently lose all spellcasting abilities.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Mordenkainen’s Disjunction","class":"Magic-User"},"magic user succor":{"name":"Succor","level":"9","school":"Alteration/Enchantment","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"One individual","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1–4 days","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Succor\n\nSchool: Alteration/Enchantment\nLevel: 9\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1–4 days\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One individual\nThis spell is essentially the same as the 7th-level cleric spell succor. A magic-user’s succor teleports without error the individual who breaks the enchanted object and speaks the command word. If the reverse is used, the archmage is brought to the individual’s presence. Unlike the cleric version, the summoned archmage has no choice but to answer the summons, making this version rare. Intervening planes have a cumulative 1% chance each of causing irrevocable loss of the individual or spellcaster involved in the succor. Material Component: Gem material worth at least 5,000 gp. It may be faceted or unfaceted. Components can be enchanted only once per month, usually on the night of a clear full moon. At that time, the object is set for the type of succor and final destination, either the casting location or an area well known to the mage.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Magic-User: Succor","class":"Magic-User"},"illusionist audible glamer":{"name":"Audible Glamer","level":"1","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"6” + 1” per level","duration":"3 rounds per level","aoe":"Hearing range","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Audible Glamer\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 3 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Hearing range\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 2nd-level magic-user spell audible glamer.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Audible Glamer","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist change self":{"name":"Change Self","level":"1","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"2d6 rounds + 2 rounds per level","aoe":"The illusionist","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Change Self\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 2d6 rounds + 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The illusionist\nThis spell allows the illusionist to alter their appearance, including clothing and equipment. The illusionist may appear 1 foot shorter or taller, thin, fat, or in between, and may appear human, humanoid, or any generally man-shaped bipedal creature.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Change Self","class":"Illusionist"},"change self":{"name":"Change Self","level":"1","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"2d6 rounds + 2 rounds per level","aoe":"The illusionist","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Change Self\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 2d6 rounds + 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The illusionist\nThis spell allows the illusionist to alter their appearance, including clothing and equipment. The illusionist may appear 1 foot shorter or taller, thin, fat, or in between, and may appear human, humanoid, or any generally man-shaped bipedal creature.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist chromatic orb":{"name":"Chromatic Orb","level":"1","school":"Alteration/Evocation","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Chromatic Orb\n\nSchool: Alteration/Evocation\nLevel: 1\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell creates a small globe of colored magical energy in the illusionist’s hand, which may be hurled at a target within 3”. The orb has +3 to hit at 1” or less, +2 beyond 1” to 2”, and +1 beyond 2” to 3”. If it misses, it dissipates harmlessly. The orb affects even creatures normally struck only by very powerful magic weapons, though magic resistance applies. The color determines the effect, and higher-level illusionists can create stronger colors.\n\nMinimum Caster Level\tOrb Color\tDamage\tSpecial Effect\n1\tPearly\t1d4\tLight; failed save blinds for 1 round per level\n2\tRuby\t1d6\tHeat; melts ice and may reduce Strength and Dexterity by 1\n3\tFlame\t1d8\tFire; ignites combustibles and may deal +2 fire damage\n4\tAmber\t1d10\tBlindness for 5–8 rounds unless saved\n5\tEmerald\t1d12\tStinking cloud effect around target\n6\tTurquoise\t2d8\tElectrical damage; may magnetize ferrous metal\n7\tSapphire\t2d4\tParalysis for 5–20 rounds unless saved\n10\tAmethyst\tSpecia