st"},"illusionist blur":{"name":"Blur","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"3 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"The illusionist","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Blur\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 3 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The illusionist\nThe illusionist’s outline becomes blurred, shifting, and wavering. Missile and melee attacks against the caster are made at -4 on the first attempt and -2 on later attacks. The spell also grants +1 on saving throws against direct magical attacks.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Blur","class":"Illusionist"},"blur":{"name":"Blur","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"3 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"The illusionist","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Blur\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 3 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The illusionist\nThe illusionist’s outline becomes blurred, shifting, and wavering. Missile and melee attacks against the caster are made at -4 on the first attempt and -2 on later attacks. The spell also grants +1 on saving throws against direct magical attacks.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist deafness":{"name":"Deafness","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"6”","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Deafness\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell makes the target totally deaf. The effect can be removed only by dispel magic or by the caster. Material Component: Beeswax.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Deafness","class":"Illusionist"},"deafness":{"name":"Deafness","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"6”","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Deafness\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell makes the target totally deaf. The effect can be removed only by dispel magic or by the caster. Material Component: Beeswax.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist detect magic":{"name":"Detect Magic","level":"2","school":"Divination","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"1” path, 6” long","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Detect Magic\n\nSchool: Divination\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” path, 6” long\nThis spell is similar to the cleric and magic-user versions of detect magic.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Detect Magic","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist fascinate":{"name":"Fascinate","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"3”","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Fascinate\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell creates an illusion around the caster, making the illusionist appear to the target as a trusted or desired companion. Unless the target saves, it follows the caster if doing so does not create undue danger. If the caster can converse with the target, the target obeys requests as long as 3d6 does not exceed the caster’s Comeliness. Dangerous or unreasonable requests add +1 to +6 to the roll. If the roll exceeds Comeliness, the spell breaks and the subject becomes enraged. Animal-intelligence creatures remain fascinated for 1d4 days, and if treated well, may willingly befriend the caster afterward with a chance equal to 2% per point of Comeliness. Nonintelligent creatures are unaffected.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Fascinate","class":"Illusionist"},"fascinate":{"name":"Fascinate","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"3”","duration":"Special","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Fascinate\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell creates an illusion around the caster, making the illusionist appear to the target as a trusted or desired companion. Unless the target saves, it follows the caster if doing so does not create undue danger. If the caster can converse with the target, the target obeys requests as long as 3d6 does not exceed the caster’s Comeliness. Dangerous or unreasonable requests add +1 to +6 to the roll. If the roll exceeds Comeliness, the spell breaks and the subject becomes enraged. Animal-intelligence creatures remain fascinated for 1d4 days, and if treated well, may willingly befriend the caster afterward with a chance equal to 2% per point of Comeliness. Nonintelligent creatures are unaffected.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist fog cloud":{"name":"Fog Cloud","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"1”","duration":"4 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"4” wide, 2” high, 2” deep cloud","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Fog Cloud\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4” wide, 2” high, 2” deep cloud\nThis spell creates a greenish billowing cloud of mist resembling cloudkill. It moves away from the caster at 1” per round. It behaves like cloudkill in movement, but only obscures vision as wall of fog does.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Fog Cloud","class":"Illusionist"},"fog cloud":{"name":"Fog Cloud","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"1”","duration":"4 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"4” wide, 2” high, 2” deep cloud","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Fog Cloud\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4” wide, 2” high, 2” deep cloud\nThis spell creates a greenish billowing cloud of mist resembling cloudkill. It moves away from the caster at 1” per round. It behaves like cloudkill in movement, but only obscures vision as wall of fog does.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist hypnotic pattern":{"name":"Hypnotic Pattern","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"3” × 3” square","components":"S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Hypnotic Pattern\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 3” × 3” square\nThis spell creates a weaving, turning pattern of subtle colors in the air. Creatures looking at it may become fascinated and stand gazing at it for as long as the caster maintains the pattern. The spell can affect up to 24 total levels or Hit Dice of creatures, and all affected creatures must be within the area. Material Component: A glowing stick of incense or a crystal rod filled with phosphorescent material.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Hypnotic Pattern","class":"Illusionist"},"hypnotic pattern":{"name":"Hypnotic Pattern","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"3” × 3” square","components":"S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Hypnotic Pattern\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 3” × 3” square\nThis spell creates a weaving, turning pattern of subtle colors in the air. Creatures looking at it may become fascinated and stand gazing at it for as long as the caster maintains the pattern. The spell can affect up to 24 total levels or Hit Dice of creatures, and all affected creatures must be within the area. Material Component: A glowing stick of incense or a crystal rod filled with phosphorescent material.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist improved phantasmal force":{"name":"Improved Phantasmal Force","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"6” + 1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"4 square inches + 1 square inch per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Improved Phantasmal Force\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 4 square inches + 1 square inch per level\nThis spell is like phantasmal force, but the caster can maintain it with minimal concentration and move at half normal speed while doing so. The illusion includes minor sounds, though not intelligible speech. If the illusionist concentrates on the form of the phantasm, it continues for 2 rounds after concentration ends.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Improved Phantasmal Force","class":"Illusionist"},"improved phantasmal force":{"name":"Improved Phantasmal Force","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"6” + 1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"4 square inches + 1 square inch per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Improved Phantasmal Force\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 4 square inches + 1 square inch per level\nThis spell is like phantasmal force, but the caster can maintain it with minimal concentration and move at half normal speed while doing so. The illusion includes minor sounds, though not intelligible speech. If the illusionist concentrates on the form of the phantasm, it continues for 2 rounds after concentration ends.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist invisibility":{"name":"Invisibility","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Invisibility\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 2nd-level magic-user spell invisibility.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Invisibility","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist magic mouth":{"name":"Magic Mouth","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"Special","duration":"Special","aoe":"One object","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Magic Mouth\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One object\nThis spell is the same as the 2nd-level magic-user spell magic mouth.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Magic Mouth","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist mirror image":{"name":"Mirror Image","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"3 rounds per level","aoe":"6-foot radius around caster","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mirror Image\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 3 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6-foot radius around caster\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 2nd-level magic-user spell mirror image, except it creates 1d4+1 images.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Mirror Image","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist misdirection":{"name":"Misdirection","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Misdirection\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell misdirects information from detection spells, including detect charm, detect evil, detect invisibility, detect lie, detect magic, and detect snares & pits. The detection spell reveals the wrong area, wrong creature, or the opposite truth for spells such as detect evil or detect lie. The caster directs the effect on the creature or item being detected. If the detector fails a saving throw, the misdirection succeeds.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Misdirection","class":"Illusionist"},"misdirection":{"name":"Misdirection","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Misdirection\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell misdirects information from detection spells, including detect charm, detect evil, detect invisibility, detect lie, detect magic, and detect snares & pits. The detection spell reveals the wrong area, wrong creature, or the opposite truth for spells such as detect evil or detect lie. The caster directs the effect on the creature or item being detected. If the detector fails a saving throw, the misdirection succeeds.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist ultravision":{"name":"Ultravision","level":"2","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns + 1 turn per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Ultravision\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 6 turns + 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nExcept as noted above, this spell is essentially the same as the 4th-level magic-user spell ultravision. Highly intelligent creatures may be able to detect invisible creatures using natural or magically bestowed ultravision. Material Component: Powdered essence of carrots.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Ultravision","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist ventriloquism":{"name":"Ventriloquism","level":"2","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"1” per level, maximum 9”","duration":"4 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"One object","components":"V, M","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Ventriloquism\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 1” per level, maximum 9”\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: One object\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 1st-level magic-user spell ventriloquism.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Ventriloquism","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist whispering wind":{"name":"Whispering Wind","level":"2","school":"Alteration/Phantasm","range":"Special","duration":"Special","aoe":"2-foot radius","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Whispering Wind\n\nSchool: Alteration/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2-foot radius\nThis spell sends a message or sound effect on a gentle magical breeze. It can travel tens of feet underground or miles above ground equal to the caster’s level. A 3rd-level illusionist can send it 30 feet underground or 3 miles outdoors. On arrival, it delivers a whisper-quiet message or sound for up to 2 segments, then vanishes. It also vanishes if the target is beyond range, more than 2 hours pass, or it is dispelled. The message may contain up to 12 words, or the spell may deliver 12 seconds of other sound. The wind may travel from 1” to 20” per round. No spells may be cast through it.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Whispering Wind","class":"Illusionist"},"whispering wind":{"name":"Whispering Wind","level":"2","school":"Alteration/Phantasm","range":"Special","duration":"Special","aoe":"2-foot radius","components":"V, S","ct":"2 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Whispering Wind\n\nSchool: Alteration/Phantasm\nLevel: 2\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 2 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2-foot radius\nThis spell sends a message or sound effect on a gentle magical breeze. It can travel tens of feet underground or miles above ground equal to the caster’s level. A 3rd-level illusionist can send it 30 feet underground or 3 miles outdoors. On arrival, it delivers a whisper-quiet message or sound for up to 2 segments, then vanishes. It also vanishes if the target is beyond range, more than 2 hours pass, or it is dispelled. The message may contain up to 12 words, or the spell may deliver 12 seconds of other sound. The wind may travel from 1” to 20” per round. No spells may be cast through it.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist delude":{"name":"Delude","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"The illusionist","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Delude\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: The illusionist\nThis spell allows the illusionist to replace the aura of their own alignment with that of another creature within a 3” radius. The creature copied must be of higher than animal intelligence. The target creature retains its actual alignment. Any attempt to know alignment detects only the aura the illusionist has chosen to assume. Detect good or detect evil detects only the substituted creature’s aura. The creature whose aura is copied radiates magic, but the illusionist radiates magic only to the creature whose aura has been exchanged. If delude is used with change self or alter self, the illusionist’s actual class is completely hidden, and the illusionist appears to be whatever class they have chosen. The saving throw applies only to the aura transfer.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Delude","class":"Illusionist"},"delude":{"name":"Delude","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"The illusionist","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Delude\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: The illusionist\nThis spell allows the illusionist to replace the aura of their own alignment with that of another creature within a 3” radius. The creature copied must be of higher than animal intelligence. The target creature retains its actual alignment. Any attempt to know alignment detects only the aura the illusionist has chosen to assume. Detect good or detect evil detects only the substituted creature’s aura. The creature whose aura is copied radiates magic, but the illusionist radiates magic only to the creature whose aura has been exchanged. If delude is used with change self or alter self, the illusionist’s actual class is completely hidden, and the illusionist appears to be whatever class they have chosen. The saving throw applies only to the aura transfer.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist phantom steed":{"name":"Phantom Steed","level":"3","school":"Conjuration/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Phantom Steed\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a quasi-real, horse-like creature. The mount can be ridden only by the illusionist who created it, or by a person for whom the illusionist specifically creates the mount. All phantom steeds have black heads and bodies, gray manes and tails, smoke-colored insubstantial hooves that make no sound, and milky-colored eyes. They do not fight, but normal animals shun them, so only monstrous creatures will attack them. If a phantom steed takes more than 12 points of damage, the dweomer is dispelled and the mount vanishes. A phantom steed moves at a maximum rate of 4” per caster level. It appears to have saddle, bit, and bridle, but it cannot carry saddlebags or similar gear, only its rider and what the rider carries. At 8th level, it can pass over sandy, muddy, or swampy ground without difficulty. At 10th level, it can pass over water as if it were firm, dry ground. At 12th level, it can travel through the air as if on firm land, allowing it to cross chasms and similar gaps, though it cannot casually take off and fly. At 14th level, it can perform as if it were a pegasus.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Phantom Steed","class":"Illusionist"},"phantom steed":{"name":"Phantom Steed","level":"3","school":"Conjuration/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Phantom Steed\n\nSchool: Conjuration/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a quasi-real, horse-like creature. The mount can be ridden only by the illusionist who created it, or by a person for whom the illusionist specifically creates the mount. All phantom steeds have black heads and bodies, gray manes and tails, smoke-colored insubstantial hooves that make no sound, and milky-colored eyes. They do not fight, but normal animals shun them, so only monstrous creatures will attack them. If a phantom steed takes more than 12 points of damage, the dweomer is dispelled and the mount vanishes. A phantom steed moves at a maximum rate of 4” per caster level. It appears to have saddle, bit, and bridle, but it cannot carry saddlebags or similar gear, only its rider and what the rider carries. At 8th level, it can pass over sandy, muddy, or swampy ground without difficulty. At 10th level, it can pass over water as if it were firm, dry ground. At 12th level, it can travel through the air as if on firm land, allowing it to cross chasms and similar gaps, though it cannot casually take off and fly. At 14th level, it can perform as if it were a pegasus.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist phantom wind":{"name":"Phantom Wind","level":"3","school":"Alteration/Phantasm","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"1” broad path","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Phantom Wind\n\nSchool: Alteration/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” broad path\nThis spell creates a wind that cannot be seen or felt. The movement of air can blow light objects, flutter curtains and drapes, flap loose clothing such as capes and cloaks, fan fires, and move clouds of gaseous material such as wall of fog, fog cloud, or cloudkill. The wind moves in the direction the illusionist points. Its effects are felt in a progressively longer path as the spell continues, moving at 1” per round, and lasting along the entire course of the path. For example, the spell could move several sailed vessels, but the first affected by the wind would move the farthest.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Phantom Wind","class":"Illusionist"},"phantom wind":{"name":"Phantom Wind","level":"3","school":"Alteration/Phantasm","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"1” broad path","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Phantom Wind\n\nSchool: Alteration/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” broad path\nThis spell creates a wind that cannot be seen or felt. The movement of air can blow light objects, flutter curtains and drapes, flap loose clothing such as capes and cloaks, fan fires, and move clouds of gaseous material such as wall of fog, fog cloud, or cloudkill. The wind moves in the direction the illusionist points. Its effects are felt in a progressively longer path as the spell continues, moving at 1” per round, and lasting along the entire course of the path. For example, the spell could move several sailed vessels, but the first affected by the wind would move the farthest.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist wraithform":{"name":"Wraithform","level":"3","school":"Alteration/Illusion","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"The illusionist","components":"S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wraithform\n\nSchool: Alteration/Illusion\nLevel: 3\nComponents: S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The illusionist\nThis spell makes the illusionist and all their gear insubstantial. The caster can be hit only by +1 or better magic weapons, or by creatures otherwise able to affect beings struck only by magic weapons. Most undead ignore someone in wraithform, believing the caster to be a wraith or spectre, though a lich or special undead may save versus spell at -4 to recognize the dweomer. The illusionist can pass through small holes, narrow openings, and even cracks, along with anything worn or held, while the spell lasts. No attack is possible in wraithform, except against creatures on the Ethereal Plane, where attacks in both directions are normal. Dispel illusion and dispel magic are the only ways to force the illusionist back to normal form. The caster may return to normal form at will, but doing so ends the spell. Material Components: A bit of gauze and a wisp of smoke.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Wraithform","class":"Illusionist"},"wraithform":{"name":"Wraithform","level":"3","school":"Alteration/Illusion","range":"0","duration":"2 rounds per level","aoe":"The illusionist","components":"S, M","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Wraithform\n\nSchool: Alteration/Illusion\nLevel: 3\nComponents: S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 2 rounds per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: The illusionist\nThis spell makes the illusionist and all their gear insubstantial. The caster can be hit only by +1 or better magic weapons, or by creatures otherwise able to affect beings struck only by magic weapons. Most undead ignore someone in wraithform, believing the caster to be a wraith or spectre, though a lich or special undead may save versus spell at -4 to recognize the dweomer. The illusionist can pass through small holes, narrow openings, and even cracks, along with anything worn or held, while the spell lasts. No attack is possible in wraithform, except against creatures on the Ethereal Plane, where attacks in both directions are normal. Dispel illusion and dispel magic are the only ways to force the illusionist back to normal form. The caster may return to normal form at will, but doing so ends the spell. Material Components: A bit of gauze and a wisp of smoke.\n\nIllusionist Spells, 4th Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist dispel magic":{"name":"Dispel Magic","level":"4","school":"Abjuration","range":"9”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"3” cube","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Dispel Magic\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 9”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” cube\nThis spell is essentially identical to the 3rd-level clerical spell dispel magic. An illusionist casts it as if two levels lower than actual level. For example, a 9th-level illusionist casts dispel magic as a 7th-level caster.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Dispel Magic","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist rainbow pattern":{"name":"Rainbow Pattern","level":"4","school":"Alteration/Phantasm","range":"1”","duration":"Special","aoe":"3” × 3” square area","components":"S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Rainbow Pattern\n\nSchool: Alteration/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 3” × 3” square area\nThis spell creates a pastel, glowing, rainbow-hued band of interplaying patterns. Its effect is the same as hypnotic pattern. However, once cast, the illusionist need only gesture in the desired direction, and the pattern slowly moves that way at 3” per round. It persists without further attention for 1d3 rounds, and all creatures affected by the dweomer, up to 24 total levels or Hit Dice, follow the moving rainbow of light. If the pattern leads its targets into a dangerous area, such as through flame or off a cliff, they receive a second saving throw. If the lights are completely blocked from view, such as by obscurement, the spell is negated. Material Components: A crystal prism and a piece of phosphor.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Rainbow Pattern","class":"Illusionist"},"rainbow pattern":{"name":"Rainbow Pattern","level":"4","school":"Alteration/Phantasm","range":"1”","duration":"Special","aoe":"3” × 3” square area","components":"S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Rainbow Pattern\n\nSchool: Alteration/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: S, M\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 3” × 3” square area\nThis spell creates a pastel, glowing, rainbow-hued band of interplaying patterns. Its effect is the same as hypnotic pattern. However, once cast, the illusionist need only gesture in the desired direction, and the pattern slowly moves that way at 3” per round. It persists without further attention for 1d3 rounds, and all creatures affected by the dweomer, up to 24 total levels or Hit Dice, follow the moving rainbow of light. If the pattern leads its targets into a dangerous area, such as through flame or off a cliff, they receive a second saving throw. If the lights are completely blocked from view, such as by obscurement, the spell is negated. Material Components: A crystal prism and a piece of phosphor.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist solid fog":{"name":"Solid Fog","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"3”","duration":"2d4 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"2 cubic “ per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Solid Fog\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 2d4 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2 cubic “ per caster level\nThis spell creates an area of fog similar to wall of fog. These rolling, billowing vapors behave like wall of fog in most respects, but only a very strong wind can move them. Any creature attempting to move through the solid fog progresses at a rate of only 1 foot per 1” of normal movement rate per round. Gust of wind cannot affect it. Fireball, flame strike, or wall of fire burns it away in a single round. Material Components: A pinch of dried, powdered peas combined with powdered animal hoof.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Solid Fog","class":"Illusionist"},"solid fog":{"name":"Solid Fog","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"3”","duration":"2d4 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"2 cubic “ per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Solid Fog\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 2d4 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2 cubic “ per caster level\nThis spell creates an area of fog similar to wall of fog. These rolling, billowing vapors behave like wall of fog in most respects, but only a very strong wind can move them. Any creature attempting to move through the solid fog progresses at a rate of only 1 foot per 1” of normal movement rate per round. Gust of wind cannot affect it. Fireball, flame strike, or wall of fire burns it away in a single round. Material Components: A pinch of dried, powdered peas combined with powdered animal hoof.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist vacancy":{"name":"Vacancy","level":"4","school":"Alteration/Phantasm","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"1” radius per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Vacancy\n\nSchool: Alteration/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” radius per caster level\nThis spell causes an area to appear vacant, neglected, and unused. Observers see dust, cobwebs, dirt, or other signs typical of a long-abandoned place. If they pass through the area, they seem to leave tracks, tear away cobwebs, and otherwise interact with the false appearance. Unless they actually contact an object cloaked by the spell, the place seems empty of what it actually contains. Merely brushing an invisible object does not disturb the spell; only forceful contact gives any chance to notice something is wrong. The spell is a powerful combination of advanced invisibility and illusion, but it can cloak only nonliving things. Living creatures are not made invisible, though their presence does not otherwise disturb the spell. If forceful contact with a cloaked object occurs, affected creatures can penetrate the spell only if they discover several objects they cannot see; each such creature then receives a saving throw versus spell. Failure means the creature believes only those objects are invisible. Dispel illusion or dispel magic removes the dweomer. True seeing, a gem of seeing, and similar effects penetrate the deception, but detect invisibility does not. Material Component: A square of finest black silk worth at least 100 gp.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Vacancy","class":"Illusionist"},"vacancy":{"name":"Vacancy","level":"4","school":"Alteration/Phantasm","range":"1” per level","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"1” radius per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Vacancy\n\nSchool: Alteration/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” radius per caster level\nThis spell causes an area to appear vacant, neglected, and unused. Observers see dust, cobwebs, dirt, or other signs typical of a long-abandoned place. If they pass through the area, they seem to leave tracks, tear away cobwebs, and otherwise interact with the false appearance. Unless they actually contact an object cloaked by the spell, the place seems empty of what it actually contains. Merely brushing an invisible object does not disturb the spell; only forceful contact gives any chance to notice something is wrong. The spell is a powerful combination of advanced invisibility and illusion, but it can cloak only nonliving things. Living creatures are not made invisible, though their presence does not otherwise disturb the spell. If forceful contact with a cloaked object occurs, affected creatures can penetrate the spell only if they discover several objects they cannot see; each such creature then receives a saving throw versus spell. Failure means the creature believes only those objects are invisible. Dispel illusion or dispel magic removes the dweomer. True seeing, a gem of seeing, and similar effects penetrate the deception, but detect invisibility does not. Material Component: A square of finest black silk worth at least 100 gp.\n\nIllusionist Spells, 5th Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist advanced illusion":{"name":"Advanced Illusion","level":"5","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"6” + 1” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"4 square “ + 1 square “ per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Advanced Illusion\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 4 square “ + 1 square “ per level\nThis spell is essentially a spectral forces spell operating through a program determined by the caster, similar to programmed illusion. The illusionist need not concentrate on the spell for more than 5 segments after casting, because the program has begun and continues on its own. The illusion has visual, full auditory, olfactory, and thermal components. If a viewer actively attempts to disbelieve the dweomer, they receive a saving throw versus spell. If a viewer successfully disbelieves and communicates that fact to others who can understand the communication, each such viewer gains a saving throw versus spell with a +4 bonus. Material Components: A bit of fleece and several grains of sand.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Advanced Illusion","class":"Illusionist"},"advanced illusion":{"name":"Advanced Illusion","level":"5","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"6” + 1” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"4 square “ + 1 square “ per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Advanced Illusion\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 4 square “ + 1 square “ per level\nThis spell is essentially a spectral forces spell operating through a program determined by the caster, similar to programmed illusion. The illusionist need not concentrate on the spell for more than 5 segments after casting, because the program has begun and continues on its own. The illusion has visual, full auditory, olfactory, and thermal components. If a viewer actively attempts to disbelieve the dweomer, they receive a saving throw versus spell. If a viewer successfully disbelieves and communicates that fact to others who can understand the communication, each such viewer gains a saving throw versus spell with a +4 bonus. Material Components: A bit of fleece and several grains of sand.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist dream":{"name":"Dream","level":"5","school":"Alteration-Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Special","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"Special","ct":"1 day","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Dream\n\nSchool: Alteration-Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: Special\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 1 day\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is a form of limited wish, but with far narrower scope. The illusionist must find a comfortable place to rest, lie prone, compose their thoughts on the desired result, and then go to sleep. If the illusionist sleeps undisturbed for at least 8 hours, the dream magic takes effect 1d12 hours later. Possible effects include recovery of lost hit points, restoration of a body member such as a hand or foot, success in locating an object not heavily protected by magical wards, discovery of a means of entrance or escape, location of a safe wilderness path, improvement of chances to gain rich treasure, or an estimate of enemy strength. If a creature scried by the spell has 7 or more Hit Dice, it may save versus spell. If successful, it is undetected by the dream and may sense the illusionist as if detecting invisible. A dream is not an ultra-powerful spell, and its results must be strictly limited. The examples above represent the spell’s maximum capability. Results never exceed those limits permanently. For example, if a recently slain companion were dreamed alive, the companion would live for only 1 turn per caster level, then return to death unless more permanent magic were used. Dream cannot be affected by extension or permanency. An illusionist can use this spell only once per week. If cast twice in the same week, the second casting automatically fails and the illusionist ages 1d10 years.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Dream","class":"Illusionist"},"dream":{"name":"Dream","level":"5","school":"Alteration-Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Special","duration":"Special","aoe":"Special","components":"Special","ct":"1 day","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Dream\n\nSchool: Alteration-Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: Special\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: 1 day\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is a form of limited wish, but with far narrower scope. The illusionist must find a comfortable place to rest, lie prone, compose their thoughts on the desired result, and then go to sleep. If the illusionist sleeps undisturbed for at least 8 hours, the dream magic takes effect 1d12 hours later. Possible effects include recovery of lost hit points, restoration of a body member such as a hand or foot, success in locating an object not heavily protected by magical wards, discovery of a means of entrance or escape, location of a safe wilderness path, improvement of chances to gain rich treasure, or an estimate of enemy strength. If a creature scried by the spell has 7 or more Hit Dice, it may save versus spell. If successful, it is undetected by the dream and may sense the illusionist as if detecting invisible. A dream is not an ultra-powerful spell, and its results must be strictly limited. The examples above represent the spell’s maximum capability. Results never exceed those limits permanently. For example, if a recently slain companion were dreamed alive, the companion would live for only 1 turn per caster level, then return to death unless more permanent magic were used. Dream cannot be affected by extension or permanency. An illusionist can use this spell only once per week. If cast twice in the same week, the second casting automatically fails and the illusionist ages 1d10 years.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist magic mirror":{"name":"Magic Mirror","level":"5","school":"Enchantment-Divination","range":"Touch","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 hour","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Magic Mirror\n\nSchool: Enchantment-Divination\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 hour\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is virtually the same as the 4th-level magic-user spell magic mirror. It uses the same material components, except that if the illusionist casts a vision spell in place of the normal components, the mirror scries properly, though the vision spell itself does not function normally.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Magic Mirror","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist tempus fugit":{"name":"Tempus Fugit","level":"5","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"5 turns per level","aoe":"1” radius","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Tempus Fugit\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nReversible: Yes\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 5 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” radius\nThis powerful illusion affects the minds and bodies of all creatures within the area. The spell causes affected creatures to perceive time as passing much faster. Creatures entering the area after casting are also affected. Every turn, or 10 minutes, spent under tempus fugit seems like a full hour to those within the dweomer. Their bodily functions are accelerated accordingly, so they must eat, sleep, and otherwise function at the faster perceived rate. The duration of other spells cast within the area is also accelerated. One hour seems like six, and four hours seems like a full day. This acceleration allows rest, spell renewal, and recovery of lost hit points. The reverse slows perceived time: an hour seems like only a turn, and a day seems like only four hours. The reverse requires no special preparation. In either form, the illusionist is also affected. Under the reverse, the effect always lasts at least 1 turn after the caster wishes it dispelled, because the caster’s reactions are greatly slowed.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Tempus Fugit","class":"Illusionist"},"tempus fugit":{"name":"Tempus Fugit","level":"5","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"5 turns per level","aoe":"1” radius","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Tempus Fugit\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nReversible: Yes\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 5 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” radius\nThis powerful illusion affects the minds and bodies of all creatures within the area. The spell causes affected creatures to perceive time as passing much faster. Creatures entering the area after casting are also affected. Every turn, or 10 minutes, spent under tempus fugit seems like a full hour to those within the dweomer. Their bodily functions are accelerated accordingly, so they must eat, sleep, and otherwise function at the faster perceived rate. The duration of other spells cast within the area is also accelerated. One hour seems like six, and four hours seems like a full day. This acceleration allows rest, spell renewal, and recovery of lost hit points. The reverse slows perceived time: an hour seems like only a turn, and a day seems like only four hours. The reverse requires no special preparation. In either form, the illusionist is also affected. Under the reverse, the effect always lasts at least 1 turn after the caster wishes it dispelled, because the caster’s reactions are greatly slowed.\n\nIllusionist Spells, 6th Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist death fog":{"name":"Death Fog","level":"6","school":"Alteration-Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"1d4 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"2 cubic “ per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Death Fog\n\nSchool: Alteration-Evocation\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1d4 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2 cubic “ per caster level\nThis spell creates an area of solid fog with the added property of being highly acidic. The vapors are deadly to living things. Vegetation exposed to them dies according to size: grass and similar small plants in 2 rounds, bushes and shrubs in 4 rounds, small trees in 8 rounds, and large trees in 16 rounds. Animal life not immune to acid suffers damage based on exposure time: 1 point on the 1st round, 2 points on the 2nd round, 4 points on the 3rd round, and 8 points on the 4th and each succeeding round. Otherwise, death fog has the same characteristics as solid fog. Material Components: A pinch of dried and powdered peas, powdered animal hoof, and strong acid of any kind, including highly distilled vinegar or acid crystals.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Death Fog","class":"Illusionist"},"death fog":{"name":"Death Fog","level":"6","school":"Alteration-Evocation","range":"3”","duration":"1d4 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"2 cubic “ per caster level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Death Fog\n\nSchool: Alteration-Evocation\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1d4 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 2 cubic “ per caster level\nThis spell creates an area of solid fog with the added property of being highly acidic. The vapors are deadly to living things. Vegetation exposed to them dies according to size: grass and similar small plants in 2 rounds, bushes and shrubs in 4 rounds, small trees in 8 rounds, and large trees in 16 rounds. Animal life not immune to acid suffers damage based on exposure time: 1 point on the 1st round, 2 points on the 2nd round, 4 points on the 3rd round, and 8 points on the 4th and each succeeding round. Otherwise, death fog has the same characteristics as solid fog. Material Components: A pinch of dried and powdered peas, powdered animal hoof, and strong acid of any kind, including highly distilled vinegar or acid crystals.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist mislead":{"name":"Mislead","level":"6","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"1”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mislead\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 6\nComponents: S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a phantasmal double of the illusionist while simultaneously cloaking the real illusionist with improved invisibility. The illusionist is then free to move elsewhere while the phantasm seems to move away. The phantasm can speak and gesture as if real, and it includes full olfactory and touch components. Detect illusion, true seeing, true sight, or a gem of seeing reveals the illusion for what it is. Detect invisibility, true sight, true seeing, a gem of seeing, or a robe of eyes can detect the invisible illusionist.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Mislead","class":"Illusionist"},"mislead":{"name":"Mislead","level":"6","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"1”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Special","components":"S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mislead\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 6\nComponents: S\nRange: 1”\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell creates a phantasmal double of the illusionist while simultaneously cloaking the real illusionist with improved invisibility. The illusionist is then free to move elsewhere while the phantasm seems to move away. The phantasm can speak and gesture as if real, and it includes full olfactory and touch components. Detect illusion, true seeing, true sight, or a gem of seeing reveals the illusion for what it is. Detect invisibility, true sight, true seeing, a gem of seeing, or a robe of eyes can detect the invisible illusionist.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist phantasmagoria":{"name":"Phantasmagoria","level":"6","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"6”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"4 square “ + 1 square “ per caster level","components":"V, S","ct":"6 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Phantasmagoria\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 4 square “ + 1 square “ per caster level\nThis spell prepares a special form of spectral forces triggered by a specific action. The phantasmagoria typically includes full visual, auditory, olfactory, and touch illusion involving falling, sliding, or rapid movement. The effect can make subjects believe they are moving this way, or that something else is doing so. For example, it may trigger when a creature falls into a pit, reaches the center of an area, opens a door, or performs a similar action. The subjects might believe they are falling for scores of feet, sliding helplessly into an unknown area, or being struck by a wall of water rushing from beyond a newly opened door. Unlike programmed illusion, phantasmagoria must always involve something falling or rushing, or a dwindling perspective.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Phantasmagoria","class":"Illusionist"},"phantasmagoria":{"name":"Phantasmagoria","level":"6","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"6”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"4 square “ + 1 square “ per caster level","components":"V, S","ct":"6 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Phantasmagoria\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 6 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 4 square “ + 1 square “ per caster level\nThis spell prepares a special form of spectral forces triggered by a specific action. The phantasmagoria typically includes full visual, auditory, olfactory, and touch illusion involving falling, sliding, or rapid movement. The effect can make subjects believe they are moving this way, or that something else is doing so. For example, it may trigger when a creature falls into a pit, reaches the center of an area, opens a door, or performs a similar action. The subjects might believe they are falling for scores of feet, sliding helplessly into an unknown area, or being struck by a wall of water rushing from beyond a newly opened door. Unlike programmed illusion, phantasmagoria must always involve something falling or rushing, or a dwindling perspective.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist mirage arcane":{"name":"Mirage Arcane","level":"6","school":"Illusion/Phantasm-Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"1” per level radius","components":"V, S; M optional","ct":"3 or 6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mirage Arcane\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm-Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S; M optional\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 or 6 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” per level radius\nThis spell is similar to vacancy, but more powerful and elaborate. It also resembles the mirage cantrip. The spell allows the illusionist to make an area appear as something other than it is, according to whatever place the caster envisions. The spell remains as long as the caster maintains faint concentration, and after concentration ends it persists for 6 turns plus 1 turn per caster level. Faint concentration can be maintained during normal conversation, but not while spellcasting, in melee, or after being harmed. The mirage must be of a place the illusionist has personally seen. If the caster has a small bit of material connected with the place envisioned, the illusion takes on a form of reality. In its basic form, with a 3-segment casting time, forceful contact and tactile discovery are necessary to have any hope of discovering the magic, short of magical detection. In its more complex form, with a material component and 6-segment casting time, detection is possible only by magical means. Either form is subject to dispel illusion or dispel magic. As with powerful illusions, belief can cause appropriate effects on the viewer’s body, though belief does not usually affect the laws of nature and magic. Under this spell, a viewer might walk across hot coals thinking they are in a shallow cooling stream and take no damage, dine on imaginary food and be nutritionally satisfied, or rest on sharp stones believing them to be a featherbed. Gravity is not affected, so an illusory bridge across a chasm does not support a believer. Witnesses see such a person suddenly disappear and do not connect it with an illusion unless they already know magic is involved.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Mirage Arcane","class":"Illusionist"},"mirage arcane":{"name":"Mirage Arcane","level":"6","school":"Illusion/Phantasm-Alteration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"1” per level radius","components":"V, S; M optional","ct":"3 or 6 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Mirage Arcane\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm-Alteration\nLevel: 6\nComponents: V, S; M optional\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 or 6 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” per level radius\nThis spell is similar to vacancy, but more powerful and elaborate. It also resembles the mirage cantrip. The spell allows the illusionist to make an area appear as something other than it is, according to whatever place the caster envisions. The spell remains as long as the caster maintains faint concentration, and after concentration ends it persists for 6 turns plus 1 turn per caster level. Faint concentration can be maintained during normal conversation, but not while spellcasting, in melee, or after being harmed. The mirage must be of a place the illusionist has personally seen. If the caster has a small bit of material connected with the place envisioned, the illusion takes on a form of reality. In its basic form, with a 3-segment casting time, forceful contact and tactile discovery are necessary to have any hope of discovering the magic, short of magical detection. In its more complex form, with a material component and 6-segment casting time, detection is possible only by magical means. Either form is subject to dispel illusion or dispel magic. As with powerful illusions, belief can cause appropriate effects on the viewer’s body, though belief does not usually affect the laws of nature and magic. Under this spell, a viewer might walk across hot coals thinking they are in a shallow cooling stream and take no damage, dine on imaginary food and be nutritionally satisfied, or rest on sharp stones believing them to be a featherbed. Gravity is not affected, so an illusory bridge across a chasm does not support a believer. Witnesses see such a person suddenly disappear and do not connect it with an illusion unless they already know magic is involved.\n\nIllusionist Spells, 7th Level","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist shadow walk":{"name":"Shadow Walk","level":"7","school":"Illusion-Enchantment","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Shadow Walk\n\nSchool: Illusion-Enchantment\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nTo cast this spell, the illusionist must be in an area of heavy shadows. The caster and any touched creatures are transported to the edge of the Prime Material Plane where it borders the Plane of Shadow. In this region, the illusionist can move at a relative rate of up to 7 leagues per turn, moving normally along the borders of the Plane of Shadow while remaining aware of their position relative to the Prime Material Plane. This allows rapid travel by stepping from the Plane of Shadow back to the Prime Material Plane, with the destination controlled by the illusionist. Shadow walk can also be used to travel to other planes bordering the Plane of Shadow, but doing so requires a perilous transit through the Plane of Shadow to reach another planar border. Touched creatures also make the transition. They may follow the illusionist, wander into Shadowland, or stumble back onto the Prime Material Plane. If lost or abandoned by the illusionist, there is a 50% chance for either of the latter two outcomes. Unwilling creatures receive a saving throw; success negates the effect.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Shadow Walk","class":"Illusionist"},"shadow walk":{"name":"Shadow Walk","level":"7","school":"Illusion-Enchantment","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"1 segment","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Shadow Walk\n\nSchool: Illusion-Enchantment\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 segment\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nTo cast this spell, the illusionist must be in an area of heavy shadows. The caster and any touched creatures are transported to the edge of the Prime Material Plane where it borders the Plane of Shadow. In this region, the illusionist can move at a relative rate of up to 7 leagues per turn, moving normally along the borders of the Plane of Shadow while remaining aware of their position relative to the Prime Material Plane. This allows rapid travel by stepping from the Plane of Shadow back to the Prime Material Plane, with the destination controlled by the illusionist. Shadow walk can also be used to travel to other planes bordering the Plane of Shadow, but doing so requires a perilous transit through the Plane of Shadow to reach another planar border. Touched creatures also make the transition. They may follow the illusionist, wander into Shadowland, or stumble back onto the Prime Material Plane. If lost or abandoned by the illusionist, there is a 50% chance for either of the latter two outcomes. Unwilling creatures receive a saving throw; success negates the effect.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist weird":{"name":"Weird","level":"7","school":"Evocation-Illusion/Phantasm","range":"3”","duration":"Special","aoe":"2” radius","components":"V, S","ct":"7 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Weird\n\nSchool: Evocation-Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 2” radius\nTo cast this spell, the illusionist must be able to converse with the subject or subjects. During casting, the illusionist calls out to them, declaring that their final fate or doom is upon them. The magic is so powerful that even subjects who make their saving throw are paralyzed with fear for 7 segments and lose 1d4 Strength points, which return after 7 rounds. Subjects who fail their saving throw face their nemesis: the opponent or opponents they most fear and that are most inimical to them. Actual combat then occurs, and no magical escape is possible. The foe is real for all intents and purposes. If the subjects lose, they die. If they slay the weird created by the dweomer, they emerge unharmed, with no loss of items apparently used and no loss of spells apparently expended. They gain experience for defeating the weird, if applicable. Each combat round seems normal but takes only 1 segment of real time. The illusionist must concentrate fully to maintain the spell.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Weird","class":"Illusionist"},"weird":{"name":"Weird","level":"7","school":"Evocation-Illusion/Phantasm","range":"3”","duration":"Special","aoe":"2” radius","components":"V, S","ct":"7 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Weird\n\nSchool: Evocation-Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 7\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 7 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 2” radius\nTo cast this spell, the illusionist must be able to converse with the subject or subjects. During casting, the illusionist calls out to them, declaring that their final fate or doom is upon them. The magic is so powerful that even subjects who make their saving throw are paralyzed with fear for 7 segments and lose 1d4 Strength points, which return after 7 rounds. Subjects who fail their saving throw face their nemesis: the opponent or opponents they most fear and that are most inimical to them. Actual combat then occurs, and no magical escape is possible. The foe is real for all intents and purposes. If the subjects lose, they die. If they slay the weird created by the dweomer, they emerge unharmed, with no loss of items apparently used and no loss of spells apparently expended. They gain experience for defeating the weird, if applicable. Each combat round seems normal but takes only 1 segment of real time. The illusionist must concentrate fully to maintain the spell.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist colored lights":{"name":"Colored Lights","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Colored Lights\n\nType: Alteration\nArea of Effect: Special\nCasting Time: ½ segment\nThis cantrip creates one or more globes of pastel light. The caster may create one 1-foot-diameter globe, two 6-inch globes, three 4-inch globes, or four 3-inch globes. The globes may be any pastel color. Each globe illuminates a radius equal to five times its diameter: a 1-foot globe sheds light in a 5-foot radius, while a 3-inch globe illuminates a 15-inch radius. As long as the caster concentrates, the globes remain active and may float near or rest upon the caster within 1” range. The caster may move them back and forth, up and down, or otherwise direct them as desired. Their light does not cast reflections beyond 1”, and the light cannot be detected beyond 3”. Pale blue or pink light does not affect infravision or ultravision, but other colors disturb those visual abilities. To cast it, the illusionist speaks the desired color and number of globes, then speaks a magic word such as noma or mazda, while directing the globes with one or more fingers.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Colored Lights","class":"Illusionist"},"colored lights":{"name":"Colored Lights","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Colored Lights\n\nType: Alteration\nArea of Effect: Special\nCasting Time: ½ segment\nThis cantrip creates one or more globes of pastel light. The caster may create one 1-foot-diameter globe, two 6-inch globes, three 4-inch globes, or four 3-inch globes. The globes may be any pastel color. Each globe illuminates a radius equal to five times its diameter: a 1-foot globe sheds light in a 5-foot radius, while a 3-inch globe illuminates a 15-inch radius. As long as the caster concentrates, the globes remain active and may float near or rest upon the caster within 1” range. The caster may move them back and forth, up and down, or otherwise direct them as desired. Their light does not cast reflections beyond 1”, and the light cannot be detected beyond 3”. Pale blue or pink light does not affect infravision or ultravision, but other colors disturb those visual abilities. To cast it, the illusionist speaks the desired color and number of globes, then speaks a magic word such as noma or mazda, while directing the globes with one or more fingers.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist dim":{"name":"Dim","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Dim\n\nType: Alteration\nArea of Effect: Special\nCasting Time: ½ segment\nThis cantrip weakens an existing light source or causes the air itself to become less permeated by light. It can affect about six torches, a medium-sized fire such as a fireplace or campfire, seventy-two candles, or even a light or continual light spell. Affected light sources shed at best half their normal radiance for 1 full round. Torches burn only as brightly as candles; candles merely glow dimly; a fire gives only torchlike illumination; and magical light spells dim to half brightness. The affected light must be within 1” of the caster. To cast it, the illusionist speaks a magical phrase, such as bee-row-nout or rhee-oh-stat, and makes a downward motion with one hand.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Dim","class":"Illusionist"},"dim":{"name":"Dim","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Dim\n\nType: Alteration\nArea of Effect: Special\nCasting Time: ½ segment\nThis cantrip weakens an existing light source or causes the air itself to become less permeated by light. It can affect about six torches, a medium-sized fire such as a fireplace or campfire, seventy-two candles, or even a light or continual light spell. Affected light sources shed at best half their normal radiance for 1 full round. Torches burn only as brightly as candles; candles merely glow dimly; a fire gives only torchlike illumination; and magical light spells dim to half brightness. The affected light must be within 1” of the caster. To cast it, the illusionist speaks a magical phrase, such as bee-row-nout or rhee-oh-stat, and makes a downward motion with one hand.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist haze":{"name":"Haze","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1” cube","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Haze\n\nType: Alteration\nArea of Effect: 1” cube\nCasting Time: ½ segment\nThis cantrip makes the atmosphere in the chosen area cloudy, as if layered with smoke or filled with floating dust. Creatures attempting to fire missiles or cast spells at a target screened by the haze are hindered. The screened target is 5% harder to hit, so missile attacks suffer -1 “to hit,” and saving throws are made at +1. If an effect would normally allow no saving throw, the haze grants a 5% chance to save. Hiding in shadows is also 5% more effective when screened by this cantrip. The haze lasts 1 round. It must be cast within 1” of the caster. A good breeze, rain, or similar atmospheric condition destroys the haze, and a gust of wind spell disperses it immediately. To cast it, the illusionist hums a melody while making passes before the body with the hands.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Haze","class":"Illusionist"},"haze":{"name":"Haze","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1” cube","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Haze\n\nType: Alteration\nArea of Effect: 1” cube\nCasting Time: ½ segment\nThis cantrip makes the atmosphere in the chosen area cloudy, as if layered with smoke or filled with floating dust. Creatures attempting to fire missiles or cast spells at a target screened by the haze are hindered. The screened target is 5% harder to hit, so missile attacks suffer -1 “to hit,” and saving throws are made at +1. If an effect would normally allow no saving throw, the haze grants a 5% chance to save. Hiding in shadows is also 5% more effective when screened by this cantrip. The haze lasts 1 round. It must be cast within 1” of the caster. A good breeze, rain, or similar atmospheric condition destroys the haze, and a gust of wind spell disperses it immediately. To cast it, the illusionist hums a melody while making passes before the body with the hands.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist mask":{"name":"Mask","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One person","components":"","ct":"1/6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Mask\n\nType: Illusion\nArea of Effect: One person\nCasting Time: 1/6 segment\nThis cantrip lets the caster alter their own visage, or the visage of another chosen human, demi-human, or humanoid, by illusion. Ears, hair, head shape, facial features, and similar aspects of appearance may be changed. The mask is detectable only if a viewer peers closely or uses illusion-detecting ability or magic. The effect lasts 3–6 rounds. To cast it, the illusionist touches their face, thinks of the desired features, and speaks a word descriptive of the intended visage.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Mask","class":"Illusionist"},"mask":{"name":"Mask","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"One person","components":"","ct":"1/6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Mask\n\nType: Illusion\nArea of Effect: One person\nCasting Time: 1/6 segment\nThis cantrip lets the caster alter their own visage, or the visage of another chosen human, demi-human, or humanoid, by illusion. Ears, hair, head shape, facial features, and similar aspects of appearance may be changed. The mask is detectable only if a viewer peers closely or uses illusion-detecting ability or magic. The effect lasts 3–6 rounds. To cast it, the illusionist touches their face, thinks of the desired features, and speaks a word descriptive of the intended visage.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist mirage":{"name":"Mirage","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"2 square “","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Mirage\n\nType: Illusion\nArea of Effect: 2 square “\nCasting Time: ½ segment\nThis cantrip causes an area to appear as something other than it is. It creates an illusory scene covering the area. The area must be relatively flat and featureless, and the mirage must depict an actual place that exists at the time and that the caster has personally seen. A saving throw versus spell applies. The cantrip lasts as long as the caster concentrates, though each round there is a cumulative 5% chance that it wavers and reveals its true nature. Touching the mirage instantly dispels it, as do dispel illusion or dispel magic. To cast it, the illusionist speaks a word or two descriptive of the mirage and makes a single pass. After that, concentration maintains the effect.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Mirage","class":"Illusionist"},"mirage":{"name":"Mirage","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"2 square “","components":"","ct":"½ segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Mirage\n\nType: Illusion\nArea of Effect: 2 square “\nCasting Time: ½ segment\nThis cantrip causes an area to appear as something other than it is. It creates an illusory scene covering the area. The area must be relatively flat and featureless, and the mirage must depict an actual place that exists at the time and that the caster has personally seen. A saving throw versus spell applies. The cantrip lasts as long as the caster concentrates, though each round there is a cumulative 5% chance that it wavers and reveals its true nature. Touching the mirage instantly dispels it, as do dispel illusion or dispel magic. To cast it, the illusionist speaks a word or two descriptive of the mirage and makes a single pass. After that, concentration maintains the effect.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist noise":{"name":"Noise","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1” radius","components":"","ct":"1/6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Noise\n\nType: Illusion\nArea of Effect: 1” radius\nCasting Time: 1/6 segment\nThis cantrip creates illusory sound of whatever general nature the caster desires, though the sound is indistinct and confusing. It may resemble many voices murmuring behind a thick door or at a great distance, the rush of wings and wind together, shuffling and scraping as if many people were moving things or walking slowly in a distant place, or similar effects. All creatures within the area of effect are subject to the cantrip, but each receives a saving throw. Success negates the noise for that individual. The range is 1” for the cantrip’s radius of sound. To cast it, the illusionist points a digit at the desired area and softly imitates the kind of noise desired.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Noise","class":"Illusionist"},"noise":{"name":"Noise","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"1” radius","components":"","ct":"1/6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Noise\n\nType: Illusion\nArea of Effect: 1” radius\nCasting Time: 1/6 segment\nThis cantrip creates illusory sound of whatever general nature the caster desires, though the sound is indistinct and confusing. It may resemble many voices murmuring behind a thick door or at a great distance, the rush of wings and wind together, shuffling and scraping as if many people were moving things or walking slowly in a distant place, or similar effects. All creatures within the area of effect are subject to the cantrip, but each receives a saving throw. Success negates the noise for that individual. The range is 1” for the cantrip’s radius of sound. To cast it, the illusionist points a digit at the desired area and softly imitates the kind of noise desired.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist rainbow":{"name":"Rainbow","level":"0","school":"Alteration","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"Special","components":"","ct":"1/3 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Rainbow\n\nType: Alteration\nArea of Effect: Special\nCasting Time: 1/3 segment\nThis cantrip creates a plane of pastel colors that duplicates a rainbow. The band is 30 feet long and 1 foot wide. The illusionist may make it arch like a bow, remain as a ribbon, twist, turn, or take similar shapes. One end of the rainbow must be within 1” of the caster when the cantrip is cast. The colors glow softly and remain visible even in total normal darkness. If no motion is desired, the caster may leave the rainbow’s vicinity. If motion is desired, the caster must remain within 1” and control it by hand gestures. The rainbow lasts 1 round, then fades. Creatures that fail a saving throw versus spell gaze at it for 1–4 segments, or 2–5 segments if the caster keeps it in motion. To cast it, the illusionist speaks a name of power, such as garland or pegee-lee, while forming a pyramid with the fingers of both hands.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Rainbow","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist two-d’lusion":{"name":"Two-D’lusion","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"4 square “","components":"","ct":"1/6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Two-D’lusion\n\nType: Illusion\nArea of Effect: 4 square “\nCasting Time: 1/6 segment\nThis cantrip is very similar to phantasmal force in most respects, but creates only a two-dimensional illusion of whatever the caster desires. If any viewer sees it from an angle more than 45 degrees from its horizontal or vertical viewing axis, the illusion’s nature is immediately apparent. It is invisible from the side or rear. It is dispelled by touch, dispel illusion, or dispel magic. The cantrip lasts as long as the caster concentrates. To cast it, the illusionist speaks a phrase descriptive of the illusion while making a circular motion with a closed hand.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Two-D’lusion","class":"Illusionist"},"two-d’lusion":{"name":"Two-D’lusion","level":"0","school":"Illusion","range":"","duration":"","aoe":"4 square “","components":"","ct":"1/6 segment","save":"","save_type":"","description":"Two-D’lusion\n\nType: Illusion\nArea of Effect: 4 square “\nCasting Time: 1/6 segment\nThis cantrip is very similar to phantasmal force in most respects, but creates only a two-dimensional illusion of whatever the caster desires. If any viewer sees it from an angle more than 45 degrees from its horizontal or vertical viewing axis, the illusion’s nature is immediately apparent. It is invisible from the side or rear. It is dispelled by touch, dispel illusion, or dispel magic. The cantrip lasts as long as the caster concentrates. To cast it, the illusionist speaks a phrase descriptive of the illusion while making a circular motion with a closed hand.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist continual darkness":{"name":"Continual Darkness","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"6”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"3” radius globe","components":"V, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Continual Darkness\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 3” radius globe\nWhen this spell is cast, a globe of impenetrable darkness is created. The effects of this darkness, as well as the material component of the spell, are the same as the 2nd-level magic-user spell darkness, 15’ radius.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Continual Darkness","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist continual light":{"name":"Continual Light","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"6”","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"6” radius globe","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Continual Light\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 6”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 6” radius globe\nThis spell is the same as the 2nd-level cleric continual light spell, except as noted above.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Continual Light","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist dispel illusion":{"name":"Dispel Illusion","level":"3","school":"Abjuration","range":"1” per level","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Dispel Illusion\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell lets the illusionist dispel any phantasmal force, with or without audible glamer, cast by a non-illusionist. Against illusion/phantasm spells cast by another illusionist, it has the same chance of success as dispel magic: a base 50% chance, adjusted downward by 2% or upward by 5% for each level of experience by which the dispelling illusionist is lower or higher than the illusionist who cast the spell to be dispelled.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Dispel Illusion","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist fear":{"name":"Fear","level":"3","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"0","duration":"Special","aoe":"6” long cone, 3” diameter at end, ½” at base","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Fear\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 6” long cone, 3” diameter at end, ½” at base\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 4th-level magic-user spell fear.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Fear","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist hallucinatory terrain":{"name":"Hallucinatory Terrain","level":"3","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"2” + 2” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"4” × 4” square area + 1” × 1” square area per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 rounds","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Hallucinatory Terrain\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 2” + 2” per level\nCasting Time: 5 rounds\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 4” × 4” square area + 1” × 1” square area per level\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 4th-level magic-user spell hallucinatory terrain.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Hallucinatory Terrain","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist illusionary script":{"name":"Illusionary Script","level":"3","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Special","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Creature reading the script","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Illusionary Script\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature reading the script\nThis spell allows the illusionist to write instructions or other information on parchment, paper, skin, or a similar surface. The writing appears to be some form of foreign or magical script. Only the person, class of persons, or other intended reader designated by the illusionist can read it, though another illusionist recognizes it as illusionary script. Others attempting to read it become confused as if affected by a confusion spell for 5 to 20 turns, minus 1 turn for each experience level they have attained. Material Component: A specially manufactured lead-based ink made by an alchemist.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Illusionary Script","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionary script":{"name":"Illusionary Script","level":"3","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Special","duration":"Permanent","aoe":"Creature reading the script","components":"V, S, M","ct":"Special","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Illusionary Script\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Special\nCasting Time: Special\nDuration: Permanent\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature reading the script\nThis spell allows the illusionist to write instructions or other information on parchment, paper, skin, or a similar surface. The writing appears to be some form of foreign or magical script. Only the person, class of persons, or other intended reader designated by the illusionist can read it, though another illusionist recognizes it as illusionary script. Others attempting to read it become confused as if affected by a confusion spell for 5 to 20 turns, minus 1 turn for each experience level they have attained. Material Component: A specially manufactured lead-based ink made by an alchemist.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist invisibility, 10’ radius":{"name":"Invisibility, 10’ Radius","level":"3","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"10’ radius of creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Invisibility, 10’ Radius\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10’ radius of creature touched\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level magic-user spell invisibility, 10’ radius. It follows the same general rules as the 2nd-level magic-user spell invisibility.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Invisibility, 10’ Radius","class":"Illusionist"},"invisibility, 10’ radius":{"name":"Invisibility, 10’ Radius","level":"3","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"Special","aoe":"10’ radius of creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Invisibility, 10’ Radius\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 10’ radius of creature touched\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level magic-user spell invisibility, 10’ radius. It follows the same general rules as the 2nd-level magic-user spell invisibility.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist non-detection":{"name":"Non-Detection","level":"3","school":"Abjuration","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"5’ radius of spell caster","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Non-Detection\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 5’ radius of spell caster\nBy casting this spell, the illusionist makes themself invisible to divination spells such as clairaudience, clairvoyance, detection spells, and ESP. It also prevents location by magic items such as crystal balls and medallions of ESP. Material Component: A pinch of diamond dust.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Non-Detection","class":"Illusionist"},"non-detection":{"name":"Non-Detection","level":"3","school":"Abjuration","range":"0","duration":"1 turn per level","aoe":"5’ radius of spell caster","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Non-Detection\n\nSchool: Abjuration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 0\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 1 turn per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 5’ radius of spell caster\nBy casting this spell, the illusionist makes themself invisible to divination spells such as clairaudience, clairvoyance, detection spells, and ESP. It also prevents location by magic items such as crystal balls and medallions of ESP. Material Component: A pinch of diamond dust.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist paralyzation":{"name":"Paralyzation","level":"3","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"2” × 2” area","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Paralyzation\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 2” × 2” area\nThis spell allows the illusionist to create illusory muscle slowdown in creatures whose combined Hit Dice do not exceed twice the illusionist’s experience level. If affected creatures fail their saving throws, they become paralyzed. The effect must be removed by dispel illusion or dispel magic, though the illusionist may dismiss it at any time.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Paralyzation","class":"Illusionist"},"paralyzation":{"name":"Paralyzation","level":"3","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"2” × 2” area","components":"V, S","ct":"3 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Paralyzation\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 2” × 2” area\nThis spell allows the illusionist to create illusory muscle slowdown in creatures whose combined Hit Dice do not exceed twice the illusionist’s experience level. If affected creatures fail their saving throws, they become paralyzed. The effect must be removed by dispel illusion or dispel magic, though the illusionist may dismiss it at any time.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist rope trick":{"name":"Rope Trick","level":"3","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"2 turns per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Rope Trick\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 2 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell is the same as the 2nd-level magic-user spell rope trick.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Rope Trick","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist spectral force":{"name":"Spectral Force","level":"3","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"6” + 1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"4 square” + 1 square” per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Spectral Force\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 4 square” + 1 square” per level\nThis spell creates an illusion that includes sound, smell, and thermal components. Otherwise, it is similar to the 2nd-level improved phantasmal force spell. The spell lasts for 3 rounds after concentration ends.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Spectral Force","class":"Illusionist"},"spectral force":{"name":"Spectral Force","level":"3","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"6” + 1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"4 square” + 1 square” per level","components":"V, S, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Spectral Force\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 6” + 1” per level\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 4 square” + 1 square” per level\nThis spell creates an illusion that includes sound, smell, and thermal components. Otherwise, it is similar to the 2nd-level improved phantasmal force spell. The spell lasts for 3 rounds after concentration ends.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist suggestion":{"name":"Suggestion","level":"3","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"3”","duration":"4 turns + 4 turns per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, M","ct":"3 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Suggestion\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 3\nComponents: V, M\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 3 segments\nDuration: 4 turns + 4 turns per level\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: One creature\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 3rd-level magic-user spell suggestion.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Suggestion","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist confusion":{"name":"Confusion","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"8”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Up to 4” × 4”","components":"V, S, M","ct":"4 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Confusion\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: 8”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Up to 4” × 4”\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 4th-level magic-user spell confusion. See also the 7th-level druid confusion spell.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Confusion","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist dispel exhaustion":{"name":"Dispel Exhaustion","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"3 turns per level","aoe":"1 to 4 persons","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Dispel Exhaustion\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 3 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 to 4 persons\nThis spell allows the illusionist to restore 50% of lost hit points to all persons touched during the round it is cast, up to a maximum of four persons. It gives affected persons the illusion that they are fresh and well. Stamina is renewed, but when the spell duration ends, each recipient drops back to their actual hit point strength. The spell also allows recipients to move at double speed for 1 round every turn, similar to haste.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Dispel Exhaustion","class":"Illusionist"},"dispel exhaustion":{"name":"Dispel Exhaustion","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"3 turns per level","aoe":"1 to 4 persons","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Dispel Exhaustion\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 3 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1 to 4 persons\nThis spell allows the illusionist to restore 50% of lost hit points to all persons touched during the round it is cast, up to a maximum of four persons. It gives affected persons the illusion that they are fresh and well. Stamina is renewed, but when the spell duration ends, each recipient drops back to their actual hit point strength. The spell also allows recipients to move at double speed for 1 round every turn, similar to haste.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist emotion":{"name":"Emotion","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"4” × 4” area","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Emotion\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 4” × 4” area\nWhen this spell is cast, the illusionist projects one of four emotions:\n\nFear: This is the same as the spell of the same name, but because it is not illusory, the saving throw is made at -2. It counters and is countered by rage.\n\nHate: This raises morale, saving throws, “to hit” rolls, and damage by +2. It counters and is countered by hopelessness.\n\nHopelessness: This has the same effect as the symbol of hopelessness. It counters and is countered by hate.\n\nRage: This causes the recipient to become berserk, attack at +1 “to hit,” deal +3 hit points of damage, and gain a temporary +5 hit points. The recipient fights without a shield and without regard for their own life. It counters and is countered by fear.\n\nThe spell lasts as long as the illusionist continues concentrating on the chosen emotion.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Emotion","class":"Illusionist"},"emotion":{"name":"Emotion","level":"4","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"4” × 4” area","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"Negates","save_type":"","description":"Emotion\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: Negates\nArea of Effect: 4” × 4” area\nWhen this spell is cast, the illusionist projects one of four emotions:\n\nFear: This is the same as the spell of the same name, but because it is not illusory, the saving throw is made at -2. It counters and is countered by rage.\n\nHate: This raises morale, saving throws, “to hit” rolls, and damage by +2. It counters and is countered by hopelessness.\n\nHopelessness: This has the same effect as the symbol of hopelessness. It counters and is countered by hate.\n\nRage: This causes the recipient to become berserk, attack at +1 “to hit,” deal +3 hit points of damage, and gain a temporary +5 hit points. The recipient fights without a shield and without regard for their own life. It counters and is countered by fear.\n\nThe spell lasts as long as the illusionist continues concentrating on the chosen emotion.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist improved invisibility":{"name":"Improved Invisibility","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"4 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Improved Invisibility\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is similar to invisibility, but the recipient can attack by missile fire, melee combat, or spellcasting while remaining unseen. However, there can sometimes be telltale traces, such as a shimmer, allowing an observant opponent to attack the invisible recipient. Such attacks are made at -4 “to hit,” and the invisible recipient makes all saving throws at +4.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Improved Invisibility","class":"Illusionist"},"improved invisibility":{"name":"Improved Invisibility","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"Touch","duration":"4 rounds + 1 round per level","aoe":"Creature touched","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Improved Invisibility\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 4 rounds + 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Creature touched\nThis spell is similar to invisibility, but the recipient can attack by missile fire, melee combat, or spellcasting while remaining unseen. However, there can sometimes be telltale traces, such as a shimmer, allowing an observant opponent to attack the invisible recipient. Such attacks are made at -4 “to hit,” and the invisible recipient makes all saving throws at +4.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist massmorph":{"name":"Massmorph","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"1” per level","duration":"Special","aoe":"1” × 1” square per level","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Massmorph\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 1” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: Special\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: 1” × 1” square per level\nExcept as noted above, this spell is the same as the 4th-level magic-user spell massmorph.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Massmorph","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist minor creation":{"name":"Minor Creation","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Minor Creation\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the illusionist to create a nonliving item of vegetable nature, such as soft goods, rope, wood, or similar materials. The created item cannot exceed 1 cubic foot per caster level in volume. The caster must have at least a tiny piece of matter of the same type as the item to be created, such as twisted hemp to create rope or a splinter of wood to create a door.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Minor Creation","class":"Illusionist"},"minor creation":{"name":"Minor Creation","level":"4","school":"Alteration","range":"Touch","duration":"6 turns per level","aoe":"Special","components":"V, S, M","ct":"1 turn","save":"None","save_type":"","description":"Minor Creation\n\nSchool: Alteration\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: Touch\nCasting Time: 1 turn\nDuration: 6 turns per level\nSaving Throw: None\nArea of Effect: Special\nThis spell allows the illusionist to create a nonliving item of vegetable nature, such as soft goods, rope, wood, or similar materials. The created item cannot exceed 1 cubic foot per caster level in volume. The caster must have at least a tiny piece of matter of the same type as the item to be created, such as twisted hemp to create rope or a splinter of wood to create a door.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist phantasmal killer":{"name":"Phantasmal Killer","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Phantasmal Killer\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell creates the illusion of the most fearsome thing imaginable to the subject, drawing from the creature’s subconscious fears and forming them into a visible horror. Only the caster and the recipient can see the phantasmal killer. If it successfully hits, the victim dies from fright. The beast attacks as a 4-Hit-Die monster against its victim. It is invulnerable to attacks and can pass through all barriers because it exists only in the victim’s mind.\n\nThe only defenses are to disbelieve it, which can be attempted only once, or to slay or render unconscious the illusionist who cast it. The disbelief check is not a standard saving throw: the subject rolls 3d6 and must score equal to or less than their Intelligence. Magic resistance is checked first. Wisdom bonuses apply as reductions to the die roll, and other modifiers may apply, including bonuses for surprise and penalties if the subject has previously been attacked by the spell, is an illusionist, or wears a helm of telepathy. If a target successfully disbelieves while wearing a helm of telepathy, the killer can be turned upon the illusionist, who must then disbelieve it or suffer its attack.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Phantasmal Killer","class":"Illusionist"},"phantasmal killer":{"name":"Phantasmal Killer","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"One creature","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Phantasmal Killer\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: One creature\nThis spell creates the illusion of the most fearsome thing imaginable to the subject, drawing from the creature’s subconscious fears and forming them into a visible horror. Only the caster and the recipient can see the phantasmal killer. If it successfully hits, the victim dies from fright. The beast attacks as a 4-Hit-Die monster against its victim. It is invulnerable to attacks and can pass through all barriers because it exists only in the victim’s mind.\n\nThe only defenses are to disbelieve it, which can be attempted only once, or to slay or render unconscious the illusionist who cast it. The disbelief check is not a standard saving throw: the subject rolls 3d6 and must score equal to or less than their Intelligence. Magic resistance is checked first. Wisdom bonuses apply as reductions to the die roll, and other modifiers may apply, including bonuses for surprise and penalties if the subject has previously been attacked by the spell, is an illusionist, or wears a helm of telepathy. If a target successfully disbelieves while wearing a helm of telepathy, the killer can be turned upon the illusionist, who must then disbelieve it or suffer its attack.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist shadow monsters":{"name":"Shadow Monsters","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"2” × 2”","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Shadow Monsters\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 2” × 2”\nThis spell creates semi-real phantasms of one or more monsters. The total Hit Dice of the shadow monster or monsters cannot exceed the illusionist’s experience level. For example, a 10th-level illusionist can create one 10-Hit-Die creature, two 5-Hit-Die creatures, or another equivalent combination. All monsters created by one casting must be of the same kind.\n\nThe monsters have 20% of their normal hit points. Roll their normal Hit Dice and multiply by .20; fractions below .4 are dropped, while .4 or higher rounds up to 1 hit point. If a creature viewing the shadow monsters fails its saving throw and believes the illusion, the monsters function normally with respect to Armor Class and attack forms. If the viewer succeeds, the monsters are Armor Class 10 and deal only 20% of normal melee damage, again dropping fractions below .4 and rounding .4 or higher upward.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Shadow Monsters","class":"Illusionist"},"shadow monsters":{"name":"Shadow Monsters","level":"4","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"2” × 2”","components":"V, S","ct":"4 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Shadow Monsters\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 4\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 4 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 2” × 2”\nThis spell creates semi-real phantasms of one or more monsters. The total Hit Dice of the shadow monster or monsters cannot exceed the illusionist’s experience level. For example, a 10th-level illusionist can create one 10-Hit-Die creature, two 5-Hit-Die creatures, or another equivalent combination. All monsters created by one casting must be of the same kind.\n\nThe monsters have 20% of their normal hit points. Roll their normal Hit Dice and multiply by .20; fractions below .4 are dropped, while .4 or higher rounds up to 1 hit point. If a creature viewing the shadow monsters fails its saving throw and believes the illusion, the monsters function normally with respect to Armor Class and attack forms. If the viewer succeeds, the monsters are Armor Class 10 and deal only 20% of normal melee damage, again dropping fractions below .4 and rounding .4 or higher upward.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist chaos":{"name":"Chaos","level":"5","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Up to 4” × 4”","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Chaos\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Up to 4” × 4”\nThis spell is similar to the 7th-level druid confusion spell, but all creatures in the area of effect are confused for the spell’s duration. Only fighters, other than paladins or rangers, and illusionists can combat the spell’s effects and are allowed a saving throw. Similarly, monsters that do not use magic and have Intelligence 4, semi-intelligent, or lower are entitled to saving throws. Material Components: A small disc of bronze and a small rod of iron.","notes":"","link":"","select_value":"Illusionist: Chaos","class":"Illusionist"},"chaos":{"name":"Chaos","level":"5","school":"Enchantment/Charm","range":"½” per level","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"Up to 4” × 4”","components":"V, S, M","ct":"5 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Chaos\n\nSchool: Enchantment/Charm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S, M\nRange: ½” per level\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: Up to 4” × 4”\nThis spell is similar to the 7th-level druid confusion spell, but all creatures in the area of effect are confused for the spell’s duration. Only fighters, other than paladins or rangers, and illusionists can combat the spell’s effects and are allowed a saving throw. Similarly, monsters that do not use magic and have Intelligence 4, semi-intelligent, or lower are entitled to saving throws. Material Components: A small disc of bronze and a small rod of iron.","notes":"","link":"","class":"Illusionist"},"illusionist demi-shadow monsters":{"name":"Demi-Shadow Monsters","level":"5","school":"Illusion/Phantasm","range":"3”","duration":"1 round per level","aoe":"2” × 2”","components":"V, S","ct":"5 segments","save":"Special","save_type":"","description":"Demi-Shadow Monsters\n\nSchool: Illusion/Phantasm\nLevel: 5\nComponents: V, S\nRange: 3”\nCasting Time: 5 segments\nDuration: 1 round per level\nSaving Throw: Special\nArea of Effect: 2” × 2”\nThis spell is similar to the 4th-level spell shadow monsters, except that the monsters created have 40% of their normal hit points. Their damage potential is 40% of nor